(47, '1/ Last week @Outpost Club - Saying hello and saying goodbye', 1, '1-last-week-outpost-club---saying-hello-and-saying-goodbye', 'outpost-blog/blog-outpost-club/2017/10/1/last-week-outpost-saying-hello-and-saying-goodby', '1/ Last week @Outpost Club - Saying hello and saying goodbye', '1/ Last week @Outpost Club - Saying hello and saying goodbye', 'Summer is officially over! And with that, a lot of people are leaving and new people are coming in. ', '<p>Summer is officially over! And with that, a lot of people are leaving and new people are coming in. In summer, we get a lot of people that are in the city for an internship, and now a lot of students, working people, and digital nomads are coming in.</p>', '<p>Summer is officially over! And with that, a lot of people are leaving and new people are coming in. In summer, we get a lot of people that are in the city for an internship, and now a lot of students, working people, and digital nomads are coming in.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Staying in a coliving space in New York, you&rsquo;ll meet a lot of people from all different backgrounds, which is great! But it\'s also hard to say goodbye sometimes to people you&rsquo;ve lived with for months!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Every week we write about one of our members and their experiences here at Outpost Club in our coliving spaces in New York City. You can find these stories <a href=\"../blog_category/membermonday\" rel=\"nofollow\">here</a>.</p>', '1-last-week-outpost-club.jpg', 1, '2017-10-12 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(48, 'Welcome to the East-Bushwick House!', 1, 'welcome-to-the-east-bushwick-house', '', 'Welcome to the East-Bushwick House!', 'Welcome to the East-Bushwick House!', 'Today we are so happy to announce that we are opening our fifth Coliving space here in New York City', '<p>Today we are so happy to announce that we are opening our fifth Coliving space here in New York City! The East-Bushwick House is also one of our biggest locations so far, with 15 bedrooms and 6.</p>', '<p>Today we are so happy to announce that we are opening our fifth Coliving space here in New York City! The East-Bushwick House is also one of our biggest locations so far, with 15 bedrooms and 6 full bathrooms! Below you can find some more information on the location of the house, the rooms and the amenities included.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>THE SCOOP <br />The East Bushwick House is our most recent addition to the Outpost Club family. With its &hellip; floors and 15 bedrooms, It&rsquo;s one of our biggest locations so far. We even have a spacious backyard!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Welcome to the East-Bushwick House! (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/welcome-to-the-east-bushwick-house/outpostclub.jpg\" alt=\"Welcome to the East-Bushwick House! (Image-1)\" /></p>\r\n<p>LOCATION:<br />Located on the East side of Bushwick-Brooklyn, This Co-living space is in an up-and-coming neighborhood of Bushwick..&nbsp;<strong>The East-Bushwick House is a five-minute walk to the L train on Wilson Ave and a fifteen-minute walk to the JMZ trains on the Halsey Street stop.</strong>&nbsp;The location is near coffee shops, pizza joints and a couple of bars.</p>\r\n<p>THE SPACE:&nbsp;<br />The house is a newly built space with central air, updated appliances, and hardwood floors. This house is equipped with 15 bedrooms, a Kitchen on each floor and the basement is a living room and coworking space. All of the common areas are massive in comparison to your average New York City apartment.&nbsp;<strong>This space is move-in ready;&nbsp;</strong>all you have to do is show up with your suitcase.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><img title=\"Welcome to the East-Bushwick House! (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/welcome-to-the-east-bushwick-house/outpost-club-1.jpg\" alt=\"Welcome to the East-Bushwick House! (Image-2)\" /></p>\r\n<h3>THE KITCHENS/DINING ROOM&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>There is a kitchen on every floor in the house. The Kitchens form the core of the house, and for good reason. On each floor (all members have access to every floor) the kitchen and dining room are the first rooms you enter into.&nbsp;These spaces each have dining room tables and the downstair dining room is even large enough to sit 10-12 people. These spaces are used for potluck dinners, solo meals, and even chats in the evening over a glass of wine.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Amenities include: gas stoves, stainless steel fridges, microwaves, large sinks, coffee makers, blenders, plenty of cabinets (you will be assigned one), cookware, tableware, cutting boards, and anything else you would need in a kitchen.<br />&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Also included: salt, pepper, sugar, coffee grounds, olive oil, paper towels, and dish soap, all of which is routinely restocked.<br />&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Security: 24/7 security in common areas.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><img title=\"Welcome to the East-Bushwick House! (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/welcome-to-the-east-bushwick-house/outpost-club-3.jpg\" alt=\"Welcome to the East-Bushwick House! (Image-3)\" /></p>\r\n<h3>THE (CO)LIVING ROOM</h3>\r\n<p>The living room has <em>three</em> large couches and 55&rsquo;\' screen TV (with Netflix!!!). This is where we host movie nights, game nights, and unplanned hangouts. This space is equipped with everything you need to relax.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Living room also includes:&nbsp;coffee tables, pillows, lamps, <em>knickknacks</em>, house slippers to walk around in, and nice people.</li>\r\n<li>Security: 24/7 security in common areas</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>THE COWORKING SPACE</h3>\r\n<p>The co-working space in this house is massive, and we&rsquo;ll make sure you have everything you need to have a productive time! This room comfortably holds up to <em>ten</em> people working simultaneously. There\'s lots of desk space to make sure your work time is productive. Additionally, there are many common spaces throughout the house that our members use to work.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Amenities: Desks, chairs, conveniently placed outlets, a printer, a scanner and a fax machine to make sure you are prepared for anything work throws at you.</li>\r\n<li>Security: 24/7 security in common areas.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr />\r\n<div>\r\n<p><img title=\"Welcome to the East-Bushwick House! (Image-4), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/welcome-to-the-east-bushwick-house/B8D91921-F5A0-4EC9-BB6B-A19797685610.jpg\" alt=\"Welcome to the East-Bushwick House! (Image-4)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Welcome to the East-Bushwick House! (Image-5), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/welcome-to-the-east-bushwick-house/D5E69EED-F255-4BBA-8944-050C215592C4.jpg\" alt=\"Welcome to the East-Bushwick House! (Image-5)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Welcome to the East-Bushwick House! (Image-6), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/welcome-to-the-east-bushwick-house/076554D9-A376-4C68-A58A-E27114FA9562.jpg\" alt=\"Welcome to the East-Bushwick House! (Image-6)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Welcome to the East-Bushwick House! (Image-7), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/welcome-to-the-east-bushwick-house/45BA16BE-D485-4E85-B1A1-DC5C2E050070.jpg\" alt=\"Welcome to the East-Bushwick House! (Image-7)\" /></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>THE BEDROOMS</h3>\r\n<p>Your room will be move-in ready, just like the rest of the house. There&rsquo;s no need to even bring a pillow. There are single and shared rooms, depending on availability and your price range.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Amenities: memory foam twin-sized mattresses, memory foam pillows, extension cords to your bedside, shelving, hooks, bed linens, towels, and a closet/organizational tools</li>\r\n<li>Services: <strong>B</strong><strong>ed linens and towels are washed/replaced once a week</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr />\r\n<div>\r\n<p><img title=\"Welcome to the East-Bushwick House! (Image-8), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/welcome-to-the-east-bushwick-house/2021F283-472A-4C6D-A371-20D3098FD114.jpg\" alt=\"Welcome to the East-Bushwick House! (Image-8)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Welcome to the East-Bushwick House! (Image-9), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/welcome-to-the-east-bushwick-house/72D9B14C-5086-48D9-A6EA-451239549B93.jpg\" alt=\"Welcome to the East-Bushwick House! (Image-9)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Welcome to the East-Bushwick House! (Image-10), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/welcome-to-the-east-bushwick-house/AC16DD7C-C4A3-47E7-B878-2765FF5483BB.jpg\" alt=\"Welcome to the East-Bushwick House! (Image-10)\" /></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>The BATHROOMS</h3>\r\n<p>We provide everything you would need for the bathroom as well.&nbsp;There are six full bathrooms and<em>&nbsp;</em>one half bathroom so that you&rsquo;ll never have to wait.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Also included: toilet paper and shampoo and body wash, which will never be empty! We also provide hairdryers,&nbsp;no need to bring your own</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>THE BACKYARD</h3>\r\n<p>Yes, we even have a back yard! This space has tables and chairs so can work outside in the spring, summer and autumn. This space holds many parties, get-togethers, barbeques, and celebrations.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>THROUGHOUT THE HOUSE</h3>\r\n<p>In addition to everything above, all of your utilities (electric, gas, water, and wifi)&nbsp;are included in your membership. Each of our new homes incorporate the newest advancements in home technology, like high bandwidth routers, NestTM security and temperature control systems, updated appliances, and energy-efficient lighting. For all the furniture and beds we used only best suppliers, real wooden surfaces, durable metals, and sleek countertops. We worked with interior designers to make the place comfortable for all members in any room of the house. We&rsquo;ve thought of all the little things you need to feel right at home upon arrival.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h2>Thanks for reading! To find out more about our other locations, <a href=\"../new-york\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">click here</a>.</h2>', 'outpostclub.jpg', 1, '2017-10-15 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(49, '2/ Last week @Outpost - We opened a new House!', 1, '2-last-week-outpost---we-opened-a-new-house', 'outpost-blog/blog-outpost-club/2017/10/22/some-more-insights-in-our-latest-achievement', '2/ Last week @Outpost - We opened a new House!', '2/ Last week @Outpost - We opened a new House!', 'Outpost Club Opens Its Biggest Home Yet, The East Bushwick House', '<p>Outpost Club Opens Its Biggest Home Yet, The East Bushwick HouseThe East Bushwick House will be an experiment in the use of space, a testament to Outpost Club&rsquo;s commitment to experimentation.NEW.</p>', '<p><strong>Outpost Club Opens Its Biggest Home Yet, The East Bushwick House</strong></p>\r\n<p>The East Bushwick House will be an experiment in the use of space, a testament to Outpost Club&rsquo;s commitment to experimentation.</p>\r\n<p>NEW YORK, October 16th, 2017 &mdash; On Monday, Outpost Club will move in its first member to the East Bushwick House, expanding Outpost&rsquo;s New York City portfolio and bringing more affordable housing to New York based startups, entrepreneurs, professionals, students, and newcomers.</p>\r\n<p>The East Bushwick House Outpost Club&rsquo;s 3 house in the Bushwick Neighborhood, allowing Outpost to further accommodate the growing demand for its coliving services.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>East Bushwick is becoming an increasingly choice among budget renters, as the neighborhood combines charm with affordability. Bars, cafes and restaurants are starting to pop up all over the neighborhood.</p>\r\n<p>The house itself is Outpost&rsquo;s largest location in terms of both square footage and bedrooms. The house has 14 bedrooms, and four main common areas, allowing members to explore different parts of the house.</p>\r\n<p>The house&rsquo;s design is the result of the things we learned when opening our previous houses&rdquo; said Sergii Starostin, Outpost Club Partner and CEO. &ldquo;We learned that we needed to entice members of separate floors to interact with one another. It takes a lot more than a house to create a community; if the interior design is right, it can facilitate interactions that might not have happened otherwise.</p>\r\n<p>Coliving is a relatively new concept for New York renters and coliving operators, so each house&rsquo;s design is an experiment in the use of space.</p>\r\n<p>Each common area has a different purpose in this house. This means that if members need something from another area of the house, they must go to that area and interact with people who traditionally hangout their. We hope this allows members to more naturally build relationships with each other&rdquo; said Alex Prykhodko, Outpost Club Partner and Operations Manager.</p>\r\n<p>Outpost Club plans to continue opening houses in New York, but for the moment the East Bushwick House is their crowning achievement.</p>', 'we-opened-a-new-house.jpg', 1, '2017-10-21 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(50, '3/ Last week @Outpost - We now own the whole building!', 1, '3-last-week-outpost---we-now-own-the-whole-building', 'outpost-blog/blog-outpost-club/2017/10/29/3/-last-week-outpost-we-now-own-the-whole-building', '3/ Last week @Outpost - We now own the whole building!', '3/ Last week @Outpost - We now own the whole building!', 'This week we have the pleasure to announce that we now own the full building at Bushwick House!', '<p>Every week we want to share a little bit more about what\'s going on in our company behind the scenes. This week we have the pleasure to announce that we now own the full building at Bushwick House!</p>', '<p>Every week we want to share a little bit more about what\'s going on in our company behind the scenes. This week we have the pleasure to announce that we now own the full building at Bushwick House!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>When we first opened the Bushwick House a couple months back, we only had the first floor, backyard and the lower level. Now we also own the second and the third floor bringing the Bushwick house from 5 bedrooms to now 13!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>The second and third level all have single bedrooms (4 on each level) with all basic amenities included:&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Furniture</li>\r\n<li>Bed linen</li>\r\n<li>Storage Space</li>\r\n<li>Desk</li>\r\n<li>Towel</li>\r\n<li>Pillow</li>\r\n<li>Shared kitchen (one on each floor)</li>\r\n<li>Access to downstairs living room with 55 inch TV (Netflix and Chromcast incl)</li>\r\n<li>Access to the backyard through the lower level.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>', 'we-now-own-the-whole-building.jpg', 1, '2017-11-02 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(51, 'About our Halloween party...', 1, 'about-our-halloween-party', '', 'About our Halloween party...', 'About our Halloween party...', 'Here at Outpost, we organized a great Halloween party where 50 of our members came together in one of our locations to have a great time together! Personally, I love these cross-location parties ;)', '<p>Hey guys! How was your Halloween?</p>', '<p>Hey guys! How was your Halloween?&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Here at Outpost, we organized a great Halloween party where 50 of our members came together in one of our locations to have a great time together! Personally, I love these cross-location parties ;) You\'ll meet so many new people from within the Outpost community, it\'s like you make friends automatically ;)</p>\r\n<p>The party happened in our newest location, The East-Bushwick House so that all members could experience our latest achievement!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"About our Halloween party... (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/About%20our%20Halloween%20party/Pasted_image_at_2017_11_02_11_16_AM_(3).jpg\" alt=\"About our Halloween party... (Image-1)\" /></p>\r\n<p>Outpost Club provided drinks for everyone above 21, we tested out our new foosball table and we had a great costume contest! Everyone looked great ;) And we even did a costume contest!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Richard, the house leader from The Flatbush House, won! Dressed as \'The Fruit Ninjas\', a character from The Walking Dead.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Congrats Richard! And we hope to be organizing many more of these awesome community events soon!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'Pasted_image_at_2017_11_02_11_16_AM_(3).jpg', 1, '2017-11-02 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(52, 'Our Check-In experience here @Outpost', 1, 'our-check-in-experience-here-outpost', 'outpost-blog/blog-outpost-club/2017/11/6/the-check-in-experience-here-outpostedit', 'Our Check-In experience here @Outpost', 'Our Check-In experience here @Outpost', 'You did it! You took the step of moving to New York City and we are so happy you decided you want to stay with us! ', '<p>You did it! You took the step of moving to New York City and we are so happy you decided you want to stay with us! We know this step can be scary, so in this article, we want to share with you what</p>', '<p>You did it! You took the step of moving to New York City and we are so happy you decided you want to stay with us! We know this step can be scary, so in this article, we want to share with you what you should expect when you arrive here. Here @Outpost, we have a \'House Leader\'. The house leader is someone from within the community that has lived at the house you arrive in for a while and knows the in\'s and out\'s of the building and the company.</p>\r\n<p>He/She will make sure your room is:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Ready before you arrive</li>\r\n<li>They\'ll give you a fresh towel and bed sheets</li>\r\n<li>They will open the door for you</li>\r\n<li>Help you through our Move-In procedure (Which most importantly involves giving you the WiFi Password ;))</li>\r\n<li>They\'ll help you with any questions you have during the duration of your stay</li>\r\n<li>They\'ll make sure everyone behaves responsibly, handles broken appliances...</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>It\'s our mission to make the Check-In procedure here as smooth and pleasurable as possible for you and I hope you enjoy your stay with us!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>If you\'re interested in staying with us or want more information, <a href=\"../join-us\">fill out our form</a> here and someone on our team will contact you ASAP!&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'our-check-in-experience.jpeg', 1, '2017-11-05 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(53, 'Why Coliving? Live, work and play with like-minded people. (Source Coliving.com)', 1, 'why-coliving-live-work-and-play-with-like-minded-people-source-colivingcom', 'outpost-blog/blog-outpost-club/2017/11/9/why-coliving-live-work-and-play-with-like-minded-people-source-colivingcom', 'Why Coliving? Live, work and play with like-minded people', 'Why Coliving? Live, work and play with like-minded people. (Source Coliving.com)', 'This article was published on www.coliving.com, they post amazing content about the coliving industry that we would love to share with you', '<p>(This article was published on www.coliving.com, they post amazing content about the coliving industry that we would love to share with you guys) COLIVING CAN BE A LOT OF THINGS TO A LOT OF.</p>', '<h2><em>(This article was published on <a href=\"http://www.coliving.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.coliving.com</a>, they post amazing content about the coliving industry that we would love to share with you guys)</em></h2>\r\n<h3>Coliving can be a lot of things to a lot of different people. For many professionals, it is the chance to extend their personal network, or engage in team building in new environment.</h3>\r\n<p>Coliving can be a lot of things to a lot of different people. For many professionals, it is the chance to extend their personal network, or engage in team building in new environment. For some, coliving takes on a more personal tone. It can be a chance to <a href=\"http://www.huffingtonpost.com/kristine-scotto/the-importance-of-worklif_b_10128144.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">reinstate balance</a>&nbsp;to a busy work schedule, or a moment to cultivate new relationships through sharing.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Workers today are questioning the rhyme and reason behind work more than ever before. Younger generations have had to embrace change and thus quickly adapt to less than perfect economic circumstances. But, the need for rapid change has seen various positive outcomes, such as the development of a booming global coworking scene and more recently, coliving.</p>\r\n<p>As the concept of collaboration over competition has become more commonplace, there is now a global community of professionals who wouldn&rsquo;t do it any other way. This flexible and imaginative workforce is looking to test the boundaries of the modern workforce, and open to sharing more than just a desk. Rather than just <a href=\"https://hbr.org/2016/04/what-do-millennials-really-want-at-work\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">working for the weekend</a>, workers want to bring the joys of the weekend into the workplace. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Not just fun and games</h2>\r\n<p>Many digital nomads swear by their time <a href=\"https://www.entrepreneur.com/article/237446\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">out of the office</a>. Those who are permitted to work remotely can now turn to coworking and coliving when they need to step away from their routine. Our very human need to change scenery every once in awhile is no longer only associated with lack of commitment, but rather it&rsquo;s associated with <a href=\"https://hbr.org/2015/05/why-people-thrive-in-coworking-spaces\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">workplace wellbeing and productivity</a>.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>While coliving may seem like a vacation at first, many spaces are set-up for those who need to get things done. Platforms like <a href=\"https://www.roam.co/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Roam</a>, a startup that has a global network of coliving spaces, encourages productivity by offering members fully equipped workspace in a homey environment. Digital nomads, entrepreneurs and companies can choose from a variety of locations without having to stress about logistics. In fact, one of the reasons coliving spaces have become so popular is because they provide high quality and reliable workspaces so members can relax and focus on their experience without having to worry about whether or not they can connect to Wifi.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Places like <a href=\"http://www.hackerparadise.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Hacker Paradise</a>&nbsp;know how important work is, but they also value time off. Taking care of logistics, like accommodation, functional workspace and community curation, the Hacker Paradise team allows participants to focus on getting to know one another and creating room for fruitful collaborations flow.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Live together, grow together</h2>\r\n<p><img title=\"Why Coliving? Live, work and play with like-minded people. (Source Coliving.com) (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Why%20Coliving/Source_coliving.jpg\" alt=\"Why Coliving? Live, work and play with like-minded people. (Source Coliving.com) (Image-1)\" /></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.freepik.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Designed by jcomp / Freepik</a></p>\r\n<p>Ready or not, joining a coliving space is immediately becoming a part of a vibrant community. Luckily, those who are new to coliving can expect that their housemates are also there for a similar reason. No matter the reason for coliving, the movement attracts a certain type of personality, one that is curious, open and ready for a change. Through common understanding, coliving spaces are home to ready-made communities. For those who have been on the road alone for a while they can ease their loneliness by joining a coliving space. In the case of companies which work closely together, meeting new people and forming potential partnerships can be an enriching professional experience.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>As everyone has different needs, coliving spaces are designed to offer various programs, workshops, and activities. In addition, many spaces have a set of guidelines&nbsp;that they expect participants to follow. House rules can help participants get the most out of their experience, as there is a sense of order and clarity that colivers can abide by. One of the benefits of coliving is having the chance to grow by learning how others live. By making sure that that basics are covered, like designated quiet hours and cleanliness, keeps members from having unnecessary disagreements.</p>\r\n<p>While coliving is not for everyone, &nbsp;it&rsquo;s important to remember even those who are not outwardly social can still greatly benefit (and enjoy) the experience of living with others. For those who might prefer to spend their time alone, coliving can be a wonderful way learn in a new moment and throughout their everyday lives. Whether extroverted or introverted, colivers can benefit from each other\'s&rsquo; differences, which is a great life lesson no matter where you are in your career or personal life.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Understanding play as a form of productivity</h2>\r\n<p>The way of the working world in countries that have undergone an Industrial Revolution is often focused on getting a job that will pay the bills until you retire. Added pressure comes from being made to feel that you need to love what you do. The combination creates a one size fits all model for success, which let&rsquo;s face it, doesn&rsquo;t really work. The rise of precarious work has led workers to question the path to success. For example, financial incentives are no longer the only way to keep workers happy, but rather allowing them to <a href=\"https://www.dezeen.com/2016/04/05/co-living-shared-collective-accommodation-housing-millennials-trend-common-wework/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">enjoy </a>is key.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>A very large part of the coliving model is focused on play. While coliving spaces are commonly built for professionals, the foundation of coliving is based on relationships cultivated through experience. Like traveling to a new country, or learning a new skill, bonding with a new person can be just as inspiring. Rather than just saying hello on your way to the office, coliving gives you the chance to meet your new coworkers through sharing experiences. Or rather, going on an adventure and playing together.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Many coliving spaces organize day trips and excursions.&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.sun-desk.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Sun Desk</a>&nbsp;is a great example of a coliving space trying to located the ideal work/life balance. The Moroccan-based spaces take advantage of the natural surroundings and local community. They offer surfing in partnership with the local surf school, or day trips to the local markets and surrounding areas, which are great ways to get to know your neighbour, inside and out. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><em>(This article was published on <a href=\"http://www.coliving.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.coliving.com</a>, they post amazing content about the coliving industry that we would love to share with you guys)</em></h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'Source_coliving.jpg', 1, '2017-11-08 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(54, 'Thanksgiving At Outpost Club', 1, 'thanksgiving-at-outpost-club', 'outpost-blog/blog-outpost-club/2017/12/1/thanksgiving-at-outpost-club', 'Thanksgiving At Outpost Club', 'Thanksgiving At Outpost Club', 'Happy Thanksgiving! I know, we\'re a little late to the party, but we just wanted to share this article about our thanksgiving party here at Outpost a few weeks ago. For all members who stay', '<p>Happy Thanksgiving! I know, we\'re a little late to the party, but we just wanted to share this article about our thanksgiving party here at Outpost a few weeks ago. For all members who stayed in.</p>', '<p><strong>Happy Thanksgiving! I know, we\'re a little late to the party, but we just wanted to share this article about our thanksgiving party here at Outpost a few weeks ago. For all members who stayed in New York City for Thanksgiving, Outpost Club really tried to create a sense of family and tradition. This is what happened!&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>While many of our members went home to be with their families this Thanksgiving, not everyone was able to do so. And a lot of our international members were interested in experiencing what this America holiday was like. Having heard about this, we knew it would be a great opportunity to have an event on a day that everyone has off!</p>\r\n<p>Our lovely house leaders that stayed in New York for holiday ran the show. In the morning, everyone woke up super early to meet up at the Thanksgiving Day Parade. Most of our members had never been to the parade, so it\'s clear to see their excitement in the pictures below.</p>\r\n<p>Then, later in the afternoon, the members went back to the Ridgewood and Knickerbocker House, and had Thanksgiving dinners! Outpost Club provided many of the mainstays (turkey, mashed potatoes, stuffing, and pumpkin pie) while members were encouraged to bring their own dishes as well. In the end, our members\' bellies were full and a true American Thanksgiving was a success!</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><img ti