(80, 'Outpost Club Welcomes Mirena to the Team!', 1, 'outpost-club-welcomes-mirena-to-the-team', 'outpost-blog/blog-outpost-club/2017/9/5/outpost-club-welcomes-mirena-to-the-teamedit', 'Outpost Club Welcomes Mirena to the Team!', 'Outpost Club Welcomes Mirena to the Team!', 'Though she\'s been with us for a while, Outpost Club would like to officially introduce Mirena to the world as one of our great house leaders', '<p>Though she\'s been with us for a while, Outpost Club would like to officially introduce Mirena to the world as one of our great house leaders!</p>', '<p>Though she\'s been with us for a while, Outpost Club would like to officially introduce Mirena to the world as one of our great house leaders!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Club Welcomes Mirena to the Team! (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Club_Welcomes_Mirena/mirenasq.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Club Welcomes Mirena to the Team! (Image-1)\" /></p>\r\n<p>What&rsquo;s your name?&nbsp;<br /><em>Mirena!</em></p>\r\n<p>Where are you from?<br /><em>I came to NYC from San Fransisco</em></p>\r\n<p>What house do you live in?<br /><em>The Bedford House (the best house!)</em></p>\r\n<p>How long have you lived with Outpost Club?<br /><em>I have been with outpost club since April</em></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Club Welcomes Mirena to the Team! (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Club_Welcomes_Mirena/21433043_10212415339911492_1607971042550332303_n.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Club Welcomes Mirena to the Team! (Image-2)\" /></p>\r\n<p>Other than being a house leader, who are you?When you&rsquo;re not being a house leader, what do you do?<br /><em>I am a former airbnb host, and like kayaking and culture. I am also an artist!</em></p>\r\n<p>Favorite event so far?<br /><em>My favorite event so far was karaoke night, everyone sang really well.</em></p>\r\n<p>Why live at Outpost Club? What do you like about it?<br /><em>What I love about living here is meeting people from all over the world. </em></p>\r\n<p>Any additional info?<br /><em>My solo show - Ingredients of a Subway Car - opens next week! Take a look! (Picture on the right)</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Also, Check me out on Instagram:&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/mirenarhee/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://www.instagram.com/mirenarhee/</a></p>', 'mirenasq.jpg', 1, '2017-09-04 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(81, 'Why Work in Coliving?', 1, 'why-work-in-coliving', 'outpost-blog/blog-outpost-club/2017/9/6/why-work-in-coliving', 'Why Work in Coliving?', 'Why Work in Coliving?', 'It\'s a rapidly growing industry. There seem to be new companies opening coliving spaces everyday', '<p>As we Are starting to expand our operations, we thought it might be a good idea to give a breakdown of the benefits of working for Outpost Club. So here is our list of reasons to live/work in</p>', '<h3>As we Are starting to expand our operations, we thought it might be a good idea to give a breakdown of the benefits of working for Outpost Club. So here is our list of reasons to live/work in coliving:</h3>\r\n<p><strong><em>It\'s a rapidly growing industry.</em></strong><br />There seem to be new companies opening coliving spaces everyday. Nevertheless, the industry is still small, and developing skills that only a small group of people currently have gives you a great advantage when looking for jobs.</p>\r\n<p><strong><em>You\'re surrounded by motivated people.</em></strong><br />When living and working with people who took a chance on entering this new industry, you\'ll be surrounded by people who get it. By \"get it\" we mean that they understand this:&nbsp;the way in which we\'ve historically thought about our housing accommodations and our working hours is changing. These are people at the forefront of a rapid shift in the way we live our daily lives.</p>\r\n<p><em><strong>You can commute to your kitchen, or anywhere for that matter.</strong> </em><br />All of our employees (and members who are freelancing/working from home) use our spaces to work from home, productively. Some sit in the kitchen, some sit in the coworking space, but regardless, home becomes a place of work during the day.</p>\r\n<p><strong><em>You\'re working for a community, not an apartment building.</em></strong><br />Work has more meaning when you are truly a part of something, that\'s why most of our employees both work and live in our spaces. When the work you do directly impacts your surroundings, it is obvious that your work holds importance.</p>\r\n<p><strong><em>If it\'s a startup, you can have a large impact, quickly.</em></strong><br />When you work at a startup, it\'s all-hands-on-deck. If you can show that you are an integral part of the team, you will gain new responsibilities, quickly. You might be tasked with revamping the entire communications strategy and executing it, or hiring and managing the newest employees, or creating the agenda and running meetings with your supervisors. All of which are valuable skills for any job, and you can gain them quickly at a startup.</p>\r\n<p><em><strong>And our favorite benefit: </strong>You\'ll meet people from all over the world</em><br />If you live and work in our spaces for as little as six months, you are likely to live with as many as 15 nationalities at any given time, and over 50 nationalities over the duration of that stay. Some of our employees like to say \"I have a home to stay at in over 30 countries, all from the friends I\'ve made here.\"</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'eastbushwick_small-co-space.jpg', 1, '2017-09-05 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(82, 'Member Monday Nawar Firdaws', 1, 'member-monday-nawar-firdaws', 'outpost-blog/blog-outpost-club/2018/2/12/member-monday-nawar-firdawsedit', 'Member Monday Nawar Firdaws', 'Member Monday Nawar Firdaws', 'Member Monday: Nawar Firdaws', '<p>WELCOME TO OUR MEMBERS\' PROFILE SERIES, WHERE WE SHARE THE STORIES OF WHY THEY MOVED TO NYC, AND ALSO WHAT THEY LIKE ABOUT THEIR TIME HERE. THIS WEEK WE&rsquo;RE INTRODUCING YOU TO NAWAR WHO STAYED WITH.</p>', '<h3>Welcome to our members\' profile series, where we share the stories of why they moved to NYC, and also what they like about their time here. This week we&rsquo;re introducing you to Nawar who stayed with us for 4 months.&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Tell us a little about yourself</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>\"As you already know, my name is Nawar Idrus. I came all the way from the land of good weather, good food, and extremely friendly people - Malaysia. For those who are unfamiliar with the country, it\'s located in between Thailand and Singapore!\"</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>What brought you to NYC?</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>\"I work as a journalist back home, but I\'ve always wanted to experience life in the Big Apple (I blame various Hollywood movies for my obsession on NYC). So my company and I came to an agreement where I was allowed to work remotely for a few months.\"</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>What has been your best experience here?</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>\"It\'s hard to pinpoint one, to be honest. Every week - the weekends especially - has been filled with different, yet equally memorable experiences. But if I have to think of one, I would say the Halloween party thrown by Outpost Club, which took place on the second week of my stay at the Bushwick House. That was probably the moment I loved most, because it was at the party that I met the people who are now my best friends.</em></p>\r\n<p><em>I also got to go up on the rooftop of Outpost\'s East Bushwick house, which was a really cool moment.\"</em></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Member Monday Nawar Firdaws (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Member_Monday/20180212_165511.jpg\" alt=\"Member Monday Nawar Firdaws (Image-1)\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>What do you think of coliving?</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>\"I think it\'s great! When I moved here all by myself, I was worried it would be difficult to make friends. Especially since from what I\'ve read about NYC, I had this impression that everyone is too busy with their own lives to spend time getting to know someone new.</em></p>\r\n<p><em>But being in a coliving environment like Outpost Club - where you have housemates who share the same \"big city move\" story - has made the process of forming true friendships a lot easier.</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Being able to explore the city with friends instead of by yourself, also made the experiences so much more fun!</em></p>\r\n<p><em>And not having to worry about signing a lease, or buying furniture, etc, took a load off my shoulder. I\'m really glad for that :) \"</em></p>', '20180212_165511.jpg', 1, '2018-02-11 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(83, 'Outpost Club Enjoys Flavor-Filled Day Out with Ben and Jerry\'s', 1, 'outpost-club-enjoys-flavor-filled-day-out-with-ben-and-jerrys', 'outpost-blog/blog-outpost-club/2018/2/13/outpost-club-enjoys-flavor-filled-day-out-with-ben-and-jerrys', 'Outpost Club Enjoys Flavor-Filled Day Out with Ben and Jerry\'s', 'Outpost Club Enjoys Flavor-Filled Day Out with Ben and Jerry\'s', 'Outpost Club Enjoys Flavor-Filled Day Out with Ben and Jerry\'s', '<p>Two heads are better than one. This can\'t be truer when it comes to exploring a city as massive and as exciting as the Big Apple.</p>', '<p>Two heads are better than one. This can\'t be truer when it comes to exploring a city as massive and as exciting as the Big Apple.</p>\r\n<p>While there is always something to do here, deciding or even finding out which ones are worth spending your time on can be quite a daunting task.</p>\r\n<p>That\'s why having a community, and more specifically friends to plan your days out is very important.</p>\r\n<p>One of our members, Tacia Duarte, can testify to this.</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Club Enjoys Flavor-Filled Day Out with Ben and Jerry\'s (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Club_Enjoys_Flavor-Filled/IMG_20180207_174117465.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Club Enjoys Flavor-Filled Day Out with Ben and Jerry\'s (Image-1)\" /></p>\r\n<h3>\"<em>While we see each other in the house all the time, when we&rsquo;re doing something together outside it helps us become a better family</em>,&rdquo;</h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">-&nbsp;Farhan Khawaja, a YouTuber who lives in our Knickerbocker House</p>\r\n<p>Tacia, along with the new friends she made at our Knickerbocker House&nbsp;had put their heads together as they do every week, and landed themselves on a flavor-filled Wednesday at <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/2301422870084147/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Ben and Jerry\'s</a>&nbsp;launching of its new secret flavors!</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;<em>We have a great community at Knickerbocker House, where we are always sharing ideas on our <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/outpostclubNY/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Facebook group</a></em>,&rdquo; she said. &ldquo;<em>This particular event was suggested by Evan who is a pastry chef. And hey, we are always down to whatever involves food!</em>&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>But the food wasn\'t the only delight they experienced. For some members, the adventure had also allowed them the opportunity to explore the Winter Garden at <a href=\"https://brookfieldplaceny.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Brookfield Place</a>.</p>\r\n<p>The best part was that they had a guide to really show them the spot\'s hidden gems. Enter Farhan Khawaja, a YouTuber who also lives in our Knickerbocker House.</p>\r\n<p>Brookfield Place was the spot he visited whenever he felt depressed. It was his safe place, one that he was happy to share with his <a href=\"../\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Outpost</a>&nbsp;family.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;<em>I love it there because the view is spectacular. You can see the water and the amazing crowd outdoors. It also has a restaurant called <a href=\"https://brookfieldplaceny.com/directory/skinny-pizza\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Skinny Pizza</a> where I can get my comfort food: an extra large, gluten-free pizza</em>,&rdquo; said Farhan. &ldquo;<em>So being able to bring my housemates there was amazing as it helped us bond even more!</em>&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>\"<em>While we see each other in the house&nbsp;all the time, when we&rsquo;re doing something together outside it helps us become a better family</em>,&rdquo;&nbsp;he continued.</p>\r\n<p>Go check out the photos they took! Don\'t they look like they had a blast? So come stay with us&nbsp;and join in the fun!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div><img title=\"Outpost Club Enjoys Flavor-Filled Day Out with Ben and Jerry\'s (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Club_Enjoys_Flavor-Filled/IMG_20180207_173800209.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Club Enjoys Flavor-Filled Day Out with Ben and Jerry\'s (Image-2)\" /> The gang, full of ice cream!</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>You can also follow Tacia and Farhan&rsquo;s NYC adventures through their Facebook and Instagram. Just find them by clicking the links below!</p>\r\n<p>Facebook:&nbsp;Tacia Duarte&nbsp;and Farhan Khawaja&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Instagram:&nbsp;taciafunsize&nbsp;and doctestosterone</p>', 'IMG_20180207_174117465.jpg', 1, '2018-02-12 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(84, 'Because Everyone Is Entitled to The Day Of Love ', 1, 'everyone-is-entitled-to-the-day-of-love-', '', 'Because Everyone Is Entitled to The Day Of Love ', 'Because Everyone Is Entitled to The Day Of Love ', 'Valentine\'s Day doesn\'t have to be a lonely one just because you\'re single', '<p>Valentine\'s Day doesn\'t have to be a lonely one just because you\'re single.</p>', '<p>Valentine\'s Day doesn\'t have to be a lonely one just because you\'re single.</p>\r\n<p>We at the <a href=\"../\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Outpost Club</a>&nbsp;knows that all too well. That\'s why we decided to celebrate the day of love in a true coliving style: by throwing a big bash that centered around friendship and community!</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Because Everyone Is Entitled to The Day Of Love (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/BECAUSE_EVERYONE/GIF.gif\" alt=\"Because Everyone Is Entitled to The Day Of Love (Image-1)\" /></p>\r\n<p>As with all the parties we had thrown for our members, the idea for Outpost\'s Valentine\'s Day bash came from the coming together of our <a href=\"../new-york\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">house</a>&nbsp;leaders and members.</p>\r\n<p>This year the Knickerbocker House&nbsp;decided to play host, led by its house leader the amazing Tacia Duarte who also happens to be our community manager.</p>\r\n<p><strong>\"We thought hey, why should we miss out on all the fun that Valentine\'s day has to offer just because we are single?\" said Tacia. \"So we got our single members together - even the ones who aren\'t - to celebrate the love between friends, with us!\"</strong></p>\r\n<p>The planning began three weeks ago. When they had everything down to the T, Tacia posted the event details on all our houses\'&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/outpostclubNY/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Facebook</a>&nbsp;groups.</p>\r\n<p>We must say that we got a little too excited by the level of interest we received. That, as you can see from the pictures, was the reason why we went all out to make sure our members have a day they&rsquo;ll never forget.</p>\r\n<p>Yap, we got cheese fondue, chocolate fountain, and even strawberries and grapes to go with them! Of course there were also a bunch of other homemade snacks that everyone shared while getting to know each other better.</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Because Everyone Is Entitled to The Day Of Love (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/BECAUSE_EVERYONE/choc%2Bfountain.jpg\" alt=\"Because Everyone Is Entitled to The Day Of Love (Image-2)\" /></p>\r\n<p>And thanks to the brilliance of our organizing team, our members got more than 50% off for tickets to a <strong>Valentine\'s Day special comedy show</strong>&nbsp;at the UCB theatre.</p>\r\n<p>\"We all had a really great time! Everyone, even our new members felt welcome. We had great food, great conversation, and best of all, great company,\" said Tacia. \"So, mission accomplished!\"</p>\r\n<p>Go ahead and check out the photos of the party. Hopefully they\'ll bring a smile to your face, the way they did for us!</p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, do follow Tacia and Outpost Club on our social media, A little warning though, you might suffer from great anticipation at the thought of <a href=\"../join-us\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">joining us</a>!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><img title=\"Because Everyone Is Entitled to The Day Of Love (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/BECAUSE_EVERYONE/group%2Bpic%2B1-1.jpg\" alt=\"Because Everyone Is Entitled to The Day Of Love (Image-3)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Because Everyone Is Entitled to The Day Of Love (Image-4), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/BECAUSE_EVERYONE/group%2Bpic%2B2.jpg\" alt=\"Because Everyone Is Entitled to The Day Of Love (Image-4)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Because Everyone Is Entitled to The Day Of Love (Image-5), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/BECAUSE_EVERYONE/pic%2B3.jpg\" alt=\"Because Everyone Is Entitled to The Day Of Love (Image-5)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Because Everyone Is Entitled to The Day Of Love (Image-6), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/BECAUSE_EVERYONE/pic%2B6.jpg\" alt=\"Because Everyone Is Entitled to The Day Of Love (Image-6)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Because Everyone Is Entitled to The Day Of Love (Image-7), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/BECAUSE_EVERYONE/pic%2B7.jpg\" alt=\"Because Everyone Is Entitled to The Day Of Love (Image-7)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Because Everyone Is Entitled to The Day Of Love (Image-8), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/BECAUSE_EVERYONE/pic%2B9.jpg\" alt=\"Because Everyone Is Entitled to The Day Of Love (Image-8)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Because Everyone Is Entitled to The Day Of Love (Image-9), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/BECAUSE_EVERYONE/pic%2B10.jpg\" alt=\"Because Everyone Is Entitled to The Day Of Love (Image-9)\" /></p>\r\n</div>', 'GIF.gif', 1, '2018-02-15 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(85, 'Outpost Club Celebrates Oseé\'s 30th Birthday Bash!', 1, 'outpost-club-celebrates-oses-30th-birthday-bash', '', 'Outpost Club Celebrates Oseé\'s 30th Birthday Bash!', 'Outpost Club Celebrates Oseé\'s 30th Birthday Bash!', 'Osée Koss knows just the right way to make a perfect margarita.', '<p>Os&eacute;e Koss knows just the right way to make a perfect margarita.</p>', '<p>Os&eacute;e Koss knows just the right way to make a perfect margarita.</p>\r\n<p>\"Lime juice, triple sec, and rum. You also need to put some salt around the cocktail glass,&rdquo; said Os&eacute;e. &ldquo;Then you will have the salty taste that compliments the drink really well, because margarita is a very sweet cocktail.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>But the secret ingredient that had put his <a href=\"../\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Outpost</a> family into a party mood as they celebrated his 30th birthday last Saturday, was \"friendship.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Almost 20 of our members from various Outpost houses had braved the rain and cold winter weather to party with Os&eacute;e at our Ridgewood House. And like the French man, most of them had moved to NYC on their own.</p>\r\n<p>That&rsquo;s why the party, just like all the different ones we organize every month, presented the perfect opportunity for our members to get to know each other. Especially those who have just recently joined us.</p>\r\n<p>Although Os&eacute;e - who is also a graphic designer and a YouTuber - is anything but a newcomer to the Outpost community.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;I stayed at Outpost Club the first time I came to NYC, which was about three years ago. I had such a good experience that this is now my third stay with Outpost. I love it here,\" he said. \"It\'s so easy to make friends, and through these parties we also get to have fun with each other! It just makes me feel like I\'m a part of a really cool community.\"</p>\r\n<p>The way Os&eacute;e viewed the party was spot on to the way our other members did. One of our house leaders, Simon Bogdanov, said after the party which went on for about 5 hours, he went home not only with a full stomach (there were lots of cupcakes and chocolates!), but also with some new friends.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;Os&eacute;e told me about the party a couple of weeks ago. So through our <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/outpostclubNY/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Facebook</a> group, I got everyone at the Bushwick House together,&rdquo; he said. &ldquo;We had so much fun! I also got to know some members who have just moved into the Ridgewood House. We are now Facebook friends!&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>And &ldquo;fun&rdquo; is the perfect way to describe the birthday bash! But we don&rsquo;t want you to just take our words for it. We&rsquo;ll let the pictures do the talking.</p>\r\n<p>If you want to join in the fun (we know you want to), come stay with us!</p>\r\n<p>You can also click the links below to check out Os&eacute;e and Simon&rsquo;s social media to get a glimpse of what life in NYC and Outpost Club looks like.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>', 'outpost-club-celebrates-oses-30th-birthday-bash.jpeg', 1, '2018-02-16 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(86, '7 Reasons Why You Should Co-Live With Outpost Club', 1, '7-reasons-why-you-should-co-live-with-outpost-club', 'outpost-blog/blog-outpost-club/2018/2/20/7-reasons-why-you-should-co-live-with-outpost-club ', '7 Reasons Why You Should Co-Live With Outpost Club', '7 Reasons Why You Should Co-Live With Outpost Club', 'NYC is one of the largest cities in the world, with an estimated 8.6 million population size. With it being the headquarters of every major company, it comes to no surprise that almost everyone.', '<p>NYC is one of the largest cities in the world, with an estimated 8.6 million population size. With it being the headquarters of every major company, it comes to no surprise that almost everyone.</p>', '<p><strong>NYC is one of the largest cities in the world, with an estimated 8.6 million population size. With it being the headquarters of every major company, it comes to no surprise that almost everyone with a global-sized dream has, or plans to move to the Big Apple at some point in their life.</strong></p>\r\n<p>But moving here is not as easy as packing your bags and checking into the first hotel you come across. First of all, hotels are ridiculously expensive, and so are other types of accommodation. Even if you are lucky enough to find one that is affordable, chances are you will end up in a shoe-box sized apartment.</p>\r\n<p>It is also easy to feel lonely and lost in a city this size, where everyone is too busy chasing after their own American dream to just stop and say hello to a stranger they meet on the bustling streets of NYC.</p>\r\n<p>This brings us to the number one reason why you should opt for co-living.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>1. COMMUNITY</h3>\r\n<p>Co-living, as you will discover when you come and live with us in Outpost Club, provides you with the most important element when moving to a new city: community. The second you check into our co-living space, you will get to meet people from all sorts of backgrounds. Some of them may even have a story similar to yours.</p>\r\n<p>To make the assimilation process even easier, we at Outpost Club regularly organize events that get residents from all of our six houses together. Our members are also encouraged to host their own get-togethers, like potluck dinners and game nights. Recently one house even threw an &ldquo;Ugly Sweater Party&rdquo;. Can you imagine a better way to break the ice with your new Housemates?</p>\r\n<p>Basically, with co-living you&rsquo;ll end up with friends who you can spend your nights in with. And you\'ll always have someone to do something with on the weekends.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"7 Reasons Why You Should Co-Live With Outpost Club (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/7_REASONS/rene-bohmer-490009-unsplash.jpg\" alt=\"7 Reasons Why You Should Co-Live With Outpost Club (Image-1)\" /></p>\r\n<h3>2. JUST BRING YOUR SUITCASE</h3>\r\n<p>Remember when we said that moving to New York can be challenging? Well, we aim to make this process as convenient as possible for you. As a start, you can move in with us whenever you want to! And all you need is just your suitcase. We take care of the rest. Towels? Comfortable beds and sheets? Shampoos and body gel? Pots and pans? We got them all sorted for you.</p>\r\n<p>You also won&rsquo;t have to worry about the nitty-gritty of maintaining an apartment. If any of the appliances are not working, you just have to let us know and we&rsquo;ll take care of it. To top it off, we have professional cleaners coming over twice a week to clean the spaces.. including your room!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>3. FREE COFFEE!</h3>\r\n<p>This one deserves the exclamation mark and a stand-alone mention, as we all know there isn\'ta problem that can\'t be solved with a cup of coffee. To help you kick-start your day - or night if you\'re the \"burn the midnight oil\" type of person - we supply good quality coffee powder so you can have your dose of caffeine anytime you need it.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"7 Reasons Why You Should Co-Live With Outpost Club (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/7_REASONS/Copy%2Bof%2BIMG_4114.jpg\" alt=\"7 Reasons Why You Should Co-Live With Outpost Club (Image-2)\" /></p>\r\n<h3>4. SHARED SPACE = MORE SPACE</h3>\r\n<p>Almost everything in NYC is expensive. While it might be alright to skim on certain luxuries like entertainment and shopping, you shouldn\'t have to compromise on your resting space when you just want to sit back and relax.</p>\r\n<p>From a fully furnished bedroom with not just a bed, but also shelves, cabinet spaces and reading lights, to a common living room complete with a 55-inch TV, big couches, and a co-working space (just to name a few); we provide them all for your comfort. Also, as you are paying for membership instead of just rent, you can move around our six different houses if you wish to.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"7 Reasons Why You Should Co-Live With Outpost Club (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"https://cdn2.hubspot.net/hubfs/4068949/Imported_Blog_Media/Screen+Shot+2018-02-20+at+15_29_59_png_59.png\" alt=\"7 Reasons Why You Should Co-Live With Outpost Club (Image-3)\" /></p>\r\n<h3>5. SAFETY</h3>\r\n<p>At Outpost Club you never have to worry about your safety, or even of your belongings. Our common spaces have CCTV cameras, our houses all have code-access front doors, on site house leaders, and august home security locks!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>6. NO KEYS, NO WORRIES</h3>\r\n<p>We have replaced the traditional key system with automated locks that are either password or phone-operated. This means you don\'t have to worry about taking your keys (or forgetting them) with you everytime you leave the house.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>7. MOBILITY</h3>\r\n<p>Right now we have spaces in six locations all over Bushwick, Bedford-Stuyvesant, Brooklyn and Ridgewood Queens. All our houses are close to the subway, local stores, as well as restaurants and bars. We know such places, especially ones that are reasonably priced, are not easy to find. So we found them for you. You\'re welcome :)</p>\r\n<p>If you are interested in what we have to offer, or perhaps just want to know more about our houses, go and <a href=\"../\" target=\"_blank\">check out our website!</a> You can also read what our former and current members have to say about their stay with us.</p>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"//cdn.embedly.com/widgets/media.html?src=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Fmaps%2Fd%2Fembed%3Fmid%3D1auTDUCQMxu4x5uNSz2_xs-aIb8m5zCB1%26hl%3Den_US&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Fmaps%2Fd%2Fviewer%3Fmid%3D1auTDUCQMxu4x5uNSz2_xs-aIb8m5zCB1%26hl%3Den_US&amp;image=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Fmaps%2Fd%2Fthumbnail%3Fmid%3D1auTDUCQMxu4x5uNSz2_xs-aIb8m5zCB1%26hl%3Den_US&amp;key=61d05c9d54e8455ea7a9677c366be814&amp;type=text%2Fhtml&amp;schema=google&amp;wmode=opaque\" width=\"100%\" height=\"400px\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>', '7-reasons-why-you-should-co-live-with-outpost-club.jpg', 1, '2018-02-19 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(87, 'Meet Tacia Duarte, Our Community Manager And Your New Best Friend', 1, 'meet-tacia-duarte ', 'blog-outpost-club/2018/2/20/meet-tacia-duarte-our-community-manager-and-your-new-best-friend', 'Meet Tacia Duarte, Our Community Manager And Your New Best Friend', 'Meet Tacia Duarte, Our Community Manager And Your New Best Friend', 'Meet Tacia Duarte, Our Community Manager And Your New Best Friend.', '<p>Tacia Duarte loves anything and everything that shouts \"Community!\"</p>', '<p>Tacia Duarte loves anything and everything that shouts \"Community!\"</p>\r\n<p>This is because the artistic Brazilian, like many of our members, had moved to the city all by herself, making her appreciate the perks of being a part of a community that she can also call her family.</p>\r\n<p>And with her fun and outgoing personality, balanced with the right amount of responsibility, Tacia has made everyone around her feel right at home at the very first meeting itself.</p>\r\n<p>So we don\'t really need to list the reasons she\'s our Community Manager, and the leader of Outpost\'s <a href=\"../the-knickerbocker-house\" rel=\"nofollow\">Knickerbocker House</a>&nbsp;.</p>\r\n<p>But what we will do, is help you get to know her a little better. After all, when you move into one of our houses, we\'re pretty sure she\'ll be your guide for everything cool New York&nbsp;has to offer, as well as the best friend to spend your nights out with!</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Meet Tacia Duarte, Our Community Manager And Your New Best Friend (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Meet_Tacia_Duarte/IMG_2515.jpg\" alt=\"Meet Tacia Duarte, Our Community Manager And Your New Best Friend (Image-1)\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>What brought you to New York?</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>So, I\'m a fine artist. I create designer toys, caricatures and miniatures. I came to New York to pursue my passion, to experience the huge artistic community here.&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>How did you become a member of the <a href=\"../\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Outpost</a>&nbsp;team?</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>I have been a member of the Outpost Club since late July last year. Right from the beginning, I was always very involved with the team and with the staff, as I wanted to be a part of what they are creating here.</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Because of my interest in helping the Outpost team build on this community, I became Knickerbocker\'s house leader in October. Then they invited me to be a community manager, to help take care of the other houses.</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>What is your role?</strong></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Meet Tacia Duarte, Our Community Manager And Your New Best Friend (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Meet_Tacia_Duarte/img-34.jpg\" alt=\"Meet Tacia Duarte, Our Community Manager And Your New Best Friend (Image-2)\" /></p>\r\n<p><em>As the community manager, my job is to make sure every member has a great experience while they\'re staying at the Outpost Club. So I go to all the houses and meet with the members. I also plan events to help bring the members together!</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>What is your favorite Outpost moment?</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>Recently I threw <a href=\"../blog/everyone-is-entitled-to-the-day-of-love-\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Valentine\'s Day</a>&nbsp;party at the Knickerbocker House. That was a lot of fun! We had people from the other houses coming over; we prepared dinner, we had fondue and chocolate fountain, which was really cool. Afterwards we all went to watch a comedy show in UCB theatre.</em></p>\r\n<p>Well,&nbsp;that\'s all we have for now. If you want to know more about Tacia, check out the video below. You can also follow her and Outpost Club on social media to see all the fun she\'s been having with us!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'IMG_2515.jpg', 1, '2018-02-19 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0);
