(88, 'Member Mondays Yasir Afzal', 1, 'member-mondays-yasir-afzal', 'outpost-blog/blog-outpost-club/2018/2/26/life-as-an-intern-in-nyc-as-told-by-oneedit', 'Member Mondays Yasir Afzal', 'Member Mondays Yasir Afzal', 'Member Mondays: Yasir Afzal', '<p>Yasir Afzal didn\'t need much time at all to describe his experience interning in NYC.</p>', '<p>Yasir Afzal didn\'t need much time at all to describe his experience interning in NYC.</p>\r\n<p>\"Felt like home,\" he said, a simple three-word statement which embodies a feeling every NYC newcomers hope for.</p>\r\n<p>The man who hailed from Richmond, Virginia, had stayed at <a href=\"../\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Outpost Club</a>\'s Knickerbocker House&nbsp;throughout his 10-week internship program at McGarryBowen&nbsp;in June last year.</p>\r\n<p>It was, in his own words, \"the best decision I could have made when moving to NYC as a first-timer.\"</p>\r\n<p>Having experienced life in the Big Apple, Yasir now wished to share the things he had learned with others who have either recently moved to the city for an internship, or those who are planning to do so in the near future.</p>\r\n<p>So read on to learn more about his experiences, and maybe pick up a tip or two on how to make the most of your time in one of the most exciting cities in the world.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Q: Tell us about your internship experience here.</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div><img title=\"Member Mondays Yasir Afzal (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Member_Mondays/20476083_10154771355878457_1403857605965616377_n.jpg\" alt=\"Member Mondays Yasir Afzal (Image-1)\" /> YASIR AT HIS INTERNSHIP WITH MCGARRYBOWEN</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>&ldquo;Overall, being an intern in NYC allowed me to gain the confidence already within me to do something I never thought I&rsquo;d be able to pull off. Fake it till you make it I always say.&rdquo;</em></p>\r\n<p><em>I, along with 16 other interns, </em><em>were</em><em> split by </em><em>department</em><em> and given accounts to work on over the course of the internship. Interns ranged from juniors in college to a 30-year-old who wanted to become an advertiser.</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Throughout the internship, mentorship sessions/workshops were set up by HR where industry vets and agency employees would share valuable information about the advertising world.</em></p>\r\n<p><em>I was able to work on high exposure brands which I was then able to see in real-world settings (i.e. TV spots).</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Q: What was the most exciting bit about your internship?</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>&ldquo;Look out for FREE events on Facebook!&rdquo;</em></p>\r\n<p><em>I got to meet Jim O&rsquo;Heir, who plays Jerry Gergich on Parks and Recreation. He wrote and starred in an indie movie where one of my agency&rsquo;s Creative Directors helped produce. I, along with four other interns that RSVP&rsquo;d to go, met him for drinks in a fancy bar in Times Square </em><em>beforehand,</em><em> and got a private viewing with Jim and other cast/crew members at the movie theater around the corner. All drinks and movie tickets were paid for!!!!</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Ya know, just a normal Wednesday in the Big Apple.</em></p>\r\n<p><em>The morning of the Summer Solstice, I got to practice yoga with about 200 other yogis in the middle of Times Square. The event was sponsored by Aerie, and we all got to keep the yoga mats they branded.</em></p>\r\n<p><em>After it was done, I hopped on the subway and was still able to make it </em><em>to</em><em> work on time. Definitely a surreal moment finding peace and tranquility in the middle of all the hustle and bustle that is Times Square at 8 a.m. on a weekday.</em></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Member Mondays Yasir Afzal (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Member_Mondays/Robertas.jpg\" alt=\"Member Mondays Yasir Afzal (Image-2)\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>Q: What were the challenges you faced?</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>&ldquo;NYC has no time for </em><em>second guessing</em><em>.&rdquo;</em></p>\r\n<p><em>It was very easy to get left behind both in the city itself and in the workplace, so I really had to make an effort to be seen and heard.</em></p>\r\n<p><em>BUDGET. I spent </em><em>waaaaay</em><em> too much on alcohol. Pregame &gt; buying drinks at the bar.</em></p>\r\n<p><em>(Also), living with a roommate can be tough, but living in a whole HOUSE of roommates can be even tougher. Find your balance.</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Q: How did you overcome these challenges?</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>&ldquo;Leave your old life behind and come to NYC to start a fresh, new one.&rdquo;</em></p>\r\n<p><em>While it is fun meeting new people, having to also live with them can be a challenge. I definitely had to have an open mind and prioritize RESPECT. If you use your time in NYC and at Outpost with positivity, then you&rsquo;ll be able to make friendships that&rsquo;ll last a lifetime!</em></p>\r\n<p><em>In terms of packing, think minimalist. Be open to the city. Make eye contact with everyone. Talk to people you wouldn&rsquo;t normally talk to. Try new cuisines. New York is the portal to the world. There are so many languages spoken in the city and so many different cuisines to enrich your pallet.</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Stay aware of your surroundings and always make sure you have your wallet, phone, and keys on you. BRING AN EXTERNAL CHARGER. It&rsquo;s a scary feeling when your phone is on low battery, and you just took the wrong subway and got yourself lost (happened to me multiple times). Carry some cash for drunk munchies at Halal Cart at 1 a.m.</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Q: How did your stay in Outpost Club help you overcome the challenges you faced?</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>&ldquo;They helped relieve so many stresses and took care of a lot on the domestic end.&rdquo;</em></p>\r\n<p><em>That really helped in terms of me being able to allocate a lot of my time and energy on other things.</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Since I graduated college a couple of weeks before I moved to NYC, I was already under a lot of stress and pressure. So it was so nice to be able to rely on Outpost for a lot of the trivial stuff, like not having to bring toilet paper or having to worry about keeping kitchen necessities stocked.</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Outpost also has really <a href=\"../new-york\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">good locations</a>&nbsp;throughout New York City that are near public transit and grocery store, so I always felt like I was in the middle of things and not on the outskirts of town.</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Q: Did you find the environment and the facilities provided by Outpost Club helpful for your internship?</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>&ldquo;NYC is so full of different energies; it was nice to have a place to come back to and feel a sense of calm.&rdquo;</em></p>\r\n<p><em>My time at the Knickerbocker House was clean and spacious. I just had one roommate, which really helped space-wise. Very modern aesthetic and positive energy.</em></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Member Mondays Yasir Afzal (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Member_Mondays/July%2B4th.jpg\" alt=\"Member Mondays Yasir Afzal (Image-3)\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>Q: What should the future interns expect from their stay here?</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>&ldquo;Coming into the house I never expected to meet people I felt so connected to.&rdquo;</em></p>\r\n<p><em>If you are staying long-term at an Outpost house, be involved! Meet everyone in the house and share your life with them.</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Obviously</em><em>, you can&rsquo;t make friends with everyone, so just stay as respectful and positive as you can,&nbsp;and everything should be just fine.&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Q: Any advice for future NYC interns?</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>&ldquo;People don&rsquo;t remember what you did, they remember how you made them feel.&rdquo;</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Be yourself and enjoy your time in one of the greatest cities in the universe. I certainly did.</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '20476083_10154771355878457_1403857605965616377_n.jpg', 1, '2018-02-25 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(89, 'Outpost Celebrates Tacia\'s Birthday With A City Crawl', 1, 'outpost-celebrates-tacias-birthday-with-a-city-crawl', '', 'Outpost Celebrates Tacia\'s Birthday With A City Crawl', 'Outpost Celebrates Tacia\'s Birthday With A City Crawl', 'Outpost Celebrates Tacia\'s Birthday With A City Crawl', '<p>What do you do when your best friend\'s birthday falls on a weekend?</p>', '<p>What do you do when your best friend\'s birthday falls on a weekend?</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div><img title=\"Outpost Celebrates Tacia\'s Birthday With A City Crawl (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Celebrates_Tacias/20180224_193659_1519685138501.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Celebrates Tacia\'s Birthday With A City Crawl (Image-1)\" /> Tacia and Clement at the City Crawl</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>You party it up of course! Well, at least that\'s how we, at the <a href=\"../\" target=\"_blank\">Outpost Club</a>, celebrated our member and awesome community manager Tacia Duarte\'s&nbsp;birthday last Saturday. With a bar crawl around NYC.</p>\r\n<p>The event was planned by our responsible, yet fun house leaders from East Bushwick, Karisa Desjardins, and&nbsp;Ridgewood\'s&nbsp;Talia Simpson.</p>\r\n<p>As per the usual, they informed all our members&nbsp;of the plan through the houses\' respective <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/outpostclubNY/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Facebook</a>&nbsp;groups. And the adventure began soon after.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div><img title=\"Outpost Celebrates Tacia\'s Birthday With A City Crawl (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Celebrates_Tacias/20180224_193103_1519685380972.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Celebrates Tacia\'s Birthday With A City Crawl (Image-2)\" /> The gang at 123 Burger Shot Beer</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>We started off with $1 burgers, $2 shots, and $3 beers at&nbsp;123 Burger Shot Beer&nbsp;pub that is located between the 50th and 51st street.</p>\r\n<p>Because what\'s a better way to jumpstart a party, than to loosen yourself up with cheap snacks and \"energy drinks\", right?</p>\r\n<p>The pub\'s chilled and casual ambiance, accompanied by musical hits that ranged from Britney Spears\' \"Hit Me Baby One More Time\" to 50 cent\'s \"In Da Club\", also helped set our mood right from the get-go.</p>\r\n<p>After about a couple of hours, as the sun began to set, marking the time for dinner, we moved on to The Taco Shop&nbsp;in West Village for some margaritas and surprise, surprise, less than $4 tacos.</p>\r\n<p>That was where we showcased our love for Tacia, by getting her a cake and a chorus of the \"Happy Birthday\" song.</p>\r\n<p>The night ended on a bright note, and red faces for some of us.</p>\r\n<p>So again, we would like to wish Tacia a very happy birthday! And a massive thank you to Karisa and Talia for giving our members another memory to be cherished.</p>\r\n<p>Check out the photos to join in the celebration, and see all the fun we had. You can also follow us on social media for more!</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Celebrates Tacia\'s Birthday With A City Crawl (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Celebrates_Tacias/IMG_3610.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Celebrates Tacia\'s Birthday With A City Crawl (Image-3)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Celebrates Tacia\'s Birthday With A City Crawl (Image-4), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Celebrates_Tacias/20180224_171235_1519685742517.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Celebrates Tacia\'s Birthday With A City Crawl (Image-4)\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Celebrates Tacia\'s Birthday With A City Crawl (Image-5), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Celebrates_Tacias/20180224_193204_1519685281118.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Celebrates Tacia\'s Birthday With A City Crawl (Image-5)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Celebrates Tacia\'s Birthday With A City Crawl (Image-6), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Celebrates_Tacias/20180224_193246_1519685213740.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Celebrates Tacia\'s Birthday With A City Crawl (Image-6)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Celebrates Tacia\'s Birthday With A City Crawl (Image-7), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Celebrates_Tacias/20180224_193659_1519685138501.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Celebrates Tacia\'s Birthday With A City Crawl (Image-7)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Celebrates Tacia\'s Birthday With A City Crawl (Image-8), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Celebrates_Tacias/20180224_193835_1519685074735.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Celebrates Tacia\'s Birthday With A City Crawl (Image-8)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Celebrates Tacia\'s Birthday With A City Crawl (Image-9), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Celebrates_Tacias/20180224_194053_1519684933118.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Celebrates Tacia\'s Birthday With A City Crawl (Image-9)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Celebrates Tacia\'s Birthday With A City Crawl (Image-10), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Celebrates_Tacias/20180224_195800_1519684835339.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Celebrates Tacia\'s Birthday With A City Crawl (Image-10)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Celebrates Tacia\'s Birthday With A City Crawl (Image-11), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Celebrates_Tacias/IMG_3601.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Celebrates Tacia\'s Birthday With A City Crawl (Image-11)\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Celebrates Tacia\'s Birthday With A City Crawl (Image-12), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Celebrates_Tacias/IMG_3605.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Celebrates Tacia\'s Birthday With A City Crawl (Image-13), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Celebrates_Tacias/IMG_3607.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Celebrates Tacia\'s Birthday With A City Crawl (Image-13)\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Celebrates Tacia\'s Birthday With A City Crawl (Image-14), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Celebrates_Tacias/IMG_3609.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Celebrates Tacia\'s Birthday With A City Crawl (Image-14)\" /></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>Facebook:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/outpostclubNY/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Outpost Club</a></p>\r\n<p>Instagram:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://bit.ly/2yKHwih\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">@outpostcoliving</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '20180224_193659_1519685138501.jpg', 1, '2018-02-26 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(156, '7 Independent Brooklyn Bookstores Worth Visiting', 1, '7-independent-brooklyn-bookstores-worth-visiting', '', '7 Independent Brooklyn Bookstores Worth Visiting', '7 Independent Brooklyn Bookstores Worth Visiting', 'Brooklyn is home to dozens of independent bookstores that have us covered for everything from comics to books on the occult', '<p>Brooklyn is home to dozens of independent bookstores that have us covered for everything from comics to books on the occult. Here are seven Brooklyn bookstores that we love to visit.</p>', '<p>When the days get shorter and the nights chillier, not much sounds better than staying home and curling up with a good book. Fortunately for us, Brooklyn is home to dozens of independent bookstores that have us covered for everything from comics to books on the occult.</p>\r\n<h3>Here are seven Brooklyn bookstores that we love to visit:</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Books Are Magic</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>225 Smith St (Cobble Hill)</em></p>\r\n<p>Books Are Magic is an open, airy space with a huge selection. Little things like a poetry gumball machine and children&rsquo;s book nook will make you feel the love for all things literary.</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"7 Independent Brooklyn Bookstores Worth Visiting (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/books%20are%20magic_1.png\" alt=\"7 Independent Brooklyn Bookstores Worth Visiting (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>Credit:&nbsp;@booksaremagicbk/Instagram</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Better Read Than Dead</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>867 Broadway (Bushwick) </em></p>\r\n<p>Better Read than Dead is a tiny used book shop tucked into an alley off Broadway. It&rsquo;s built into an old shipping container that has been extended to the street to give shoopers more space, and is bursting with both classics and unique used titles you&rsquo;d be hard-pressed to find anywhere else.</p>\r\n<p><em>Near the Bushwick and <a href=\"../the-bed-stuy-house\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Bed-Stuy</a> houses.</em></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"7 Independent Brooklyn Bookstores Worth Visiting (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/better%20read%20than%20dead_1.png\" alt=\"7 Independent Brooklyn Bookstores Worth Visiting (Image-2)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p><em>Credit: @better_read_than_dead_bk/Instagram</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Molasses Books</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>770 Hart St. (Bushwick) </em></p>\r\n<p>The coolest thing about Molasses Books is the barter system: You can trade your old books for something from their shop, or even something from their beer and wine selection. It&rsquo;s a quiet shop with a decent amount of seating and free WiFi.</p>\r\n<p><em>Near the <a href=\"../the-bed-stuy-house\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Bed-Stuy House </a>and easily accessible from the Ridgewood House.</em></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"7 Independent Brooklyn Bookstores Worth Visiting (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/molasses_1.png\" alt=\"7 Independent Brooklyn Bookstores Worth Visiting (Image-3)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<em>Credit: @molassesbooks/Instagram</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Unnameable Books</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>600 Vanderbilt Ave (Prospect Heights) </em></p>\r\n<p>Unnameable Books may be simple on the outside, but it has a heart of gold. It can take a bit of a hunt to find what you&rsquo;re looking for, but reviewers have compared it to The Strand in terms of the breadth of its selection. It also buys back books from customers, so you can get cash or credit for more books.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img title=\"7 Independent Brooklyn Bookstores Worth Visiting (Image-4), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/unnameable_1.png\" alt=\"7 Independent Brooklyn Bookstores Worth Visiting (Image-4)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p><em>Credit: @unnameablebooks/Instagram</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>WORD Bookstore</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>126 Franklin St (Greenpoint)</em></p>\r\n<p>WORD is an airy space with a great selection of new releases and local publications. Head to the events space in the basement for author readings and other literary events.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"7 Independent Brooklyn Bookstores Worth Visiting (Image-5), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/word_1.png\" alt=\"7 Independent Brooklyn Bookstores Worth Visiting (Image-5)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p><em>Credit: @wordbookstores/Instagram</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>McNally Jackson</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>76 N 4th St, Unit G (Williamsburg)</em></p>\r\n<p>McNally Jackson&rsquo;s original SoHo location was so popular that they decided to open a second location in Williamsburg. Its minimalist design and an abundance of natural lighting make it the perfect place to browse to your heart&rsquo;s content.</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"7 Independent Brooklyn Bookstores Worth Visiting (Image-6), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/mcnallyjackson_1.png\" alt=\"7 Independent Brooklyn Bookstores Worth Visiting (Image-6)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p><em>Credit: @mcnallyjackson/Instagram</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Spoonbill &amp; Sugartown</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>218 Bedford Ave (Williamsburg)</em></p>\r\n<p><em>99 Montrose Ave (Bushwick)</em></p>\r\n<p>Spoonbill &amp; Sugartown now has two Brooklyn locations, and visiting each of them is a treat. The original Williamsburg location has been a destination for area book lovers since 1999. They have a decent used section, but what&rsquo;s really impressive is their indie book and magazine collection.</p>\r\n<p><em>Easily accessible via subway from the East Williamsburg and Ridgewood houses.&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"7 Independent Brooklyn Bookstores Worth Visiting (Image-7), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/spoonbill_1.png\" alt=\"7 Independent Brooklyn Bookstores Worth Visiting (Image-7)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p><em>Credit: @spoonbillbooks/Instagram</em></p>', 'StockSnap_FYEZGHNQVR.jpg', 1, '2018-11-01 05:00:00', NULL, 0, 0, 0),
(90, 'The Appeal of Living in Bushwick', 1, 'the-appeal-of-living-in-bushwick', '', 'The Appeal of Living in Bushwick | Outpost Club blog', 'The Appeal of Living in Bushwick', 'New Yorkers are starting to see and appreciate the charm of living in Bushwick. Read on for all information about living and apartments in Bushwick.', '<p>We asked our members about why they like Bushwick and there were some pretty great themes that stood out!</p>', '<h3><em>We asked our members about why they like Bushwick and there were some pretty great themes that stood out!</em></h3>\r\n<p>Bushwick&nbsp;has long ditched its old &ldquo;crime-laden&rdquo;, rough reputation. Last year it was ranked second on Property Shark&rsquo;s top 2017 &ldquo;<strong>Real Estate Pros Choose NYC&rsquo;s Hottest Neighborhoods&rdquo;</strong><a href=\"https://www.propertyshark.com/Real-Estate-Reports/2017/01/17/NYC-real-estate-market-predictions\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">.</a>&nbsp;It came on top of even neighborhoods such as the Lower and the Upper East Side that are traditionally known to be the more popular places to live.</p>\r\n<p>This is attributed largely to the rapid development of the area that has driven up its property market price - while still being in the affordable range - to invite in more of the middle-class group.</p>\r\n<p>The artsy vibe contributed by the various hip cafes and street arts that sprung up over the last few years have also pulled in the youth as well as the hipster community into the area.</p>\r\n<p>In short, along with a safer neighborhood, Bushwick also offers an attractive lifestyle that caters to all types of people. Hence why <a href=\"../\" target=\"_blank\">Outpost Club</a>&nbsp;has three of its houses&nbsp;located in this area.</p>\r\n<p>Read on for more reasons why Bushwick is the place to live, compiled from the input provided by Outpost\'s members&nbsp;themselves.</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"The Appeal of Living in Bushwick (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/Screen%20Shot%202019-03-08%20at%203.21.58%20PM.png\" alt=\"The Appeal of Living in Bushwick (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<h3>1. Diversity</h3>\r\n<div><br /><em><strong>\"Bushwick is one of the more diverse neighborhoods in Brooklyn. I have lived in four major US cities, and only Brooklyn offers the opportunity to meet people from all sorts of backgrounds.\",&nbsp;</strong></em>Simon Bogdanov, Outpost\'s Bushwick House member since October 2017.</div>\r\n<p>Bushwick has a truly diverse population that is visible even when you\'re simply walking down the street to a corner store five minutes away from your apartment. It is also reflected in the composition of our Bushwick&nbsp;and East Bushwick&rsquo;s Houses.</p>\r\n<p>The diversity makes for an interesting night out, where you can expect to meet and befriend different people with their own unique styles as well as cultural backgrounds.</p>\r\n<div><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"The Appeal of Living in Bushwick (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/The_Appeal_of_Living/UNADJUSTEDNONRAW_thumb_502b-1.jpg\" alt=\"The Appeal of Living in Bushwick (Image-2)\" /></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\">Oscar Cerrato</div>\r\n<h3>2. Street Arts</h3>\r\n<p><em><strong>\"Bushwick is unique for its urban style. It\'s very wild, in the sense that it\'s also edgy.\",&nbsp;</strong></em>Oscar Cerrato, Outpost\'s Bushwick House member since August 2017.</p>\r\n<p>Bushwick has a huge and impressive street art scene that gives the area a cool artistic feel.</p>\r\n<p>It is made even more exciting with organized murals coordinated by Bushwick-native Joe Ficalora, through his project coined as <strong>\"The Bushwick Collective\".</strong></p>\r\n<p>There are also plenty of gallery spaces you can visit to check out the neighborhood\'s booming art scene.</p>\r\n<p>And if you\'re a fan of street arts and photography, just take your camera out on a bright sunny day and you\'re all set for some Instagram-worthy photos!</p>\r\n<h3>3. Affordability</h3>\r\n<p><em><strong>\"NYC is expensive. There is only a handful of neighborhoods that are affordable, and Bushwick is one of them.\",</strong> </em>Simon Bogdanov, self-proclaimed \"broke\" UX designer.</p>\r\n<p>Bushwick has unparalleled options when it comes to affordable items.</p>\r\n<p>Just 10 minutes&rsquo; walk from Outpost\'s Bushwick House is the L Train Vintage&nbsp;shop that boasts of being \"the most affordable vintage clothing\" in New York City.</p>\r\n<p>And then there is the \"Deli and Grill\" store just at the corner of Jefferson Street, where our house is located. It has pretty much everything you need - from the standard cooking items, to complete meals like our members\' favorite: chicken over rice (it costs only $5!).</p>\r\n<p>If you\'re more of a pizza kind of person, several spots like <strong><a href=\"https://www.jimmyspizzeriamenu.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Jimmy\'s Pizza</a>&nbsp;</strong>offer a personal-sized pie at just $5.</p>\r\n<h3>4. Safety</h3>\r\n<div><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"The Appeal of Living in Bushwick (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/The_Appeal_of_Living/img-35.jpg\" alt=\"The Appeal of Living in Bushwick (Image-3)\" />Jacob Shapiro</div>\r\n<p><em><strong>\"There is this international reputation of Brooklyn being dangerous. But when members come they quickly realize that it\'s not so. I feel comfortable walking around Bushwick at any time of day or night. My female friends say the same.\",&nbsp;</strong></em>Jacob Shapiro, Outpost\'s <a href=\"../nyc-rooms-for-rent\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">New York</a> account manager.</p>\r\n<p>Bushwick was once known as an unsafe area. But this has changed over the last few years, with the rate of crimes reported decreasing significantly.</p>\r\n<p>In fact, Bushwick was noted to be much safer&nbsp;compared to other popular neighborhoods such as Williamsburg, Greenwich Village, and Midtown Manhattan.</p>\r\n<h3>5. Location</h3>\r\n<div><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"The Appeal of Living in Bushwick (Image-4), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/The_Appeal_of_Living/11010983_10203359178132955_3443272589415548904_n.jpg\" alt=\"The Appeal of Living in Bushwick (Image-4)\" /></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\">Ana Xavier</div>\r\n<p><em><strong>\"Bushwick\'s location is really good as it has four subway lines. And there are also a lot of places you can go to chill.\",&nbsp;</strong></em>Ana Xavier, Outpost\'s Bushwick House member since February 2018.</p>\r\n<p>Bushwick has four subway lines: the L, J, M, and Z. On top of that, there are also three bus lines that will take you to major parts of the city.</p>\r\n<p>This means transportation will never be on the list of things you&rsquo;d have to worry about when living here. You&rsquo;ll never run out of options to pick from, to ensure you get to your destination within reasonable time.</p>\r\n<p>The neighborhood also has a variety of bars, eateries, and coffee shops for you to explore. A favorite among our members is <strong>Father Knows Best,</strong> where you can get a pint of beer for as low as $5.</p>\r\n<p>If you\'re a vegetarian (and vegan),&nbsp;Routine&nbsp;is the perfect place for you. It is located just a short walk from the Wilson Avenue stop on the L train, and has an interior that would make for some great photos!</p>\r\n<p>Be sure to experience all these for yourself by making a visit to Bushwick an item on your weekend to-do-list. You can also check out our social media pages to get a glimpse of what the neighborhood has to offer!</p>\r\n<p>The allure of Bushwick is indescribable, and once you visit the neighborhood, you\'ll see why it\'s great. To appreciate the beauty of Bushwick you need to live there. Outpost has six community-focused <a href=\"../new-york\" target=\"_blank\">houses</a> to choose from that make life in Bushwick even better. Explore our community homes and imagine life in this burgeoning area of ​​Brooklyn.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Facebook:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/outpostclubNY/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Outpost Club</a></p>\r\n<p>Instagram:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://bit.ly/2yKHwih\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">@outpostcoliving</a></p>', 'Screen Shot 2019-03-08 at 3.21.58 PM.png', 1, '2018-02-27 06:00:00', '2022-11-01 07:04:03', 0, 0, 0),
(245, '#MemberMonday: Claire Watt', 1, 'membermonday-claire-watt', '', '#MemberMonday: Claire Watt', '#MemberMonday: Claire Watt', 'This week’s #MemberMonday feature is Claire Watt, a member of the East Bushwick House and a writer who loves getting lost in Brooklyn. ', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This week&rsquo;s </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">#MemberMonday</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> feature is Claire Watt, a member of the East Bushwick House and a writer who loves getting lost in Brooklyn. </span></p>', '<p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This week&rsquo;s </span><strong>#MemberMonday</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> feature is Claire Watt, a member of the East Bushwick House and&nbsp;a writer who loves getting lost in Brooklyn. </span></em></p>\r\n<h3><strong>Tell us a bit about yourself.</strong></h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">I&rsquo;m from England and have always wanted to live in New York City, so when I finished my Master&rsquo;s in Creative Writing I decided there was no time like the present to visit and see what it\'s really like. I enjoy writing poetry and fiction and I think New York is the perfect place for this: There are so many other writers and events like workshops and spoken-word evenings going on every day.</span></p>\r\n<h3><strong><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"#MemberMonday: Claire Watt (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/39520168_10215500766445648_3075130007647944704_n.jpg\" alt=\"#MemberMonday: Claire Watt (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" />What\'s your favorite Outpost memory? </strong></h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">I&rsquo;m new to Outpost, but I&rsquo;ve been to the Halloween and New Year&rsquo;s Eve parties. What I love is the sense of community and how welcoming everyone is at events like these. </span></p>\r\n<h3><strong>What&rsquo;s your favorite part of New York?</strong></h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">My two favorite areas so far are Bushwick/East Williamsburg (the border) and the area around Bowery in Manhattan. I love going to the writers workshops at </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ange Noir Cafe</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> in East Williamsburg and </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Molasses Books</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> in Bushwick. In Manhattan, the open mic nights at </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Bowery Poetry</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> are really fun and I just generally enjoy walking around the area. I still haven&rsquo;t been to DUMBO, which is the next thing on my list.</span></p>\r\n<h3><strong>What are you working on now?</strong></h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">I&rsquo;m working on a novel that is actually partly set in New York, so I&rsquo;m trying to immerse myself in the landscape of the city. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">I&rsquo;m also sending my poems off for publication.</span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>', '39520168_10215500766445648_3075130007647944704_n.jpg', 0, '2019-03-11 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(91, 'The Bushwick House and East Bushwick House Neighborhood Guide', 1, 'bushwick-and-east-bushwick-house-neighborhood-guide', '', 'The Bushwick House and East Bushwick House Neighborhood Guide', 'The Bushwick House and East Bushwick House Neighborhood Guide', 'The Bushwick House and East Bushwick House Neighborhood Guide', '<p>The Bushwick House and East Bushwick house neighborhood guide if you&rsquo;re new to the area, we understand how tough that can be. We have members coming from all over the world and many of them at the start didn&rsquo;t know much about America, let alone Bushwick! let.</p>', '<h3><em>If you&rsquo;re new to the area, we understand how tough that can be. We have members coming from all over the world and many of them at the start didn&rsquo;t know much about America, let alone Bushwick! Let us help you with some of the basics, so you can start exploring the neighborhood almost immediately. This guide applies to both the Bushwick and East Bushwick Houses, which are located just about 7 minutes away from each other.</em></h3>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h2><strong>Subway/Travel</strong></h2>\r\n<p><strong>It\'s really up to you, but here are the main ways to get to Manhattan!</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>The J, M, Z train &ndash; Halsey Street</h3>\r\n<p>The J, M and Z lines stop at Halsey Street, just 10 minutes&rsquo; walk from the Bushwick House, and 15 minutes from the East Bushwick House. The M train, however, will no longer stop here by April 2018.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the Bushwick House - walk: 11 minutes; bike: 7 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Bushwick House - bus: 10 minutes; walk: 16 minutes; bike: 5 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>The L train &ndash; Wilson Avenue</h3>\r\n<p>There is also the Wilson Avenue stop on the L train that is about 10- minute walk from the Bushwick House, and 5 minutes from the East Bushwick House.</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the Bushwick House -&nbsp;walk: 12 minutes; bike: 4 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Bushwick House - walk: 7 minutes; bike: 3 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>The L train &ndash; Halsey St</h3>\r\n<p>The Halsey Street stop on the L train is roughly the same distance: 15 minutes&rsquo; walk from the Bushwick House and 6 minutes from the East Bushwick House.</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the Bushwick House - bus: 12 minutes; walk: 15 minutes; bike: 4 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Bushwick House - walk: 6 minutes; bike: 3 minutes</em></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h2><strong>Gyms</strong></h2>\r\n<p><strong>Having a tough time finding your new gym? here are some options below:</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Blink Fitness Gates - 1002 Gates Ave, Brooklyn, NY</h3>\r\n<p>Blink Fitness\' membership begins at as low as $15 a month. But with it comes high-quality equipment, great music to set you in a workout mood, and plenty of room for a breather in between.</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the Bushwick House &nbsp; &nbsp;- bus: 15 minutes; walk: 16 minutes; bike: 6 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Bushwick House &nbsp; &nbsp;- bus: 20 minutes; train: 22 minutes; walk: 25 minutes; bike: 8 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>World Gym of Ridgewood - 1661 Weirfield St, Ridgewood, NY</h3>\r\n<p>World Gym promises its members the best in all aspects. Modern equipment? Check. An atmosphere that sends your body and mind into pre-workout excitement? Check. Experts that can help you achieve your fitness goal? Check.</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the Bushwick House - Bus: 10 minutes; walk: 13 minutes; bike: 4 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Bushwick House - Bus: 8 minutes; walk: 13 minutes; bike: 5 min</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Planet Fitness - 329 Wyckoff Ave, Ridgewood, NY</h3>\r\n<p>You can become a member of Planet Fitness at just $10 a month. It also comes with free fitness training and free WiFi access!</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the Bushwick House - Bus: 14 minutes; walk: 14 minutes; bike: 4 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Bushwick House - Train: 10 minutes; bus: 12 minutes; walk: 17 minutes; bike: 6 minutes</em></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h2><strong>Groceries</strong></h2>\r\n<p><strong>Looking to grab quick groceries? There are plenty of options you can pick from, but we have listed three that suit your every need.</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"The Bushwick House and East Bushwick House Neighborhood Guide (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/The_Bushwick_House/20180306_152327_1520565489547.jpg\" alt=\"The Bushwick House and East Bushwick House Neighborhood Guide (Image-1)\" /></p>\r\n<h3>Deli and Grill - 472 Wilson Ave, Brooklyn, NY</h3>\r\n<p>Deli &amp; Grill has every basic household needs. The reason it&rsquo;s one of our members&rsquo; top pick, however, is the fact that it also offers a wide variety of freshly prepared meals. From breakfast menu of sandwiches to lunch and dinner favorites of chicken, beef, and lamb over rice, the store has it all. The best part is its affordable price.</p>\r\n<p>The store is located just a short 1-minute walk from the Bushwick House, and 8 minutes from the East Bushwick House.</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the Bushwick House - walk: 1 minute</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Bushwick House &nbsp; &nbsp;- walk: 8 minutes; bike: 2 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Fresh Food Mart &amp; Deli - 711 Knickerbocker Ave, Brooklyn, NY</h3>\r\n<p>If you&rsquo;re looking for fresh produce but are not in the mood to go grocery shopping, Fresh Food Mart &amp; Deli is the perfect place for you.</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the Bushwick House - walk: 4 minutes; bike: 1 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Bushwick House - walk: 7 minutes; bike: 3 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Food Bazaar - 454 Wyckoff Ave, Brooklyn, NY</h3>\r\n<p>The Wyckoff Food Bazaar is a great spot for fresh produce. What makes it stands out from other grocery stores around the area, however, is the array of international products available. If you&rsquo;re missing food from &ldquo;back home&rdquo;, you can whip them up yourself with the items available here. &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the Bushwick House - train: 12 minutes; bus: 12 minutes; walk: 10 minutes; bike: 4 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Bushwick House - train: 13 minutes; bus: 11 minutes; walk: 13 minutes; bike: 5 minutes</em></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h2><strong>Parks</strong></h2>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Do you like people watching on a saturday afternoon? Here\'s the spot.</strong></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"The Bushwick House and East Bushwick House Neighborhood Guide (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/The_Bushwick_House/20180306_161532_1520566492850-1.jpg\" alt=\"The Bushwick House and East Bushwick House Neighborhood Guide (Image-2)\" /></p>\r\n<h3>Irving Square Park</h3>\r\n<p>Stepping out for fresh air can do wonders for your day. Especially when the weather is nice. So if you find yourself looking for a spot to just relax and observe, head on to the Irving Square Park!</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the Bushwick House - walk: 5 minutes; bike: 2 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Bushwick House - walk: 5 minutes; bike: &nbsp;2 minutes</em></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h2><strong>Food</strong></h2>\r\n<p><strong>The neighborhood offers an unlimited variety of eateries at affordable prices. Here are a few that we recommend, based on the input provided by our former and current members.</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Fazio&rsquo;s Pizza - 709 Knickerbocker Avenue, Brooklyn, NY</h3>\r\n<p>Fazio&rsquo;s brought a taste of authentic Sicilian and Neopolitan pizza into Bushwick, at a competitive price.</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the Bushwick House - walk: 4 minutes; bike: 1 minute</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Bushwick House - walk: 7 minutes; bike: 3 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"The Bushwick House and East Bushwick House Neighborhood Guide (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/The_Bushwick_House/20180306_161441_1520566350065.jpg\" alt=\"The Bushwick House and East Bushwick House Neighborhood Guide (Image-3)\" /></p>\r\n<h3>Jimmy&rsquo;s Pizza - 561 Wilson Ave, Brooklyn, NY</h3>\r\n<p>We&rsquo;ve thrown countless of pizza parties at our two Bushwick-based houses. And our go-to place for this? It&rsquo;s Jimmy&rsquo;s Pizza.</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the Bushwick House - walk: 5 minutes; bike: 2 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Bushwick House - walk: 4 minutes; bike: 1 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3>Golden Thai - 469 Irving Ave, Brooklyn, NY</h3>\r\n<p><img title=\"The Bushwick House and East Bushwick House Neighborhood Guide (Image-4), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/The_Bushwick_House/img-44.jpg\" alt=\"The Bushwick House and East Bushwick House Neighborhood Guide (Image-4)\" /></p>\r\n<p>This restaurant will make you feel like you&rsquo;re in Thailand, both for its d&eacute;cor and its authentic-flavored food. Check out its weekdays&rsquo; lunch special, where you can get a complete set of meal at just $8.95. It&rsquo;s also a great spot to go on a date.</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the Bushwick House - walk: 7 minutes; bike: 2 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Bushwick House - walk: 8 minutes; bike: 3 minutes</em></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h2><strong>Coffee shops</strong></h2>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Looking for a quick pick-me-up? Or just a place to work? Take a look at these hot spots.</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"The Bushwick House and East Bushwick House Neighborhood Guide (Image-5), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/The_Bushwick_House/20180301_134900_1519931136308.jpg\" alt=\"The Bushwick House and East Bushwick House Neighborhood Guide (Image-5)\" /></p>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3>Father Knows Best - 611A Wilson Ave, Brooklyn, NY</h3>\r\n<p>Yes, Father Knows Best is also a great place for coffee. Take our word for it, its hot chocolate is to die for.</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the Bushwick House - bus: 4 minutes; walk: 8 minutes; bike: 3 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Bushwick House - walk: 2 minutes; bike: 1 minute</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"The Bushwick House and East Bushwick House Neighborhood Guide (Image-6), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/The_Bushwick_House/20180306_152955_1520566112906.jpg\" alt=\"The Bushwick House and East Bushwick House Neighborhood Guide (Image-6)\" /></p>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Angela&rsquo;s Bakery - 717 Knickerbocker Ave, Brooklyn, NY</h3>\r\n<p>The bakery has designs that suit all occasions. Even the pastries available for sit-in customers were beautifully decorated, with great flavors to match. So head here if you&rsquo;re looking for a nice spot to just sip on that warm cup of tea while treating your taste buds with its famous Dominican pastries.</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the Bushwick House - walk: 4 minutes; bike: 2 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Bushwick House - walk: 6 minutes; bike: 2 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h1><strong>Nightlife</strong></h1>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Want to have a fun night out on the town? Check out these place not too far from home!</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"The Bushwick House and East Bushwick House Neighborhood Guide (Image-7), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/The_Bushwick_House/img-16.jpg\" alt=\"The Bushwick House and East Bushwick House Neighborhood Guide (Image-7)\" /></p>\r\n<h3>Father Knows Best - 611A Wilson Ave, Brooklyn, NY</h3>\r\n<p>Father Knows Best is a great spot to hang out any night of the week. Besides great music and affordable drinks, it also hosts different events every night, like jazz and trivia nights.</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the Bushwick House - bus: 4 minutes; walk: 8 minutes; bike: 3 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Bushwick House - walk: 2 minutes; bike: 1 minute</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div><img title=\"The Bushwick House and East Bushwick House Neighborhood Guide (Image-8), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/The_Bushwick_House/nowadays.jpg\" alt=\"The Bushwick House and East Bushwick House Neighborhood Guide (Image-8)\" /> Mister Sunday\'s at Nowadays</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Nowadays - 56-06 Cooper Ave, Ridgewood, NY</h3>\r\n<p>From the outside, the bar/restaurant looks like an abandoned building. The internal exterior, however, is a different story. The space is massive, providing plenty of room for dancing. When the weather is nice, the parties are held in the bar&rsquo;s outdoor space.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div><img title=\"The Bushwick House and East Bushwick House Neighborhood Guide (Image-9), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/The_Bushwick_House/img-6.jpg\" alt=\"The Bushwick House and East Bushwick House Neighborhood Guide (Image-9)\" /> Mister Saturday\'s at Nowadays</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the Bushwick House - bus: 12 minutes; walk: 16 minutes; bike: 5 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Bushwick House - walk: 7 minutes; bike: 3 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"The Bushwick House and East Bushwick House Neighborhood Guide (Image-10), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/The_Bushwick_House/20180306_155456_1520566253309.jpg\" alt=\"The Bushwick House and East Bushwick House Neighborhood Guide (Image-10)\" /></p>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3>The Deep End - 1080 Wyckoff Ave, Ridgewood, NY</h3>\r\n<p>The Deep End has everything you could possibly need for a great night out. From food like chicken wings, burgers, and tacos, to reasonably priced drinks, it has it all. The bar also hosts Karaoke nights and different events every week.</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the ushwick House - bus: 11 minutes; walk: 16 minutes; bike: 5 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the ast Bushwick House - walk: 7 minutes; bike: 4 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h2><strong>Post Offices</strong></h2>\r\n<p><strong>Want to send some stuff to friends or family? Check out your three main options in walking distance.&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>United States Postal Service - 1369 Broadway, Brooklyn, NY</h3>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the Bushwick House - bus: 14 minutes; walk: 15 minutes; bike &ndash; 5 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Bushwick House - Train: 21 minutes; bus: 19 minutes; walk: 24 minutes; bike: 7 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>United States Postal Service - 805 MacDonough St, Brooklyn, NY</h3>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the Bushwick House - Bus: 13 minutes; walk: 16 minutes; bike: 5 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Bushwick House - Bus: 6 minutes; walk: 13 minutes; bike: 4 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"The Bushwick House and East Bushwick House Neighborhood Guide (Image-11), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/The_Bushwick_House/20180306_160920_1520565986651.jpg\" alt=\"The Bushwick House and East Bushwick House Neighborhood Guide (Image-11)\" /></p>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3>Bushwick Post -&nbsp;620 Wilson Ave, Brooklyn, NY</h3>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the Bushwick House - walk: 9 minutes; bike: 3 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Bushwick House - walk: 4 minutes; bike: 1 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><em><strong>THAT\'S ALL FOR NOW! WE CONSIDER THIS A LIVING DOCUMENT, SO IF YOU HAVE ANY SUGGESTION OF PLACES TO ADD, OR TIPS FOR THE PLACES ALREADY ON THE LIST, LET US KNOW! YOU CAN COMMENT BELOW OR EMAIL US AT INFO@OUTPOST-CLUB.COM </strong></em></h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '20180306_152327_1520565489547.jpg', 1, '2018-03-10 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0);
