(224, '#MemberMonday: Mika Camps', 1, 'membermonday-mika-camps', '', '#MemberMonday: Mika Camps', '#MemberMonday: Mika Camps', 'For this week’s #MemberMonday, we’re introducing Mika Camps, a member at our East Bushwick House. Read on to learn what Mika’s been working on at the UN and where he’s headed next.', '<p>For this week&rsquo;s #MemberMonday, we&rsquo;re introducing Mika Camps, a member at our East Bushwick House. Read on to learn what Mika&rsquo;s been working on at the UN and where he&rsquo;s headed next.</p>', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">For this week&rsquo;s </span><strong><a href=\"../blog_category/membermonday\">#MemberMonday</a></strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, we&rsquo;re introducing Mika Camps, a member at our </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">East Bushwick House</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. Read on to learn what Mika&rsquo;s been working on at the UN and where he&rsquo;s headed next.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><img title=\"#MemberMonday: Mika Camps (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost.jpg\" alt=\"#MemberMonday: Mika Camps (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Tell us a bit about yourself.</h3>\r\n<p>I&rsquo;m 23 and I&rsquo;m from Belgium, where I grew up in both the Dutch- and French-speaking part of the country. I graduated from law school last summer and arrived in New York in early September for an internship at the UN. I\'ve been living here at Outpost ever since.</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">When I&rsquo;m not studying or working, I love watching movies, going to concerts and playing soccer. I want to add &ldquo;reading books&rdquo; but I&rsquo;ve carried the same two books to about 11 countries by now and it\'s just not happening.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><br /></span></p>\r\n<h3>What&rsquo;s your favorite Outpost memory?</h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">My favorite Outpost memory is also my first one: the hiking trip to Bear Mountain. The weather was great, the hike and views were amazing, we barbecued by the water and I got to meet a bunch of really cool people.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><br /></span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><br /></span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Other than that, Thanksgiving in our house was definitely a highlight. When you go to the liquor store and come back with a Christmas tree, you know it\'s gonna be a good day.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><br /></span></p>\r\n<h3>Do you have a favorite place in Brooklyn?</h3>\r\n<p>Is it lame to say DUMBO? Probably, but it&rsquo;s amazing.</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In fairness, Brooklyn has so many great spots it&rsquo;s hard to choose. I really love downtown Brooklyn and Greenpoint; they have a very different but equally great vibe.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><br /></span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><br /></span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">To actually answer the question: the William Vale hotel in Williamsburg. It&rsquo;s an awesomely designed building and hands down the best rooftop in Brooklyn (make that New York). Honorable mention: Sunset Park.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><br /></span></p>\r\n<h3>What are you currently working on? What are you doing next?</h3>\r\n<p>I&rsquo;m currently wrapping up my internship at the UN&rsquo;s Department of Peacekeeping Operations. I specifically work on the disarmament of combatants and their reintegration into society after civil wars and armed conflicts. Pretty cool stuff.</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">What I&rsquo;m doing next: two months of traveling through South America. After that, your guess is as good as mine, but it will probably be in a place I&rsquo;ve never been before.</span></p>', 'Outpost.jpg', 1, '2019-01-07 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(92, 'Member Profile Osée Koss', 1, 'member-profile-ose-koss', 'blog-outpost-club/2018/3/19/member-profile-ose-koss', 'Member Profile Osée Koss', 'Member Profile Osée Koss', 'Member Profile: Osée Koss', '<p>Welcome to our members\' profile series, where we share the stories of why they moved to NYC, and also what they like about their time here. This week we&rsquo;re introducing you to Os&eacute;e who stayed with.</p>', '<p><em>Welcome to our members\' profile series, where we share the stories of why they moved to NYC, and also what they like about their time here. This week we&rsquo;re introducing you to Os&eacute;e who stayed with us 3 times in 3 years! We hope you enjoy this article.&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Tell us a little about yourself</strong></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Member Profile Os&eacute;e Koss (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Member_Profile/20180211_011011.jpg\" alt=\"Member Profile Os&eacute;e Koss (Image-1)\" /></p>\r\n<p>My name is Os&eacute;e Koss! I am French, from the city of Lyon in France. I\'m a freelance graphic designer. I also manage my own YouTube channel with a website about my passion for the Asian culture.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What brought you to NYC?</strong></p>\r\n<p>This is my third time in New York City! Every year I feel the need to return. I like to lose myself in the dynamism of the city, to seek inspiration, to meet new people with stories different from mine. For me New York City is the crossroads of the world.</p>\r\n<p>What has been your best experience here?</p>\r\n<p>This is a difficult question. Of course, the first time! I mean the first time of all things is extraordinary, but a first time in New York City is magic. Even the first burger!</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Member Profile Os&eacute;e Koss (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Member_Profile/img-28.jpg\" alt=\"Member Profile Os&eacute;e Koss (Image-2)\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>What do you think of coliving?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Coliving does not fit everyone! I think people should really understand the meaning of the word. The willingness to share an important living space as a home should be a choice, and not a constraint. Everyone does not have the same lifestyle habits!&nbsp;Without sharing, without respect for others, coliving is impossible!</p>\r\n<p><strong>What has been your best experience in the time you have stayed with Outpost?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Every time we laugh together, it\'s a <a href=\"../blog/outpost-club-celebrates-oses-30th-birthday-bash\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">real moment of happiness</a>! Whenever I learn something from another person is amazing! Each experience with Outpost is unique and appreciable!</p>\r\n<p>One day I was not in a good mood and I was annoyed to have to wait to use the kitchen. I think my roommate noticed it because he apologized for making me wait, and he went to cook upstairs instead! (I forgot that in the Ridgewood House there are three kitchens). I felt really stupid, so I went back to him to apologize too, and we ended up cooking together! A lot of fun and we laughed at the situation</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Member Profile Os&eacute;e Koss (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Member_Profile/27983448_10204243500765715_302302136131598426_o.jpg\" alt=\"Member Profile Os&eacute;e Koss (Image-3)\" /></p>', '20180211_011011.jpg', 1, '2018-03-18 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(93, 'Outpost Enjoys The Sun With A BBQ Party', 1, 'outpost-enjoys-the-sun-with-a-bbq-party', '', 'Outpost Enjoys The Sun With A BBQ Party', 'Outpost Enjoys The Sun With A BBQ Party', 'Outpost Enjoys The Sun With A BBQ Party', '<p>March has been quite a moody month, with grey skies and wet days. So when you get the rare days of sunshine, how do you celebrate it?</p>', '<p>March has been quite a moody month, with grey skies and wet days. So when you get the rare days of sunshine, how do you celebrate it?</p>\r\n<p>By throwing a BBQ party in our backyard, of course! At least that\'s what we, at <a href=\"../\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Outpost Club</a>, did.</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Enjoys The Sun With A BBQ Party (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Enjoys_The_Sun/20180309_192542_1520784974146.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Enjoys The Sun With A BBQ Party (Image-1)\" /></p>\r\n<p>A couple of weeks ago, our Bushwick House&nbsp;leader Simon Bogdanov&nbsp;noticed that the Saturday of March 10th would be a break from what had been a long and cold week.</p>\r\n<p>With the help of all Bushwick House members, they planned the BBQ party that saw more than 20 of our present and former members&nbsp;in attendance.</p>\r\n<p>It started at 3pm and while we had expected the party to end by the time the sun sets, it ended up lasting all the way past midnight!</p>\r\n<p>Simon\'s \"Russian sweet tea\" might have played a role in that, although hey, we aren\'t complaining. While none of our members got the tan line they expected, they did leave with a great story to tell.</p>\r\n<p>Just look at the pictures we took of them! If the kind of fun they had, and have been having fits the image you have when planning that trip or move to NYC, then <a href=\"../join-us\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">join</a>&nbsp;us!</p>\r\n<p>Facebook:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/outpostclubNY/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Outpost Club</a></p>\r\n<p>Instagram: <a href=\"https://bit.ly/2yKHwih\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">@outpostcoliving</a>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Enjoys The Sun With A BBQ Party (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Enjoys_The_Sun/20180309_191947_1520784806291.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Enjoys The Sun With A BBQ Party (Image-2)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Enjoys The Sun With A BBQ Party (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Enjoys_The_Sun/20180309_192542_1520784974146.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Enjoys The Sun With A BBQ Party (Image-3)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Enjoys The Sun With A BBQ Party (Image-4), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Enjoys_The_Sun/20180310_165502_1520794073103-1.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Enjoys The Sun With A BBQ Party (Image-4)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Enjoys The Sun With A BBQ Party (Image-5), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Enjoys_The_Sun/20180310_165801_1520794164887-1.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Enjoys The Sun With A BBQ Party (Image-5)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Enjoys The Sun With A BBQ Party (Image-6), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Enjoys_The_Sun/20180310_170735_1520818220951-1.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Enjoys The Sun With A BBQ Party (Image-6)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Enjoys The Sun With A BBQ Party (Image-7), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Enjoys_The_Sun/20180310_170745_1520818350608-2.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Enjoys The Sun With A BBQ Party (Image-7)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Enjoys The Sun With A BBQ Party (Image-8), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Enjoys_The_Sun/20180310_175119_1520824823127%2B(1).jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Enjoys The Sun With A BBQ Party (Image-8)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Enjoys The Sun With A BBQ Party (Image-9), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Enjoys_The_Sun/20180310_175119_1520824823127.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Enjoys The Sun With A BBQ Party (Image-9)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Enjoys The Sun With A BBQ Party (Image-10), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Enjoys_The_Sun/20180310_175135_1520824716013.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Enjoys The Sun With A BBQ Party (Image-10)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Enjoys The Sun With A BBQ Party (Image-11), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Enjoys_The_Sun/20180310_184917_1520825219090.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Enjoys The Sun With A BBQ Party (Image-11)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Enjoys The Sun With A BBQ Party (Image-12), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Enjoys_The_Sun/20180310_185016_1520824957231.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Enjoys The Sun With A BBQ Party (Image-12)\" /></p>\r\n</div>', '20180309_192542_1520784974146.jpg', 1, '2018-03-18 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(94, 'Ridgewood Neighborhood Guide', 1, 'ridgewood-neighborhood-guide', '', 'Ridgewood Neighborhood Guide', 'Ridgewood Neighborhood Guide', 'Ridgewood Neighborhood Guide', '<p>Ridgewood neighborhood guide if you&rsquo;re new to the area, we understand how tough that can be. We have members coming from all over the world and many of them at the start didn&rsquo;t know much about america, let alone the mixed.</p>', '<h3><em>If you&rsquo;re new to the area, we understand how tough that can be. We have members coming from all over the world and many of them at the start didn&rsquo;t know much about America, let alone the mixed neighborhood of Ridgewood, Queens! Let us help you with some of the basics, so you can start exploring the neighborhood almost immediately.</em></h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><strong>Subway/Travel</strong></h2>\r\n<p><strong>It\'s really up to you, but here are the main ways to get to Manhattan!</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>The M train - Forest Ave</h3>\r\n<p>The M train is located just a minute&rsquo;s walk from the house. Now, how convenient is that? To get there, you just have to make a left when you exit the house. You can&rsquo;t miss it!</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the Ridgewood House - walk: 1 minute</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>The L train &ndash; Myrtle-Wyckoff Avenue</h3>\r\n<p>The L train&rsquo;s Myrtle-Wyckoff Avenue is 12-minute&rsquo;s walk from the house. Here&rsquo;s a tip: On weekdays, you can take the M train here.</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the Ridgewood House - walk: 12 minutes; bike: 4 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><strong>Gym</strong></h2>\r\n<p><strong>Having a tough time finding your new gym? here are some options below:</strong></p>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3>Ridgewood Yoga Studio - 16-23 Hancock St, Ridgewood</h3>\r\n<p>If you&rsquo;re looking for an affordable and accessible yoga studio, this is the spot! They even offer a special promo for new students, where you can sign up for 3 classes at just $25.</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the Ridgewood House - &nbsp;bus: 9 minutes; walk: 11 minutes; bike: 5 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>World Gym of Ridgewood - 1661 Weirfield St, Ridgewood, NY</h3>\r\n<p>World Gym offers serious, no-nonsense workout. We didn&rsquo;t say it, they did. To ensure this, the gym provides its members with modern and high-quality equipment.</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the Ridgewood House - Bus: 9 minutes; walk: 11 minutes; bike: 3 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Planet Fitness - 329 Wyckoff Ave, Ridgewood, NY 11385</h3>\r\n<p>Planet Fitness promises a judgment-free zone for its members, by providing a comfortable, safe and energetic environment. It is also affordable, with membership prices starting at just $10 a month!</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the Ridgewood House - Train: 6 minutes; walk: 12 minutes; bike: 4 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><strong>Groceries</strong></h2>\r\n<p><strong>Looking to grab quick groceries? There are plenty of options you can pick from, but we have narrowed them down to four that suit your every need.</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Ridgewood Neighborhood Guide (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Ridgewood_Neighborhood/img-48.jpg\" alt=\"Ridgewood Neighborhood Guide (Image-1)\" /></p>\r\n<h3>Hetman Fine Foods and Deli - 65-66 Forest Avenue, Ridgewood</h3>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the Ridgewood House - walk: 3 minutes, bike: 2 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Ridgewood Neighborhood Guide (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Ridgewood_Neighborhood/img-9.jpg\" alt=\"Ridgewood Neighborhood Guide (Image-2)\" /></p>\r\n<h3>7 Star Deli &amp; Tobacco - Ridgewood, NY</h3>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the Ridgewood House - walk: 5 minutes; bike: 1 minute</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Rony&rsquo;s Deli &amp; Grill &nbsp;- 792 Onderdonk Ave, Ridgewood</h3>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the Ridgewood House - walk: 3 minutes; bike: 1 minute</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Food Bazaar Supermarket - 454 Wyckoff Ave, Brooklyn, NY</h3>\r\n<p>The Wyckoff Food Bazaar is a great spot for fresh produce. What makes it stands out from other grocery stores around the area, however, is the array of international products available. If you&rsquo;re missing food from &ldquo;back home&rdquo;, you can whip them up yourself with the items available here. &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the Ridgewood House - train: 8 minutes; bus: 9 minutes; walk: 12 minutes; bike: 4 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Vitelio\'s Marketplace -&nbsp;1883 Madison St, Ridgewood, NY 11385</h3>\r\n<p>Vitelio\'s is the closest super market to the Ridgewood house and has a decent selection of items. The prices are a bit high, but the proximity to the house makes up for it if you\'re looking to make a quick meal.</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the Ridgewood House -&nbsp;walk: 3 minutes; bike: 1 minute</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><strong>Parks</strong></h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Ridgewood Neighborhood Guide (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Ridgewood_Neighborhood/20180317_194835_1521338589928.jpg\" alt=\"Ridgewood Neighborhood Guide (Image-3)\" /></p>\r\n<h3>Rosemary&rsquo;s Park</h3>\r\n<p>Take a break from the indoors by going for a walk at Rosemary&rsquo;s Playground. It&rsquo;s also a good spot for sporting activities. So why don&rsquo;t plan for a friendly basketball or soccer match between your housemates?</p>\r\n<p>Distance from the Ridgewood House - walk: 3 minutes; bike: 1 minute</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><strong>Food</strong></h2>\r\n<p><strong>The neighborhood offers an unlimited variety of eateries at affordable prices. Here are a few that we recommend, based on the input provided by our former and current members.</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Super Pollo - 865 Woodward Ave, Ridgewood, NY 11385</h3>\r\n<p><img title=\"Ridgewood Neighborhood Guide (Image-4), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Ridgewood_Neighborhood/20180317_195946_1521336542188.jpg\" alt=\"Ridgewood Neighborhood Guide (Image-4)\" /></p>\r\n<p>Super Pollo is known for its outstanding Mexican cuisine that are prepared with only the highest quality of fresh ingredients. It\'s also the perfect place for a date, with fairy lights surrounding the restaurant.</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the Ridgewood House - walk: 3 minutes; bike: 3 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Rama Thai - 881 Woodward Ave, Ridgewood, NY 11385</h3>\r\n<p>5 steamed dumplings, $4.99. Fried Calamari, $5.99. Thai\'s signature dish - the sweet and sour soup called Tom Yum, $4.99. Authentic Thai Food = priceless. Need we say more about why this restaurant made to our recommendation list?</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the Ridgewood House - walk: 3 minutes; bike: 3 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Ridgewood Neighborhood Guide (Image-5), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Ridgewood_Neighborhood/img-18.jpg\" alt=\"Ridgewood Neighborhood Guide (Image-5)\" /></p>\r\n<h3>Bosna Express- 791 Fairview Ave, Ridgewood, NY 11385</h3>\r\n<p>This neighborhood joint looks simple from the outside. But it offers tasty and authentic Balkan delicacies that you have to try out!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the Ridgewood House - walk: 1 minute; bike: 1 minute</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Garlic to Chicken- 6692 Forest Ave, Ridgewood, NY 11385</h3>\r\n<p>Fans of K-pop and all things Korean, this is a must-visit spot for you guys. Try out their Korean style fried chicken. We promise you won\'t regret it.</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the Ridgewood House - walk: 1 minute; bike: 1 minute</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Madison Pizza - 775 Woodward Ave, Ridgewood, NY 11385</h3>\r\n<p>Good news: their\'s great pizza right around the corner! Madison Pizza is rightacross the street from the Rosemary&rsquo;s Park, and thier plain slice of pizza is great! Also try their pepperoni pinwheels :)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><strong>Coffee shops</strong></h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Norma&rsquo;s Corner - 59-02 Catalpa Ave, Ridgewood, NY 11385</h3>\r\n<p>If you&rsquo;ve ever wanted to travel to Europe but never had a chance to do so, spend a morning on a sunny weekend having breakfast here. It&rsquo;ll take you away from Brooklyn, into a small French town.</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the Ridgewood House - walk: 4 minutes; bike: 3 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Topos Bookstore Cafe - 788 Woodward Ave, Ridgewood, NY 11385</h3>\r\n<p><img title=\"Ridgewood Neighborhood Guide (Image-6), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Ridgewood_Neighborhood/20180317_192059_1521337115086.jpg\" alt=\"Ridgewood Neighborhood Guide (Image-6)\" /></p>\r\n<p>What&rsquo;s better than a cozy spot where you can read and enjoy a cup of coffee? Topos&hellip; Topos is better. This is because on top of being a hip and chic caf&eacute;, it also allows you to rent a wide array of popular contemporary literature, and the relatively uncommon vintage editions.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the Ridgewood House - walk: 1 minute; bike: 1 minute</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Ridgewood Neighborhood Guide (Image-7), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Ridgewood_Neighborhood/img-33.jpg\" alt=\"Ridgewood Neighborhood Guide (Image-7)\" /></p>\r\n<h3>Fruitti Yummy - 5751 Myrtle Ave</h3>\r\n<p>This is definitely the perfect spot to cool yourself down on a warm day!</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the Ridgewood House - walk: 7 minutes; bike: 2 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Tornado Crepe - 1808 Weirfield St, Ridgewood</h3>\r\n<p>The crepes here definitely fit the cafe\'s name. They come with tasty and exquisite fillings that are filled to the brim of huge spongy cones. The best part is they are also affordable despite being incredibly unique to the neighborhood!</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the Ridgewood House - walk: 8 minutes; bike: 2 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><strong>Nightlife</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>The Ridgewood Ale House -&nbsp;5738 Myrtle Ave, Ridgewood</h3>\r\n<p>If you\'re looking for a quality spot to watch sports with your Outpost friends, head over to the Ridgewood Ale House. Why? Because not only do they have great snacks in the form of pizza and chicken wings, they also have booths that are fitted with flatscreen TVs!</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Ridgewood Neighborhood Guide (Image-8), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Ridgewood_Neighborhood/20180317_202253_1521338666218.jpg\" alt=\"Ridgewood Neighborhood Guide (Image-8)\" /></p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the Ridgewood House - walk: 8 minutes; bike: 2 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Acres BBQ &nbsp;-&nbsp;57-42 Myrtle Ave, Flushing, NY 11385</h3>\r\n<p>Looking for good food in addition to good drinks? Acres BBQ is your place! On Thursdays they also hold a trivia, hosted by Geeks Who Drink.</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the Ridgewood House - walk: 8 minutes; bike: 2 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>The Deep End - 1080 Wyckoff Ave, Ridgewood</h3>\r\n<p>The Deep End has everything you could possibly need for a great night out. From food like chicken wings, burgers, and tacos, to reasonably priced drinks, it has it all. The bar also hosts Karaoke nights and different events every week.</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the Ridgewood House - bus: 12 minutes; walk: 18 minutes; bike: 5 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Dromedary Urban Tiki Bar - 266 Irving Ave, Brooklyn</h3>\r\n<p>This bar offers tiki-style cocktails and doubles as an event space. It feature monthly burlesque shows, comedy shows, a drink\'n\'draw night, live music, weekly trivia &amp; karaoke nights, movie screenings, among many others!</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the Ridgewood House - train: 10 minutes; bus: 14 minutes; walk: 17 minutes; bike: 6 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>These are just some of the more popular ones. There are plenty other cool bars you should checkout, like the Elmekkah Bar and Grill at 277 Wyckoff Ave, and Victor&rsquo;s Bar &amp; Restaurant!</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><strong>Post office</strong></h2>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3>United States Postal Service - 6060 Myrtle Ave, Ridgewood</h3>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the Ridgewood House - bus: 9 minutes; walk: 12 minutes; bike &ndash; 4 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>United States Postal Service - 6080 Woodbine St, Ridgewood</h3>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the Ridgewood House - bus: 7 minutes; walk: 9 minutes; bike: 4 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><em><strong>THAT\'S ALL FOR NOW! WE CONSIDER THIS A LIVING DOCUMENT, SO IF YOU HAVE ANY SUGGESTION OF PLACES TO ADD, OR TIPS FOR THE PLACES ALREADY ON THE LIST, LET US KNOW! YOU CAN COMMENT BELOW OR EMAIL US AT INFO@OUTPOST-CLUB.COM</strong></em></h3>', 'img-48.jpg', 1, '2018-03-18 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(95, 'Lifetime Friendship Formed at Outpost Club – Simon and Oscar', 1, 'lifetime-friendship-formed-at-outpost-club--simon-and-oscar', '', 'Lifetime Friendship Formed at Outpost Club – Simon and Oscar', 'Lifetime Friendship Formed at Outpost Club – Simon and Oscar', 'Lifetime Friendship Formed at Outpost Club – Simon and Oscar', '<p>There is saying that goes something like this: As your best friend, I\'ll always pick you up when you fall.. after I finish laughing.</p>', '<p><img title=\"Lifetime Friendship Formed at Outpost Club &ndash; Simon and Oscar (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/LIFETIME_FRIENDSHIP/20180224_194528_1521779113713.jpg\" alt=\"Lifetime Friendship Formed at Outpost Club &ndash; Simon and Oscar (Image-1)\" /></p>\r\n<p>There is saying that goes something like this:&nbsp;As your best friend, I\'ll always pick you up when you fall.. after I finish laughing.</p>\r\n<p>That saying describes the friendship between Russian-born Simon Bogdanov&nbsp;and Honduras-born Oscar Ochoa to the T.</p>\r\n<p>They were introduced as roommates in <a href=\"../\" rel=\"nofollow\">Outpost Club</a>\'s Bushwick House&nbsp;just a few months ago, in October 2017 to be exact.</p>\r\n<p>\"My first impression of Simon? I thought he looks like someone I can get along with. I was right, because he\'s friendly and easy going. Although I also thought he was annoying at first,\" said Oscar, before bursting into laughter. \"He had.. a peculiar sense of humor. But I learn to understand him, and now he\'s one of my great friends!\"</p>\r\n<p>\"I just silently hoped he doesn\'t snore,\" said Simon. \"Just kidding. In all seriousness, I thought he was a really cool guy.\"</p>\r\n<p>But according to the duo, it was their common interests that solidified their friendship.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\"We share common interests, like cars and drinks,\" said Simon.</p>\r\n<p>\"And we both like girls,\" Oscar interjected. \"Just have to make that clear.\"</p>\r\n<p>\"As we are both car enthusiasts, in November last year we went on a road trip to Cold Spring together. It was really fun to have someone to do that with. To be your partner-in-crime almost,\" Simon continued.</p>\r\n<p>\"We drove separate cars by the way. It\'s not like we were holding hands or whatever. Again, just need to make that clear,\" added Oscar.</p>\r\n<p>In just a short few months, Oscar and Simon have made memories that took others a lifetime to accomplish.</p>\r\n<p>One of them was when they pranked a fellow housemate by putting a sock on her room\'s doorknob.</p>\r\n<p>\"She is also a really good friend of ours. And because she didn\'t know we were pulling a prank on her, she slept on the couch that night thinking something was going on in her shared room!\" Simon said. \"It was definitely a good morning for us.\"</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Lifetime Friendship Formed at Outpost Club &ndash; Simon and Oscar (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/LIFETIME_FRIENDSHIP/img-54.jpg\" alt=\"Lifetime Friendship Formed at Outpost Club &ndash; Simon and Oscar (Image-2)\" /></p>\r\n<p>Oscar had another fond memory to share.</p>\r\n<p>\"It was of the time when we went to a bar, and Simon was dancing with several girls. It was funny.. And sad to watch, because he can\'t dance,\" said Oscar. \"Oh and also, he was wearing sweatpants.. like a grandpa.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>\"I tried,\" added Simon.</p>\r\n<p>Their story definitely brought a smile to our faces. Whoever said that NYC is a lonely place to live in, said so because they have never met the kind of members&nbsp;we have here at Outpost Club! So join us&nbsp;and build your own memory of a lifetime friendship.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Facebook:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/outpostclubNY/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Outpost Club</a></p>\r\n<p>Instagram:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://bit.ly/2yKHwih\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">@outpostcoliving</a>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '20180224_194528_1521779113713.jpg', 1, '2018-03-22 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(309, 'Destination: Ange Noir Cafe', 1, 'destination-ange-noir-cafe', '', 'Destination: Ange Noir Cafe', 'Destination: Ange Noir Cafe', 'We have a million things to say about Ange Noir Cafe — all of them good, all of them with gooey eyes.', '<p>We have a million things to say about Ange Noir Cafe&nbsp;&mdash; all of them good, all of them with gooey eyes. Looking for a place to chill out? Perfect. Need to sit down and get some work done? You&rsquo;ve got it. Ange Noir is the \"room of requirement\" of Brooklyn cafes (and the best part is that not everybody knows about it yet).</p>', '<p>We have a million things to say about <strong>Ange Noir Cafe</strong>&nbsp;&mdash; all of them good, all of them with gooey eyes. Looking for a place to chill out? Perfect. Need to sit down and get some work done? You&rsquo;ve got it. Ange Noir is the \"room of requirement\" of Brooklyn cafes (and the best part is that not everybody knows about it yet).</p>\r\n<p>Located a short walk from the Morgan Ave. stop on the L train, Ange Noir is both spacious and intimate, with a relaxed yet welcoming vibe. Choose from a selection of red puffed-up cushioned chairs in the open-plan main room filled with dark wood and exposed brick, or head into the back room for privacy and a quiet place to work. The staff are always friendly and ready to serve up a selection of coffee, pastries or food, depending on your fancy.</p>\r\n<p>Ange Noir is owned by a French couple who really know their food, meaning the menu is surprisingly extensive for a small cafe, including homemade sandwiches, bagels, salads and even crepes. There\'s also a nice selection of&nbsp;flavored and iced coffees as well as on-the-go snacks. With daily opening times from 7:30 a.m.&ndash;7 p.m., it&rsquo;s the perfect place to drop in for breakfast, lunch, dinner or some combination of them all.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Destination: Ange Noir Cafe (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/1_9.jpg\" alt=\"Destination: Ange Noir Cafe (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo: JD C.,<em> Yelp</em></p>\r\n<p>Ange Noir is particularly popular for meet-up groups, including <strong>Bushwick Writers Group</strong> and several boardgamers, who compete for table space on Sunday afternoons. If you&rsquo;re new to the city, it&rsquo;s a wonderful place to meet people, as these groups are perpetually welcoming to newcomers. It&rsquo;s people like this who give Ange Noir its signature friendly, creative atmosphere, while at the same time, you&rsquo;ll find others happily working or drinking coffee on their own if you\'re not feeling sociable.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><br /><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Destination: Ange Noir Cafe (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/1_10.jpg\" alt=\"Destination: Ange Noir Cafe (Image-2)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo: Nurry S.&nbsp;<em>Yelp</em></p>\r\n<p>The back room converts into a live music venue by night, transforming this cafe into a low-key bar. Simply walk through the red phone booth&nbsp;to find a stage ready to welcome Brooklyn&rsquo;s best indie talent, Hellphone, the perfect place to spend a relaxed Friday or Saturday night. Show times are announced on their Facebook Page, so be sure to check in regularly for updates and recommendations.</p>\r\n<p>With such a variety of happenings and the possibility of all-day crepes, it&rsquo;s easy to see why we love this hidden away Bushwick cafe.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Destination: Ange Noir Cafe (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/3_12.jpg\" alt=\"Destination: Ange Noir Cafe (Image-3)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /><em>Photo: Steven J. Yelp</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>Ange Noir Cafe</em></p>\r\n<p>247 Varet St.</p>\r\n<p>Brooklyn</p>\r\n<p>11206</p>', '3_4.jpg', 1, '2019-10-13 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(96, 'Outpost members go public with their singing skill​​​​​​​', 1, 'outpost-members-go-public-with-their-singing-skill', '', 'Outpost members go public with their singing skill​​​​​​​', 'Outpost members go public with their singing skill​​​​​​​', 'Outpost members go public with their singing skill​​​​​​​', '<p>Raise your hand, like we are doing right now, if you know that one person who loves giving out solo performances in the bathroom.</p>', '<p>Raise your hand, like we are doing right now, if you know that one person who loves giving out solo performances in the bathroom.</p>\r\n<p>For their sake - and yours too if they\'re belting out those tunes every morning of EVERY DAY - take them out for a karaoke night!</p>\r\n<p>That\'s what we at the <a href=\"../\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Outpost Club</a> did on Tuesday.</p>\r\n<p>Our community manager Tacia Duarte organized the event a couple of weeks prior, after she found a great spot that lets you sing one song for free with every drink you buy.</p>\r\n<p>We had a great turnout despite it being on a work day! They even stayed up until 11pm rocking on to Beyonce, Eminem, and ACDC, just to name a few.<br />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Yap, that\'s how much our members love to showcase their amazing singing talent.</p>\r\n<p>Check out the pictures to see how seriously they took the opportunity to take their singing skills out of the bathroom, and into the dance floor.</p>\r\n<p>The best part is that they get to do this with the friends they made at Outpost Club.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"../join-us\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Join</a> us if this is the kind of fun you hope to experience in NYC!<br />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost members go public with their singing skill​​​​​​​ (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_members/20180320_210751_1521678815734.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost members go public with their singing skill​​​​​​​ (Image-1)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost members go public with their singing skill​​​​​​​ (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_members/20180320_210754_1521678923314.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost members go public with their singing skill​​​​​​​ (Image-2)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost members go public with their singing skill​​​​​​​ (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_members/20180320_210950_1521679023947.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost members go public with their singing skill​​​​​​​ (Image-3)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost members go public with their singing skill​​​​​​​ (Image-4), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_members/20180320_212836_1521679462094-1.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost members go public with their singing skill​​​​​​​ (Image-4)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost members go public with their singing skill​​​​​​​ (Image-5), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_members/20180320_214205_1521679244994-1.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost members go public with their singing skill​​​​​​​ (Image-5)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost members go public with their singing skill​​​​​​​ (Image-6), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_members/20180320_214206(0)_1521761071363.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost members go public with their singing skill​​​​​​​ (Image-6)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost members go public with their singing skill​​​​​​​ (Image-7), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_members/IMG_2582_1521760582745.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost members go public with their singing skill​​​​​​​ (Image-7)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost members go public with their singing skill​​​​​​​ (Image-8), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_members/IMG_2584_1521749923016.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost members go public with their singing skill​​​​​​​ (Image-8)\" /></p>\r\n</div>', '20180320_210751_1521678815734.jpg', 1, '2018-03-23 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(97, 'Member Profile Giselle Carrozzi', 1, 'member-profile-giselle-carrozzi', 'blog-outpost-club/2018/3/26/member-profile-giselle-carrozzi', 'Member Profile Giselle Carrozzi', 'Member Profile Giselle Carrozzi', 'his week we’re introducing you to Giselle who stayed with us at our Bushwick House', '<p>Welcome to our members\' profile series, where we share the stories of why they moved to NYC, and also what they like about their time here. this week we&rsquo;re introducing you to Giselle who stayed.</p>', '<p><strong>Welcome to our members\' profile series, where we share the stories of why they moved to NYC, and also what they like about their time here. This week we&rsquo;re introducing you to Giselle who stayed with us at our Bushwick House. We hope you enjoy this article.&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Member Profile Giselle Carrozzi (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Member_Giselle/img-43.jpg\" alt=\"Member Profile Giselle Carrozzi (Image-1)\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>Tell us a little about yourself</strong></p>\r\n<p>I\'m a Brazilian from S&atilde;o Paulo - Brazil\'s largest city and one of the world&rsquo;s most populous and dynamic urban areas - known for its gastronomic offerings, endless cultural activities, and busy nightlife. I&rsquo;m currently working in the marketing department in a law firm here.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What brought you to NYC?</strong></p>\r\n<p>I first came for a vacation. New York has always been a dream, thanks to Hollywood. I also wanted (and needed) to improve my English skills, while acquiring a new personal experience. Then I was all by myself in this big, beautiful, crazy city.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What has been your best experience here?</strong></p>\r\n<p>In New York, you never know what&rsquo;s going to happen. There is so much to do and see. The art scene preserves the best from around the world; you can try food from every part of the world; there are endless cultural activities, diverse group of people and the coolest music scene.</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Member Profile Giselle Carrozzi (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Member_Giselle/25446482_1492186544232013_8737768199699230938_n.jpg\" alt=\"Member Profile Giselle Carrozzi (Image-2)\" /></p>\r\n<p>Simple things like walking the streets of New York City by yourself is amazing in itself. Every day I found myself on a new adventure.</p>\r\n<p>My best experience was when I broke my barrier of fear and shyness and went alone to a nightclub to see a DJ that I love. I cannot describe the happiness I felt in that moment.</p>\r\n<p>And it\'s hard to name just one, because every day was a challenge: braving the freezing cold, meeting new people, learning about new cultures and a different language. I must say, traveling and staying in NYC has changed my life.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What do you think of coliving?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Finding a place to stay that combines good price and great location in NYC is a real challenge. You need to have a lot of money saved up, and be able to take up different living opportunities.</p>\r\n<p>I find that the best part of living in a coliving is the interaction with people. You can communicate with everybody. Also, the sense of community makes you remember that person-to-person communication nowadays is rare.</p>\r\n<p>Sometimes it\'s a challenge to figure out everyone\'s personalities. But for me, that point was essential in the process of learning different cultures. This made me grow up as a person. You can be by yourself if you want, or hang out with the people in the house. Both are ok.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What\'s been your best experience in the time you have stayed at Outpost?</strong></p>\r\n<p>The Outpost experience was memorable and unique as a whole. It&rsquo;s hard to pinpoint just one. The location of Bushwick House, being on the coolest Brooklyn neighborhood was amazing for me!</p>\r\n<p>I also can say that the New Year&rsquo;s party organized at the house was essential in making me feel like part of NY and Outpost. And the day that we (Simon, Amanda and Nawar) went to a karaok&ecirc; bar was so funny and crazy. I miss the people from Outpost!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Facebook: Giselle Carrozzi and <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/outpostclubNY/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Outpost Club</a></p>\r\n<p>Instagram: Giselle Carrozzi and<a href=\"https://bit.ly/2yKHwih\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">&nbsp;Outpost_club</a></p>', 'img-43.jpg', 1, '2018-03-25 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `s_blog` (`id`, `name`, `type`, `url`, `old_url`, `meta_title`, `meta_keywords`, `meta_description`, `annotation`, `text`, `image`, `visible`, `date`, `date_modified`, `featured`, `rating`, `votes`) VALUES
(98, 'The Bed-Stuy House Neighborhood Guide', 1, 'the-bed-stuy-house-neighborhood-guide', '', 'The Bed-Stuy House Neighborhood Guide', 'The Bed-Stuy House Neighborhood Guide', 'The Bed-Stuy House Neighborhood Guide', '<p>If you&rsquo;re new to the area, we understand how tough that can be. We have members coming from all over the world and many of them at the start didn&rsquo;t know much about America, let alone the mixed.</p>', '<h3><em><strong>If you&rsquo;re new to the area, we understand how tough that can be. We have members coming from all over the world and many of them at the start didn&rsquo;t know much about America, let alone the mixed neighbourhood of <a href=\"../the-bedstuy-house\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Bed-Stuyvesant</a>! Let us help you with some of the basics, so you can start exploring the neighborhood almost immediately.</strong></em></h3>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h2><strong>Subway/Travel</strong></h2>\r\n<p><strong>It\'s really up to you, but here are the main ways to get to Manhattan!</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>The M train - Myrtle Avenue</h3>\r\n<p>The M train is a 7-minute walk from the House. Just make a left when you exit the House, another left on either Marcus Garvey Boulevard or Lewis Avenue, then make a right on Myrtle Avenue.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Bed-Stuy House - walk: 7 minutes; bike: 2 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>The G Train - Myrtle-Willoughby Ave</h3>\r\n<p>The G train is a little further than the M-train, but still conveniently located with just about 10-minutes&rsquo; walk from the House. To get there, make a right when you exit the House, then make a right once you&rsquo;ve made it to Marcy Avenue. Walk three blocks and voila, you&rsquo;ve reached the Myrtle-Willoughby Ave.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Bed-Stuy House - walk: 10 minutes; bike: 3 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h2><strong>Gym</strong></h2>\r\n<p><strong>Having a tough time finding your new gym? here are some options below</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Planet Fitness - 777 Broadway, Brooklyn</h3>\r\n<p>Planet Fitness promises a judgment-free zone for its members, by providing a comfortable, safe and energetic environment. It is also affordable, with membership prices starting at just $10 a month!</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Bed-Stuy House - walk: 10 minutes; bike: 5 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Crunch - Bushwick - 785 Flushing Ave, Brooklyn</h3>\r\n<p>The basic membership at Crunch will cost you only $10 per month. With just $10 extra, you will also get access to group fitness classes and live video workouts!</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Bed-Stuy House - walk: 11 minutes; bike: 4 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>CrossFit Outbreak Bed Stuy - 1107, 492 Throop Ave, Brooklyn</h3>\r\n<p>\"CrossFit makes people better\". That\'s the gym\'s motto. It does this by promoting workouts as a movement and a lifestyle. So head here if fun and interesting workouts are your \"thing\".</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Bed-Stuy House - walk: 12 minutes; bike: 6 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h2><strong>Groceries</strong></h2>\r\n<p><strong>Looking to grab quick groceries? There are plenty of options you can pick from, but we have narrowed them down to four that suit your every need.</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Gawad Deli Grocery - 207 Hart St, Brooklyn</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Bed-Stuy House - walk: 2 minutes; bike: 1 minute</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Al Hajjaji Food Corp. - 107 Hart St, Brooklyn</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Bed-Stuy House - walk: 6 minutes; bike: 1 minute</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"The Bed-Stuy House Neighborhood Guide (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/The_Bed_Stuy/img-13.jpg\" alt=\"The Bed-Stuy House Neighborhood Guide (Image-1)\" /></p>\r\n<h3>Natural Mini Market - Kosciuszko &nbsp;St, Brooklyn</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Bed-Stuy House - bus: 6 minutes; walk: 8 minutes; bike: 3 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Bravo Supermarkets - 844 DeKalb Ave, Brooklyn</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Bed-Stuy House - walk: 5 minutes; bike: 2 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Junior&rsquo;s Food Outlets - 994 Myrtle Ave, Brooklyn</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Bed-Stuy House - walk: 5 minutes; bike: 2 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h2><strong>Coffee shops</strong></h2>\r\n<p><strong>Need your morning fix? Here are some places hand picked for you</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"The Bed-Stuy House Neighborhood Guide (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/The_Bed_Stuy/20180324_151701_1522023782963.jpg\" alt=\"The Bed-Stuy House Neighborhood Guide (Image-2)\" /></p>\r\n<h3>Marcy &amp; Myrtle Cafe - 574 Marcy Avenue, Brooklyn</h3>\r\n<p>This is one of the places in the neighborhood that had immediately caught our eyes. Both the exterior and interior designs make for amazing photographs! It doesn\'t hurt that their coffee and pastries are also mouth-watering.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Bed-Stuy House - bus: 8 minutes; walk: 10 minutes; bike: 2 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Brooklyn Whiskers - 760 Bushwick Ave, Brooklyn</h3>\r\n<p>This cafe is heaven-sent for vegans. It specializes in plant-based pastries and other Insta-worthy custom creations.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Bed-Stuy House - bus: 13 minutes; walk: 14 minutes; bike: 5 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Bedford Hill Coffee Bar - 343 &nbsp;Franklin Ave, Brooklyn</h3>\r\n<p>Bedford Hill Coffee Bar claims to be an ideal spot for first-time dates, meetings between long lost friends, and everyday visitors. We agree! Besides coffee and tea, it also serves beer and wine.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Bed-Stuy House - bus: 15 minutes; walk: 24 minutes; bike: 7 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Ange Noir Cafe - 247 Varet St</h3>\r\n<p>Do you want a taste of France? The head on to the Ange Noir Cafe which is owned and operated by a French couple. The cafe has options that cater to all types of dietary preferences, including vegan and gluten-free fare.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Bed-Stuy House - bus: 19 minutes; walk: 20 minutes; bike: 7 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h2><strong>Coworking Space</strong></h2>\r\n<p><img title=\"The Bed-Stuy House Neighborhood Guide (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/The_Bed_Stuy/Screen%2BShot%2B2018-03-26%2Bat%2B16_03_11_png_11.jpg\" alt=\"The Bed-Stuy House Neighborhood Guide (Image-3)\" /></p>\r\n<h3><strong>BKYLN Commons - 774 Broadway Avenue, </strong><strong>Brooklyn </strong></h3>\r\n<p>BKLYN Commons is an ever-growing coworking community of entrepreneurs, small business owners, and remote employees. As a member of BKC, you\'ll have access to gorgeous workspaces, unique common areas, business-grade printers, flexible conference rooms, and numerous monthly networking events!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Looking for an office close to home? Take a tour at <a href=\"https://bklyncommons.com/bushwick/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">BKLYN Commons</a>. BKYLN is a partnered with Outpost Club, and they are excited to offer all of the Outpost community 25% the first two months when they join BKLYN Commons. The locations are BEAUTIFUL and their Bushwick location is near to the Bed-Stuy house!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h2><strong>Food</strong></h2>\r\n<p>The neighborhood offers an unlimited variety of eateries at affordable prices. Here are a few that we recommend, based on the input provided by our former and current members.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"The Bed-Stuy House Neighborhood Guide (Image-4), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/The_Bed_Stuy/20180324_160534_1522024162038.jpg\" alt=\"The Bed-Stuy House Neighborhood Guide (Image-4)\" /></p>\r\n<h3>BKLYN Blend - 194 Tompkins Ave, Brooklyn</h3>\r\n<p>This neighborhood joint looks simple from the outside. But it offers tasty and authentic Balkan delicacies that you have to try out!</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Bed-Stuy House - bus: 6 minutes; walk: 6 minutes; bike: 1 minute</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Little Skips - 941 Willoughby Ave, Brooklyn</h3>\r\n<p>Head here if you\'re into high-quality yet affordable sandwiches. The two we would recommend are the cafe\'s Vegan LBT - made with smokey maple tempeh bacon, tomato, mixed greens and house-made vegan cilantro-lime aioli, served on wheat toast - and The Norwegian -made with goat cheese, smoked salmon, tomato, avocado, red onion, mixed greens &amp; honey-lemon vinaigrette, served on grilled multigrain.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Bed-Stuy House - bus: 9 minutes; walk: 13 minutes; bike: 6 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"The Bed-Stuy House Neighborhood Guide (Image-5), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/The_Bed_Stuy/20180324_160506_1522023602191.jpg\" alt=\"The Bed-Stuy House Neighborhood Guide (Image-5)\" /></p>\r\n<h3>Rocco Pizza - 765 Dekalb Ave Brooklyn</h3>\r\n<p>A slice of pizza costs only $2! Check out Rocco&rsquo;s specialty pizzas too. Our suggestion? Eat in rather than take-away. Because the interior design will make you feel like you&rsquo;re dining in a small, family-owned restaurant in Italy. Buon Appetito!</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Bed-Stuy House - bus: 5 minutes; walk: 7 minutes; bike: 2 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3>Fermento - 1412, 358 Kosciuszko St, Brooklyn</h3>\r\n<p>Fermento offers food all day long. It&rsquo;s a great spot for those who care, and want to contribute towards the preservation of the environment.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Bed-Stuy House - walk: 4 minutes; bike: 2 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h2><strong>Nightlife</strong></h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Alphaville</h3>\r\n<p>This versatile space has something for everyone. So go and enjoy the good food and drinks here, while being accompanied by live music.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Bed-Stuy House - bus: 17 minutes; walk: 21 minutes; bike: 9 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"The Bed-Stuy House Neighborhood Guide (Image-6), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/The_Bed_Stuy/img-53.jpg\" alt=\"The Bed-Stuy House Neighborhood Guide (Image-6)\" /></p>\r\n<h3>Bizarre Bushwick - 12 Jefferson St, Brooklyn</h3>\r\n<p><em>&ldquo;Assorted Madness and The Unexpected.&rdquo;</em></p>\r\n<p>According to the New York Magazine, the owner of Bizarre are filmmakers. This is definitely translated in the monthly shows this space organizes. Go check it out!</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Bed-Stuy House - bus: 9 minutes; walk: 11 minutes; bike: 5 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Wine-o</h3>\r\n<p>This bar offers a variety of wines, including those that are made with grapes grown without synthetic chemicals. It also organizes a \"tasting evening\" every Friday. &nbsp;Now that would make for great and educational night out.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Bed-Stuy House - walk: 9 minutes; bike: 2 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h2><strong>Parks</strong></h2>\r\n<p><strong>One thing we love about this neighborhood is how it is surrounded by parks. If you ever need to wind down from a stressful day, a simple 20-30 minutes around the various parks here would definitely do the magic.</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Herbert Von King Park - Lafayette Avenue, Brooklyn</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Bed-Stuy House - walk: 11 minutes; bike: 4 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div><img title=\"The Bed-Stuy House Neighborhood Guide (Image-7), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/The_Bed_Stuy/20180324_153455_1522023697946.jpg\" alt=\"The Bed-Stuy House Neighborhood Guide (Image-7)\" /> Pulaski Park</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Pulaski Park</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Bed-Stuy House - walk: 1 minute; bike: 1 minute</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Marcy Park - 753 Myrtle Ave, Brooklyn</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Bed-Stuy House - bus: 12 minutes; walk: 13 minutes; bike: 3 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h2><strong>Post office</strong></h2>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>United States Postal Service - 47 Debevoise St, Brooklyn</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Bed-Stuy House - bus: 11 minutes; walk: 13 minutes; bike: 5 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>US Post Office - 21 Manhattan Ave, Brooklyn</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Bed-Stuy House - bus: 11 minutes; walk: 15 minutes; bike: 5 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>United States Postal Service - 609 Myrtle Ave Ste A, Brooklyn</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Bed-Stuy House - bus: 17 minutes; walk: 22 minutes; bike: 6 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>United States Postal Service - 1369 Broadway, Brooklyn</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Bed-Stuy House - train: 15 minutes; bus: 18 minutes; walk: 23 minutes; bike: 9 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3><em><strong>THAT\'S ALL FOR NOW! WE CONSIDER THIS A LIVING DOCUMENT, SO IF YOU HAVE ANY SUGGESTION OF PLACES TO ADD, OR TIPS FOR THE PLACES ALREADY ON THE LIST, LET US KNOW! YOU CAN comment below or EMAIL US AT INFO@OUTPOST-CLUB.COM</strong></em></h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'img-13.jpg', 1, '2018-03-25 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(99, 'Destination: Jefferson Street', 1, 'destination-jefferson-street', 'blog-outpost-club/2018/3/28/destination-jefferson-street', 'Destination: Jefferson Street', 'Destination: Jefferson Street', 'Murals on Jefferson Street', '<p>A mural on Jefferson Street</p>', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div><img title=\"Destination: Jefferson Street (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Destination_Jefferson_Street/20180227_150402_1522121139499.jpg\" alt=\"Destination: Jefferson Street (Image-1)\" /> A mural on Jefferson Street</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Just about 10 minutes\' walk from Outpost\'s Knickerbocker House is a street bursting with colors.</p>\r\n<p>The walls on every block that line up the Jefferson Street serve as pieces of canvas for a well-known art-movement organization, <a href=\"http://thebushwickcollective.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">The Bushwick Collective</a>.</p>\r\n<p>The movement was conceived by Bushwick native Joe Ficalora, and has contributed to the change the neighborhood has seen in the last few years.</p>\r\n<p>On a bright, sun-blessed day, Jefferson Street gives out a celebratory vibe. Almost carnival-like. On a rainy and gloomy day, the vibe turned into one that sucks you in, making you feel like part of the street arts surrounding you.</p>\r\n<p>Jefferson street represents Brooklyn at its core, as the center of arts and cultures. This is why it is <a href=\"../\" target=\"_blank\">Outpost\'s</a> destination pick for our members, and top of <a href=\"https://foursquare.com/top-places/bushwick-brooklyn/best-places-arts\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Foursquare\'s 15 Best Places for Arts in Bushwick</a>.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div><img title=\"Destination: Jefferson Street (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Destination_Jefferson_Street/img-41.jpg\" alt=\"Destination: Jefferson Street (Image-2)\" /> Tours of the graffiti in this area are very common!</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The theme is also represented in the people living around the area - the artistic community who lives and breathes art; from the way they dress to the things they do for a living.</p>\r\n<p>To some, the reason they moved to New York City.</p>\r\n<p>So go spend a day walking around the area and soaking in the arts that have made <a href=\"../blog/the-appeal-of-living-in-bushwick\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Bushwick</a> the center of New York\'s art scene. Bring your camera along, because every corner offers a sight worth capturing.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><img title=\"Destination: Jefferson Street (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Destination_Jefferson_Street/20180227_152915_1522123382025.jpg\" alt=\"Destination: Jefferson Street (Image-3)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Destination: Jefferson Street (Image-4), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Destination_Jefferson_Street/20180227_155912_1522121704993.jpg\" alt=\"Destination: Jefferson Street (Image-4)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Destination: Jefferson Street (Image-5), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Destination_Jefferson_Street/20180227_150259_1522121032000.jpg\" alt=\"Destination: Jefferson Street (Image-5)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Destination: Jefferson Street (Image-5), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Destination_Jefferson_Street/20180227_155942_1522121869170.jpg\" alt=\"Destination: Jefferson Street (Image-5)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Destination: Jefferson Street (Image-6), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Destination_Jefferson_Street/20180227_150547_1522121241061.jpg\" alt=\"Destination: Jefferson Street (Image-6)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Destination: Jefferson Street (Image-7), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Destination_Jefferson_Street/20180227_160036_1522123503447.jpg\" alt=\"Destination: Jefferson Street (Image-7)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Destination: Jefferson Street (Image-8), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Destination_Jefferson_Street/20180227_152104_1522121422049.jpg\" alt=\"Destination: Jefferson Street (Image-8)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Destination: Jefferson Street (Image-9), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Destination_Jefferson_Street/20180227_152734_1522122755584.jpg\" alt=\"Destination: Jefferson Street (Image-9)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Destination: Jefferson Street (Image-10), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Destination_Jefferson_Street/20180227_145331_1522122873552.jpg\" alt=\"Destination: Jefferson Street (Image-10)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Destination: Jefferson Street (Image-11), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Destination_Jefferson_Street/20180227_145645_1522120801401.jpg\" alt=\"Destination: Jefferson Street (Image-11)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Destination: Jefferson Street (Image-12), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Destination_Jefferson_Street/20180227_145710_1522120934637.jpg\" alt=\"Destination: Jefferson Street (Image-12)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Destination: Jefferson Street (Image-13), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Destination_Jefferson_Street/20180227_145738_1522123099140.jpg\" alt=\"Destination: Jefferson Street (Image-13)\" /></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Facebook:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/outpostclubNY/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Outpost Club</a></p>\r\n<p>Instagram: <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/outpostcoliving\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">@outpostcoliving</a></p>', '20180227_150402_1522121139499.jpg', 1, '2018-03-27 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(100, '5 Things About Bushwick House Leader: Simon Bogdanov', 1, '5-things-about-bushwick-house-leader-simon-bogdanov', '', '5 Things About Bushwick House Leader: Simon Bogdanov', '5 Things About Bushwick House Leader: Simon Bogdanov', '5 Things About Bushwick House Leader: Simon Bogdanov', '<p>\"If you can make it there, you\'ll make it anywhere; it\'s up to you, New York, New York.\"</p>', '<p>\"<strong><em>If you can make it there, you\'ll make it anywhere; it\'s up to you, New York, New York</em></strong>.\"</p>\r\n<p>&mdash; Frank Sinatra</p>\r\n<p>New York City is the place where dreams are made of - Jay Z got it right with this quote. Isn\'t that why millions of people took the risk of leaving the comfort of their homes behind, to move to a city that offers endless opportunities for those who dare to dream?</p>\r\n<p>But here\'s the reality that most people realized after they had taken the plunge: NYC can be challenging, with its fast-paced environment and the hurdles that can make you feel like only the fittest will survive this concrete jungle.</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"5 Things About Bushwick House Leader: Simon Bogdanov (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/5_Things/img-3.jpg\" alt=\"5 Things About Bushwick House Leader: Simon Bogdanov (Image-1)\" /></p>\r\n<p>That\'s why friends - one like <a href=\"https://www.outpost-club.com/\"><strong>Outpost</strong></a>\'s Bushwick House&nbsp;leader Simon Bogdanov - is the key to making it here.</p>\r\n<p>The Russian-born UX designer moved to the States with his family at a very young age. Four years ago he decided to pack his bags and make NYC his new home. Despite the challenges he faced here, Simon never gave up. Instead, he picked up all the tricks to survive NYC and make it a mission to help those who share the same big city dream he has.</p>\r\n<p>This has quickly made him our <a href=\"https://www.outpost-club.com/blog/\">members</a>\' go-to person for all things NYC.</p>\r\n<p>From networking techniques and creating the perfect resume, to finding out the best chicken and waffles spot in NYC, Simon can help you achieve your dreams while making sure you have the best time of your life.</p>\r\n<p>So read on for the five things you should know about him.</p>\r\n<p><strong>1) A People Person</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>I moved to New York 4 years ago, so I know what it\'s like moving to the city. I believe that co-living and Outpost Club is a great way to help people who had moved here, and I simply want to be a part of it.</em></p>\r\n<p><em>As a house leader, I make sure everyone who is staying here have a great time. If there\'s anything I can help out with, I try to do so.</em></p>\r\n<p><em>The best part is I get to organize </em><a href=\"https://www.outpost-club.com/blog-outpost-club/2018/2/15/because-everyone-is-entitled-to-the-day-of-love-outpost-club\"><em>parties</em></a><em>, and get paid for it.&nbsp;</em><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;<br /><strong>2) Loves Diversity</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>One thing I love about the US is how diverse it is, and the fact that I get to meet people from all over the world. Outpost Club is also a great environment for that. Everyone here is from different countries and speak different languages. So we always talk about our cultures, and learn a little bit of this and that.</em></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"5 Things About Bushwick House Leader: Simon Bogdanov (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/5_Things/img-20.jpg\" alt=\"5 Things About Bushwick House Leader: Simon Bogdanov (Image-2)\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>3) Fun Party Buddy</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>We always have something to do on the weekends here at Outpost. Every now and then we organize something fun at the house, like a housemate bonding time where we have a few drinks- one, two, three, 10, 20.&nbsp;Afterwards we would head to the city and do everything fun.</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>4) Funny</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>A Mexican magician does a trick. He says to the audience: I will disappear on the count of three. He goes uno, dos, and disappears. He disappeared without a \'tres\'.</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>5) Better Than Yelp</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>I was schooled outside the US, so I know geography well (just kidding!). Learning NYC has been pretty easy for me because I know how to read a map, and this led me to discover new, fun places.</em></p>\r\n<p><em>So I love taking our members see the city and discovering new food. Especially if they never had American food before!</em></p>\r\n<p>Well,&nbsp;that\'s five. But there are still so much more to know about Simon! So go ahead and follow him, and Outpost Club on social media, to join in the adventures we get into every day.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/7SSg7Sy6NRQ?wmode=opaque&amp;enablejsapi=1\" width=\"100%\" height=\"400px\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p>Facebook:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/simon.bogdanov?ref=br_rs\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Simon Bogdanov </a>and <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/outpostclubNY/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Outpost Club</a></p>\r\n<p>Instagram: <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/simonbogdanov/?hl=en\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Simon Bogdanov</a> and<a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/outpost_club/?hl=en\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">&nbsp;outpost_club</a>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'img-3.jpg', 0, '2018-03-04 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(351, 'Ways to take care of your mental health during the COVID-19 pandemic', 1, 'ways-to-take-care-of-your-mental-health-during-the-covid-19-pandemic', '', 'Ways to take care of your mental health during the COVID-19 pandemic', 'Ways to take care of your mental health during the COVID-19 pandemic', 'It’s okay to say we’re in the midst of crazy, unprecedented times. It’s also okay to say that your mental health is a priority and that looking after your wellbeing during the global COVID-19 crisis is important. Whether you’re cooped up in your apartment or worrying about friends and family overseas, there are ways to ensure the chaos doesn’t become too much for you.', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It&rsquo;s okay to say we&rsquo;re in the midst of crazy, unprecedented times. It&rsquo;s also okay to say that your mental health is a priority and that looking after your wellbeing during the global </span><a href=\"https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/index.html\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">COVID-19</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> crisis is important. Whether you&rsquo;re cooped up in your apartment or worrying about friends and family overseas, there are ways to ensure the chaos doesn&rsquo;t become too much for you.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It&rsquo;s okay to say we&rsquo;re in the midst of crazy, unprecedented times. It&rsquo;s also okay to say that your mental health is a priority and that looking after your wellbeing during the global </span><a href=\"https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/index.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">COVID-19</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> crisis is important. Whether you&rsquo;re cooped up in your apartment or worrying about friends and family overseas, there are ways to ensure the chaos doesn&rsquo;t become too much for you.</span></p>\r\n<h1><strong><strong>1. Accept that you&rsquo;re sad (or angry or scared... or any other emotion)</strong></strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The first step to taking care of your mental health is to accept whatever emotions you&rsquo;re feeling right now as valid and real. Oftentimes, we end up in a state of denial in times of shock which can lead to depression, anxiety or emotional outbursts later down the line. Turn to others and open up about your concerns&mdash;you&rsquo;ll realise that everyone is feeling a whole host of emotions based on their own circumstances and that you certainly are not alone. Sharing your fears and thoughts is not a weakness and will actually bring you emotionally closer to your friends or family.</span>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Ways to take care of your mental health during the COVID-19 pandemic (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/benefits/restation-8.jpg\" alt=\"Ways to take care of your mental health during the COVID-19 pandemic (Image-1)\" width=\"462\" height=\"308\" /></p>\r\n<h1><strong><strong>2. But&nbsp;give yourself space from negativity</strong></strong></h1>\r\n<p>If you\'re able to,&nbsp;allow yourself mental space from keeping up with the news and discussing the pandemic with others. The coping strategy best suited to you will depend on your personality, but you can try segmenting your time so that you have a designated hour (or more) of each day where you allow yourself to think about or read the latest news articles and feel your feelings, then spending the rest of the day engaged in activities designed to distract yourself from the current global situation.</p>\r\n<p>Our minds have a habit of throwing up negative eventualities (e.g. &ldquo;What if this goes on forever?&rdquo;), so try countering these negative questions with positive ones (e.g. &ldquo;What if this reduces global warming?&rdquo; or &ldquo;What if this brings me closer to my friends and family?&rdquo;).&nbsp;Try&nbsp;reading &ldquo;good&rdquo; news headlines as well as negative reports and take the global situation one step at a time. Take every day as it comes and try to give yourself things to look forward to on a regular basis, remembering that this will pass.</p>\r\n<h1><strong>3.&nbsp;</strong><strong style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Stay connected with others (virtually)</strong>&nbsp;</h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">One of the hardest parts of this pandemic is being physically distant from friends and family, but virtual platforms such as </span><a href=\"https://www.skype.com/en/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Skype</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> can go a long way to helping you not only keep in contact with them but in tricking your brain into thinking you&rsquo;re interacting with people. Human contact is important for mental health, but video calling can go some way toward undoing the negative effects of isolation. More and more entertainment venues are even putting on video conference parties, from Instagram Live concerts to &ldquo;</span><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/houseofyes/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">digital dance parties</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">&rdquo; which can simulate being out and about with friends without actually leaving the house.</span></p>\r\n<h1><strong><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Ways to take care of your mental health during the COVID-19 pandemic (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/1_18.jpg\" alt=\"Ways to take care of your mental health during the COVID-19 pandemic (Image-2)\" width=\"436\" height=\"527\" />4.&nbsp;</strong><strong style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Take care of others</strong>&nbsp;</h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Doing good deeds for other people gives us a major mental health boost, making us feel great and offering a distraction from negative thoughts. If you&rsquo;re able to leave your house, why not offer to buy essential goods for vulnerable people in your neighborhood (leaving everything on their doorstep to ensure a no-contact delivery)? Otherwise, you can get online and donate to one of the many non-profit organizations helping those struggling during the pandemic. Or why not donate your time&mdash;you could volunteer to supplement the home schooling of a child whose parents or carers don&rsquo;t have the ability or resources to adequately do so themselves or offer your professional skills for free to someone whose small business can&rsquo;t afford a contractor right now.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Ways to take care of your mental health during the COVID-19 pandemic (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/IMG_0372.jpeg\" alt=\"Ways to take care of your mental health during the COVID-19 pandemic (Image-3)\" width=\"513\" height=\"385\" /></span></p>\r\n<h1><strong>5.&nbsp;</strong><strong style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Keep exercising</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We all know that exercising is beneficial to our mental health, but just because you can&rsquo;t go to the gym doesn&rsquo;t mean you have to stop exercising. Take full advantage of the opportunity to exercise and get fresh air, even if you only speed walk around the block or run like crazy for a grand total of 3 minutes. Any amount or duration of exercise can have a positive effect on your mental health, just exposing yourself to some vitamin D will give your brain and body a much needed boost. If you can&rsquo;t go outside right now, you can turn your bedroom into a yoga studio or simply do jumping jacks in your room. You can find plenty of home exercise videos on </span><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=umcrqneCpo4\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Youtube</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, as well as trying subscription services such as </span><a href=\"https://yogainternational.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Yoga International</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> to boost your mood without leaving the house.</span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>', '1_21.jpg', 1, '2020-03-16 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(101, 'Outpost Recommends: Father Knows Best', 1, 'outpost-recommends-father-knows-best', '', 'Outpost Recommends: Father Knows Best', 'Outpost Recommends: Father Knows Best', 'Father Knows Best\'s location in Bushwick', '<p>Father Knows Best\'s location in Bushwick</p>', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div><img title=\"Outpost Recommends: Father Knows Best (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Recommends/20180301_134900_1519931136308-1.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Recommends: Father Knows Best (Image-1)\" /> Father Knows Best\'s location in Bushwick&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Bushwick&nbsp;has gained a reputation for being a go-to spot for the hip and the artistic. But it hasn\'t always been this way.</p>\r\n<p>Long before the mushrooming of hipster-approved art-themed pubs and cafe, certain corners of the borough were decorated only by the stereotypical Chinese take-out restaurants and fast food outlets.</p>\r\n<p>This did not sit well with Chris Taha when he visited Bushwick\'s Wilson Ave three years ago.</p>\r\n<p>\"What makes this neighborhood so beautiful is the array of artists, musicians, and creatives. (There are) so many different types of people with so many amazing qualities to offer,\" said Taha.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\"(But) I felt their talent was being underutilized. So we wanted to create a space where they can share their ideas, their creativity, and collaborate in really cool ways,\" he added.</p>\r\n<p>An idea for a community-based space struck him then. Together with business partner Colleen Makary, they founded Father Knows Best.</p>\r\n<p>\"My dad is an artist. That\'s partially why I came up with the name Father Knows Best. I grew up in this whole artist lifestyle,&nbsp;and I feel Bushwick is a cool representation of that. And I want to dedicate the place to my dad,\" said Taha.</p>\r\n<p>Father Knows Best, located just 9 minutes\' walk from our Bushwick House, and about 5 minutes from the East Bushwick House, has quickly become a favorite among Outpost\'s&nbsp;members.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div><img title=\"Outpost Recommends: Father Knows Best (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Recommends/20180228_130508_1519932198338.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Recommends: Father Knows Best (Image-2)\" /> The inside of Father Knows Best</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>It\'s easy to see why. The place doubles as a cafe during the day, and a bar that serves food all the way until midnight.</p>\r\n<p>\"We have amazing brunch that has been really cool and unexpected. On a Friday night you can typically expect music - definitely hip-hop, definitely a little bit louder,\" said Taha.</p>\r\n<p>\"But on Wednesdays, we\'ve got a nice trivia night. If you want to do a Tinder date on a Monday and listen to some mellow live jazz, you can do that too,\" he added. \"It\'s like an array of different events. We\'re not just a hip-hop, or jazz, or a trivia spot. There\'s a little bit of everything for everyone.\"</p>\r\n<p>Its simple and creative layout accompanied by a spacious outdoor area in the back, give the place a cool, chilled vibe that is perfect for those who are looking for a fun, yet relaxing night out.</p>\r\n<p>The space also offers a perfect working environment during the day, with plug points provided at almost every seating options available.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div><img title=\"Outpost Recommends: Father Knows Best (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Recommends/20180228_122731_1519933177839.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Recommends: Father Knows Best (Image-3)\" /> Chris Taha, Co-Founder of Father Knows Best</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\"Our plans for the future is to stay as involved in the community as possible, and to keep inspiring creativity and collaborations between our neighbors,\" said Taha.</p>\r\n<p>\"So we (also) hold fundraisers for the local schools, free yoga in the backyard, and we even offered free art classes for kids, on the weekends last summer.\"</p>\r\n<p>Check out the different events that are going on at Father Knows Best every night, as well as its menu, by visiting <a href=\"http://www.fathersbk.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.fathersbk.com</a>.</p>\r\n<p>While you&rsquo;re at it, be sure to follow us on our <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/outpostclubNY/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Facebook</a> and <a href=\"https://bit.ly/2yKHwih\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Instagram</a>!</p>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/p0CTcu27htI?wmode=opaque&amp;enablejsapi=1\" width=\"100%\" height=\"400px\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Recommends: Father Knows Best (Image-4), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Recommends/20180228_125843_1519934246181.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Recommends: Father Knows Best (Image-4)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Recommends: Father Knows Best (Image-5), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Recommends/20180228_130322_1519933883321.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Recommends: Father Knows Best (Image-5)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Recommends: Father Knows Best (Image-6), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Recommends/20180228_130353_1519934614017.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Recommends: Father Knows Best (Image-6)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Recommends: Father Knows Best (Image-7), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Recommends/20180228_130645_1519933521050.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Recommends: Father Knows Best (Image-7)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Recommends: Father Knows Best (Image-8), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Recommends/20180228_130823_1519933685277.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Recommends: Father Knows Best (Image-8)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Recommends: Father Knows Best (Image-9), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Recommends/20180301_134641_1519931724111.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Recommends: Father Knows Best (Image-9)\" /></p>\r\n</div>', '20180301_134900_1519931136308-1.jpg', 1, '2018-03-05 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(102, 'Saturday Night Latin Fever With Outpost Club', 1, 'saturday-night-latin-fever-with-outpost-club', '', 'Saturday Night Latin Fever With Outpost Club', 'Saturday Night Latin Fever With Outpost Club', 'Saturday Night Latin Fever With Outpost Club', '<p>\"What kind of activities are you interested in?\"</p>', '<p>\"What kind of activities are you interested in?\"</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div><img title=\"Saturday Night Latin Fever With Outpost Club (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Saturday_Night/IMG_20180303_212559869_BURST000_COVER_TOP.jpg\" alt=\"Saturday Night Latin Fever With Outpost Club (Image-1)\" /> Outpost Club members learning how to salsa!</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>This is a question we often ask our members&nbsp;because ultimately, organizing events that can strengthen the sense of community among them is our utmost priority.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Over the course of last week their answers had unanimously been \"a dance class\". So that\'s exactly what we provided them with: a free salsa lesson.</p>\r\n<p>\"<strong>A lot of members were asking for dance classes,\"</strong> said <a href=\"../\" rel=\"nofollow\">Outpost</a>\'s community manager Tacia Duarte.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\"And I know some of the members from the Bushwick House&nbsp;have been going to salsa parties. So I thought it would be a good idea to combine the two,\" she added.</p>\r\n<p>After about a week of planning, the amazing team we have at Outpost successfully secured our members a free hour-long salsa lesson that took place at <strong>Club Cache</strong>&nbsp;last Saturday night.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div><img title=\"Saturday Night Latin Fever With Outpost Club (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Saturday_Night/img-47.jpg\" alt=\"Saturday Night Latin Fever With Outpost Club (Image-2)\" /> The post-class salsa dance party :)</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>This was followed by an all-night Latin dance party where our members got to put what they learned into practice!</p>\r\n<p>\"Most members wanted to dance but they didn\'t know how to. So the class was a good excuse to make people go, even if they don\'t know how to dance,\" said Tacia.</p>\r\n<p>16 members joined us, making the night another one to be remembered.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\"It was good to do something different with the people you see every day,\" said Tacia. \"And we had a lot of fun!\"</p>\r\n<p>The fun was definitely reflected on their faces, as you can see from the photos we took of the party. So go and check them out! Who knows, soon it might be <a href=\"../join-us\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">you</a>&nbsp;in the pictures.</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><img title=\"Saturday Night Latin Fever With Outpost Club (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Saturday_Night/IMG_20180303_211807505.jpg\" alt=\"Saturday Night Latin Fever With Outpost Club (Image-3)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Saturday Night Latin Fever With Outpost Club (Image-4), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Saturday_Night/IMG_20180303_221928981_1520274041772(1).jpg\" alt=\"Saturday Night Latin Fever With Outpost Club (Image-4)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Saturday Night Latin Fever With Outpost Club (Image-5), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Saturday_Night/IMG_20180303_212551244.jpg\" alt=\"Saturday Night Latin Fever With Outpost Club (Image-5)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Saturday Night Latin Fever With Outpost Club (Image-6), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Saturday_Night/IMG_20180303_222913413_1520278068853.jpg\" alt=\"Saturday Night Latin Fever With Outpost Club (Image-6)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Saturday Night Latin Fever With Outpost Club (Image-7), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Saturday_Night/IMG_20180303_212554353.jpg\" alt=\"Saturday Night Latin Fever With Outpost Club (Image-7)\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Saturday Night Latin Fever With Outpost Club (Image-8), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Saturday_Night/IMG_20180303_212609293.jpg\" alt=\"Saturday Night Latin Fever With Outpost Club (Image-8)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Saturday Night Latin Fever With Outpost Club (Image-9), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Saturday_Night/IMG_20180303_224309439_1520276670645.jpg\" alt=\"Saturday Night Latin Fever With Outpost Club (Image-9)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Saturday Night Latin Fever With Outpost Club (Image-10), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Saturday_Night/IMG_20180303_224339298_1520279666691(1).jpg\" alt=\"Saturday Night Latin Fever With Outpost Club (Image-10)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Saturday Night Latin Fever With Outpost Club (Image-11), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Saturday_Night/IMG_20180303_224509107_1520274613115.jpg\" alt=\"Saturday Night Latin Fever With Outpost Club (Image-11)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Saturday Night Latin Fever With Outpost Club (Image-12), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Saturday_Night/IMG_20180303_224512522_BURST000_COVER-1.jpg\" alt=\"Saturday Night Latin Fever With Outpost Club (Image-12)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Saturday Night Latin Fever With Outpost Club (Image-13), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Saturday_Night/IMG_20180303_225133729_1520273722889(1).jpg\" alt=\"Saturday Night Latin Fever With Outpost Club (Image-13)\" /></p>\r\n</div>', 'IMG_20180303_212559869_BURST000_COVER_TOP.jpg', 1, '2018-03-06 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(103, 'Last Weekend @ Outpost', 1, 'last-weekend--outpost', 'outpost-blog/blog-outpost-club/2018/4/10/last-weekend-outpost', 'Last Weekend @ Outpost', 'Last Weekend @ Outpost', 'New York City offers a variety of exciting activities, especially now that spring has arrived. Most people, however, miss out on all these fun because they have no one to experience them with.', '<p>Last Weekend @ Outpost</p>', '<p>New York City offers a variety of exciting activities, especially now that spring has arrived. Most people, however, miss out on all these fun because they have no one to experience them with.</p>\r\n<p>This is something our members never have to worry about.</p>\r\n<p>Last weekend they got the opportunity to have fun flexing both their mental and physical muscles in the company of the friends they\'ve made at <a href=\"../\" target=\"_blank\">Outpost Club</a>.</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Last Weekend @ Outpost (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Last_Weekend/20180406_222100-1_1523381483509.jpg\" alt=\"Last Weekend @ Outpost (Image-1)\" /></p>\r\n<p>It started on Friday night when they joined forces to make their way out of the Escape Room. As always, the event was planned a couple of weeks ahead, giving our members ample time to prepare themselves for the exciting challenges awaited them.</p>\r\n<p>Our amazing team here even managed to secure a good deal for our members. Tickets that normally cost $30 were made available at just $16!</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;We have to solve puzzles to get as much objects as we can within an hour. They accumulate points (millions of $),&rdquo; said Oscar Ochoa, a member of our Bushwick House who participated in the event. &ldquo;We managed to get 39 points = $39 million. Which is pretty good... if it was actual dollars.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>The next day they gathered again to kick some butts (some had their butts kicked) at International Pillow Fight Day held in Washington Square Park.</p>\r\n<p>They sure broke some sweat running away from the children who we have to say, were pretty aggressive when armed with a pillow.</p>\r\n<p>Just look at the pictures to see how our members suffered in their hands!</p>\r\n<p>After the \"workout\", they headed to our Knickerbocker House for some pizza and a relaxing couple hours of Fight Club.</p>\r\n<p>Now doesn\'t that sound like a great and memorable weekend?</p>\r\n<p>If you want to be part of the fun, come live with us!</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><img title=\"Last Weekend @ Outpost (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Last_Weekend/20180407_161648_1523138801743.jpg\" alt=\"Last Weekend @ Outpost (Image-2)\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Last Weekend @ Outpost (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Last_Weekend/20180407_161658_1523137495748.jpg\" alt=\"Last Weekend @ Outpost (Image-3)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Last Weekend @ Outpost (Image-4), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Last_Weekend/20180407_163807_1523137883299.jpg\" alt=\"Last Weekend @ Outpost (Image-4)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Last Weekend @ Outpost (Image-5), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Last_Weekend/20180407_164035_1523139178186.jpg\" alt=\"Last Weekend @ Outpost (Image-5)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Last Weekend @ Outpost (Image-6), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Last_Weekend/20180407_164048_1523139034660.jpg\" alt=\"Last Weekend @ Outpost (Image-6)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Last Weekend @ Outpost (Image-7), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Last_Weekend/20180407_165623_1523238683915.jpg\" alt=\"Last Weekend @ Outpost (Image-7)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Last Weekend @ Outpost (Image-8), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Last_Weekend/20180407_170337_1523138701756.jpg\" alt=\"Last Weekend @ Outpost (Image-8)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Last Weekend @ Outpost (Image-9), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Last_Weekend/received_10156132127805242_1523241730601-1.jpg\" alt=\"Last Weekend @ Outpost (Image-9)\" /></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>Facebook: <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/outpostclubNY/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Outpost Club</a></p>\r\n<p>Instagram: <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/outpostcoliving\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Outpost_Club</a></p>', '20180406_222100-1_1523381483509.jpg', 1, '2018-04-09 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0);
