(104, 'The Flatbush House Neighborhood Guide', 1, 'the-flatbush-house-neighborhood-guide', '', 'The Flatbush House Neighborhood Guide', 'The Flatbush House Neighborhood Guide', 'The Flatbush House Neighborhood Guide', '<p>If you&rsquo;re new to the area, we understand how tough that can be. We have members coming from all over the world and many of them at the start didn&rsquo;t know much about America, let alone the bustling.</p>', '<h3><em><strong>If you&rsquo;re new to the area, we understand how tough that can be. We have members coming from all over the world and many of them at the start didn&rsquo;t know much about America, let alone the bustling neighbourhood of Flatbush! Let us help you with some of the basics, so you can start exploring the neighborhood almost immediately.</strong></em></h3>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h2><strong>Subway/Travel</strong></h2>\r\n<p><strong>It\'s really up to you, but here are the main ways to get to Manhattan!</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>The 2 and the 5 Train - Beverly Rd.</h3>\r\n<p>The 2-train and the 5-train are right around the corner, just a-minute walk from the House. They will take you to Manhattan in 30 minutes. To get there, just step out of the House, turn left immediately, and walk straight on. You can&rsquo;t miss it!</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Flatbush House - walk: 1 minute; bike: 1 minute</strong></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h2><strong>Gym</strong></h2>\r\n<p><strong>Having a tough time finding a gym that suits your physical need? Here are some nearby our Knickerbocker House that you can check out.</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"The Flatbush House Neighborhood Guide (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/The_Flatbush_House/20180408_194213_1523280844312.jpg\" alt=\"The Flatbush House Neighborhood Guide (Image-1)\" /></p>\r\n<h3>Crunch Flatbush - 1038 Flatbush Avenue, Brooklyn.&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>The basic membership at Crunch will cost you only $10 per month. With just $10 extra, you will also get access to group fitness classes and live video workouts!</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Flatbush House - walk: 12 minutes; bike: 4 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>24-Hour Fitness - 2163 Tilden Avenue, Brooklyn.&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>24-Hour Fitness knows that for some, taking the first step towards a healthy lifestyle is the hardest. So it provides a community instead of a boot camp-like gym. Here you can take your own time and workout at your own pace, with experts ready to support you at all times. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Flatbush House - walk: 11 minutes; bike: 3 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Blink Fitness - 833 Flatbush Ave, Brooklyn.</h3>\r\n<p>Blink promises more than just a fit physique. It offers a community that will work with you to achieve your fitness goal.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Flatbush House - walk: 19 minutes; bike: 6 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Ditmas Park Yoga Society - East 19th Street, Brooklyn.&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>You don\'t need experience to start learning yoga here. All you need is discipline and you\'re all set! They also provide a traditional yet progressive form of hands-on Chinese massage therapy.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Flatbush House - walk: 14 minutes; bike: 5 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h2><strong>Coffee shops</strong></h2>\r\n<p><strong>Need your morning fix? Check out these places, hand-picked just for you.</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Dunkin Donuts - 1467 Nostrand Ave, Brooklyn.&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>Head here for a quick coffee and breakfast before work. It\'s just a few minutes&rsquo; walk from the House, and for just a few dollars, you\'d be set for the rest of the morning.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Flatbush House - walk: 7 minutes; bike: 4 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"The Flatbush House Neighborhood Guide (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/The_Flatbush_House/img-7.jpg\" alt=\"The Flatbush House Neighborhood Guide (Image-2)\" /></p>\r\n<h3>Taste the Tropics - 1839 Nostrand Ave, Brooklyn.&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>Get a taste of the tropical islands with Taste of Tropics&rsquo; ice creams. It would be especially perfect on warm sunny days!</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Flatbush House - bus: 5 minutes; walk: 6 minutes; bike: 2 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3>El Ranchito Poblano - 1228 Flatbush Ave, Brooklyn.&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>This small restaurant serves authentic Mexican and American food. You can expect a full American breakfast here for just under $5.</p>\r\n<p>They also have a coffee bar where a Fresh Roast Arabica Coffee will only costs you $1.50.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Flatbush House - bus: 10 minutes; train: 11 minutes; walk: 14 minutes; bike: 5 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h2><strong>Food</strong></h2>\r\n<p><strong>The neighborhood offers an unlimited variety of eateries at affordable prices. Here are a few that we recommend, based on the input provided by our former and current members.</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Tastee Pattee - 3122 Church Ave, Brooklyn.&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>Head over to Tastee Pattee if you want authentic and affordable Jamaican food. This spot is always packed and we&rsquo;re not surprised. It&rsquo;s worth the wait!</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Flatbush House - walk: 10 minutes; bike: 3 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"The Flatbush House Neighborhood Guide (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/The_Flatbush_House/20180408_193833_1523276849575.jpg\" alt=\"The Flatbush House Neighborhood Guide (Image-3)\" /></p>\r\n<h3>Island Express - 998 Flatbush Ave, Brooklyn.&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>This establishment is simple, affordable, and perfect for those who are on a tight budget but craving for good food. It serves Caribbean food made only with fresh ingredients.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Flatbush House - walk: 12 minutes; bike: 4 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>ZuriLee Restaurant - 755 Flatbush Ave, Brooklyn.&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>Who doesn\'t love pizza? We know our members do, especially when accompanied by a good movie and even better friends. So try something different with ZuriLee&rsquo;s Caribbean pizzas!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>The Farm on Adderly - 1108 Cortelyou Rd, Brooklyn.&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>Every neighborhood should provide a spot that is perfect for first dates. In Flatbush, it\'s the rustic farm-to-table Farm on Adderly.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Flatbush House - bus: 22 minutes; walk: 23 minutes; bike: 7 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h2><strong>Nightlife</strong></h2>\r\n<p><strong>If you don&rsquo;t want to spend the night in, head to these joints that are no more than 20 minutes&rsquo; walk from the house</strong></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"The Flatbush House Neighborhood Guide (Image-4), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/The_Flatbush_House/20180408_184023_1523368999433.jpg\" alt=\"The Flatbush House Neighborhood Guide (Image-4)\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Hookah Lounge - 1744 Nostrand Ave, Brooklyn.&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>This lounge is located just a couple minutes&rsquo; walk from the House. So if you\'re bored staying in all night, grab a couple of your housemates and hang here instead.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Flatbush House - walk: 2 minutes; bike: 1 minute</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"The Flatbush House Neighborhood Guide (Image-5), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/The_Flatbush_House/20180408_185933_1523276753216.jpg\" alt=\"The Flatbush House Neighborhood Guide (Image-5)\" /></p>\r\n<h3>FIB Tattoo Bar - 1051 Flatbush Ave, Brooklyn.&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3>FIB Tattoo Bar takes pride in being the first tattoo bar in Brooklyn. It also specializes in cocktails and mix drinks that change according to the season.</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Flatbush House - walk: 11 minutes; bike: 4 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"The Flatbush House Neighborhood Guide (Image-6), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/The_Flatbush_House/20180408_184918_1523276549882.jpg\" alt=\"The Flatbush House Neighborhood Guide (Image-6)\" /></p>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3>Sycamore Flower Shop and Bar - 1118 Cortelyou Rd, Brooklyn.&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>We highly recommend this bar for a first date. It combines a flower shop and a bar. Check out the backyard which is beautiful during the day, and even better at night.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Flatbush House - bus: 29 minutes; walk: 22 minutes; bike: 7 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Sip Unwine - 1197 Flatbush Ave, Brooklyn.&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>Sip and unwind from a long week of work at this bar. They offer great cocktails at great prices. Be sure to check out the snacks available here too!</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Flatbush House - bus: 11 minutes; walk: 15 minutes; bike: 5 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><img title=\"The Flatbush House Neighborhood Guide (Image-7), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/The_Flatbush_House/20180408_194129_1523368878632.jpg\" alt=\"The Flatbush House Neighborhood Guide (Image-7)\" /></p>\r\n<h2><strong>Other Fun Stuff</strong></h2>\r\n<p><strong>Want go out but don\'t want to leave flatbush, Don\'t worry! There are things to do!</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Kings Theater -&nbsp;1027 Flatbush Ave, Brooklyn, NY 11226.&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>Looking to go out to a premire event? There are some great shows, concerts, and conventions at Kings Theater!</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Flatbush House - walk: 12 mintues; Bike 5 mins</strong></p>\r\n<h2>&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h2><strong>Parks</strong></h2>\r\n<p><strong>There are several parks close by, inviting you to jog, work outside or temporarily escape from city life.</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"The Flatbush House Neighborhood Guide (Image-8), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/The_Flatbush_House/prospectpark-e1497909025369.jpg\" alt=\"The Flatbush House Neighborhood Guide (Image-8)\" /></p>\r\n<h3>Prospect Park - Brooklyn.&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>This place is perfect if you want to escape the city for a moment. Grab a bike and ride around the park a couple times, it\'s serene. On Sunday\'s during the summer Prospect Park Hosts the the Smorgasburg,&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Flatbush House - bus: 29 minutes; train: 25 minutes; walk: 27 minutes; bike: 18 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Paerdegat Park - 706 E 40th St, Brooklyn.&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Flatbush House - bus: 16 minutes; walk: 21 minutes; bike: 6 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Nostrand Park - 3002 Foster Ave, Brooklyn.&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Flatbush House - walk: 11 minutes; bike: 3 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h2><strong>Groceries</strong></h2>\r\n<p><strong>Looking to grab quick groceries? There are plenty of options you can pick from, but we have narrowed them down to a few that suit your every need.</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Salman Deli - 2918 Beverley Rd, Brooklyn.&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Flatbush House - walk: 1 minute; bike: 1 minute</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>El Duende - 1053 Rogers Ave, Brooklyn.&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Flatbush House - walk: 4 minutes; bike: 2 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>GNR Grocery Corp. - 2709 Avenue D, Brooklyn.</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Flatbush House - walk: 9 minutes; bike: 3 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Flatbush Caton Market - 2184 Clarendon Rd, Brooklyn.&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Flatbush House - walk: 11 minutes; bike: 3 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Dollar Tree - 1183 Flatbush Ave, Brooklyn.&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Flatbush House - walk: 14 minutes; bike: 5 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>JS Flatbush Farm - 1124 Flatbush Ave, Brooklyn.</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Flatbush House - walk: 12 minutes; bike: 4 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>KP Farm market - 1887 Nostrand Ave, Brooklyn.&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Flatbush House - walk: 8 minutes; bike: 2 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Key Food - 1905 Nostrand Ave, Brooklyn.&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Flatbush House - walk: 9 minutes; bike: 3 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h2><strong>Post office</strong></h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>United States Postal Service - 1525 Newkirk Ave Ste 1.&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Flatbush House - bus: 19 minutes; train: 20 minutes; walk: 24 minutes; bike: 9 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>United States Postal Service - 2273 Church Ave, Brooklyn.&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Flatbush House - bus: 11 minutes; train: 11 minutes; walk: 15 minutes; bike: 5 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>United States Postal Service - 315 Empire Blvd, Brooklyn.&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Flatbush House - train: 9 minutes; walk: 27 minutes; bike: 12 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>United States Postal Service - 1284 Utica Ave, Brooklyn.&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Flatbush House - bus: 17 minutes; walk: 27 minutes; bike: 8 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3><em><strong>THAT\'S ALL FOR NOW! WE CONSIDER THIS A LIVING DOCUMENT, SO IF YOU HAVE ANY SUGGESTION OF PLACES TO ADD, OR TIPS FOR THE PLACES ALREADY ON THE LIST, LET US KNOW! YOU CAN COMMENT BELOW OR EMAIL US AT INFO@OUTPOST-CLUB.COM</strong></em></h3>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h2>&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '20180408_194213_1523280844312.jpg', 1, '2018-04-10 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(105, 'Member Profile Srishti Tewari', 1, 'member-profile-srishti-tewari', 'blog-outpost-club/2018/4/2/member-profile-srishti-tewari', 'Member Profile Srishti Tewari', 'Member Profile Srishti Tewari', 'Member Profile: Srishti Tewari', '<p>WELCOME TO OUR MEMBERS\' PROFILE SERIES, WHERE WE SHARE THE STORIES OF WHY THEY MOVED TO NYC, AND ALSO WHAT THEY LIKE ABOUT THEIR TIME HERE. THIS WEEK WE&rsquo;RE INTRODUCING YOU TO SRISHTI TEWARI WHO.</p>', '<h3><em>WELCOME TO OUR MEMBERS\' PROFILE SERIES, WHERE WE SHARE THE STORIES OF WHY THEY MOVED TO NYC, AND ALSO WHAT THEY LIKE ABOUT THEIR TIME HERE. THIS WEEK WE&rsquo;RE INTRODUCING YOU TO SRISHTI TEWARI WHO STAYED WITH US AT OUR KNICKERBOCKER HOUSE. </em><img title=\"Member Profile Srishti Tewari (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Member_Srishti_Tewari/img-38.jpg\" alt=\"Member Profile Srishti Tewari (Image-1)\" /></h3>\r\n<p><strong>Tell us a little about yourself</strong></p>\r\n<p>I\'m an intern who love to travel. So when I found out that I\'d get to travel through my internship, it was just perfect. I love music too, mostly Bollywood. I\'m also immigrant. I came to America 6 years ago and since then, I\'ve been on different adventures of exploring new places, people, and myself.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What are the 5 fun things we should know about you?</strong></p>\r\n<p>I love to sing and dance. I\'m down to travel anywhere and anytime. I love long walks, and I can talk about almost anything. I can whistle to any song. That\'s pretty fun.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What brought you to NYC?</strong></p>\r\n<p>One of my rotation sites happens to be in Brooklyn. Thankfully, I accepted it. Because even though it was my first time in a big city, I love every single bit of it.<br />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Member Profile Srishti Tewari (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Member_Srishti_Tewari/20180214_191410_1518719625798.jpg\" alt=\"Member Profile Srishti Tewari (Image-2)\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>What have been your best experiences here?</strong></p>\r\n<p>It was definitely visiting the museums, or anything to do with walking on the streets of Manhattan. I love the vibrant, buzzing, busy streets with totally mesmerizing buildings. Above all, I felt a sense of belonging in the city.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What do you think of coliving?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Prior to living at the Knickerbocker House, I was suspicious of the coliving system. But in reality it worked our better for me since I got to be friends with my lovely housemates, who I got to explore the city with.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What\'s been your best experience in the time you have stayed with Outpost?</strong></p>\r\n<p>It was my last day in NYC. Everyone came to the house to meet me. It showed that the friendship I formed with the housemates is so genuine and authentic. <br />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Facebook: SRISHTI TEWARI and <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/outpostclubNY/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Outpost Club </a><br />Instagram: Srishti Tewari and <a href=\"https://bit.ly/2yKHwih\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">@outpostcoliving</a></p>', 'img-38.jpg', 1, '2018-04-01 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(106, 'The Knickerbocker House Neighborhood Guide', 1, 'the-knickerbocker-house-neighborhood-guide', '', 'The Knickerbocker House Neighborhood Guide', 'The Knickerbocker House Neighborhood Guide', 'The Knickerbocker House Neighborhood Guide', '<p>If you&rsquo;re new to the area, we understand how tough that can be. We have members coming from all over the world and many of them at the start didn&rsquo;t know much about America, let alone the lively.</p>', '<h3><em><strong>If you&rsquo;re new to the area, we understand how tough that can be. We have members coming from all over the world and many of them at the start didn&rsquo;t know much about America, let alone the lively neighborhood of Bushwick! Let us help you with some of the basics, so you can start exploring the neighborhood almost immediately.</strong></em></h3>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h2><strong>Subway/Travel</strong></h2>\r\n<p><strong>It\'s really up to you, but here are the main ways to get to Manhattan!</strong><br />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>The M train - Knickerbocker Ave</h3>\r\n<p>M train is a 2-minute walk from the house. Just make a right when you exit the house, a left on Knickerbocker Avenue, and walk until you see the Knickerbocker Ave stop. You can&rsquo;t miss it.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Knickerbocker House - walk: 2 minutes; bike: 1 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>The L Train - Dekalb Ave</h3>\r\n<p>The L Train is about a 5-minute walk from the house. Make a left when you walk out of the house, and walk two blocks to Wyckoff Ave. Make another left on Wyckoff and walk to Stockholm Street. The stop is called Dekalb Ave.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Knickerbocker House - walk: 5 minutes; bike: 2 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h2><strong>Gym</strong></h2>\r\n<p><strong>Having a tough time finding a gym that suits your physical need? Here are some nearby our Knickerbocker House that you can check out.</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"The Knickerbocker House Neighborhood Guide (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/The_Knickerbocker_House/20180331_162947_1522604413681.jpg\" alt=\"The Knickerbocker House Neighborhood Guide (Image-1)\" /></p>\r\n<h3>Blink Fitness Bushwick - 399 Knickerbocker Ave, Brooklyn</h3>\r\n<p>Blink Fitness\' membership begins at as low as $15 a month. But with it comes high-quality equipment, great music to set you in a workout mood, and plenty of room for a breather in between.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Knickerbocker House - walk: 1 minute; bike: 2 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Planet Fitness - 329 Wyckoff Ave, Ridgewood</h3>\r\n<p>You can become a member of Planet Fitness at just $10 a month. It also comes with free fitness training, and free WiFi access!</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Knickerbocker House - train: 8 minutes; bus: 8 minutes; walk: 12 minutes; bike: 4 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Gym X Boxing - 59 Malcolm X Blvd, Brooklyn</h3>\r\n<p>This gym is a little on the pricey side but with a monthly membership fee of $140, you will also get access to a personal fitness trainer 3 times per week.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Knickerbocker House - bus: 14 minutes; walk: 19 minutes; bike: 8 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h2><strong>Groceries</strong></h2>\r\n<p><strong>Looking to grab quick groceries? There are plenty of options you can pick from, but we have narrowed them down the major ones where you can get everything you need. &nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><img title=\"The Knickerbocker House Neighborhood Guide (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/The_Knickerbocker_House/20180331_181823_1522604765642.jpg\" alt=\"The Knickerbocker House Neighborhood Guide (Image-2)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"The Knickerbocker House Neighborhood Guide (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/The_Knickerbocker_House/20180331_183402_1522604873552.jpg\" alt=\"The Knickerbocker House Neighborhood Guide (Image-3)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"The Knickerbocker House Neighborhood Guide (Image-4), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/The_Knickerbocker_House/20180401_124127_1522601017720.jpg\" alt=\"The Knickerbocker House Neighborhood Guide (Image-4)\" /></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>City Fresh - 2401, 229 Knickerbocker Ave, Brooklyn</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Knickerbocker House - walk: 8 minutes; bike: 4 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Key Food - 72 - 80 Wyckoff Ave, Brooklyn</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Knickerbocker House - bus: 8 minutes; walk: 9 minutes; bike: 3 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Mr Lemon - 410 Knickerbocker Ave, Brooklyn</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Knickerbocker House - walk: 1 minute; bike: 1 minute</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Hi! Mango Natural Market - 341 Knickerbocker Ave, Brooklyn</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Knickerbocker House - walk: 4 minutes; bike: 2 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Great Land Deli - 290 Knickerbocker Ave, Brooklyn</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Knickerbocker House - walk: 6 minutes; bike: 3 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Angel&rsquo;s Fruit Market - 272 Knickerbocker Ave, Brooklyn</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Knickerbocker House - walk: 7 minutes; bike: 3 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h2><strong>Coffee shops</strong></h2>\r\n<p><strong>Need your morning fix? Check out these places, hand-picked just for you.</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"The Knickerbocker House Neighborhood Guide (Image-5), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/The_Knickerbocker_House/20180331_165819_1522601376925.jpg\" alt=\"The Knickerbocker House Neighborhood Guide (Image-5)\" /></p>\r\n<h3>Dweebs - 1434 Dekalb Ave, Brooklyn</h3>\r\n<p>Ny.eater.com listed Dweebs as one of <a href=\"https://ny.eater.com/maps/best-cafe-coffee-shop-new-york-city-brooklyn-queens/abbotsford-road\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">29 Outstanding Coffee Shops in NYC</a>, and we agree. It also has a patio with wooden chairs facing the street that are great for people-watching.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Knickerbocker House - walk: 5 minutes; bike: 3 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"The Knickerbocker House Neighborhood Guide (Image-6), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/The_Knickerbocker_House/img-10.jpg\" alt=\"The Knickerbocker House Neighborhood Guide (Image-6)\" /></p>\r\n<h3>Variety Coffee Roaster - 146 Wyckoff Ave, Brooklyn</h3>\r\n<p>Grubstreet.com listed Variety Coffee Roster as one of the \"absolute best lattes in New York\". This cafe is also listed as one of the 10 Best Places to Drink Coffee in NYC.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Knickerbocker House - walk: 5 minutes; bike: 2 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3>Kave Espresso Bar - 119 Knickerbocker Ave, Brooklyn</h3>\r\n<p>Kave serves organic espresso beverages, coffee, tea, and all sorts of baked goods. It also has a garden patio and free Wi-Fi. What else can one asks for??</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Knickerbocker House - walk: 13 minutes; bike: 5 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"The Knickerbocker House Neighborhood Guide (Image-7), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/The_Knickerbocker_House/img-19.jpg\" alt=\"The Knickerbocker House Neighborhood Guide (Image-7)\" /></p>\r\n<h3>Molasses Books - 770 Hart St, Brooklyn</h3>\r\n<p>Molasses Books functions as a used bookstore, a cafe, and a bar. It might be a tad small, but its atmosphere and interior design makes for a perfect spot to just chill and read.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Knickerbocker House - walk: 6 minutes; bike: 3 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Foster Sundry - 215 Knickerbocker Ave, Brooklyn</h3>\r\n<p>Foster Sundry is a specialty grocery that is also popular for its food, coffee and draft beers. Try out the cheeses available here. They have a wide variety of American and European artisan cheeses that are made by \"real people, on real farms\".</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Knickerbocker House - walk: 9 minutes; bike: 4 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"The Knickerbocker House Neighborhood Guide (Image-8), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/The_Knickerbocker_House/20180331_193530_1522600472408.jpg\" alt=\"The Knickerbocker House Neighborhood Guide (Image-8)\" /></p>\r\n<h3>Bushwick Public House - 1288 Myrtle Ave, Brooklyn</h3>\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s a coffee shop by day and a chilled bar by night. This spot also has a basement that serves as a dance floor!</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Knickerbocker House - walk: 7 minutes; bike: 3 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h2><strong>Food</strong></h2>\r\n<p><strong>The neighborhood offers an unlimited variety of eateries at affordable prices. Here are a few that we recommend, based on the input provided by our former and current members.</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"The Knickerbocker House Neighborhood Guide (Image-9), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/The_Knickerbocker_House/20180331_165421_1522601182379.jpg\" alt=\"The Knickerbocker House Neighborhood Guide (Image-9)\" /></p>\r\n<h3>Knickerbocker Bagel -&nbsp;367 Knickerbocker Ave, Brooklyn, NY 11237</h3>\r\n<p>We highly recommend this spot for a hearty breakfast. Knickerbocker Bagel offers a wide array of delicacies but the restaurant\'s specialty has got to be its bagels and cream cheese.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Knickerbocker House - walk: 2 minutes; bike: 2 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Le Garage - 157 Suydam St</h3>\r\n<p>Craving a good, authentic French food and experience? Then head to Le Garage, a restaurant run by French mother and daughter duo.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Knickerbocker House - walk: 10 minutes; bike: 5 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Archie\'s Bar &amp; Pizza - 128 Central Ave</h3>\r\n<p>Archie&rsquo;s is on Thrillist&rsquo;s <a href=\"https://www.thrillist.com/eat/new-york/best-bushwick-restaurants-brooklyn\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Best Bushwick Restaurant</a> list for a reason. The pizzas served here come with thick crusts and drooping with tasty toppings. It also has more of a bar-vibe than the typical family-friendly that is often associated with pizza hubs.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Knickerbocker House - walk: 12 minutes; bike: 6 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Syndicated Bar Theater Kitchen - 40 Bogart St</h3>\r\n<p>Restaurant + bar + movie theater = a perfect spot for a day out and a date</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Knickerbocker House - train: 12 minutes; bus: 11 minutes; walk: 18 minutes; bike: 7 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Heavy Woods - 50 Wyckoff Ave</h3>\r\n<p>This is the place to go if you want to enjoy authentic Cajun food in a cozy and relaxed environment. The service here is great too!</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Knickerbocker House - walk: 10 minutes; bike: 3 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"The Knickerbocker House Neighborhood Guide (Image-10), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/The_Knickerbocker_House/img-37.jpg\" alt=\"The Knickerbocker House Neighborhood Guide (Image-10)\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Ali&rsquo;s - 280 Knickerbocker Ave, Brooklyn</h3>\r\n<p>Ali&rsquo;s serves delicious home-cooked Lebanese cuisines made with natural chicken, Angus beef, and American lamb. Head here if you&rsquo;re craving for some mediterranean dishes!</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Knickerbocker House - walk: 6 minutes; bike: 3 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h2><strong>Nightlife</strong></h2>\r\n<p><strong>If you don&rsquo;t want to spend the night in, head to these joints that are no more than 20 minutes&rsquo; walk from the house</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Darlings - 242 Himrod St</h3>\r\n<p>Darlings is a cozy bar just near the house. You can come here to watch sports and drink some beers with your friends, or be entertained by local DJs at night. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Knickerbocker House - walk: 1 minute; bike: 1 minute</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"The Knickerbocker House Neighborhood Guide (Image-11), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/The_Knickerbocker_House/20180331_190804_1522602346221.jpg\" alt=\"The Knickerbocker House Neighborhood Guide (Image-11)\" /></p>\r\n<h3>Sally Roots - 195 Wyckoff Ave</h3>\r\n<p>This is a great spot for a casual night out with your friends. Be sure to check out the backyard which we must say, is pretty sweet.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Knickerbocker House - walk: 6 minutes; bike: 2 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Old Stanley\'s Bar - 226 Wyckoff Ave</h3>\r\n<p>Go back to basic at Old Stanley\'s where you can sit back, play a couple of rounds of pinball, and darts while enjoying a pint of beer with chicken wings or some hotdog.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Knickerbocker House - walk: 9 minutes; bike: 3 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"The Knickerbocker House Neighborhood Guide (Image-12), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/The_Knickerbocker_House/20180331_191923_1522603595605.jpg\" alt=\"The Knickerbocker House Neighborhood Guide (Image-12)\" /></p>\r\n<h3>Dromedary Urban Tiki Bar - 266 Irving Ave</h3>\r\n<p>Try out Dromedary&rsquo;s tiki-style cocktails while enjoying its monthly burlesque shows, comedy skits, live music, and weekly trivia, among many other fun activities this place organizes.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Knickerbocker House - walk: 6 minutes; bike: 1 minute</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Elmekkah Bar and Grill - 277 Wyckoff Ave</h3>\r\n<p>Elmekkah is a spacious lounge popular among hookah lovers. It\'s also a nice place to go dancing with DJs spinning every weekend, and visitors encouraged to make every space in the lounge a dance floor.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Knickerbocker House - walk: 10 minutes; bike: 3 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Mood Ring - 1260 Myrtle Ave</h3>\r\n<p>Mood Ring is interesting for its unique astrology theme. Everything from its cocktail to its dance floor are based, and are constantly changing in line with the 12 horoscope signs.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Knickerbocker House - walk: 10 minutes; bike: 4 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><strong>Parks</strong></h2>\r\n<p><strong>One thing we love about this neighborhood is how it is surrounded by parks. If you ever need to wind down from a stressful day, a simple 20-30 minutes around the various parks here would definitely do the magic.</strong></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"The Knickerbocker House Neighborhood Guide (Image-13), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/The_Knickerbocker_House/20180331_183947_1522604057715.jpg\" alt=\"The Knickerbocker House Neighborhood Guide (Image-13)\" /></p>\r\n<h3>Maria Hernandez Park - Knickerbocker Ave &amp; Starr St, Brooklyn</h3>\r\n<p>We absolutely love this park. It has corners for sports and benches where you can just sit, relax with a book, or enjoy the sights around you. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Knickerbocker House - walk: 8 minutes; bike: 5 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><strong>Post office</strong></h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>United States Postal Service - 86 Wyckoff Ave, Brooklyn</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Knickerbocker House - bus: 7 minutes; walk: 8 minutes; bike: 3 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>United States Postal Service - 1369 Broadway, Brooklyn</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Distance from the Knickerbocker House - bus: 16 minutes; walk: 21 minutes; bike: 8 minutes</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><em><strong>THAT\'S ALL FOR NOW! WE CONSIDER THIS A LIVING DOCUMENT, SO IF YOU HAVE ANY SUGGESTION OF PLACES TO ADD, OR TIPS FOR THE PLACES ALREADY ON THE LIST, LET US KNOW! YOU CAN COMMENT BELOW OR EMAIL US AT INFO@OUTPOST-CLUB.COM</strong></em></h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '20180331_162947_1522604413681.jpg', 1, '2018-04-01 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(107, 'Helpful App for coliving - DownToDash', 1, 'helpful-app-for-coliving---downtodash', 'blog-outpost-club/2018/4/5/helpful-app-for-coliving-downtodash', 'Helpful App for coliving - DownToDash', 'Helpful App for coliving - DownToDash', 'A 2016 survey by the American Osteopathic Association found that 72% of more than 2000 Americans polled reported having felt a sense of loneliness. 31% of them experienced loneliness at the very', '<p>A 2016 survey by the American Osteopathic Association found that 72% of more than 2000 Americans polled reported having felt a sense of loneliness. 31% of them experienced loneliness at the very.</p>', '<p>A <a href=\"https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/survey-finds-nearly-three-quarters-72-of-americans-feel-lonely-300342742.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">2016 survey</a> by the American Osteopathic Association found that 72% of more than 2000 Americans polled reported having felt a sense of loneliness. 31% of them experienced loneliness at the very least, once a week.</p>\r\n<p>It doesn\'t help that making friends is especially challenging in a big city like New York, where everyone is always rushing somewhere trying to make ends meet.</p>\r\n<p>Then there are those with countless of friends, yet find it difficult to meet people with similar interests.</p>\r\n<p>Most of our members fall in either one of these categories, having moved to NYC with nothing but their suitcases.</p>\r\n<p>That\'s why this week <a href=\"../\" target=\"_blank\">we</a> have chosen <a href=\"http://downtodash.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">DownToDash</a> as our recommended app for co-living.</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Helpful App for coliving - DownToDash (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Helpful_App/img-29.jpg\" alt=\"Helpful App for coliving - DownToDash (Image-1)\" /></p>\r\n<p>DownToDash is a mobile app that connects people based on the activities they are interested in, like workouts, sports, food and travel, among many other things.</p>\r\n<p>Now it is helping Outpost Club attract more people to our community, and connecting our members to each other.</p>\r\n<p>Through this app, users can create a specific plan. For example, a game of basketball on Sunday, at 10am. Other users who are interested to participate in this activity will then opt to join.</p>\r\n<p>The app also allows users to discover events, classes and activities that are going on around them.</p>\r\n<p>While finding people of mutual interests is quite easy in a coliving setup that Outpost provides, having DownToDash at your fingertips can make your community activities even more interesting. The more the merrier, right?</p>\r\n<p>So be sure to give this app a go, and let us know what you think of it!</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Helpful App for coliving - DownToDash (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Helpful_App/img-49.jpg\" alt=\"Helpful App for coliving - DownToDash (Image-2)\" /></p>', 'img-29.jpg', 1, '2018-04-04 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0);
