(108, 'Outpost April Newsletter!', 1, 'outpost-april-newsletter', '', 'Outpost April Newsletter!', 'Outpost April Newsletter!', 'Hello again everyone at the Outpost Club!', '<p>Hello again everyone at the Outpost Club!</p>', '<p>Hello again everyone at the Outpost Club!</p>\r\n<p>In this month\'s newsletters, we have summarized what has been going on throughout the month here at Outpost.</p>\r\n<p>We have also included other information that may be of interest to you, like the events going on in the coming month, as well as movies and Netflix show recommendations.</p>\r\n<p>So read on for more of this!</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>What&rsquo;s New At OutposT</h3>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost April Newsletter! (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_April/Screen%2BShot%2B2018-03-26%2Bat%2B16_03_11_png_11.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost April Newsletter! (Image-1)\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>New Partnerships!</strong></p>\r\n<p>Outpost gains a new partner for all our members! This partnership with <a href=\"https://bklyncommons.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">BKLYN Commons</a> will allow Outpost members a chance to work in a fully-equipped co-working spaces. Enjoy a 25% discount for the first two months of becoming a member of the ever-growing coworking community of entrepreneurs, small business owners, and remote employees.</p>\r\n<p>As a member of BKC, you&rsquo;ll have access to gorgeous workspaces, unique common areas, business-grade printers, flexible conference rooms, and numerous monthly networking events!</p>\r\n<p>State that you are an Outpost Club member in the \"How did you hear about us\" section when booking a tour to receive the discount!</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>App of the Month</h3>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost April Newsletter! (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_April/DTD%2Bhow%2Bit%2Bworks.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost April Newsletter! (Image-2)\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>DownToDash</strong></p>\r\n<p>72% of Americans suffer from loneliness. 88% of people who move into new cities find it difficult to make friends. There are also those with plenty of friends but still find it difficult to meet people with whom they can share specific activities.</p>\r\n<p>DownToDash has a solution for all of them! It is an app that connects people based on common activities, and now it is helping Outpost Club attract more people to our community, and connecting our members to each other..</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>Upcoming Events at Outpost Club&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>We know you\'ve loved all the events organized by, and for our members. And that\'s great! Because they were planned with one and only one aim: to make sure you feel like part of a community. So do join in the ones we have planned for you next. Maybe you\'ll end up making new best friends that can keep you company on your nights in, or party it up on your nights out!</p>\r\n<p>Find below the events you can look forward to this April:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost April Newsletter! (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_April/29570740_1667076893382742_4289782088049434799_n.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost April Newsletter! (Image-3)\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>Escape Room Party - April 6th</strong></p>\r\n<p>Imagine this: You\'re trapped in a room. But there with you are friends that can make you laugh your way out of any tense situation. Together you have to find a way out by solving a series of challenges in just 60 minutes.</p>\r\n<p>Sounds fun? We thought so too! That\'s why an escape room party is on our agenda for this month. So join Outpost Club\'s team and let\'s help each other escape the room in record-breaking time!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost April Newsletter! (Image-4), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_April/matthew-kane-94147-unsplash.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost April Newsletter! (Image-4)\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Yoga and Snacks at BedStuy House - April 14th</strong></p>\r\n<p>Get those body working and prepped for summer by joining us at the Yoga and Snacks evening planned for mid-April.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost April Newsletter! (Image-5), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_April/img-56.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost April Newsletter! (Image-5)\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>City Bike Ride - April 28th</strong></p>\r\n<p>Let\'s go biking around the city. Besides the opportunity to enjoy the beautiful sight of spring coming to live, you\'ll also get to have a laugh with your Outpost friends.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost April Newsletter! (Image-6), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_April/john-matychuk-491429-unsplash.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost April Newsletter! (Image-6)\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>School of Rock BBQ - April 28th</strong></p>\r\n<p>Enjoy the sun while being serenaded by a talented group of musicians from the School of Rock! Our own live band event? Check!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>If you\'re as excited as we are about these events, and you are a current or previous member<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/groups/outpostclub/events/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">!</a> Also stay tuned for additional information that will be shared in your respective houses\' Facebook group.</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>Events Coming to NYC</h3>\r\n<p>Are you looking for something fun to do around the city? If so, check out these events that we have compiled for you.</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost April Newsletter! (Image-7), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_April/30124536_1675969969160101_6170062232597037056_o.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost April Newsletter! (Image-7)\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>International Pillow Fight Day 2018</strong></p>\r\n<p>The annual <strong>International Pillow Fight Day</strong> is happening at 3pm this coming Saturday (April 7th)! Plan a day out with your Outpost friends and take the pillow fight out of the House and into the Washington Square Park.</p>\r\n<p>Be sure to bring your own pillow, but if you can\'t, just buy one at Mattress Firm&rsquo;s NoHo store for $5. Money from the pillow sales will go to Mattress Firm Foster Kids Program, to provide foster children with enriching learning opportunities.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost April Newsletter! (Image-8), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_April/jens-moser-572312-unsplash.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost April Newsletter! (Image-8)\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>Tribeca Film Festival</strong></p>\r\n<p>Robert De Niro and co.\'s annual Tribeca Film Festival is a must-to-do item if you\'re in New York. It casts a spotlight on local indie features, documentaries, and foreign films, among many others. The festival is taking place from April 18th to April 29th in Lower Manhattan.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost April Newsletter! (Image-9), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_April/26841358_1112309275577379_3417361768139703152_o.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost April Newsletter! (Image-9)\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>Sakura Matsuri Cherry Blossom Festival NYC</strong></p>\r\n<p>Celebrate Spring by soaking in the beauty of the rare cherry-blossom at the Sakura Matsuri Festival NYC. There are also nearly 60 Japanese-themed events and performances planned for the festival. It only runs for two days, from April 28th to the 29th, at Brooklyn Botanic Garden. A tickets costs $30, but you can get it for only $25 if you\'re a student.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost April Newsletter! (Image-10), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_April/588A2778.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost April Newsletter! (Image-10)\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>Brooklyn Folk Festival</strong></p>\r\n<p>The 10th Annual Brooklyn Folk Festival is taking place on April 6th to the 8th, featuring over 40 bands, workshops, and film screenings.</p>\r\n<p>If you\'re into folk and bluegrass music, this festival that will be held at St. Ann&rsquo;s Church, 157 Montague Street, Brooklyn, is perfect for you.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>Outpost Club Recommendation: Best Movies In Theatres&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>Movie lovers, there are a couple of new movies coming out next month. So let\'s make a plan for a day out at the cinema with your Outpost Club family! Also, save some bucks by getting unlimited entries at just $9.95 a month.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Avengers: Infinity War</strong><br />This latest installment of Marvel&rsquo;s Avengers has been described as the &ldquo;deadliest showdown of all time.&rdquo; So be sure to follow the Avengers in their quest to save the universe from Thanos.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Truth or Dare</strong><br />A popular drinking game takes a twisted turn in Blumhouse Production\'s Truth or Dare. The movie that is coming out on xxx follows a group of students haunted by an entity that won\'t let them stop playing, until all of them are dead. Will there be any survivor? Watch the movie to find out.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>I Feel Pretty</strong><br />Sometimes a little self-belief can change your whole outlook of the world. Follow Any Schumer on her journey of self-appreciation in I Feel Pretty.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>Outpost Club Recommendation: Best New Movies On Netflix</h3>\r\n<p>Sometimes it\'s nice just to sit back and relax after a long week of work. We get it. So why don\'t plan for a movie get-together at one of Outpost\'s houses? Get some popcorn, pizza, and soda, and enjoy an entertaining night-in with the other members. The more, the merrier! Here are some great movies that have received our thumbs up:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Se7en</strong></p>\r\n<p>Follow Detectives William Somerset and David Mills as they take on a serial killer who kills those representing each of the seven deadly sins.</p>\r\n<p>Morgan Freeman, Brad Pitt, Kevin Spacey, and Gwyneth Paltrow starred in this 90&rsquo;s blockbuster that now has its own cult following.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost April Newsletter! (Image-11), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_April/Scarface.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost April Newsletter! (Image-11)\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Scarface</strong></p>\r\n<p>Scarface, starring Al Pacino, is another movie that has become a cult classic.</p>\r\n<p>It tells the story of how Cuban refugee Tony Montana, who arrives in 1980s Miami, rises to become a powerful drug kingpin.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost April Newsletter! (Image-12), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_April/img-4.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost April Newsletter! (Image-12)\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Seven Pounds</strong></p>\r\n<p>Ben Thomas, played by Will Smith, is living with huge regret over a past mistake. To find redemption, he sets out to help save the lives of seven strangers by donating his organs to them. Complications arise when he falls in love with cardiac patient, Emily.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>How Was Your March At Outpost Club?</h3>\r\n<p>Now we\'ve covered what\'s in store for next month, let\'s revisit some of the great moments we\'ve shared this month.</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost April Newsletter! (Image-13), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_April/IMG_20180303_224339298_1520279666691.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost April Newsletter! (Image-13)\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Saturday Night Latin Fever With Outpost</strong></p>\r\n<p>We kicked of the month of March with an hour-long&nbsp;salsa lesson. This was followed by an all-night Latin dance party where our members got to put what they learned into practice.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost April Newsletter! (Image-14), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_April/20180310_170745_1520818350608-1.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost April Newsletter! (Image-14)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost April Newsletter! (Image-15), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_April/20180309_192542_1520784974146-1.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost April Newsletter! (Image-15)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost April Newsletter! (Image-16), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_April/20180310_165502_1520794073103.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost April Newsletter! (Image-16)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost April Newsletter! (Image-17), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_April/20180310_175119_1520824823127%2B(1)-1.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost April Newsletter! (Image-17)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost April Newsletter! (Image-18), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_April/20180310_175135_1520824716013-1.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost April Newsletter! (Image-18)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost April Newsletter! (Image-19), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_April/20180310_185016_1520824957231-1.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost April Newsletter! (Image-19)\" /></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p><strong>BBQ at Outpost</strong></p>\r\n<p>Outpost Club celebrated the last week of winter with a BBQ out in the backyard of our Bushwick House. Dozens of our present and former members showed up to mingle and enjoy the variety of homemade delicacies.</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost April Newsletter! (Image-20), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_April/20180320_212836_1521679462094.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost April Newsletter! (Image-20)\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Karaoke Night</strong></p>\r\n<p>We know how much our members love to sing. That\'s why we organized a karaoke night that gave our members a chance to showcase their singing talent in the company of their Outpost friends!</p>\r\n<p>We had also introduced three of our present and former members this month: Oose Koss, Giselle Carrozzi, and Srishti Tewari. Get to know them better by reading and sharing their stories.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3><em><strong>See You Again Next Month!</strong></em></h3>\r\n<p>We hope you have enjoyed our events as much as we did! Thank you for joining us and making them memorable. Don\'t fret if you had missed any of them. Just check out the articles and pictures of the events to have a feel of what they were like.</p>\r\n<p>Our goal is only truly achieved if we have made you feel like being at home during your stay with us. So we hope you will continue having a great time at Outpost Club!&nbsp;</p>', 'Screen.jpg', 1, '2018-04-05 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(109, 'Member Profile Marie Hurpeau', 1, 'member-profile-marie-hurpeau', 'blog-outpost-club/2018/4/9/kxek43k6hiia1bchr8pfiitb3yjxq9', 'Member Profile Marie Hurpeau', 'Member Profile Marie Hurpeau', 'Member Profile: Marie Hurpeau', '<p>WELCOME TO OUR MEMBERS\' PROFILE SERIES, WHERE WE SHARE THE STORIES OF WHY THEY MOVED TO NYC, AND ALSO WHAT THEY LIKE ABOUT THEIR TIME HERE. THIS WEEK WE&rsquo;RE INTRODUCING YOU TO MARIE WHO STAYED AT.</p>', '<h3><em>Welcome to our members\' profile series, where we share the stories of why they moved to NYC, and also what they like about their time here. This week we&rsquo;re introducing you to Marie who stayed at our Bushwick House. We hope you enjoy this article.&nbsp;</em></h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Member Profile Marie Hurpeau (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Member_Marie/20180407_165623_1523238683915-1.jpg\" alt=\"Member Profile Marie Hurpeau (Image-1)\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>Tell us a little about yourself</strong></p>\r\n<p>I&rsquo;m Marie, a French girl from Nancy, France. I came to NYC for an internship, in my last year of school. I work in television, like a journalist, and I write reports and magazine articles for a French channel!</p>\r\n<p><strong>What brought you to NYC?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Haha sorry for repeating. I came for an internship with Independent Production Society, for a French television channel.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What has been your best experience here?</strong></p>\r\n<p>For now, I think my best experience here is meeting different people with different cultures!</p>\r\n<p><strong>What do you think of coliving?</strong></p>\r\n<p>It is a pretty good experience when you arrive in a new city where you know nobody! With coliving it is easier to meet new friends, and feel good in a new place! It&rsquo;s like getting a new family!</p>\r\n<p><strong>What\'s been your best experience in the time you have stayed </strong><strong>with</strong><strong> Outpost?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Hmm.. I think it&rsquo;s the <a href=\"../blog/outpost-enjoys-the-sun-with-a-bbq-party\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">BBQ</a> in March. Because there were a lot of people with different personalities, and we ate really great food! But all the moments of co-living life were very good too, just having a simple time and enjoy!</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><img title=\"Member Profile Marie Hurpeau (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Member_Marie/20180310_165801_1520794164887.jpg\" alt=\"Member Profile Marie Hurpeau (Image-2)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Member Profile Marie Hurpeau (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Member_Marie/20180310_170735_1520818220951-2.jpg\" alt=\"Member Profile Marie Hurpeau (Image-3)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Member Profile Marie Hurpeau (Image-4), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Member_Marie/20180310_185016_1520824957231-2.jpg\" alt=\"Member Profile Marie Hurpeau (Image-4)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Member Profile Marie Hurpeau (Image-5), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Member_Marie/20180407_165623_1523238683915-1.jpg\" alt=\"Member Profile Marie Hurpeau (Image-5)\" /></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Facebook: Marie Hrp and <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/outpostclubNY/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Outpost Club</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Instagram: Marie Hrp and <a href=\"https://bit.ly/2yKHwih\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">@outpostcoliving</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '20180407_165623_1523238683915-1.jpg', 1, '2018-04-08 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(110, 'March events and movies in New York', 1, 'march-events-and-movies-in-new-york', 'blog-outpost-club/march-2018-events', 'March events and movies in New York', 'March events and movies in New York', 'Are you looking for something fun to do around the city in March 2018? If so, check out these events that we have compiled for you.', '<p>Are you looking for something fun to do around the city? If so, check out these events that we have compiled for you.</p>', '<h2>Upcoming Events in New York</h2>\r\n<p>Are you looking for something fun to do around the city? If so, check out these events that we have compiled for you.</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"March events and movies in New York (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/March_events/st-patricks-day-1.jpg\" alt=\"March events and movies in New York (Image-1)\" /></p>\r\n<h2>St. Patrick\'s Day</h2>\r\n<p>St. Patrick\'s Day is one if the not the most festive day in Ireland. It takes place every year on March 17, the date that marked the death of Saint Patrick, the foremost patron saint of Ireland.<br />The Irish are known to celebrate this day with massive parades.. and a whole day of drinking. But you don\'t have to travel all the way to Ireland to get a feel of the festivity. Just suit yourself up in green attire and join in the parade that will start at 11am. The participants will march up from the 44th Street all the way to the 79th Street. Along the way - on the 50th Street to be exact - you will get to see the St. Patrick\'s Cathedral. The parade is expected to end at 5.00pm, just about the time that happy hour starts!</p>\r\n<h2>Asia Week New York</h2>\r\n<p>The Asia Week New York is taking place from the 15th to the 24th of March. So be sure to spend a few days learning about the Asian art and culture at various museums, galleries, auction houses and cultural institutions around New York City. Participating venues are the Noguchi Museum, China Institute, Museum of Modern Art and the Rubin Museum of Art. Theme-related films, symposia, and tours - among many other activities - will also be held throughout the week. Check out the link below for the full schedule!<br /><a href=\"http://www.asiaweekny.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.asiaweekny.com</a>/&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>OUTPOST CLUB RECOMMENDATION</h2>\r\n<p>Movie lovers, there are a couple of new movies coming out next month. So let\'s make a plan for a day out at the cinema with your Outpost Club family! Also, save some bucks by getting unlimited entries at just $9.95 a month. You can do so by applying for a movie pass here:&nbsp; <a href=\"https://www.moviepass.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://www.moviepass.com/</a>.</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Death Wish</strong></h3>\r\n<p><img title=\"March events and movies in New York (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/March_events/death%2Bwish.jpeg\" alt=\"March events and movies in New York (Image-2)\" /></p>\r\n<p>Bruce Willis stars as Dr. Paul Kersey in this thriller/action movie that centers around a surgeon-turned-vigilante. After having his wife and daughter brutally attacked by home intruders, Kersey decided to take on a new persona and cleanse his city from criminals. But the question plaguing the public\'s mind when they learn of this anonymous vigilante is whether he is a guardian angel, or a Grim Reaper itself.<br />The movie has received an approval rating of 97% on Rotten Tomatoes, and an average of 8.3/10 on Metacritic.<br />Trailer:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HzILu6yyA20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HzILu6yyA20</a></p>\r\n<h3><strong>Isle of Dogs</strong></h3>\r\n<p><img title=\"March events and movies in New York (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/March_events/21-isle-of-dogs-w1200-h630.jpg\" alt=\"March events and movies in New York (Image-3)\" /></p>\r\n<p>Who doesn\'t love dogs, right? Especially when they are given a voice by an ensemble of amazing cast that includes Bryan Cranston,&nbsp;Edward Norton,&nbsp;Bill Murray, and Scarlett Johansson.<br />The Isle of Dogs follows the journey of a boy, Atari, who is on a mission to search for his dog that has been quarantined on a remote island due to \"canine flu\".<br />The movie has bagged Wes Anderson an award for Best Director at the 68th Berlin International Film Festival.<br />Trailer:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dt__kig8PVU\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dt__kig8PVU</a></p>\r\n<h2>Best New Movies On Netflix</h2>\r\n<p>Sometimes it\'s nice just to sit back and relax after a long week of work. We get it. So why don\'t plan for a movie get-together at one of Outpost\'s houses? Get some popcorn, pizza, and soda, and enjoy an entertaining night-in with the other members. The more, the merrier!<br />Here are some great movies that have received our thumbs up.<br />-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>The Jungle Book (2016) - March 10</strong><br />The Jungle Book tells the story of Mowgli, an orphaned human boy who was raised in a jungle by his animal guardians. Follow Mowgli as he sets out to discover himself while evading some life-threatening obstacles!<br />Bill Murray,&nbsp;Idris Elba,&nbsp;Lupita Nyong\'o,&nbsp;Scarlett Johansson, and Christopher Walken are among the amazing ensemble that has lent their voices to tell the classic we all grew up with.<br />Need more reasons to watch it? What about the fact that the movie was ranked the 36th-highest-grossing film of all time? It also won an Academy Award for Best Visual Effects.<br />Trailer:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5mkm22yO-bs\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5mkm22yO-bs</a><br />-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>Guardians of the Galaxy - March 20</strong><br />Peter Quill, a brash adventurer, finds himself the subject of a bounty hunt after stealing a mysterious orb coveted by Ronan, a powerful villain. In his attempt to evade Ronan and protect the universe, Quill is forced to work with a quartet of misfits.<br />Chris Pratt,&nbsp;Zoe Saldana,&nbsp;Dave Bautista,&nbsp;Vin Diesel, and Bradley Cooper are among the stars of this movie.<br />The film became the third-highest-grossing film in the Marvel Cinematic Universe, behind The Avengers and Iron Man 3.<br />Trailer:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=d96cjJhvlMA\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=d96cjJhvlMA</a><br />-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>The Hitman\'s Bodyguard - March 31</strong><br />This movie will keep you on the edge of your seat. It follows the challenges faced by a bodyguard, played by Ryan Reynolds,&nbsp; as he tries to protect the world\'s most notorious hitman played by Samuel L. Jackson.<br />Gary Oldman and Salma Hayek also starred in this blockbuster movie.<br />Trailer:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=F4Afusxc2SM\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=F4Afusxc2SM</a></p>', 'st-patricks-day-1.jpg', 1, '2018-03-03 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(111, 'Valentine\'s Day at Outpost Club', 1, 'valentines-day-at-outpost-club', 'outpost-blog/blog-outpost-club/st-valentines-day-outpost-club', 'Valentine\'s Day at Outpost Club', 'Valentine\'s Day at Outpost Club', 'Valentine\'s Day at Outpost Club', '<p>You never know where and when you\'ll meet your best friend, significant other, or your future spouse. Those moments when things just click are hard to come by. Mo matter your situation, the.</p>', '<p>You never know where and when you\'ll meet your best friend, significant other, or your future spouse. Those moments when things just click are hard to come by.Mo matter your situation,, the red-hearted holiday might make even the most confident dater feel insecure. However, starting a simple conversation about the holiday, joking around with like-minded people, or picking a low-key gift for friends and family can take the stress out of the day and turn it into something you enjoy!</p>\r\n<p>Approaching Valentine&rsquo;s Day tough, because it is as much about your partner&rsquo;s feelings as it is your own. You may discover you have wildly different ideas about how the day should be spent.</p>\r\n<p>At <a href=\"../\" rel=\"nofollow\">Outpost Club</a>,&nbsp;we\'ve heard many of these types of stories as members pass through our halls. We\'ve even heard some great stories about falling in love within our community! All our members spend a lot of time in around one another, so sometimes it\'s just bound to happen. We love when our members engage with one another, because new friends and relationships are always made.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>See pictures of our valentine\'s day event below!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><img title=\"Valentine\'s Day at Outpost Club (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Valentines_Day/IMG_9364.jpg\" alt=\"Valentine\'s Day at Outpost Club (Image-1)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Valentine\'s Day at Outpost Club (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Valentines_Day/IMG_9365.jpg\" alt=\"Valentine\'s Day at Outpost Club (Image-2)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Valentine\'s Day at Outpost Club (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Valentines_Day/IMG_9367.jpg\" alt=\"Valentine\'s Day at Outpost Club (Image-3)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Valentine\'s Day at Outpost Club (Image-4), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Valentines_Day/IMG_9373.jpg\" alt=\"Valentine\'s Day at Outpost Club (Image-4)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Valentine\'s Day at Outpost Club (Image-5), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Valentines_Day/IMG_9381.jpg\" alt=\"Valentine\'s Day at Outpost Club (Image-5)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Valentine\'s Day at Outpost Club (Image-6), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Valentines_Day/IMG_9382.jpg\" alt=\"Valentine\'s Day at Outpost Club (Image-6)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Valentine\'s Day at Outpost Club (Image-7), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Valentines_Day/IMG_9383.jpg\" alt=\"Valentine\'s Day at Outpost Club (Image-7)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Valentine\'s Day at Outpost Club (Image-8), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Valentines_Day/IMG_9384.jpg\" alt=\"Valentine\'s Day at Outpost Club (Image-8)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Valentine\'s Day at Outpost Club (Image-9), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Valentines_Day/IMG_9455.jpg\" alt=\"Valentine\'s Day at Outpost Club (Image-9)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Valentine\'s Day at Outpost Club (Image-10), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Valentines_Day/IMG_9457.jpg\" alt=\"Valentine\'s Day at Outpost Club (Image-10)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Valentine\'s Day at Outpost Club (Image-11), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Valentines_Day/IMG_9459.jpg\" alt=\"Valentine\'s Day at Outpost Club (Image-11)\" /></p>\r\n</div>', 'IMG_9364.jpg', 1, '2017-02-22 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(112, 'Helpful Apps for Coliving', 1, 'helpful-apps-for-coliving', '', 'Helpful Apps for Coliving', 'Helpful Apps for Coliving', 'Here are some coliving applications that we, at Outpost Club use in day-to-day basis and hence, are able to vouch for their advantages', '<p>Coliving is unique to other forms of accommodation in the sense that it offers a stimulating environment for interaction among members. It often houses more people than the average flats as well..</p>', '<header>\r\n<p><em>Coliving is unique to other forms of accommodation in the sense that it offers a stimulating environment for interaction among members. It often houses more people than the average flats as well. From our experience being in the business, this is where mobile applications play a big role. It helps ensure the highest level of enjoyment among members, and facilitate communication amongst them. Here are some coliving applications that we, at <a href=\"../\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Outpost Club</a> use in day-to-day basis and hence, are able to vouch for their advantages.&nbsp; &nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</header>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h3>WHAT TO DO IN A NEW CITY?</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Eventbrite</strong></p>\r\n<p>Eventbrite is a great platform to find out the events that are taking place around the city. You can also create and share your own activities. From music festivals, networking events, to parties, just to name a few, this app has it all.</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Helpful Apps for Coliving (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Helpful_Apps/apps%20for%20coliving%204.png\" alt=\"Helpful Apps for Coliving (Image-1)\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>BandsInTown</strong></p>\r\n<p>BandsInTown is a \"platform where artists and fans connect\". It even notifies users of the tours and bands that are playing in their area. In 2014, the app was listed as one of Business Insider\'s world\'s greatest apps.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Fever</strong></p>\r\n<p>Fever lists everything you can do to have a great time in the city. This includes, but is not limited to concerts, exhibitions, comedy shows and deals at restaurants. It allows you to choose three types of activities you\'re interested in, and provides a list that caters to those interests.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Meetup</strong></p>\r\n<p>Meetup is a platform where you can meet people and be part of a community in a less formal setting. You can pick activities of your interest and see all connected events going around the city. This app is a favorite among our members who are new to city.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>WORK SPACE&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>Even though our members love our coworking spaces within our houses, here are some coworking spaces that uses apps that our members have suggested to us.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Spacious</strong></p>\r\n<p>Spacious partners with the best restaurants in the city. At just $129 per month, members get to co-work at beautiful spaces where they can network, relax, and connect with each other. Members also have access to high speed wi-fi and outlets, unlimited coffee and tea, as well as dinner.</p>\r\n<h3><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Helpful Apps for Coliving (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Helpful_Apps/Apps_for_coliving%201.jpg\" alt=\"Helpful Apps for Coliving (Image-2)\" /></h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Above, one of Spacious\' many locations</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Breather</strong></p>\r\n<p>If you\'re here for business, Breather is the right place for you and your team to work. It provides you with a private space without the distractions that often come with working in a co-working spots. Breather also supplies all the things you need to ensure maximum productivity, including whiteboards and high speed wi-fi.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>FINANCE</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Splitwise</strong></p>\r\n<p>This app is perfect among friends and roommates, providing a cost-splitter. What\'s great is that groups can split big items, record payments, and do interpersonal bill splitting within a group. Splitwise takes all previous bills into account, allows you to \"settle up\" with anyone in the group.</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Helpful Apps for Coliving (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Helpful_Apps/apps%20for%20coliving%202.jpg\" alt=\"Helpful Apps for Coliving (Image-3)\" /><br />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Venmo</strong></p>\r\n<p>If you are looking to make cash payments immediately to friends, the most popular tool is Venmo. Link this app to your bank account and you can pay anyone at any time.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>COMMUNICATION</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Facebook Messenger</strong></p>\r\n<p>Probably the most useful app for communicating between members. What\'s great about the messenger is that almost everyone has a facebook, no need to download a new app for newcomers. You can send all important updates through here, members use it to meet up all over the city, and we can plan events directly in the application.<br />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Slack</strong></p>\r\n<p>Also a great method of communication, and is a little less persistent than facebook messenger. You can create different subjects within groups for the sake of holding different conversations at the same time.<br />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>WhatsApp</strong></p>\r\n<p>We like WhatsApp for communicating with our Alumni. It something that many of our members use, and is a great way to have big groups stay in touch</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>TRAVEL</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Coliving all about sharing</strong>, and becuase of this, car-sharing programs works perfectly for our members. Here are some of the ones our members use.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Car2Go</strong></p>\r\n<p>Car2go is a carsharing app that allows you to rent a car whenever you need it. The renting process is hassle-free, as everything you need to rent one is just right there at the tip of your finger. It costs less than $0.50 per minute and you don\'t even have to worry about parking charges, fuel, or signing up for insurance</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Helpful Apps for Coliving (Image-4), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Helpful_Apps/apps%20for%20coliving%203.jpg\" alt=\"Helpful Apps for Coliving (Image-4)\" /><br />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>If you decide to <a href=\"../join-us\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">join us</a>,&nbsp;many of our houses are located in the zone where hundreds of car2go cars are located!</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Reach Now</strong></p>\r\n<p>Dreaming of driving luxurious BMWs and MINIs? ReachNow allows you to do this at flat rates and competitive per day pricing. Users can pick-up any available car at the location of their choice, and drop it off at select areas.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>City Mapper</strong></p>\r\n<p>City Mapper makes traveling via public transport much easier. The app helps guide you to your destination, by informing you of which subway and bus to get on. It also provides the timing of the public transport you need to take on, and the costs of taking them.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>FOOD&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Seamless</strong></p>\r\n<p>Seamless is the most popular way to order food online. It partners with thousands of eateries. All you have to do is choose a restaurant and place your order and voila, you\'re all set to either pick up, or have the food delivered to your doorstep.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Sun Basket</strong></p>\r\n<p>With this app, you get to have the freshest organic ingredients delivered directly to you. You can also subscribe to recipes for healthy meals that only take under 30 minutes to prepare.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Food Kick</strong></p>\r\n<p>Whether you\'re having a bad day and just needed to unwind, or enjoying a night in with your friends, Food Kick is there to deliver what you need: quick meal hacks that combine food and drinks fitted for your mood.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><hr /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h3><em><strong>THAT\'S ALL FOR NOW! WE CONSIDER THIS A LIVING DOCUMENT, SO IF YOU HAVE ANY SUGGESTION OF APPS, WEBSITES OR TIPS FOR APPS ALREADY ON THE LIST, LET US KNOW! YOU CAN COMMENT BELOW OR EMAIL US AT INFO@OUTPOST-CLUB.COM</strong></em></h3>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'Apps_for_coliving 1.jpg', 1, '2018-04-24 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(113, 'Member Profile Gloria Mesa', 1, 'member-profile-gloria-mesa', '', 'Member Profile Gloria Mesa', 'Member Profile Gloria Mesa', 'Member Profile: Gloria Mesa', '<p>WELCOME TO OUR MEMBERS\' PROFILE SERIES, WHERE WE SHARE THE STORIES OF WHY THEY MOVED TO NYC, AND ALSO WHAT THEY LIKE ABOUT THEIR TIME HERE. THIS WEEK WE&rsquo;RE INTRODUCING YOU TO GLORIA WHO STAYED.</p>', '<h3><strong><em>WELCOME TO OUR MEMBERS\' PROFILE SERIES, WHERE WE SHARE THE STORIES OF WHY THEY MOVED TO NYC, AND ALSO WHAT THEY LIKE ABOUT THEIR TIME HERE. THIS WEEK WE&rsquo;RE INTRODUCING YOU TO GLORIA WHO STAYED WITH US AT OUR EAST BUSHWICK HOUSE. </em></strong>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Tells us a little about yourself &nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>My name is Gloria Mesa. I was born in Kinshasa, it is the capital city in the Democratic Republic of Congo. My family and I immigrated to the United States when I was eight years old. Prior to moving to New York City, I was living in North Carolina. I am the youngest of five children, I have two older brothers and two older sisters. I studied abroad twice when I was in college; I really love traveling and learning about different cultures.</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Member Profile Gloria Mesa (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Member_GloriaMesa/tmp_2018041609393568249.jpg\" alt=\"Member Profile Gloria Mesa (Image-1)\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>What brought you to NYC?</strong></p>\r\n<p>I am completing a service year program with the Department of Health and Mental Hygiene in Brooklyn.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What has been your best experience here?</strong></p>\r\n<p>There is no other place in the world like New York City. I love how this city has so much to offer and there is always something to do. My best experience here so far has been being able to explore all the different boroughs and learning about the different cultures. One of my favorite places that I have discovered is the Malcolm Shabazz Harlem Market. It is a beautiful market that has a lot of unique items.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What do you think of co-living?</strong></p>\r\n<p>I think it is a great option for folks who moved to the city alone. It allows you to meet a lot of different people that can become a part of your support system. As great and beautiful New York City is, it is quite common to also feel lonely while living here. Co-living creates a space for you to be able to meet others and formulate good friendships.</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Member Profile Gloria Mesa (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Member_GloriaMesa/pic%2B9-2.jpg\" alt=\"Member Profile Gloria Mesa (Image-2)\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>What\'s been your best experience in the time you have stayed with Outpost?</strong></p>\r\n<p>I love coming home and having someone there present to talk about how my day was. It has been a refreshing experience to meet so many people from all over the world. I enjoy having conversations with other people and learning about what they are passionate about and what thrives them to be the best version of themselves. I have made some friends with some members who stayed with Outpost and we have remained in contact even after they left and that has been pretty awesome.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What are the 5 fun things we should know about you?</strong></p>\r\n<p>1. I am vegan<br />2. I am bi-lingual<br />3. I am extremely passionate about social justice &nbsp;<br />4. I love dancing to afrobeat and soca music<br />5. I am a sucker for deep conversations</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><em><strong>Thanks all for now! We thank Gloria for taking the time to talk with us and being a great member of Outpost! Check out her social media below:</strong></em></h3>\r\n<h3><em><strong>Facebook: Gloria Mesa and <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/outpostclubNY/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Outpost Club </a></strong></em></h3>\r\n<h3><em><strong>Instagram: <a href=\"https://bit.ly/2yKHwih\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">@outpostcoliving</a></strong></em><br />&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p><img title=\"Member Profile Gloria Mesa (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Member_GloriaMesa/IMG-20180416-WA0013.jpg\" alt=\"Member Profile Gloria Mesa (Image-3)\" /></p>', 'tmp_2018041609393568249.jpg', 1, '2018-04-15 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(361, 'Virtual activities you can do with friends', 1, 'virtual-activities-you-can-do-with-friends', '', 'Virtual activities you can do with friends', 'Virtual activities you can do with friends', 'With everyone losing track of the number of days we’ve been in quarantine now, you may also have found that your enthusiasm for video chatting your friends has dipped as well. Nothing left to talk about but the next meal you’re going to prepare? No problem! Try these virtual activities with your friends to liven up your hangouts.', '<p>With everyone losing track of the number of days we&rsquo;ve been in quarantine now, you may also have found that your enthusiasm for video chatting your friends has dipped as well. Nothing left to talk about but the next meal you&rsquo;re going to prepare? No problem! Try these virtual activities with your friends to liven up your hangouts.</p>', '<p>With everyone losing track of the number of days we&rsquo;ve been in quarantine now, you may also have found that your enthusiasm for video chatting with your friends has dipped as well. Nothing left to talk about but the next meal you&rsquo;re going to prepare? No problem! Try these virtual activities with your friends to liven up your hangouts.</p>\r\n<h1><strong>Reinvent the old games</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So many of the classic games and game shows can be adapted to a video conferencing format. Get all your friends on a call together and try playing virtual bingo, Pictionary or even just create a quiz for you all to play. It may take some creativity but most games can be played live online, especially if you and a friend both have the same board games lying round the house.</span></p>\r\n<h1><strong>Try out new games</strong></h1>\r\n<p>There are also plenty of games which can be played online and let you interact with other players live, such as Animal Crossing*, some versions of The Sims* and Call of Duty*. This combines all the fun of sitting at home and geeking out in lockdown with the chance to actually bond and hang out with your friends. And if you&rsquo;re looking for something truly interactive, we love Jackbox* games which allows you to each play the same game against friends on your phone while video calling each other.</p>\r\n<h1><strong>Watch a movie together</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><a href=\"http://netflix.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Netflix</a> now has a new function where you can watch online with a friend. Been meaning to catch that movie together before lockdown set in? Now you can. It&rsquo;s a great way to wallow in your PJs and actually feel social at the same time, as you can exchange witty remarks and shocking tidbits live with your friend over the video while you watch.</span></p>\r\n<h1><strong>Dress up together</strong></h1>\r\n<p>One of the frustrating things about being at home is that there&rsquo;s nothing to get dressed up for anymore. But it doesn&rsquo;t have to be that way! Why not dress up with your friends&mdash;whether it&rsquo;s a themed party (we know you have a drawer filled with costumes at home somewhere) or a night of pure glam, it&rsquo;s sure to get everybody having a good time. Or better yet, why not all wear that outfit that you love but you never get the chance to wear? From medieval banquet dresses to cosplay outfits to ballgowns, the possibilities of your closet are just waiting to be explored.</p>\r\n<h1><strong>Get cooking</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It seems like everyone is cooking in quarantine like never before. But you&rsquo;re cooking doesn&rsquo;t have to be a solo enterprise. Simply arrange with friends to get the same ingredients and follow the same recipe and you&rsquo;ve got yourself a party. Hangout on video conference while you chop, saut&eacute;, fry, bake and wait and then look forward to eating your concoctions together at the same time. You can even make it a competition if you&rsquo;re looking for a challenge (although the points will have to be on presentation only, unless you trust your friends to honestly self-report on their own meal&rsquo;s taste!)</span></p>\r\n<h1><strong>Do a scavenger hunt</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Most of us have many of the same objects lying around their houses, so why not take advantage of this and make it into a fun quarantine game with friends to play over video chat? Set a timed challenge for the first person to find a toothbrush, the first person to bring back a chopped carrot&mdash;or anything else. You can even scramble up words into anagrams to make the scavenger hunt harder or go the whole way and create an elaborate game with&nbsp;different stages and checkpoints for you all to reach.</span></p>\r\n<h1><strong>Get arty</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So long as you and your friends all have the same arts and crafts tools, there&rsquo;s no limit to the arty activities you can get up to on a video call while you catch up with each other. Whether it&rsquo;s knitting, jewelry making or anything else, it&rsquo;s always better to do your hobbies with friends on the other end of the line. You could even work on your drawing skills by taking turns to draw portraits of one another. Anything you make will be a living memory to this difficult, bizarre time of your life&mdash;when hopefully you got the chance to bond virtually with your friends despite the distance.</span><br /><br /></p>', '2_16.jpg', 1, '2020-04-20 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0);
