(115, 'Member Profile Chris Ward', 1, 'member-profile-chris-ward', 'blog-outpost-club/2018/4/23/8mrn3iv6pjdqpcpyuqquolr06qr4bs', 'Member Profile Chris Ward', 'Member Profile Chris Ward', 'This Week We’re Introducing You to Chris Ward Who Stayed With.', '<p>Welcome to Our Members\' Profile Series, Where We Share the Stories Of Why They Moved To NYC, and Also What They Like About Their Time Here. This Week We&rsquo;re Introducing You to Chris Ward Who Stayed With.</p>', '<h3><em><strong>WELCOME TO OUR MEMBERS\' PROFILE SERIES, WHERE WE SHARE THE STORIES OF WHY THEY MOVED TO NYC, AND ALSO WHAT THEY LIKE ABOUT THEIR TIME HERE. THIS WEEK WE&rsquo;RE INTRODUCING YOU TO CHRIS WARD WHO STAYED WITH US AT OUR FLATBUSH HOUSE. </strong></em>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p><img title=\"Member Profile Chris Ward (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Member_Chris/IMG_20180303_224339298_1520279666691-1.jpg\" alt=\"Member Profile Chris Ward (Image-1)\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>Tell us a little about yourself</strong></p>\r\n<p>My name is Chris Ward, I&rsquo;m 32 and I&rsquo;m from Philadelphia.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What brought you to NYC?</strong></p>\r\n<p>I came to NYC for a new job opportunity. I work in a hospital as an IT programmer.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>What have been your best experiences here?</strong></p>\r\n<p>My best experience here has been hanging out with new friends made at Outpost! It&rsquo;s not a shameless plug, I honestly mean that, haha! Being new to the city, it has been a great way to get to know people, make new friends and have a great time.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What do you think of coliving?</strong></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Member Profile Chris Ward (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Member_Chris/20180320_214205_1521679244994-4.jpg\" alt=\"Member Profile Chris Ward (Image-2)\" /></p>\r\n<p>Coliving has a lot of advantages, but the key for me is the people. It reminded me of MTV Real World the first day I walked into the Outpost house at Flatbush! Such a diverse group, it&rsquo;s pretty cool to be around. The downside is obviously we like our space as people. Eventually, I&rsquo;m sure I&rsquo;ll want that back, but for now, I&rsquo;m lovin it!</p>\r\n<p><strong>What\'s been your best experience in the time you have stayed with Outpost?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Good question, we have done a lot of things since I&rsquo;ve been here! We just had a 90s party that was a lot of fun! I haven&rsquo;t had a house party like that in a while, it was perfect nostalgia and good times!</p>\r\n<p><strong>What are the 5 fun things we should know about you?</strong></p>\r\n<p>1) I&rsquo;m stoked for an upcoming trip to Colombia<br />2) I am a Latino that can&rsquo;t speak Spanish or dance a good Salsa (I am working hard on both!)<br />3) I am also a writer and independent filmmaker<br />4) my pen name is CV Ward<br />5) I have just released a short teaser comic on Facebook! (Ok, this IS a shameless plug!) would love it for people to go check it out and give feedback on the short survey linked on it.</p>\r\n<p>See Chris\' work and social media below!</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Member Profile Chris Ward (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Member_Chris/111.jpg\" alt=\"Member Profile Chris Ward (Image-3)\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>Facebook: CV Ward and <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/outpostclubNY/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Outpost Club </a></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Instagram: CV Ward and <a href=\"https://bit.ly/2yKHwih\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">@outpostcoliving</a></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'IMG_20180303_224339298_1520279666691-1.jpg', 1, '2018-04-22 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(116, 'Outpost Celebrates Talia’s 24th Birthday In Style', 1, 'outpost-celebrates-talias-24th-birthday-in-style', '', 'Outpost Celebrates Talia’s 24th Birthday In Style', 'Outpost Celebrates Talia’s 24th Birthday In Style', 'Outpost Club member Talia Simpson sure knows how to throw a party!', '<p>Outpost Club member Talia Simpson sure knows how to throw a party!</p>', '<p><img title=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Celebrates/IMG_20180414_225107139.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-1)\" /></p>\r\n<p>Outpost Club member Talia Simpson sure knows how to throw a party!</p>\r\n<p>The birthday girl who turned 24 last weekend turned on the heat and made our Ridgewood House a dance floor that got everyone &ldquo;moving like Jagger&rdquo;. Along with her friends, both from Outpost and outside, Talia who is also our Ridgewood House leader successfully threw one of the best birthday parties we\'ve had!</p>\r\n<p>They had balloons scattered all over the floor, fairy lights to set everyone in a party mood, and a DJ that got everyone pumped up all night long. Those who were over 21 also got to enjoy a couple of drinks Talia made herself.</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Celebrates/img-84.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-2)\" /></p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;It\'s called jungle juice. Basically a bunch of vodka, fruits, and juice,&rdquo; said Talia. &ldquo;I also made slime juice which had the same thing, plus gummy bears and kool aid.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>\"It was a great time! Good music, good people and an overall awesome night! Wouldn\'t have asked for a better group of people to spend the night with,&rdquo; she added. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Just check out the photos to see how &ldquo;dope\" the party was. You too can celebrate your birthday in style, by becoming a <a href=\"../join-us\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">member</a> of Outpost Club&rsquo;s community!</p>\r\n<p>Facebook: <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/outpostclubNY/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Outpost Club </a></p>\r\n<p>Instagram: <a href=\"https://bit.ly/2yKHwih\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">@outpostcoliving</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Celebrates/20180414_235545_1523930767249.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-3)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-4), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Celebrates/20180414_235808_1523930855231.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-4)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-5), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Celebrates/20180415_000116_1523932025118.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-5)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-6), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Celebrates/20180415_000146_1524072590146.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-6)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-7), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Celebrates/20180415_000653_1523933997384.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-7)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-8), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Celebrates/20180415_001124_1523934226294.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-8)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-9), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Celebrates/20180415_001436_1523935491088.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-9)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-10), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Celebrates/20180415_001802_1523934897922.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-10)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-11), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Celebrates/20180415_001930_1523935056403.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-11)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-12), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Celebrates/tmp_2018041609393568249-1.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-12)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-13), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Celebrates/IMG_20180414_225337216.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-13)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-14), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Celebrates/IMG_20180414_225459857_LL.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-14)\" /></p>\r\n<img title=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-15), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Celebrates/_DSC1747.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-15)\" />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-16), outpost-club.com\" src=\"https://cdn2.hubspot.net/hubfs/4068949/Imported_Blog_Media/_DSC1753.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-16)\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-17), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Celebrates/_DSC1754.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-17)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-18), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Celebrates/_DSC1756.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-18)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-19), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Celebrates/_DSC1761.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-19)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-20), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Celebrates/_DSC1762.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-20)\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-22), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Celebrates/IMG_20180414_225111388_LL.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-21)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-23), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Celebrates/IMG_20180414_225457897_LL.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-23)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-24), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Celebrates/IMG_20180414_225259051_LL.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-24)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-25), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Celebrates/IMG_20180414_225650516_LL.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-25)\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-26), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Celebrates/IMG_20180414_225410503_LL.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-26)\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-27), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Outpost_Celebrates/IMG_20180414_225250378_LL.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Celebrates Talia&rsquo;s 24th Birthday In Style (Image-27)\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>', 'IMG_20180414_225107139.jpg', 1, '2018-04-22 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(117, 'Member Profile Ana Carolina', 1, 'member-profile-ana-carolina', 'outpost-blog/-member-profile-ana-carolina', 'Member Profile Ana Carolina', 'Member Profile Ana Carolina', 'This Week We’re Introducing You to Ana Who Stayed With.', '<p>Welcome to Our Members\' Profile Series, Where We Share the Stories Of Why They Moved To Nyc, And Also What They Like About their Time Here. This Week We&rsquo;re Introducing You to Ana Who Stayed With.</p>', '<h3><em>WELCOME TO OUR MEMBERS\' PROFILE SERIES, WHERE WE SHARE THE STORIES OF WHY THEY MOVED TO NYC, AND ALSO WHAT THEY LIKE ABOUT THEIR TIME HERE. THIS WEEK WE&rsquo;RE INTRODUCING YOU TO ANA WHO STAYED WITH US AT OUR BUSHWICK HOUSE. </em>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Tell us a little about yourself </strong><br /><br /><em>I&rsquo;m Ana Carolina Xavier, from Brazil. I&rsquo;m 25 years old, and I&rsquo;m studying to be a social worker. </em><br /><br /><strong>What brought you to NYC?</strong><br /><img title=\"Member Profile Ana Carolina (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Member_Ana/20180214_190853_1518715827186_1518716918236_1521779185799.jpg\" alt=\"Member Profile Ana Carolina (Image-1)\" /><em>I came to visit NYC, but ended up taking some English classes to improve my English.</em><br /><br /><strong>What have been your best experiences here?</strong><br /><br /><em>I think my best experience here was when I got lost on the first day. It was amazing because I ended up discovering a lot of new places. It was a great experience. </em><br /><br /><strong>What do you think of coliving</strong>?<br /><br /><em>I really like it. I love that there&rsquo;s a lot of people from different countries, and you get to be friends with all of them. I think it&rsquo;s a very cool experience and the best way to make friends!</em><br /><br /><img title=\"Member Profile Ana Carolina (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Member_Ana/20180214_194335_1518717113176.jpg\" alt=\"Member Profile Ana Carolina (Image-2)\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>What\'s been your best experience in the time you have stayed with Outpost?</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>I think it was the </em><em>V</em><em>alentine&rsquo;s Day</em><em> party. I got to know a lot of different people and everyone treated me so nice, that I love it so much. I really enjoyed the comedy show that we went after the party too. I found it really cool and funny!</em><br /><br /></p>\r\n<p>Facebook: Ana Carolina Xavier and <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/outpostclubNY/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Outpost Club </a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Instagram: Ana Carolina Xavier and <a href=\"https://bit.ly/2yKHwih\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">@outpostcoliving</a></p>', 'FB_IMG_1525122516599.jpg', 1, '2018-04-30 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(118, 'Neighborhood Guide: East Williamsburg', 1, 'neighborhood-guide-east-williamsburg', 'outpost-blog/-neighborhood-guide-east-williamsburg', 'Neighborhood Guide: East Williamsburg', 'Neighborhood Guide: East Williamsburg', 'Outpost Club\'s East Williamsburg Neighborhood Guide', '<p>If you&rsquo;re new to the area, we understand how tough that can be. We have members coming from all over the world and many of them at the start didn&rsquo;t know much about America, let alone the exciting.</p>', '<p><em><strong>IF YOU&rsquo;RE NEW TO THE AREA, WE UNDERSTAND HOW TOUGH THAT CAN BE. WE HAVE MEMBERS COMING FROM ALL OVER THE WORLD AND MANY OF THEM AT THE START DIDN&rsquo;T KNOW MUCH ABOUT AMERICA, LET ALONE THE EXCITING NEIGHBORHOOD OF EAST WILLIAMSBURG! LET US HELP YOU WITH SOME OF THE BASICS, SO YOU CAN START EXPLORING THE NEIGHBORHOOD ALMOST IMMEDIATELY.</strong> </em></p>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h2>Subway</h2>\r\n<p><strong>It\'s really up to you, but here are the main ways to get to Manhattan!</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>THE L TRAIN - GRAHAM AV.</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Williamsburg House - walk: 11 minutes; bike: 4 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>THE M TRAIN - NASSAU AV.&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Williamsburg House - walk: 15 minutes; bike: 5 minutes</em></p>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h2>GYM</h2>\r\n<p><strong>Having a tough time finding a gym that suits your physical need? Here are some nearby our East Williamsburg House that you can check out.</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>CROSSFIT OUTBREAK EAST WILLIAMSBURG&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>208 Frost St, Brooklyn. </strong><a href=\"https://goo.gl/maps/KUbRX9NRp3q\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Maps</a></p>\r\n<p>CrossFit is a movement and a lifestyle, promising to get all its members (even the recovering couch potatoes) doing everything they once thought was impossible.</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Williamsburg House - walk: 5 minutes; bike: 1 minute</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>BROOKLYN ZOO NY</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>230 Bogart St, Brooklyn.&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Brooklyn Zoo is a sprawling, industrial fitness space that caters to those interested in parkour training, aerial arts, tumbling and even trampoline. Its monthly membership starts at just $150.</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Williamsburg House - bus: 12 minutes; walk: 17 minutes; bike: 5 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>THE SCULPTED BODY NYC&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>354 Graham Ave, Brooklyn.&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>The Sculpted Body NYC was founded with the goal to help others improve their lives and well being through proper fitness and nutrition.It uses traditional and non-traditional fitness and nutrition models to create programs that are molded to each client.</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Williamsburg House - bus: 6 minutes; walk: 11 minutes; bike: 4 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>GROCERIES</h2>\r\n<p><strong>Looking to grab quick groceries? There are plenty of options you can pick from, but we have narrowed them down to a few that suit your every need. </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>CTOWN SUPERMARKETS&nbsp;<img title=\"Neighborhood Guide: East Williamsburg (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/NEIGHBORHOOD_GUIDE/20180415_182338_1524927226714.jpg\" alt=\"Neighborhood Guide: East Williamsburg (Image-1)\" /></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>330 Graham Ave, Brooklyn.</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Williamsburg House - walk: 12 minutes; bike: 4 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>KEY FOOD SUPERMARKET&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>57 Kingsland Ave, Brooklyn.</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Williamsburg House - walk: 4 minutes; bike: 1 minute</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>MR. GRAHAM\'S MARKET&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Neighborhood Guide: East Williamsburg (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/NEIGHBORHOOD_GUIDE/20180415_182500_1524926245182.jpg\" alt=\"Neighborhood Guide: East Williamsburg (Image-2)\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>344 Graham Ave, Brooklyn.&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Williamsburg House - walk: 11 minutes; bike: 4 min&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>AMIR DELI GROCERY</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>49 Kingsland Ave, Brooklyn.&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Williamsburg House - walk: 4 minutes; bike: 1 minute</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>HARVEST DELI</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>31 Kingsland Ave, Brooklyn.&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Williamsburg House - walk: 5 minutes; bike: 1 minute</em></p>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h2>COFFEE SHOPS</h2>\r\n<p><strong>Need your morning fix? Check out these places, hand-picked just for you.</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>TAR PIT COFFEE SHOP</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>135 Woodpoint Rd, Brooklyn.&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Neighborhood Guide: East Williamsburg (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/NEIGHBORHOOD_GUIDE/20180415_183656_1524926694392.jpg\" alt=\"Neighborhood Guide: East Williamsburg (Image-3)\" /></p>\r\n<p>Start your morning at Tar Pit, just a few minutes&rsquo; walk from the House. The layout is incredibly cute and the wide window at the front is perfect for people-watching. Be sure to try out their Kyoto style iced coffee<strong>!</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Williamsburg House - walk: 5 minutes; bike: 1 minute</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>CHARTER COFFEE HOUSE</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>309 Graham Ave #1, Brooklyn.&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Neighborhood Guide: East Williamsburg (Image-4), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/NEIGHBORHOOD_GUIDE/20180415_171130_1524925674512.jpg\" alt=\"Neighborhood Guide: East Williamsburg (Image-4)\" /></p>\r\n<p>You can get all sorts of roasters here. From Counter Culture, Ceremony, and Middle State, they have it all, prepared through a wide array of brewing methods<strong>. </strong>Ask the baristas about the coffee and tea served here. There&rsquo;s a story to each of them!</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Williamsburg House - walk: 13 minutes; bike: 4 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>VARIETY COFFEE ROASTERS&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>368 Graham Avenue, Brooklyn. </strong><br /><br />This is your quintessential Brooklyn cafe that serves more than just beverages that appeal to your taste and smell senses. It is also frequented by Brooklyn&rsquo;s eclectic crowd that appeals to your sight.</p>\r\n<p>Grubstreet.com&nbsp;listed Variety Coffee Roster as one of the \"absolute best lattes in New York\". This cafe is also listed as one of the&nbsp;10 Best Places to Drink Coffee&nbsp;in NYC.</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Williamsburg House - bus: 5 minutes; walk: 10 minutes; bike: 3 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>THE BAGEL STORE&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>754 Metropolitan Ave, Brooklyn.</strong> <br /><br />The Bagel Store is located right off the Graham Avenue stop. It is well known for its rainbow bagel which also makes for a perfect Instagram picture! Its other delicacies are also perfect for those with sweet tooth. Just note that it accepts cash only.</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Williamsburg House - bus: 5 minutes; walk: 11 minutes; bike: 3 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /><strong>RINGOLEVIO&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>490 Humboldt St, Brooklyn. </strong><br /><br />Head here if you&rsquo;re in a mood for brunch classics on the weekend.They also have vintage records stacked behind the bar, which gives it a very Brooklyn-hip type of feel.</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Williamsburg House - walk: 5 minutes; bike: 3 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /><strong>THE END</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>522 Metropolitan Ave, Brooklyn.</strong><br /><br />This is the spot for health-conscious individuals who are also coffee addicts. Their coffee will give you the kick you need to start the day, but healthy enough that you won\'t be worrying about calorie count all day.</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Williamsburg House - bus: 6 minutes; walk: 16 minutes; bike: 6 minutes</em></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h2>FOOD&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<p><strong>The neighborhood offers an unlimited variety of eateries at affordable prices. Here are a few that we recommend, based on the input provided by our former and current members.</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>HUMBOLDT AND JACKSON&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>434 Humboldt Street, Brooklyn. </strong><br /><br />Humboldt &amp; Jackson is an American restaurant, bar and event space that serves a locally sourced menu, paired with made-in-USA drinks. It also play host to a variety of events that include film screenings.</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Williamsburg House - walk: 7 minutes; bike: 2 minutes<br /><br /><br /></em></p>\r\n<p><strong>FORCELLA LA PIZZA DE NAPOLI&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Neighborhood Guide: East Williamsburg (Image-5), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/NEIGHBORHOOD_GUIDE/20180415_192120_1524927086391.jpg\" alt=\"Neighborhood Guide: East Williamsburg (Image-5)\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>485 Lorimer St, Brooklyn.</strong><br /><br />A night in doesn\'t mean compromising on quality. Forcella&rsquo;s pizzas taste exactly like how pizzas should.. straight from Italy. Plan an Italian-themed night in with your housemates and make the pizza here the centrepiece.</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Williamsburg House - bus: 16 minutes; walk: 19 minutes; bike: 6 minutes<br /><br /></em></p>\r\n<p><br /><strong>DESTEFANO\'S STEAKHOUSE&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>89 Conselyea St, Brooklyn.&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>The steak here will not disappoint. Pair it up with their selection of wine and voila, you\'ll have a perfect steak dinner to be remembered.</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Williamsburg House - bus: 6 minutes; walk: 14 minutes; bike: 4 minutes<br /><br /><br /></em></p>\r\n<p><strong>MOTHER\'S&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>347 Graham Ave, Brooklyn.&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Mother&rsquo;s serves all types of burgers and a wide range of New York craft beers, all at a very reasonable price. They also have a nice patio you can enjoy your food at!</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Williamsburg House - bus: 5 minutes; walk: 11 minutes; bike: 4 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Neighborhood Guide: East Williamsburg (Image-6), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/NEIGHBORHOOD_GUIDE/20180415_182636(0)_1524926482118.jpg\" alt=\"Neighborhood Guide: East Williamsburg (Image-6)\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>HAREFIELD ROAD&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>769 Metropolitan Ave, Brooklyn.&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Harefield Road is famous for its weekend brunch, for good reasons. The food make for a great hangover cure, and they are cheap! Try out their much-raved about Bloody Mary too.</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Williamsburg House - bus: 6 minutes; walk: 16 minutes; bike: 5 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>KELLOGG\'S DINER</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>518 Metropolitan Ave, Brooklyn.&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>This 24-hour diner offers everything from a breakfast menu to main meals that include seafood dishes. It also serves Greek and Italian specialties, and mouth-watering desserts such as banana cream pie and chocolate layer cake.</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Williamsburg House - bus: 6 minutes; walk: 16 minutes; bike: 5 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>NIGHTLIFE&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<p><strong>Wind down after a busy day/week at work by visiting one of the spots listed with your Outpost friends. They&rsquo;re also perfect if you&rsquo;re looking to be outside on a nice sunny day, but don&rsquo;t want to go too far just to relax.</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>BASIK&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Neighborhood Guide: East Williamsburg (Image-7), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/NEIGHBORHOOD_GUIDE/20180415_181921_1524925771813.jpg\" alt=\"Neighborhood Guide: East Williamsburg (Image-7)\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>323 Graham Ave, Brooklyn.</strong></p>\r\n<p>Basik is a laid-back bar with a really nice backyard. They also organize different events every night. On Mondays, the happy hour lasts all night long!</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Williamsburg House - bus: 5 minutes; walk: 12 minutes; bike: 4 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>ROCKA ROLLA</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>486 Metropolitan Ave, Brooklyn.</strong><br /><br />Rocka Rolla is the place to go if you like rock n roll and people-watching. The crowd is always unpredictable, and so are the drinks. Our favorite part of the bar? It\'s their vintage jukebox!</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Williamsburg House - bus: 7 minutes; walk: 17 minutes; bike: 6 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>BARCADE</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>388 Union Ave, Brooklyn. </strong><br />Pacman? Check. Daytona? Check. Barcade is basically a massive arcade located in East Williamsburg&rsquo;s Union Avenue. Smack right in the middle of the arcade is a bar that serves all kind of drinks. Just make sure you eat before you go, as food is not on the menu.</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Williamsburg House - bus: 9 minutes; walk: 19 minutes; bike: 6 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p><br /> <br /><strong>DON PEDRO</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>90 Manhattan Avenue, Brooklyn. </strong><br /><br />Don Pedro is a classic Mexican bar that features live music and really cheap drinks. They also serve the best burrito you can find in Brooklyn.</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Williamsburg House - bus: 15 minutes; walk: 25 minutes; bike: 8 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>PARKS</h2>\r\n<p><strong>COOPER PARK.&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Neighborhood Guide: East Williamsburg (Image-8), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/NEIGHBORHOOD_GUIDE/20180415_185135_1524926954797.jpg\" alt=\"Neighborhood Guide: East Williamsburg (Image-8)\" /></p>\r\n<p>Cooper Park is the hidden gem of East Williamsburg. It\'s massive and provides a beautiful space for those looking for a breath of fresh air and temporarily escape from city life.</p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Williamsburg House - walk: 9 minutes; bike: 3 minutes</em></p>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h2>POST OFFICE&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<p><strong>USPS</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>94 Nassau Ave, Brooklyn.&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Williamsburg House - bus: 9 minutes; walk: 15 minutes; bike: 6 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>UNITED STATES PORTAL SERVICE</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>263 S 4th St, Brooklyn.&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>Distance from the East Williamsburg House - bus: 10 minutes; walk: 25 minutes; bike: 10 minutes</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><strong>THAT\'S ALL FOR NOW! WE CONSIDER THIS A LIVING DOCUMENT, SO IF YOU HAVE ANY SUGGESTION OF PLACES TO ADD, OR TIPS FOR THE PLACES ALREADY ON THE LIST, LET US KNOW! YOU CAN COMMENT BELOW OR EMAIL US AT </strong><a href=\"mailto:INFO@OUTPOST-CLUB.COM\">INFO@OUTPOST-CLUB.COM</a><strong>. </strong></h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '20180415_171130_1524925674512.jpg', 1, '2018-05-02 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(119, 'Outpost Club May Newsletter', 1, 'outpost-club-may-newsletter', '', 'Outpost Club May Newsletter', 'Outpost Club May Newsletter', 'Outpost Club\'s monthly update for the month of May', '<p>Hello again everyone from Outpost Club!</p>', '<p><em>Hello again everyone from&nbsp;Outpost Club!</em></p>\r\n<p><em>In this month\'s newsletters, we have summarized what has been going on throughout the month.</em></p>\r\n<p><em>We have also included other information that may be of interest to you, like the events going on in the coming month, as well as movies and Netflix show recommendations.</em></p>\r\n<p><em>So read on for more of this!</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>What&rsquo;s New With Outpost Club</h2>\r\n<p>Outpost gains a new partner for all our members! This partnership with BKLYN Commons will allow Outpost members a chance to work in a fully-equipped co-working spaces. Enjoy a 50% discount on their open desk memberships! A $150 savings! Also available is a 15% discount on membership for&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>BKLYN Commons\'&nbsp;office&nbsp;space and dedicated desk rental rates.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>As a member of BKC, you&rsquo;ll have access to gorgeous workspaces, unique common areas, business-grade printers, flexible conference rooms, and numerous monthly networking events!</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Club May Newsletter (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/OUTPOST_CLUB_MAY/S9CIu_lSafPEG_VtkCHTJw-default.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Club May Newsletter (Image-1)\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Upcoming Events at Outpost Club</h2>\r\n<p>We know you\'ve loved all the events organized by, and for our members. And that\'s great! Because they were planned with one and only one aim: to make sure you feel like part of a community. So do join in the ones we have planned for you next. Maybe you\'ll end up making new best friends that can keep you company on your nights in, or party it up on your nights out!</p>\r\n<p>Here are some of the events you can look forward to.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Bushwick Spring BBQ - May 19th</strong></p>\r\n<p>Celebrate spring with us at our Bushwick Spring BBQ!</p>\r\n<p><strong>Deadpool 2 in Theatre - May 20th</strong></p>\r\n<p>Come see the highly anticipated sequel with Outpost Club members as excited as you are!</p>\r\n<p><strong>School of Rock BBQ - May 28th</strong></p>\r\n<p>Enjoy the sun while being serenaded by a talented group of musicians from the School of Rock! Our own live band event? Check!</p>\r\n<p><em><strong>If you\'re as excited as we are about these events, stay tuned for additional information that will be shared in our </strong><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/groups/outpostclub/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><strong>Outpost Club NYC Current Members Facebook group.</strong></a></em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Events Coming to NYC</h2>\r\n<p>Are you looking for something fun to do around the city? If so, check out these events that we have compiled for you.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Fleet Week in NYC</strong></p>\r\n<p>Fleet Week in NYC is an annual seven-day celebration held to honor United States&rsquo; Navy, Coast Guard and Marine Corps members. The event starts with a parade that features a fleet of vessels and tall ships along the Hudson river. This is followed by military demonstrations and a Memorial Day ceremony, among many other activities.</p>\r\n<p>It takes place on May 23rd all through May 29th at different venues that include the New York Harbor, Manhattan&rsquo;s Pier 92, Staten Island&rsquo;s USS The Sullivans Pier, the Military Island Eisenhower Park, the Flagship Brewery and the Soldiers\' and Sailors\' Memorial Monument.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Washington Square Outdoor Art Exhibit</strong></p>\r\n<p>The Washington Square Outdoor Art Exhibit takes place twice a year, from May 26th to June 3rd. It is a sidewalk show that starts from University Place at East 13th Street and continues along the east side of Washington Square Park to West 3rd Street. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>So if you&rsquo;re into art, be sure to check out this event that showcases fine artists and craft artisans from around the New York metropolitan area, and other parts of the world.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Japan Day in NYC</strong></p>\r\n<p>Learn about the Japanese culture while enjoying a nice afternoon surrounded by the beautiful Spring air by visiting Central Park&rsquo;s annual Japanese Day this May 14th. Plenty of programs have are in the lineup, starting with Japanese Taiko Drumming at 10.30am.</p>\r\n<p><strong>David Bowie is</strong></p>\r\n<p>Get a full insight on the chart topping artist at the Brooklyn Museum this Spring.</p>\r\n<p>The exhibition provides a look into his creative process, through more than 400 objects that include his original costumes, 85 handwritten lyric sheets, original album art, photographs, and videos.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Outpost Club Recommendation: Best Movies In Theaters&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<p>Movie lovers, there are a couple of new movies coming out next month. So let\'s make a plan for a day out at the cinema with your Outpost Club family!</p>\r\n<p>Also, save some bucks by getting unlimited entries at just $9.95 a month. You can do so by applying for a movie pass here:&nbsp;https://www.moviepass.com/.<br /><br /></p>\r\n<p><strong>Deadpool 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>Loved the first Deadpool? Then you have to watch the second instalment of the foul-mouthed Marvel&rsquo;s comic hero. L.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><br /><strong>Solo: A Star Wars Story</strong><br /><br />A popular drinking game takes a twisted turn in Blumhouse Production\'s Truth or Dare. The movie that is coming out on xxx follows a group of students haunted by an entity that won\'t let them stop playing, until all of them are dead. Will there be any survivor? Watch the movie to find out.</p>\r\n<p><br /><br /><strong>The Guardians</strong><br /><br />Sometimes a little self-belief can change your whole outlook of the world. Follow Any Schumer on her journey of self-appreciation in I Feel Pretty.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Outpost Club Recommendation: Best New Movies On Netflix</h2>\r\n<p>Sometimes it\'s nice just to sit back and relax after a long week of work. We get it. So why don\'t plan for a movie get-together at one of Outpost\'s houses? Get some popcorn, pizza, and soda, and enjoy an entertaining night-in with the other members. The more, the merrier!</p>\r\n<p>Here are some great movies that have received our thumbs up.</p>\r\n<p><strong><br />Mamma Mia!</strong></p>\r\n<p>Mamma Mia! is a 2008 musical romantic comedy film. Meryl Streep leads the film through her role as a single mother to Sophie, played by Amanda Seyfried. Pierce Brosnan, Colin Firth and Stellan Skarsg&aring;rd play the three possible fathers to Sophie, who is determined to find out which one will walk her down the aisle.<br /><br />Mamma Mia! was the 5th highest-grossing film of 2008.<a href=\"https://youtu.be/znmZoVkCjpI\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><br /><br /></a></p>\r\n<p><strong>Wanted</strong></p>\r\n<p>James McAvoy plays the role of Wesley Gibson, an office worker whose monotonous life took a turn after the murder of his estranged father. Fox, played by Angelina Jolie then recruits him into a secret society of assassins, which has more secrets that he initially suspects.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://youtu.be/7pQQHnqBa2E\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><br /><br /></a></p>\r\n<p><strong><em>The Bourne Ultimatum</em></strong></p>\r\n<p>Ben Thomas, played by Will Smith, is living with huge regret over a past mistake. To find redemption, he sets out to help save the lives of seven strangers by donating his organs to them. Complications arise when he falls in love with cardiac patient, Emily.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>How Was Your April At Outpost Club?</h2>\r\n<h4>Now we\'ve covered what\'s in store for this month, let\'s revisit some of the great moments we\'ve shared last month.&nbsp;Last month was a blast! Take a look at one of many of our events that took place during the month of April, and make sure to come to May&rsquo;s events!&nbsp;</h4>\r\n<h2>Talia&rsquo;s Birthday Bash</h2>\r\n<p>The birthday girl who turned 24 last weekend turned on the heat and made our Ridgewood House a dance floor that got everyone &ldquo;moving like Jagger&rdquo;. Along with her friends, both from&nbsp;<a href=\"../\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Outpost</a>&nbsp;and outside, Talia who is also our&nbsp;Ridgewood House&nbsp;leader successfully threw one of the best birthday parties we\'ve had!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Club May Newsletter (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/OUTPOST_CLUB_MAY/_DSC1747.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Club May Newsletter (Image-2)\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>See You Again Next Month!</h2>\r\n<p>We hope you have enjoyed our events as much as we did! Thank you for joining us and making them memorable. Don\'t fret if you had missed any of them. Just check out the articles and pictures of the events to have a feel of what they were like.</p>\r\n<p>Our goal is only truly achieved if we have made you feel like being at home during your stay with us. So we hope you will continue having a great time at Outpost Club!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '_DSC1747.jpg', 1, '2018-05-15 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0);
