(161, 'Going to the Macy\'s Thanksgiving Day Parade? Here\'s What to Know', 1, 'going-to-the-macys-thanksgiving-day-parade-heres-what-to-know', '', 'Going to the Macy\'s Thanksgiving Day Parade? Here\'s What to Know', 'Going to the Macy\'s Thanksgiving Day Parade? Here\'s What to Know', 'One of New York City’s treasured Thanksgiving traditions is the Macy’s Thanksgiving Day Parade. Here are our tips for making the most of your parade experience.', '<p>One of New York City&rsquo;s treasured Thanksgiving traditions is the Macy&rsquo;s Thanksgiving Day Parade. Here are our tips for making the most of your parade experience.</p>', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">One of New York City&rsquo;s treasured Thanksgiving traditions is the </span><strong>Macy&rsquo;s Thanksgiving Day Parade</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, the world&rsquo;s largest parade and the second-longest-running Thanksgiving parade in the U.S. (after Philadelphia&rsquo;s). </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It&rsquo;s also the only good reason to drag yourself out of bed before 6 a.m. on a holiday -- but to really make it worth it, you need to find a prime viewing spot to experience the magic of the dozens of balloons and floats that will be winding their way from Central Park through Midtown. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Here are our tips for making the most of your parade experience: </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Know the route -- and where there&rsquo;s no public viewing</h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The parade route starts at 77th St. &amp; Central Park West, heads down Central Park West to Columbus Circle and continues along the park before turning south on 6th Ave. The parade then continues south on 6th Ave. before stopping at Macy&rsquo;s Herald Square on 34th St. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">There&rsquo;s no public viewing on 6th Ave. from 34th to 38th streets due to the TV broadcast, and on 34th St. between Broadway and 7th Ave. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">There&rsquo;s limited public viewing on the south side of 34th St. between Broadway and 7th Ave.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Stick to the beginning of the parade route for the least-crowded views</h3>\r\n<p>The closer you get to Herald Square, the more crowds you&rsquo;ll find. Your best bet for a mostly unobstructed view is the west side of Central Park West in the 60s or 70s, as the east side isn&rsquo;t open to spectators.</p>\r\n<p>If you arrive late or don&rsquo;t mind missing some of the floats to have a more relaxing experience, you can always try walking through Central Park starting north of 86th Street; head south and you&rsquo;ll find a few hills that offer a good vantage point of the balloons.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Arrive early</h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The parade may not start until 9 a.m. on Nov. 22, but you&rsquo;ll want to make the trek from Brooklyn early if you want a shot at a good view; about 3.5 million people turn up every year to view the spectacle. Try to be in place by 6:30 a.m. for the best spots. </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Be prepared</h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It won&rsquo;t be much warmer than freezing by the time the parade starts -- and you&rsquo;ll be standing around for at least an hour before it even begins. Wear layers, bring a hat and gloves and don&rsquo;t forget a thermos of coffee or hot cocoa to help keep you warm until the fun starts. </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Don&rsquo;t rely on the subway if you don&rsquo;t have to</h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We all know how unreliable the New York City subway system can be. If you&rsquo;re running short on time, consider taking a Lyft once you&rsquo;re in Manhattan, or walking if you encounter delays in Midtown. There&rsquo;s no reason your fate has to rest in the hands of the MTA on an already busy day. </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<br /><em>Photo credit: Frank Camp/Creative Commons</em><br /><br /><br /><br /></p>', '3596400831_fd8126e69e_b-min.jpg', 1, '2018-11-16 06:00:00', NULL, 0, 0, 0),
(162, '#MemberMonday: Jake Wolfe', 1, 'membermonday-jake-wolfe', '', '#MemberMonday: Jake Wolfe', '#MemberMonday: Jake Wolfe', 'For this week\'s #MemberMonday, we\'re introducing you to Jake Wolfean artist who lives at Outpost Club\'s East Bushwick House. Jake\'s made big things happen since moving to New York.', '<p>For this week\'s #MemberMonday, we\'re introducing you to Jake Wolfean artist who lives at Outpost Club\'s East Bushwick House. Jake\'s made big things happen since moving to New York.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p>For this week\'s #MemberMonday, we\'re introducing you to Jake Wolfean artist who lives at Outpost Club\'s East Bushwick House. Jake\'s made big things happen since moving to New York; read on to find out more:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img title=\"#MemberMonday: Jake Wolfe (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/F242818E-7C93-4C32-A3AC-87FBA6D1E018.jpeg\" alt=\"#MemberMonday: Jake Wolfe (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<h3>Tell us a bit about yourself.&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>I originally grew up in a small town called Lawrenceburg, IN, just outside of Cincinnati, OH. I spent my entire life there until I decided to move to Savannah, GA a year ago to pursue my education in Luxury Fashion Management. In my spare time, I love to write for publications on issues in the fashion industry, or I spend a lot of time on social media researching engagement analytics (I&rsquo;m such a nerd lol). The social media aspect ties into my passion for photography as well, where I spend most of my time in film, developing by hand.</p>\r\n<p>I ended up in New York by chance actually! I&rsquo;m here fulfilling an internship position with RKPR, managing sample pulls with fashion publications/celebrity clientele, and creating organic following engagement with social media influencers to better our client&rsquo;s brand. I&rsquo;m August I received an offer from my boss with 2 weeks to move to New York, so I took the opportunity and here I am! Haha.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>What&rsquo;s your favorite Outpost memory?</h3>\r\n<p>I don&rsquo;t particularly have a favorite because I have so many. I chose Outpost because I wanted a sense of community in a city where I knew nobody. However, some of my favorite memories have definitely been watching my friend group experience different cultures in a welcoming environment, or sitting around at the table together listening to Lindsey sing with their guitar. It&rsquo;s a real sense of family here.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Do you have a favorite place in Brooklyn?&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>I&rsquo;m definitely basic when I say I love Dumbo (lol).&nbsp;That area in particular reminds me a lot of Cincinnati, so it&rsquo;s a little feeling of home now that I don&rsquo;t get to visit often. There&rsquo;s still so much of Brooklyn I haven&rsquo;t discovered yet, so if anyone has any recommendations, I want them!</p>\r\n<h3><br /><br />What are you currently working on?&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>Although I came to New York for a job in fashion PR, I&rsquo;ve been working on a few projects here and there. I recently was signed to an agency in Manhattan, and now I&rsquo;ve been working on television shows, commercials, and campaigns! Unfortunately I can&rsquo;t talk about most of them (damn NDA&rsquo;s), but I will say to watch next season of Billions on Showtime.&nbsp;Otherwise, I really work a lot with brand influencing on my Instagram, and be sure to look out for the launch of my IGTV channel come January!</p>\r\n<p><em>Follow Jake on Instagram:&nbsp;</em>@<em>gldnnboy</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Photo: @thequarterrican</em></p>', '579D62C6-6606-4D2A-A7F6-D50BAF39F6D4.jpeg', 1, '2018-11-16 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(163, '4 Things Outpost Club Is Thankful For in 2018', 1, '4-things-outpost-club-is-thankful-for-in-2018', '', '4 Things Outpost Club Is Thankful For in 2018', '4 Things Outpost Club Is Thankful For in 2018', 'Happy Thanksgiving, everyone. We’ve had a great year at Outpost Club, and we want to take this opportunity to express our gratitude to everyone who helped make 2018 special. Here’s to you, Outposters.', '<p>Happy Thanksgiving, everyone. We&rsquo;ve had a great year at Outpost Club, and we want to take this opportunity to express our gratitude to everyone who helped make 2018 special. Here&rsquo;s to you, Outposters.</p>', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Happy Thanksgiving, everyone. We&rsquo;ve had a great year at Outpost Club, and we want to take this opportunity to express our gratitude to everyone who helped make 2018 special. Here&rsquo;s to you, Outposters. </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><strong>We&rsquo;re thankful for our amazing community </strong></h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Our goal at Outpost Club is to help build lasting connections between people while making it easier to rent in New York. We&rsquo;re grateful to our members and the friends of Outpost who help </span><a href=\"../blog\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">make each of our events a success</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and fill our houses with positive vibes.</span></p>\r\n<p><br /><img title=\"4 Things Outpost Club Is Thankful For in 2018 (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/hiking.png\" alt=\"4 Things Outpost Club Is Thankful For in 2018 (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /><br /><br /></p>\r\n<h3><strong>We&rsquo;re thankful for the diversity of our members</strong></h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We&rsquo;ve been lucky enough to have members who have hailed from nearly every state in the U.S. and more than 50 countries. Our members speak dozens of languages and are generous with sharing their cultures with their housemates. We have entrepreneurs, writers, artists, musicians, chefs and a host of other professions represented among our members. We&rsquo;re thankful for everything we&rsquo;ve been able to learn through our diversity.</span></p>\r\n<p><br /><img title=\"4 Things Outpost Club Is Thankful For in 2018 (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/halloween.png\" alt=\"4 Things Outpost Club Is Thankful For in 2018 (Image-2)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /><br /><br /></p>\r\n<h3><strong>We&rsquo;re thankful we&rsquo;ve been able to continue to grow</strong></h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This year was full of excitement for Outpost Club: We opened our first house outside of Brooklyn -- the Central Park Manhattan House -- as well as welcomed our </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">East Williamsburg</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and </span><a href=\"../the-downtown-brooklyn-house\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Downtown Brooklyn</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> houses into the fold. We&rsquo;re looking forward to continuing to grow in years to come! </span></p>\r\n<p><br /><img title=\"4 Things Outpost Club Is Thankful For in 2018 (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/east%20williamsburg.png\" alt=\"4 Things Outpost Club Is Thankful For in 2018 (Image-3)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /><br /><br /></p>\r\n<h3><strong>We&rsquo;re thankful for our wonderful city</strong></h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">From the </span><a href=\"../blog/destination-jefferson-street\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">colorful murals of Bushwick</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> to the towering skyscrapers of Midtown, New York City never fails to show us something interesting. Whether we&rsquo;re </span><a href=\"../blog/outpost-club-welcomes-autumn-on-the-water\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">kayaking on the East River</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> or </span><a href=\"../blog/beach-day-with-outpost-club\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">spending the day at Rockaway Beach</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, we can&rsquo;t help but think that New York is the most magical place in the world. We&rsquo;re thankful we get to share it with you, Outposters.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"4 Things Outpost Club Is Thankful For in 2018 (Image-4), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/37084999605_38c9ca75f0_h.jpg\" alt=\"4 Things Outpost Club Is Thankful For in 2018 (Image-4)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /><br /><br /></p>\r\n<p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Photo credits: Charlotte Ryckeboer | <a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/sama093/37084999605/in/photolist-Yv5jmV-6Ub9S5-787YZj-3yn2ko-oNin98-73UWUS-ny1gwr-5bWM3m-54wXxN-8DZsYy-pAqjSa-8DvP7r-Aw7iP-deRXxA-pbQynw-cr6bed-9wxHYM-dAY5NJ-5CEfkW-acAgz3-8hP5y7-8qaSLp-q2YECH-9sPMJX-P9NGGU-pzLzjc-6hWkAa-pRXTxH-aHGQrD-7U4uDQ-7T288o-9Bwsrp-97K2wH-caaMbY-6ibQy1-CxWnKY-48tLSq-8kFSHq-8kCD8V-anPAWm-p8mAUX-oysvB-6jLTpx-AmNceT-3dtrCu-9nirdW-doMnf4-4J63vL-78DF9b-c8Wsx7\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Sama093/Flickr/Creative Commons</a> (Bottom)&nbsp;</span></em></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>', 'Screen Shot 2018-11-20 at 3.24.26 PM.png', 1, '2018-11-20 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(164, 'Our 5 Favorite Brooklyn Coffee Shops', 1, 'our-5-favorite-brooklyn-coffee-shops', '', 'Our 5 Favorite Brooklyn Coffee Shops', 'Our 5 Favorite Brooklyn Coffee Shops', 'We never need an excuse to pop into one of Brooklyn’s many coffee shops, but cold weather seems like the perfect opportunity to visit some of our favorites', '<p>We never need an excuse to pop into one of Brooklyn&rsquo;s many coffee shops, but with the weather getting colder, it&nbsp;seems like the perfect opportunity to visit some of our favorites. Here are five that keep us coming back for more.</p>', '<p>There&rsquo;s not much that&rsquo;s cozier than escaping the cold weather in a local caf&eacute; with a steaming mug of coffee to read a book or just people watch.</p>\r\n<p>We never need an excuse to pop into one of Brooklyn&rsquo;s many coffee shops, but now&nbsp;seems like the perfect opportunity to visit some of our favorites. Here are five that keep us coming back for more:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Variety Coffee Roasters</strong></h3>\r\n<p>Variety is a New York City mini-chain that&rsquo;s been around since 2008. We love the Bushwick location for its plentiful seating, thoughtful decor and -- of course -- great coffee. Variety is a great place to get some work done or just people watch, and it&rsquo;s just a short L train ride from our East Bushwick and Bushwick houses. If you want to try the Williamsburg location, it&rsquo;s a 10-minute walk from the East Williamsburg House.</p>\r\n<p><em>146 Wyckoff Ave., Bushwick</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"10 Our 5 Favorite Brooklyn Coffee Shops (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Screen%20Shot%202018-11-24%20at%202.15.27%20PM.png\" alt=\"Our 5 Favorite Brooklyn Coffee Shops (Image-1)\" /></em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>@varietycoffee/Instagram</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Cafe Madeline</h3>\r\n<p>Cafe Madeline is a cozy, laptop-friendly spot that&rsquo;s known for its expansive menu; you can&rsquo;t really go wrong regardless of what you order. The Flatbush cafe also has a full espresso bar, so you can take the opportunity to order everything from a s&rsquo;mores latte to a rose latte with real rose petals. The spot is a 15-minute walk from the Flatbush House.</p>\r\n<p><em>1603 Cortelyou Rd., Flatbush</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"10 Our 5 Favorite Brooklyn Coffee Shops (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Screen%20Shot%202018-11-24%20at%202.16.52%20PM.png\" alt=\"Our 5 Favorite Brooklyn Coffee Shops (Image-2)\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>@cafemadeline.cortelyou/Instagram</em><br /><br /><br /></p>\r\n<h3>Dot &amp; Line</h3>\r\n<p>A 10-minute walk from the <a href=\"../the-downtown-brooklyn-house\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Downtown Brooklyn House</a> lies Dot &amp; Line, you&rsquo;ll find one of the best hidden treasures in Boerum Hill: Dot &amp; Line, a husband-and-wife-owned shop that feels delightfully Brooklyn when you step inside. The coffee is delicious without coming off as pretentious or trying too hard, just as Brooklyn coffee should be.</p>\r\n<p><em>253 Bergen St., Boerum Hill</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"10 Our 5 Favorite Brooklyn Coffee Shops (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Screen%20Shot%202018-11-24%20at%202.18.38%20PM.png\" alt=\"Our 5 Favorite Brooklyn Coffee Shops (Image-3)\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>@ms.coffeeeee/Instagram</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Brooklyn Roasting Company</h3>\r\n<p>Of Brooklyn Roasting Company&rsquo;s seven locations, we&rsquo;re in love with the DUMBO spot for it&rsquo;s open spaces, comfy couches and artsy, industrial vibe -- and, of course, for the delicious coffee. This also happens to be the company&rsquo;s roasting headquarters, so visit on a weekday to watch the magic happen.</p>\r\n<p><em>25 Jay Street, DUMBO</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"10 Our 5 Favorite Brooklyn Coffee Shops (Image-4), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Screen%20Shot%202018-11-24%20at%202.20.21%20PM.png\" alt=\"Our 5 Favorite Brooklyn Coffee Shops (Image-4)\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>@ladolcegia/Instagram</em><br /><br /><br /></p>\r\n<h3>Dweebs</h3>\r\n<p>Dweebs is a low-key, cheerful spot in Bushwick that makes us want to put our laptops away and enjoy the moment. On top of some truly killer cold brew, Dweebs features an eclectic variety of local art for purchase, as well as games like Scrabble and Stratego if you&rsquo;re in the mood to stick around for a while. The shop is a 20-minute walk from our East Bushwick and Bushwick houses, or a 5-minute walk from the DeKalb L stop.</p>\r\n<p><em>1434 DeKalb Ave., Bushwick</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"10 Our 5 Favorite Brooklyn Coffee Shops (Image-5), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Screen%20Shot%202018-11-24%20at%202.45.40%20PM.png\" alt=\"Our 5 Favorite Brooklyn Coffee Shops (Image-5)\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>@kae_kishimoto/Instagram</em><br /><br /><br /></p>', 'Screen Shot 2018-11-24 at 2.12.12 PM.png', 1, '2018-11-20 06:00:00', NULL, 0, 0, 0),
(166, '10 Holiday Events Happening in Brooklyn', 1, '10-holiday-events-happening-in-brooklyn', '', '10 Holiday Events Happening in Brooklyn', '10 Holiday Events Happening in Brooklyn', 'It’s beginning to look a lot like Christmas … and with Christmas (and Hanukkah!) comes a plethora of events to help you get into the holiday spirit, if that’s what you’re into.', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It&rsquo;s beginning to look a lot like Christmas &hellip; and with Christmas (and Hanukkah!) comes a plethora of events to help you get into the holiday spirit, if that&rsquo;s what you&rsquo;re into. Read on for 10 festive events taking place in Brooklyn in the coming weeks. </span></p>', '<p>It&rsquo;s beginning to look a lot like Christmas &hellip; and with Christmas (and Hanukkah!) comes a plethora of events to help you get into the holiday spirit, if that&rsquo;s what you&rsquo;re into. Read on for 10 festive events taking place in Brooklyn in the coming weeks.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Arkham: A Dark Holiday Celebration</strong></p>\r\n<p>Is a darker holiday more your vibe? Join BIZARRE Bushwick on Nov. 30 starting at 10:30 p.m. to open the week of Krampusnacht, the half-demon who punishes naughty children during the Christmas season.</p>\r\n<p>Arkham: A Dark Holiday Celebration will feature goth, industrial, post-punk, dark &lsquo;80s and more. Let your inner darkness out with absinthe cocktails and get your fortune told by Devil Dice Tarot. No cover.</p>\r\n<p><em>BIZARRE Bushwick, 12 Jefferson St., Bushwick</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>10th-Annual Latke Festival </strong></p>\r\n<p>The 10th-Annual Latke Festival is being held at the Brooklyn Museum on Dec. 3 from 6 p.m. - 8:30 p.m. More than two dozen varieties of potato pancakes from chefs around New York will be available for tasting, and participants get to help pick the best of the bunch. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Tickets start at $75 and the lower level includes unlimited latke and food tastings, along with beer, wine, cocktails and nonalcoholic beverages.</p>\r\n<p><em>Brooklyn Museum, 200 Eastern Pkwy., Prospect Park</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"10 Holiday Events Happening in Brooklyn (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Screen%20Shot%202018-11-28%20at%201.20.08%20PM.png\" alt=\"10 Holiday Events Happening in Brooklyn (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Credit: @gpfood/Instagram</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>DUMBO Holiday Tree Lighting</strong></p>\r\n<p>Head to the Pearl Street Triangle for the annual DUMBO Holiday Tree Lighting Ceremony on Dec. 6. The event takes place between 4 p.m.-7 p.m., but the tree is lit at 6 p.m. sharp. Hot cocoa and treats will be served.</p>\r\n<p>The occasion is also an opportunity to give back: If you&rsquo;d like, take an unwrapped toy for a child ages 0 to 14 for the Big Brooklyn Holiday Toy Drive.</p>\r\n<p><em>Pearl Street Triangle, 155 Water St., DUMBO</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Harry and the Potters&rsquo; 9th-Annual Yule Ball</strong></p>\r\n<p>If you&rsquo;re a Harry Potter fan, celebrate the holiday season like the witch or wizard you are at Harry and the Potters&rsquo; 9th-Annual Yule Ball at the Bell House on Dec. 15. Punk band Harry and the Potters have played hundreds of Harry Potter-themed shows over the years and were even named one of the best live shows of 2005 by Pitchfork. They&rsquo;ll be joined by the Whomping Willows, Tonks and the Aurors and the Swedish Shortsnouts to round out the night. Tickets are $22 and doors open at 5 p.m. for a 5:30 p.m. start.</p>\r\n<p><em>The Bell House, 149 7th St., Gowanus</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>The Mad Hatter&rsquo;s G&amp;T Party: Xmas Special</strong></p>\r\n<p>Head down the rabbit hole to experience Winter in Wonderland at the Mad Hatter&rsquo;s G&amp;T Party. Get started with a complimentary cocktail, then create three crazy molecular cocktails, all inside a cottage perched on top of a double-decker bus in East Williamsburg. Tickets also include snacks.</p>\r\n<p>The two-hour event is taking place on multiple dates throughout October.&nbsp;Tickets start at $40.</p>\r\n<p><em>Mad Hatter&rsquo;s Bus pop-up, 173 Morgan Ave., East Williamsburg</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"10 Holiday Events Happening in Brooklyn (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Screen%20Shot%202018-11-28%20at%201.18.13%20PM.png\" alt=\"10 Holiday Events Happening in Brooklyn (Image-2)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Credit: @jules_of_nyc/Instagram</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Wandering Winter Solstice Concert</strong></p>\r\n<p>Celebrate the winter solstice on Dec. 21 -- the shortest day of the year -- with Make Music New York at the Brooklyn Botanic Garden. Franz Schubert&rsquo;s 1828 song cycle<em> Winterreise </em>will be performed with the help of the crowd (via hand-held radios). The performance will migrate through different parts of the grounds, giving you the opportunity to visit recently restored sections of the garden.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>Brooklyn Botanic Garden, 990 Washington Ave., Prospect Park </em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Dyker Heights Christmas Lights Tour</strong></p>\r\n<p>One of the most popular holiday attractions in Brooklyn is the Dyker Heights christmas lights tour, and for good reason: tens of thousands of bulbs will transport you to a magical Christmas wonderland throughout the month of December.</p>\r\n<p>Plan to visit between mid-December and Christmas to get the full experience, and remember that many of the homeowners turn their lights off around 9 p.m.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>11th to 13th aves. (Dyker Heights Blvd) from 83rd to 86th streets, Dyker Heights</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"10 Holiday Events Happening in Brooklyn (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Screen%20Shot%202018-11-28%20at%201.15.38%20PM.png\" alt=\"10 Holiday Events Happening in Brooklyn (Image-3)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Credit: @Newyork_IG/Instagram</em><br /><br /></p>\r\n<p><strong>8th-Annual House of YES Xmas Spectacular </strong></p>\r\n<p>House of Yes has a host of festive events planned for Dec. 18-23 at the 8th-Annual House of YES Xmas Spectacular. Get ready to dance the night away in a holiday fever dream the likes of which only House of Yes could imagine, including Christmas trees, dancing presents, Santas and more. Tickets start at $30.</p>\r\n<p>In the mood for more on Christmas Eve? RSVP for free for a limited time for the Misfit Christmas on Dec. 24. House of Yes saved their best holiday shenanigans for last and have planned a blowout with cookies and milk, spiked hot cocoa, chinese food and movies, snow, runaway reindeer and more.</p>\r\n<p><em>House of Yes, 2 Wyckoff Ave., Bushwick</em><br /><br /><br /></p>\r\n<p><strong>Starry Night: A Night of Stargazing and Drinks</strong></p>\r\n<p>Head to Parklife on Dec. 18 from 8 p.m.-10 p.m. for Starry Night: A Night of Stargazing and Drinks. Expect to see the moon (of course), Orion and hopefully the Orion Nebula with a local astronomer and enjoy some drink specials while you gaze.</p>\r\n<p><em>Parklife, 636 Degraw St., Boerum Hill</em></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>', 'StockSnap_R0CX35EZFB-min.jpg', 1, '2018-11-27 06:00:00', NULL, 0, 0, 0),
(165, '#MemberMonday: Juan Ordóñez', 1, 'membermonday-juan-ordez', '', '#MemberMonday: Juan Ordóñez', '#MemberMonday: Juan Ordóñez', 'For this week’s #MemberMonday, we’re introducing you to Juan Ordóñez, a content creator at the East Bushwick House. ', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">For this week&rsquo;s </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">#MemberMonday</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, we&rsquo;re introducing you to Juan Ord&oacute;&ntilde;ez, a content creator at the </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">East Bushwick House</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. Juan has some exciting projects in the works and we can&rsquo;t wait to see them unfold. </span></p>', '<p>For this week&rsquo;s <strong>#MemberMonday,</strong> we&rsquo;re introducing you to Juan Ord&oacute;&ntilde;ez, a content creator at the East Bushwick House. Juan has some exciting projects in the works and we can&rsquo;t wait to see them unfold.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"10 #MemberMonday: Juan Ord&oacute;&ntilde;ez (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/juan-min.jpg\" alt=\"#MemberMonday: Juan Ord&oacute;&ntilde;ez (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Tell us about yourself.</h3>\r\n<p>I&rsquo;m a content creator, which means I basically create content like photos, videos and motion graphics for different social media brands. I post most of my work on Instagram (I&rsquo;m @nukanchik -- it means &ldquo;our people&rdquo; in Quechua). I do have a website, but I find it useless nowadays since everyone is using social media sites to represent brands.</p>\r\n<p>I was born here in Brooklyn but raised in Ecuador until I was 13. I lived for 3 years in Texas and when I was 16 I came to New York for vacation and ended up staying. I found so much culture that I could relate to and I didn&rsquo;t feel like an outsider anymore. I love taking photos, making movies, writing, biking, drinking coffee and eating sushi.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>What&rsquo;s your favorite Outpost Club memory?</h3>\r\n<p>I would say my favorite Outpost Club memory would be the <strong>Halloween party </strong>that was held in our house this year; everyone from different houses came through and we were all having fun.</p>\r\n<p>P.S., I love everything about the Outpost Club. It&rsquo;s a dream house.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>What&rsquo;s your favorite thing about Brooklyn?</h3>\r\n<p>I&rsquo;m a fan of Greenpoint. It&rsquo;s so chilled, laid back and colorful. There are some cool murals around and you can get the perfect view of the city -- and it&rsquo;s right next to McCarren Park.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>What are you working on right now?</h3>\r\n<p>I can&rsquo;t really say much, but the company that I&rsquo;m working with is The Soap Box. You can find them on Instagram: <strong>@tsbxco</strong>. Our media team is planning to launch something revolutionary that will change people&rsquo;s lives, so keep an eye on it!</p>', 'juan-min.jpg', 1, '2018-11-26 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(358, 'Our 5 favorite at-home exercises', 1, 'our-5-favorite-at-home-exercises', '', 'Our 5 favorite at-home exercises', 'Our 5 favorite at-home exercises', 'Keeping fit in quarantine may seem like a struggle, but there are a surprising amount of isolation exercise routines and programs cropping up all over the internet which you can do from the confines of your four walls.', '<p>Keeping fit in quarantine may seem like a struggle, but there are a surprising amount of isolation exercise routines and programs cropping up all over the internet which you can do from the confines of your four walls.</p>', '<p>Keeping fit in quarantine may seem like a struggle, but there are a surprising amount of isolation exercise routines and programs cropping up all over the internet which you can do from the confines of your four walls.</p>\r\n<h1><strong>1. Burpees</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">According to personal trainer </span><a href=\"https://www.businessinsider.com/how-to-work-out-at-home-in-case-coronavirus-quarantine-2020-3?r=US&amp;IR=T\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Bryan Goldberg</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, burpees (also known as squat thrusts) are the most effective form of at-home exercise in a confined space. A burpee is a full body exercise, beginning in a standing position, moving into a squat with your hands on the ground, then kicking your feet back into a plank position and immediately returning to a squat position before standing up. You can find full instructions and a visual guide </span><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TU8QYVW0gDU\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">here</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. Always remember to go at your own pace, so why not start with 5 or 10 at a time and build up the amount of burpees you complete in a day gradually? Just make sure any fury friends are out the way first!</span></p>\r\n<h1><strong>2.&nbsp;</strong><strong style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Squats</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Squats are one of the most accessible forms of at-home exercise. They&rsquo;re also one of the best ways of burning fat and building muscle that you can do without the help of a personal trainer (or even a mirror). Try the </span><a href=\"https://www.coachmag.co.uk/exercises/full-body-workouts/1655/30-day-squat-challenge\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">30 day squat challenge</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> to build up your fitness in a controlled, effective way. The best part of this challenge is the structure it will give your life in quarantine. Watch the next 30 days pass you by with a tighter, more agile physique as your reward.</span></p>\r\n<h1><strong><strong>3. Skipping</strong></strong>&nbsp;</h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Why not add some childhood nostalgia into your workout routine? Skipping is both fun and good exercise, making it the perfect way to lift your spirits in quarantine. According to the </span><a href=\"https://www.brsa.org.uk/skipping-rope-as-sports-training/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">British Skipping Rope Association</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, skipping is a great full body workout; it can help boost your immune system, improve your overall health and just one hour of the activity can burn 1,600 calories.</span></p>\r\n<h1><strong>4.&nbsp;</strong><strong style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Stair training</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Whether you&rsquo;re isolating in a house with stairs or an apartment block with probably even more stairs, stairs are the one piece of exercise equiptment most people have available to them. Stair training is also a surprisingly great form of exercise and the perfect way to feel as though you&rsquo;re moving in these otherwise static times. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">According to </span><a href=\"https://www.runsociety.com/training/stair-climbing-vs-running/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Run Society</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, the benefits of stair climbing are huge, with the vertical movement in particular making for an effective workout, as your leg muscles are forced to resist gravity to lift your body while the rest of your body must stabilize and balance. Stair climbing is ideal for training your calves, hamstrings, glutes and quads, toning your lower body and boosting your stamina. Try walking or running up and down your most accessible stairs for 15-20 minutes, gradually building your workout up to 30 minutes. Just be&nbsp;sure to practice social distancing if you encounter other people from outside your household.</span></p>\r\n<h1><strong>5.&nbsp;</strong><strong style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Jumping jacks</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Jumping jacks are fun and, let&rsquo;s face it, we all know how to do them. This activity is also incredibly versatile as you can do as many as you feel comfortable doing in your workout. According to </span><a href=\"https://www.healthline.com/health/fitness-exercise/jumping-jacks\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Healthline</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, jumping jacks work your heart, lungs and muscles at the same time by combining aerobic exercise and resistance work and are specifically good for working your glutes, quadriceps and hip flexors. They&rsquo;re great for both movement and agility and the ideal activity to do while listening to your favorite 80s songs on repeat. So why not get your leg warmers on and start jumping?</span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>', '2_12.jpg', 1, '2020-04-12 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
