(188, '#MemberMonday: Franco Palomo', 1, 'membermonday-franco-palomo', '', '#MemberMonday: Franco Palomo', '#MemberMonday: Franco Palomo', 'This week\'s #MemberMonday will introduce you to Franco Palomo, a budding architect who lives in the Bed-Stuy House', '<p>This week\'s #MemberMonday will introduce you to Franco Palomo, a budding architect who lives in the Bed-Stuy House. Read on to learn more about his projects and what his mom\'s biggest complaint about him is.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>This week\'s <strong>#MemberMonday</strong> will introduce you to Franco Palomo, a budding architect who lives in the <a href=\"../the-bed-stuy-house\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Bed-Stuy House</a>. Read on to learn more about his projects and what his mom\'s biggest complaint about him is.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"5 #MemberMonday: Franco Palomo (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Screen%20Shot%202018-12-03%20at%2012.41.33%20PM.png\" alt=\"#MemberMonday: Franco Palomo (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<h3>Tell us a bit about yourself.</h3>\r\n<p>I was born and raised in Austin, Texas, and currently studying architecture at UT Austin. Being in architecture school has allowed to study and work abroad in some amazing places. Last year I had the opportunity to study and travel through Europe with some of my classmates. We visited 12 different countries in 4 months. Now I&rsquo;m currently doing a 6-month internship for an architecture firm in Lower Manhattan. I&rsquo;ll be wrapping up the internship in a few weeks and heading back to Austin to finish my last semester. I have no clue where life will take me after that!</p>\r\n<p>In my spare time I enjoy listening to music, going to concerts, watching movies, drawing and taking photos. New friends say I&rsquo;m easy-going. Old friends tell me I need to work on my texting. Roommates would say I need to go out more. Co-workers say I&rsquo;m always snacking. Mom says I never call.</p>\r\n<h3>What&rsquo;s your favorite Outpost memory?</h3>\r\n<p>The Knickerbocker House! I met some of the coolest people there. Will always remember the countless nights we either stayed in and watched movies or went out as a group to our local bar. These are the types of nights that turn roommates into family.</p>\r\n<h3>Do you have a favorite place in Brooklyn?</h3>\r\n<p>I really enjoy walking around Williamsburg. Gives me hipster Austin, Texas, vibes that make me feel at home in a different city. The architect in me loves that area because of Domino Park &hellip; such a nicely designed park with a great view of Manhattan. 12/10 would recommend.</p>\r\n<h3>What are you currently working on?</h3>\r\n<p>At the office I&rsquo;m currently working on a few things: a renovation of an apartment building on the Upper East Side, a pavilion in Miami and a synagogue in upstate NY. Other tasks done at work include: trying to look busy, buying plane tickets, thinking of clever Instagram captions (<strong>@franco.cean)</strong>, writing this Member Monday and calling my mom.</p>', 'Screen Shot 2018-12-03 at 12.41.33 PM.png', 1, '2018-12-03 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(189, 'Outpost Club Expands to Manhattan', 1, 'outpost-club-expands-to-manhattan', '', 'Outpost Club Expands to Manhattan', 'Outpost Club Expands to Manhattan', 'Renting in New York should be as easy as buying a cup of coffee. That’s why Brooklyn-based co-living startup Outpost Club is expanding across the East River with its first house in Manhattan, just a few blocks from Central Park.', '<p>Renting in New York should be as easy as buying a cup of coffee. That&rsquo;s why Brooklyn-based co-living startup Outpost Club is expanding across the East River with its first house in Manhattan, just a few blocks from Central Park.</p>', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">MANHATTAN -- Renting in New York should be as easy as buying a cup of coffee. That&rsquo;s why Brooklyn-based co-living startup Outpost Club is expanding across the East River with its first house in Manhattan, just a few blocks from Central Park. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Central Park Manhattan House represents a new chapter for Outpost Club as it continues to further its mission to make living in New York more affordable while providing a built-in community for new members and removing the typical hassles between roommates. </span></p>\r\n<p><em><strong>&ldquo;We&rsquo;re working toward our goal to make living affordably and easy in all five boroughs of New York City,&rdquo; </strong>Outpost Club CEO Sergii Starostin said.<strong> &ldquo;Expanding into Manhattan is the next logical step for us, so we&rsquo;re excited.&rdquo; </strong></em></p>\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The company currently has seven co-living houses: six in <a href=\"../rooms-for-rent-in-brooklyn\" target=\"_blank\">Brooklyn</a>, in the Williamsburg, Boerum Hill, Bushwick, Flatbush and Bed-Stuy neighborhoods, and one house in Ridgewood, Queens. </span></h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Central Park Manhattan House has 22 bedrooms across five apartments, each of which are fully furnished -- including a shared kitchen with all kitchen appliances and essentials, including pans, dishes&nbsp;and dish soap. All rooms at the house are private, and each room comes with a memory foam mattress, pillows, extension cords, bed linens and towels. Bathrooms throughout the house come with regularly re-stocked essentials like toilet paper and hand soap. All utilities are wired and ready for use. Tenants just need to bring their suitcases.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><em>&ldquo;Our end goal is to make it so anyone can find a place to live, sign a lease, pay and move in within a reasonable amount of time, just by using their phone,&rdquo; </em></strong><em>S</em><em>tarostin said.</em><strong><em> &ldquo;We do the legwork to make sure every potential housemate is thoroughly vetted so our members don&rsquo;t have to.&rdquo;</em></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Membership with Outpost Club is a flexible, month-to-month commitment that does not require extensive documents, large deposits or guarantors, but the longer the commitment, the better the price. The minimum lease length is one month. </strong></p>\r\n<h3><strong>Private rooms at the Central Park Manhattan House start at $1490.</strong></h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Outpost Club was founded in 2016 by a team who knows what it&rsquo;s like to move to new places and start from scratch. Outpost founders have developed a process to make it incredibly easy to move to New York, with no scams, hidden fees, startup costs or massive security deposits. Outpost Club members gain an instant community with opportunities to socialize, network and grow, all in beautiful and convenient houses at affordable prices.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><img title=\"5 Outpost Club Expands to Manhattan (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/350manhattan_large-5.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Club Expands to Manhattan (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"5 Outpost Club Expands to Manhattan (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/350manhattan_large-10.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Club Expands to Manhattan (Image-2)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"5 Outpost Club Expands to Manhattan (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/350manhattan_large-13.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Club Expands to Manhattan (Image-3)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>', '350manhattan_large-5.jpg', 1, '2018-12-04 06:00:00', NULL, 0, 0, 0),
(190, '5 Reasons Coliving Might Be for You', 1, '5-reasons-coliving-might-be-for-you', '', '5 Reasons Coliving Might Be for You', '5 Reasons Coliving Might Be for You', 'Coliving has exploded in popularity over the past couple years, and for good reason', '<p>Coliving has exploded in popularity over the past couple years, and for good reason: The benefits of building a community with others -- in addition to sharing space -- are far-reaching. Here are five reasons you might want to give coliving a try.</p>', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Coliving has exploded in popularity over the past couple years, and for good reason: The benefits of building a community with others -- in addition to sharing space -- are far-reaching. Here are five reasons you might want to give coliving a try.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You like experiencing different cultures</span></h2>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We all know New York is a great place to meet people from around the world, but aside from traveling, sharing space is a great way to learn about other places and cultures. Our members hail from nearly every state in the U.S. and dozens of countries, speak a variety of languages and love sharing their cultures with one another. Regardless of where you&rsquo;re from, you&rsquo;ll fit right in.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You like exploring new neighborhoods</span></h2>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Part of the fun of living in New York City is the diversity of its neighborhoods; it&rsquo;s difficult to get bored when you have such a variety of cultures, personalities and entertainment everywhere you go. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Why tie yourself down to just one spot, then? For the length of your lease with Outpost Club, you&rsquo;re welcome to switch between any of our houses in Bushwick, Williamsburg, Flatbush, <a href=\"../the-downtown-brooklyn-house\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Boerum Hill</a>, &nbsp;<a href=\"../the-bed-stuy-house\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Bed-Stuy</a> and the <a href=\"../central-park-manhattan-house\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Upper West Side</a>. How&rsquo;s that for variety?</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You want to network in a new city</span></h2>\r\n<p>We love the sheer variety of experiences our members bring with them to Outpost Club. We have entrepreneurs, musicians, writers, artists, chefs and more at our houses. Chances are, if you&rsquo;re interested in something, we have a member who&rsquo;s doing it as you read this.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"5 Reasons Coliving Might Be for You (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Screen%20Shot%202018-12-06%20at%2011.38.24%20AM.png\" alt=\"5 Reasons Coliving Might Be for You (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You need a flexible living arrangement </span></h2>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Do you need a spot for just a month or two, or are you looking for a long-term lease? We&rsquo;ve got you covered, either way. Apply and you could be moving in as little as a day. How easy is that? </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Our homes are fully furnished and WiFi and utilities are included with your membership. We provide everything from the blender to toilet paper, so you never have to worry about running out of anything important -- all you have to bring with you is your suitcase. </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You want to be a part of \"something\"</span></h2>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It can be difficult to find your place in a new city, especially somewhere as big as New York. Sure, you can find roommates and explore your new neighborhood on your own, but it can be easy to end up acting like a hermit when you don&rsquo;t know anyone. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><a href=\"../coliving\" target=\"_blank\">Coliving</a> has a way of making you feel like less of a tiny fish in a giant pond, though. You&rsquo;ll move into a built-in community of people who welcome new experiences and new people with open arms, and -- before you know it -- you&rsquo;ll find yourself feeling right at home.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'Screen Shot 2018-12-06 at 11.35.36 AM.png', 1, '2018-12-06 06:00:00', NULL, 0, 0, 0),
(191, '#MemberMonday: Charlotte Ryckeboer', 1, 'membermonday-charlotte-ryckeboer', '', '#MemberMonday: Charlotte Ryckeboer', '#MemberMonday: Charlotte Ryckeboer', 'For this week’s #MemberMonday, meet Charlotte Ryckeboer, Outpost Club’s awesome photographer and a member at the East Williamsburg House', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">For this week&rsquo;s </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">#MemberMonday</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, meet Charlotte Ryckeboer, Outpost Club&rsquo;s awesome photographer and a member at the </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">East Williamsburg House</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. You&rsquo;ve probably seen her at one of our events!</span></p>', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">For this week&rsquo;s </span><strong>#MemberMonday</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, meet Charlotte Ryckeboer, Outpost Club&rsquo;s awesome photographer and a member at the </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">East Williamsburg House</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. You&rsquo;ve probably seen her at one of our events! </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><img title=\"#MemberMonday: Charlotte Ryckeboer (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Screen%20Shot%202018-12-10%20at%202.56.20%20PM.png\" alt=\"#MemberMonday: Charlotte Ryckeboer (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><strong>Tell us a bit about yourself. </strong></h2>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">I&rsquo;m a 21-year-old film student from Belgium and am currently studying at SVA New York for one semester. Besides film, I&rsquo;m also interested in photography (</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">@ryckeboer_photo</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> on instagram). I like to take portraits of people and animals in my free time and I&rsquo;m also the photographer for Outpost. I capture all the fun moments we have with Outpost Club.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><strong>What&rsquo;s your favorite Outpost memory?</strong></h2>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">My favorite Outpost &nbsp;memory was the </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">hiking trip to Bear Mountain</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">! It was so beautiful and I made a lot new friends.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h2><strong>What&rsquo;s your favorite part of Brooklyn? </strong></h2>\r\n<p>My favorite thing about Brooklyn is DUMBO! It&rsquo;s such a lovely neighborhood and a great spot to take photographs, as well!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><strong>What are you working on right now? </strong></h2>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Right now I&rsquo;m making a short film, but I can&rsquo;t tell you much about it yet. But here is a little sneak peek:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><img title=\"#MemberMonday: Charlotte Ryckeboer (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Screen%20Shot%202018-12-10%20at%203.33.25%20PM.png\" alt=\"#MemberMonday: Charlotte Ryckeboer (Image-2)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /> </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'Screen Shot 2018-12-10 at 2.56.20 PM.png', 1, '2018-12-10 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
