(193, 'Review from Nawar about The Bushwick House', 2, 'review-from-nawar-about-the-bushwick-house', '', 'Nawar / The Bushwick House', 'Review from Nawar about The Bushwick House', 'What Nawar thinks about The Bushwick House - customer review about Outpost Club', '', '<p>It\'s a great place to stay for those who <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">is new to New York.</span></p>', 'nawar.png', 1, '2018-12-01 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(194, 'Review from Olga about The Bushwick House', 2, 'review-from-olga-about-the-bushwick-house', '', 'Olga / The Bushwick House', 'Review from Olga about The Bushwick House', 'What Olga thinks about The Bushwick House - customer review about Outpost Club', '', '<p>Great location, made friends and memories.</p>', 'olga.png', 1, '2018-12-01 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(195, 'Review from Ethan about The Ridgewood House', 2, 'review-from-ethan-about-the-ridgewood-house', '', 'Ethan / The Ridgewood House', 'Review from Ethan about The Ridgewood House', 'What Ethan thinks about The Ridgewood House - customer review about Outpost Club', '', '<p>This is a good option for those looking to stay in NYC short term (and even long term) for a decent price. Everyone in the house is really friendly. The space is nice and the neighborhood has great food options.</p>', 'ethan.png', 1, '2018-12-01 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(196, 'Review from Robert about The Bushwick House', 2, 'review-from-robert-about-the-bushwick-house', '', 'Robert / The Bushwick House', 'Review from Robert about The Bushwick House', 'What Robert thinks about The Bushwick House - customer review about Outpost Club', '', '<p>Bushwick is an up and coming area. Nice apartment. Air conditioning, lounge and rooms</p>', 'robert.png', 1, '2018-08-01 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(197, 'Review from Svenja about The Ridgewood House', 2, 'review-from-svenja-about-the-ridgewood-house', '', 'Svenja / The Ridgewood House', 'Review from Svenja about The Ridgewood House', 'What Svenja thinks about The Ridgewood House - customer review about Outpost Club', '', '<p>Moving into this place was the best thing that could have happened to me during my time in NYC. I was living at another place before where with lots of troubles and needed a new solution asap. Anyone who ever lived in NY knows about the difficulty of finding a nice and affordable place in the city. This house offers pretty much everything you need, they even provide shampoo haha! It is a very nice coliving place..everything looks exactly as on the pictures, it\'s always clean and it offers you the perfect chance to get to know people from all over the world. Give it a try, living in New York is not cheap but this place orders you a lot for a pretty good price. You\'ll have me back someday :)</p>', 'svenja.png', 1, '2018-12-03 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(198, 'Review from Ammon about The East Bushwick House', 2, 'review-from-ammon-about-the-east-bushwick-house', '', 'Ammon / The East Bushwick House', 'Review from Ammon about The East Bushwick House', 'What Ammon thinks about The East Bushwick House - customer review about Outpost Club', '', '<p>Excellent environment and location, really appreciated the basement and rooftop access. The space is kept clean, the design is beautiful.</p>', 'ammon.png', 1, '2018-12-03 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(199, 'Review from André about The Bushwick House', 2, 'review-from-andr-about-the-bushwick-house', '', 'André / The Bushwick House', 'Review from André about The Bushwick House', 'What André thinks about The Bushwick House - customer review about Outpost Club', '', '<p>I would like to say that Simon was awesome!! He&rsquo;s really good person, He&rsquo;s happy and funny, It&rsquo;s so good to us guests when we&rsquo;re abroad. If you&rsquo;re traveling alone It&rsquo;s not a problem because you can know a lot of diferent people in his house. Some times he do a little party to eat and drink some thing and this party you can do some friend or just know another person or culture. I really recommend to stay at Simon&rsquo;s house (Outpost Club). Enjoy your stay!</p>', 'andr.png', 1, '2018-12-01 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(200, 'Review from Andres about The Ridgewood House', 2, 'review-from-andres-about-the-ridgewood-house', '', 'Andres / The Ridgewood House', 'Review from Andres about The Ridgewood House', 'What Andres thinks about The Ridgewood House - customer review about Outpost Club', '', '<p>The Ridgewood house was awesome and I would definitely stay there again. You get I to meet people from all walks of life. The Ridgewood neighborhood has a lot of neat little humble restaurants and stores. I would recommend checking out Julia\'s beer and wine! It\'s near the house!</p>', 'andres.png', 1, '2018-12-03 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(201, 'Review from Tikva about The Ridgewood House', 2, 'review-from-tikva-about-the-ridgewood-house', '', 'Tikva / The Ridgewood House', 'Review from Tikva about The Ridgewood House', 'What Tikva thinks about The Ridgewood House - customer review about Outpost Club', '', '<p>Good place to stay. Plenty of communication and the people were nice and easy to get along with.</p>', 'tikva.png', 1, '2018-12-01 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(202, 'Review from Lathaniel about The East Bushwick House', 2, 'review-from-lathaniel-about-the-east-bushwick-house', '', 'Lathaniel / The East Bushwick House', 'Review from Lathaniel about The East Bushwick House', 'What Lathaniel thinks about The East Bushwick House - customer review about Outpost Club', '', '<p>This AirBnB is a real home away from home. It is new, stylish, clean and very well-kept. The location is close to subway, yet the area very quiet and suburban with close facilities (shops, bars &amp; hotspots). The facilities here include washer, dryer TV and communal space. It is a true apartment style house away from home. Also no need to bring houseware. Everything is provided. Alex and co were very generous and communicated in timely manner (thanks Jacob, Karisa and Erik), house mates were amazing! I felt welcomed and had all questions answered if needed. I honestly would not bother trying anywhere else, just because the bar and standard has been set. This is how to run a business! When I return for Holiday or Work, Outpost is where I\'ll always be going! Love you guys! :)</p>', 'lathaniel.png', 1, '2018-12-02 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(203, 'Review from Bernard about The Flatbush House', 2, 'review-from-bernard-about-the-flatbush-house', '', 'Bernard / The Flatbush House', 'Review from Bernard about The Flatbush House', 'What Bernard thinks about The Flatbush House - customer review about Outpost Club', '', '<p>This a great value. The place is stylish and has great amenities.</p>', 'bernard.png', 1, '2018-12-01 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(204, 'Review from Tom about The Flatbush House', 2, 'review-from-tom-about-the-flatbush-house', '', 'Tom / The Flatbush House', 'Review from Tom about The Flatbush House', 'What Tom thinks about The Flatbush House - customer review about Outpost Club', '', '<p>As advertised, hassle free, great communication</p>', 'tom.png', 1, '2018-12-01 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(205, 'Review from Debbie about The Bushwick House', 2, 'review-from-debbie-about-the-bushwick-house', '', 'Debbie / The Bushwick House', 'Review from Debbie about The Bushwick House', 'What Debbie thinks about The Bushwick House - customer review about Outpost Club', '', '<p>Highly recommended for solo travelers. It is easy to get around and there are convenient stores almost every other blocks. It&rsquo;s a pretty safe neighborhood as well, so solo travelers don&rsquo;t have to worry about that, especially female travelers. It is also very easy to cook in the kitchen because the equipment is pretty complete. The outpost club is really helpful and friendly, so feel free to ask them questions if you have any.</p>', 'debbie.png', 1, '2018-12-03 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(206, 'Review from Max about The Flatbush House', 2, 'review-from-max-about-the-flatbush-house', '', 'Max / The Flatbush House', 'Review from Max about The Flatbush House', 'What Max thinks about The Flatbush House - customer review about Outpost Club', '', '<p>Thoroughly enjoyed my month-long stay here. The place is very welcoming, comfortable, and clean. Would recommend this location to anyone!</p>', 'max.png', 1, '2018-12-01 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(207, 'Review from Natacha about The Flatbush House', 2, 'review-from-natacha-about-the-flatbush-house', '', 'Natacha / The Flatbush House', 'Review from Natacha about The Flatbush House', 'What Natacha thinks about The Flatbush House - customer review about Outpost Club', '', '<p>I stay at Flatbush\'s house and then I moved to Bedford\'s house. This is something that I really thought cool: if you need for any reason to move to another Outpost house, you can if they have a bed available. The places are nice, you can save some money with food because people always let something when they left. You may have some issues with train lines after 10pm, and on weekends, because some lines stop working or just delay more than the usual so be prepared. People on Bedford\'s house was amazing and made my staying at the house and in NY better and funnier. They are always having some party or celebration with all the houses, time to time. Any issue you can talk with Valentin or Jacob, they will help you wherever you need.</p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>', 'natacha.png', 1, '2018-12-03 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(208, 'Review from Rey about The Bushwick House', 2, 'review-from-rey-about-the-bushwick-house', '', 'Rey / The Bushwick House', 'Review from Rey about The Bushwick House', 'What Rey thinks about The Bushwick House - customer review about Outpost Club', '', '<p>I genuinely enjoyed my time at the Ridgewood house, the hosts of the house were both great, attentive , extremely welcoming and kind hosts that were always catering to our needs and available to hear any concerns the residents, including myself, had. The house was very clean and very spacious with AWESOME amenities (we all LOVED the big screen tv with netflix!) and was conveniently located next to the subway (right next door!).</p>', 'rey.png', 1, '2018-12-03 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(209, 'Review from Pratap about The Bushwick House', 2, 'review-from-pratap-about-the-bushwick-house', '', 'Pratap / The Bushwick House', 'Review from Pratap about The Bushwick House', 'What Pratap thinks about The Bushwick House - customer review about Outpost Club', '', '<p>It\'s well maintained, and the hospitality is good. While I was there Simon conducted pizza making party, and it\'s awesome! And I already booked the future stay with them.</p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>', 'pratap.png', 1, '2018-12-03 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(210, 'Review from Ranon about The Clark House', 2, 'review-from-ranon-about-the-clark-house', '', 'Ranon / The Ridgewood House', 'Review from Ranon about The Clark House', 'What Ranon thinks about The Clark House - customer review about Outpost Club', '', '<p>Staying at Outpost turned out to be a great experience! At first I was unsure if I would like staying in a house full of so many people, but Jacob and the residents at Ridgewood made me feel at home as soon as I arrived and made my stay enjoyable. I\'ll definitely recommend this place to friends!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a style=\"color: #c01e32;\" href=\"../the-clark-house\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferer\">Explore The Clark House</a></p>', 'ranon.png', 1, '2018-12-03 06:00:00', '2022-08-05 14:20:59', NULL, 0, 0),
(211, 'Review from Jazlyn about The Williamsburg House', 2, 'review-from-jazlyn-about-the-williamsburg-house', '', 'Jazlyn / The Williamsburg House', 'Review from Jazlyn about The Williamsburg House', 'What Jazlyn thinks about The Williamsburg House - customer review about Outpost Club', '', '<p>Fine place to stay if you are in nyc and are looking for a place with amenities you need.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a style=\"color: #c01e32;\" href=\"../the-williamsburg-house\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferer\">Explore The Williamsburg House</a></p>', 'jazlyn.png', 1, '2018-12-03 06:00:00', '2022-08-05 14:19:42', NULL, 0, 0),
(212, 'Review from Emanuela about The Bushwick House', 2, 'review-from-emanuela-about-the-bushwick-house', '', 'Emanuela / The Bushwick House', 'Review from Emanuela about The Bushwick House', 'What Emanuela thinks about The Bushwick House - customer review about Outpost Club', '', '<p>The place is awesome! I think it is very difficult to find such a clean, modern, well equipped and well organized place in NYC. Many things I didn&rsquo;t expected were provided like tea, coffee, salt and pepper and oil. Also they provide slippers to stay in the house! Once a week, all floors are cleaned. On each floor you have all you need and if something is being used by somebody else you can take that from the other floors: all is for everybody in the building. Each floor has a loundry machine, a dryer and a dishwasher. Also, they organize events to stay altogether. But even if you don&rsquo;t go to, this place always give you much more chances to meet people and never be alone than any other renting solution! There are many parts in the house where you can relax, not only your bedroom! I&rsquo;m definitely satisfied of this place and I feel very lucky to have found it!</p>', 'emanuela.png', 1, '2018-12-02 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(213, 'Review from Elie about The Greenpoint House', 2, 'review-from-elie-about-the-greenpoint-house', '', 'Elie / The Greenpoint House', 'Review from Elie about The Greenpoint House', 'What Elie thinks about The Greenpoint House - customer review about Outpost Club', '', '<p>Overall great co-living space. You get to meet lots of folks from different corners of the world and that\'s what I loved about it. Location is great, literally one minute walk to Line M\'s Forest Avenue. Lots of shops within walking distance, and most importantly it seems like a safe neighborhood.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a style=\"color: #c01e32;\" href=\"../the-greenpoint-house\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferer\">Explore The Greenpoint House</a></p>', 'elie.png', 1, '2018-12-03 06:00:00', '2022-08-05 14:17:37', NULL, 0, 0),
(214, 'Review from Rebecca about The Bed-Study House', 2, 'review-from-rebecca-about-the-bed-study-house', '', 'Rebecca / The Bed-Study House', 'Review from Rebecca about The Bed-Study House', 'What Rebecca thinks about The Bed-Study House - customer review about Outpost Club', '', '<p>This is a perfect place for a short or long stay in New York. The apartment was stylish and has great amenities. I would definitely stay here again should I end up in New York sometime soon.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a style=\"color: #c01e32;\" href=\"../the-bed-stuy-house\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferer\">Explore Bed-Study House</a></p>', 'rebecca.png', 1, '2018-12-03 06:00:00', '2022-08-05 14:15:53', NULL, 0, 0),
(215, 'Review from Blake about The Bed-Study House', 2, 'review-from-blake-about-the-bed-study-house', '', 'Blake / The Bed-Stuy House', 'Review from Blake about The Bed-Study House', 'What Blake thinks about The Bed-Stuy House - customer review about Outpost Club', '', '<p>Amazing host and an amazing experience! Extremely friendly host that plan multiple group events a week. The apartment has cleaners come by twice a week so the place was always clean. laundry on site. Located in a quiet neighborhood. Public transportation within a 5 minute walk. Amazing amenities. I highly recommend Outpost.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a style=\"color: #c01e32;\" href=\"../the-bed-stuy-house\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferer\">Explore Bed-Study House</a></p>', 'blake.png', 1, '2018-12-03 06:00:00', '2022-08-05 14:15:18', NULL, 0, 0),
(216, 'Destination: Braven Brewing Company ', 1, 'destination-braven-brewing-company-', '', 'Destination: Braven Brewing Company ', 'Destination: Braven Brewing Company ', 'Nestled in industrial Bushwick in a neighborhood packed with art galleries is Braven Brewing Company, a recently opened craft brewery, bar and kitchen whose founders hope will become an area mainstay -- and for good reason.', '<p dir=\"ltr\">Nestled in industrial Bushwick in a neighborhood packed with art galleries is Braven Brewing Company, a recently opened craft brewery, bar and kitchen whose founders hope will become an area mainstay -- and for good reason.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</p>', '<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>by Lauren Vega</em></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Nestled in industrial Bushwick in a neighborhood packed with art galleries is <a href=\"https://www.bravenbrewing.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Braven Brewing Company</a>, a recently opened craft brewery, bar and kitchen whose founders hope will become an area mainstay -- and for good reason.</p>\r\n<p>The brewery itself is modern without being too minimalist, its industrial-chic decor giving off a cozy vibe that embraces you as soon as you open the door. The 4-foot fence around the brewing area welcomes curious patrons to take a look at the brewing process.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">The tap list is broad enough to suit any beer-lover&rsquo;s palate, with brews on one recent visit ranging from Guilty Feet -- a sour ale brewed with cranberries -- to the more familiar Bushwick Pilsner, based on the pilsners brewed in Bushwick for over a century.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">The kitchen adds some class to what you might normally think of when it comes to bar food, with dishes like fish and chips, a southern-fried chicken sandwich and the vegan Beyond burger sure to satisfy late-night cravings.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">The company itself has been around since 2013, with co-founders Eric Feldman and Marshall Thompson having moved from homebrewing in 2009 to distributing through local businesses and finally opening their first brick-and-mortar brewery in September of this year.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Braven is also heavily involved in Brooklyn&rsquo;s creative scene, having partnered with institutions like the Bushwick Film Festival and the Bushwick Collective. It&rsquo;s no wonder the brewery wants to appeal to local writers, artists and musicians -- and from what we&rsquo;ve seen, it works. In fact, we&rsquo;re so excited about having Braven in the neighborhood that we&rsquo;re hoping to work more closely with the brewery in the future, so keep an eye on the Outpost blog for more details!<br /><br /><em>Braven Brewing Company | 52 Harrison Pl, Bushwick | M-F 5 p.m.-12 a.m.; Sa-Su 11 a.m.-12 a.m.</em></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><em><img title=\"Destination: Braven Brewing Company (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Event_BravenBrewingCo_GrandOpening-52.jpg\" alt=\"Destination: Braven Brewing Company (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></em></p>', 'Braven Beer Flight.jpg', 1, '2018-12-12 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(217, '#MemberMonday: Marcia Lima', 1, 'membermonday-marcia-lima', '', '#MemberMonday: Marcia Lima', '#MemberMonday: Marcia Lima', 'For this week’s #MemberMonday, we’re introducing you to Marcia, a full-time traveler from Brazil and our East Bushwick and Bushwick house leader', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">For this week&rsquo;s </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">#MemberMonday</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, we&rsquo;re introducing you to Marcia, a full-time traveler from Brazil and our </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">East Bushwick</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Bushwick</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> house leader. Read on to find out what she&rsquo;s doing now that she&rsquo;s free to travel the world.</span></p>', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">For this week&rsquo;s </span><strong>#MemberMonday</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, we&rsquo;re introducing you to Marcia, a full-time traveler from Brazil and our </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">East Bushwick</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Bushwick</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> house leader. Read on to find out what she&rsquo;s doing now that she&rsquo;s free to travel the world.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><img title=\"#MemberMonday: Marcia Lima (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/Screen%20Shot%202018-12-17%20at%202.08.07%20PM.png\" alt=\"#MemberMonday: Marcia Lima (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></span></p>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Tell us a bit about yourself.</span></h2>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">I&rsquo;m a translator and full-time traveler from Brazil. Three years ago I sold everything I had, gave up on the idea of renting an apartment long-term and went out to discover the world. I try to stay at least 6 months in each country, so I haven&rsquo;t been to too many places yet, but I&rsquo;m in no rush whatsoever.</span></p>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">What\'s your favorite thing about Outpost?</span></h2>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">I love the sense of community between everyone at Outpost, and the fact we have creative minds from all over the world coming together in these beautiful houses in New York is really something special. Also, the events are always so interesting! I want to go to as many as I can.</span></p>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Do you have a favorite place in Brooklyn? Where do you want to explore more?</span></h2>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">My instagram handle (</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">@_BKbound_</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">) says it all: It doesn&rsquo;t matter where I am in the world -- I&rsquo;m always thinking of going back to Brooklyn. So, it&rsquo;s really impossible to pick just one favorite place: I love catching a late night movie at Nitehawk Cinema; going to Red Hook when I&rsquo;m craving some key-lime pie; thrift shopping at all the L Train Vintage stores; working remotely from the beautiful Brooklyn Public Library; eating at the many amazing Latino restaurants when I want to reconnect with my roots &hellip; You have a different thing to do every day and night and this is what I love the most about Brooklyn.</span></p>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">What are you working on right now?</span></h2>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">I&rsquo;m the house leader for the Bushwick and East Bushwick houses, which is the coolest gig in the world because I&rsquo;ve been able to meet amazing people and try to make their lives easier from the moment they get to the city. Apart from that, I&rsquo;m a localization curator for a GIF company, and I do subtitling and research for a streaming company. I&rsquo;m also trying to work on some photography and writing projects.</span></p>', 'Screen Shot 2018-12-17 at 2.08.07 PM.png', 1, '2018-12-14 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(218, 'Here\'s What You Should Do If Your Roommate Isn\'t Pulling Their Weight', 1, 'heres-what-you-should-do-if-your-roommate-isnt-pulling-their-weight', '', 'Here\'s What You Should Do If Your Roommate Isn\'t Pulling Their Weight | Outpost Club blog', 'Here\'s What You Should Do If Your Roommate Isn\'t Pulling Their Weight', 'Living with other people is a series of compromises and getting used to everyone’s unique habits and needs. We all have to put work into keeping the atmosphere in our houses positive and respectful, but sometimes that balance gets thrown off when someone isn’t pulling their weight.', '<p>Living with other people is a series of compromises and getting used to everyone&rsquo;s unique habits and needs. We all have to put work into keeping the atmosphere in our houses positive and respectful, but sometimes that balance gets thrown off when someone isn&rsquo;t pulling their weight. Here\'s what you should do when that happens.</p>', '<p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">At Outpost, your house leader is someone you&rsquo;re going to want to get to know very well. They&rsquo;re your main connection to the company and will be there for you if you have questions about Outpost or if you need help with anything. Our house leaders are vital to Outpost and their wells of knowledge run deep. As part of our Ask a House Leader series, here&rsquo;s an answer to one recent question for them:</span></em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Q: What should I do if my roommate isn&rsquo;t pulling their weight?</h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A: Living with other people is a series of compromises and getting used to everyone&rsquo;s unique habits and needs. We all have to put work into keeping the atmosphere in our houses positive and respectful, but sometimes that balance gets thrown off when someone isn&rsquo;t pulling their weight. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Maybe your roommate takes hour-long showers in the morning when everyone is trying to get ready, or uses more than their share of the fridge. More than likely, they&rsquo;re not doing it on purpose and probably haven&rsquo;t noticed anything is wrong. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">That&rsquo;s why it&rsquo;s important not to react to this kind of situation with passive-aggression; if someone doesn&rsquo;t realize what they&rsquo;re doing, they won&rsquo;t notice sarcastic remarks or sideways glances. Instead, it&rsquo;s important to diffuse the situation in a straightforward, polite manner. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Talk to the person privately and explain what you&rsquo;d like addressed. Try not to sound accusatory -- merely tell them what&rsquo;s been bothering you and how you&rsquo;d like it addressed. Speaking in person is so much more effective than group messages or even individual texts. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The vast majority of the time, just talking to someone will fix the issue. In those rare cases where it&rsquo;s not enough, though, that&rsquo;s where your house leader comes in! Never hesitate to bring something like this up to your house leader; we&rsquo;ll either deal with it ourselves, or, where necessary, escalate accordingly. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Here are some basic guidelines to follow to make sure your house is a positive place for everyone who lives there: </span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Always take out the trash, wipe down the kitchen counters and make sure the dishwasher is loaded and unloaded on your cleaning day.</li>\r\n<li>Keep in mind that people may be sleeping when you get home late or leave early, and respect quiet hours.</li>\r\n<li>Be respectful of your roommates&rsquo; time in the morning; no one wants to be late to work because their roommate was locked in the bathroom all morning.</li>\r\n<li>Respect the fridge and cabinet space of the rest of the house.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">With those guidelines in mind, you&rsquo;ll rarely run into a situation where a house leader needs to step in, but we&rsquo;re always around if you need us!</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Sadly, there are times when it is impossible to speak the same language as your partner. If this happens, you can either <a href=\"../philadelphia\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">rent a room</a> by yourself or try to get in touch with the other person to reach a solution. Options for singles and <a href=\"../coliving\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">co living</a> are available at Outpost Club.</p>', 'Screen Shot 2018-12-19 at 11.24.00 AM.png', 1, '2018-12-19 06:00:00', '2022-11-01 07:38:25', NULL, 0, 0),
(219, '4 Reasons You Don’t Want to Miss Outpost’s New Year’s Eve Party', 1, '4-reasons-you-dont-want-to-miss-outposts-new-years-eve-party', '', '4 Reasons You Don’t Want to Miss Outpost’s New Year’s Eve Party', '4 Reasons You Don’t Want to Miss Outpost’s New Year’s Eve Party', 'What makes Outpost Club’s New Year\'s Eve party special? Here are five reasons you’re going to want to find out for yourself:', '<p>What makes Outpost Club&rsquo;s New Year\'s Eve party special? Here are five reasons you&rsquo;re going to want to find out for yourself:</p>', '<p>Ah, New York. Home to the famous New Year&rsquo;s Eve ball drop and countless parties all fighting for your attention as we ring in the new year. But what makes Outpost Club&rsquo;s party special? Here are four reasons you&rsquo;re going to want to find out for yourself:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>We&rsquo;re taking you back in time</h2>\r\n<p>The &lsquo;90s really did feel like all that and a bag of chips. If you&rsquo;re a &lsquo;90s kid, get ready for a ride on the nostalgia train to a time when your biggest concern was which kind of Lunchable you could convince your mom to buy, or whether your Slinky was tangled beyond recovery. If you&rsquo;re a &lsquo;00s kid -- well, everyone knows the &lsquo;90s didn&rsquo;t end until about 2004, anyway.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>New Year&rsquo;s Eve in New York is expensive</h2>\r\n<p>Let&rsquo;s face it: The holiday season can be draining on your bank account even without worrying about getting a ticket to a bar or club party. And that&rsquo;s not even including paying above-average drink prices. Why go through the trouble when you can have the same amount of fun for the cost of your drinks at Outpost&rsquo;s party?</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Your friends are coming</h2>\r\n<p>Need we say more?</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>It&rsquo;s going to be a blast</h2>\r\n<p>Neon, check. Light show, check. <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">&lsquo;90s outfits? That&rsquo;s on you.&nbsp;</span>Snack, drink and dance your heart out to everyone&rsquo;s favorite &lsquo;90s bands, visit the &lsquo;90s-themed photo booth and let out your competitive side on the Twister mat -- or toss around a Koosh ball, walk a Slinky down the stairs and plan a sticky-hand attack on your friends. And, of course, don&rsquo;t forget to RSVP here. See you at the East Bushwick House on New Year&rsquo;s Eve! &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>The Outpost Club New Year&rsquo;s Eve party is for Outpost Club members, alumni and friends.</em></p>', 'Screen Shot 2018-12-20 at 5.55.26 PM.png', 1, '2018-12-20 06:00:00', NULL, 0, 0, 0);
