(233, 'Tips for practicing self-care this February', 1, 'tips-for-practicing-self-care-this-february', '', 'Tips for practicing self-care this February', 'Tips for practicing self-care this February', 'In the depths of winter, when all you want to do is eat soup and curl up under your covers to wait for spring, it can be easy to forget to do the things that keep you feeling human', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In the depths of winter, when all you want to do is eat soup and curl up under your covers to wait for spring, it can be easy to forget to do the things that keep you feeling human -- but prioritizing your well-being is especially important during the winter months, when it&rsquo;s estimated that </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">one in five of us</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> suffer from either the winter blues or seasonal affective disorder.</span></p>', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In the depths of winter, when all you want to do is eat soup and curl up under your covers to wait for spring, it can be easy to forget to do the things that keep you feeling human -- but prioritizing your well-being is especially important during the winter months, when it&rsquo;s estimated that </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">one in five of us</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> suffer from either the winter blues or seasonal affective disorder. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Winter can feel especially tough on this side of the holiday season, when images of chestnuts roasting over an open fire and sugar plums dancing aren&rsquo;t enough to distract from the frigid temperatures and gray skies, and the short days make spring feel like it&rsquo;s an eternity away. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">There are things you can do to stay on top of your mental health game even if you&rsquo;re short on vitamin D, though. Practicing self-care looks different for everyone (as it should), but at its heart it means you&rsquo;re taking action to protect your own health and happiness. Here are some tips to get you started: </span></p>\r\n<h2>Stick to a routine</h2>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It&rsquo;s tempting to stay in bed for as long as possible to avoid the cold and darkness of the early morning -- or to go to bed earlier and earlier because night comes so early and it&rsquo;s miserable outside -- but you really won&rsquo;t be doing yourself any favors. For some people, winter means feeling lethargic and unmotivated, so doing small things like waking up at the same time every morning or listening to a favorite podcast every day on the way home from work can help restore some normalcy to what can be a bleak time of year. </span></p>\r\n<h2>But don&rsquo;t be afraid to switch things up</h2>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">February may be the shortest month, but it can feel never-ending when it&rsquo;s cold out. You don&rsquo;t have to make major changes if you feel like you&rsquo;re stuck in a rut, but switching things up can be an act of self-care; cooking new recipes, trying a hobby you normally wouldn&rsquo;t or even changing your hairstyle can all help you shake the blues. </span></p>\r\n<h2>Get moving</h2>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In the immortal words of Elle Woods, &ldquo;Exercise gives you endorphins. Endorphins make you happy.&rdquo; Stress and anxiety can make wintertime blues feel even worse, and exercise is a known reliever of both. </span></p>\r\n<p><strong>The Mayo Clinic</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> notes that getting outdoors within a couple of hours of waking up is especially helpful, so adding a morning walk or jog to your daily routine might be just what the doctor ordered. </span></p>\r\n<h2>Give yourself a break</h2>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Self care is both a physical and a mental act of self-preservation and love, and sometimes what you need most is just to give both your body and your mind a time-out, especially during winter when our immune systems are </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">working in overdrive</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> to keep us healthy. So grab a book, make some tea, turn on The Great British Baking Show, and get recharging: It&rsquo;s the least you can do. </span></p>', 'matthew-henry-58760-unsplash.jpg', 1, '2019-02-01 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(234, '#MemberMonday: Julian Scholler', 1, 'membermonday-julian-scholler', '', '#MemberMonday: Julian Scholler', '#MemberMonday: Julian Scholler', 'For this week\'s #MemberMonday, we\'re introducing Julian Scholler, our house leader at the East Williamsburg and Downtown Brooklyn houses. ', '<p>For this week\'s #MemberMonday, we\'re introducing Julian Scholler, our house leader at the&nbsp;East Williamsburg and Downtown Brooklyn&nbsp;houses.</p>', '<p>For this week\'s <strong>#MemberMonday</strong>, we\'re introducing Julian Scholler, our house leader at the&nbsp;East Williamsburg and <a href=\"../the-downtown-brooklyn-house\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Downtown Brooklyn</a>&nbsp;houses. Read on for some spot-on recommendations in Williamsburg.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"#MemberMonday: Julian Scholler (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/50940286_1984679831837303_7013577054864015360_n.jpg\" alt=\"#MemberMonday: Julian Scholler (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<h2>Tell us a bit about yourself.&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<p>I am Austrian and live in the beautiful and super interesting city of Vienna. Although I love my country, I haven&rsquo;t spent much time there in the last couple of years because I love to travel! Studying in Brazil, interning in Costa Rica and volunteering in Uganda have been some of my most amazing long-term travels so far.</p>\r\n<h2>What do you think of your Outpost Club experience?</h2>\r\n<p>Coliving at Outpost is amazing! I love to meet people from all different kinds of countries and backgrounds. Right now I am staying at the East Williamsburg House and we have members from Russia, Japan, the US, France, Italy, Australia and many more. I really appreciate the opportunity to learn about foreign cultures every day and making friends from all over the planet is very easy when you\'re living together.</p>\r\n<h2>Do you have a favorite place in Brooklyn?</h2>\r\n<p>My favorite place in Brooklyn is Williamsburg. This neighborhood is packed with small caf&eacute;s, amazing restaurants and a couple of breathtaking rooftop bars -- and also features some of the best street art in the area. I especially like the rooftop at the William Vale Hotel and a brunch place called Sunday in Brooklyn.</p>\r\n<h2>What are you working on now?</h2>\r\n<p>I would like to have my own coliving space in Vienna, Austria. So my current mission here in New York City is to look for ideas and inspiration for my own coliving space back home in Austria. New York City is a super trendy city and many highly interesting projects can be found here, not only in the accommodation sector but also in many other shared spaces like public spaces, restaurants or food halls.&nbsp;</p>', '50940286_1984679831837303_7013577054864015360_n.jpg', 1, '2019-02-04 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(235, '6 ways to celebrate Black History Month in New York', 1, '6-ways-to-celebrate-black-history-month-in-new-york', '', '6 ways to celebrate Black History Month in New York | Outpost Club blog', '6 ways to celebrate Black History Month in New York | Outpost Club blog', 'There’s a painful history of racism toward the black community that must not be forgotten, and the mix of events below is meant to both celebrate the black community and educate us on where we currently stand on racial equality in the U.S.', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">New York City&rsquo;s black community has a rich cultural history and is the largest in the U.S.; there&rsquo;s plenty to celebrate during black history month. There&rsquo;s also a painful history of racism toward the black community that must not be forgotten, and the mix of events below is meant to both celebrate the black community and educate us on where we currently stand on racial equality in the U.S. </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">New York City&rsquo;s black community has a rich cultural history and is the largest in the U.S.; there&rsquo;s plenty to celebrate during black history month. There&rsquo;s also a painful history of racism toward the black community that must not be forgotten, and the mix of events below is meant to both celebrate the black community and educate us on where we currently stand on racial equality in the U.S. </span></p>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Rethinking Black Women Freedom Fighters</span></h2>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Stories of women leaders within the fight for black liberation often go untold. Join Ula Taylor, Joseph Fitzgerald and Keith Gilyard on Feb. 7 at 6:30 p.m. as they discuss how black women negotiated racism, patriarchy, the U.S. class system and a Cold War world while fighting to accomplish their own dreams.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\"Let My People Sing!\" Celebrating Black History Month</span></h2>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Honor and remember injustice, suffering and the dignity of human struggle in the face of oppression through the universal language of music on Feb. 16 at 7 p.m. at Saint John\'s In the Village, 224 Waverly Place</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. </span></p>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Shwick Black Market</span></h2>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Support black-owned small businesses at the Shwick Black Market, 774 Broadway in Bed-Stuy. Shop from more than 50 local vendors, enjoy musical performances and more.</span></p>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Profiled: A Black History Month Celebration</span></h2>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Profiled wants to show that talking about race doesn&rsquo;t have to be uncomfortable. It features comics who humorously discuss their experiences with racial profiling and will entertain you while educating you about difficult topics like mass incarceration and the war on drugs.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Harlem Food Tour</span></h2>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Harlem-based tour company </span><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Taste Harlem </span></em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">offers food and cultural tours that teach participants about the history and culture of Harlem while appreciating the rich variety of cuisine on offer in the neighborhood.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">&ldquo;Power to the People&rdquo;</span></h2>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">NYC Parks Ebony Society&rsquo;s exhibition Power to the People celebrates the kind of public demonstration that has long taken place in New York City parks, drawing on both the city&rsquo;s history of protest and current social conflicts. The exhibit is open through Feb. 28 at the Arsenal Gallery, in Central Park at 64th Street and 5th Ave.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2019 Harlem Fine Arts Show</span></h2>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Harlem Fine Arts Show celebrates the African Diaspora while showcasing cultural ideas and raising awareness of international, national and local black artists. The New York City stop will take place Feb. 14-17 at the Historic Riverside Church, 490 Riverside Dr. in Morningside Heights.&nbsp;</span></p>', 'file-20180111-101492-edbhzj.jpg', 1, '2019-02-06 06:00:00', NULL, 0, 0, 0),
(236, 'Destination: Doaba Deli', 1, 'destination-doaba-deli', '', 'Destination: Doaba Deli', 'Destination: Doaba Deli', 'Doaba Deli’s unassuming storefront just a few blocks from our Central Park Manhattan House belies the true gem within: a delightful array of Indian food that will make any vegetarian squeal with delight.', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Doaba Deli&rsquo;s unassuming storefront just a few blocks from our </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Central Park Manhattan House</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> belies the true gem within: a delightful array of Indian food that will make any vegetarian squeal with delight.</span></p>', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Doaba Deli&rsquo;s unassuming storefront just a few blocks from our </span><a href=\"../central-park-manhattan-house\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Central Park Manhattan House</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> belies the true gem within: a delightful array of Indian food that will make any vegetarian squeal with delight. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Fresh-baked naan, samosas the size of your fist and a seemingly endless rotation of curries will keep you coming back whenever you&rsquo;re on the Upper West Side. Get your choice of four curries with rice and a side salad for $8 for a filling and reasonably priced lunch.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Just don&rsquo;t expect to find the full menu every day, as part of the fun of visiting Doaba is finding out what&rsquo;s on offer that day, whether you go for their Punjabi kadi, chana masala or chana saag. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The owners of Doaba Deli only add to the delight; their warmth and friendliness (along with their food, of course) really make you feel like you&rsquo;re eating a home-cooked meal no matter how far from home you are. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you&rsquo;re lucky, you&rsquo;ll be able to grab a spot at one of the three tables in the tiny space and enjoy talking to the owners and people watching as you enjoy your food, but don&rsquo;t count on it during dinnertime or shift changes. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">There&rsquo;s no need to be disappointed if you can&rsquo;t find a table, though. The deli is only a couple of blocks from Central Park, making it the perfect choice for a picnic lunch. </span></p>\r\n<p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Find Doaba Deli at 945 Columbus Ave. on the Upper West Side. </span></em></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Destination: Doaba Deli (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/Screen%20Shot%202019-02-08%20at%2012.29.41%20PM.png\" alt=\"Destination: Doaba Deli (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Photo: Deniece L/Yelp</span></em></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Destination: Doaba Deli (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/Screen%20Shot%202019-02-08%20at%2012.31.51%20PM.png\" alt=\"Destination: Doaba Deli (Image-2)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Photo: Emily M/Yelp</span></em></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Destination: Doaba Deli (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/Screen%20Shot%202019-02-08%20at%2012.35.49%20PM.png\" alt=\"Destination: Doaba Deli (Image-3)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\"><em>Jing K/Yelp</em></span></p>', 'Screen Shot 2019-02-08 at 12.28.14 PM.png', 1, '2019-02-08 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(237, 'Treat yourself to a chocolate fountain this Valentine’s Day', 1, 'treat-yourself-to-a-chocolate-fountain-this-valentines-day', '', 'Treat yourself to a chocolate fountain this Valentine’s Day', 'Treat yourself to a chocolate fountain this Valentine’s Day', 'There are a few things most of us can appreciate whether we find ourselves single or in a relationship come Valentine’s Day: chocolate, gooey cheese and good beer', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">There are a few things most of us can appreciate whether we find ourselves single or in a relationship come Valentine&rsquo;s Day: chocolate, gooey cheese and good beer. That&rsquo;s why we&rsquo;re combining all three for Valentine&rsquo;s at Outpost this year. </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">There are a few things most of us can appreciate whether we find ourselves single or in a relationship come Valentine&rsquo;s Day: chocolate, gooey cheese and good beer. That&rsquo;s why we&rsquo;re combining all three for Valentine&rsquo;s at Outpost this year. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Head over to </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Braven Brewing</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, 52 Harrison Place in Bushwick, at around 8 p.m. on Valentine&rsquo;s Day for a chill evening with your roommates, your significant other or anyone else who can appreciate spending an evening hanging out and dipping things into melted chocolate and cheese. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We&rsquo;ll have a chocolate fountain and cheese fondue set up at the brewery, so come in, grab a pint, and get dipping! We&rsquo;re excited to be able to partner with Braven on this, as they&rsquo;ve been a very welcome addition to Bushwick and we love to see our neighborhoods thrive. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Here&rsquo;s what&rsquo;s on the menu for the evening: </span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Chocolate fountain</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Strawberries</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Brownies</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pound cake</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Marshmallows</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Cheese fondue with emmental and smoked gruyere </span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">French baguette</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sourdough </span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Gherkins </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Find out what Braven has on tap right now </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">here</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. See you there! </span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>', 'Screen Shot 2019-02-13 at 3.29.12 PM.png', 1, '2019-02-12 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(238, 'Coliving brings rooms for rent for less than $1000 per month to NYC', 1, 'coliving-brings-rooms-for-rent-for-less-than-1000-per-month-to-nyc', '', 'Coliving brings rooms for rent for less than $1000 per month to NYC | Outpost Club blog', 'Coliving brings rooms for rent for less than $1000 per month to NYC', 'With coliving, you can get a great room in Brooklyn, Queens or Manhattan for less than $1,000 per month without sacrificing any of the quality you’re used to.', '<p>With coliving, you can get a great room in Brooklyn, Queens or Manhattan for less than $1,000 per month without sacrificing any of the quality you&rsquo;re used to.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p>Renting in <a href=\"../nyc-rooms-for-rent\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">New York City</a> can be a stressful experience, especially if you haven&rsquo;t actually moved here yet. You have to worry about figuring out which neighborhood you want to live in and finding roommates who won&rsquo;t keep you up all night or steal your food (or worse), and even if you find the apartment of your dreams, you can bet that it&rsquo;ll be off the market within about five minutes.</p>\r\n<p>Even if you do manage to find somewhere awesome to live, you&rsquo;ll probably have to deal with paying a broker&rsquo;s fee on top of a high deposit and first and last month\'s rent. It&rsquo;s a wonder anyone moving to New York is able to find somewhere to live at all, let alone somewhere that feels like home.</p>\r\n<p>That&rsquo;s where coliving comes in. Coliving allows people to build communities around shared spaces while cutting back on the cost of things like utilities and household essentials everyone uses. With coliving, you can get a great room in Brooklyn, Queens or Manhattan for less than $1,000 per month without sacrificing any of the quality you&rsquo;re used to.</p>\r\n<h3>Coliving is the best way to experience NYC</h3>\r\n<p>The best part of coliving, of course, is that you&rsquo;re also finding a new community as soon as you arrive in your new city -- you won&rsquo;t have to worry about trying to make new friends in a city of 8.6 million.</p>\r\n<p>You might move in as a stranger, but in no time at all you&rsquo;ll find yourself spending evenings having conversations over a glass of wine with your roommates, watching movies in our massive coliving rooms or getting to know people from other houses at our events. At Outpost Club, you&rsquo;ll never run out of opportunities to meet new people and explore New York.</p>\r\n<h3>Find apartments in Brooklyn, Manhattan and Queens</h3>\r\n<p>Whether you want something close to the office or close to great nightlife, you&rsquo;ll be able to find a coliving house that meets your needs. We&rsquo;ve designed <a href=\"../our-houses\">each of our houses</a> to complement their neighborhoods and be comfortable, inviting spaces for all of our members. Every house includes multiple community spaces with ample room to work, cook or just hang out.</p>\r\n<p>We&rsquo;ll also provide you with a move-in guide for your neighborhood when you arrive so you can check out all the best restaurants, bars, cafes and other local businesses near your apartment.</p>\r\n<p>Whether you want to walk through Central Park on your commute every day or stroll past Bushwick&rsquo;s art walls on your way to dinner, Outpost Club houses throughout Brooklyn, Manhattan and Queens will allow you to live in New York for less than $1,000 per month while enjoying a quality home and vibrant community.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Outpost Club has gathered all the data you need to know about <a href=\"../coliving\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">co living</a> for you. You only need to decide on the apartment of your desires. Why not share the wonderful things and feelings in the world with your closest friends?</p>', 'Screen Shot 2019-02-15 at 4.23.14 PM.png', 1, '2019-02-15 06:00:00', '2022-11-01 07:42:02', NULL, 0, 0),
(239, 'Ask a House Leader: What should I do if my house needs restocking?', 1, 'ask-a-house-leader-what-should-i-do-if-my-house-needs-restocking', '', 'Ask a House Leader: What should I do if my house needs restocking?', 'Ask a House Leader: What should I do if my house needs restocking?', 'At Outpost, your house leader is someone you’re going to want to get to know very well. They’re your main connection to the company and will be there for you if you have questions about Outpost or if you need help with anything. Our house leaders are vital to Outpost and their wells of knowledge run deep. As part of our Ask a House Leader series, here’s an answer to one recent question for them.', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">At Outpost, your house leader is someone you&rsquo;re going to want to get to know very well. They&rsquo;re your main connection to the company and will be there for you if you have questions about Outpost or if you need help with anything. Our house leaders are vital to Outpost and their wells of knowledge run deep. As part of our Ask a House Leader series, here&rsquo;s an answer to one recent question for them.</span></p>', '<p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">At Outpost, your house leader is someone you&rsquo;re going to want to get to know very well. They&rsquo;re your main connection to the company and will be there for you if you have questions about Outpost or if you need help with anything. Our house leaders are vital to Outpost and their wells of knowledge run deep. As part of our Ask a House Leader series, here&rsquo;s an answer to one recent question for them:</span></em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Q: What should I do if my apartment runs out of something like paper towels or soap?</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A: One of the super convenient things about living at Outpost is that membership is all-inclusive: We don&rsquo;t have to worry about keeping track of whether we have enough laundry detergent for the coming weekend or whether our toilet paper will last us until our next grocery shopping trip. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">That said, it&rsquo;s good to know what Outpost provides and regularly restocks: </span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Olive oil</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Coffee and tea</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sugar</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Salt and pepper</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Shampoo and body wash</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Hand and dish soap</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Paper towels and toilet paper</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Cleaning supplies</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Printer paper and ink</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You usually won&rsquo;t have to worry about being out of anything on that list because our cleaning team checks every apartment on for things that could be running low and restocks them if necessary.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you do find yourself in need of one of the above items and it&rsquo;s not cleaning day, the best thing to do is get in touch with &hellip; drum roll &hellip; your house leader! Part of our role is making sure Outpost houses stay in tip-top shape between our once- or twice-weekly cleanings, and that includes restocking items we&rsquo;re running low on. </span></p>\r\n<p>As always, you can reach us via your house&rsquo;s Facebook messenger group, or, obviously, you&rsquo;re welcome to tell us in person the next time you see us around.</p>', 'no7nae2l57vfhvdfxfef.jpeg', 1, '2019-02-20 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(373, 'Dorms Aren\'t Your Only Option This School Year', 1, 'dorms-arent-your-only-option-this-school-year', '', 'Dorms Aren\'t Your Only Option This School Year', 'Dorms Aren\'t Your Only Option This School Year', 'If you\'re looking for a sense of safety and normalcy when returning to school this fall, Outpost housing can make your semester start seamlessly with fully-furnished apartments that offer month-to-month rentals. Our newest Lafayette house in the charming Brooklyn neighborhood of Bed-Stuy is only a 20-minute walk to Pratt, so you don\'t have to worry about catching the subway in time! ', '<p>If you\'re looking for a sense of safety and normalcy when returning to school this fall, Outpost housing can make your semester start seamlessly with fully-furnished apartments that offer month-to-month rentals. Our newest Lafayette house in the charming Brooklyn neighborhood of Bed-Stuy is only a 20-minute walk to Pratt, so you don\'t have to worry about catching the subway in time!&nbsp;</p>', '<p>If you\'re looking for a sense of safety and normalcy when returning to school this fall, Outpost housing can make your semester start seamlessly with fully-furnished apartments that offer month-to-month rentals. Our newest <a href=\"../the-lafayette-house\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Lafayette House</a> in the charming Brooklyn neighborhood of Bed-Stuy is only a 20-minute walk to Pratt, so you don\'t have to worry about catching the subway in time!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Build your own community&nbsp;</strong></h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Outpost offers a variety of unit sizes and bedroom types all across New York City and New Jersey, so you can find an apartment that\'s perfectly suited for you and all your friends to create your own educational pod. Our units come equipped with all you\'ll need for this academic year, including kitchen supplies, bedding, TVs and organization tools. We make sure that your move is stress-free and that you have everything you need for the duration of your stay. All you have to bring is your suitcase!</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img title=\"Dorms Aren\'t Your Only Option This School Year (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/SC2029_OMD_Ste1C_085_2.jpg\" alt=\"Dorms Aren\'t Your Only Option This School Year (Image-1)\" width=\"521\" height=\"347\" /></p>\r\n<h3><strong>Flexibility with your stay</strong></h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">With the conditions of the pandemic shifting on a nearly daily basis, signing a full-year lease might be a commitment that leaves you with more uncertainty than peace of mind. With Outpost, you can sign up for a single semester, entire school year or even just a month &mdash; no need to worry about finding a sublease or paying for rent once you move out.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><img title=\"Dorms Aren\'t Your Only Option This School Year (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/SC2029_OMD_Comm1_207_2.jpg\" alt=\"Dorms Aren\'t Your Only Option This School Year (Image-2)\" width=\"533\" height=\"355\" /></span></p>\r\n<h3><strong>Safety during the pandemic&nbsp;</strong></h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Compared to your average dorm hall or apartment building, Outpost houses have a limited amount of foot traffic that makes them safer while COVID-19 continues to spread. We also include a monthly cleaning service in our membership, so you can be sure your apartment will be sanitized by professionals. You can create your own educational pod at Outpost and socially distance safely with your friends!</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img title=\"Dorms Aren\'t Your Only Option This School Year (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/SC2029_OMD_Ste2C_132_2.jpg\" alt=\"Dorms Aren\'t Your Only Option This School Year (Image-3)\" width=\"530\" height=\"353\" /></p>\r\n<h3><strong>Perfect space for students&nbsp;</strong></h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">With high-speed WiFi already running upon your arrival and ample workplaces throughout our houses, you\'ll have everything you need to work and play. Some of our houses, like the newest Lafayette House, have co-working spaces that can fit up to 8-10 students for those late-night study sessions or group projects. You can avoid public spaces and stay safe without having to do your homework from bed!&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><img title=\"Dorms Aren\'t Your Only Option This School Year (Image-4), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/SC2029_OMD_Comm1_194_2.jpg\" alt=\"Dorms Aren\'t Your Only Option This School Year (Image-4)\" width=\"541\" height=\"361\" /></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo by <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/@mattragland?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Matt Ragland</a> on <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/s/photos/studying?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Unsplash</a></p>', 'matt-ragland-02z1I7gv4ao-unsplash.jpg', 1, '2020-08-03 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(240, 'How to meet people when you’re new to New York', 1, 'how-to-meet-people-when-youre-new-to-new-york', '', 'How to meet people when you’re new to New York', 'How to meet people when you’re new to New York', 'You might think it’s easy to meet people in New York City, but that\'s not always the case. Here are our tips to overcome this social winter.', '<p>You might think it&rsquo;s easy to meet people in New York City, but that\'s not always the case. Here are our tips to overcome this social winter.</p>', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">With a population of 8.6 million, you might think it&rsquo;s easy to meet people in <a href=\"../nyc-rooms-for-rent\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">New York City</a>. But the truth is that most of those people are rushing through the streets without the time or the desire to add more people to their circle of friends. In terms of meeting people, New York is a </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">&ldquo;</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">water, water everywhere&rdquo;</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> situation &mdash; but that&rsquo;s not to say you can&rsquo;t cut through those waves.</span></p>\r\n<h2>Explore a hobby</h2>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">NYC has everything on offer. Ever thought about </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">live comic art drawing</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">? Or </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">inline skating by the Empire State Building</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">? Finding a hobby is one of the best ways to meet new people, because it instantly lets you into a circle of friends with similar interests. And chances are, if the people you meet like the same things you like, you&rsquo;ll probably like them too. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Websites like Meetup</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">&nbsp;and Facebook events are good for this. Personally, I recommend the </span><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/groups/112346805899492/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Bushwick Writers Group</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, which holds bi-weekly &ldquo;Write Your Ass Off&rdquo; workshops and more.</span></p>\r\n<h2>Become a regular</h2>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Explore your local area and you&rsquo;ll be surprised how friendly the locals can be. Just going to your favorite bars or coffee shops on a regular basis can be the first step toward finding new friends. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you&rsquo;re not from the States, you might be surprised at how talkative strangers are at bars and restaurants. This isn&rsquo;t them being creepy (mostly). New Yorkers are open, friendly people when you&rsquo;re not blocking their way on the sidewalk and they&rsquo;ll jump at the opportunity to explain their city and make recommendations to newcomers. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Some of our favorites are </span><strong>Bootleg Bar</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and </span><strong>Braven Brewing Company</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> in Bushwick, </span><strong>Burly Coffee</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> in Bed-Stuy and </span><strong>Ange Noir Cafe</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> in East Williamsburg.</span></p>\r\n<h2>Take advantage of tech</h2>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Apps for meeting friends have recently become trendy, including </span><strong>Bumble BFF</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and the networking app </span><strong>Shapr</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>.</strong> Swipe right or left to find the perfect person and if you match, you can meet in real life. Or why not try the &ldquo;experience&rdquo; options on </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Meetup</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and </span><a href=\"https://www.airbnb.com/s/experiences\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Airbnb</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, where you can take a workshop or a walking tour and get chatting? Facebook groups like </span><strong>Girl Gone International</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and </span><strong>Expats World in New York</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> can also help you meet other newbies through events held regularly in the city.</span></p>\r\n<h2>Try coliving</h2>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Although all of these options may work, they all rely on luck and your willingness to put yourself out there and corner your new friends into seeing you again. By far the easiest way to meet people is coliving, because your new friends won&rsquo;t forget to call you back or give you a fake name (you know where they live, after all). </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Coliving throws together groups of <a href=\"../blog_category/membermonday\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">like-minded people</a></span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">&nbsp;and, at least at Outpost, helps you break the ice with a series of fun events, including </span><a href=\"../blog/outpost-club-welcomes-autumn-on-the-water\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">trips</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, </span><a href=\"../blog/outpost-club-rings-in-the-new-year\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">parties</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and </span><a href=\"../blog/what-we-learned-at-outposts-blind-sculpting-party\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">workshops</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. You also know that everyone you meet has been vetted by our team, so you can sail away into the sunset on your brand new friendship with complete peace of mind.</span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>', 'wilmer-martinez-757492-unsplash.jpg', 1, '2019-02-22 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(241, '#MemberMonday: Florencia Muñoz', 1, 'membermonday-florencia-muoz', '', '#MemberMonday: Florencia Muñoz', '#MemberMonday: Florencia Muñoz', 'For this week’s #MemberMonday, we talked to Florencia Muñoz, an aspiring psychologist and one of our new house leaders. Read on to find out what she loves about Brooklyn.', '<p>For this week&rsquo;s #MemberMonday, we talked to Florencia Mu&ntilde;oz, an aspiring psychologist and one of our new house leaders. Read on to find out what she loves about Brooklyn.</p>', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This week&rsquo;s </span><strong>#MemberMonday</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> feature is Florencia Mu&ntilde;oz, one of our new house leaders and an aspiring psychologist. Florencia loves exploring the parks and bookstores of Brooklyn.</span></p>\r\n<h1><strong><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"#MemberMonday: Florencia Mu&ntilde;oz (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/IMG_0372.jpeg\" alt=\"#MemberMonday: Florencia Mu&ntilde;oz (Image-1)\" width=\"505\" height=\"379\" />Tell us a bit about yourself.</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">I am a psychologist who likes old-school music, films and books. I&rsquo;m also an animal lover (especially dogs). I like to keep my life simple and uncomplicated and I try to enjoy every moment. I&rsquo;m studying for my GRE and I&rsquo;m also a house leader at Outpost, which is really fun.</span></p>\r\n<h1><strong>What\'s your favorite Outpost memory? </strong></h1>\r\n<p>I met my best friend this summer here at the Bed-Stuy house. I&rsquo;ve had so many great times with the people at Outpost, it&rsquo;s hard to pick just one.</p>\r\n<h1><strong>What&rsquo;s your favorite part of New York?</strong></h1>\r\n<p>I really love Clinton Hill. It&rsquo;s full of parks and I like walking and sightseeing at the same time. There are plenty of doggie parks which makes up for the fact that I can&rsquo;t have a dog myself here in NYC. I also love discovering used bookstores in Brooklyn; it&rsquo;s a great place to explore.</p>\r\n<h1><strong>What are you working on now?</strong></h1>\r\n<p>I&rsquo;m working on being a good house leader and providing a good service with new guests. Besides that I&rsquo;m working on studying for my GRE.</p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>', 'FullSizeRender-2.jpg', 1, '2019-02-25 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(242, 'Destination: Dun-Well Doughnuts', 1, 'destination-dun-well-doughnuts', '', 'Destination: Dun-Well Doughnuts', 'Destination: Dun-Well Doughnuts', 'Dun-Well Donuts is our favorite place to satisfy our sweet tooth in East Williamsburg', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Dun-Well Donuts</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> is our favorite place to satisfy our sweet tooth in East Williamsburg. Located on Montrose Avenue, just around the corner from the Montrose L stop and our </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">East Williamsburg House</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, this cafe is doughnut and coffee heaven with a conscience.</span></p>', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Dun-Well Donuts</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> is our favorite place to satisfy our sweet tooth in East Williamsburg. Located on Montrose Avenue, just around the corner from the Montrose L stop and our </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">East Williamsburg House</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, this cafe is doughnut and coffee heaven with a conscience.</span></p>\r\n<p>Established in 2011, Dun-Well began with a Simpsons episode and a doughnut craving. Christopher Hollowell (the \"Well\" in Dun-Well) called up his old college friend Dan Dunbar (the \"Dun\" in Dun-Well), looking for a quality vegan doughnut shop in NYC. To their amazement, they couldn&rsquo;t find anything that made the cut, so they decided to do it themselves &mdash; opening NYC\'s first all-vegan doughnut cafe.</p>\r\n<p>Dun-Well is a gem on Montrose Avenue. Step through the glass doors into a vintage interior with plenty of seating and natural light, and, of course, a large glass case filled with a variety of delicious doughnut flavors.</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Destination: Dun-Well Doughnuts (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/2345678.jpg\" alt=\"Destination: Dun-Well Doughnuts (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Each doughnut is handcrafted daily, with a changing menu, which means you&rsquo;re always getting something special. The daily menu is announced on their </span><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/dunwelldoughnuts/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Instagram</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> (which will make you hungry just looking at it), with a rotating list of 200 varieties. Our recent favorites have been The Homer, a signature pink sprinkles doughnut inspired by the Simpsons, the PB &amp; J and a delicious Blueberry French Toast. You can choose from regular, filled or cake doughnuts, starting from just $1.50 each or &frac12; dozen for $14.</span></p>\r\n<p>There&rsquo;s also a complete range of espresso and coffee drinks on offer, expertly prepared on a top-of-the-line La Marzoccos, and a selection of tea and other drinks, making it the perfect place to chill out with friends or work on your screenplay for an afternoon.</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Even though Montrose Avenue is filled with trendy cafes and bakeries, Dun-Well has beaten the odds to become a successful business, with </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">a second store</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> recently opened on the Lower East Side in Manhattan. This is a testament to the quality of their doughnuts, which you wouldn&rsquo;t be able to tell were vegan if we hadn&rsquo;t just told you.</span></p>\r\n<p>At the heart of Dun-Well&rsquo;s philosophy is ethics; they&rsquo;re committed to using only quality ingredients and supporting local businesses. All of their products are free of animal or animal-derived ingredients and both their coffee and doughnuts are made with organic ingredients. In fact, their coffee is organic, Fair Trade and Rainforest Alliance certified, hand roasted daily by local Brooklyn Roasting Company. Now that&rsquo;s some feel-good indulgence.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Destination: Dun-Well Doughnuts (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/Dun-Well-Doughnuts-2.jpg\" alt=\"Destination: Dun-Well Doughnuts (Image-2)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /><br /><br /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Open hours: Monday to Friday, 7 am - 7pm; Saturday and Sunday, 8 am - 7pm</span></p>\r\n<p>Address: 222 Montrose Ave, Brooklyn, NY 10221</p>\r\n<p>Phone: 1-347-294-0871.</p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>', 'Dun-Well-Doughnuts-2.jpg', 1, '2019-02-28 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0);
