(249, 'Destination: Arepera Guacuco', 1, 'destination-arepera-guacuco', '', 'Destination: Arepera Guacuco', 'Destination: Arepera Guacuco', 'Maybe you stopped by Arepera Guacuco because you smelled the fresh empanadas and arepas wafting into the street, or maybe you’ve walked past it a million times on your way home to our Bed-Stuy House but never been inside', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Maybe you stopped by </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Arepera Guacuco</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> because you smelled the fresh empanadas and arepas wafting into the street, or maybe you&rsquo;ve walked past it a million times on your way home to our </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Bed-Stuy House</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> but never been inside. Either way, now is the time to try our new favorite Bed-Stuy spot.</span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Maybe you stopped by </span><strong>Arepera Guacuco</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> because you smelled the fresh empanadas and arepas wafting into the street, or maybe you&rsquo;ve walked past it a million times on your way home to our </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Bed-Stuy House</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> but never been inside. Either way, now is the time to try our new favorite Bed-Stuy spot.</span></p>\r\n<p>Guacuco is one of those places where you can find both authenticity and a welcoming atmosphere; somewhere that is just as vibrant in taste as it is in spirit. This Venezuelan restaurant, located just a 5-minute walk from our <a href=\"../the-bed-stuy-house\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Bed-Stuy House</a> and a short walk from our South Williamsburg House, has a no-frills, minimalistic interior, filled with primary colors, exposed brickwork, plants and even a hammock on the wall. Step inside to colorful murals set against wooden chairs and a fully stocked bar in the corner.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Destination: Arepera Guacuco (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/Guacuco.jpg\" alt=\"Destination: Arepera Guacuco (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;Arepera&rdquo; literally means &ldquo;a place that sells arepas,&rdquo; and &ldquo;Guacuco&rdquo; is the name of the Venezuelan beach where owner Leonardo Molina was born. This encapsulates the two sides of this restaurant and bar: its dedication to both family values and good food. Made from Carmen&rsquo;s mother&rsquo;s secret recipe, the arepas at Arepera Guacuco are freshly made every day. In fact, the entire menu is full of fresh, authentic ingredients. Find a selection of Venezuelan salads, empanadas and traditional dishes, including asopado de mariscos, cachapa, carite frito and, of course, arepas.</p>\r\n<p>Our favorite is anything involving the shredded beef, which has a knack for melting in your mouth that we simply can&rsquo;t explain. We love their version of Venezuela&rsquo;s national dish, pabellon criollo (juicy shredded beef and sweet plantain, topped with aged cheese, rice, beans and a plain arepa on the side). Guacuco focuses on quality and all of their arepas and empanadas are made with 100% cornflour (using Harina P.A.N) and are gluten free and fresh to order. The wall art includes a mural of a Venezuelan beach and of a map of Bed-Stuy, capturing the unique fusion of cultures that Guacuco holds.</p>\r\n<p>Although the food is great, Arepera Guacuco has much more to offer than just a simple dinner spot. First of all, let&rsquo;s get back to that bar we mentioned. Their cocktails are delicious. Enjoy a sweet passion fruit mojito with fresh mint leaves, followed by a Venezuela libra. Or how about a coconut caipirinha, or a traditional pisco sour? If you arrive early, stop by for happy hour and stay for dinner for the perfect evening out.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><img title=\"Destination: Arepera Guacuco (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/arepera-du-plateau-4.jpg\" alt=\"Destination: Arepera Guacuco (Image-2)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Guacuco even has its own venue, The Back Room, tucked behind the restaurant and bar with a regular schedule of live music and stand up comedy. Find the latest listings on their Instagram, </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">@thebackroomatguacuco</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. And if you wake up hungover on Sunday craving a bloody Mary, they&rsquo;ve got a solution for that too, with a delicious weekend brunch menu. What else could you ask for?</span></p>\r\n<p>Find the Bed-Stuy branch at 360 Throop Ave. and their sister Bushwick restaurant at 44 Irving Ave.</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Arepas Guacuco</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, Bed-Stuy,</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">360 Throop Avenue</span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>', 'Guacuco-5-Web.jpg', 1, '2019-03-21 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(250, 'Why Bed-Study is a great place to live', 1, 'why-bed-study-is-a-great-place-to-live', '', 'Why Bed-Study is a great place to live', 'Why Bed-Study is a great place to live', 'Bedford-Stuyvesant, known as Bed-Stuy to New Yorkers, is a unique mix of old and new, south of Bushwick and Williamsburg and accessible on the A, C, J and G trains. It’s also home to our Bed-Stuy House and just a short walk from our Bushwick, East Bushwick and South Williamsburg houses. Read on for our top reasons to live in Bed-Stuy.', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Bedford-Stuyvesant</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, known as Bed-Stuy to New Yorkers, is a unique mix of old and new, south of Bushwick and Williamsburg and accessible on the A, C, J and G trains. It&rsquo;s also home to our </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Bed-Stuy House</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and just a short walk from our </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Bushwick</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">East Bushwick</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">South Williamsburg houses</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. Read on for our top reasons to live in Bed-Stuy.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>Bedford-Stuyvesant</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>,</strong> known as Bed-Stuy to New Yorkers, is a unique mix of old and new, south of Bushwick and Williamsburg and accessible on the A, C, J and G trains. It&rsquo;s also home to our </span><a href=\"../the-bed-stuy-house\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Bed-Stuy House</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and just a short walk from our </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Bushwick</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">East Bushwick</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">South Williamsburg houses</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. Read on for our top reasons to live in Bed-Stuy.</span></p>\r\n<h1><strong>The history</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Bed-Stuy, like neighboring </span><strong>Bushwick</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and </span><strong>Williamsburg</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>,</strong> is now a major hub for young artistic types, but it has nevertheless kept its rich cultural history. The neighborhood is famous for its authentic brownstone homes and you can find Anne and Romanesque Revival architecture juxtaposed against modern coffee shops and new builds, especially along Nostrand Avenue and Halsey Street.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Why Bed-Study is a great place to live (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/bedford_stuyvesant_real_estate_2.jpg\" alt=\"Why Bed-Study is a great place to live (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Bed-Stuy is rich in 18th-century Dutch history and Revolutionary War heritage, as well as black American civil rights history, with monuments like </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Restoration Plaza </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">on Fulton Street. It is the site of </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Our Lady</strong> of Victory</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, a neo-Gothic, 19th-century Catholic church, at 583 Throop Ave. Check out the full list of the area&rsquo;s </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">historic buildings</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> here.</span></p>\r\n<h1><strong>The art scene</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Bed-Stuy is an artist&rsquo;s paradise, in part due to the emerging artists who have made the neighborhood their home in recent years. Just walking along the street will lead you to an array of murals, such as the </span><a href=\"https://donyc.com/p/biggie-smalls\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Biggie mural</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> on the corner of Bedford Ave. and Quincy St., and the artistic tribute to </span><strong>rapper OBD</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, one of the founding members of the </span><strong>Wu-Tang Clan</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, at 448 Franklin Ave.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Explore emerging and established artists at the </span><strong>Richard Beavers Gallery</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and </span><strong>The Bishop Gallery</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. But it doesn&rsquo;t stop there; art is woven into the very fabric of Bed-Stuy living. Local coffee shops like </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Mary&rsquo;s Coffee Shop</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, just a short walk from our Bed-Stuy House, are filled with local art hanging on the walls, and spaces like the </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Living Gallery</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> at 1094 Broadway hold regular art classes and live music performances, with a rotating display of art at your fingertips.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Why Bed-Study is a great place to live (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/https---hypebeast.com-image-2017-05-notorious-big-mural-taken-down-tw.jpg\" alt=\"Why Bed-Study is a great place to live (Image-2)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1><strong>The particularly eclectic mix of food, drink and culture</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Bed-Stuy has significant Caribbean, Trinidadian and Haitian communities, which means there are a variety of authentic eateries on offer. Try </span><strong>Grandchamps</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, at 197 Patchen Ave., for amazing Haitian food, including bone-in stewed chicken, fried fish and griot. Get delicious French food at the </span><strong>Georges-Andres Vintage Cafe</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, or grab an Eastern European coffee at </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Zabka Eastern European Cafe</strong>.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Bed-Stuy is a true mix of old and new. Find historic community options peppered with modern coffee shops, restaurants, bars and, of course, affordable vintage stores. The crowning jewel of the latter is </span><strong>Harold and Maude Vintage</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, with genuine vintage pieces at affordable prices. Another favorite, </span><strong>The Meat Market</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, at 380 Tompkins Ave., may look like a butcher shop outside, but inside you&rsquo;ll find a range of high quality, ethical picks. Bed-Stuy is also rich in artsy bars like </span><strong>C&rsquo;mon Everybody</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, which hosts up-and-coming musicians and special events, including regular burlesque shows.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Why Bed-Study is a great place to live (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/harold-and-maude2.jpg\" alt=\"Why Bed-Study is a great place to live (Image-3)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1><strong>The green spaces</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Green space is hard to come by in New York City. One of the best parts of Bed-Stuy is the unexpected abundance of parks and green spaces that this neighborhood holds. </span><strong>Herbert Von King Park</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>,</strong> one of Brooklyn&rsquo;s first parks, is a green oasis right in the middle of Bed-Stuy, designed by Frederick Law Olsted (of the same duo who designed Central Park and Prospect Park). Find fitness equipment, a baseball field and even the outdoor </span><strong>Eubie Blake Auditorium</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, where you can find free jazz concerts in the summer. Or in the south end of Bed-Stuy, find beautiful </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Fulton Park</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, a little slice of Washington Square Park brought east into Brooklyn, with chess tables and flowers galore. This community-feeling park is home to an annual </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">art fair </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">in the summer and a </span><strong>Halloween parade</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> in the fall.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Bed-Stuy is also just a short walk from Brooklyn&rsquo;s largest and most famous park, </span><strong>Prospect Park</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. This 526-acre has specially designated cycle tracks, &agrave; la Central Park, and even a zoo. Take a picnic lunch and whittle away a Sunday afternoon on the grass. Environmentalists will love the </span><strong>Magnolia Tree Earth Center</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> on Lafayette Ave., dedicated to urban beautification and community sustainability, as well as the large number of </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">community gardens</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> scattered around the neighborhood.</span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>', 'https---hypebeast.com-image-2017-05-notorious-big-mural-taken-down-tw.jpg', 1, '2019-03-21 05:00:00', NULL, 0, 0, 0),
(252, '#MemberMonday: Natalie Gillespie Gaskins', 1, 'membermonday-natalie-gillespie-gaskins', '', '#MemberMonday: Natalie Gillespie Gaskins', '#MemberMonday: Natalie Gillespie Gaskins', 'This week’s #MemberMonday feature is Natalie from Minneapolis, a lover of arts and culture and the newest member of our East Bushwick House.', '<p>This week&rsquo;s #MemberMonday feature is Natalie from Minneapolis, a lover of arts and culture and the newest member of our East Bushwick House.</p>', '<p>This week&rsquo;s <strong>#MemberMonday</strong> feature is Natalie from Minneapolis, a lover of arts and culture and the newest member of our East Bushwick House.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img title=\"#MemberMonday: Natalie Gillespie Gaskins (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/55719211_965068490550369_1687623531136811008_n.jpg\" alt=\"#MemberMonday: Natalie Gillespie Gaskins (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1>Tell us a bit about yourself.</h1>\r\n<p>Hey, everyone! I\'m Natalie and I just moved to NYC from Minneapolis, MN, about a week ago. Minneapolis is famous for its abundance of lakes, the Boundary Waters, the Coen Brothers, and Prince.</p>\r\n<h1>What\'s your favorite Outpost memory?</h1>\r\n<p>That\'s a really tough question: I\'ve made so many great memories at Outpost Club. Honestly, my time here has been so memorable because of the people I\'ve met. I\'ve made friends for life from all over the world and the best memories are yet to come!</p>\r\n<h1>What&rsquo;s your favorite part of New York?</h1>\r\n<p>Location-wise, I love DUMBO. The area reminds me a lot of the Mill City District in Minneapolis, so it\'s become a \"home away from home\" spot for me. Overall, there is just so much to love about this city: the diversity, art, music, food, fashion, etc. It\'s hard to pick just one.</p>\r\n<h1>What are you working on now?</h1>\r\n<p>I first came to New York last summer for an internship with Warner Music Group and that\'s when I fell in love with the city. I knew I would return at some point and upon re-arrival, I\'ve started working with a tech startup in Long Island City. On the side, I love to sing, so I may have to get out and perform some time soon!</p>', '55719211_965068490550369_1687623531136811008_n.jpg', 1, '2019-03-25 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(253, 'Why we love spring in New York City', 1, 'why-we-love-spring-in-new-york-city', '', 'Why we love spring in New York City', 'Why we love spring in New York City', 'Spring is finally here, which in New York City means several things: Locals crawl out from within their tiny apartments and start exploring and  smiling again', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Spring is finally here, which in New York City means several things: Locals crawl out from within their tiny apartments and start exploring and smiling again; w</span>e all start walking places once more, appreciating the murals and the brownstones we have around us; Mr. Softee trucks glide through town and the city just somehow seems more welcoming, brighter and energetic. Read on to find out why we love spring in NYC.</p>', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Spring is finally here, which in <a href=\"../nyc-rooms-for-rent\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">New York City</a> means several things: Locals crawl out from within their tiny apartments and start exploring and smiling again; w</span>e all start walking places once more, appreciating the murals and the brownstones we have around us; Mr. Softee trucks glide through town and the city just somehow seems more welcoming, brighter and more energetic. Read on to find out why we love spring in NYC.</p>\r\n<h1><strong>Everything shifts al fresco</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Spring signals the beginning of the city returning&nbsp;from its winter hibernation into the outdoors. Restaurants and cafes spill out onto the streets, shops open their windows and rooftops dust off their fairy lights. Annual outdoor favorites like </span><strong>Grand Banks</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, </span><strong>Frying Pan</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and the rooftop at&nbsp;</span><strong>Le Bain</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> return, giving you a chance to get your dose of vitamin D alongside your social life.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We love Brooklyn&rsquo;s </span><strong>Smorgasburg</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, the largest weekly open-air food market in America, which draws up to 30,000 visitors a week. This year, the market will open on April 6 and run every Saturday at East River State Park and every Sunday at Prospect Park.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Why we love spring in New York City (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/JvP_092714_0497_print.jpg\" alt=\"Why we love spring in New York City (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;<em>Photo: Smorgasburg</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Brooklyn Flea</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> will be moving outside to their summer DUMBO location starting April 7, with 80 vendors selling vintage clothes, knick-knacks and delicious food every Sunday. We&rsquo;re also looking forward to the opening of the new </span><strong>Time Out DUMBO</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> food market this spring. Wonderful&nbsp;Brooklyn rooftops like </span><strong>Our Wicked Lady</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, one of the </span><strong>top ten rooftops in NYC</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, will also be reopening soon, with weekly Monday night karaoke starting April 1.</span></p>\r\n<h1><strong>The trees are blooming</strong></h1>\r\n<p>People who say New York is a concrete jungle have obviously not visited in the spring. Spring sees the annual rebirth of nature in the city, from park life to flowers. At the top of the list are the cherry blossom festivals, which you can catch all around the city.</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We love the annual </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Orchid Show</strong> </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">at New York Botanical Garden in the Bronx, where thousands of orchids transform the Enid A. Haupt Conservatory into a spring wonderland, from Feb. 23 to April 28.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The theme of this year&rsquo;s festival is </span><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Orchid Show: Singapore</span></em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, which includes special Orchid Evenings where you can come after dark and see the Supertrees alongside an incredible light display, highlighting the orchids&rsquo; natural beauty, with a side-helping of drinks, snacks and live entertainment.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><img title=\"Why we love spring in New York City (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/Brooklyn-Botanic-Garden-Cherry-Blossom-Festival-2017-Prospect-Heights-Prospect-Park-NYC.jpg\" alt=\"Why we love spring in New York City (Image-2)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Photo: Untapped Cities</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Brooklynites should try the famous </span><strong>Sakura Matsuri Cherry Blossom Festival</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> at Brooklyn Botanic Garden, an exciting weekend of Japanese culture and nature, where you can enjoy Taiko drummers, J-rock bands and stand-up comics across the festival&rsquo;s two stages, plus a Japanese tearoom, art gallery, mini flea market and even a cosplay fashion show. Roosevelt Island also has its own </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Cherry Blossom Festival</strong> </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">on April 13, which is free and open to the public without registration.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Or if you&rsquo;re not quite ready for the outside world, check out </span><strong>Macy&rsquo;s Flower Show</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, a giant arrangement of flowers spread throughout their flagship Herald Square store. This year&rsquo;s theme is </span><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Journey to Paradisios, </span></em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">an outer space experience explored through the medium of flowers.</span></p>\r\n<h1><strong>The parks are perking up</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We love </span><strong>Central Park</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and </span><strong>Prospect Park</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> in the spring more than any other season, as well as the many </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">smaller parks</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> dotted across the city. Listen to the blue-jays in Central Park&rsquo;s </span><strong>Sheep Meadow</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, followed by a rowboat trip beside&nbsp;</span><strong>Bow Bridge</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> for just $15 an hour, or bike, run or picnic throughout Prospect Park&rsquo;s tranquil 526 acres. NYC is famous for its Crabapple, Magnolia, Weeping Cherry, Dogwoods and Eastern Redbuds, which truly come to life in the spring.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">For something different, try </span><strong>Brooklyn Grange</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, the world&rsquo;s largest rooftop soil farm, which has two-and-a-half acres of agricultural produce spread between its two sites at Long Island City and Brooklyn Navy Yard. This agricultural marvel grows more than 50,000 pounds of tomatoes, leafy greens, carrots and other produce every year, making it the perfect place to walk around on a tour, volunteer or take one of their educational classes in the spring sun.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img title=\"Why we love spring in New York City (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/Brooklyn-Grange-Roof.jpg\" alt=\"Why we love spring in New York City (Image-3)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo: <em>Inhabitat.com</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1><strong>The baseballs are flying</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Last, but not least, s</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">pring is the beginning of baseball season. April is the start of Major League Baseball\'s regular season, and</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> you can catch the&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Mets</strong>,</span> <strong>Yankees</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> or minor league games across </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">all five boroughs. Even if you don&rsquo;t follow America\'s Pastime, the food and the atmosphere at </span><strong>Citi Field</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> or </span><strong>Yankee Stadium</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> are an experience in themselves. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Check out </span><a href=\"https://www.mlb.com/mets\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">the Mets\'</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and </span><a href=\"https://www.mlb.com/yankees\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Yankees\'</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> schedules at mlb.com.</span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Why we love spring in New York City (Image-4), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/-nymets-citifield-queens-nyc-courtesy-new-york-mets-rs38649_cespedes_darnaud__large.jpg\" alt=\"Why we love spring in New York City (Image-4)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo:<em> NYCgo</em></p>', 'JvP_092714_0497_print.jpg', 1, '2019-03-26 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(254, '#MemberMonday: Jorge Sebastián Rodríguez', 1, 'membermonday-jorge-sebastin-rodrguez', '', '#MemberMonday: Jorge Sebastián Rodríguez', '#MemberMonday: Jorge Sebastián Rodríguez', 'This week\'s #MemberMonday is Jorge, a musician and photographer from Madrid and a new member at our South Williamsburg House.', '<p>This week\'s&nbsp;#MemberMonday&nbsp;is&nbsp;Jorge, a musician and photographer from Madrid and a new member at our South Williamsburg House.</p>', '<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This week\'s&nbsp;<strong>#MemberMonday&nbsp;</strong>is&nbsp;Jorge, a musician and photographer from Madrid and a new member at our South Williamsburg House.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"#MemberMonday: Jorge Sebasti&aacute;n Rodr&iacute;guez (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/1116061_10152305544152889_1513970820_o.jpg\" alt=\"#MemberMonday: Jorge Sebasti&aacute;n Rodr&iacute;guez (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1>Tell us a bit about yourself.</h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Hey! I&rsquo;m Jorge, a guitar player from Madrid (Spain)! I&rsquo;ve just moved to New York and I will be staying until October studying music.</span></p>\r\n<h1>What\'s your favorite Outpost memory?</h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">I&rsquo;ve only been here for a few weeks but the parties are turning out to have pretty funny moments!</span></p>\r\n<h1>What&rsquo;s your favorite part of New York?</h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">I love walking around downtown Manhattan taking pictures of every view that the city offers (I&rsquo;m into photography as a side hobby). It&rsquo;s awesome to see classic corners that appear in top films. </span></p>\r\n<h1>What are you working on now?</h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">I&rsquo;m going to be studying music for two semesters at the Collective School of Music. I&rsquo;m really into jamming and making music that mixes different genres, in particular I love the mix of funk, rock and atmospheric sounds. If you want to jam, let me know!</span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>', '1116061_10152305544152889_1513970820_o.jpg', 1, '2019-04-01 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(255, 'Welcoming spring with sunshine and succulents', 1, 'welcoming-spring-with-sunshine-and-succulents', '', 'Welcoming spring with sunshine and succulents', 'Welcoming spring with sunshine and succulents', 'Succulents: desert plants whose fleshy leaves and stems are actively storing water every chance they get', '<p>Succulents: desert plants whose fleshy leaves and stems are actively storing water every chance they get. The benefit of this is that these plants are drought-resistant, so no need to worry if you forget to water it for a week or two. We replanted our very own succulents this past Saturday during our first community-wide succulent planting event.</p>', '<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><img title=\"Welcoming spring with sunshine and succulents (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/IMG_0006.JPG\" alt=\"Welcoming spring with sunshine and succulents (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Succulents: desert plants whose fleshy leaves and stems are actively storing water every chance they get.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The benefit of this is that these plants are drought-resistant, so no need to worry if you forget to water it for a week or two. These plants are ideal for those of us who are constantly on the go.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We replanted our very own succulents this past Saturday during our first community-wide succulent planting event. Members and friends of Outpost were invited over to the </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">East Williamsburg House</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, where we decorated little pots with paint and placed each one of our tiny friends in a new home with fresh soil. Every attendee got their very own succulent to take away with them as a keepsake!</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">I placed mine on the window ledge right next to my bed. It&rsquo;s a cute little reminder of how cool it is that Outpost provides us with so many opportunities to connect with and engage with other members who are living in our community.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Check out how the event went below:</span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /><br /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img title=\"Welcoming spring with sunshine and succulents (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/IMG_0001.JPG\" alt=\"Welcoming spring with sunshine and succulents (Image-2)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><br /><img title=\"Welcoming spring with sunshine and succulents (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/IMG_0002.JPG\" alt=\"Welcoming spring with sunshine and succulents (Image-3)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><img title=\"Welcoming spring with sunshine and succulents (Image-4), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/IMG_0004.JPG\" alt=\"Welcoming spring with sunshine and succulents (Image-4)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img title=\"Welcoming spring with sunshine and succulents (Image-5), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/IMG_0009.JPG\" alt=\"Welcoming spring with sunshine and succulents (Image-5)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The painting aspect of my project turned out to be pretty mediocre, but the process was quite therapeutic. And speaking of therapy, April 6th is our </span><strong>Coloring and Chocolate</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> event, where we will be indulging in chocolate and coloring books for National Stress Awareness Month. Stay tuned..</span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>', 'IMG_0009.JPG', 1, '2019-04-03 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(256, 'Outpost Club Opens Its Ninth Co-Living House in New York City', 1, 'outpost-club-opens-its-ninth-co-living-house-in-new-york-city', '', 'Outpost Club Opens Its Ninth Co-Living House in New York City', 'Outpost Club Opens Its Ninth Co-Living House in New York City', 'Renting in New York just got easier, thanks to a new 30-person house opened by Outpost Club', '<p>Renting in New York just got easier, thanks to a new 30-person house opened by Outpost Club, Brooklyn&rsquo;s largest and most flexible coliving company and a leader in building strong, dynamic communities of people with shared passions and values -- all while bringing together convenience and quality in New York City&rsquo;s competitive housing market.</p>', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Renting in New York just got easier, thanks to a new 30-person house opened by Outpost Club, Brooklyn&rsquo;s largest and most flexible coliving company and a leader in building strong, dynamic communities of people with shared passions and values -- all while bringing together convenience and quality in New York City&rsquo;s competitive housing market.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The new South Williamsburg House is located near where the Williamsburg, Bushwick and Bedford-Stuyvesant neighborhoods meet, offering members the opportunity to live in a culturally rich, diverse area with a strong sense of community. The house itself offers the perfect escape from the stress of everyday life, with large common areas, a spacious backyard lounge and a rooftop with a beautiful view of the Manhattan skyline. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">&ldquo;We&rsquo;re excited to continue to expand and to make living in New York easier for anyone who is moving to the city,&rdquo; Outpost Club CEO Sergii Starostin said. &ldquo;We have members from all over the world who bring their passions and culture to New York City, and we all benefit.&rdquo; </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The six-apartment, fully furnished South Williamsburg House comes with all the essentials and affords members the opportunity to interact with young professionals, creatives and recent graduates from all over the world, thanks to a dozen monthly Outpost events designed with the diversity of our members in mind, and large, open spaces built for socializing in every house. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The company currently has <a href=\"../new-york\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">nine co-living houses</a>&nbsp;in New York: seven in Brooklyn, in the Williamsburg, Boerum Hill, Bushwick, Flatbush and Bed-Stuy neighborhoods; one in Ridgewood, Queens; and one in Manhattan near the border of Harlem and the Upper East Side.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Membership with Outpost Club is attractive to recent graduates and young professionals due to flexible commitments that do not require extensive documentation, large deposits or guarantors. Pricing is always transparent and the minimum lease length is one month. All-inclusive membership at the South Williamsburg House starts as low as $790. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Outpost Club, Brooklyn&rsquo;s leading coliving operator with nine houses and 200 members, was founded in 2016 by a team who knows what it&rsquo;s like to move to new places and start from scratch. Outpost Club aims to make it incredibly easy to move to New York, with no scams, hidden fees, startup costs or massive security deposits. Outpost Club members gain an instant community with opportunities to socialize, network and grow, all in beautiful and convenient houses at affordable prices. <a href=\"../\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Find more information here</a>.&nbsp;</span><br /><br /></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><img title=\"Outpost Club Opens Its Ninth Co-Living House in New York City (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/04.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Club Opens Its Ninth Co-Living House in New York City (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Club Opens Its Ninth Co-Living House in New York City (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/12.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Club Opens Its Ninth Co-Living House in New York City (Image-2)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Club Opens Its Ninth Co-Living House in New York City (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/09.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Club Opens Its Ninth Co-Living House in New York City (Image-3)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Club Opens Its Ninth Co-Living House in New York City (Image-4), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/23.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Club Opens Its Ninth Co-Living House in New York City (Image-4)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Club Opens Its Ninth Co-Living House in New York City (Image-5), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/29.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Club Opens Its Ninth Co-Living House in New York City (Image-5)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost Club Opens Its Ninth Co-Living House in New York City (Image-6), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/27.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost Club Opens Its Ninth Co-Living House in New York City (Image-6)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'outpost-club-opens-its-ninth-co-living-house-in-new-york-city.jpg', 1, '2019-04-02 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(357, '5 skills you can learn online', 1, '5-skills-you-can-learn-online', '', '5 skills you can learn online', '5 skills you can learn online', 'Looking for something to do with your evenings in isolation? If you’re looking to learn a new skill with your new found downtime but don’t know where to start, we’ve got you covered. Sometimes, the possibilities of the internet can be overwhelming, so here are our favorite skills to learn online we think you’ll love.', '<p>Looking for something to do with your evenings in isolation? If you&rsquo;re looking to learn a new skill with your new found downtime but don&rsquo;t know where to start, we&rsquo;ve got you covered. Sometimes, the possibilities of the internet can be overwhelming, so here are our favorite skills to learn online we think you&rsquo;ll love.</p>', '<p>Looking for something to do with your evenings in isolation? If you&rsquo;re looking to learn a new skill with your new found downtime but don&rsquo;t know where to start, we&rsquo;ve got you covered. Sometimes, the possibilities of the internet can be overwhelming, so here are our favorite skills to learn online we think you&rsquo;ll love.</p>\r\n<h1><strong>1.&nbsp;</strong><strong style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Coding</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Many of today&rsquo;s kids are already being taught coding in schools, which means it might become the new normal in our professional lifetimes. So why not take this opportunity to learn how to code? You can learn the basics for free online, allowing you to build your own websites, apps and much more.</span> <a href=\"http://www.codecademy.com/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Code Academy</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> has a free online coding program or why not try Hardvard&rsquo;s </span><a href=\"https://www.edx.org/course/harvardx/harvardx-cs50x-introduction-computer-1022\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Introduction to Computer Science</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> course online for free? If you can afford one-on-one training, we love the </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">subscription-model certification courses from </span><a href=\"https://www.udacity.com/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Udacity</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, which includes the added help of a tutor to answer your coding questions for just $19 a class. For practical help, </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">the free Practical JavaScript course from </span><a href=\"https://watchandcode.com/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Watch and Code</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> is a popular choice, as it centers around a single project to put your skills into practice. Or why not make coding fun and learn through playing games? </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">T</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">he </span><a href=\"https://education.minecraft.net/get-started/).\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Minecraft: Educational Edition</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">&nbsp;is used for teaching kids in schools, using activities which are just as fun and absorbing for adults.</span></p>\r\n<h1><strong>2. Speed reading</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Speed reading is a skill which can make all the difference to both your professional and your personal life. Being able to skim passages, documents and even novels can save you masses of time while still getting the important content from the words. </span><a href=\"http://www.spreeder.com/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Spreeder</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> is a free online program designed to help you improve your reading and comprehension skills in order to hone in on texts, helping you to double or even triple the speed at which you read.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h1><strong>3. Languages</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Now is the perfect opportunity to brush up on your language skills, whether that&rsquo;s reminding yourself of your high school French or taking a stab at Arabic for the first time. For online language practice which you can fit into your everyday routine, try </span><a href=\"http://www.duolingo.com/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Duolingo</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, available as an app or online, where you can learn Spanish, French, Portuguese, Italian, English and more in daily bitesize chunks for free. Or if you&rsquo;re looking for one-on-one language courses (via webcam, of course), we love </span><a href=\"https://www.apprentus.com/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Apprentus</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, an online database of language teachers at reasonable prices, complete with reviews and information on their training so you can be sure you&rsquo;re getting the support you need at a budget that works for you.</span></p>\r\n<h1><strong>4. Mindfulness</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Mindfulness is an important life skill which can improve your quality of life more than you might expect. Mindfulness is all about being present in the now, both mentally and physically. You can practice mindfulness through mental activities, including apps such as <a href=\"https://www.headspace.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Headspace</a>, or physical activities such as yoga. We love the guided meditation videos on Youtube by <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCu_mPlZbomAgNzfAUElRL7w\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">The Mindful Movement</a>, which come in both short clips and longer immersive meditation sessions, making it the perfect way to immerse yourself in the present moment and forget your stresses.</span></p>\r\n<h1><strong>5. Writing</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Being able to write well can improve the quality of your professional work and your personal correspondence. Thankfully, you can learn the art of writing online during isolation with online courses, such as </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Macalester College</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\'s <a href=\"https://www.macalester.edu/academics/writewell/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">lecture series</a>. Or if you&rsquo;re looking for professional writing courses with a tutor or even one-on-one writing tuition, check out <a href=\"http://writingclasses.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Gotham Writers</a>, NYC&rsquo;s leading writing school whose courses have now all switched to online for the time being. If you\'re more interested in journalism, try </span><a href=\"http://en.wikiversity.org/wiki/Journalism\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Wikiversity\'s course selection</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> or explore the many, many courses available for free on <a href=\"http://coursera.org\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Coursera</a>.</span></p>', '2_13.jpg', 1, '2020-04-09 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(257, '#MemberMonday: Beau Mantor', 1, 'membermonday-beau-mantor', '', '#MemberMonday: Beau Mantor', '#MemberMonday: Beau Mantor', 'This week\'s #MemberMonday is Beau, an actor and director from California and a member of our Ridgewood House.', '<p>This week\'s&nbsp;#MemberMonday&nbsp;is Beau, an actor and director from California and a&nbsp;member of our Ridgewood House.</p>', '<p style=\"text-align: left;\">This week\'s&nbsp;<strong>#MemberMonday</strong>&nbsp;is Beau, an actor and director from California and a&nbsp;member of our Ridgewood House.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"#MemberMonday: Beau Mantor (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/51325143_2407055642855025_2138509562943111168_n.jpg\" alt=\"#MemberMonday: Beau Mantor (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<h1>Tell us a bit about yourself.</h1>\r\n<p>I moved out to New York from Tracy, California (it\'s an hour east of San Francisco) a little over 9 months ago. I studied Theatre Arts at Loyola Marymount University in Los Angeles and moved out here shortly after graduation. My goal is to be an actor/director so I figured I will give New York a shot for a couple years.</p>\r\n<h1>What\'s your favorite Outpost memory?</h1>\r\n<p>My favorite Outpost memory is when we took a couple vans up to Bear Mountain and hiked to the top. Then we had a big barbecue along the lake there and even went to a free zoo nearby. It was a much needed break from the city and it was great for making friends because we got to spend the whole day together.</p>\r\n<h1>What&rsquo;s your favorite part of New York?</h1>\r\n<p>My favorite part of New York is Brooklyn Bridge Park and Brooklyn Heights. It still feels like you\'re in the city, but it\'s more peaceful and less crowded.</p>\r\n<h1>What are you working on now?</h1>\r\n<p>I\'ve been working on writing short comedy sketches as well as a short film that talks about suicide and mental illness.</p>', '51325143_2407055642855025_2138509562943111168_n.jpg', 1, '2019-04-08 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0);
