(267, 'Destination: Little Skips', 1, 'destination-little-skips', '', 'Destination: Little Skips', 'Destination: Little Skips', 'Little Skips is something of a Bushwick legend. Since its opening nine years ago, it’s made a name for itself as one of the original and still the best community-focused cafes in Brooklyn', '<p>Little Skips is something of a Bushwick legend. Since its opening nine years ago, it&rsquo;s made a name for itself as one of the original and still the best community-focused cafes in Brooklyn, with a dedication to top coffee, co-working and local events. Located on the corner of Myrtle and Willoughby, in between the Central Avenue M stop and the Myrtle M, J and Z stops, this cafe is a little slice of tranquility on your doorstep.</p>', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Little Skips is something of a Bushwick legend. Since its opening nine years ago, it&rsquo;s made a name for itself as one of the original and still the best community-focused cafes in Brooklyn, with a dedication to top coffee, co-working and local events. Located on the corner of Myrtle and Willoughby, in between the Central Avenue M stop and the Myrtle M, J and Z stops, this cafe is a little slice of tranquility on your doorstep.</span></p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Destination: Little Skips (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/GaKYS8PUVw4j8urLhnN1XQ.jpg\" alt=\"Destination: Little Skips (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Photo: Bushwick Daily</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Little Skips</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> is the brainchild of Linda Thach and her best friends, built out of an old carburetor shop and transformed into something wonderful. Outside, you&rsquo;ll notice the colorful graffiti and posters adorning the doorway and the large window with the white &lsquo;Little Skips&rsquo; logo stencilled on and you&rsquo;ll instantly feel at home. The vibe inside is relaxed and geared towards creatives and co-workers during the day, with speedy Wi-Fi and strong coffee that will fuel you all the way through that first draft. The high ceilings and ample windows means there&rsquo;s plenty of light and opportunities for people-watching, while the colorful walls will inspire you, as you realize that the pictures are a rotating display by community artists instead of stock images bought from Ikea.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The main focus of the Little Skips menu is the coffee. This cafe serves Counter Culture coffee and puts on a daily rotating menu of different drip coffees for the coffee connoiseur in you. Prices are reasonable, with a small drip coffee starting at just $2.50 and a wide selection of cold brew, lattes and other espresso-based drinks in the $4.00 region. We love the Bomb Latte (a latte sweetened with Condensed milk) and the Jack &amp; Taylor (a latte sweetened with Maple syrup), both for $4.75, and the summer iced drink menu includes the delicious Iced Thai Tea and Iced Dirty Thai. They also serve a range of tea drinks and the counter is always filled with a selection of baked goods to munch away at while you chat or work.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Destination: Little Skips (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/2018-07-14%2B05.47.50%2B1.jpg\" alt=\"Destination: Little Skips (Image-2)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Photo: Little Skips</span></em></p>\r\n<p>And don&rsquo;t worry, Little Skips also serves food. With a kitchen that stays open until 7:30 p.m. daily, this includes cheap bagels ($2.25) with a choice of toppings, as well as vegan options and gluten-free substitute bread. There&rsquo;s also a list of simple but delicious twist-dishes, including avocado toast topped with pickled radish, baby arugula and honey-lemon vinaigrette and a mean grilled cheese that can be made with vegan cheese, as well as sandwiches and salads.</p>\r\n<p>We love the delicious M-Train, made with goat cheese, pesto, sliced turkey, tomato, red onion, hard-boiled egg and honey on multigrain toast and the vegan BLT, made with smoked maple tempeh bacon, tomato, mixed greens and house-made cilantro-lime aioli. The salads are simple, starting at $7, and they come as a base of greens onto which you can then add your choice of a range of toppings, including prosciutto and Granny Smith apples.</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">One thing that makes Little Skips different is its dedication to the Brooklyn community, which is shown through both the art on the walls and a schedule of regular events. May 10th is the launch of the Spring Art show, where a whole host of local artists will be hung on the walls of the coffee shop for the first time</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, including </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">M Erazo, Rosalind Watson, Avery Webster-Hobbs and Robin Grant. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">And every Tuesday, Little Skips holds an </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">open mic</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> night, which includes performances of spoken word, music, comedy, dance and anything else you can think of, where locals and visitors alike can sign up and perform in a non-judgmental atmosphere. They also hold regular live music shows, where you can sip on beer and wine while listening to some up-and-coming local talent.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Destination: Little Skips (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/2018-07-14%2B05.45.42%2B1.jpg\" alt=\"Destination: Little Skips (Image-3)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Photo: Little Skips</span></em></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">By no</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">w, you can probably see why we love this place -- and we </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">love it even more because it&rsquo;s just an 11-minute walk from our </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">South Williamsburg House</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and a short trip from our </span><a href=\"../montrose-williamsburg-house\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Montrose Williamsburg</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">&nbsp;and </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><a href=\"../the-bed-stuy-house\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Bed-Stuy</a>&nbsp;houses</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. Over the last 9 years, Little Skips has expanded to </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">f</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">our locations</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> across New York, so you&rsquo;re probably not too far from one of the branches, even if the original isn&rsquo;t in your neighborhood.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Little Skips</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">941 Willoughby Avenue</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Brooklyn, NY 11221</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">M-F: 7am - 8pm</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sat/Sun: 8am - 8pm.</span></p>', 'GaKYS8PUVw4j8urLhnN1XQ.jpg', 1, '2019-05-02 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(268, '#MemberMonday: Beatrice Micheli', 1, 'membermonday-beatrice-micheli', '', '#MemberMonday: Beatrice Micheli', '#MemberMonday: Beatrice Micheli', 'This week\'s #MemberMonday is Beatrice from Italy, a talented pastry chef and a member of our South Williamsburg House.', '<p>This week\'s #MemberMonday is Beatrice from Italy, a talented pastry chef and a member of our South Williamsburg House.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p>This week\'s <strong>#MemberMonday</strong> is Beatrice from Italy, a talented pastry chef and a member of our South Williamsburg House.</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"#MemberMonday: Beatrice Micheli (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/59334995_1008023782724940_33767329233895424_n.jpg\" alt=\"#MemberMonday: Beatrice Micheli (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<h1>Tell us a bit about yourself.</h1>\r\n<p>Hey! I&rsquo;m Beatrice and I&rsquo;m from Italy! I moved to&nbsp;NYC almost 6 month ago with a J1 visa program and I&rsquo;m staying here until December!</p>\r\n<h1>What\'s your favorite Outpost memory?</h1>\r\n<p>Outpost parties, for sure! When I first got to NYC I was so scared because I didn\'t know anyone, but I immediately made friends here at Outpost Club! The people I\'ve met here are my American family right now! We have so much fun and we&rsquo;re making great memories together.</p>\r\n<h1>What&rsquo;s your favorite part of New York?</h1>\r\n<p>DUMBO! I love art and I think the view of Manhattan by the water is the perfect setting to paint a picture. There&rsquo;s something magic in the air, especially at sunset!</p>\r\n<h1>What are you working on now?</h1>\r\n<p>I&rsquo;m working as a Pastry Chef at a restaurant in Midtown! I&rsquo;m really dedicated to my job; I want to learn as much as I can while I\'m here and this is a great opportunity to learn different techniques and flavors.</p>', '59334995_1008023782724940_33767329233895424_n.jpg', 1, '2019-05-06 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(269, 'The 9 Most Instagrammable Spots in Central Park', 1, 'the-9-most-instagrammable-spots-in-central-park', '', 'The 9 Most Instagrammable Spots in Central Park', 'The 9 Most Instagrammable Spots in Central Park', 'At 843 acres, Central Park is the largest park in Manhattan. Here are nine of the most Instagrammable spots in Central Park to get you started.', '<p>At 843 acres, Central Park is the largest park in Manhattan. It has been the setting of major and low-budget films, musical performances, weddings, wedding proposals and -- for that reason -- plenty of tourism. The park bustles with activity and beauty year-round and is filled with so many unique and interesting sights, you couldn&rsquo;t possibly capture them all in one day. However, you can fit many of them! Here are nine of the most Instagrammable spots in Central Park to get you started.</p>', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">At <a href=\"https://www.centralpark.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">840 acres</a>, Central Park is the largest park in Manhattan. It has been the setting of major and low-budget films, musical performances, weddings, wedding proposals and -- for that reason -- plenty of tourism. The park bustles with activity and beauty year-round and is filled with so many unique and interesting sights, you couldn&rsquo;t possibly capture them all in one day. However, you can fit most of them! Here are nine of the most Instagrammable spots in Central Park to get you started.</span></p>\r\n<h2>The Carousel</h2>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The original carousel was <a href=\"https://freetoursbyfoot.com/things-to-do-in-central-park/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">run by a horse or mule</a> underneath the platform that was trained to start and stop at the attendant\'s command; it has burned down twice since then. It&rsquo;s now up and running with 57 horses and runs 7 days a week in the summer. A great example of American folk art, these ponies are a beauty to behold and even more fun to ride!</span></p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"The 9 Most Instagrammable Spots in Central Park (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/Screen%20Shot%202019-05-01%20at%201.17.29%20PM.png\" alt=\"The 9 Most Instagrammable Spots in Central Park (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Bethesda Terrace</h2>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Bethesda Terrace is considered the heart of Central Park. The tree-lined mall leads up to the terrace, where you&rsquo;ll find the gorgeous Angel of Waters statue right at the center. The statue is symbolic for purifying the water of <a href=\"../nyc-rooms-for-rent\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">New York</a> so that it is safe to drink. Bethesda Terrace is also the filming place of many films, including the last scenes of Avengers, Elf, Gossip Girl and Sex and the City. Definitely make sure to add this one to your list!</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"The 9 Most Instagrammable Spots in Central Park (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/Screen%20Shot%202019-05-06%20at%204.43.17%20PM.png\" alt=\"The 9 Most Instagrammable Spots in Central Park (Image-2)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" />&nbsp;<br /><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">@justineayala</span>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Alice In Wonderland Statue</h2>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Located at the north end of the pond, this statue shows Alice and the Mad Hatter Tea Party. The design for the statue itself was taken from the illustration in the first edition of the novel that was ever released. The story has since been turned into a major motion picture and is known as an iconic piece of American pop culture. Fun thing to note -- you can climb this sculpture!</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img title=\"The 9 Most Instagrammable Spots in Central Park (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/Screen%20Shot%202019-05-06%20at%205.42.26%20PM.png\" alt=\"The 9 Most Instagrammable Spots in Central Park (Image-3)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /><br />@simplystephanye</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">Diana Ross Playground</h2>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Did you know there is a playground named after legendary R&amp;B singer Diana Ross? Well, now you do, and it\'s a playground that was proposed and funded by Diana Ross herself in 1986 (more on that <a href=\"https://ny.curbed.com/maps/central-park-new-york-city-things-to-do\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">here</a>). Today, the park is still a fixture and is open to the public on the park&rsquo;s west side. Pretty neat, eh?</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img title=\"The 9 Most Instagrammable Spots in Central Park (Image-4), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/Screen%20Shot%202019-05-01%20at%201.43.27%20PM.png\" alt=\"The 9 Most Instagrammable Spots in Central Park (Image-4)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\"><br />Strawberry Fields and the Imagine Mosaic</h2>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Both the fields and mosaic have an interesting history, as they were dedicated to John Lennon and Yoko Ono -- his widow -- who lived in the Dakota Building just outside the park before Lennon&rsquo;s passing. Strawberry Fields&rsquo; grassy lawn is lined with trees and various types of foliage and is recognized as a Garden of Peace by 121 different countries!</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Imagine Mosaic, located at the center point of Strawberry Fields, is the field&rsquo;s main attraction. It was designed by Italian mosaic artists and donated by Naples, Italy, during the planning of the garden after John Lennon&rsquo;s death. These works are truly inspiring and certainly not to be missed!<br /></span><br /><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"The 9 Most Instagrammable Spots in Central Park (Image-5), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/8b8546428828179352ce3144a8a6cb07.jpg\" alt=\"The 9 Most Instagrammable Spots in Central Park (Image-5)\" width=\"564\" height=\"752\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Central Park Zoo</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Central Park is so large, you can fit an entire zoo inside it &hellip; and this zoo is full of photo opportunities! It was also a major setting of the animated movie Madagascar. Though parts of the movie&rsquo;s setting are fictionalized, </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Delacorte Clock and the Sea Lion Pool are actually shown!<br /></span><br /><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"The 9 Most Instagrammable Spots in Central Park (Image-6), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/Screen%20Shot%202019-05-06%20at%204.44.47%20PM.png\" alt=\"The 9 Most Instagrammable Spots in Central Park (Image-6)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">@lydiastravels.x</span></p>\r\n<h2>The Mall&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You&rsquo;ll easily be able to identify the Mall, because it is the only path in Central Park that is laid out as a straight line. The mall is lined on both sides by a cathedral ceiling of American elm trees and is home to one of the largest collections of these trees in the U.S. Follow The Mall all the way to the end and you&rsquo;ll find yourself at Bethesda Arcade. </span><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">When Harry Met Sally, Maid In Manhattan, Breakfast at Tiffany&rsquo;s, Home Alone 2, Vanilla Sky, Enchanted</span></em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and other films have all had famous scenes set here.<br /><br /><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"The 9 Most Instagrammable Spots in Central Park (Image-7), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/Screen%20Shot%202019-05-01%20at%201.33.58%20PM.png\" alt=\"The 9 Most Instagrammable Spots in Central Park (Image-7)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /><br /></span></p>\r\n<h2>Bow Bridge</h2>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This 60-foot structure is one of the most photographed and filmed spots in Central Park. </span><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Spider Man 3</span></em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and </span><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Night At The Museum</span></em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> have scenes filmed here, marriage proposals have taken place here and during the warmer months, rowboats can be seen floating underneath. Needless to say, Bow Bridge is a hot spot and is as charming as it is popular.</span><br /><br /><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"The 9 Most Instagrammable Spots in Central Park (Image-8), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/974b3517fdd15f7207261925192b3b33.jpg\" alt=\"The 9 Most Instagrammable Spots in Central Park (Image-8)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Sheep\'s Meadow</h2>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sheep&rsquo;s Meadow was used for grazing sheep until 1934, when they were moved to Prospect Park due to a fear that out-of-work New Yorkers would eat them during the Great Depression. It was afterwards turned into a lawn where locals can often be seen out on the grass, basking in the sunlight.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img title=\"The 9 Most Instagrammable Spots in Central Park (Image-9), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/Screen%20Shot%202019-05-06%20at%205.44.30%20PM.png\" alt=\"The 9 Most Instagrammable Spots in Central Park (Image-9)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /><br />@ampersandattire&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Hope this list inspires you to visit Central Park and create your own adventure to share with the world!</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '64dab7ac2739fce04f56f7bff7f49fc1.jpg', 1, '2019-05-06 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(271, 'Outpost San Francisco Is Officially Open', 1, 'outpost-san-francisco-is-officially-open', '', 'Outpost San Francisco Is Officially Open', 'Outpost San Francisco Is Officially Open', 'It’s only been a few weeks since we announced we were planning to expand to the West Coast, and we’re excited to say that as of today, that dream has become a reality', '<p>It&rsquo;s only been a few weeks since we announced we were planning to expand to the West Coast, and we&rsquo;re excited to say that as of today, that dream has become a reality. The Outpost Japantown House is now officially open!</p>', '<p>It&rsquo;s only been a few weeks since we announced we were planning to expand to the West Coast, and we&rsquo;re excited to say that as of today, that dream has become a reality. The Outpost Japantown House is now officially open.</p>\r\n<p>The Japantown House is newly renovated and fully furnished with everything you\'ll need to feel at home -- all you have to bring is your suitcase. The house\'s gorgeous views and spacious common areas are the perfect respite from hectic city life, and the Japantown neighborhood is chock-full of dining and entertainment options, from mom-and-pop shops to the restaurants of world-renowned chefs.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The location is central to some of our favorite parts of San Francisco, from vibrant Haight-Ashbury to the scenic Golden Gate Park and Presidio views to the nightlife of SoMa and the Mission. From the Japantown House, you\'ll be able to explore everything the City by the Bay has to offer.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Membership at the Japantown House includes utilities, WiFi, Netflix, access to exclusive events, regular cleaning and consistently stocked household essentials like coffee, tea, paper towels, soap and toilet paper -- and, best of all, the opportunity to make friends with people from all over the world. Your Gold membership includes added benefits like more flexibile stays, exclusive membership rates, access to longer guest stays and more. Check out the details <a href=\"../memberships\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">here</a>.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Want to join us? Head over <a href=\"../join-us\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">here</a>&nbsp;and we\'ll be in touch!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost San Francisco Is Officially Open (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/outpost-san-francisco-is-officially-open-5.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost San Francisco Is Officially Open (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost San Francisco Is Officially Open (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/outpost-san-francisco-is-officially-open-4.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost San Francisco Is Officially Open (Image-2)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost San Francisco Is Officially Open (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/outpost-san-francisco-is-officially-open-3.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost San Francisco Is Officially Open (Image-3)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost San Francisco Is Officially Open (Image-4), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/outpost-san-francisco-is-officially-open-2.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost San Francisco Is Officially Open (Image-4)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Outpost San Francisco Is Officially Open (Image-5), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/outpost-san-francisco-is-officially-open-1.jpg\" alt=\"Outpost San Francisco Is Officially Open (Image-5)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>', '26.jpg', 1, '2019-05-10 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(270, 'Why Boerum Hill is a great place to live', 1, 'why-boerum-hill-is-a-great-place-to-live', '', 'Why Boerum Hill is a great place to live | Outpost Club blog', 'Why Boerum Hill is a great place to live', 'Boerum Hill is like the movie-set version of Brooklyn. Balanced place for living and working with beautiful parks and independent vibe.', '<p>Boerum Hill is like the movie-set version of Brooklyn. Walking around, you&rsquo;ll be struck by the gorgeous red brick, historic brownstones and leafy streets. Similar to its sister neighborhoods Cobble Hill and Carroll Gardens, it&rsquo;s almost as though the entire neighborhood is slowly exhaling: the area is a quiet, picturesque retreat from the bustle of Manhattan, without being boring.</p>', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Boerum Hill is like the movie-set version of Brooklyn. Walking around, you&rsquo;ll be struck by the gorgeous red brick, historic brownstones and leafy streets. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Similar to its sister neighborhoods </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Cobble Hill</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Carroll Gardens</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">it&rsquo;s almost as though the entire neighborhood is slowly exhaling: the area is a quiet, picturesque retreat from the bustle of Manhattan, without being boring.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Why Boerum Hill is a great place to live (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/Boerum-Hill.jpg\" alt=\"Why Boerum Hill is a great place to live (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /><em>Photo: Brooklyn Bridge Realty</em></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Boerum Hill was first settled in the 1800s as a family-centric Manhattan suburb (the name coming from the Boerum family, whose farm occupied most of the area). Nowadays, the family vibe remains, but the refurbished townhouses and new options to eat, drink and play has attracted a younger, fashionable crowd. Here&rsquo;s our insight into why Boerum Hill is a great place to live.</p>\r\n<h3>The balance between quiet and busy</h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Boerum Hill has done a magical thing: it has managed to strike that perfect balance between quiet and busy. This is one of the reasons it&rsquo;s so popular with Manhattan commuters, particularly those working in Lower Manhattan and Wall Street. Boerum Hill is right in the West of Brooklyn, so the trendy atmosphere of the Lower East Side has made the jump across the Brooklyn Bridge. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">At the same time, you&rsquo;ll be surprised by how quiet the neighborhood is when walking around from our </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Downtown Brooklyn House</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, which is located in the heart of the neighborhood. The airy streets are lined with trees and dog walkers in both summer and winter alike and the historic buildings, mostly consisting of three-story row houses built between 1840 and 1870, are some of the most beautiful in the city. It&rsquo;s not uncommon to see locals lounging on their stoops in the summer sun. Boerum Hill is one of those rare places where you can feel like you&rsquo;re in the middle of nowhere, when really you&rsquo;re always within a block or two of a restaurant, cafe or bar.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Why Boerum Hill is a great place to live (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/carousel-large.jpg\" alt=\"Why Boerum Hill is a great place to live (Image-2)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /><em>Photo: Brooklyn Bridge Park</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We love how Boerum Hill is just a 25 minute walk from the water; stand out on the pier at </span><strong>Brooklyn Bridge Park Pier 5</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and marvel at the amazing Manhattan skyline in front of you. It feels like you&rsquo;ve walked to the edge of the earth, when really you&rsquo;re just a stone&rsquo;s throw from home. At the same time, you can walk onto any part of Smith Street or Atlantic Avenue, the two thoroughfares of Boerum Hill, and find rows of people sat outside chatting in the innumerable restaurants and cafes.</span></p>\r\n<h3><strong>The independent vibe</strong></h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Boerum Hill is full of independent cafes, restaurants and shops -- more so than any other Brooklyn neighborhood -- which makes exploring even more fun than usual. We love bar </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">61 Local</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, which holds regular writing workshops and open mic evenings through the </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Brooklyn Poets Yawp</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Little Sweet Cafe</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> is a popular cafe for daytime treats with a relaxed, old-world vibe, while </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Greenlight Bookstore</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> is one of our favorite independent bookstores in the entire city, with a program of regular talks and events. In fact, the whole of Smith Street is lined with restaurants and bars including </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Saul</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Clover Club</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Joya</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, which has now become a destination spot for Brooklyn foodies, while Atlantic Avenue is a center for boutique shopping. Big names like </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Jonathan Adler</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Nunu Chocolates</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> have their flagship stores here, while specialty stores like </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Cheryl Kleinman Cakes</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Acorn</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> gives this popular street a more intimate feel. Boerum Hill is also home to many artists who own art galleries in the neighborhood, including </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Invisible Dog Art Center</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Roulette</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Issue Project Room</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, and </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">BAM</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. All of this combined makes for a carefree atmosphere geared towards browsing, with a small town, outer-borough pace of life in a location just a few stops from Manhattan.</span></p>\r\n<h3><strong>With one amazing exception</strong></h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Not everything is independent, though. One thing about Boerum Hill which is reason enough to move here on its own is that it has one of only two </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Trader Joe&rsquo;s</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> in Brooklyn. Trader Joe&rsquo;s is a chain supermarket that is basically refrigerated wonderfulness: It&rsquo;s the best place to get good quality and affordable fruit and vegetables in NYC. There&rsquo;s also a </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Wholefoods</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, so you&rsquo;ll be spoiled for choice for healthy options if you choose Boerum Hill as your base.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Why Boerum Hill is a great place to live (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/0_4200_84_2716_two_nyc-midtown-florist-greenhouse-jbk0042.jpg\" alt=\"Why Boerum Hill is a great place to live (Image-3)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /><em>Photo: <a href=\"https://www.airbnb.co.uk/locations/new-york/boerum-hill\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Airbnb</a></em><br /></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Did we mention the transport connections?</strong></h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Boerum Hill is one of the best located Brooklyn neighborhoods, situated on the west side of Brooklyn. Our </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Downtown Brooklyn House</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, in the heart of the neighborhood, is just a 34 minute journey to Times Square and a 21 commute to Wall Street. Bergen Street Station, in the middle of the neighborhood, is conveniently located on the F and the G lines, making travelling both into the city and around Brooklyn itself a breeze, while a short walk will bring you to the 2 and the 3 trains at Hoyt Street and the A and C trains at Hoyt-Schermerhorn for easy access to Downtown and Uptown Manhattan.</span></p>\r\n<p>All in all, we think the location combined with the relaxed vibes makes Boerum Hill an amazing place to live in Brooklyn and t&rsquo;s easy to see why it&rsquo;s one of the most popular neighborhoods in the city.</p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>\r\n<p>Do you still disagree that Boerum Hill is a fantastic place to live? This region exemplifies balance in all things, and with us you may choose a balanced version of your <a href=\"../new-york\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">apartment</a> right now.</p>', 'Boerum-Hill.jpg', 1, '2019-08-14 05:00:00', '2022-11-01 07:26:12', NULL, 0, 0),
(274, 'Why Flatbush is a great place to live', 1, 'why-flatbush-is-a-great-place-to-live', '', 'Why Flatbush is a great place to live | Outpost Club blog', 'Why Flatbush is a great place to live', 'Flatbush is a community-centred neighborhood with plenty of green space, located to the south of Prospect Park. Together with Outpost Club, let\'s figure out why Flatbush is a great place.', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Flatbush is a community-centred neighborhood with plenty of green space, located to the south of </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Prospect Park</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. The neighborhood is known for being a melting pot of West Indian, Russian, Pakistani and other communities and it </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">includes the area from Parkside Avenue on the north to Avenue H on the south, with Coney Island and New York avenues on the west and east, placing it right in the middle of Brooklyn. So here are our top reasons why Flatbush is a great place to live.</span></p>', '<p>Flatbush is a community-centered neighborhood with plenty of green space located south of <strong>Prospect Park</strong>. The neighborhood is known for being a melting pot of West Indian, Russian, Pakistani and other communities, and it includes the area from Parkside Avenue on the north to Avenue H on the south, with Coney Island and New York avenues on the west and east, placing it right in the middle of Brooklyn. So here are our top reasons why Flatbush is a great place to live.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Why Flatbush is a great place to live (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/prospect-park-alliance-tours-brooklyn-1-1.jpg\" alt=\"Why Flatbush is a great place to live (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /><em>Photo: Brownstoner.com</em></p>\r\n<h2>The open space</h2>\r\n<p>Considering it&rsquo;s in the middle of Brooklyn, you&rsquo;d be surprised by how much space you have in Flatbush. There&rsquo;s no rubbing shoulders like in Midtown Manhattan -- everyone has room to breathe. The streets are wide and leafy and there are plenty of parks in the area, including <strong>Paerdegat Park</strong><strong>,</strong> a tree-filled green space with sports courts, benches and a playground just a short walk from our <a href=\"../the-flatbush-house\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Flatbush House</a>, and <strong>Holy Cross Cemetery</strong>, the burial ground of several noteworthy New Yorkers, such as the notorious Louis Capone. Our Flatbush House is also just a short walk from famous Prospect Park, Brooklyn&rsquo;s own version of Manhattan&rsquo;s Central Park.</p>\r\n<p>Designed by Olmsted and Vaux, the same brains behind <a href=\"../blog/the-9-most-instagrammable-spots-in-central-park\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Central Park</a>, this park is 526 acres of fresh air, including a man-made pond and the bulk of Brooklyn\'s remaining indigenous forest. This park even has its very own zoo and the first urban-area Audubon Center, as well as an ice rink, bandstand and athletic equipment. In the summer, Prospect Park is famous for its concerts and events as well a plenty of informal gatherings, including sports teams, joggers and picnickers. Bliss.</p>\r\n<h2>The range of eating, drinking and doing options</h2>\r\n<p>Flatbush is statistically one of the city&rsquo;s most diverse neighborhoods, which shows in the number of different things to eat, drink and do. <strong>Zurilee Pizza</strong> serves some of the best<strong> Caribbean pizza</strong>, starting at just $12 per pie. Their signature dish, the bake and saltfish pizza, is the star of the show and will leave you wanting more. We love Werkstatt for Viennese Bratwurst and schnitzel and Sip Unwine for delicious fusion tapas and fine wine.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Weird and wonderful combinations abound in Flatbush, including Brooklyn&rsquo;s first tattoo parlor and bar, <strong>FIB Tattoo Bar</strong>, and the bar-slash-flowershop&nbsp;<strong>Sycamore Bar and Flowershop</strong>. The&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.brooklyncenter.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Brooklyn Center for the Performing Arts at Brooklyn College</a> is a great spot to see emerging and established artists, or for shopping we recommend <strong>Muffets Closet</strong> and <strong>Le Point</strong>. Flatbush Avenue and Cortelyou Road are the main hubs of culture and retail options, just a short walk from our Flatbush House.</p>\r\n<h2>The history</h2>\r\n<p>Flatbush is filled with history, something that will hit you when you walk by the large, expansive Victorian homes along Bedford Avenue and other pre-war houses near <a href=\"http://www.brooklyn.cuny.edu/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Brooklyn College</a>. The neighborhood is the popular site of Brooklyn history tours, particularly for Victorian enthusiasts. The restored <a href=\"http://www.kingstheatre.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Kings Theater</a> is a landmark in itself, having been built in 1929.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Why Flatbush is a great place to live (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/kings-venue-2-1920x1280.jpg\" alt=\"Why Flatbush is a great place to live (Image-3)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /><em>Photo: Kings Theatre</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>This beautiful and decadent theatre seats more than 3,000 people. Originally a movie theatre, since its renovation and re-opening in 2010 it is now a live performance venue, with a program of varied events to entertain the neighborhood. Flatbush is also home to the <strong>Flatbush Reformed Dutch Church</strong>, built in 1654, and <strong>NYC&rsquo;s oldest high school</strong> (attended by Barbra Streisand, Neil Diamond, and others).</p>\r\n<h2>The affordability</h2>\r\n<p>Flatbush is one of the more affordable Brooklyn neighborhoods. Flatbush Ave. is filled with discount stores and affordable Caribbean delis, and many of our favorite cafes, restaurants and bars have excellent deals. For instance, <strong>Koko Ramen</strong> has a daily happy hour from 12 p.m.&ndash;7 p.m. on both drinks and food, and our favorite Mexican restaurant, <strong>Taqueria Maria and Ricardo</strong>, serves tostadas starting at just $4.95.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Why Flatbush is a great place to live (Image-4), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/2013228-dollar-van2.jpg\" alt=\"Why Flatbush is a great place to live (Image-4)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /><em>Photo: BlogTO.com</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Flatbush is also one of the only Brooklyn neighborhoods to have <strong><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dollar_van\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">dollar vans</a></strong>. Think of these as a mixture between Uber Pool and the bus: You pay $2 and you can hop on the van&rsquo;s pre-set route, hopping off again at your stop. It&rsquo;s quick and convenient and above all, cheap. You can find out more information and download the app here. We think that&rsquo;s reason enough on its own to consider living in Flatbush, particularly in the wake of the L-train slowdown, don&rsquo;t you?</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>After considering these points, if you still feel confident, we will be pleased to assist you in finding a <a href=\"../new-york\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">rental home</a> in this lovely area. You won\'t be dissatisfied with Flatbush, and we will make every effort to give you the nicest home possible.</p>', 'Flatbush-what-to-expect-1.jpg', 1, '2019-05-30 05:00:00', '2022-11-01 07:16:24', NULL, 0, 0),
(364, 'New Hobbies to Try From Home', 1, 'new-hobbies-to-try-from-home', '', 'New Hobbies to Try At Home', 'New Hobbies to Try From Home', 'During quarantine we have an abundance of free time — hours we used to spend in transit to work, hanging out with friends, or exploring the city. If you’re burnt out on Netflix and scrolling endlessly through social media, it might be time to pick up a new hobby to fill up some of that free time. Here are our favorite hobbies that are Outpost apartment-friendly!', '<p>During quarantine we have an abundance of free time &mdash; hours we used to spend in transit to work, hanging out with friends or exploring the city. If you&rsquo;re burnt out on Netflix and scrolling endlessly through social media, it might be time to pick up a new hobby to fill up some of your days. Here are our favorite hobbies that are Outpost apartment-friendly!</p>', '<p>During quarantine we have an abundance of free time &mdash; hours we used to spend in transit to work, hanging out with friends or exploring the city. If you&rsquo;re burnt out on Netflix and scrolling endlessly through social media, it might be time to pick up a new hobby to fill up some of that free time. Here are our favorite hobbies that are Outpost apartment-friendly!</p>\r\n<h2>Chef It Up</h2>\r\n<p>Now that we can&rsquo;t sit down at our favorite restaurants for a gourmet meal, it&rsquo;s time to try out your hand at cooking from home. Choose your top five favorite meals to eat out and recreate them at home &mdash; you can amp up your chef skills and impress your roommates with delicious dishes to share. Not sure where to start? Try out this delicious and fresh avocado shrimp ceviche&nbsp;<a href=\"https://therecipecritic.com/shrimp-ceviche-recipe/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">recipe</a>&nbsp;that only uses seven ingredients!</p>\r\n<h2>Bullet Journal</h2>\r\n<p>If you&rsquo;re looking for a new way to stay organized and flex your creativity, buy a blank journal and build a personalized bullet planner from scratch. Plan your workouts, grocery store trips, online seminars and workflow for each week &mdash; bonus points for adding in drawings and color-coding your routines. This is a great way to stay motivated and on-track even during quarantine! If you\'re new to journaling, follow <a href=\"https://artisthue.com/how-to-start-a-bullet-journal/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">this guide</a>&nbsp;to begin a pro-bullet planner even as a beginner.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Learn a New Language</h2>\r\n<p>What a better time to add a valuable skill to your resume! With apps like Duolingo at your fingertips, it&rsquo;s never been easier to pick up a new language. Build a routine with at least&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.nbcnews.com/better/pop-culture/how-learn-new-language-15-minute-day-installments-ncna872776\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">15 minutes</a>&nbsp;a day dedicated to learning &mdash; even incremental studying and practice will boost your language skills!</p>\r\n<h2>Become Your Own Bartender</h2>\r\n<p>Rather than shelling out $10 for a take-out cocktail, learn how to mix your own signature creations. Create your go-to drink you usually order at the nearest bar or make new summer cocktails with muddled fruit, simple syrup or fresh herbs. Your next Zoom happy hour will feel even more celebratory with a homemade concoction in-hand. Here\'s <a href=\"https://www.brit.co/fancy-cocktail-recipes/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">14 recipes</a> to give a shake!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Programming</h2>\r\n<p>Get ahead and learn how to program! Nearly every industry relies on digital programming in some capacity, so this skill can go far and set you apart from your peers. LinkedIn has a <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/learning\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">free one month trial </a>with lessons from experts, or try out one of these <a href=\"https://hackernoon.com/21-websites-to-learn-programming-for-free-5101c1ddf0c\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">21 free websites</a>&nbsp;to start learning code.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>DIY Outfit Upgrades</h2>\r\n<p>If you&rsquo;re looking for a wardrobe makeover without breaking the bank, try some DIY clothing revamps. Whether you bust out a needle and thread to turn that ratty old tee into a <a href=\"http://theessentialsclub.com/blog-posts/shirred-crop\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">crop top</a> or create your own personalized and <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8KHGNUrYkWk\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">trendy tie-dye set</a>, there are a plethora of online guides to make even the oldest outfits look brand new.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Photo credit: Amber Maxwell Boydell</em></p>', 'amber-maxwell-boydell-lZwLB8OLs1Y-unsplash.jpg', 1, '2020-05-18 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0);
