(275, 'What happens to your mail after you leave Outpost?', 1, 'what-happens-to-your-mail-after-you-leave-outpost', '', 'What happens to your mail after you leave Outpost?', 'What happens to your mail after you leave Outpost?', 'As part of our Ask a House Leader series, here’s an answer about your mails', '<p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">At Outpost, your house leader is someone you&rsquo;re going to want to get to know very well. They&rsquo;re your main connection to the company and will be there for you if you have questions about Outpost or if you need help with anything. Our house leaders are vital to Outpost and their wells of knowledge run deep. As part of our Ask a House Leader series, here&rsquo;s an answer to one recent question for them</span></em></p>', '<p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">At Outpost, your house leader is someone you&rsquo;re going to want to get to know very well. They&rsquo;re your main connection to the company and will be there for you if you have questions about Outpost or if you need help with anything. Our house leaders are vital to Outpost and their wells of knowledge run deep. As part of our Ask a House Leader series, here&rsquo;s an answer to one recent question for them:</span></em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Q: What happens to my mail after I leave?</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A: One of the great things about Outpost is there&rsquo;s no waiting in for your mail. Getting your mail is simple (we&rsquo;ve explained it in a dedicated <a href=\"../blog/ask-a-house-leader-how-does-getting-mail-work\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">blog post</a>) and your house leader is always ready to answer any mail-related questions. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">But when the time comes that you move on from Outpost to a new home (sob), you have to take a few steps to change your mailing address:</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Fill out a </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">change of address form</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> with USPS as soon as you move out, or even a day or two before. This is the fastest and easiest way to change your address. All you need is an email address and you&rsquo;ll get an instant confirmation that the change has been processed. This should only cost you a dollar. (There are some scammers offering to do this for a service fee of $40 -- avoid these!)</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you don&rsquo;t like doing things online, you can also go to your </span><a href=\"https://tools.usps.com/go/POLocatorAction_input\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">local post office</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and request a Mover&rsquo;s Guide packet, in which you&rsquo;ll find a PS Form 3575. Just fill this out at the counter and hand it in at the post office (this option can take up to five business days).</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We know that life is hectic and it&rsquo;s only human to forget to change your address with the stress of moving out. If that happens, we do collect mail of old members every so often </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">and return them to the post office to return to sender, but we can&rsquo;t guarantee this or accept responsibility for what may happen to missed mail, so it\'s always safest to just make sure you\'ve changed your address in time -- especially if you know you\'re expecting a letter or package.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you have any more questions,</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> you can reach your house leader via your house&rsquo;s Facebook Messenger group, or, obviously, you&rsquo;re welcome to ask us in person the next time you see us around!</span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>', 'pope-moysuh-229262-unsplash.jpg', 1, '2019-05-13 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(276, '#MemberMonday: Nícolas Raposo', 1, 'membermonday-ncolas-raposo', '', '#MemberMonday: Nícolas Raposo', '#MemberMonday: Nícolas Raposo', 'Meet Nícolas from Brazil, the House Leader at our Central Park Manhattan House and a lover of all things philosophical and cultural.\r\n', '<p>Meet N&iacute;colas from Brazil, the House Leader at our Central Park Manhattan House and a lover of all things philosophical and cultural.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p>Meet N&iacute;colas from Brazil, the House Leader at our Central Park Manhattan House and a lover of all things philosophical and cultural.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1><strong>Tell us a bit about yourself.</strong></h1>\r\n<p>I&rsquo;m N&iacute;colas and I&rsquo;m from a small town in Brazil called Teres&oacute;polis. I like soccer, reading, museums and hiking and I am getting into rock climbing and learning about wine! I&rsquo;m here in NYC to immerse myself in the English language and learn about educational opportunities outside of my home country.</p>\r\n<h1><strong>What\'s your favorite Outpost memory?</strong></h1>\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s tough to choose just one Outpost memory as a favorite! I have had lovely times at parties in Bushwick, peaceful moments in the beautiful rooms in Manhattan and great nights out in the city with Outpost friends from multiple houses.</p>\r\n<h1><strong>What&rsquo;s your favorite part of New York?</strong></h1>\r\n<p>My favorite part of New York (besides the people) is that I can find a place to cater to whatever mood I\'m in, all in the same&nbsp;city. If I Google anything in the world, it has some representation right here in NYC. When I miss Brazilian food, I can find it in multiple boroughs.</p>\r\n<h1><strong>What are you working on now?</strong></h1>\r\n<p>Right now I&rsquo;m working on improving my English. I&rsquo;m interested in philosophy and literature, so I&rsquo;ve been reading about these things as well -- and I\'m always busy with my House Leader work as well as exploring the city!</p>', '56837264_2209600795821337_3730892121276678144_n.jpg', 1, '2019-05-13 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(279, 'Destination: Bushwick Grind', 1, 'destination-bushwick-grind', '', 'Destination: Bushwick Grind', 'Destination: Bushwick Grind', 'Bright and down-to-earth, the community-centric Bushwick Grind focuses on creating a great experience for their patrons. ', '<p>Bright and down-to-earth, the community-centric Bushwick Grind focuses on creating a great experience for their patrons.</p>', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Bright and down-to-earth, the community-centric Bushwick Grind focuses on creating a great experience for their patrons. They are a prime example of local eatery excellence in Brooklyn, not only in their mouth-watering and aesthetically pleasing drinks and dishes but also in their ability to create a comfortable, friendly atmosphere. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This location is great for decompressing, kicking back with friends or getting work done, whether it be a meeting or otherwise. Enjoy favorites like coffee, espresso and tea, as well as entrees for every meal and lighter fare and specialty drinks for a more casual dining experience. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The warm staff members are all about customizing each dish or drink to your dietary needs, serving great gluten-free and vegan options. They use all-natural ingredients sourced from local vendors, so eating well here simultaneously boosts the Brooklyn community. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">They serve all-day brunch Fridays through Sundays, provide free WiFi and host events periodically to engage the community and promote local artists. (Speaking of local artists, the restaurant is host to a bright, colorful mural that balances out the place&rsquo;s earthy vibe.)</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You feel the acceptance of the Grind as soon as you step in. You don&rsquo;t need to dress up to eat well and have a good time here; you are just fine as you are. The crowd you&rsquo;ll find here is just as grounded as the locale; they reinforce the refreshing, laid-back energy of the place. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In the very likely case that you want to share the goodness with co-workers, friends and family, Bushwick Grind can cater and/or host your events. If you&rsquo;re craving the food but can&rsquo;t stay long, there are pick-up options as well as delivery through the UberEats and Seamless apps.</span></p>\r\n<p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Located a 5-minute walk from our South Williamsburg House and an 8-minute walk from our Montrose Williamsburg House. Find Bushwick Grind at 63 Whipple Street in Brooklyn.</span></em></p>\r\n<p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><img title=\"Destination: Bushwick Grind (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/avocado_tower_3.jpg\" alt=\"Destination: Bushwick Grind(Image-1)\" /></span></em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Susa Breese/Outpost Club</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><em><img title=\"Destination: Bushwick Grind (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/interior_1.jpg\" alt=\"Destination: Bushwick Grind(Image-2)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Susa Breese/Outpost Club</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><em><img title=\"Destination: Bushwick Grind (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/storefront_3_wide.jpg\" alt=\"Destination: Bushwick Grind(Image-3)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Susa Breese/Outpost Club</em>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'storefront_3_wide.jpg', 1, '2019-06-06 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(278, 'Destination: Devoción Coffee & Roastery', 1, 'destination-devocion-coffee--roastery', '', 'Destination: Devoción Coffee & Roastery', 'Destination: Devoción Coffee & Roastery', 'If you like fresh coffee, you’re going to love Devocion: It\'s one coffee shop that really stays true to its mission of delivering carefully sourced coffee beans to its patrons.', '<p>If you like fresh coffee, you&rsquo;re going to love Devocion: It\'s one coffee shop that really stays true to its mission of delivering carefully sourced coffee beans to its patrons.</p>', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you like fresh coffee, you&rsquo;re going to love Devocion: It\'s one coffee shop that really stays true to its mission of delivering carefully sourced coffee beans to its patrons. Every cup of coffee brewed at Devocion has been roasted with beans from hand-selected farms in areas of Columbia that have been suffering from internal conflict. </span></p>\r\n<p>As an extra measure, Devocion makes sure to participate in fair-trade practices, even investing in social and environmental programs to help farmers thrive. Once harvested, the coffee beans are then shipped via FedEx and roasted here in NYC -- making a difference in the lives of Columbian farmers and bringing you the freshest coffee possible!</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Devocion has three locations in the New York City area -- including Williamsburg, Downtown Brooklyn and Flatiron in Manhattan (their newest location). You&rsquo;ll know it\'s Devocion by the golden yellow panel with black lettering.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">On the other side of the wooden doors you&rsquo;ll be immersed in a world that brings pure Colombian flavor to life. The fragrant aromas aren&rsquo;t the only things that&rsquo;ll beckon you to stay -- the interior decor at this &ldquo;botica de cafe&rdquo; is as tropical as the beans themselves. Inside you&rsquo;ll find foliage-lined walls with plants of different kinds, WiFi, outlets, large windows and plenty of seating. The rooftop windows at Devocion let in plenty of sunlight and provide a lovely view of trees cascading above. The calm and inviting ambiance makes this a great spot to study, work or chat with friends over an iced latte.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You don&rsquo;t have to take it iced, though -- Devocion also offers hot coffees, cold brews, aromatic infusions and a unique array of pastries to satiate your cravings, all of which start at around $5. Fan favorites include the guava croissants. Just remember to bring your debit cards as this is a cashless establishment, so paper bills will not be accepted.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><br /><img title=\"Destination: Devoci&oacute;n Coffee &amp; Roastery (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/Screen%20Shot%202019-05-24%20at%2012.06.12%20PM.png\" alt=\"Destination: Devoci&oacute;n Coffee &amp; Roastery (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /><br /><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Devocion - Williamsburg/Yelp</span></em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Roastery &amp; Coffee Shop - Williamsburg</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">69 Grand St. (at Wythe)</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Brooklyn, NY 11249</span></p>\r\n<p><strong>DOWNTOWN BROOKLYN</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">276 Livingston St</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Brooklyn, NY 11201</span></p>\r\n<p><strong>Devoci&oacute;n Coffee Flatiron District</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">25 East 20th Street </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">New York, NY 10003</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><em>Main image credit:&nbsp;Mika I./Yelp</em></strong><br /><br /></p>', 'Screen Shot 2019-05-24 at 12.07.37 PM.png', 1, '2019-05-24 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(331, 'Member Monday: Agustina Cal', 1, 'member-monday-agustina-cal', '', 'Member Monday: Agustina Cal', 'Member Monday: Agustina Cal', 'Get to know cultural exchange enthusiast, former dancer and Outpost House Leader Agustina Cal for this week\'s Member Monday.', '<p>Get to know cultural exchange enthusiast, former dancer and Outpost House Leader Agustina Cal for this week\'s Member Monday.</p>', '<p>Get to know cultural exchange enthusiast, former dancer and Outpost House Leader Agustina Cal for this week\'s Member Monday.</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"Member Monday: Agustina Cal (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/IMG_0002.JPG\" alt=\"Member Monday: Agustina Cal (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<h1>Tell us a bit about yourself.</h1>\r\n<p>I have been a house leader at Outpost since October of 2019. My passion for cultural exchange pushed me to start traveling at a very young age. I have been fortunate enough to make friends from very different backgrounds over the years. I was a dancer for the Joffrey Ballet back in the day and am currently seeking a career in health and fitness.</p>\r\n<h1>What\'s your favorite Outpost memory?</h1>\r\n<p>My favorite Outpost memory is the day that I arrived in NYC. George, the manager welcomed me as if I was family. Outpost\'s team is comprised of caring, warm and generous people and behind their actions, there is always an intention to go further than needed.</p>\r\n<h1>What\'s your favorite part of New York?</h1>\r\n<p>My favorite part of New York is the Highline and all of the art galleries in SoHo. It is very inspiring to know that you live surrounded by artists where society constantly moves to change and evolve.</p>\r\n<h1>What are you working on now?</h1>\r\n<p>I am currently volunteering at Outpost for several of their houses in the city. I am happy to be part of their project since it makes many people\'s lives better and therefore is a step toward a better world. Many of my roommates and friends in this community acknowledge how much easier it is to keep their work/life balance by sharing our coliving space. It provides them with the opportunity to share their city experiences with new friends and never feel alone again. Thank you Outpost for an incredible journey.</p>', 'IMG_0002.JPG', 1, '2019-12-02 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(332, '5 most Instagrammable SF winter spots', 1, '5-most-instagrammable-sf-winter-spots', '', '5 most Instagrammable SF winter spots', '5 most Instagrammable SF winter spots', 'Winter is a magical time to snap photos of the city lit up and gleaming.', '<p>Winter is a magical time to snap photos of the city lit up and gleaming.</p>', '<h1><strong>1. Union Square at Christmas</strong></h1>\r\n<p><strong>Address:&nbsp;333 Post St, San Francisco, CA 94108</strong></p>\r\n<p><br /><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"5 most Instagrammable SF winter spots (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/1_30.jpg\" alt=\"5 most Instagrammable SF winter spots (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo: <em>TripSavvy</em></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Union Square is always festive with a huge tree and an ice skating rink at the center of the square. Head down to this Instagram spot and pop into festive Macy&rsquo;s at the same time.</span></p>\r\n<h1><strong>2. Holmes Bakery</strong></h1>\r\n<p><strong>Address:&nbsp;1042 Larkin St, San Francisco, CA 94109</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"5 most Instagrammable SF winter spots (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/3_20.jpg\" alt=\"5 most Instagrammable SF winter spots (Image-2)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo: <em>PictoSee</em></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Home of the famous &ldquo;I Got Baked in San Francisco&rdquo; neon sign, this bakery is a winter Insta hot spot with some of the best cronuts in the city.</span></p>\r\n<h1><strong>3.&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.sfmoma.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">San Francisco Museum of Art</a></strong></h1>\r\n<h4>Address: 151 3RD Street, San Francisco, CA 94103</h4>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"5 most Instagrammable SF winter spots (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/2_22.jpg\" alt=\"5 most Instagrammable SF winter spots (Image-3)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo: <em>SFMOMA&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">SFMOMA is one of the most popular galleries in SF with one of the largest range of modern and contemporary art in the US. Enjoy work from artists like Andy Warhol, Frida Kahlo, and Louise Stettner while snapping pics in front of the art.</span></p>\r\n<h1><strong>4. Home Cafe</strong></h1>\r\n<h4>Address: 1222 Noriega Streer, San Francisco,&nbsp;CA 94122</h4>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"5 most Instagrammable SF winter spots (Image-4), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/1_31.jpg\" alt=\"5 most Instagrammable SF winter spots (Image-4)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo: <em>June R., Yelp</em></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Home Cafe is famous for its beautifully designed coffee. The intricate latte art makes it an ideal location to warm up during the winter while refreshing your feed. There are two locations in the city and we love the </span><strong>Noriega Street Home location</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.</span></p>\r\n<h1><strong>5. <a href=\"https://www.ferrybuildingmarketplace.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">San Francisco Ferry Building</a></strong></h1>\r\n<p><strong>Address:&nbsp;<a>One Ferry Building,&nbsp;</a><a>San Francisco, CA 94111</a></strong></p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"5 most Instagrammable SF winter spots (Image-5), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/2_23.jpg\" alt=\"5 most Instagrammable SF winter spots (Image-5)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo: <em>Chowhound&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We love the food market at this historic ferry terminal. During the winter, you can snap the beautiful lights draped around the walls for the ultimate warm and fuzzy feeling inside.</span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>', '2_5.jpg', 1, '2019-12-04 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(333, 'Destination: Nitehawk Cinema', 1, 'destination-nitehawk-cinema', '', 'Destination: Nitehawk Cinema', 'Destination: Nitehawk Cinema', 'Looking for a place to hide out until winter is over without giving up your social life? Nitehawk Cinema is the answer.', '<p>Looking for a place to hide out until winter is over without giving up your social life? Nitehawk Cinema is the answer.</p>', '<p>Looking for a place to hide out until winter is over without giving up your social life? Nitehawk Cinema is the answer.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.nitehawkcinema.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Nitehawk Cinema</a>, located on the east side of Williamsburg, is a hipster, artsy hangout with a twist. Sit back, relax and enjoy getting your regular dose of culture with a selection of independent, foreign and classic films, curated for quality. And of course you can watch it all in luxury; enjoy the big, comfy sofas and chairs and grab a cocktail from the bar or a pizza from the restaurant to complete the perfect night in (but out).</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Destination: Nitehawk Cinema (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/1_34.jpg\" alt=\"Destination: Nitehawk Cinema (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" />Photo: <em><a href=\"http://www.nitehawkcinema.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Nitehawk Cinema</a></em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Right now, they&rsquo;re showing <em>Waves </em>(2019), <em>Knives Out </em>(2019), <em>JoJo Rabbit </em>(2019), <em>Parasite </em>(2019), <em>Knives and Skin </em>(2019) and <em>Black Christmas </em>(1974). <em>Waves </em>stars Kelvin Harrison Jr. and Taylor Russel, telling the story of a suburban African-American family in South Florida, as they deal with issues of forgiveness and familial love in the wake of loss. You can watch the trailer and find out more here.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">There are also Friday and Saturday night &ldquo;Midnite&rdquo; movies, starting at 12am, every week. This month, they&rsquo;re showing <em>Knives and Skin </em>(2019), which traces the investigation of a young girl&rsquo;s disappearance in a rural Midwest town, led by an inexperienced local sherriff, making for a chilling teen noir filled with a bitter loss of innocence (watch the trailer here).</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Destination: Nitehawk Cinema (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/3_21.jpg\" alt=\"Destination: Nitehawk Cinema (Image-2)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;Photo: <em><a href=\"http://www.nitehawkcinema.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Nitehawk Cinema</a></em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">There are even different dining special to suit each of the movies on show. Nitehawk puts together food and drinking pairings. Right now if you go to see <em>The Waves</em>, you can enjoy a vodka cocktail (&ldquo;In Tyler&rsquo;s Shadow&rdquo;) and a Cuban-spiced burger big enough to share.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">There&rsquo;s also a full menu which includes vegan and gluten free options (we love the vegan popcorn and the &ldquo;Beyond&rdquo; vegan burger) and you can order your food and drink during the film and have a friendly server bring it to your table. You can even drop by the intimate bar after your movie for a cosy answer to a winter&rsquo;s night out.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><em>Nitehawk Cinema</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><em>136 Metropolitan Ave</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><em>Brooklyn</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><em>NY 11249</em></p>', '3_5.jpg', 1, '2019-12-06 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(281, 'Five Japantown Coffee Shops We Love', 1, 'five-japantown-coffee-shops-we-love', '', 'Five Japantown Coffee Shops We Love | Outpost Club blog', 'Five Japantown Coffee Shops We Love', 'Japantown is a hub of culture and coffee in the heart of San Francisco', '<p>Japantown is a hub of culture and coffee in the heart of San Francisco. There&rsquo;s everything from quiet cafes for studying to stylish spots for meeting friends, but how do you narrow down your choices? Here are five of our favorite coffee shops within walking distance of our Japantown House.</p>', '<p>Japantown is a hub of culture and coffee in the heart of San Francisco. There&rsquo;s everything from quiet cafes for studying to stylish spots for meeting friends, but how do you narrow down your choices? Here are five of our favorite coffee shops within walking distance of our Japantown House.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><strong>YakiniQ Cafe</strong></h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>YakiniQ Cafe is our go-to spot for a quiet space to write, work or catch up with friends. This peaceful cafe has quick WiFi, a laid-back vibe, plenty of outlets and friendly staff who don&rsquo;t mind if you buy one coffee and sit there all afternoon.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>White walls lined with art and a mixture of comfy sofas and wooden chairs create an inspirational environment and the space is host to regular <strong>&ldquo;Shut up and Write</strong>&rdquo; events, which in itself is a seal of approval in our books.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"9 Five Japantown Coffee Shops We Love (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/o_4.jpg\" alt=\"Five Japantown Coffee Shops We Love (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Photo: Ashley K., Yelp&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>We love their selection of sandwiches and coffees, especially their specialty -- the amazing sweet potato latte, with real pieces of sweet potato inside. (It&rsquo;s less strange than it sounds!) They also do a mean iced soy latte, lavender latte and hazelnut latte, making their own syrups in house, which go perfectly with their Yuzu pound cake, selection of cookies or Kona Coffee Macaron.</p>\r\n<p><strong><em>1640 Post St, 94115 (1-minute walk from our Japantown House)</em></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Cafe Hana</strong></h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Cafe Hana is the closest affordable caffeine fix to our Japantown House. Located just a 1-minute walk from your front door in the Japan </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Center\'s West Mall, this cosy coffee shop is your first stop for specialty drinks, sandwiches and pastries. Their food and snack menu is extensive, including sandwiches, ice cream, coffee and jelly drinks, making it one of the most popular coffee shops in the mall. </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Coffee starts at just $2 a cup, ranging from plain old drip coffee to adventurous treats like the famous </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Geisha Float and \"Frios.\" This Japanese cafe is famous for its affordable takoyaki, which make a great snack at $5 for six pieces. Just be aware that seating is limited, so it&rsquo;s more of a grab and go place than somewhere to stand and stare. </span></p>\r\n<p><strong><em>1737 Post St, 94115 (1-minute walk)</em></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"9 Five Japantown Coffee Shops We Love (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/o_7.jpg\" alt=\"Five Japantown Coffee Shops We Love (Image-2)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Photo: Cris L., Yelp</em>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Quetzal Internet Cafe</strong></h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Quetzal is a good option if you want a coffee shop with a large variety of food, including both indulgent and healthy options, as well as comfortable chairs. Enjoy a choice of bagels, lattes, smoothies and crepes, starting at just $4.95. With outlets and ethernet connections at most seats and quick, reliable WiFi, it&rsquo;s a great place to work. And as day turns to night, we&rsquo;re fans of their happy hour, which runs daily from 3 p.m.&ndash;9 p.m. with wine ($5.95), beer ($4.25) and mimosas ($5.95) at reduced prices.</p>\r\n<p><strong><em>1234 Polk St, 94109 (13-minute walk)</em></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Cafe Murano</strong></h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This bright, yellow-walled cafe is a cute spot to meet or study any time of the week, with a range of comfy couches to nestle into and even outdoor, cafe-style tables for the summer months. We love their wide selection of espresso drinks and affordable bagels (especially the salmon and lox), paninis and sandwiches. They also do a great breakfast, with pastries and oatmeal galore. </span>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><em>1777 Steiner St, 94115 (7-minute walk)</em></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Tan Tan Coffee Shop</strong></h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Tan Tan Coffee Shop is an oasis from the hustle and bustle of Japantown life. This tiny tea and coffee shop, located in the Japan Center, is deceptively under the radar. Step back into the Victorian era with hanging lights, dark wooden panels and real china crockery while you enjoy a variety of English and Japanese teas and coffees, including espresso drinks and even a whisked ceremonial matcha tea, as well as colorful cakes and other patisserie treats. </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"9 Five Japantown Coffee Shops We Love (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/o_8.jpg\" alt=\"Five Japantown Coffee Shops We Love (Image-3)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Photo: Elaine Y., Yelp</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We love their iced mocha, matcha tea and, of course, the matcha cakes. It&rsquo;s not a place to work, but to relax. In fact, part of the quirkiness is that no one is ever quite sure when Tan Tan will open; its friendly owner simply opens when she feels like it.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><em>1825 Post St, 94115 (4-minute walk)</em></strong></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>\r\n<p>Japanese society is known for its minimalism, and residents frequently favor cozy, compact homes. There are many wonderful possibilities for single apartments available to people, but keep in mind that <a href=\"../coliving\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">co living</a> is always more enjoyable.</p>', 'o_1.jpg', 1, '2019-06-20 05:00:00', '2022-11-01 07:28:40', NULL, 0, 0),
(283, '9 Things to Enjoy in Downtown Brooklyn', 1, '9-things-to-enjoy-in-downtown-brooklyn', '', '9 Things to Enjoy in Downtown Brooklyn', '9 Things to Enjoy in Downtown Brooklyn', 'Are you having a slow week? Downtown Brooklyn is just what the doctor ordered', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Are you having a slow week? Downtown Brooklyn is just what the doctor ordered. This cultural hub contains an incomparable concentration of the best life has to offer. From low to high priced, these are some of our favorite things about Downtown Brooklyn:</span></p>', '<p>Are you having a slow week? Downtown Brooklyn is just what the doctor ordered. This cultural hub contains an incomparable concentration of the best life has to offer. From low to high priced, these are some of our favorite things about Downtown Brooklyn:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>1. Open Seating &amp; Green Space</h3>\r\n<p><img title=\"9 Things to Enjoy in Downtown Brooklyn (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/pier_1.JPG\" alt=\"9 Things to Enjoy in Downtown Brooklyn (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>There are so many special alcoves hidden around the Brooklyn Bridge Park. Each spot has a beautiful view of the New York skyline, as well as unique goings-on such as live music and community gatherings. It&rsquo;s always a delight to be around so much vibrance. Sounds to me like it&rsquo;s time for a picnic, huh?&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>Brooklyn Bridge Park, free</em></p>\r\n<p><em><img title=\"9 Things to Enjoy in Downtown Brooklyn (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/bridge_3.jpg\" alt=\"9 Things to Enjoy in Downtown Brooklyn (Image-2)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></em></p>\r\n<h3>2. Street Art &amp; City Life</h3>\r\n<p>Up and down York Street -- or really, anywhere from Pearl to Plymouth to the park -- you will see gorgeous murals, parks, galleries, views, cafes and shops. It&rsquo;s great fun to walk about and spot something new around every corner. The area has so much character, and the things you will find will truly brighten your day.</p>\r\n<p><em>DUMBO to Brooklyn Heights, free</em></p>\r\n<p><em><img title=\"9 Things to Enjoy in Downtown Brooklyn (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/skyline_3.jpg\" alt=\"9 Things to Enjoy in Downtown Brooklyn (Image-3)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></em></p>\r\n<h3>3. Photo Opportunities</h3>\r\n<p>There are moments when you will get to these locations and your jaw will drop. Each spot is designed to have a good time there while just sitting in awe of the glorious skyline. Bring your camera or anyone you want to impress.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>Jane&rsquo;s Carousel, 1 Main Street, Washington Street, Brooklyn Heights Promenade, free</em>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>4. Biking</h3>\r\n<p>Unless you bring your own bike, making the experience free, there are Citi Bike stations throughout the park where you can pick up and drop off a bike to ride around on while you enjoy the park.</p>\r\n<p><em>Brooklyn Bridge Park, $/free</em>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>5. Rock Climbing</h3>\r\n<p>Have you ever wanted to just climb under the Manhattan Bridge? Well, that is actually something you can do, you adventurous individual. Great for beginners or experienced climbers.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>99 Plymouth Street, $</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>6. Roller Skating &amp; Recreational Sports</h3>\r\n<p>Pier 2 is open for public skating from noon to 10:30 p.m. and provides areas for basketball, handball and more. If you&rsquo;re looking to move around and have some fun, this is the place to go.</p>\r\n<p><em>Brooklyn Bridge Park, $</em>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>7. Great Food &amp; Bubble Tea</h3>\r\n<p>If you&rsquo;re looking for a meal on a budget that doesn&rsquo;t skimp on quality, check out Hanco&rsquo;s, a Vietnamese restaurant that serves some of the best spring rolls in Brooklyn, as well as specialty teas that&rsquo;ll rock your world.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>Hanco&rsquo;s at 147 Montague Street, $</em></p>\r\n<p><em>&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<h3>8. Pizza</h3>\r\n<p>Don&rsquo;t be fooled by the name Grimaldi&rsquo;s next door; Juliana&rsquo;s is the real deal, the authentic works of the famous and incredible pizzaiola Patsy Grimaldi. They do not take reservations, so expect to wait in line for the best pizza you will ever have. It&rsquo;s been voted the best pizza in New York City and in America on multiple occasions.</p>\r\n<p><em>Juliana&rsquo;s Pizza at 19 Old Fulton Street, $$</em></p>\r\n<p><em><img title=\"9 Things to Enjoy in Downtown Brooklyn (Image-4), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/boat_1.jpg\" alt=\"9 Things to Enjoy in Downtown Brooklyn (Image-4)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></em></p>\r\n<h3>9. Fine Dining</h3>\r\n<p>There is a boat in the water on Pier 6 that is a full-on restaurant. It has an incredible view, vibrant energy and deliciously creative dishes, not to mention oysters galore. It&rsquo;s a fun and exciting experience to have dinner on the water, and definitely worth a try.</p>\r\n<p><em>Pilot at Pier 6 Brooklyn Bridge Park, $$$</em></p>\r\n<p><em>&nbsp;</em></p>', 'skyline_3.jpg', 1, '2019-06-26 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(363, '5 famous sights and landmarks you can explore virtually', 1, '5-famous-sights-and-landmarks-you-can-explore-virtually', '', '5 famous sights and landmarks you can explore virtually', '5 famous sights and landmarks you can explore virtually', 'Doesn’t it seem like now you can’t cross borders, you want more than ever to visit those sights and landmarks on your bucket list? Thankfully, many of the locations of your dreams are actually available to explore online. Here are our picks of our favorite five.', '<p>Doesn&rsquo;t it seem like now you can&rsquo;t cross borders, you want more than ever to visit those sights and landmarks on your bucket list? Thankfully, many of the locations of your dreams are actually available to explore online. Here are our picks of our favorite five.</p>', '<p>Doesn&rsquo;t it seem like now you can&rsquo;t cross borders, you want more than ever to visit those sights and landmarks on your bucket list? Thankfully, many of the locations of your dreams are actually available to explore online. Here are our picks of our favorite five.</p>\r\n<h1><strong>1. The Great Wall of China</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The </span><a href=\"https://www.history.com/topics/ancient-china/great-wall-of-china\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Great Wall of China</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> is probably China&rsquo;s most famous landmark. More than 13,000 miles long, this ancient wall is one of the </span><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/New7Wonders_of_the_World\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">New 7 Wonders of the World</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. Originally conceived by Emperor Qin Shi Huang in the third century B.C. as a protective measure against invaders, this amazing structure can be viewed online today at this link </span><a href=\"https://www.thechinaguide.com/destination/great-wall-of-china\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">here</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, where you can virtually walk along its famous pathway and look down at the valleys below.</span></p>\r\n<h1><strong>2. The Taj Mahal</strong></h1>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://artsandculture.google.com/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Google Arts and Culture</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> have digitized a huge amount of resources in time for quarantine. One of the many sights you can explore on their database of maps and tours is the </span><a href=\"https://whc.unesco.org/en/list/252/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Taj Mahal</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. This incredible mausoleum of white marble, built between 1631 and 1648 under emperor Shah Jahan in memory of his favorite wife, is one of the most distinctive images of India and another of the </span><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/New7Wonders_of_the_World\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">New 7 Wonders of the World</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. We know you can&rsquo;t get to India right now, so simply click </span><a href=\"https://artsandculture.google.com/streetview/IgGJcPeTu3akmQ?sv_lng=78.04163579068563&amp;sv_lat=27.17459587078385&amp;sv_h=57.58308783182413&amp;sv_p=-4.127420568213054&amp;sv_pid=yXjh2l-sGP0AAAGuolDECw&amp;sv_z=0.21723071622066936\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">here</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> to see it come to life.</span></p>\r\n<h1><strong>3. Disney World</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">I don&rsquo;t know about you, but we need a little fun in our lives right now. That&rsquo;s why we&rsquo;re heading straight for virtual Disney World. Yes, you read that right&mdash;you can now experience your favorite roller coasters online, from Big Thunder Mountain, to Jungle Cruise to the Haunted Mansion, all for free. The Youtube channel </span><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCYyJUEtYv-ZW7BgjhP3UbTg\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Virtual Disney World</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> has a selection of </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">360&ordm; interactive videos which take you through the rides like&nbsp;you&rsquo;re sitting in one of the seats yourself. It&rsquo;s a pretty realistic experience which makes for the perfect way to relax after a long day.</span></p>\r\n<h1><strong>4. Angkor Wat</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This incredible &ldquo;city of temples&rdquo; located in the heart of Cambodia can now be explored online. The largest religious monument in the world, </span><a href=\"https://whc.unesco.org/en/list/668/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Angkor Wat</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> was originally built as a Hindu temple complex in the first half of the 12th century, from which it was gradually transformed into a centre of Buddhist worship. Explore the five towers of Angkor Wat and the surrounding temples in the virtual tour at </span><a href=\"https://www.virtualangkor.com/\">Virtual Angkor</a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. The project even includes 360&ordm; video simulations by archaeologists, historians and CGI artists which recreate life as it was in the 13th century.</span></p>\r\n<h1><strong>5. Palace of Versailles</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Located in Versailles, France, the </span><a href=\"http://en.chateauversailles.fr/discover/estate/palace\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Palace of Versailles</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> is described on its website as &ldquo;</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">one of the greatest achievements in French 17</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">th</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> century art&rdquo; and this isn&rsquo;t wrong at all. What began as </span><a href=\"http://en.chateauversailles.fr/discover/history/great-characters/louis-xiii\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Louis XIII</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\'s old hunting pavilion was transformed and extended by his son, </span><a href=\"http://en.chateauversailles.fr/discover/history/great-characters/louis-xiv\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Louis XIV</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, and is now one of the most beautiful and embellished residences in the world, from the </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Hall of Mirrors to the King\'s Grand Apartments and beyond. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Thanks to </span><a href=\"https://artsandculture.google.com/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Google Arts and Culture</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, you can now explore the interior of this opulent residence, </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">listed as a World Heritage Site for 30 years, from the comfort of your living room</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. From high ceilings to precious artworks to glamorous, historic furnishings, this famous French landmark is sure to intrigue you (if not give you more than a little home-envy). You can find the virtual tour online by clicking </span><a href=\"https://artsandculture.google.com/streetview/palace-of-versailles/cwE5CwK49O0y5Q?sv_lng=2.1204786000000695&amp;sv_lat=48.8051117&amp;sv_h=197&amp;sv_p=0&amp;sv_pid=hNvuL7DMigMQkjP6BRku1A&amp;sv_z=1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">here</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.</span></p>', '2_18.jpg', 1, '2020-04-21 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0);
