(292, '5 Brooklyn Vegan Cafes We Love', 1, '5-brooklyn-vegan-cafes-we-love', '', '5 Brooklyn Vegan Cafes We Love', '5 Brooklyn Vegan Cafes We Love', 'Brooklyn is known for its vegan eateries. Just Googling “vegan cafes” pulls up a wide selection of red pins all across the borough, but how do you know which ones are the best? ', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Brooklyn is known for its vegan eateries. Just Googling &ldquo;vegan cafes&rdquo; pulls up a wide selection of red pins all across the borough, but how do you know which ones are the best? Or which vegan cheese won&rsquo;t stick to the roof of your mouth? Don&rsquo;t worry, we&rsquo;ve picked our top five cafes &mdash; all tried and tested &mdash; to make the process easier.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p>Brooklyn is known for its vegan eateries. Just Googling &ldquo;vegan cafes&rdquo; pulls up a wide selection of red pins all across the borough, but how do you know which ones are the best? Or which vegan cheese won&rsquo;t stick to the roof of your mouth? Don&rsquo;t worry, we&rsquo;ve picked our top five cafes &mdash; all tried and tested &mdash; to make the process easier.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"5 Brooklyn Vegan Cafes We Love (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/laurenking_hartbreakers-01.png\" alt=\"5 Brooklyn Vegan Cafes We Love (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" />Photo: LaurenQueen.com</p>\r\n<h1><strong>1.</strong>&nbsp;Hartbreakers</h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Top of the list has to be Hartbreakers, located (you guessed it) on Hart Street in Bushwick. This retro-style cafe is the perfect combination of style and substance. It&rsquo;s an ideal Instagram spot, plus the food is actually good. Pick up sandwiches, salads and a selection of fries throughout the day from the friendly staff and rest happily in the assurance that every single item on the menu is vegan (yay!). What&rsquo;s more, their substitutes are shockingly good, especially their seitan, which features in a range of mock-meat dishes.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We love the Early Morning Traffic Jam sandwich, made with seasoned tofu, seitan bacon, cheddar, sauteed kale and red pepper jam, or try the Dream On salad with crispy chickpeas, grilled merguez sausage, artichoke and pink couscous. Their waffle fries are also something special, which of course come drenched in the most delicious vegan cheese.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">820 Hart St, Brooklyn, NY 11237</span></em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1><strong>2.&nbsp;</strong><strong>Amituofo Vegan Cuisine</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Head to Bogart Street in East Williamsburg for the best pan-Asian vegan cuisine in Brooklyn. Amituofo is a 100-percent plant-based Asian-inspired restaurant and cafe with an amazing menu of convincing substitutes and vegetable dishes alike. The upmarket yet relaxed atmosphere is an ideal setting for lunch with friends or a weeknight dinner to yourself.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Our favorite items on the menu are the fried tofu, which comes perfectly marinated, and the sauteed bok choy. Aside from this, you can get everything from cream cheese wontons to barbecue imitation pork at Amituofo. Insider tip: Amituofo is also available on delivery services like Uber Eats, so you don&rsquo;t even have to leave your home to enjoy it!</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">19 Bogart St, Brooklyn, NY 11206</span></em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"5 Brooklyn Vegan Cafes We Love (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/hcmp74976_358834.jpg\" alt=\"5 Brooklyn Vegan Cafes We Love (Image-2)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" />Photo:&nbsp;<em>EcoRDN, HappyCow.net</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1><strong>3.&nbsp;</strong><strong>Brooklyn Whiskers</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If your sweet-tooth cravings are a struggle for your veganism, don&rsquo;t despair. Brooklyn Whiskers, with locations in Bushwick and Greenpoint, has the best tasting pastries to keep you straight. They specialize in plant-based sweet and savory pastries, including croissants, scones, brownies and everything else you might be craving, as well as breakfast and lunch options like bagels and doughnuts. Of course, you can get a coffee to pair with your pastry, and they even make custom birthday and cupcakes for special occasions (or sweet-tooth emergencies).</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">760 Bushwick Ave, Brooklyn, NY 11221</span></em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1><strong>4.&nbsp;</strong><strong>VSpot</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This latin kosher vegan restaurant and cafe is a Brooklyn institution. Founded in 2006 in Park Slope, VSpot is known for its traditional Columbian dishes made vegan, including delicious vegan arepas and empanadas. VSpot Brooklyn is an ideal place to spend an afternoon or evening sampling the possibilities of what food can be with a little imagination. We love their weekend brunch, with tacos, scrambled tofu and vegan steak (and, of course, mimosas).</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">156 5th Ave, Brooklyn, NY 11217</span></em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1><strong>5.&nbsp;</strong><strong>Screamer&rsquo;s Pizzeria</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Giving up pizza is one of the hardest things about becoming vegan, and giving up New York Pizza makes you a saint. Luckily, Screamer&rsquo;s Pizzeria has you covered. With the best vegan cheese we&rsquo;ve tasted, their pizzas really hit the spot. Try a pie or grab a slice with a range of toppings to choose from, including classic cheese, white, seitan sausage and seitan pepperoni. You can even make your own pizza, mixing and matching the all-vegan toppings to your heart&rsquo;s content. Find Screamer&rsquo;s Pizzeria at two locations in Greenpoint and Crown Heights for your answer to a cruelty-free New York Pizza experience.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">620 Manhattan Ave, Brooklyn, NY 11222</span></em></p>\r\n<p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">685 Franklin Ave, Brooklyn, NY 11238</span></em></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>', 'laurenking_hartbreakers-01.png', 1, '2019-07-31 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(293, 'Member Monday: Megan Timmons', 1, 'member-monday-megan-timmons', '', 'Member Monday: Megan Timmons', 'Member Monday: Megan Timmons', 'Meet Megan, an aspiring broadway star from Indiana and a member of our South Williamsburg House.', '<p>Meet Megan, an aspiring broadway star from Indiana and a member of our South Williamsburg House.</p>', '<p>Meet Megan, an aspiring broadway star from Indiana and a member of our South Williamsburg House.</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Member Monday: Megan Timmons (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/23376625_10208059365521563_5799378760392697134_n.jpg\" alt=\"Member Monday: Megan Timmons (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<h1>Tell us a bit about yourself</h1>\r\n<p>I am from Indiana. I recently graduated from Ohio Northern University where I got my BFA in Musical Theatre and Dance. I spent the last year of my life as a tour actor/director with Missoula Children&rsquo;s Theatre where I got to visit 30 states and 2 Canadian provinces, and taught and performed with thousands of kids from the age 4-18. Now I&rsquo;m here living in the city I&rsquo;ve always wanted to live in and pursuing my dream of being on Broadway.</p>\r\n<h1>What\'s your favorite Outpost memory?</h1>\r\n<p>My favorite Outpost memory would be the few weeks where a group of us liked to workout on the roof.</p>\r\n<h1>What&rsquo;s your favorite part of New York?</h1>\r\n<p>I love Central Park! It&rsquo;s my favorite place to read or people watch.What are you working on now?</p>\r\n<p>I am currently a server at the Juniors on 45th and Broadway (with fellow Outpost member Patrick Riley) and am going to auditions whenever I get the chance.</p>', '23376625_10208059365521563_5799378760392697134_n.jpg', 1, '2019-08-01 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(294, 'Why coliving is better than college dorms this autumn', 1, 'why-coliving-is-better-than-college-dorms-this-autumn', '', 'Why coliving is better than college dorms this autumn', 'Why coliving is better than college dorms this autumn', 'So, college is coming up and you’re wondering where you’re going to live. A dorm might be the first option that comes to mind, but in New York City, there are plenty of other ways to live. Co-living is a new way of living that has become extremely popular in New York--and for good reason. Read on to find out why you should consider co-living this Autumn semester.', '<p>So, college is coming up and you&rsquo;re wondering where you&rsquo;re going to live. A dorm might be the first option that comes to mind, but in New York City, there are plenty of other ways to live. Co-living is a new way of living that has become extremely popular in New York--and for good reason. Read on to find out why you should consider co-living this Autumn semester.</p>', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So, college is coming up and you&rsquo;re wondering where you&rsquo;re going to live. A dorm might be the first option that comes to mind, but in New York City, there are plenty of other ways to live. Coliving is a new way of living that has become extremely popular in New York -- and for good reason. Read on to find out why you should consider co-living this autumn semester.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><strong><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Why coliving is better than college dorms this autumn (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/1.jpg\" alt=\"Why coliving is better than college dorms this autumn (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></strong></strong></p>\r\n<h1><strong><strong>1. It&rsquo;s more flexible</strong></strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">With a college dorm, you either sign up for the entire year or not at all. That&rsquo;s a big commitment and a gamble that you&rsquo;ll like the neighborhood, your roommates, and dorm life in general. With co-living, life is more flexible. At Outpost, our minimum contract period is only a month, which you can extend once you&rsquo;re sure you like us. What&rsquo;s even better is that with our gold membership, you can sign up for the entire semester or year and still have the freedom to move between any of our eleven houses in New York (and even our houses in San Francisco for vacations) at any time, which means you can change neighborhoods or roommates if you&rsquo;re unhappy or simply want to try something new.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Why coliving is better than college dorms this autumn (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/09.jpg\" alt=\"Why coliving is better than college dorms this autumn (Image-2)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></span></p>\r\n<h1><strong>2. It&rsquo;s more affordable</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">College dorms can vary in price, but what co-living offers is a completely all inclusive rate, with all the things you didn&rsquo;t even know you needed provided for you. When you first move into a college dorm, start-up costs can really catch you off guard. Buying hangers, bedding, toiletries and seasonings are all hidden costs that can really add up on a student budget. When you move into Outpost, everything&rsquo;s included. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You kitchen comes filled with everything from cutlery to cooking equipment, paper towels to a coffee maker. Your bathroom will be decked out and regularly re-stocked with soap, shampoo, toilet paper and even a hairdryer. We even have co-working spaces with printers and regularly re-stocked ink.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Your bedroom will be move-in ready, with a memory foam mattress and pillow, extension cords to your bedside, shelving, hooks, hangers and even bed linens and a towel, so all you need to bring is your suitcase.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h1><strong>3. It&rsquo;s cleaner&nbsp;</strong></h1>\r\n<p>You may have heard the horror stories about communal floor bathrooms and kitchens in college dorms, particularly Freshman dorms. The rumors are true. Dorm bathrooms are often shared between a large number of people and may not be cleaned regularly--so much so that it&rsquo;s common practice for students to wear flip-flops in the shower in order to avoid fungal infections. At Outpost, we have plenty of bathrooms and always at least one kitchen located within your private, shared apartment. These are cleaned weekly by our in-house cleaning team, who even re-stock everything from toilet paper to salt, so you&rsquo;ll never have to worry about waiting in line or trying to find a clean mug again.</p>\r\n<p><strong><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Why coliving is better than college dorms this autumn (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/4th%20July-9_1.jpg\" alt=\"Why coliving is better than college dorms this autumn (Image-3)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></strong></p>\r\n<h1><strong>4. You&rsquo;ll meet a wider variety of people&nbsp;</strong></h1>\r\n<p>College dorms are often populated with 18 year olds, running around in togas, studying similar things. There&rsquo;s nothing wrong with that, but co-living allows you to get out of this bubble. At Outpost, you&rsquo;ll meet a variety of people from all over the world, of all ages and occupations. Graduate students in particular will find relief from the typical frat house culture of college dorms and almost all students agree it&rsquo;s nice to have roommates who can connect you back to the real world. Outpost holds regular community events to help you meet people both people in your own house and in other houses, so there&rsquo;s a wide choice of things to do, from parties, to beach trips, to writing groups.</p>\r\n<p><strong><img title=\"Why coliving is better than college dorms this autumn (Image-4), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/2.jpg\" alt=\"Why coliving is better than college dorms this autumn (Image-4)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></strong></p>\r\n<h1><strong>5. It feels more like home</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Most college dorms haven&rsquo;t been refurbished for several generations and almost all have an industrial, cold feel about them. At Outpost, all of our homes are newly</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> renovated and we&rsquo;ve worked with interior designers to create the most modern, comfortable spaces possible. There&rsquo;s heat and air conditioning in every room, as well as state of the art appliances, hardwood floors and advanced security systems in common areas. There&rsquo;s also more space to hang out than in your average dorm, as most of our houses have backyards or rooftops and every one has dedicated co-working space. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We also provide laundry facilities on-site in every house (even if we can&rsquo;t provide a parent who will do it for you&hellip;).</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>', '4th July-52.jpg', 1, '2019-08-05 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(295, 'Destination: 111 Minna Gallery', 1, 'destination-111-minna-gallery', '', 'Destination: 111 Minna Gallery', 'Destination: 111 Minna Gallery', '111 Minna Gallery looks unassuming from the outside, but inside there’s a tardis full of artsy entertainment', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">111 Minna Gallery</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> looks unassuming from the outside, but inside there&rsquo;s a tardis full of artsy entertainment. Step through the bright red door of this SoMa gallery and find a concealed art haven-slash-events space that will be your new favorite SF hangout.</span></p>', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">111 Minna Gallery</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> looks unassuming from the outside, but inside there&rsquo;s a tardis full of artsy entertainment. Step through the bright red door of this SoMa gallery and find a concealed art haven-slash-events space that will be your new favorite SF hangout.</span></p>\r\n<p>Just a short walk from our SoMa House, 111 Minna is an oasis of creativity in the middle of downtown San Francisco. The gallery was founded in 1993 with a mission to make art sociable and accessible. Today, 111 Minna is equally known for its arts as for its events. The 4,700-square-foot space features art from up-and-coming artists in a variety of styles, including sculpture and installations, with new exhibitions swooping in on a regular basis. The space is open-plan and tranquil, with hardwood floors and high ceilings, giving 111 Minna a warehouse vibe that perfectly frames the modern art hanging on and around its walls. But art isn&rsquo;t all this gallery offers.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Destination: 111 Minna Gallery (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/3.jpg\" alt=\"Destination: 111 Minna Gallery (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Photo:&nbsp;<em>111 Minna Gallery, Yelp</em></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This SoMa gallery also has two full bars and a full schedule of events for your artsy needs. Describing itself as &ldquo;SF&rsquo;s melting pot for creative minds,&rdquo; the venue hosts everything from book readings to dance parties, to film screenings and fashion shows, with something going on almost every day of the week. In the next week alone, there&rsquo;s a free Wednesday morning yoga class with coffee, a performance night featuring the music of Jimmy Waters and a comedy show.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Destination: 111 Minna Gallery (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/3_1.jpg\" alt=\"Destination: 111 Minna Gallery (Image-2)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo:&nbsp;<em>111 Minna Gallery, Yelp</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Even if events aren&rsquo;t your thing, 111 Minna is a great place to hang out during the day or night. By day, the gallery is a coffee shop with large leather couches and speedy Wi-Fi perfect for your remote working needs, transforming into a bar by night, with a very reasonable happy hour for struggling artists.</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The laid-back atmosphere, friendly staff and open-minded philosophy of this gallery breathe the mantra &ldquo;art for art&rsquo;s sake.&rdquo; And with an ever-changing supply of local and international art hanging on the walls, it&rsquo;s the perfect place to relax after work, hang out with friends or make your new office for the day.</span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>\r\n<p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">111 Minna Gallery</span></em></p>\r\n<p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">111 Minna St.,&nbsp;</span></em></p>\r\n<p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">San Francisco,&nbsp;</span></em></p>\r\n<p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">CA 94105</span></em></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>', '2.jpg', 1, '2019-08-07 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(296, 'How to visit your favorite NYC galleries and museums for free', 1, 'how-to-visit-your-favorite-nyc-galleries-and-museums-for-free', '', 'How to visit your favorite NYC galleries and museums for free', 'How to visit your favorite NYC galleries and museums for free', 'When you live in New York, getting to see all the galleries and museums you want can be expensive', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">When you live in New York, getting to see all the galleries and museums you want can be expensive. But with a little know-how, you can enter many of your favorite museums for free. All you need is good timing (or a library card)...&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p>When you live in New York, getting to see all the galleries and museums you want can be expensive. But with a little know-how, you can enter many of your favorite museums for free. All you need is good timing (or a library card)...&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"How to visit your favorite NYC galleries and museums for free (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/3_2.jpg\" alt=\"How to visit your favorite NYC galleries and museums for free (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo:&nbsp;<em>Kristian D. Yelp</em></p>\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>The Frick</strong></h1>\r\n<p><strong>The Frick </strong>is a historic New York City mansion with a range of original artworks, including pieces by Rembrandt and Hans Holbein, inside. The Frick offers \'pay what you wish\' entry on Wednesdays, from 2 p.m. to 6 p.m. You have to be in line by 5 p.m. to take advantage of the offer, but if you make it in time for 5, you\'re guaranteed admission.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>But if you don&rsquo;t have Wednesday off work, &ldquo;First Fridays&rdquo; at the Frick is the perfect way to round off your Friday afternoon. On the first Friday of every month, the Frick opens its doors free to the public. And there&rsquo;s more than just art on offer; you&rsquo;ll also find live jazz music playing beside the fountain in the courtyard, as well as snacks and free drawing supplies, so you can try your hand at replicating the works of art (or your friends). Just make sure you arrive early, as admission starts at 6 p.m., but the line starts building up at 5 p.m or earlier.</p>\r\n<h1><strong>The MET</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><a href=\"https://www.metmuseum.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">The MET</a> is expensive, but what most people don&rsquo;t know is that you can &ldquo;pay what you wish&rdquo; if you&rsquo;re a New York State resident--and as an Outpost member, you are! Just go to the </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Museum admissions desk with a valid ID and present your membership agreement as proof of address and enjoy this museum for nearly free.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>The MET also runs &ldquo;Met Fridays&rdquo; every Friday, with performances, classes and other entertainment until 9 p.m, all included with your museum ticket. The full event schedule can be found here. The MET has a beautiful roof terrace which comes alive on Friday evenings, making it the perfect location to watch the sunset with a cultural twist.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"How to visit your favorite NYC galleries and museums for free (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/2_1.jpg\" alt=\"How to visit your favorite NYC galleries and museums for free (Image-2)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" />Photo: <em>Guggenheim.org</em>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1><strong>The Guggenheim</strong></h1>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.guggenheim.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">The Guggenheim</a> is a masterpiece of Frank Lloyd Wright&rsquo;s architectural talent, and inside isn&rsquo;t half bad either. The Guggenheim is free on Saturdays, from 5 - 8 p.m., where you can enjoy the Impressionist, Early Modern and Contemporary artwork without burning a hole in your pocket. If you are able to shell out for admission, the gallery stays open later on Tuesdays with drinks, film screenings, talks, refreshments and of course art, until 9 p.m. Plus, until December, on the first Tuesday of every month the Guggenheim will host &ldquo;Silent Nights,&rdquo; where you can experience the gallery in &ldquo;a uniquely contemplative atmosphere,&rdquo; including dimmed lights and sweet silence in the rotunda as well as the galleries.</p>\r\n<h1><strong>MoMa</strong></h1>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.moma.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">The Museum of Modern Art</a>, one of the most famous and prestigious modern art museums in the world, is free every Friday from 4 - 8 p.m. However, it&rsquo;s currently closed and won&rsquo;t reopen again until October 2019 (but it&rsquo;s certainly worth the wait!).&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1><strong>And some lesser known galleries and museums we love</strong></h1>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"How to visit your favorite NYC galleries and museums for free (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/3_3.jpg\" alt=\"How to visit your favorite NYC galleries and museums for free (Image-3)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" />Photo: <em>Themorgan.org</em></p>\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: left;\">The Morgan Library &amp; Museum</h1>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.themorgan.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">The Morgan</a> is the private collection of J. Pierpont Morgan (of J. P Morgan), consisting of rare books, as well as exquisite manuscripts, drawings and other artifacts. The building itself is an architectural marvel, a Neoclassical masterpiece just waiting to be explored. The Morgan is free on Fridays from 7 - 9 p.m.</p>\r\n<h1>Neue Gallery</h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><a href=\"http://neuegalerie.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">The Neue Gallery</a> is famous as the home of Gustav Klimt&rsquo;s painting, </span><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Kiss. </span></em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Aside from that, it houses the best German and Austrian art in New York City. The museum is free on the first Friday of every month from 6 - 9 p.m and for a limited time (through September 2, 2019) guests can enter at all times for half price.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"How to visit your favorite NYC galleries and museums for free (Image-4), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/3_4.jpg\" alt=\"How to visit your favorite NYC galleries and museums for free (Image-4)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Photo: <em>Neuegallery.org</em></span>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1><strong>The Bronx Zoo</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><a href=\"http://www.bronxzoo.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">The Bronx Zoo</a> is the world&rsquo;s largest metropolitan zoo, home to over 6,000 animals. The acres and acres of greenery will make you feel like you&rsquo;re in the middle of the countryside and you can enjoy it all for free all day, every Wednesday.</span></p>\r\n<h1><strong>Brooklyn Botanic Garden</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Entry to the beautiful <a href=\"https://www.bbg.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Brooklyn Botanic Garden</a> is free on Friday mornings until 12 p.m from March through November. During the winter months (December through February) it&rsquo;s free every weekday, so if you can bear the breeziness, that&rsquo;s your time to go.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"How to visit your favorite NYC galleries and museums for free (Image-5), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/2_2.jpg\" alt=\"How to visit your favorite NYC galleries and museums for free (Image-5)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /><br /></strong>Photo: Publicgardens.org</p>\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Bonus tips</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you have a New York Library card &nbsp;you can sign up for a <strong>NYC Culture Pass</strong>. These passes are one-time reservations that offer you and a friend free entry to a wide list of museums, including those listed above, such as The Guggenheim, Frick, MET, Morgan, and even The Whitney, so it&rsquo;s ideal for those who can&rsquo;t make the trip at the free times listed here. If you&rsquo;re staying in the city for a while, sign up for an IDNYC ID card and get free membership to a wide variety of cultural institutions, including the Met, MoMa and more (and of course, membership means free entry). Find details and sign up </span><a href=\"https://www1.nyc.gov/site/idnyc/index.page\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">here</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you can&rsquo;t or don&rsquo;t want to get either of these cards, Bank of America customers also get free entry to a list of NYC museums on the first full weekend of every month. Find the list of included museums </span><a href=\"https://about.bankofamerica.com/en-us/what-guides-us/arts-and-culture/partners.html#fbid=5I2AO2K6uOq\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">here</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>', '3.jpg', 1, '2019-08-17 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(297, 'Member Monday: María García González', 1, 'member-monday-mara-garca-gonzlez', '', 'Member Monday: María García González', 'Member Monday: María García González', 'Meet María from Chile, a chemist, traveler and the House Leader at our Bushwick House.', '<p>Meet Mar&iacute;a from Chile, a chemist, traveler and the House Leader at our Bushwick House.</p>', '<p>Meet Mar&iacute;a from Chile, a chemist, traveler and the House Leader at our Bushwick House.</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Member Monday: Mar&iacute;a Garc&iacute;a Gonz&aacute;lez (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/3_6.jpg\" alt=\"Member Monday: Mar&iacute;a Garc&iacute;a Gonz&aacute;lez (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<h1>Tell us a bit about yourself.</h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Hello everyone! My name is Mar&iacute;a. I am 24 years old and I&nbsp;am from&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Chile, the longest country in South America, full of mountains and volcanos. I recently finished my studies in Chemistry and I decided to take a break far from home by coming to NYC!&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">I have always been passionate about filling my life with new adventures and staying in NYC with Outpost is my latest one!&nbsp;I love outdoor activities, meeting new people and learning about them, including sharing life experiences, as well as singing and dancing (especialy latin rythims like salsa or bachata!).&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h1>What\'s your favorite Outpost memory?</h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It\'s hard to pick! One good memory&nbsp;with Outpost was&nbsp;the Roaring 20\'s party we had at the Knickerbocker House. All the House Leaders met up before to help set up the party. It\'s nice to get to know the&nbsp;people I\'m&nbsp;working with at events like this, and this is just the beginning! There are so many more memories to come...</span></p>\r\n<h1>What&rsquo;s your favorite part of New York?</h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">I could say that it is difficult to pick my favorite part of NYC, but for now I can say that besides Brooklyn Bridge it would be Chinatown because there are so many bakeries right next to each other and I am a big fan of sweets!</span></p>\r\n<h1>What are you working on now?</h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Some of my goals for this year are to improve my English for my next adventure: I\'ve never been to Europe and I\'d love to go there after here! After this, I\'m going to look for my dream job: something that will let me travel the world as I work. I want to continue helping people and doing everything with love as I always do, because life is so beautiful and I am so fortunate to be where I am&nbsp;in this moment... s&eacute; siempre &uacute;nicamente t&uacute;!</span><br /><br /></p>', '3_1.jpg', 1, '2019-08-08 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(301, 'Member Monday: Tara Johnson', 1, 'member-monday-tara-johnson', '', 'Member Monday: Tara Johnson', 'Member Monday: Tara Johnson', 'Meet Tara from Canada, a marketing student, traveler, and aspiring diving instructor!', '<p>Meet Tara from Canada, a marketing student, traveler, and aspiring diving instructor!</p>', '<p>Meet Tara from Canada, a marketing student, traveler, and aspiring diving instructor!</p>\r\n<h1>Tell us a bit about yourself.</h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Hi, world! I am a 20-year-old political science graduate from Canada. I lived at Outpost for the summer while I interned for an event production company in Midtown Manhattan. I love the arts, nature and all things vintage!</span></p>\r\n<h1>What\'s your favorite Outpost memory?</h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">I don\'t just have one memory in particular, but I really enjoyed the community aspect of Outpost. It was always interesting to sit around the dining room table and talk with my international housemates! I am beyond thankful to have met so many wonderful people in New York.</span></p>\r\n<h1>What&rsquo;s your favorite part of New York?</h1>\r\n<p>I love that there is always something to do &mdash; either free or paid. You can find anything at any time that suits your interests. From a late-night, one-dollar pizza run (the pizza at 23rd and 7th is my favorite) to a last-minute concert in Brooklyn (download Bandsintown to find concerts)&nbsp;to a fun workout (get a free trial for ClassPass)!</p>\r\n<h1>What are you working on now?</h1>\r\n<p>I\'m back in Canada to begin a graduate program in Montreal for marketing! Once I finish, I plan on traveling around a bit &mdash; no countries picked yet, but I have promised myself to get my PADI certification within the next 2 years.</p>', 'Image-1.jpg', 1, '2019-08-26 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(298, 'Our top 5 remote and co-working spots in San Francisco', 1, 'our-top-5-remote-and-co-working-spots-in-san-francisco', '', 'Our top 5 remote and co-working spots in San Francisco | Outpost Club blog', 'Our top 5 remote and co-working spots in San Francisco', 'Considering how famous San Francisco is for its start-ups, you’d be surprised how hard it is to find a coffee shop with WiFi and comfy chairs where you can spend the day working remotely', '<p>Considering how famous San Francisco is for its start-ups, you&rsquo;d be surprised how hard it is to find a coffee shop with WiFi and comfy chairs where you can spend the day working remotely, either alone or with others on your team. To help you get started, we&rsquo;ve picked the top five remote and co-working hotspots for you to choose from.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p>Considering how famous San Francisco is for its start-ups, you&rsquo;d be surprised how hard it is to find a coffee shop with WiFi and comfy chairs where you can spend the day working remotely, either alone or with others on your team. To help you get started, we&rsquo;ve picked the top five remote and co-working hotspots for you to choose from.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Our top 5 remote and co-working spots in San Francisco (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/1_1.jpg\" alt=\"Our top 5 remote and co-working spots in San Francisco (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" />Photo:&nbsp;<em>The Station SF, Facebook</em></p>\r\n<h3>The Station SF</h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Located between FiDi and North Beach, this slick coffee shop is the perfect place to get some serious work done. The speedy WiFi and calm atmosphere is the ideal environment for work, added to by the hardwood floors, large windows and comfy chairs. Choose from a full coffee, breakfast and lunch menu, including a long list of espresso-based drinks featuring a local roast: Sightglass coffee. The food is made daily from scratch and the cold pressed juice is the perfect workday fuel.</span></p>\r\n<h3>Verve Coffee Roasters</h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Verve is like something out of a design magazine: a relaxed coffee shop with pine, pastels, plants and art, making it the most inspirational place for your work day. Sink into the comfortable window seats and watch the baristas at work from behind a glass screen as you wonder how they managed to make the coffee this good. The group tables with plenty of laptop space are perfect for co-working, and the reliable WiFi will keep you productive throughout the day. Verve roasts its own coffee in its flagship location, Santa Cruz, meaning it&rsquo;s always fresh and sustainable. Try the nitro flash cold brew with oat milk for the perfect caffeine hit (and maybe a sandwich, too).</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Our top 5 remote and co-working spots in San Francisco (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/1_2.jpg\" alt=\"Our top 5 remote and co-working spots in San Francisco (Image-2)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo:&nbsp;<em>Lillian C. Yelp</em></p>\r\n<h3>Mercury Cafe</h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Mercury Cafe is an ideal workplace with a conscience in the heart of Hayes Valley. This light and airy space is filled with wooden tables and good vibes, with trees peering in from outside, and you can rest assured while you work through the day that all of the food and coffee you buy is sustainably sourced. The coffee is locally roasted, direct-trade from Four Barrel Coffee and you can pick anything from sandwiches to their ever-popular homemade scones. There&rsquo;s even beer and wine for when you&rsquo;re feeling the writer&rsquo;s block. Together with the friendly staff and quick WiFi, it&rsquo;s a great place to work remotely.</span></p>\r\n<h3>Workshop Cafe</h3>\r\n<p>What some call the future of co-working, Workshop Cafe has two locations in SF. It&rsquo;s basically a mixture of a library, an office and a coffee shop, with colorful, modern decor, comfy chairs and an industrial-style setting. There are multiple work areas, including booths (each with their own outlet), easy chairs and stools, spread across an open-plan warehouse, with a cafe at the far end selling coffee, sandwiches, juice and everything else you could need to be productive. The one snag is the price: You pay per hour and reserve your seat, in a sort of short-term version of WeWork. But believe us, with features including seamless WiFi and the ability to suggest music for the curated playlist, it&rsquo;s certainly worth investing in to get your work done.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Our top 5 remote and co-working spots in San Francisco (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/21.jpg\" alt=\"Our top 5 remote and co-working spots in San Francisco (Image-3)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo: <em>Workshop Cafe&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<h3>Golden Gate Park</h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Why not head outdoors for a day of remote working? The city introduced free public WiFi in 2014, so you can access your files in the great outdoors. We love sitting by the observatory in Golden Gate Park, with the shade angled perfectly over our laptop screen and the world of remote working at our fingertips.</span></p>\r\n<p>A work trip to San Francisco is fantastic. The best 5 locations to work outside the home have been compiled for you. But what could be better than going back to your own New York apartment? You don\'t yet have an apartment? You can <a href=\"../new-york\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">rent the apartment</a> of your dreams with the aid of Outpost Club.</p>', '1.jpg', 1, '2019-08-21 05:00:00', '2022-11-01 07:30:56', NULL, 0, 0),
(299, '5 Nob Hill Bookstores We Love', 1, '5-nob-hill-bookstores-we-love', '', '5 Nob Hill Bookstores We Love', '5 Nob Hill Bookstores We Love', 'Looking for some great bookstores in Nob Hill? We’ve got you covered with our 5 favorites.', '<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Looking for some great bookstores in Nob Hill? We&rsquo;ve got you covered with our 5 favorites.</span></p>', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Looking for some great bookstores in Nob Hill? We&rsquo;ve got you covered with our 5 favorites.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><img title=\"5 Nob Hill Bookstores We Love (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/FE62339A-1148-4063-8402-A49DE76806FA-1500x600.jpeg\" alt=\"5 Nob Hill Bookstores We Love (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></span></p>\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"http://russianhillbookstore.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">1. Russian Hill Bookstore</a></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2162 Polk St</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This rustic shop is known for their helpful, enthusiastic staff and great selection. They will be happy to give you recommendations and help you find exactly what you&rsquo;re looking for. There are places to sit and read and plenty of books, comics, games, cards, gifts and vinyl/sheet music. If you&rsquo;re looking for everything from 1563 to 2019, this is the place for you! It\'s a local favorite.</span></p>\r\n<h1><a href=\"https://argonautbookshop.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">2. Argonaut Book Shop</a></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">786 Sutter St</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you&rsquo;re looking for a purely vintage bookstore, this is the place for you. They have some rich history within their walls and great views out their windows! Multiple floors of expertly organized and curated bookshelves. It&rsquo;s very well decorated and there is a Banksy across the street! It&rsquo;s run by knowledgeable staff and is a great place to go to if you want the in on Bay Area history and local authors. It\'s antique bookstore heaven!</span></p>\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><img title=\"5 Nob Hill Bookstores We Love (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/lf%20banners%20shot%201%20br.jpg\" alt=\"5 Nob Hill Bookstores We Love (Image-2)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /><a href=\"http://www.citylights.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">3. City Lights Booksellers and Publishers</a><br /></span></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">261 Columbus Ave</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A beat era-inspired three-floor bookstore with a whole floor dedicated to poetry, City Lights is a small, quiet haven for readers. It&rsquo;s been alive and kicking in this beautiful area of SF since the 1950&rsquo;s. Owner Lawrence Ferlinghetti, who celebrated his 100th birthday just recently, was arrested back in the day for publishing and selling work by Allen Ginsberg! A true literary cultural revolutionary, and the space reflects that. A must visit!</span></p>\r\n<h1><a title=\"Book Passage Nob Hill San Francisco\" href=\"https://www.bookpassage.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">4. Book Passage</a></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ferry Building, One, #42</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Often mistaken for a Wes Anderson film set, this cute independent bookstore is off-beat in the best way. You&rsquo;ll be simply taken by its charm and character, and their helpful and authentic staff will help you through their selection of fun and unique cards, gifts and books. Book Passage is a great place to get to know local authors, and be sure not to miss their sweet author events!</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><img title=\"5 Nob Hill Bookstores We Love (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/o_20.jpg\" alt=\"5 Nob Hill Bookstores We Love (Image-3)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></span></p>\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: left;\"><a title=\"Alexander Book Company Nob Hill San Francisco\" href=\"https://www.alexanderbook.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">5. Alexander Book Company</a></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">50 2nd St</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Fashioned with its own in-house coffee shop, Alexander Book Company is a lovely place to browse and meet locals! Three floors of great selection comes along with a wonderful, helpful staff that are ready to order whatever you want for you and are knowledgeable and efficient. They have used books, new books, unique gifts, and a bargain bin outside. They also have a frequent buyer program that helps us bookworms get a free book after every 10 purchases. You could browse all day and be engaged and entertained!</span></p>', 'Screen Shot 2019-10-03 at 6.29.42 PM.png', 1, '2019-10-02 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(300, 'Outpost Club Announces Operational Management Agreement with Bedly', 1, 'outpost-club-announces-operational-management-agreement-with-bedly', '', 'Outpost Club Announces Operational Management Agreement with Bedly', 'Outpost Club Announces Operational Management Agreement with Bedly', 'Outpost Club, a trusted Brooklyn-based real estate technology operator, announced today that it has come to an agreement to take over operational management for some of Bedly\'s properties in Manhattan and New Jersey.', '<p>Outpost Club, a trusted Brooklyn-based real estate technology operator, announced today that it has come to an agreement to take over operational management for some of Bedly\'s properties in Manhattan and New Jersey.</p>', '<p>Outpost Club, a trusted Brooklyn-based real estate technology operator, announced today that it has come to an agreement to take over operational management for some of Bedly\'s properties in Manhattan and New Jersey. The Bedly platform will also be operationally supported by Outpost.</p>\r\n<p>Outpost will maintain the housing provider\'s current agreements with all Bedly members, including deposit and rent obligations, which will be rolled over into the Outpost system.</p>\r\n<p>Outpost currently operates in New York City and in San Francisco, using its proven coliving model to make more efficient use of urban housing while helping members build tight-knit communities within their own houses and throughout Outpost. Bedly members in Manhattan and New Jersey will now be able to benefit from the company\'s all-inclusive services.</p>\r\n<p>\"We\'re diligently working on a plan to make this transition go as smoothly as possible, with minimal impact on the members,\" said Outpost CEO Sergii Starostin. \"We\'re looking forward to welcoming Bedly members into the Outpost community, and to providing them with the high level of service our members have come to expect from us.\"</p>\r\n<p>Bedly support staff will work through August to ensure current members are at ease as operational management transitions to Outpost. The support team can be reached at support@bedly.com.</p>\r\n<p>\"We are pleased to work with Outpost to transition a portion of our portfolio across Manhattan and New Jersey,\" said Bedly CEO Martin Greenberg. \"Bedly was the first coliving company in the world and we have brought dramatic and structural change to the industry. The coliving category will live on and have a lasting positive impact for all renters.\"</p>\r\n<p>All deposits are accounted for and everyone has been communicated with regarding next steps, according to Greenberg.</p>\r\n<p><strong>About Outpost</strong></p>\r\n<p>Outpost Club, one of New York\'s leading coliving operators with 15 houses and more than 270 members, operates in the $600B U.S. rental market. Outpost makes better use of cities\' existing housing through master leases to build strong communities of people who see value in shared space. For more information, visit www.outpost-club.com.</p>\r\n<p><strong>About Bedly</strong></p>\r\n<p>Bedly created the coliving category that has changed the way people live across the world. They have more than 600 members and had raised over $7M of capital. Their homes span across Boston, New Jersey and New York City. For more information, visit www.bedly.com.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Contact:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Lauren Vega<br />Marketing Manager<br />Outpost Club<br />lauren.vega@outpost-club.com</p>', 'Screen Shot 2019-08-26 at 12.16.19 PM.png', 1, '2019-08-01 05:00:00', NULL, 1, 0, 0);
