(302, 'How much money you can save by coliving', 1, 'how-much-money-you-can-save-by-coliving', '', 'How much money you can save by coliving', 'How much money you can save by coliving', 'As you know, coliving at Outpost means everything is included; from furnishings to cleaning to security, your membership is a flat fee that takes care of everything', '<p>As you know, coliving at Outpost means everything is included; from furnishings to cleaning to security, your membership is a flat fee that takes care of everything. But how does this actually add up to savings in the long term? Here&rsquo;s our rundown of how much you can save by coliving.</p>', '<p>As you know, coliving at Outpost means everything is included; from furnishings to cleaning to security, your membership is a flat fee that takes care of everything. But how does this actually add up to savings in the long term? Here&rsquo;s our rundown of how much you can save by coliving.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"How much money you can save by coliving (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/1_3.jpg\" alt=\"How much money you can save by coliving (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<h1><strong>Initial start-up fees</strong></h1>\r\n<p>Before monthly costs accrue, you have the initial start-up savings of coliving to consider. In the hunt for a traditional apartment, you might find yourself having to pay a broker fee. In NYC, broker fees are notoriously high, averaging one month&rsquo;s rent or 15% of the annual rent according to <a href=\"https://medium.com/@Hauseit/how-much-are-broker-fees-for-renting-an-apartment-in-nyc-363c96a35729\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Medium</a>. That&rsquo;s $1,000 or more gone instantly, although if you&rsquo;re lucky you might find one of the newly popular no-fee brokers (so long as you&rsquo;re able to avoid a scam).&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>On top of that is the application fee for the apartment, averaging around $100 or more, while at Outpost we don&rsquo;t charge application fees or undertake extensive reference checks, making moving in both affordable and quick.</p>\r\n<p>Apartments in New York and San Francisco don&rsquo;t usually come furnished, so unless you&rsquo;re lucky enough to find a perfectly timed sublet, you&rsquo;re looking at buying at least a bed and a dresser &mdash; if not more (depending on how fancy you&rsquo;re feeling).&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Let&rsquo;s say you&rsquo;re scrimping and saving; at a minimum you&rsquo;ll spend $100 on a bed frame and $100 on a mattress, while most people will end up spending more in the region of $400 for both. A dresser will be another $40 - $200. Then there&rsquo;s the living room... unless you want to sit on your pizza boxes for a year, a couch will set you back anywhere between $200 to $600 (but let&rsquo;s veer on the conservative side and say you find a roommate willing to split it with you).</p>\r\n<p><em>Start-up cost savings of fully furnished coliving: $440 - $2000.</em></p>\r\n<p>After these one-time expenses, the monthly fees begin. So how much money can you save per month by coliving?</p>\r\n<h1><strong>Monthly saving on utilities &hellip; and more</strong></h1>\r\n<p><img title=\"How much money you can save by coliving (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/2_3.jpg\" alt=\"How much money you can save by coliving (Image-2)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>In an Outpost coliving house, all of your utilities are included, even WiFi. According to <a href=\"https://smartasset.com/mortgage/what-is-the-cost-of-living-in-new-york-city\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Smart Asset</a>, The average basic utilities package for a 915-square-foot apartment in New York costs $145.55, including heating, electricity and water. WiFi prices average at $62.77 per month, and that&rsquo;s without having super speedy unlimited access and streaming. Even if you share with a roommate, that&rsquo;s $72.78 on utilities and $31.39 on WiFi. Anybody else starting to lose count?&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>Savings per month on utilities and WiFi: $104.17 - $208.32.</em></p>\r\n<h1><strong>All the little things</strong></h1>\r\n<p>Outpost also provides all those little things that add up without you realizing that they do. So let&rsquo;s try to add them &hellip; Your bathroom is regularly restocked with toilet paper ($0.84 per roll, with the assumption two rolls a week are being used per person [feel free to debate that one]), as well as shower gel ($3 - $9 per bottle, per month) and shampoo (another $3 - $9 per bottle, per month). There&rsquo;s also a hairdryer, but let&rsquo;s say you brought one with you.</p>\r\n<p>In the coliving area, we include Netflix ($8.99 per month) as well as a printer and ink (costing between $1 and $10 per month, depending if you&rsquo;re a student or work from home).</p>\r\n<p>In the kitchen, we provide olive oil ($3 - $8 per bottle), as well as spices ($5 per month average), paper towels ($2 per month) and coffee and tea ($12 per month minimum). Then there&rsquo;s dish soap and garbage bags ($2 per month minimum). That&rsquo;s not even counting the kitchen utensils and little things in your bedroom&hellip; like hangers (who ever remembers hangers?) and the added benefits of cleaning and security that living at Outpost offers.</p>\r\n<p><em>Savings on the little things: $46.71 - much, much more.</em>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img title=\"How much money you can save by coliving (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/3_7.jpg\" alt=\"How much money you can save by coliving (Image-3)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>That means that by coliving, even the thriftiest shopper can save $440 in start-up fees, as well as $150.88 per month at a minimum (and are you really buying that $3 shampoo every month?). Now, doesn&rsquo;t that make you feel less guilty about getting that extra drink at the bar last weekend? Cheers!</p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>', '1_1.jpg', 1, '2019-09-05 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(303, 'Destination: SoMa StrEat Food Park', 1, 'destination-soma-streat-food-park', '', 'Destination: SoMa StrEat Food Park', 'Destination: SoMa StrEat Food Park', 'SoMa StrEat Food Park is our favorite place to spend a chilled night of eating, drinking and socializing (often with a view of a game)', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">SoMa StrEat Food Park</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> is our favorite place to spend a chilled night of eating, drinking and socializing (often with a view of a game). This street food market is always buzzing in the evenings, providing the perfect backdrop for a weekday night out.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>SoMa StrEat Food Park</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> is our favorite place to spend a chilled night of eating, drinking and socializing (often with a view of a game). This street food market is always buzzing in the evenings, providing the perfect backdrop for a weekday night out.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Destination: SoMa StrEat Food Park (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/1_4.jpg\" alt=\"Destination: SoMa StrEat Food Park (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" />Photo: SoMa StrEat Food Park</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">SoMa StrEat Food Park plays daily host to a selection of curated food trucks with some of the best food that SF has to offer. With everything from pizza to Thai food, to empanadas and poke bows, there&rsquo;s something for every taste. And with different vendors everyday, you&rsquo;ll never get bored of the same dish. Although it&rsquo;s hard to pick a favorite, we love the Korean fried chicken and garlic fries by </span><strong>Kokio Republic</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, one of the best-value SF eateries we&rsquo;ve found and a regular returning star at SoMa StrEat Food Park.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Destination: SoMa StrEat Food Park (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/2_4.jpg\" alt=\"Destination: SoMa StrEat Food Park (Image-2)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo: SoMa StrEat Food Park</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">And it&rsquo;s not just about the food. SoMa StrEat Food Park also has large TV screens and carnival games to keep you entertained, all with a side of reasonably priced beer and wine. Describing itself as a &ldquo;culinary playground,&rdquo; it&rsquo;s certainly more on the play side than your average restaurant, with regular special events (like &ldquo;Avocado Con&rdquo;), game screenings (like Warriors games) and trivia nights to keep you entertained. There&rsquo;s even free WiFi for those who like to stay connected while they play.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>Sit outside in the San Francisco sun next to one of the conveniently placed heat lamps or hop on board the Magic Bus for an indoor seating experience beyond the norm.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Open every day for lunch and dinner and from Monday to Saturday until 9 p.m., SoMa StrEat Food Park is the perfect place to relax after work and try a little bit of everything, from bao buns, to Merlot, to your first Warriors game.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Destination: SoMa StrEat Food Park (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/3_8.jpg\" alt=\"Destination: SoMa StrEat Food Park (Image-3)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Photo: SoMa StrEat Food Park</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">428 11th St @ Division St.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">San Francisco, 94103.</span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /></p>', '1_2.jpg', 1, '2019-09-11 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(304, '5 things to do on weeknights in Bushwick', 1, '5-things-to-do-on-weeknights-in-bushwick', '', '5 things to do on weeknights in Bushwick', '5 things to do on weeknights in Bushwick', 'Is the L train slowdown holding you back on weeknights? No problem. If you’re a Bushwick resident, everything you need to keep yourself entertained is in your neighborhood', '<p>Is the L train slowdown holding you back on weeknights? No problem. If you&rsquo;re a Bushwick resident, everything you need to keep yourself entertained is in your neighborhood. Here are our five favorite things to do on a weeknight in buzzing Bushwick (and we&rsquo;re betting you can walk to most of them!).</p>', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Is the L train slowdown holding you back on weeknights? No problem. If you&rsquo;re a Bushwick resident, everything you need to keep yourself entertained is in your neighborhood. Here are our five favorite things to do on a weeknight in buzzing Bushwick (and we&rsquo;re betting you can walk to most of them!).</span></p>\r\n<h1>The Topaz:&nbsp;<em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Mondays, 8 p.m.</span></em></h1>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"5 things to do on weeknights in Bushwick (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/1_5.jpg\" alt=\"5 things to do on weeknights in Bushwick (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /><em>Photo: The Topaz</em></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Every Monday night, </span><strong>The Topaz</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> runs a varied and welcoming open mic in its backroom. Walk past the bar and through a set of unassuming wooden doors to find this hidden gem; the wood-panelled event space is filled with comfy chairs and open-minded individuals just waiting to share their talents with you.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Out of the many open mic nights in Bushwick, we love The Topaz because it attracts a small, talented crowd without being pretentious. You&rsquo;ll find musicians, poets, comedians and everyone else performing for your pleasure and you can even sign up yourself if you go early.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h1>Bushwick Writer&rsquo;s Group:&nbsp;<em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Tuesdays and Thursdays, 7 p.m.</span></em></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Every Tuesday and Thursday night, </span><strong>Bushwick Writer&rsquo;s Group</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> holds &ldquo;Write your Ass Off&rdquo; sessions at </span><strong>Ange Noir Cafe</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and </span><strong>Swallow Cafe</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> on the border of Bushwick and East Williamsburg. Basically, a bunch of writers turn up, sit down and unplug from other distractions for a few hours to finally get that novel/book of essays/term paper finished.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">BWG holds their silent writing sessions in &ldquo;sprints,&rdquo; meaning you&rsquo;ll write for twenty minutes, take a break or grab a coffee, then start writing again, and so on. You don&rsquo;t have to read your work aloud or read the work of others; the point is simply to work on whatever you like in the allotted time. And if you end up chatting with some of the fabulous writers who frequent this group, that&rsquo;s just a bonus.</span></p>\r\n<h1>House of Yes:&nbsp;<em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Thursdays, 10 p.m.</span></em></h1>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"5 things to do on weeknights in Bushwick (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/2_5.jpg\" alt=\"5 things to do on weeknights in Bushwick (Image-2)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" />Photo: House of Yes</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">If you haven&rsquo;t already heard of the famous <strong><a href=\"https://houseofyes.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">House of Yes</a></strong>, now is the time to find out what all the fuss is about, because this nightlife extravaganza is located right on your doorstep in Bushwick. Named as one of Time Out&rsquo;s <a href=\"https://www.timeout.com/things-to-do/best-things-to-do-in-the-world\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">50 best things to do in the world right now</a>, you&rsquo;ll find weird and wonderful themed nights, toe-tapping music and disco balls galore -- and entry is completely free on Thursday nights with an RSVP.</p>\r\n<h1>Phil&rsquo;s:<strong>&nbsp;</strong><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Thursdays, 9 p.m.</span></em></h1>\r\n<p><strong>Phil&rsquo;s</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> on Knickerbocker Avenue is one of the best under-the-radar bars in Bushwick -- so much so that it&rsquo;s not even on Google Maps (yet). This laid-back bar, complete with outdoor patio and friendly staff, holds free comedy nights every Thursday starting at 9 p.m. and going on &lsquo;til late. Enjoy some of Bushwick&rsquo;s best comedic talent along with cheap drinks, with Phil&rsquo;s &ldquo;Happiest Hour&rdquo; running throughout the show, which includes $3 High Life drafts and $5 house wine.</span></p>\r\n<h1>Bodeguita:&nbsp;<em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Tuesdays, 9 p.m.</span></em></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Every tuesday, </span><strong>Bodeguita</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> holds live jazz nights that are completely free and available for walk-ins. We love the chilled vibes of this Bushwick favorite and the high standard of music they bring every week is always a treat (with an easy walk home). Shows run from 9 p.m. to late, but if you arrive between 5 p.m. and 8 p.m. you can take advantage of their Happy Hour. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Bodeguita</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> hosts different musicians every week, followed by an open jam at 10:15 p.m., so if you feel like getting involved, you&rsquo;re welcome!</span></p>\r\n<h1>Bonus: The Keep:<strong>&nbsp;</strong><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Wednesdays, 10 p.m.</span></em></h1>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"5 things to do on weeknights in Bushwick (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/3_9.jpg\" alt=\"5 things to do on weeknights in Bushwick (Image-3)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /><em>Photo: Brooklyn Paper</em></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Technically in Ridgewood but just a few blocks from the throng of central Bushwick, </span><strong>The Keep</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> is a bar like no other. This venue is decorated with hanging lamps, stained glass windows and velvet chairs, to the point that you&rsquo;ll almost question whether you&rsquo;ve stepped into a Brooklyn dive bar or 18th-century France. Every Wednesday night, The Keep holds a late-night jazz jam that attracts Bushwick&rsquo;s best musicians. It&rsquo;s completely free, friendly and wonderfully creative.</span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>', '3_2.jpg', 1, '2019-09-14 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(305, 'Member Monday: Leonid Verdinsky', 1, 'member-monday-leonid-verdinsky', '', 'Member Monday: Leonid Verdinsky', 'Member Monday: Leonid Verdinsky', 'Meet Leonid, a cultured traveler and the house leader at our Japantown House.\r\n', '<p>Meet Leonid, a cultured traveler and the house leader at our Japantown House.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p>Meet Leonid, a cultured traveler and the house leader at our Japantown House.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img title=\"Member Monday: Leonid Verdinsky (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/1_6.jpg\" alt=\"Member Monday: Leonid Verdinsky (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<h1>Tell us a bit about yourself.</h1>\r\n<p>All my life I lived on Sakhalin island (close to Japan) before I left to I study linguistics and philosophy at a university in St. Petersburg. I love fashion, cinema, design and anything art-related.&nbsp;I enjoy creating music, films and beautiful aesthetic clothing; it all inspires me so much. Now I&rsquo;m 20 and I live in Japantown, San Francisco, which is ironically very close to my home culture. Here I&rsquo;m starting a new life and making my dreams come true!</p>\r\n<h1>What\'s your favorite Outpost memory?</h1>\r\n<p>I adore our house. Everyone can find something to do and I found plenty of friends here. We always have fun, cook delicious food, explore the city and the beautiful nature of California!</p>\r\n<h1>What&rsquo;s your favorite part of San Francisco?</h1>\r\n<p>Our house is located in Japantown, which&nbsp;reminds me of my childhood, I feel at home here! There are so many&nbsp;cool Japanese restaurants and I love the Batteries to Bluffs Trail; you can see the Golden Gate there! Nature in San Francisco and California is amazing and I highly recommend the vintage stores. I also like to visit the cult cities of the Silicon Valley and Santa Cruz, because I love the beaches there! Go to Tahoe if you want to see beautiful mountains.</p>\r\n<h1>What are you working on now?</h1>\r\n<p>I\'m actually getting ready for college. I want to go to film school and consolidate my knowledge. I\'m also working on making sure life in the Japantown house runs smoothly!</p>', '1_3.jpg', 1, '2019-09-16 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(306, 'On the pros of coliving: The social side', 1, 'on-the-pros-of-coliving-the-social-side', '', 'On the pros of coliving: The social side', 'On the pros of coliving: The social side', 'Coliving can be a very social way to live; it’s the perfect way to meet people when you’re new to the city or to reinvigorate your professional life with some networking. \r\n', '<p>Coliving can be a very social way to live; it&rsquo;s the perfect way to meet people when you&rsquo;re new to the city or to reinvigorate your professional life with some networking.&nbsp;</p>', '<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Coliving can be a very social way to live; it&rsquo;s the perfect way to meet people when you&rsquo;re new to the city or to reinvigorate your professional life with some networking.&nbsp;At Outpost, coliving offers an instant social network in which you can be as involved in (or not) as the mood takes you. Read on to find out our favorite social perks of coliving&hellip;</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"On the pros of coliving: The social side (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/1_7.jpg\" alt=\"On the pros of coliving: The social side (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<h1>Always having someone to come home to</h1>\r\n<p>Big cities can be lonely, particularly if you live on your own or choose an apartment where the roommates write in their ad that they &ldquo;keep to themselves.&rdquo; At Outpost, there&rsquo;s always someone to come home to at the end of the day, whether it&rsquo;s members in your own apartment or in the common areas of your house. Even if you don&rsquo;t feel like talking, it&rsquo;s nice to know you have the option to whine about your job over a glass of wine while you cook or watch Netflix in the common area.</p>\r\n<h1>All the fun social events</h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Outpost runs regular events in our houses, with everything from wine and cheese nights to special celebrations on holidays. These events are a great way to bond with your roommates and meet new people and they&rsquo;re always free for members.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"On the pros of coliving: The social side (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/2_6.jpg\" alt=\"On the pros of coliving: The social side (Image-2)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" />&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Recent events have included a neon glow party, a Mexican Independence Day party and even an ice cream social. Our philosophy is to include everyone and we always have things to see, taste and do at our events.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h1>A bigger network than in a regular rental</h1>\r\n<p>Coliving at Outpost gives you a much larger network than you would find in more traditional accommodation because all our members are linked by their membership to Outpost Club, no matter what house they live in. This means that you can meet members from any number of our houses at our events, expanding your social circle far beyond the confines of your individual house. And of course, if you have gold membership you can even hop around houses in your city to experience life (and the social life) at other Outpost locations.</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"On the pros of coliving: The social side (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/3_10.jpg\" alt=\"On the pros of coliving: The social side (Image-3)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We have Facebook groups for each of our houses where events and hang outs are posted as well as a Facebook Group which spans all houses across your city. Members can post in the Facebook group and invited anyone from any of our houses to attend events or simply hang out for an evening. We have an atmosphere of inclusion at Outpost, so you&rsquo;ll never find yourself without something to do or someone to see that new exhibition with.</span></p>\r\n<h1>Networking with like-minded individuals</h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Outpost naturally attracts like-minded individuals and many of our members have networked without even intending to, especially because of the coworking areas within our houses. With the vast amount of members who you&rsquo;ll have the chance to meet, you&rsquo;re bound to find someone with similar professional or creative interests to you. We&rsquo;ve had members collaborate musically together, form writer&rsquo;s groups and even help each other onto the employment ladder. The possibilities are endless, afterall.</span></p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"On the pros of coliving: The social side (Image-4), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/7.jpg\" alt=\"On the pros of coliving: The social side (Image-4)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /><br /><br /><br /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '3_3.jpg', 1, '2019-09-18 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(307, 'Destination: Cafe Erzulie', 1, 'destination-cafe-erzulie', '', 'Destination: Cafe Erzulie', 'Destination: Cafe Erzulie', 'Open seven days a week, Cafe Erzulie is our favorite Bed Stuy hang out for a chilled evening, coffee or live music session', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Open seven days a week, </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Cafe Erzulie</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> is our favorite Bed Stuy hang out for a chilled evening, coffee or live music session. Part cafe, part bar and part flower shop, this under the radar hot spot serves coffee by day and cocktails and funky beats by night.&nbsp;</span></p>', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Open seven days a week, </span><strong>Cafe Erzulie</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> is our favorite Bed Stuy hang out for a chilled evening, coffee or live music session. Part cafe, part bar and part flower shop, this under the radar hot spot serves coffee by day and cocktails and funky beats by night.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Destination: Cafe Erzulie (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/1_8.jpg\" alt=\"Destination: Cafe Erzulie (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo: <em>Edible Brooklyn</em></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Walking along Broadway during the day, you would be forgiven for thinking the unassuming, plant-covered window of Cafe Erzulie was a flower shop. And you wouldn&rsquo;t be wrong. Cafe Erzulie sells a selection of flowers and plants, with creeping leaves blending into the decor and adorning the beautifully appointed garden in the back (obviously atmospherically set off by lashings of golden string lights). But Cafe Erzulie is so much more than a flower shop.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Destination: Cafe Erzulie (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/5.jpg\" alt=\"Destination: Cafe Erzulie (Image-2)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Photo: Cafe Erzulie, <em>Facebook</em></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">During the day, the space is a chilled out coffee shop perfect for sitting with your laptop and soaking up some rays in the garden. The hidden nature of Cafe Erzulie means it&rsquo;s tranquil during the day, providing a great environment to work. Nibble away on everything from sandwiches to salads to pastries, secure in the knowledge that all the food is made from scratch daily. The coffee comes from local roasters, Devocion, and the tea is supplied by popular tea atelier, Bellocq. Espressos start at $3 and you can also get cappuccinos, lattes and all the other usuals to fuel you through that remote working day.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">By night, Cafe Erzulie switches into a hip cocktail bar with dim lights, cheap drinks and a laid back atmosphere, open late from wednesdays through Sunday. The Haitian-inspired bar is most known for its live music, with regular jazz nights in the garden during the week and at weekends. You&rsquo;ll find everything from Afro-Carribean bands to Brazilian funk to hip hop nights and live DJs, all with that classic Brooklyn feel.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Destination: Cafe Erzulie (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/3_11.jpg\" alt=\"Destination: Cafe Erzulie (Image-3)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" />Photo: <em>Bushwick Daily</em></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Kick back with a glass of wine or beer with prices starting at just $6. The delicious cocktails start at $10 and include a range of inventive concoctions as well as the typical classics. We love the &ldquo;Flowers by Leslie&rdquo;, celebrating the flowers sold next to the bar itself, which consists of mint and cucumber, St-Germain and vodka. Happy Hour hits every wednesday through saturday from 4pm to 9pm, which includes discounts on both drinks and food. Our favorite Happy Hour eats are the Tacos Crole (chicken or pork tacos with pickle and green cabbage slaw) for just $4.50, and the stuffed plantain ($7).</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If music isn&rsquo;t your thing, there are other themed nights to suit any taste, including free comedy nights every second and fourth wednesday of the month. Recently, we experienced a yoga and meditation session with live music, drinks and positive energy, billed as a &ldquo;spiritual twerk&rdquo; night. Being under the radar, all Cafe Erzulie&rsquo;s events are announced on </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">their Instagram</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> the week or night of the show, so be sure to follow them for the latest news. Just don&rsquo;t be put off by the flower shop exterior: this is speakeasy-meets-cottage-industry in the heart of Bed Stuy.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Cafe Erzulie</span></em></p>\r\n<p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">894 Broadway,&nbsp;</span></em></p>\r\n<p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Brooklyn,&nbsp;</span></em></p>\r\n<p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">NY 11206</span></em></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>', '1_4.jpg', 1, '2019-09-19 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(308, 'Member Monday: Savannah Harley', 1, 'member-monday-savannah-harley', '', 'Member Monday: Savannah Harley', 'Member Monday: Savannah Harley', 'Meet Savannah Harley, a model who walked in New York Fashion Week while living at Outpost this summer, for this week\'s Member Monday.', '<p>Meet Savannah Harley, a model who walked in New York Fashion Week while living at Outpost this summer, for this week\'s Member Monday.</p>', '<p>Meet Savannah Harley, a model who walked in New York Fashion Week while living at Outpost this summer, for this week\'s Member Monday.</p>\r\n<h1>Tell us a bit about yourself.</h1>\r\n<p>Hi there, I am a 19-year old model from Montana, but I also grew up in South Dakota and Minnesota. I lived at Outpost during the Summer of 2019 to pursue modeling with EMG Agency in Manhattan. I got the opportunity to walk in New York Fashion Week during September of my stay.</p>\r\n<h1>What\'s your favorite Outpost memory?</h1>\r\n<p>Honestly, I have so many wonderful memories with Outpost that it\'s impossible to pick just one. I would say that by far my favorite part of the stay was getting to know so many people from every background imaginable. I made so many amazing friends during my time here and I know we will continue to be friends even after I move back home.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1>What\'s your favorite part of New York?</h1>\r\n<p>I love how easy it is to find activities to do and sites to see from right outside your door. There are so many amazing museums and parks on every block that it\'s impossible to get bored here.</p>\r\n<h1>What are you working on now?</h1>\r\n<p>I will continue modeling, but I plan to return to Montana for a few months to begin my first semester of college in pre-med. I hope to transfer to a school in NYC within the following months so that I can participate in fashion week again.&nbsp;</p>', 'IMG_4465.JPG', 1, '2019-09-30 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(310, 'Things to do this fall in San Francisco', 1, 'things-to-do-this-fall-in-san-francisco', '', 'Things to do this fall in San Francisco', 'Things to do this fall in San Francisco', 'Fall is one of the most beautiful seasons in San Francisco with plenty of things to do. Read on to find our top picks for feeling the fall spirit this year.', '<p>Fall is one of the most beautiful seasons in San Francisco, with plenty of things to do. Read on to find our top picks for feeling the fall spirit this October.</p>', '<p>Fall is one of the most beautiful seasons in San Francisco, with plenty of things to do. Read on to find our top picks for feeling the fall spirit this October.</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Things to do this fall in San Francisco (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/1_11.jpg\" alt=\"Things to do this fall in San Francisco (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo: <em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Half Moon Bay Pumpkin Festival</span></em></p>\r\n<h1><strong>Apple picking</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Apple picking is a classic American fall activity, and California is particularly famous for its deliciously juicy fruit, so why not try your hand at picking your own this fall? Most of the apple-picking ranches in the Bay Area are only accessible by car, but </span><strong>Chileno Valley Ranch</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> is relatively easy to get to, just 11 miles outside of Petaluma. Chileno offers organic apples on its 600-acre ranch and is open on Sundays from 10 a.m. to 4 p.m.</span></p>\r\n<h1><strong>Pumpkin picking</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">October is pumpkin-patch season, and San Francisco has a wide selection of pumpkin patches to choose from. Our favorite is </span><strong>Clancy&rsquo;s</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>,</strong> open from now until Oct. 31 daily, from 9 a.m.&ndash;9 p.m. This historic patch first opened all the way back in 1979 and has been providing SF natives with all varieties and shapes of pumpkins ever since. They even offer hayrides for a small fee (and no, you&rsquo;re never too old for a hayride). Check them out at their new location </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">at 2101 Sloat Blvd, right by the San Francisco Zoo.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Things to do this fall in San Francisco (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/botbcrowdsailboatsalcatrazfiltered.jpg\" alt=\"Things to do this fall in San Francisco (Image-2)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" />Photo: <em>Brews on the Bay</em></span></p>\r\n<h1><strong>Brews on the Bay</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Head down to Pier 45 for Brews on the Bay this Saturday October 19, an annual SF beer festival like none other. A celebration of local San Francisco beer, Brews on the Bay features a myriad of local vendors selling everything from pumpkin beer to IPAs to sours. This year, there will be 33 rare releases and 19 first releases, available exclusively for festival attendees to taste and ponder. The festival is all the more unique because of its location on a historic WWII ship, the </span><strong>S.S. Jeremiah O&rsquo;Brien</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, and the spectacular views it offers of the Golden Gate Bridge, Alcatraz and the bay.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h1><strong>Lumpia Palooza</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Celebrate Filipino-American heritage at&nbsp;Lumpia Palooza, a festival of Filipino culture and food at the ever-wonderful Soma StrEat Food Market. Enjoy a wide range of Filipino lumpia, including garlic, kare kare and chicken afritada lumpia, as well as weird and wonderful flavors like banana and cheeseburger varieties. You can even find lumpia rolling demos, a lumpia-eating contest, house-made sangrias and of course games and live music galore. Find out more and get tickets at the&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><img title=\"Things to do this fall in San Francisco (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/1_12.jpg\" alt=\"Things to do this fall in San Francisco (Image-3)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Photo: The Better Vacation</span></p>\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Halloween</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We probably don&rsquo;t have to remind you that Halloween is in a few days, but what you might not know is just how much there is going on in the Bay Area this year. Take your pick from a variety of </span><strong>Pub Crawls</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> or take part in one of our</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">&nbsp;favorite SF Halloween activities&nbsp;by taking&nbsp;a night tour of the historic Alcatraz prison, where you can really feel the history of our local monument come off the page.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>', '1_5.jpg', 1, '2019-10-16 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(317, '5 hot-spots for those cold NYC winter nights', 1, '5-hot-spots-for-those-cold-nyc-winter-nights', '', '5 hot-spots for those cold NYC winter nights', '5 hot-spots for those cold NYC winter nights', 'Yes, the rumors are true: winter is coming. But that doesn’t mean you have to give up a social life as the days get chillier', '<div class=\"TbwUpd\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Yes, the rumors are true: </span><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">winter is coming. </span></em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">But that doesn&rsquo;t mean you have to give up a social life as the days get chillier. New York is the city of possibilities and we&rsquo;ve got more than a few possibilities of warmth lined up for you.</span></div>', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Yes, the rumors are true: </span><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">winter is coming. </span></em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">But that doesn&rsquo;t mean you have to give up a social life as the days get chillier. New York is the city of possibilities and we&rsquo;ve got more than a few possibilities of warmth lined up for you.</span></p>\r\n<p>Why not...</p>\r\n<h1>1. Try a heated rooftop bar</h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">NYC is famous for its rooftop bars, but what most people don&rsquo;t know is that many of the city&rsquo;s rooftops are weather-proofed during the winter, equipped with heating to make sure you can stay at a comfortable temperature while still enjoying the skyline views. Our favorite heated rooftop for after work drinks is </span><strong>The Press Lounge</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">boasting arguably the best views in Manhattan as well as floor to ceiling glass windows, seconded only by </span><strong>Magic Hour</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">whose indoor awning somehow keeps the famous carousel ticking on throughout the colder months. And if you&rsquo;re looking for a rooftop club, </span><strong>Le Bain</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> is a favorite among Outpost members for dancing in the clouds (even in the snow).</span></p>\r\n<h1>2. Jump into a \"Sofar\" gig</h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"5 hot-spots for those cold NYC winter nights (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/2_10.jpg\" alt=\"5 hot-spots for those cold NYC winter nights (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Photo:&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sofar Sounds</span></span></p>\r\n<p><strong>Sofar Sounds</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> is the city&rsquo;s go-to provider of new indie music talent. Almost every day, a Sofar Sounds show is taking place in NYC, showcasing the latest unsigned artists. The idea is that the musicians apply to be in the show and the audience apply for tickets (although you\'ll almost always get them); the shows consist of three or four unsigned acts playing their original songs in unique venues around the city, from gin distilleries to volunteers\' homes, and even some of our very own Outpost members have played. Patrons sit on cushions and bring their own blankets to simply relax and enjoy the music, spending the night snug and warm without a reason to go outside. If you\'re lucky, try to snag a ticket for a BYOB session in one of the private residences which makes for the perfect night in (only \'out\') in the winter.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h1>3. Explore an art gallery by night</h1>\r\n<p>Many of New York City&rsquo;s art galleries are so huge you could spend an entire day there. What you might not know is that you can spend an entire night there, too, on selected dates. Several galleries, including the <a href=\"https://www.guggenheim.org\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Guggenheim</a> and the <a href=\"https://www.metmuseum.org\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Metropolitan Museum of Art</a>, have late night winter events where you can explore the art after work. The Guggenheim&rsquo;s \"<strong>Art After Dark</strong>\" events come with live entertainment, so you can sip on a drink and listen to a DJ while you appreciate the art, while the Met run drawing classes and other activities on their \"<a href=\"https://www.metmuseum.org/events/programs/met-fridays\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Met Fridays</a>,\" all of which you can enjoy while being wonderfully warm and cosy.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"5 hot-spots for those cold NYC winter nights (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/1_16.jpg\" alt=\"5 hot-spots for those cold NYC winter nights (Image-2)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" />Photo:&nbsp;Guggenheim</p>\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: left;\">4. Head to a specialized food court</h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Food courts in NYC are exciting, vibrant places. Head to <strong>Food Gallery 32 </strong>for a wide range of home made Korean food or take a trip to <strong>Eataly</strong> for Italian cuisine you can even take home with you. If you&rsquo;re in the mood to stroll in a heated plaza, try <strong><a href=\"http://www.chelseamarket.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Chelsea Market</a></strong>,&nbsp;known as a quintessential New York experience (where you can also shop), or the new <a href=\"https://www.timeout.com/newyork/time-out-market\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Time Out Market</a> in DUMBO, which features some impressive views from its rooftop dining area while still not being within a reasonable budget.</span></p>\r\n<h1><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"5 hot-spots for those cold NYC winter nights (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/3_16.jpg\" alt=\"5 hot-spots for those cold NYC winter nights (Image-3)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></h1>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo:&nbsp;Abimelec G., Yelp</p>\r\n<h1>5. See a Broadway show</h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">No matter the weather, the show must go on, and Broadway is the perfect place to continue it. Spend your winter nights soaking up some culture in the warmth of one of Broadway&rsquo;s historic theatres. Although prices are normally high, if you use trusted partners like <strong>TodayTix</strong> or line up on the morning of the performance for \"<strong>Rush Tickets</strong>\"&nbsp;you can find some unexpected bargains.</span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>', '1_6.jpg', 1, '2019-10-30 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(312, 'Top tips for cleaning in a coliving space', 1, 'top-tips-for-cleaning-in-a-coliving-space', '', 'Top tips for cleaning in a coliving space', 'Top tips for cleaning in a coliving space', 'If you’re new to coliving, you might be a bit confused about the cleaning situation, including what you can expect to be included in Outpost’s services and what’s expected of you. Of course, at Outpost we have a regular cleaning service included in your rate, but that doesn’t mean you should leave everything for the cleaners. Cleaning in the coliving space is about everybody pulling their own weight.', '<p>If you&rsquo;re new to coliving, you might be a bit confused about the cleaning situation, including what you can expect to be included in Outpost&rsquo;s services and what&rsquo;s expected of you. Of course, at Outpost we have a regular cleaning service included in your rate, but that doesn&rsquo;t mean you should leave everything for the cleaners. Cleaning in the coliving space is about everybody pulling their own weight.</p>', '<p>If you&rsquo;re new to coliving, you might be a bit confused about the cleaning situation, including what you can expect to be included in Outpost&rsquo;s services and what&rsquo;s expected of you. Of course, at Outpost we have a regular cleaning service included in your rate, but that doesn&rsquo;t mean you should leave everything for the cleaners. Cleaning in the coliving space is about everybody pulling their own weight.</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Top tips for cleaning in a coliving space (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/1_13.jpg\" alt=\"Top tips for cleaning in a coliving space (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<h1>What you can expect the cleaners to do...&nbsp;</h1>\r\n<p>Our cleaners provide a regular service to Outpost members. You can expect them to wipe down surfaces in the kitchen and dining areas, mop the floor of the common areas, make sure the bathroom is scrubbed and restocked with toilet paper, and other essential tasks. They will also clean the floors of your room if you leave the door open to signal it is alright to do so.</p>\r\n<h1>What you can\'t expect the cleaners to do...</h1>\r\n<h1>1)&nbsp;\"Everything\"</h1>\r\n<p>Okay, it sounds obvious, but you\'d be surprised how many people get the wrong end of the stick here.&nbsp;One of the benefits of coliving at Outpost is that everything is included, including our in-house cleaners, but it&rsquo;s important to remember that you should always try to keep things clean in between visits, as far as your personal property (and dish usage) is concerned.</p>\r\n<h1>2)&nbsp;Keep things spotless in between cleanings</h1>\r\n<p>If you want to live in a tidy house (and we hope you do!), some of the cleaning will have to happen on your end. It seems simple really, but cleaning up as you go is the best way to avoid roommate arguments and keep harmony in the coliving space. Although we have regular cleaners, mess can build up quickly, so it isn&rsquo;t realistic to leave things like dishes and personal belongings in between cleaning sessions (and it shouldn&rsquo;t be the cleaners&rsquo; responsibility to deal with personal items such as dishes). Coliving is all about sharing, and sometimes that means sharing the chores as well as the fun.</p>\r\n<p>Even though you might be in a rush in the morning before work, that doesn&rsquo;t mean you can&rsquo;t clean up when you get home at night, and it&rsquo;s a lot easier doing it in small bursts than all at once. Cleaning up in small ways like doing your dishes, filling up and emptying the dishwasher and wiping down surfaces in between cleaners&rsquo; visits makes all the difference to the happiness of your fellow roommates.</p>\r\n<h1><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Top tips for cleaning in a coliving space (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/2_7.jpg\" alt=\"Top tips for cleaning in a coliving space (Image-2)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" />3)&nbsp;Keep your room clean</h1>\r\n<p>It is your room, after all, and although the cleaners will of course help you out with regular cleanings, it\'s important to keep things clean in between visits. If you&rsquo;re sharing a room, you might find that it&rsquo;s sometimes a challenge to keep things clean. The best way is to keep your own part of the room clean and avoid unnecessary mess caused by eating in your room or not putting clothes back in the closet. And when cleaning day rolls around, simply leave your door open to signal to the cleaners it&rsquo;s alright to come in and make sure that all clothes and other obstructive objects are off the floor so they can clean your room easily and efficiently.</p>', '2_1.jpg', 1, '2019-10-18 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0);
