(327, '5 best restaurants in SoMa', 1, '5-best-restaurants-in-soma', '', '5 best restaurants in SoMa', '5 best restaurants in SoMa', 'We love the SoMa neighborhood, so we\'ve put together a list of our top eateries.', '<p>We love the SoMa neighborhood, so we\'ve put together a list of our top eateries.</p>', '<p>We love the SoMa neighborhood so we\'ve put together a list of our top eateries for you to peruse and choose from.</p>\r\n<h1>1.&nbsp;The Revolution Cafe</h1>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"5 best restaurants in SoMa (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/2_24.jpg\" alt=\"5 best restaurants in SoMa (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Photo: <em>Joanna Q Z., Yelp</em></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Revolution Cafe is an American food spot that\'s part cafe, part restaurant and part wine bar.Along with great food and an intimate atmosphere, with everything from soup to salad to sangria all at a reasonable price, you can enjoy live music every night with different genres switching throughout the week.</span><br /><br /><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"5 best restaurants in SoMa (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/1_32.jpg\" alt=\"5 best restaurants in SoMa (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo: <em>Kruthi S., Yelp</em></p>\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: left;\">2.&nbsp;Marlowe</h1>\r\n<p>With a wide selection of American food and a cool, laid back atmosphere, Marlowe is one of our top SoMa destinatons. They\'re famous for their burger and their New York steak, but the menu has a wide range of vegetarian options as well, including brussel chips, crispy salads, deviled eggs and peanut butter bites.</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"5 best restaurants in SoMa (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/2_25.jpg\" alt=\"5 best restaurants in SoMa (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;Photo: <em>Nancy B., Yelp</em></p>\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: left;\">3. Zero Zero</h1>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Zero Zero is the best Italian restaurant in SoMa. We love their thin crust pizza, made with farm driven ingredients in a wood-fired oven, as well as homemade pastas and delicious soft serve ice cream. It\'s also a cute spot to drink with friends or a date.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"5 best restaurants in SoMa (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/1_33.jpg\" alt=\"5 best restaurants in SoMa (Image-2)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" />&nbsp;Photo: <em>John D., Yelp</em></p>\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;4. Manora\'s</h1>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Manora\'s Thai restaurant is SoMa\'s best Thai restaurant, serving the neighborhood affordable and delicious food since opening back in 1987. A family run business for 30 years, you can taste the authenticity in every dish.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"5 best restaurants in SoMa (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/2_26.jpg\" alt=\"5 best restaurants in SoMa (Image-3)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo: <em>Manora\'s</em></p>\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: left;\">5. South Park Cafe</h1>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"5 best restaurants in SoMa (Image-4), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/2_28.jpg\" alt=\"5 best restaurants in SoMa (Image-4)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" />Photo: <em>South Park Cafe</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">South Park Cafe is a cute cafe with affordable prices, famous for its fried chicken, lamb meatballs and rainbow vegetables. The servers are friendly, the vibe is relaxed and the drinks are well priced to go with your food.&nbsp;</p>', '1_13.jpg', 1, '2019-11-22 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(329, '5 tips for apartment hunting in a big city', 1, '5-tips-for-apartment-hunting-in-a-big-city', '', '5 tips for apartment hunting in a big city', '5 tips for apartment hunting in a big city', 'Apartment hunting in a big city can be hard. You don\'t know which neighborhoods are fun, which streets are safe, or which falafel place is the best before you\'re supposed to decide on where to live. But don\'t worry, with a little know-how, you can find the apartment of your dreams. ', '<p>Apartment hunting in a big city can be hard. You don\'t know which neighborhoods are fun, which streets are safe, or which falafel place is the best before you\'re supposed to decide on where to live. But don\'t worry, with a little know-how, you can find the apartment of your dreams.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>Apartment hunting in a big city can be hard. You don\'t know which neighborhoods are fun, which streets are safe, or which falafel place is the best before you\'re supposed to decide on where to live. But don\'t worry, with a little know-how, you can find the apartment of your dreams.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"5 tips for apartment hunting in a big city (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/2_29.jpg\" alt=\"5 tips for apartment hunting in a big city (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo: <em><a href=\"https://www.google.com/url?sa=i&amp;rct=j&amp;q=&amp;esrc=s&amp;source=images&amp;cd=&amp;ved=2ahUKEwiMz_vQsL_mAhVNzYUKHVqmAwwQjB16BAgBEAM&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2Ffathersbk%2Fcommunity%2F&amp;psig=AOvVaw3AJYXs2gWmClb7DuJ5CGOG&amp;ust=1576764708578175\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Father Knows Best</a></em></p>\r\n<h1>1. Avoid scams</h1>\r\n<p>It might go without saying, but apartment scams are often not as obvious as you think. Sites like Craigslist have a bad reputation, but they\'re not necessarily filled with scams. Red flags are more in the details; avoid apartment listings without photos or with photos which look doctored; ask to see the apartment before you put any money down (or ask for a video tour if you\'re overseas) and always trust your instincts. If something seems off, it\'s better to be safe than sorry. Asking for any money or personal details (aside from your favorite hobbies) before you\'ve seen the place is usually a scam alert.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1>2. Google search and map the neighborhood safety</h1>\r\n<p>Just because a neighborhood is a good commute or a cheap price doesn\'t mean it\'s the right one for your home. You can get to know if a neighborhood is safe without living there with the help of Google. Type in the neighborhood you\'re thinking of moving to alongside keywords like \'safety\' or go straight to the crime statistics. Be aware of the date of articles you come across; many neighborhoods in big cities have seen big changes over the last few years and often previously crime-ridden areas are now perfectly safe to live in. If you want up to date information, try Google crime maps (you can see the NYC crime map <a href=\"https://maps.nyc.gov/crime/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">here</a>) where you can see recommendations based on current statistics.</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"5 tips for apartment hunting in a big city (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/1_35.jpg\" alt=\"5 tips for apartment hunting in a big city (Image-2)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo: <em><a href=\"https://artsclubnyc.com/events/bushwick-street-art-tour\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">ArtsClub</a></em></p>\r\n<h1>3. Check there are things to see and do locally</h1>\r\n<p>You probably want to know that there are things to see and do in your new neighborhood; search&nbsp;\'bars\', \'restaurants\' or \'cafes in\' (your neighborhood name) and look at the number of pins. One great spot can make your experience of living in an apartment, so remember that quality sometimes beats quantity. You can also check out local blogs and housing blogs, like our articles on the appeal of living in different <a href=\"../nyc-rooms-for-rent\" target=\"_blank\">NYC neighborhoods</a>.</p>\r\n<h1>4. Don\'t forget the little details</h1>\r\n<p>Think about your typical week and what you might want from an apartment and neighborhood. Little things count; like what is the bus service like if the subway stops running? Can you get home at 3am in the morning, or are there city bikes nearby to shorten your commute? If you want to get the vibe of a neighborhood but can\'t go and visit, take a strong along Google street view within a few blocks\' radius.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"5 tips for apartment hunting in a big city (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/1_37.jpg\" alt=\"5 tips for apartment hunting in a big city (Image-3)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" />Photo: <a href=\"https://sf.gov\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">SF.Gov</a></p>\r\n<h1>5. Go with a trusted source</h1>\r\n<p>We\'re not saying you have to rent through a company, but it\'s better if you do. Renting through an individual simply doesn\'t offer the renter the same rights and protection. At Outpost, for instance, you can see our track record, reviews and our transparent house rules and promises to our members. You can see evidence of happy members, past and present, on our social media and blog post. This type of information indicates that you can trust us and, although apartment sources come in all shapes and sizes, it\'s still something to keep in mind when decided whether to trust an individual or a company with your money.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '1_14.jpg', 1, '2019-11-25 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(330, 'How to brighten your January in NYC', 1, 'how-to-brighten-your-january-in-nyc', '', 'How to brighten your January in NYC', 'How to brighten your January in NYC', 'January can be a dreary time of year but it doesn\'t have to be that way. Here are our top picks of NYC events to brighten up your month this January.', '<p>January can be a dreary time of year but it doesn\'t have to be that way. Here are our top picks of NYC events to brighten up your month this January.</p>', '<p>January can be a dreary time of year but it doesn\'t have to be that way. Here are our top picks of NYC events to brighten up your month this January.</p>\r\n<h2><strong>NYC Winter Lantern Festival (Now-January 12)</strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"How to brighten your January in NYC(Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/1_39.jpg\" alt=\"How to brighten your January in NYC (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" />Photo: <em>NYC Winter Lantern Festival</em></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The best way to brighten up your January is with some color. Find more than 1,000 lanterns sculpted into beautiful art on Staten Island at the NYC Winter Lantern Festival, with everything from dragons to tulips to beautiful archways to explore. There&rsquo;s even a full schedule of cultural performances, including plate spinning, Tibetan Folk Dance and Chinese Sichuan Opera magic as well as an ice skating rink to lift those winter blues.</span></p>\r\n<h2><strong>Winter Jazzfest 2020 (January 9-18)</strong></h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"How to brighten your January in NYC(Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/2_32.jpg\" alt=\"How to brighten your January in NYC (Image-2)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Now in its 16th season, the annual NYC Winter Jazzfest is back again for January 2020. Catch over 700 bands performing in venues across NYC as well as a program of discussions on gender, immigration and other social issues in the jazz world. There&rsquo;s even a jazz marathon at the center of the festival hosted across a handful of Lower Manhattan venues, complete with two nights of non-stop music from both famous cats and newcomers alike, all of which you can access with a single wristband.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h2><strong>NYC Restaurant Week (January 21&ndash;February 9)</strong></h2>\r\n<p><strong><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"How to brighten your January in NYC(Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/2_33.jpg\" alt=\"How to brighten your January in NYC (Image-3)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This popular NYC festival occurs twice a year (and January is our favorite of the two sessions because the holiday crowds have cleared out for the winter). <strong>Restaurant Week</strong> gives patrons the chance to enjoy 5-star meals at a quarter of the cost. More than 300 of New York&rsquo;s best restaurants will be offering a prix-fixe menu with their favorite dishes at ridiculously reduced prices for the occasion with two-course lunch menus starting at just $26.</span></p>\r\n<h2><strong>Martin Luther King Jr. Day (January 20)</strong></h2>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This annual celebration is held in honor of Martin Luther King Jr. and it&rsquo;s the perfect time to learn more about Black History in the city. There are regularly special exhibitions at <a href=\"https://www.nypl.org/locations/schomburg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Schomburg Center for Research in Black Culture</a>, <a href=\"https://www.mcny.org\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">The Museum of the City of New York Brooklyn</a> and the <a href=\"https://www.apollotheater.org\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Academy of Music Apollo Theater</a> as well as annual street parties throughout Harlem. This year the&nbsp;Harlem Gospel Choir will even be performing at <a href=\"https://www.sonyhall.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Sony Hall</a>.</span></p>\r\n<h2><strong>No Pants Subway Ride (January 12)</strong></h2>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"How to brighten your January in NYC(Image-4), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/3_22.jpg\" alt=\"How to brighten your January in NYC (Image-4)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo: <em>Pulsd</em></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Something that will truly brighten up your January, the &ldquo;No Pants Subway Ride&rdquo; is an annual day in which brave New Yorkers&nbsp;literally ride the subway (in the freezing weather) without their pants on, some in the name of charity and some simply in the name of laughter, organized by Improv Everywhere. If you&rsquo;re interested in getting involved, y</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">ou can </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">RSVP on Facebook</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> or take a look at the </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">event page for the after party</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> at Bar 13. Just be prepared to freeze not just your socks off.</span></p>\r\n<h2><strong>Three Kings Day Parade (January 6)</strong></h2>\r\n<p><strong><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"How to brighten your January in NYC(Image-5), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/2_34.jpg\" alt=\"How to brighten your January in NYC (Image-5)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo: <em>El Museo del Barrio</em></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The 43rd annual Three Kings Day Parade is titled <em>Nuestros Barrios Unidos: Celebrating our Collective Strength. </em>This spectacular parade is&nbsp;held in honor of New York City&rsquo;s immigrant and migrant communities past and present. Featuring real camels, colorful floats, puppets, <em>parrandas&nbsp;</em>and plenty of music and dancing, the festivities start at 11 am at 106th St and Park Ave.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h1><strong>7. Chinese New Year (January 25)</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Chinese New Year is one of the most colorful events in the New York City calendar. Head to Chinatown to catch beautiful lanterns, delicious street food and more on January 25. This year rings in the new year of the rat, one of New York City&rsquo;s most esteemed and famous residents. Now that\'s a great way to brighten up your January.</span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>', '2_7.jpg', 1, '2019-11-27 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(334, 'Member Monday: Nathalia Generoso', 1, 'member-monday-nathalia-generoso', '', 'Member Monday: Nathalia Generoso', 'Member Monday: Nathalia Generoso', 'For this week’s Member Monday, we talked to Nath Generoso, the house leader at our Upper East Side, United Nations and Lexington houses.', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">For this week&rsquo;s Member Monday, we talked to Nath Generoso, the house leader at our Upper East Side, United Nations and Lexington houses.</span></p>', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">For this week&rsquo;s Member Monday, we talked to Nath Generoso, the house leader at our Upper East Side, United Nations and Lexington houses. Read on to find out what she works on when she&rsquo;s not community building!&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><img title=\"Member Monday: Nathalia Generoso (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/78269291_2596469013741686_1258782488424087552_o.jpg\" alt=\"Member Monday: Nathalia Generoso (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></span></p>\r\n<h2>Tell us a bit about yourself.</h2>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">I have been a House Leader for Outpost since September 2019. I started in Jersey City houses and now I&rsquo;m in Upper East Side houses. I also work remotely with marketing and strategies for a company in Brazil and I </span><a href=\"http://www.nathaliageneroso.com.br\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">have a travel blog</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, where I write about the countries I&rsquo;ve been to in my 2 years as a backpacker and try to inspire women to travel by themselves too.</span></p>\r\n<h2>What\'s your favorite Outpost memory?</h2>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">My favorite Outpost memories are usually the parties they promote, because it&rsquo;s a great opportunity to meet other members and make friends and have fun.</span></p>\r\n<h2>What\'s your favorite part of New York?</h2>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">My favorite part of New York is lower Manhattan! I love to wander around Chinatown and get delicious and cheap food. The street art there is really cool and alternative, so being there makes me happy.</span></p>\r\n<h2>What are you working on now?</h2>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">I&rsquo;m planning my trips for the next year and I&rsquo;m really excited &mdash; and a little overwhelmed &mdash; about the possibilities. It&rsquo;s definitely going to be an amazing year and I can&rsquo;t wait!</span></p>', '79254181_2596468917075029_2293139943356104704_o.jpg', 1, '2019-12-09 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(335, 'Spending Christmas Away From Home: Top Tips', 1, 'spending-christmas-away-from-home-top-tips', '', 'Spending Christmas Away From Home: Top Tips', 'Spending Christmas Away From Home: Top Tips', 'In the whirlwind of fun that is traveling or living far from home, lots of us don’t have the chance to go home for the holidays. If you celebrate Christmas or even if not, it can seem like a lonely to prospect ro be thousands of miles away from family or friends over this time of year.\r\n', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In the whirlwind of fun that is traveling or living far from home, lots of us don&rsquo;t have the chance to go home for the holidays. If you celebrate Christmas or even if not, it can seem like a lonely to prospect ro be thousands of miles away from family or friends over this time of year.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p>In the whirlwind of fun that is traveling or living far from home, many of us don&rsquo;t have the chance to go home for the holidays. Whether or not you celebrate Christmas, it can seem like a lonely to prospect to be thousands of miles away from family or friends over this time of year. Here are a few tips to make the most of the rest of the holiday season if you\'re spending it away from home.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1><strong><strong>Be present in the place you&rsquo;re in right now</strong></strong></h1>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><strong><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Spending Christmas Away From Home: Top Tips (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/1_28.jpg\" alt=\"Spending Christmas Away From Home: Top Tips (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></strong></strong>Photo:&nbsp;<em>Vivienne Gucwa, <a href=\"https://www.pinterest.co.uk/pin/226024475028707763/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Pinterest</a></em></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It can be easy to focus on the negatives of not being with family during the holidays, so it&rsquo;s worth stopping and appreciating the opportunity you have before you. Look out the window or take a walk down a new street. It&rsquo;s an amazing thing to travel and to live abroad; every day you have the opportunity to meet new people and see new things. And the people around you might not be family, but friends are the family you choose for yourself. Christmas is just one day, so when you weigh it up against all the positives of your current adventure, it doesn&rsquo;t seem so bad to be where you are.</span></p>\r\n<h1><strong>Connect with other people in the same situation</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you&rsquo;re living somewhere like Outpost, there will be lots of other people in the same situation as you. Ask around in the weeks leading up to Christmas and arrange something to do on the day like secret Santa or a Christmas party. You could even cook a whole Christmas meal with everyone bringing something, which is a great way to exchange cultures and explore what other people usually eat and drink on Christmas.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><img title=\"Spending Christmas Away From Home: Top Tips (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/freestocks-org--Qf9JKLysUg-unsplash.jpg\" alt=\"Spending Christmas Away From Home: Top Tips (Image-2)\" /></span></p>\r\n<h1><strong>Explore the local cultures</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Every city has its own version of holiday celebrations. This might be the only year you&rsquo;re spending in your current location, so use it to learn about the culture. Look up listings websites to see what&rsquo;s going on in your city, where you&rsquo;ll find everything from ice rinks to carol singing to soup kitchen volunteering. For instance, New York is famous for its beautiful Christmas displays along Fifth Avenue and in Dyker Heights. Throw yourself into what the locals do and you&rsquo;ll soon see your December brighten up.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><img title=\"Spending Christmas Away From Home: Top Tips (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/marina-khrapova-nE4CsEL9Z_s-unsplash.jpg\" alt=\"Spending Christmas Away From Home: Top Tips (Image-3)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></span></p>\r\n<h1><strong>Remember, there&rsquo;s always technology</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you&rsquo;re still sad about being away from home, remember you&rsquo;re only a phone call away from a friendly voice. And you can go further than that; why not video call your loved ones on Christmas day? You can keep the video running and virtually spend the whole day together, proving that distance doesn&rsquo;t have to be a problem in the digital age.</span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>', 'freestocks-org--Qf9JKLysUg-unsplash.jpg', 1, '2019-12-18 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(336, 'Destination: Exploratorium, SF', 1, 'destination-exploratorium-sf', '', 'Destination: Exploratorium, SF', 'Destination: Exploratorium, SF', 'You’re never too old to learn something new. Although most fun, interactive museums are normally reserved for kids, Exploratorium is different.', '<p>You&rsquo;re never too old to learn something new. Although most fun, interactive museums are normally reserved for kids, Exploratorium is different.</p>', '<p>You&rsquo;re never too old to learn something new. Although most fun, interactive museums are normally reserved for kids, <a href=\"https://www.exploratorium.edu/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Exploratorium</a>&nbsp;is different.</p>\r\n<p>Located at Pier 15, Exploratorium is a fully interactive experience with exhibitions centering around explaining how our world works. Much more than a museum, it&rsquo;s an exploration of science, art and human perception with a huge collection of fun experiences to sample.</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Destination: Exploratorium, SF (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/1_29.jpg\" alt=\"Destination: Exploratorium, SF (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo: <em><a href=\"https://www.exploratorium.edu/visit/calendar/kaleidoscope\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Exploratorium</a></em></p>\r\n<p>This holiday season, they&rsquo;re holding &ldquo;Glow,&rdquo; a winter festival of lights, which includes the gleams and glistens of a whole host of special installations and kinetic sculptures as well as interactive activities, on show from now through January 20. And if you&rsquo;re not so keen on the idea of children running around you, it&rsquo;s perfect, as the program is entirely adults-only, including unique guest speakers and exhibitions.</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Destination: Exploratorium, SF (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/2_21.jpg\" alt=\"Destination: Exploratorium, SF (Image-2)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo: <em><a href=\"https://www.exploratorium.edu/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Exploratorium</a></em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Try their special installation, <em>Kaleidoscope</em>, an interactive activity consisting of an 8-foot-square light table made by artist Karina Smigla-Bobinski, where you can touch and twirl to change the layers of ink on the surface, creating hyperdynamic new images that visualize your motion energy into swirling, engaging patterns.</p>\r\n<p>Or immerse yourself in the lights of <em>Buckyball</em>, a huge 25-foot illuminated sculpture by artist Leo Villareal composed of 4,500 LED nodes in two nested geodesic spheres, shining 16 million distinct colors for its viewers. We also love the disorienting world of <em>Language Cloud, </em>Laura Stevenson&rsquo;s artistic exploration of the pattern-seeking nature of the human psyche. Scavenged and repurposed from old neon signs, this pleasantly disorienting jumble of letters and words will make you realize the beautiful plasticity of the brain.</p>\r\n<p>With even more exhibitions to explore, this adults-only event at Exploratorium makes it the perfect place for a date night or catch up with friends.</p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>', '1_12.jpg', 1, '2019-12-15 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(337, 'Destination: Magnolia Bakery', 1, 'destination-magnolia-bakery', '', 'Destination: Magnolia Bakery', 'Destination: Magnolia Bakery', 'If you’re aiming to hit the TV hotspots in the city (and we means those without the swarming crowds of tourists) or if you just want something delicious to nibble on, Magnolia Bakery should be first on your list.', '<p>If you&rsquo;re aiming to hit the TV hotspots in the city (and we means those without the swarming crowds of tourists) or if you just want something delicious to nibble on, Magnolia Bakery should be first on your list.</p>', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>If you&rsquo;re aiming to hit the TV hotspots in the city (and we means those without the swarming crowds of tourists) or if you just want something delicious to nibble on, Magnolia Bakery should be first on your list.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Destination: Magnolia Bakery (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/1_38.jpg\" alt=\"Destination: Magnolia Bakery (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo: <em><a href=\"https://freetoursbyfoot.com/magnolia-bakery/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">FreeToursByFoot</a></em></p>\r\n<p>This little West Village was first made famous by Sex in the City as the setting of Carrie and Miranda&rsquo;s gossip over a couple of cupcakes. Since then, it&rsquo;s exploded in popularity as more and more people have discovered its delectable treats, although somehow it&rsquo;s never too busy. It&rsquo;s just one of those New York City landmarks that stands there, day in day out, waiting for you to come back to time and time again. And the food isn&rsquo;t bad either.</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Destination: Magnolia Bakery (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/2_30.jpg\" alt=\"Destination: Magnolia Bakery (Image-2)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo: <em><a href=\"https://www.magnoliabakery.com/locations/rockefeller-center/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Magnolia Bakery</a></em></p>\r\n<p>Magnolia bakery has everything from cupcakes to quiches. We love their banana pudding, which is essentially little pots of joy put together as the antidote to any hard day at the office or bad break up. They even have a rotating menu of special edition items, including the amazing winter red velvet pudding and Rockettes cupcakes.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Destination: Magnolia Bakery (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/2_31.jpg\" alt=\"Destination: Magnolia Bakery (Image-3)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" />Photo: <em><a href=\"https://www.magnoliabakery.com/locations/bleecker-street/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Magnolia Bakery</a></em></p>\r\n<p>The bakery first opened in 1996 and has gone from strength to strength, opening 30 stores around the globe and 6 in NYC, although we still love the original West Village location and it homey, intimate vibe. On sunny days, you can even cross the street and sit in the park and listen to the birds. In spit of its expansion, Magnolia Bakery has kept its same dedication to quality ingredients and they&rsquo;ve stayed committed to not over-inflating their prices. And although there are lines at peak times like Friday afternoons and lunch slots, you can always get your foot inside and it&rsquo;s certainly always worth the wait.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>401 Bleecker St., and W. 11th St</em></p>\r\n<p><em>New York</em></p>\r\n<p><em>10014</em></p>', '2_6.jpg', 1, '2019-12-18 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(338, 'Our 5 favorite East Village Bars', 1, 'our-5-favorite-east-village-bars', '', 'Our 5 favorite East Village Bars', 'Our 5 favorite East Village Bars', 'The East Village is famous for its low key, artsy, underground nightlife. We’ve rounded up our 5 favorite bars in the neighborhood for any newcomer or veteran to try.', '<p>The East Village is famous for its low key, artsy, underground nightlife. We&rsquo;ve rounded up our 5 favorite bars in the neighborhood for any newcomer or veteran to try.</p>', '<p>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The East Village is famous for its low key, artsy, underground nightlife. We&rsquo;ve rounded up our 5 favorite bars in the neighborhood for any newcomer or veteran to try.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1><strong>1. Sophie&rsquo;s</strong></h1>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Our 5 favorite East Village Bars (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/1_40.jpg\" alt=\"Our 5 favorite East Village Bars (Image-1)\" width=\"1000\" height=\"595\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo: <em>Dave L., Yelp&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sophie&rsquo;s is one of the best kept secrets in the East Village. If you&rsquo;re looking for classic a dive bar away from the tourists, this low-key spot is the perfect place to start. Featuring cheap drinks, a pool table and a jukebox filled with grunge and indie music, what more could you ask for to get a sense of the real East Village spirit? Plus, the bar staff are always friendly and ready to share their wealth of knowledge on the city.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"lemon--p__373c0__3Qnnj text__373c0__2pB8f text-color--normal__373c0__K_MKN text-align--left__373c0__2pnx_ text-weight--bold__373c0__3HYJa\"><em><span class=\"lemon--span__373c0__3997G\">509 E 5th St,</span></em></p>\r\n<p class=\"lemon--p__373c0__3Qnnj text__373c0__2pB8f text-color--normal__373c0__K_MKN text-align--left__373c0__2pnx_ text-weight--bold__373c0__3HYJa\"><em><span class=\"lemon--span__373c0__3997G\">New York, NY 10003</span></em></p>\r\n<h1><strong>2. Please Don&rsquo;t Tell</strong></h1>\r\n<p><strong><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Our 5 favorite East Village Bars (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/pdt_splash.jpg\" alt=\"Our 5 favorite East Village Bars (Image-2)\" width=\"666\" height=\"501\" /></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo: <em>Please Don\'t Tell</em></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Please Don&rsquo;t Tell is one of the most popular speakeasies in the city. Sound like a paradox? It is. This speakeasy is suffering from the disease of going viral, but we can forgive Please Don&rsquo;t Tell because it&rsquo;s just so darn cool. Still an incredibly atmospheric spot with a secretive feel (you enter through a telephone box inside a restaurant), it&rsquo;s just somewhere to avoid on weekends because of the not so secret line building outside. We recommend this bar for weeknights and early evening drinks, and if you can&rsquo;t get in just cross the street over to East Village Social.</span></p>\r\n<p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">113 St Marks Pl, </span></em></p>\r\n<p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">New York, NY 10009&nbsp;</span></em></p>\r\n<h1><strong>3.&nbsp;East Village Social</strong></h1>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Our 5 favorite East Village Bars (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/1_41.jpg\" alt=\"Our 5 favorite East Village Bars (Image-3)\" width=\"960\" height=\"960\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo: <em>East Village Social</em></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">East Village Social is a wonderful, under-the-radar bar just opposite Please Don&rsquo;t Tell. This cosy hole in the wall is the perfect combination of cheap drinks, exposed brick and friendly bar staff. They even have live music most nights of the week and a regular Tuesday trivia session, making them one of the most welcoming spots in the East Village for the tight budgets of young professionals, artists and students who still want to experience that classic East Village flavor. Get there before 8pm for Happy Hour to enjoy beer and cider for just $5 (did we mention they have craft beer on tap?)</span></p>\r\n<p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">126 St Marks Pl, </span></em></p>\r\n<p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">New York, NY 10009</span></em></p>\r\n<h1><strong>4. Goodnight Sonny</strong></h1>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;<img title=\"Our 5 favorite East Village Bars (Image-4), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/3_23.jpg\" alt=\"Our 5 favorite East Village Bars (Image-4)\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1000\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Photo: <em>Goodnight Sonny</em></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">For some classic Manhattan glamor at a reasonable price, we love the tiled and wooden panelled decor of Goodnight Sonny. Serving a wide range of cocktails and even oysters at Happy Hour prices, this is the perfect place for a classic apertatif or an after dinner drink.</span></p>\r\n<p><em>134 1st Avenue, </em></p>\r\n<p><em>New York, NY 10009</em></p>\r\n<h1><strong>5. Miss Lily\'s 7A Cafe</strong></h1>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Our 5 favorite East Village Bars (Image-5), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/1_42.jpg\" alt=\"Our 5 favorite East Village Bars (Image-5)\" width=\"750\" height=\"500\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo: Miss Lily\'s</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Technically a restaurant but taking on the role of a bar at weekends, this Carribean cafe is always buzzing with patrons downing their delicious cocktails. The decor is bright and clashing, inspired by 80s Carribean diners, and the waiting staff are always ready to have a chat. They&rsquo;re famous for their live music on weekend nights as well as their Rum Bar, which includes over 100 varieties of Caribbean rum, and of course the infamous Dark and Stormy slushy machine brings patrons from across the neighborhood to Miss Lily&rsquo;s.</span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>', '3_6.jpg', 1, '2019-12-27 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(339, 'Our favorite SF festivals this January ', 1, 'our-favorite-sf-festivals-this-january-', '', 'Our favorite SF festivals this January ', 'Our favorite SF festivals this January ', 'January is a busy time in San Francisco. With so many things to see and do, we\'ve put together a list of our top festivals going on this month to get you to through the winter to spring.', '', '<p>January is a busy time in San Francisco. With so many things to see and do, we\'ve put together a list of our top festivals going on this month to get you to through the winter to spring.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1><strong>SF Sketchfest, January 9-26</strong></h1>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Our favorite SF festivals this January (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/1_43.jpg\" alt=\"Our favorite SF festivals this January (Image-1)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Photo: </span><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">SF Sketchfest</span></em></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Since 2001, </span><strong>SF Sketchfest</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> has brought an annual programme of sketch comedy to San Francisco to brighten up our January. Founded as a way to showcase the talents of six Bay Area sketch comedy groups, the festival has grown into a nationally recognized comedy festival mixing national celebrities and local favorites as well as talented, up-and-coming comics from throughout North America, including performers who regularly feature on television shows such as &ldquo;Saturday Night Live&rdquo; and &ldquo;The Upright Citizens Brigade&rdquo;. This year the program includes over 250 shows, including performances and discussions, taking place in over 20 venues across the city over 18 glorious days.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h1><strong>Women&rsquo;s March San Francisco, January 18</strong></h1>\r\n<p><strong><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Our favorite SF festivals this January (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/2_35.jpg\" alt=\"Our favorite SF festivals this January (Image-2)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Photo: </span><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Beth Thomas, </span></em><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Flickr</span></em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Join the </span><strong>Women&rsquo;s March</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> in 2020 to stand up for the rights of women everywhere and get 2020 off to a flying start. This annual march brings together women and allies from all backgrounds to march in the name of women&rsquo;s rights, with issues ranging from immigrant rights to workers rights to reproductive rights and more. This year, the rally will begin at 11am at Civic Center Plaza, and from there the march will progress through the city. Find out more information and stay up to date with any changes on the </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Eventbrite page</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and the official </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">website</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h1><strong>San Francisco Movement Arts Festival, January 24</strong></h1>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Our favorite SF festivals this January (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/2_36.jpg\" alt=\"Our favorite SF festivals this January (Image-3)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Photo: </span><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">SF Movement Arts Festival</span></em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The 6th Annual </span><strong><a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/e/san-francisco-movement-arts-festival-tickets-80082197007\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">San Francisco Movement Arts Festival</a></strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> (SFMAF) is one of our top picks for this January.&nbsp; With over 300 performers, catch the entire Grace Cathedral transformed into a stage for one night only, with the main floor, chapels, stairways and more becoming their own hubs of entertainment. Multiple performances occur simultaneously at the &ldquo;movement stations&rdquo;, so you can walk around the space and discover more and more artists as you progress. Each station will feature up to six groups performing short rotating pieces, including ballet, ethnic, ballroom dancing, Movement choirs and more. With over 90% of performers being local to the Bay Area, it&rsquo;s the perfect way to explore the SF arts scene without freezing your toes off this January. The box office opens at 5:00pm or you can find out more information on the </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Eventbrite page</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.</span></p>\r\n<h1><strong>San Francisco Tape Music Festival, January 10-12</strong></h1>\r\n<p><strong><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" title=\"Our favorite SF festivals this January (Image-4), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/unnamed.jpg\" alt=\"Our favorite SF festivals this January (Image-4)\" width=\"\" height=\"\" /></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Photo: </span><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">SF Sound</span></em></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://sfsound.org/tape\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The San Francisco Tape Music Festival</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> is a three day ode to everything music, electronic and experiential. America\'s only festival devoted to the performance of audio works projected in three-dimensional space, this unique festival features four distinct concerts of classic audio art and new fixed media compositions by 35 composers from both the Bay Area and abroad. The audience sit in complete darkness and experience the music forming around them, with productions by members of the SF Tape Music Collective and guest composers on the program. This year, the festival features contemporary &ldquo;fixed media&rdquo; compositions by eighteen international composers, including </span><strong>Francis Dhomont </strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">and </span><strong>Natasha Barrett</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> as well as tape classics by </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Pierre Schaeffer</strong> and other favorites. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Find out more on their </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">website</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.</span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /></p>', '2_8.jpg', 1, '2019-12-31 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0);
