(354, 'Museums to visit online', 1, 'museums-to-visit-online', '', 'Museums to visit online', 'Museums to visit online', 'Just because the museums are closed doesn’t mean you have to stop learning from them! In this e-age museums across the world have risen to the challenge of the current state of the COVID-19 pandemic and done the impossible: they’ve gone online.', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Just because the museums are closed doesn&rsquo;t mean you have to stop learning from them! In this e-age museums across the world have risen to the challenge of the current state of the </span><a href=\"https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-nCoV/index.html\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">COVID-19</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> pandemic and done the impossible: they&rsquo;ve gone online.</span></p>', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Just because the museums are closed doesn&rsquo;t mean you have to stop learning from them! In this e-age museums across the world have risen to the challenge of the current state of the </span><a href=\"https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-nCoV/index.html\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">COVID-19</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> pandemic and done the impossible: they&rsquo;ve gone online.</span></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://artsandculture.google.com/partner?hl=en&amp;tab=pop\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Google has partnered with over 500 museums and galleries</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> worldwide to create &ldquo;Google Arts and Culture,&rdquo; an online platform which allows you to browse museum collections online and even use Google&rsquo;s interior </span><a href=\"https://artsandculture.google.com/project/street-view\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Street View</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> to walk the gallery halls (virtually) yourself. We&rsquo;ve put together a list of our favorite picks, but you can also explore museums beyond the Google collection by searching Instagram under the hashtag </span><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/explore/tags/museumfromhome/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">#MuseumFromHome</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> for informative posts and collection insights.</span></p>\r\n<h1><strong><strong>Van Gogh Museum, Amsterdam</strong></strong></h1>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">One of the advantages of e-collections is that you can visit museums beyond your hometown or country from the comfort of your home. Now is finally your chance to check out the famous </span><a href=\"https://artsandculture.google.com/partner/van-gogh-museum?hl=en\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Van Gogh Museum</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> in Amsterdam with Google Arts and Culture. The </span><a href=\"http://www.vangoghmuseum.com/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Van Gogh Museum</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> houses the largest collection of artworks by Vincent van Gogh in the world, with over 200 hundred of the artist&rsquo;s letters, 500 drawings and more than 750 letters in its permanent collection as well as collections focusing more generally on 19th-century art history. The Google Arts and Culture page for this museum offers two online exhibits, &ldquo;</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Which Books did Vincent van Gogh Read?&rdquo; and &ldquo;Vincent van Gosh\'s love life&rdquo; as well as several collections of digital images under categories which include &ldquo;Post-Impressionism&rdquo; and &ldquo;Neo-impressionism&rdquo;, among others. You can even step virtually into the museum itself, with the ability to explore the interior of the gallery via Street View.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h1><strong><strong>MoMa, NYC</strong></strong></h1>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">New York&rsquo;s </span><a href=\"https://artsandculture.google.com/partner/moma-the-museum-of-modern-art?hl=en\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Museum of Modern Art</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> has a page on Google Arts and Culture, too. Founded in 1929, The Museum of Modern Art (MoMA) was the first museum devoted to the modern era, offering a varied collection spanning modern and contemporary art, with over 150,000 paintings, scultures, drawings, prints, photographs, architectural models and drawings as well as today\'s film and performance art. You can find everything from Monet&rsquo;s &ldquo;Water Lilies&rdquo; to Picasso&rsquo;s &ldquo;Les Demoiselles d\'Avignon&rdquo; to works by Andy Warhol in this celebrated museum, which you can now access online. On Google Arts and Culture, MoMa is currently holding the free online exhibit on Sophie Taeuber-Arp as well as several paid exhibits and events, plus you can explore a range of digital collections, including those on &ldquo;Installation art&rdquo; and &ldquo;Sculpture.&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n<h1><strong><strong>Mus&eacute;e d&rsquo;Orsay, Paris</strong></strong></h1>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://artsandculture.google.com/partner/musee-dorsay-paris?hl=en\">Mus&eacute;e d&rsquo;Orsay</a> is one of Paris&rsquo; leading art galleries, built for the Universal Exhibition of 1900 in the former Orsay railway station. This impressive museum displays art from 1848 to 1914, so why not browse their online collections and walk the halls themselves (virtually) through the &ldquo;museum view&rdquo; feature and digital collections available on Google Arts and Culture? The online exhibit, \"From Station to the Renovated Mus&eacute;e d&rsquo;Orsay\", will educate you on the history of the museum while the extensive image collections will broaden your mind with everything from oil paint to canvas to Impressionism collections on display.</p>\r\n<h1><strong><strong>National Gallery, London</strong></strong></h1>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>London&rsquo;s <a href=\"https://artsandculture.google.com/partner/the-national-gallery-london?hl=en\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">National Gallery</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> is home to </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">over 2,300 artworks, with paintings from all major traditions of Westwern Europe from late medieval artists to those of Renaissance Italy to the French Impressionists. Their collections also include many famous works, such as van Eyck&rsquo;s &ldquo;Arnolfini Portrait,&rdquo; Turner&rsquo;s &ldquo;Fighting Temeraire&rdquo; and Van Gogh&rsquo;s &ldquo;Sunflowers.&rdquo; Offering an incredible 12 online exhibitions at the moment, the current focus is on Monet, with exhibits including \"Monet\'s Rouen painting series\", \"Monet: The Water Lily Pond\" and \"Monet\'s Paris\" as well as a range of digital image collections spanning painting across oil, canvas and wood, which focus on the Renaissance.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">There are many more museums and galleries to explore beyond this. In fact, Google Arts and Culture has a wide database which you can search by location using the </span><a href=\"https://artsandculture.google.com/partner?tab=map\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">map</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> or for artworks themselves by </span><a href=\"https://artsandculture.google.com/category/art-movement?hl=en\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">historical era</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> or by </span><a href=\"https://artsandculture.google.com/category/artist?hl=en\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">artist</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. So now more than ever is the perfect time to (art) work from home!</span></p>', 'christian-fregnan-pvyWk-nXDNs-unsplash.jpg', 1, '2020-03-26 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(356, 'Outpost just made moving more affordable than ever', 1, 'outpost-just-made-moving-more-affordable-than-ever', '', 'Outpost just made moving more affordable than ever', 'Outpost just made moving more affordable than ever', 'Skip your security deposit, lock in our lowest rates ever and get one of the most flexible cancellation policies you\'ll find anywhere.', '<p>Skip your security deposit, lock in our lowest rates ever and get one of the most flexible cancellation policies you\'ll find anywhere.</p>', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We all know how stressful it can be to move to a new city. Between questionable Craigslist posts and all the little expenses we tend to forget, it can end up feeling impossible to find somewhere to live, period &mdash; let alone somewhere you&rsquo;ll be happy, with people you&rsquo;ll grow to love.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Even if you do find somewhere that fits the bill, it can end up prohibitively expensive: Between high rents, security deposits and extra fees before you move in, and then buying furnishings and supplies once you&rsquo;re there, costs can rack up quickly.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">At Outpost, though, everything is included in our flat fee, so you don\'t have to worry about utilities, WiFi, Netflix, household supplies or furnishings; all you have to bring is your suitcase. Making moving easy has always been a part of the Outpost ethos, but now we\'re taking it a step further. Here are three ways we\'re making moving to a major city more affordable than ever:&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h1><strong>Skip your security deposit</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A big reason moving is so expensive is because of security deposits! Whether you\'ll only be in the city for a few months or you don\'t know how long you\'ll be staying, you don\'t want to eat up a big chunk of your income with a security deposit you won\'t get back for months.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">That\'s why </span><a href=\"https://bit.ly/2K0FXPy\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">we\'ve partnered with HelloRented</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> to offer zero security deposit for qualified tenants. Qualified members pay a small monthly fee during their time with Outpost Club and never need to think about tying up their funds with a security deposit, allowing them to save more for the future.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h1><strong>Get our lowest rates ever&nbsp;</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We\'ve lowered our rates across New York City, Jersey City and San Francisco for new applicants, allowing you to find your new home without stressing about paying high prices as you navigate moving to a new city. Your rate applies for the length of time of your membership agreement, so you can lock in a lower rate now for the summer, when rent is traditionally at its highest.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">By taking advantage of our new, lower rates, you&rsquo;ll be able to put more of your hard-earned money in savings to make sure you&rsquo;ll always be ready for whatever comes next.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h1><strong>Lock in a more flexible cancellation policy</strong></h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We understand that now, more than ever, life changes quickly &mdash; so we\'re not going to lock you into a contract with no way out. We\'ve revamped our cancellation policy for new membership agreements so you can cancel with no additional fees up until 7 days before your move-in date.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">At Outpost, we want to make moving in and getting started in a new city as easy as ordering a cup of coffee: All you have to do is </span><a href=\"https://bit.ly/2XuDAMT\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">submit your information here</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and you can move in as soon as tomorrow. No hoops to jump through, no red tape, no surprises &mdash; just a new community and peace of mind. We hope to see you here!</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'centralpark.jpg', 1, '2020-03-27 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(365, 'Tips for Working From Home Productively ', 1, 'tips-for-working-from-home-productively-', '', 'Tips for Working From Home Productively ', 'Tips for Working From Home Productively ', 'To limit the spread of the coronavirus, many employers have traded hours in the office for time clocked in at home. So we\'ve swapped our stiff business clothes for comfortable sweats and can do our work from our couches. While there are benefits to working from home, the boundary between work life and personal life has faded — which can make a routine far more difficult to achieve. Here are our tips to stay productive, even from your living room! ', '<p>To limit the spread of the coronavirus, many employers have traded hours in the office for time clocked in at home. So we\'ve swapped our stiff business clothes for comfortable sweats and can do our work from our couches. While there are benefits to working from home, the boundary between work life and personal life has faded &mdash; which can make a routine far more difficult to achieve. Here are our tips to stay productive, even from your living room!&nbsp;</p>', '<p>To limit the spread of the coronavirus, many employers have traded hours in the office for time clocked in at home. So we\'ve swapped our stiff business clothes for comfortable sweats and can do our work from our couches. While there are benefits to working from home, the boundary between work life and personal life has faded &mdash; which can make a routine far more difficult to achieve. Here are our tips to stay productive, even from your living room!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Create a schedule</h2>\r\n<p>Whether you prefer to work your normal office hours or have shifted your day to a later time table, maintaining a schedule you can stick to is a great way to assure that you\'re not over-working or skimping on must-do tasks. One bonus of quarantine is that you\'re able to choose your own hours, just make sure it\'s a sustainable schedule!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Make an office space</h2>\r\n<p>No faster way to lose focus than working from under your blankets or while the TV blares in the background. Find an at-home office space that works for you and keep your supplies, computer and planner in one place, rather than letting your workspace extend all throughout your home. If you\'re able to have a somewhat private area for work that\'s even better &mdash; it will help you limit distractions to get through your work efficiently.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Give yourself a break&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<p>In many office environments employees are given two 15-minute breaks in addition to an hour for lunch. While it can be easy to get sucked into the task at hand, giving yourself a breather and step away from the desk can clear your head and prevent burn out. Take a short walk, prepare a healthy lunch from home or do a stretching routine to break up your day.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Transition in and out</h2>\r\n<p>Where we used to have our commute and early morning Starbucks run to mark the beginning of a workday, now we can just open our laptop. To create a better boundary between your work and personal life, create both a morning and evening routine to bookend your day. Even if you begin your workday at noon, having a \"morning\" routine before you clock in can be a better and more enjoyable way to kick off your day compared to a blaring alarm. Start strong with an at-home workout, freshly brewed cup of coffee or a hearty breakfast &mdash; whatever puts you in the best mood to begin WFH. You can finish off your day with a relaxing shower, healthy dinner or by heading outside for some sunshine.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Socialize</h2>\r\n<p>While WFH, we miss out on the natural socializing we get in an office environment. Make a point to check in with your coworkers &mdash; whether it\'s about an upcoming project or how they\'re keeping busy. A quick Zoom call can break up the monotony of your day and we could all use a bit more social interaction while quarantined.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Tackle a to-do list</h2>\r\n<p>At the beginning of every workday, make a to-do list with the essential tasks. Avoid piling on too many items because it can result in burnout. Instead, stick with the projects you are sure you can do within work hours &mdash; once you\'ve completed the list you can always work on longer-term projects or check off a few tasks for the next day.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Top photo credit: Thought Catalog</em>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'thought-catalog-505eectW54k-unsplash.jpg', 1, '2020-05-25 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(366, 'Our Top 10 Places to Get Takeout in New York City ', 1, 'our-top-10-places-to-get-takeout-in-new-york-city-', '', 'Our Top 10 Places to Get Takeout in New York City ', 'Our Top 10 Places to Get Takeout in New York City ', 'If you\'re tired of scouring through your hodge-podge pantry to find another dinner to cook, are looking to support small businesses or simply just have a hankering for your favorite NYC restaurants, it might be time to order some takeout. Instead of scrolling through Grubhub or Seamless endlessly, we\'ve hand-selected our top 10 spots to order food from — whether you\'re looking for a flavorful Pad Thai or that perfect slice of NYC pizza. Here are our favorite restaurants to get takeout from. ', '<p>If you\'re tired of scouring through your hodge-podge pantry to find another dinner to cook, are looking to support small businesses or simply just have a hankering for your favorite NYC restaurants, it might be time to order some takeout. Instead of scrolling through Grubhub or Seamless endlessly, we\'ve hand-selected our top 10 spots to order food from &mdash; whether you\'re looking for a flavorful Pad Thai or that perfect slice of NYC pizza. Here are our favorite restaurants to get takeout from.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>If you\'re tired of scouring through your hodge-podge pantry to find another dinner to cook, are looking to support small businesses or simply just have a hankering for your favorite NYC restaurants, it might be time to order some takeout. Instead of scrolling through Grubhub or Seamless endlessly, we\'ve hand-selected our top 10 spots to order food from &mdash; whether you\'re looking for a flavorful Pad Thai or that perfect&nbsp;New York slice. Here are our favorite restaurants to get takeout from.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><a href=\"https://www.seamless.com/menu/ayada-thai-restaurant-chelsea-market-75-9th-ave-new-york/1964169\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">1. Ayada</a></h2>\r\n<p>If you\'re in search of delicious curry, noodles or tom yum soup, Ayada is a safe bet to meet all your Thai-food cravings. You really can\'t go wrong with this Elmhurst spot, not to mention that there are plenty of affordable dishes to try.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><a href=\"https://www.seamless.com/menu/zooba-100-kenmare-st-new-york/1897194\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">2. Zooba</a></h2>\r\n<p>This casual restaurant chain hails all the way from Cairo and has some of the best Egyptian eats you can find in NYC. Try out their special Zooba rice pudding, made with halva, pistachios and orange-zested blue agave, or go classic with their cheese hawawshi hot-pressed on homemade baladi bread.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><a href=\"https://www.seamless.com/menu/lena-137-eldridge-st-new-york/555149\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">3. LENA&nbsp;</a></h2>\r\n<p>Classic French food has never been so comforting, whether your favorite is cheesy potatoes gratin or crispy roasted octopus. During quarantine, Lena offers a special where you can get a three-course meal for $27 and eat like a king.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><a href=\"https://www.seamless.com/menu/extra-virgin-259-w-4th-st-new-york/299130\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">4. Extra Virgin&nbsp;</a></h2>\r\n<p>For fresh Italian food that\'s perfectly suited to a warm summer day, grab takeout from this chic spot in Greenwich Village. From lemon-crusted codfish to lobster ravioli, this spot can cater to any craving.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><a href=\"https://www.seamless.com/menu/kopitiam-151-e-broadway-new-york/1027849\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">5. Kopitiam</a></h2>\r\n<p>This Malaysian joint has a colorful assortment of snacks and meals, all at an affordable price. Try out their chilled spicy sesame noodles on a hot summer day, or if you\'re feeling more adventurous, their fried oyster omelet with housemade seafood sauce.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><a href=\"https://www.seamless.com/menu/wolfnights--the-gourmet-wrap-235-bleecker-st-new-york/851332\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">6. Wolfnights</a></h2>\r\n<p>Wolfnights specializes in thick crispy wraps that come with an assortment of dips and fillings. With plenty of vegan, gluten-free and keto options, you can chow down on one of these wraps no matter your diet. My personal favorite is the Mowgli wrap, which is stuffed with charcoal-grilled cauliflower, pickled pineapple and sage aioli all in a fennel seed dough wrap.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><a href=\"https://www.seamless.com/menu/fuku-41-w-17th-st-new-york/2064446\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">7. Fuku</a></h2>\r\n<p>Chicken sandwich&nbsp;connoisseur and fanatics alike, look no further than Fuku. You won\'t be overwhelmed by the menu here because Fuku knows what they do best &mdash; a finger-licking chicken sandwich served on a fluffy potato roll with chickpea butter and habanero puree.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><a href=\"https://www.seamless.com/menu/nish-nushreade-st-88-reade-st-new-york/289779\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">8. Nish Nush</a></h2>\r\n<p>Chili falafel burgers, masabacha platters and stuffed grape leaves alike &mdash; everything on the menu at Nish Nush is delicious and fresh.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><a href=\"https://www.seamless.com/menu/keste-bleecker-271-bleecker-st-new-york/539679\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">9. Keste Bleecker</a></h2>\r\n<p>What would a New York food recommendations list be without an obligatory pizza joint? Keste Bleecker has stellar reviews on Seamless for a reason, and whether you want white or red pizza, they have a slew of&nbsp;pies with toppings like buffalo mozzarella, prosciutto, zucchini and truffle cream.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><a href=\"https://www.seamless.com/menu/bennys-burritos-113-greenwich-ave-new-york/300719\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">10. Benny\'s Burritos</a></h2>\r\n<p>With mouthwatering burritos, tacos and quesadillas for meat lovers and vegans alike, Benny\'s Burritos has options for everyone. Don\'t forget a shaken margarita to&nbsp;complete&nbsp;your meal!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo at top by&nbsp;<a href=\"https://unsplash.com/@charlesdeluvio?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Charles Deluvio</a>&nbsp;on&nbsp;<a href=\"https://unsplash.com/s/photos/take-out-food?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Unsplash</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>&nbsp;</h2>', 'charles-deluvio-D-vDQMTfAAU-unsplash.jpg', 1, '2020-06-15 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(367, 'How to Support Black Lives Matter', 1, 'how-to-support-black-lives-matter', '', 'How to Support Black Lives Matter | Outpost Club blog', 'How to Support Black Lives Matter | Outpost Club blog', 'We include an anti-discrimination clause in our leases that is actively enforced. It is essential that our members always feel welcome in their house and know that there are protections in place in the case they do encounter discrimination or racism.', '<p>Progress and justice mean that we all must be actively anti-racist and allies. The fight against systemic racism is never over, but taking real action is one way we can create change.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>On May 25, George Floyd, a 46-year-old African American man, died after he was pinned to the ground for nearly nine minutes by a white police officer. The killing gave rise to protests in at least 140 cities across the United States and globally in Australia, Britain, France and Germany under the&nbsp;network of Black Lives Matter, an international human rights movement that campaigns against violence and systemic racism toward black people. While Floyd\'s death marked the beginning of these most current protests, black people have always been disproportionately targeted and killed by police officers.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Progress and justice mean that we all must be actively anti-racist and allies. The fight against systemic racism is never over, but taking real action is one way we can create change.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Outpost Club is committed to creating safe spaces and communities across the United States through modern co-living &mdash; we encourage people from different backgrounds to come together and form a diverse community. It is essential that our members always feel welcome in their house and know that there are protections in place in the case they do encounter discrimination or racism. For this reason, we include an anti-discrimination clause in our leases that is actively enforced. We will also be making a donation to Black Lives Matter to support the groundbreaking work of this movement and will continue to work on being impactful allies moving forward.</p>\r\n<p><strong>We\'ve rounded up a few ways that you can contribute to the cause and become a better ally.&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Educate yourself: Understanding white privilege and systemic racism is one necessary step toward becoming an informed ally. Here\'s a great reading list&nbsp;you can refer to; consider creating a book club with a group of friends to hold yourself accountable. We also recommend checking out The 1619 Project, which examines the \"consequences of slavery and contributions of black Americans.\"&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Donate what you can: Whether you\'re supporting a bail fund&nbsp;for protestors who have been arrested, contributing to the&nbsp;Black Lives Matter&nbsp;movement itself, or the National Police Accountability Project, giving money is one great way to show support. For long-term change, consider making monthly donations to a group like the&nbsp;ACLU&nbsp;or local initiatives in your area.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Support black-owned businesses and creators: If you\'re about to online shop or order in from a local restaurant, you can choose to support a black-owned business. Check out these businesses in New York City, New Jersey&nbsp;and San Francisco.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Share on social media: Amplify black people\'s voices on social media by sharing and retweeting their posts. You can also share donation links or petitions to sign on your digital platform!</li>\r\n<li>Go protest: Know your rights, protest peacefully and be prepared. If you\'re trying to find out where your local protests are, check out the Instagram @justiceforgeorge and add your city to the end of the tag (@justiceforgeorgenyc)&mdash; many of these accounts provide live updates on where you can join in.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Sign petitions: If you aren\'t able to donate, petitions are a cost-free way to create change. Here are 30 petitions to start with &mdash; you can also sign here to defund the police.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Photo by <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/@nicolebaster\" rel=\"nofollow\">Nicole Baster</a> on <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Unsplash</a></em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'how-to-support-black-lives-matter.jpg', 1, '2020-06-08 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(368, 'Tips for coliving safely as the economy reopens', 1, 'tips-for-coliving-safely-as-the-economy-reopens', '', 'Tips for coliving safely as the economy reopens', 'Tips for coliving safely as the economy reopens', 'As New York City enters its second phase of reopening, residents are flocking outside after months of isolation under quarantine. While we\'re all excited to get a cocktail to-go from our favorite bar and see friends face-to-face, co-living brings a unique set of challenges when it comes to maintaining a sense of safety during a pandemic. Coronavirus cases are far lower than they were even a month ago, but proper precautions are necessary to protect both you and all your housemates. ', '<p>As New York City enters its second phase of reopening, residents are flocking outside after months of isolation under quarantine. While we\'re all excited to get a cocktail to-go from our favorite bar and see friends face-to-face, coliving brings a unique set of challenges when it comes to maintaining a sense of safety during a pandemic. Coronavirus cases are far lower than they were even a month ago, but proper precautions are necessary to protect both you and all your housemates.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>As New York City enters its second phase of reopening, residents are flocking outside after months of isolation under quarantine. While we\'re all excited to get a cocktail to-go from our favorite bar and see friends face-to-face, co-living brings a unique set of challenges when it comes to maintaining a sense of safety during a pandemic. Coronavirus cases are far lower than they were even a month ago, but proper precautions are necessary to protect both you and all your housemates.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Always wear your mask</h3>\r\n<p>One of the best ways to prevent infection is regularly wearing your mask. Most establishments require that customers wear one while inside and with parks bustling with activity it\'s always better safe than sorry. We recommend a re-usable cloth mask that you can wash frequently. In both <a href=\"https://www1.nyc.gov/assets/doh/downloads/pdf/imm/covid-19-face-covering-faq.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">New York</a> and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.cdph.ca.gov/Programs/CID/DCDC/Pages/Face-Coverings-Guidance.aspx\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">California</a>&nbsp;wearing a face mask when in public is required by law &mdash; as we re-open keeping case numbers low is paramount. Face masks reduce the risk of you infecting or becoming infected by someone with COVID-19.</p>\r\n<h3>Wash your hands</h3>\r\n<p>You might be tired of hearing this, but this recommendation is an essential step to preventing the spread of coronavirus into your communal home. After being outside, wash your hands for at least 20 seconds, making sure to lather up on the backs of your hands and in-between your fingers.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Keep it clean</h3>\r\n<p>After washing your hands, wipe down any surfaces you\'ve come into contact with while outside, including your phone, doorknobs, keys and water bottle. Contaminants can enter the house on you and your belongings, so regularly sanitizing your items will cut down any risk of exposure.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Get outside</h3>\r\n<p>The likelihood of transmission is much lower if you opt for outdoor activities. Instead of meeting up with friends at their home, maintain social distancing and meet up at a park. With the summer months upon us, it\'s a great time to catch some sun and enjoy the outdoors post-quarantine.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>If you\'re looking for more guidelines to keep yourself and housemates safe, check out the <a href=\"https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/daily-life-coping/going-out.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">CDC\'s comprehensive recommendations</a> for every activity, from grocery store protocol to taking public transportation.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo by Macau Photo Agency on Unsplash</p>', 'macau-photo-agency-ZtNIi7HiUQ8-unsplash.jpg', 1, '2020-06-29 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(369, 'Our Favorite At-Home Cocktails to Try ', 1, 'our-favorite-at-home-cocktails-to-try-', '', 'Our Favorite At-Home Cocktails to Try | Outpost Club blog', 'Our Favorite At-Home Cocktails to Try | Outpost Club blog', 'Rather than ordering a drink to-go in a plastic pouch, create a beautiful and summery beverage to share with your Outpost housemates.', '<p>If you\'re looking to amp up your bartending skills, quarantine is a perfect time to test out some new at-home creations. Rather than ordering a drink to-go in a plastic pouch, create a beautiful and summery beverage to share with your Outpost housemates. Especially in the summertime, happy hour truly can be any hour.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>If you\'re looking to amp up your bartending skills, quarantine is a perfect time to test out some new at-home creations. Rather than ordering a drink to-go in a plastic pouch, create a beautiful and summery beverage to share with your Outpost housemates. Especially in the summertime, happy hour truly can be any&nbsp;hour. You can make these recipes without any high-tech bartending tools, but an at-home cocktail shaker kit certainly won\'t hurt.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Cherry Vodka Sour</h3>\r\n<p>Want something tart and simple? This recipe only calls for four ingredients and is perfect for any hot summer day. You\'ll need limeade, tonic water, Knudsen cherries and grapefruit-flavored vodka to get shaking.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Mango Mezcal Margarita</h3>\r\n<p>The smokey mezcal in this blended drink pairs perfectly with the sweet flavor of tropical mango. This recipe only takes five minutes to mix up, but you will need a blender!</p>\r\n<h3>Cucumber Moscow Mule</h3>\r\n<p>There\'s nothing quite as refreshing and light as a Moscow mule, and this recipe has the cool summer addition of a cucumber twist. This drink is best served in a copper mug, topped with some fresh mint leaves and cucumber wheels.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Kahlua Cold Brew Coffee Cocktail</h3>\r\n<p>The only thing better than a creamy cold brew coffee on a hot summer day is one made with Kahlua. You can garnish with chocolate syrup, whipped cream or a coffee syrup flavor of your choice.</p>\r\n<h3>Strawberry Mojito</h3>\r\n<p>If you love a minty mojito in the summer months, try out this strawberry mojito recipe to mix things up. You\'ll need a batch of simple syrup to perfect this recipe &mdash; we recommend making a container full to save in the fridge for coffee and other cocktail recipes.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Grapefruit and Rosemary Gin Cocktail</h3>\r\n<p>Like a classic gin and tonic, but with a twist. It\'s sweet and slightly sour with the grapefruit and a perfect cocktail to share! Use fresh sprigs of rosemary to garnish your cocktail and make it look high-class.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Blackberry Pineapple Rum Cocktail</h3>\r\n<p>This delicious tropical cocktail is simple yet decadent. You\'ll need to make blackberry simple syrup to complete this cocktail &mdash; which can be easily added to other summer drink recipes for a fruity twist.</p>\r\n<h3>Dark and Stormy</h3>\r\n<p>A classic drink for good reason &mdash; this version is made with spiced rum which pairs well with crisp ginger beer. All you\'ll need is dark rum and ginger beer!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Photo by kyryll ushakov on <a href=\"https://unsplash.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Unsplash</a></em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'kyryll-ushakov-lwoTuByIuC4-unsplash.jpg', 1, '2020-06-22 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(370, '9 Netflix Series to Binge-Watch Now', 1, '9-netflix-series-to-binge-watch-now', '', '9 Netflix Series to Binge-Watch Now | Outpost Club blog', '9 Netflix Series to Binge-Watch Now | Outpost Club blog', ' Whether you\'re into gritty true-crime or teen dramas, we have a recommendation ready for you from an endless supply of Netflix shows to binge-watch.', '<p>You might prefer bar hopping and parties to another night in &mdash; but until the quarantine is completely over we still have time to kill and an endless supply of Netflix shows to binge-watch. Whether you\'re into gritty true-crime or teen dramas, we have a recommendation ready for you.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>You might prefer bar hopping and parties to another night in &mdash; but until the quarantine is&nbsp;lifted we still have time to kill and an endless supply of Netflix shows to binge-watch. Whether you\'re into gritty true-crime or teen dramas, we have a recommendation ready for you.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>The Get Down</h3>\r\n<p>Follow a group of teens in the 1970\'s on their adventures through New York City streets, discovering the world of hip-hop and disco along the way. If you\'re missing your favorite dance club and want to immerse yourself in the world of music, this series is for you.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Maniac</h3>\r\n<p>You might think you\'re going crazy in isolation, but it\'s nothing compared to the people in this single season show who are institutionalized before divulging in a fantasy life through induced dreams. Starring Jonah Hill and Emma Stone, Maniac is a quirky and comedic show worthy of a binge.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Queer Eye&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>A popular feel-good show that capitalizes on the satisfaction of a good makeover story. Each season takes place in a different American city as the Fab Five revamp people\'s lives through glorious home makeovers, chic haircuts, newfound cooking skills and most of all, self-confidence. If you\'re in need of a pick-me-up we highly recommend Queer Eye.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Unorthodox&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>Unorthodox is the T.V. rendition of a New York Times bestselling memoir about a young Jewish orthodox woman who endeavors to escape her community after a failed marriage. It\'s a heart-wrenching and beautiful story &mdash; with only four episodes you might just finish it all in one sitting.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>When They See Us</h3>\r\n<p>This series depicts the famous 1989 \'Central Park Five\' case when five black and Latino teens were wrongfully convicted of raping a woman in Central Park. This one-season show is poignant and compelling and a timely pick for those looking for films and T.V. related to police brutality and civil rights.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Mindhunter</h3>\r\n<p>Crime junkies and thriller fanatics alike love Mindhunter, which follows two FBI agents as they interview notorious American serial killers and catalog their psychological patterns. If you\'ve always been a Criminal Mind\'s fan this show is perfect for you.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Big Mouth&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>We all know how incredibly awkward puberty can be &mdash; Big Mouth takes all of our pre-pubescent nightmares and turns them into this R-rated cartoon.&nbsp;This series scored 100% on Rotten Tomatoes for good reason &mdash; it\'s hilarious and chock-full of incredible comedians like Maya Rudolph, Nick Kroll and John Mulaney.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Wild Wild Country</h3>\r\n<p>This docuseries details the exploits of the world\'s most controversial guru, who traveled from India to the Oregon desert to build a city for his fanatic followers. Each episode divulges further into the lives of the guru and his followers with twists and turns that become more bizarre every episode.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Dark&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>If you love a mystery that keeps you at the edge of your seat, watch Dark, a mystery set in present-day Germany. After two children disappear in the woods, four families\' darkest secrets come to light and reveal the truth.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo by <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/@molliesivaram?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Mollie Sivaram</a> on <a href=\"https://unsplash.com\" rel=\"nofollow\">Unsplash</a></p>', 'mollie-sivaram-yubCnXAA3H8-unsplash.jpg', 1, '2020-07-06 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(371, 'Add These Self-Care Tips into Your Routine', 1, 'add-these-self-care-tips-into-your-routine', '', 'Add These Self-Care Tips into Your Routine | Outpost Club blog', 'Add These Self-Care Tips into Your Routine | Outpost Club blog', 'Whether you like a long steamy shower or a healthy homemade dinner, there isn\'t one right way to self-care.  Here are a few ways you can practice self-care every day!', '<p>Whether you like a long steamy shower or&nbsp;a healthy homemade dinner, there isn\'t one right way to self-care. It\'s a time devoted to you, your mental health and physical wellbeing that is just as essential as that scheduled work call and weekly grocery store trip. While we\'re all for a luxurious face mask and home spa, self-care should also include daily habits that give you time to unwind. Here are a few ways you can practice self-care every day!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p>Whether you like a long steamy shower or a healthy homemade dinner, there isn\'t one right way to self-care. It\'s a time devoted to you, your mental health and physical wellbeing that is just as essential as that scheduled work call and weekly grocery store trip. While we\'re all for a luxurious face mask and home spa, self-care should also include daily habits that give you time to unwind. Here are a few ways you can practice self-care every day!</p>\r\n<h3>Write in a journal&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>Sometimes we move at warp-speed, rarely taking the time to sit down and process our thoughts. Journaling can help you get in touch with your emotions, act as an outlet and provides a way to track progress.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Declutter your space</h3>\r\n<p>Cleaning might not be the first thing that comes to mind when you think of self-care, but having an organized space can make the rest of your day feel far more manageable. Put away your laundry, clear out the accumulated glasses and light a candle. Rather than causing you stress, your space can become a sanctuary where you can relax and unwind.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Go outside</h3>\r\n<p>Spending time in nature and soaking up some sunshine is a foolproof way to fit self-care into your day. Whether you\'re biking to work, getting some exercise or reading a book, getting outside can help you clear your head and get some much-needed Vitamin D!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Grab a book</h3>\r\n<p>Whether you prefer motivational books or fiction, reading can inspire you and give you time away from your overflowing to-do list. Relax with a cup of tea or coffee and read a chapter every day (or more if you\'re a true book worm).&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Unplug from social media</h3>\r\n<p>It can be hard to focus on yourself while scrolling endlessly through Instagram. Take some time each day to disconnect from social media and spend that time doing one of these self-care tasks without the distraction of a Twitter notification.</p>\r\n<h3>Get moving&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>Even if you only have fifteen minutes to spare, doing a quick yoga flow or going on a walk can clear your head and allow you time to yourself. Jam out to your favorite playlist, focus on your breathing and tune into your body.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Photo by <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/@anthonytran?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Anthony Tran</a> on <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Unsplash</a></em></p>', 'anthony-tran-8i2fHtStfxk-unsplash.jpg', 1, '2020-07-13 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(372, 'Our Top 10 Places to Get Takeout in San Francisco ', 1, 'our-top-10-places-to-get-takeout-in-san-francisco-', '', 'Our Top 10 Places to Get Takeout in San Francisco | Outpost Club blog', 'Our Top 10 Places to Get Takeout in San Francisco | Outpost Club blog', 'San Francisco has an array of delicious restaurants that cook up everything from Sardinian dishes to a heaping bowl of ramen.', '<p>If you\'re tired of the takeout spot around the corner or looking for your next favorite dinner delivery, we\'ve got you covered. San Francisco has an array of delicious restaurants that cook up everything from Sardinian dishes to a heaping bowl of ramen. Skip the microwave meal and try some of the best takeout and delivery SF has to offer.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p>If you\'re tired of the takeout spot around the corner or looking for your next favorite dinner delivered, we\'ve got you covered. San Francisco has an array of delicious restaurants that cook up everything from Sardinian dishes to a heaping bowl of ramen. Skip the microwave meal and try some of the best takeout and delivery SF has to offer.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.ummasf.com/about\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">1. Um.ma</a></h3>\r\n<p>This spot offers some of the best Korean home cooking and barbeque that San Francisco has to offer &mdash; with everything from savory glazed pork belly to ox bone soup. Most of their dishes are available for delivery or takeout, so you can get your fill of Korean food even from home.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://www.laciccia.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">2. La Ciccia</a></h3>\r\n<p>La Ciccia\'s specialty is Sardinian food made with only the freshest ingredients, perfect for a healthy but delicious summer meal. Try out their oven-roasted prawns or delicious gnocchi next time you have an appetite for Italian food!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://www.elbuencomersf.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">3. El Buen Comer</a></h3>\r\n<p>While the menu at this well-known Mexican spot might be smaller for takeout and delivery, you won\'t be disappointed by their fresh tamales or slow-cooked stews.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://m.facebook.com/PocChucSF/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">4. Poc-Chuc</a></h3>\r\n<p>If you\'ve never had Mayan-inspired food before, now is the time to try. Poc-Chuc\'s dishes are bursting with flavor, whether you get a classic turkey mole or smoky marinated pork.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://www.deliboardsf.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">5. Deli Board</a></h3>\r\n<p>Looking for an SF spot that can whip up your favorite East Coast deli sandwiches? Order from Deli Board for your next work-from-home lunch and chow down on one of their savory and meaty creations.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.yelp.com/biz/chabaa-thai-cuisine-san-francisco\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">6. Chabaa Thai Cuisine</a></h3>\r\n<p>Chabaa offers a range of affordable Thai dishes like tender duck, classic noodle dishes and crispy fried chicken. Whatever you order will be packed with flavor and wallet-friendly.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://mensho.tokyo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">7. Mensho Tokyo&nbsp;</a></h3>\r\n<p>Level up your next ramen with one of the fresh bowls from Mensho Tokyo. Their staple dish is delivered brothless, so your noodles don\'t get soggy in-transit!</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/pg/LaTaqSF/menu/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">8. La Taqueria</a></h3>\r\n<p>Nothing is quite as comforting as a hearty burrito or mouthwatering taco and La Taqueria is known to whip up some of the best in SF. The restaurant is doing takeout during the pandemic &mdash; but be warned, the coveted burritos often mean a long line ahead!</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://www.mandalaysf.com/menu\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">9. Mandalay Restaurant</a></h3>\r\n<p>Mandalay has some of the best Burmese food you can find in San Francisco, with everything from pumpkin curry chicken to mango prawns. If you\'re looking for a dish that will wow your taste buds, Mandalay is a great spot to order from.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.monkskettle.com/order-online/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">10. The Monk\'s Kettle</a></h3>\r\n<p>Monk\'s Kettle has one of the best fried chicken sandwiches around, served with slaw and butter pickles. Try one with their fried brussel sprouts, parm fries or pretzel knots on the side.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Photo by <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/@heftiba?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Toa Heftiba</a> on <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/s/photos/takeout?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Unsplash</a></em></p>', 'toa-heftiba-inDRPMBfX8M-unsplash.jpg', 1, '2020-07-20 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0);
