(374, '8 Summertime Recipes to Try', 1, '8-summertime-recipes-to-try', '', '8 Summertime Recipes to Try | Outpost Club blog', '8 Summertime Recipes to Try | Outpost Club blog', 'While the weather is still hot and days are still long, it\'s time to get into the kitchen to whip up some fresh, easy and seasonal dishes.', '<p>While the weather is still hot and days are still long, it\'s time to get into the kitchen to whip up some fresh, easy and seasonal dishes. From simple avocado salads to chipotle honey chicken skewers &mdash; we\'ve compiled nine delicious summer recipes that are sure to please.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>While the weather is still hot and days are still long, it\'s time to get into the kitchen to whip up some fresh, easy and seasonal dishes. From simple avocado salads to chipotle honey chicken skewers &mdash; we\'ve compiled nine delicious summer recipes that are sure to please.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://juliasalbum.com/avocado-salad-tomatoes-mozzarella-basil-pesto/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">1. Avocado salad with tomatoes, mozzarella and basil pesto</a></h3>\r\n<p>If you\'re looking for a simple and healthy summer dish for lunch or dinner, this seasonal salad has a perfect balance of creamy soft cheese, juicy tomatoes and flavorful pesto.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.thekitchn.com/recipe-spaghetti-squash-with-asparagus-ricotta-lemon-and-thyme-186415?utm_source=pinterest&amp;utm_medium=social&amp;utm_campaign=managed&amp;utm_content=custompin&amp;crlt.pid=camp.CAhorkcVWACY\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">2. Spaghetti squash with ricotta, asparagus and lemon</a></h3>\r\n<p>Rather than a heavy pasta dish with marinara, try this summer spin on a classic Italian dinner. This dish is chock-full of seasonal veggies and fresh flavors and is perfect to share with friends or family.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.mygfguide.com/gluten-free-teriyaki-salmon-sushi-bowl-recipe/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">3. Teriyaki salmon sushi bowl</a></h3>\r\n<p>Instead of ordering your favorite sushi online, try your hand at creating this delicious teriyaki salmon bowl with avocado, edamame, spring onions and sushi rice. You can wow your friends with your chef skills &mdash; and the best part is it only takes 30 minutes!</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://stripedspatula.com/strawberry-balsamic-salsa/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">4. Strawberry balsamic salsa</a></h3>\r\n<p>It\'s time to get creative in the kitchen! Try out this sweet and tangy summertime salsa that pairs perfectly with tortilla chips, on chicken or even alongside your favorite sorbet.</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://belleofthekitchen.com/chipotle-honey-chicken-skewers-easy-summer-dinner/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">5. Chipotle honey chicken skewers</a></h3>\r\n<p>Nothing says summer quite like firing up the grill! These skewers are easy to make and make for an easy yet delicious dinner.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://joeats.net/home/spicy-shrimp-tacos/?utm_medium=social&amp;utm_source=pinterest&amp;utm_campaign=tailwind_tribes&amp;utm_content=tribes&amp;utm_term=721440400_28309432_223869\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">6. Spicy shrimp tacos with charred corn and mango salsa</a></h3>\r\n<p>Skip the taco truck and whip up these delicious spicy shrimp tacos instead! The spice compliments the charred sweetness of the salsa for a mouthwatering combination that will have you going to grab seconds!</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://coleycooks.com/blueberry-peach-crostata/?utm_medium=social&amp;utm_source=pinterest&amp;utm_campaign=tailwind_tribes&amp;utm_content=tribes&amp;utm_term=386010628_10649850_380679\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">7. Blueberry peach crostata</a></h3>\r\n<p>Don\'t forget dessert! This Italian-style tart is simple and sweet, with seasonal fruits that you can find at your local farmers market. Try it with some vanilla ice cream to create a dreamy summer treat.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://feelgoodfoodie.net/recipe/couscous-salad/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">8. Mediterranean couscous salad</a></h3>\r\n<p>This simple and healthy Mediterranean salad only takes 15 minutes to make and can be a perfect side dish, lunch or starter to share. It has a light, zesty flavor and is packed with seasonal vegetables.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Photo by <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/@ahungryblonde_?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Sara Dubler</a> on <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/s/photos/summer-food?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Unsplash</a></em></p>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>', 'sara-dubler-2lG4WEzGmG4-unsplash.jpg', 1, '2020-07-27 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(375, 'Beginners Guide to Journaling ', 1, 'beginners-guide-to-journaling-', '', 'Beginners Guide to Journaling | Outpost Club blog', 'Beginners Guide to Journaling | Outpost Club blog', 'Journaling creates self-awareness and intentionality in your life — it gives you a moment to pause and practice self-care in any setting.  We\'ve compiled some ways to build a daily journaling habit from the ground up. ', '<p>With our busy lives moving at warp speed, it can be challenging to find a time and space to slow down, process our thoughts and reflect. If there\'s one daily habit that could benefit us all, it\'s journaling. Journaling can create self-awareness and intentionality in your life &mdash; it gives you a moment to pause and practice self-care in any setting. It might seem daunting to approach a blank page, so we\'ve compiled some ways to build a daily journaling habit from the ground up.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p>With our busy lives moving at warp speed, it can be challenging to find a time and space to slow down, process our thoughts and reflect. If there\'s one daily habit that could benefit us all, it\'s journaling. Journaling creates self-awareness and intentionality in your life &mdash; it gives you a moment to pause and practice self-care in any setting. It might seem daunting to approach that blank page at first, so we\'ve compiled some ways to build a daily journaling habit from the ground up.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Guided Journal</h3>\r\n<p>For beginners, a guided journal is a great way to get your foot in the door to a full-blown journaling routine. With selected prompts and questions, you can work the muscle of self-reflection without feeling overwhelmed with where to start. You can try out <a href=\"https://www.intelligentchange.com/products/the-five-minute-journal?variant=17743094343&amp;currency=USD&amp;utm_medium=product_sync&amp;utm_source=google&amp;utm_content=sag_organic&amp;utm_campaign=sag_organic&amp;gclid=Cj0KCQjwg8n5BRCdARIsALxKb963l7C-RlnPSPhDoP-7N7EFoidwPwSRtLdOR-5PpDOP9zqzin3zGXIaAt8iEALw_wcB\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">the Five Minute Journal&nbsp;</a>or <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Today-Affirm-Journal-Nurtures-Self-Care/dp/1449495214\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Today I Affirm</a>, which fosters self-care and gratitude in your daily life.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Pick a Prompt</h3>\r\n<p>If you\'re more of a free spirit, but still unsure of how to build your journaling habit, there\'s a plethora of online resources and prompts to kickstart your writing. These<a href=\"https://www.simplyfiercely.com/start-journaling/?utm_campaign=tailwind_smartloop&amp;utm_term=40500882&amp;utm_medium=social&amp;utm_source=pinterest&amp;utm_content=smartloop\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"> four questions</a>&nbsp;are a great place to start:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>How do you feel right now?</li>\r\n<li>Why do you feel that way?</li>\r\n<li>How do you want to feel?</li>\r\n<li>What can you do to feel that way?&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>In case you get tired of those prompts, here\'s <a href=\"https://daringtolivefully.com/journal-prompts\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">119 more</a>&nbsp;that can make your journaling game even stronger.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>What to Write On</h3>\r\n<p>There are no limits to what you can write about in your journal, it\'s a space that\'s free of judgment and that can always evolve over time. Here are a <a href=\"https://healthyhappyimpactful.com/how-start-journal/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">few ways</a> you can use your journal:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Process your thoughts and feelings</li>\r\n<li>Explore gratitude and positivity</li>\r\n<li>Jot down inspirational notes</li>\r\n<li>Set and track your goals</li>\r\n<li>Plan your day&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Reflect and answer questions/prompts</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Build a Habit&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>To make journaling a sustainable and long-term practice, adding it to your daily routine is essential. Whether you like to write over your morning cup of coffee or at night time right before bed, setting aside a time to write can ensure that you don\'t slack off or miss weeks at a time. Start small &mdash; even five minutes each day can benefit you and prevent burnout.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Keep It On-Hand</h3>\r\n<p>Whether you\'re waiting for a delayed subway, on your lunch break at work, or suddenly struck with inspiration for your next project &mdash; carrying your journal with you is a sure-fire way to make sure you never miss out on impromptu writing. You can also keep track of your to-do lists and long-term goals with a journal and have the satisfaction of crossing things off as you complete them!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Photo by <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/@noemieke?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">No&eacute;mi Macavei-Kat&oacute;cz</a> on <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/s/photos/journaling?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Unsplash</a></em></p>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>', 'noemi-macavei-katocz-Af1TEGN2H9Q-unsplash.jpg', 1, '2020-08-11 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(376, '9 NYC Rooftop Bars To Try While It\'s Still Warm', 1, '9-nyc-rooftop-bars-to-try-while-its-still-warm', '', '9 NYC Rooftop Bars To Try While It\'s Still Warm | Outpost Club blog', '9 NYC Rooftop Bars To Try While It\'s Still Warm | Outpost Club blog', 'Rooftop bars have always been a destination to behold, with the hub of the city far below and nothing but clear skies and boozy drinks — what more could you want on a warm day?', '<p>There\'s nothing quite as quintessentially New York City as sipping an Aperol spritz and taking in a gorgeous skyline view. Rooftop bars have always been a destination to behold, with the hub of the city far below and nothing but clear skies and boozy drinks &mdash; what more could you want on a warm day? While some rooftops are still closed, many have reopened with socially distanced tables and plenty of fresh air. Grab your mask, a roommate, and head to a sky-high paradise.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>There\'s nothing quite as quintessentially New York City as sipping an Aperol spritz and taking in a gorgeous skyline view. Rooftop bars have always been a destination to behold, with the hub of the city far below and nothing but clear skies and boozy drinks &mdash; what more could you want on a warm day? While some rooftops are still closed, many have reopened with socially distanced tables and plenty of fresh air. Grab your mask, a roommate, and head to a sky-high paradise.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.refineryhotelnewyork.com/dine-and-drink/refinery-rooftop/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Refinery Rooftop&nbsp;</a></h3>\r\n<p>Located at the top of the Refinery Hotel in Midtown Manhattan, this hotel bar will make you feel like you\'re on a mini tropical getaway &mdash; sans airfare. Some sections of this bar are closed in a glass greenhouse, so you can sip away regardless of an impending rainstorm. With stunning views of the Empire State Building and delicious cocktails on deck, this spot is sure to please any socially-distanced crowd.</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.westlightnyc.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Westlight</a></h3>\r\n<p>This Brooklyn rooftop features stunning views of Manhattan across the East River that are even better to catch during sunset. While their refreshing cocktails are the main attraction, don\'t miss out on their tasty appetizers like fried calamari and spicy chicken empanadas. You can get in without a reservation, but to be safe we recommend booking a table in advance to avoid waiting in line.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.eataly.com/us_en/stores/nyc-flatiron/serra-by-birreria/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Serra Fiorita</a></h3>\r\n<p>If you\'re in search of an Instagrammable spot for your next cocktail sojourn, Serra Fiorita in the Flatiron District is about as picturesque as it gets. The overhead trellis is covered in colorful flowers that also inspired their light and floral cocktail menu.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.timeoutmarket.com/newyork/highlights/we-are-open-again/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Time Out Market</a></h3>\r\n<p>Come here for the rooftop view of the Brooklyn Bridge and stay for the range of mouthwatering food and delicious cocktails below. The Time Out Market is a sprawling food hall that offers everything from the mad-scientist style desserts at Ice &amp; Vice to the seafood creations at Fish Cheeks. While some of the restaurants in the hall have temporarily closed, there are still plenty of spots to grab some grub and a cocktail before heading up to the rooftop.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.230-fifth.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">230 Fifth</a></h3>\r\n<p>Normally this rooftop destination is packed with people in search of a cocktail after their 9-5, but their socially distanced tables have made this location a much more relaxed space to unwind. We recommend checking out their brunch buffet, which runs 12:00-4:00 and offers dishes like Bailey\'s french toast and cheesy omelets.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.thecrownnyc.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">The Crown</a></h3>\r\n<p>For those that want a chill rooftop vibe, check out the Crown atop the Hotel 50 Bowery in the Lower East Side. Though their food menu is smaller than some other rooftop locations, their classic drinks made with high-quality ingredients and a stellar view of Manhattan make this spot worthy of a visit.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.dearirving.com/dear-irving-on-hudson\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Dear Irving</a></h3>\r\n<p>With sweeping 360-degree views of Manhattan and an assortment of both classic and unique cocktails, Dear Irving is a high-class spot to sit back and admire the glory of New York City. Though admittedly one of the more expensive rooftops, the view makes it well worth the price tag.</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.azulrooftop.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Azul</a></h3>\r\n<p>The Azul Rooftop serves up Cuban-inspired drinks and cantina vibes &mdash; along with a stunning view of Lower Manhattan. This rooftop destination has a lounge atmosphere, so it\'s a perfect spot to take a first date or have a relaxing cocktail with your closest friends.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.elsewherebrooklyn.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Elsewhere</a></h3>\r\n<p>This spacious Bushwick dance floor has been converted into a beautiful rooftop location, so if you live in the area there\'s no need to trek to Manhattan to enjoy a cocktail and some views. They\'re only open Thursday through Sunday, so this might just be the spot to unwind after a long week of WFH.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'kelly-sikkema-AgJdd_HgFPw-unsplash.jpg', 1, '2020-08-27 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(377, 'Our Top 5 Things To Do In NYC This September', 1, 'our-top-5-things-to-do-in-nyc-this-september', '', 'Our Top 5 Things To Do In NYC This September | Outpost Club blog', 'Our Top 5 Things To Do In NYC This September | Outpost Club blog', 'As the heat of summer begins to fade and September begins, we can go some zoos, botanical gardens and museums which reopened for the public to enjoy.', '<p>As the heat of summer begins to fade and September begins, we\'re in search of safe things to do in New York City that will allow us to enjoy the end of this season. Though many indoor activities are still restricted, New York has entered phase four &mdash; which means some zoos, botanical gardens and museums&nbsp;have reopened for the public to enjoy. So grab your mask and go explore all that the city has to offer.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>As the heat of summer begins to fade and September begins, we\'re in search of safe things to do in New York City that will allow us to enjoy the end of this season. Though many indoor activities are still restricted, New York has entered phase four &mdash; which means some zoos, botanical gardens and museums have reopened for the public to enjoy. So grab your mask and go explore all that the city has to offer.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.thehighline.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">1. Stroll down the High Line at sunset</a></h3>\r\n<p>We\'ve missed the quintessential New York stroll down the High Line these past few months, but thankfully the beautiful elevated walkway has reopened and is allowing visitors with their free timed-entry reservation system. The High Line offers a unique view of the city&nbsp;from the skyscrapers along the Hudson River and cuts through neighborhoods like the Meatpacking District and Hudson Yards. With flowering gardens, art installations and views down bustling Manhattan boulevards, this converted freight rail is a must-see for any New Yorker. The walkway is only open from 12 p.m to 8 p.m, so we recommend reserving in advance and grabbing dinner nearby once the park has closed.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.nybg.org/nybg-reopens/?utm_source=google&amp;utm_medium=cpc&amp;utm_campaign=reopening&amp;gclid=CjwKCAjw4rf6BRAvEiwAn2Q76tlk76zYV8869OnnEfaKR49E3lGn2ilFyyd97WOZfWn5OUGhXZElVBoCLQAQAvD_BwE\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">2. Explore the acres at New York Botanical Garden</a></h3>\r\n<p>The sprawling 250 acres botanical garden in the Bronx is a perfect destination for those in search of a lush green getaway. From a natural waterfall at the Bronx River to sprawling meadows, the Botanical Gardens are a much-needed escape from the concrete jungle. The gardens are also using a timed-entry ticket system to keep track of visitor numbers &mdash; we recommend buying tickets online to ensure entry!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.moma.org/calendar/exhibitions\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">3. Check out the Museum of Modern Art</a></h3>\r\n<p>Through September 27 you can score free tickets to the MoMA in Manhattan, which usually costs between $14 and $25 each. Each week of timed tickets opens on Friday at 10:00 a.m and are sold out quickly, so set an alarm and get ready to reserve your spot before they\'re gone! Artists like Judd, Felix Feneon and Dorothea Lange are spotlighted in this&nbsp;iconic New York City art museum &mdash; there\'s something for everyone at the MoMA. We recommend reserving a brunch spot nearby afterward so you can sip a latte while contemplating your favorite collection.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>4. Take a trip to the thrift shops in Brooklyn</h3>\r\n<p>If you want to score some signature clothing without emptying your wallet, Brooklyn is rife with thrift stores and vintage spots that make a perfect day trip. Start off at Urban Jungle on Knickerbocker Ave before browsing Le Point Value Thrift, which is conveniently located just around the corner. You can head to Beacon\'s Closet two blocks away for&nbsp;a more curated clothing store experience &mdash; or stop at Dobbin Street Vintage Outpost for some&nbsp;funky furniture finds. Don\'t forget to sanitize your hands before and after entering the stores and wear your mask at all times while indoors!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>5. Sip on a rooftop cocktail&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>There\'s nothing quite as luxurious as sipping on your favorite cocktail on a New York rooftop. Check out our recommendations here (link to last article), with everything from converted Bushwick dance floors to elegant 360-degree views from Manhattan. Grab your closest friends, some mouthwatering appetizers and enjoy a refreshing drink outdoors while the weather is still nice!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo by <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/@simon_bak?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Simon Bak</a> on <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/s/photos/high-line?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Unsplash</a></p>', 'simon-bak-Tr05QjOiVVw-unsplash.jpg', 1, '2020-09-01 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(378, 'How To Adjust To A New Neighborhood in NYC', 1, 'how-to-adjust-to-a-new-neighborhood-in-nyc', '', 'How To Adjust To A New Neighborhood in NYC | Outpost Club blog', 'How To Adjust To A New Neighborhood in NYC | Outpost Club blog', 'Whether you\'re settling into NYC for the first time or are a seasoned New Yorker who\'s ready to try out a new neighborhood, moving is no easy feat.', '<p>Whether you\'re settling into NYC for the first time or are a seasoned New Yorker who\'s ready to try out a new neighborhood, moving is no easy feat. New York City is known for its eclectic atmosphere &mdash; each block different from the next, from the residential neighborhoods of Clinton Hill to the bustling sidewalks of mid-town. You can find hidden gems on your street that will make anywhere feel like home. Here\'s how to get settled in and make the most of your corner of the Big Apple.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>Whether you\'re settling into NYC for the first time or are a seasoned New Yorker who\'s ready to try out a new neighborhood, moving is no easy feat. New York City is known for its eclectic atmosphere &mdash; each block different from the next, from the residential neighborhoods of Clinton Hill to the bustling sidewalks of mid-town. You can find hidden gems on your street that will make anywhere feel like home. Here\'s how to get settled in and make the most of your corner of the Big Apple.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4>Midnight bites</h4>\r\n<p>If you\'re hankering for a pint of ice cream, a deli sandwich, or some falafel over rice, locating the nearest 24/7 one-stop-shop for all your snacking needs is essential. We recommend comparing prices at your three nearest shops to find the cheapest (and closest) eats because none of us are immune to the allure of a midnight snack.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4>Go-to cocktail&nbsp;</h4>\r\n<p>Whenever you\'re in need of a nightcap or glass of wine after a long day at work, your local bar is the best spot to get the job done. Check out happy hour deals and use it as an excuse to meet people from around your neighborhood or invite a friend to see your side of the city.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4>Green spaces</h4>\r\n<p>Though New York might be known as the concrete jungle, most neighborhoods have parks within walking distance so you can take some much-needed time out in nature. This is a great way to get a read on your neighborhood &mdash; we recommend heading over around sunset with a bottle of wine and a good book. Whether it\'s Central Park or Herbert Von King, having a quiet respite from the hustle of the city is a great way to unwind.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4>Scope the subway</h4>\r\n<p>Admittedly some neighborhoods in New York are more convenient to commute from than others, but the best way to get around efficiently is by becoming a master of public transportation. Find your two nearest stations and compare wait times, subway lines and distance from home.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4>One stop coffee shop</h4>\r\n<p>Whether you prefer a fancy and frothed latte or just need a piping hot cup of coffee to go, finding a cafe on your block will come in handy. Most neighborhoods have at least a few in a two block radius, so we recommend scoping out the nearest spots to find your favorite brew. Next time you\'re late for work or in dire need of a pick-me-up you won\'t need to bumble around before finding the best spot for a warm drink.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo by <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/@thoutbox?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Yonghyun Lee</a> on <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/s/photos/brooklyn?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Unsplash</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'yonghyun-lee-du8ofFw7U9E-unsplash.jpg', 1, '2020-09-21 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(379, '6 Amazing Restaurants to Try in Bed-Stuy ', 1, '6-amazing-restaurants-to-try-in-bed-stuy-', '', '6 Amazing Restaurants to Try in Bed-Stuy | Outpost Club blog', '6 Amazing Restaurants to Try in Bed-Stuy | Outpost Club blog', 'Whether you\'re in search of a nearby French bistro that will have you feeling Parisian, some piping-hot Southern comfort food, or mouthwatering Jamaican dishes — Bed-Stuy has a spot suited to your latest craving.', '<p>Along the charming streets of Bed-Stuy there are brownstones, apartment buildings and eclectic eateries with food from every corner of the world. Whether you\'re in search of a nearby French bistro that will have you feeling Parisian, some piping-hot Southern comfort food, or mouthwatering Jamaican dishes &mdash; Bed-Stuy has a spot suited to your latest craving. Here\'s our roundup of the six best restaurants in Bed-Stuy that you have to try.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p>Along the charming streets of Bed-Stuy there are brownstones, apartment buildings and eclectic eateries with food from every corner of the world. Whether you\'re in search of a nearby French bistro that will have you feeling Parisian, some piping-hot Southern comfort food, or mouthwatering Jamaican dishes &mdash; Bed-Stuy has a spot suited to your latest craving. Here\'s our roundup of the six best restaurants in Bed-Stuy that you have to try.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.samuraipapabk.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">1. Samurai Papa</a></h3>\r\n<p>Though this restaurant is only offering delivery and take-out currently, their casual Japanese dishes and an assortment of ramen make a perfect meal to order in. Their dishes are colorful, packed with flavor and will satiate any ramen craving.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.pilarny.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">2. Pilar Cuban Eatery</a></h3>\r\n<p>This family-run restaurant is known for it\'s authentic Cuban food, and is currently open both for takeout and curbside seating. Their menu boasts a selection of cocktails, empanadas and yuca fries, to only name a few. We recommend staying for dessert and trying out their guava cheese pie with an espresso on the side.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.bcrestaurantgroup.com/location/peaches-hot-house-bed-stuy/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">3. Peaches HotHouse</a></h3>\r\n<p>Even during quarantine Peaches HotHouse is bustling with activity &mdash; probably due to their delicious Southern comfort food and signature mason jar cocktails. With dishes like Nashville-style hot fried chicken, catfish mac and cheese and fresh cornbread, you\'ll want to come with an empty stomach so you can sample all they have to offer.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://www.chezoskar.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">4. Chez Oskar</a></h3>\r\n<p>Known for it\'s the laid-back atmosphere, live music and tasty French classics, Chez Oskar is the spot to be if you\'re hankering for quiche Lorraine or a fresh seafood risotto. This French bistro has adapted well to safety guidelines, with plenty of outdoor seating on the sidewalk and under tents. Bring your friends and share a half bottle of wine alongside some delicious grilled octopus.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.bunnybedstuy.com/food\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">5. Bunny</a></h3>\r\n<p>This Turkish neighborhood bistro offers seasonal and memorable bites&nbsp;like su borek with melted gruyere and crispy fried filo cigars. Bunny\'s menu changes frequently, but regardless of when you go you\'re sure to find some flavorful Turkish food that hits the spot.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://tillysbklyn.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">6. Tillys</a></h3>\r\n<p>Tillys offers a variety of delicious Caribbean food along with live music and a great atmosphere. Their Trinidadian chicken stew is bursting with flavor and curry crab and coconut dumplings are a must-try for anyone who stops by. Whether you\'re in search of a great curry or Jamaican jerk chicken, Tillys is sure to satisfy.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>What could be better for a <a href=\"../coliving\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">co living</a> friends than a fantastic Friday meal at a restaurant? Don\'t forget to take care of your needs for food, shelter, and amusement. Of course, you could prepare a delectable dish at home, but this list of eateries speaks for itself!</p>\r\n<p>Photo by <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/@cceee?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Cody Chan</a> on <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/s/photos/ramen?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Unsplash</a></p>', 'cody-chan-GXhmQt6MFX8-unsplash.jpg', 1, '2020-09-24 05:00:00', '2022-11-01 07:32:16', 0, 0, 0),
(380, 'The Best Thrift Shops in NYC', 1, 'the-best-thrift-shops-in-nyc', '', 'The Best Thrift Shops in NYC | Outpost Club blog', 'The Best Thrift Shops in NYC | Outpost Club blog', 'New York City is rife with thrift shops that carry everything from antique jewelry to household knickknacks.', '<p>Whether you\'re looking for a funky jacket for this winter or some vintage jeans to incorporate into your closet, New York City is rife with thrift shops that carry everything from antique jewelry to household knickknacks. You don\'t need to shell out your hard-earned money when there are second-hand gems just waiting to be discovered &mdash; not to mention they come at a much lower cost. Though the city may have plenty of thrift shops, some are overpriced and will cost you the same as a brand-new purchase, so we\'ve rounded up our favorite affordable faves so you can skip all the rest.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>Whether you\'re looking for a funky jacket for this winter or some vintage jeans to incorporate into your closet, New York City is rife with thrift shops that carry everything from antique jewelry to household knickknacks. You don\'t need to shell out your hard-earned money when there are second-hand gems just waiting to be discovered &mdash; not to mention they come at a much lower cost. Though the city may have plenty of thrift shops, some are overpriced and will cost you the same as a brand-new purchase, so we\'ve rounded up our favorite affordable faves so you can skip all the rest.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Urban Jungle</h3>\r\n<p>If you\'re in search of some funky eclectic finds, head to East Williamsburg to browse the sprawling expanse of Urban Jungle. This spot has everything from \'90s dresses to Hawaiian button-ups and you\'re sure to find something entirely unique to add to your closet. Though there\'s plenty to see here, don\'t expect to see modern brands &mdash; this spot has mostly kitschy vintage finds.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>L-Train Vintage&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>With locations scattered all over Manhattan (under the name No Relation Vintage) and Brooklyn, L-Train is a staple for any avid thrifter. They offer a wide selection of graphic tees, retro sweatshirts, sweater vests, jackets and vintage denim that you won\'t find anywhere else, all at a reasonable price tag.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>10 ft Single by Stella Dallas&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>10 ft Single by Stella Dallas has a bit more variety than your typical thrift store, with sections for slip dresses, chunky knit sweaters and even corset tops. The store is divided into two sections &mdash; the front room with cheaper finds and the back fully stocked with high-quality vintage pieces. There\'s a lot to see here, so get ready to hunt for some hidden thrifted treasure.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Buffalo Exchange&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>For those a bit intimidated by thrift shopping, Buffalo Exchange offers a more curated thrift experience. You can find high-end modern brands here for a fraction of the cost, along with affordable basics like jeans, blouses, and sundresses. If you\'re looking to get rid of some items, you can also sell your gently used clothing here for store credit or cash (though they are fairly picky about what items they accept).&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Mother of Junk&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>Head to Mother of Junk if you\'re ready for some home goods and thrifted mayhem. The store isn\'t very organized but has plenty of treasures for decorating your home, from funky glassware to vintage poster prints &mdash; so get ready to dig in.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Beacon\'s Closet&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>Similar to Buffalo Exchange, Beacon\'s Closet offers a curated thrift experience with plenty of modern and trendy pieces you can add to your wardrobe. Though this shop is a bit pricier than your average thrift store, you\'ll cut down on time spent scrounging through racks and racks of vintage goods.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo by <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/@visualsbyroyalz?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Anastase Maragos</a> on <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/s/photos/thrift-shop?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Unsplash</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'anastase-maragos-OCASFPLTnD8-unsplash.jpg', 1, '2020-10-20 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(381, 'Snow Day Festivities for New Yorkers', 1, 'snow-day-festivities-for-new-yorkers', '', 'Snow Day Festivities for New Yorkers', 'Snow Day Festivities for New Yorkers', 'A snowstorm in New York transforms our beloved city into a winter wonderland — the concrete jungle disguised with a frigid blanket of snow. Though our snow day festivities this winter may be limited due to the coronavirus, there\'s more than one way to make the most of the blustering weather. From an at-home cocktail-mixing competition to exploring the knee-deep snowbanks in Central Park, we have a winter activity for every type of New Yorker. ', '<p>A snowstorm in New York transforms our beloved city into a winter wonderland &mdash; the concrete jungle disguised with a frigid blanket of snow. Though our snow day festivities this winter may be limited due to the coronavirus, there\'s more than one way to make the most of the blustering weather. From an at-home cocktail-mixing competition to exploring the knee-deep snowbanks in Central Park, we have&nbsp;a winter activity for every type of New Yorker.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>A snowstorm in New York transforms our beloved city into a winter wonderland &mdash; the concrete jungle disguised with a beautiful blanket of snow. Though our snow day festivities this winter may be limited due to the coronavirus, there\'s more than one way to make the most of the blustering weather. From an at-home cocktail-mixing competition to exploring the knee-deep snowbanks in Central Park, we have&nbsp;a winter activity for every type of New Yorker.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>1. For the foodies&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>There\'s no better way to celebrate a day at home than ordering a three-course meal with a friend, roommate or partner. If you\'re feeling especially fancy you can set up your own at-home restaurant, complete with a bottle of wine and some candles. We recommend trying out new restaurants so you can support small businesses all while digging in on the best eats NYC has to offer. Make sure to give your delivery driver a hefty tip &mdash; navigating the frigid city is no easy feat and your feast will be well worth the splurge.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>2. For the art-lovers&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>Thankfully, most of New York\'s renowned museums and art galleries have reopened&nbsp;amid the pandemic, albeit with timed-entry tickets and limited capacity. Get your tickets online, bundle up and grab your mask before making your way to the Metropolitan Museum of Art, the MoMa, American Museum of Natural History, the Whitney, Brooklyn Museum or Guggenheim. For those that want to make a day of it, map out two or three museums and spend the day exploring New York\'s finest.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>3. For the cocktail enthusiasts</h3>\r\n<p>Stay cozy at home and try your very own cocktail competition with a few social bubble friends or Outpost roommates! All you\'ll need is a small cocktail shaker kit, and each participant can bring the ingredients for their chosen cocktail. Get creative with unique recipes and decorative flourishes before finishing off with scorecards to determine who is a barista-to-be.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>4. For adventurers</h3>\r\n<p>The city\'s parks are especially beautiful when covered in fresh snow, so there\'s no better time to explore than after a winter storm. You\'ll want to bundle up in your warmest gear before trekking through deep snowbanks, making snowpeople or finding the best hill to sled down. If you\'re lucky, you might catch a massive snowball fight like <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/reel/CKzhdBsn5SG/?igshid=xrjq41z9wn7d\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">this one</a> at Washington Square Park. You can also enjoy scenic ice skating at Bryant Park, Rock Center or Wollman Rink in Central Park.</p>\r\n<h3>5. For the fashionistas</h3>\r\n<p>Head to NYC\'s best shopping spots and avoid the crowd thanks to colder weather. Explore the Insta-worthy streets of SoHo or explore <a href=\"../blog/the-best-thrift-shops-in-nyc\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">these eclectic thrift destinations&nbsp;</a>for a wallet-friendly day of shopping. Make sure you\'re prepared with a mask, weather-proof snow boots and a piping hot coffee in hand to keep the cold at bay.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo by <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/@jeffreyblum?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Jeffrey Blum</a> on <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/s/photos/nyc-winter?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Unsplash</a></p>', 'jeffrey-blum-5v1QSY62ZBs-unsplash.jpg', 1, '2021-02-02 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(382, 'NYC\'s Best Outdoor Dining - Manhattan', 1, 'nycs-best-outdoor-dining---manhattan', '', 'NYC\'s Best Outdoor Dining - Manhattan | Outpost Club blog', 'NYC\'s Best Outdoor Dining - Manhattan | Outpost Club blog', 'Though outdoor dining in winter isn\'t exactly ideal, New Yorker\'s know how to make the most of it.', '<p>Though outdoor dining in winter isn\'t exactly ideal, New Yorker\'s know how to make the most of it. With chic private greenhouses, snow-dusted igloos and cozy huts for just you and your friends, you can get out of the house for a delicious meal and experience truly unique dining. Here\'s our selection of the best outdoor setups to check out in Manhattan!</p>', '<p>Though outdoor dining in winter isn\'t exactly ideal, New Yorker\'s know how to make the most of it. With chic private greenhouses, snow-dusted igloos and cozy huts for just you and your friends, you can get out of the house for a delicious meal and experience truly unique dining. Here\'s our selection of the best outdoor setups to check out in Manhattan!</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.lapecorabianca.com/nomad-menus/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">La Pecora Bianca</a></h3>\r\n<p>La Pecora Bianca has an intimate yet safe outdoor setup, with divided tables, a roof and heaters directly above you. Dig in on their mouthwatering rigatoni vodka with fresh basil and sip on a lavender spritz cocktail while catching up with friends.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://cafeteriagroup.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Cafeteria</a></h3>\r\n<p>These socially-distanced tables are set near individual heat lamps and enclosed overhead to avoid any winter gusts. Try out Cafeteria\'s unique creations, like their mac and cheese spring rolls, cornmeal calamari, chicken and waffles and chickpea fries with horseradish aioli.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.qualityeats.com/locations/upper-east-side\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Quality Eats&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></h3>\r\n<p>The private booths at Quality Eats in the Upper East Side are equally charming and warm &mdash; so you can stay cozy while digging in on a delicious veggie burger and curly fries. They have a selection of specialty warm cocktails, a raw bar and steak selection that\'s hard to pass up.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.nomosoho.com/?gclid=CjwKCAiA9vOABhBfEiwATCi7GE9oE27DE7b0tVyoqsJgTF7HM4v39x8achYnlnMgb_5HQ4lgH8FFRhoCDu4QAvD_BwE\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">NoMo Soho</a></h3>\r\n<p>If you\'re feeling luxurious, check out the artistic outdoor setup at NoMo SoHo. We recommend heading to NoMo for a delicious brunch spread, complete with avocado toast, waffle fries, french toast and crispy bacon.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.rezdora.nyc/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Rezdora</a></h3>\r\n<p>New York is known for its Italian cuisine, and Rezdora certainly lives up to the expectations. Whether you\'re keeping it classic with anolini di parma or are craving a juicy sirloin steak, this Flatiron eatery offers it all. Their separated tables are surrounded by heat lamps and have an enclosure so you can dine outside even during the most frigid winter days.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.fairfax.nyc/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Fairfax&nbsp;</a></h3>\r\n<p>Fairfax has an intimate and Insta-worthy outdoor dining set up perfect for your next date night or celebration. These cozy heated yurts are private for your party, so you can relax maskless while sipping wine. Their menu is eclectic, with options like gnocchi, sardine burgers, smoked trout toast and crispy artichokes.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.lolataverna.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Lola Taverna&nbsp;</a></h3>\r\n<p>The outdoor setup at Lola Taverna takes the cake when it comes to aesthetically pleasing outdoor dining. The archways of floral arrangements and fairy lights make this a must-see for your next romantic night out in NYC. Try out their fondue, babaganoush, lamb chop, rice pudding and greek salad.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Photo by <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/@pablomerchanm?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Pablo Merch&aacute;n Montes</a> on <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/s/photos/italian-food?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Unsplash</a></p>', 'pablo-merchan-montes-GFW3dJRiMsQ-unsplash.jpg', 1, '2021-02-05 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(383, '6 Things to Do in NYC This Valentine\'s Day', 1, '6-things-to-do-in-nyc-this-valentines-day', '', 'The Best Places to Ice Skate in NYC | Outpost Club blog', 'The Best Places to Ice Skate in NYC | Outpost Club blog', 'While Valentine\'s Day might look a bit different this year, there\'s still plenty of ways to celebrate in New York City.', '<p>While Valentine\'s might look a bit different this year, there\'s still plenty of ways to celebrate in New York City. Whether you\'re looking for a relaxing day at home or a foray&nbsp;outside for some delicious grub and cocktails, we\'ve got you covered. We could all use a little extra loving this year, no matter if you\'re spending the holiday with a partner or a few friends.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>', '<p>While Valentine\'s Day might look a bit different this year, there\'s still plenty of ways to celebrate in New York City. If you\'re looking for a relaxing day at home or a foray&nbsp;outside&nbsp;for some delicious grub and cocktails, we\'ve got you covered. We could all use a little extra loving this year, whether you\'re spending the holiday with a partner or a few friends.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Staycation</h3>\r\n<p>Get out and plan a staycation in the city, complete with a night at one of New York\'s hotels. There\'s plenty of options, from a wallet-friendly stay at <a href=\"https://www.arlohotels.com/arlo-nomad/rooms/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">the Arlo Nomad</a> to a more luxurious trip to <a href=\"https://www.thebeekman.com/?utm_source=local-listings&amp;utm_medium=organic&amp;utm_campaign=local-listings\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">the Beekman</a> hotel. A change of scenery is just what we need after months of being cooped up at home, especially if you\'re spending the night with your partner. We recommend either ordering a full spread of room service goods or finding an impromptu dinner spot in the surrounding area.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Wine and dine</h3>\r\n<p>Though this year\'s holiday might be anything but traditional, you can never go wrong with a nice meal at one of New York\'s best restaurants. We\'ve rounded up some of the <a href=\"../blog/nycs-best-outdoor-dining---manhattan\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">warmest (and tastiest) Manhattan eateries</a>, so you can skip the endless Yelp search. Whether you want a private yurt to share with your best friends or a five-course meal with your partner, the city has plenty of spots perfect for Valentine\'s Day.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Spa day</h3>\r\n<p>We all need a bit of rest and relaxation and there\'s no better time to schedule some self-care than on Valentine\'s Day. Head to the sprawling&nbsp;<a href=\"https://ny.spacastleusa.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Spa Castle</a>&nbsp;for a facial, massage, sauna session, or simply a long soak in their hot tubs. You can also try out the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://beaire.com/en/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">AIRE Ancient Baths&nbsp;</a>if you\'re in search of some&nbsp;soothing thermal springs. Many spas offer discounted Valentine\'s Day specials for you to share with your loved one or a friend &mdash; but no need to worry, you can still pamper away even if you\'re flying solo this year.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>At-home dinner date</h3>\r\n<p>Food made with love always tastes better, so shower your partner with some V-Day romance by whipping up a delicious dinner. Check out <a href=\"https://rayamaari.com/romantic-date-night-dinners-for-two/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">this roundup</a>&nbsp;of over 43 date night dinner recipes that you can make whether you\'re a cooking novice or nearly certified chef &mdash; our personal favorite is the creamy herb mozzarella stuffed chicken.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Paint and sip</h3>\r\n<p>Gear up with some canvasses, palettes, paint and your favorite bottle of wine for a safe and creative way to celebrate Valentine\'s Day. Paint the same reference image as your partner (or friends) and you\'ll finish with new pieces of art to hang on your wall as a memento of your romantic evening.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Go ice skating&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>Make the most of the beautiful winter weather in NYC by heading out for some ice skating! There are rinks all across the city so you don\'t need to travel far &mdash; just bundle up and be sure to wear a mask! We recommend going before the sun sets and finishing off the day with a warm dessert or drink at a nearby restaurant.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo by <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/@mrthetrain?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Joshua Hoehne</a> on <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/s/photos/valentines?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Unsplash</a></p>', 'joshua-hoehne-xdFOIPRt6R0-unsplash.jpg', 1, '2021-02-09 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0);
