(384, 'The Best Places to Ice Skate in NYC', 1, 'the-best-places-to-ice-skate-in-nyc', '', 'The Best Places to Ice Skate in NYC | Outpost Club blog', 'The Best Places to Ice Skate in NYC | Outpost Club blog', 'While snow is still blanketing New York City, there\'s no better way to enjoy the winter weather than ice skating at some beautifully scenic rinks.', '<p>While snow is still blanketing New York City, there\'s no better way to enjoy the winter weather than ice skating at some beautifully scenic rinks. From Brooklyn to Manhattan there\'s plenty of spots for you to glide away while safe and socially distanced.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>While snow is still blanketing New York City, there\'s no better way to enjoy the winter weather than ice skating at some beautifully scenic rinks. From Brooklyn to Manhattan there\'s plenty of spots for you to glide away while safe and socially distanced. Here\'s our roundup of the best spots to lace up!</p>\r\n<h3>Winter Village at Bryant Park&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>Though Christmas&nbsp;has passed, Bryant Park is still a charming winter wonderland. With pop-up shops, warm drinks galore and an ice skating rink at the center of it all, this Manhattan location is perfect for your next date night or a day out with friends. Be sure to purchase your <a href=\"https://www.timeout.com/new-york-kids/news/skate-reservations-opened-for-bank-of-america-winter-village-at-bryant-park-102920\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">tickets in advance</a> and bundle up! Tickets range from $21-$36 depending on the date and time you select.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3>Wollman Rink</h3>\r\n<p>Central Park is already an iconic NYC landmark, so why not take it to the next level and skate beneath the Manhattan skyline? For newbies, Wollman Rink offers affordable public skating&nbsp;classes alongside the regular public access option. You can skate for $12 on weekdays or $19 on the weekend &mdash; skate rentals will cost an additional $10.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>LeFrak Center at Lakeside</h3>\r\n<p>For one of the most affordable <a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/e/lefrak-center-at-lakeside-ice-skating-weekday-sessions-tickets-130712489575\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">ice skating options</a>, try out the rink at Prospect Park in Brooklyn! Tickets are only $7.50 on weekdays and $11 on weekends, with skate rentals also available for just $8. You can purchase online or in-person, but keep in mind that your session at LeFrak will be timed for 90-minutes.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Industry City&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>Head to <a href=\"https://industrycity.com/2021/01/winter-2020/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Industry City</a> in Brooklyn for their heated outdoor rink, scenic setup and nearby coffee shops for when you\'re craving hot cocoa. The rink is open Thursday through Sunday, so this spot makes a great weekend activity when you\'re itching to get out of the house. Tickets range from $12 to $28 with skate rentals included &mdash; purchase your tickets online ahead of time.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>World Ice Arena</h3>\r\n<p>If you\'re in search of an indoor ice skating rink for those blustery winter days, head to the <a href=\"http://en.worldice.com/rink-protocols/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">World Ice Arena</a> in Queens! The rink is operating at minimum capacity, so make sure you plan ahead to be sure you have a spot. Tickets cost about $25, and they also offer group classes with reservations.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Sky Rink at Chelsea Piers</h3>\r\n<p>You can ice skate at the indoor rink at <a href=\"https://www.chelseapiers.com/sr/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Chelsea Piers</a> year-round. Their spacious venue has sweeping views of the Hudson River along with ample room for all skaters, including figure skating and hockey. Even once winter has passed, this rink is a perfect place to keep your ice skating skills blade-sharp!</p>\r\n<p>Photo by <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/@nadinmario?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Nadin Mario</a> on <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/s/photos/ice-skating?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Unsplash</a></p>', 'nadin-mario-KghjuGP-9n8-unsplash.jpg', 1, '2021-02-11 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(385, 'The Best Flower Coffee Shops in NYC', 1, 'the-best-flower-coffee-shops-in-nyc', '', 'The Best Flower Coffee Shops in NYC | Outpost Club blog', 'The Best Flower Coffee Shops in NYC', 'The Best Flower Coffee Shops in NYC. Follow the link to read the full post on our blog. We write about living in Brooklyn, Manhattan, Queens and other boroughs of New York City.', '<p>There\'s nothing quite as Instagramable as a beautiful bouquet of flowers or carefully crafted latte &mdash; so why not get both? Flower coffee shop combos are popping up all over New York City with signature floral drinks, curated floral arrangements and a setup too cute to skip by. We\'ve rounded up the best shops all around NYC to fuel your caffeine addiction and latest plant obsession.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>There\'s nothing quite as Instagramable as a beautiful bouquet of flowers or carefully crafted latte &mdash; so why not get both? Flower coffee shop combos are popping up all over New York City with signature floral drinks, curated arrangements and a setup too cute to skip by. We\'ve rounded up the best shops all around NYC to fuel your caffeine addiction and plant obsession.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.reminyc.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Remi Flower and Coffee</a></h3>\r\n<p>Whether you\'re looking for a hand-tied bouquet, new plant or a warm rose latte to sip on, Remi Flower and Coffee is the one-stop-shop of your dreams. Their setup is chock-full of greenery, so if you\'re looking for a peaceful place to unwind, this coffee shop\'s unique green oasis is a perfect pick.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.yelp.com/biz/rosecrans-new-york?osq=flower+shop+cafe\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Rosecrans</a></h3>\r\n<p>Head to Rosecrans in Greenwich Village for a delicate cranberry Danish, almond croissant and rose water matcha. In addition to beautiful greenery and carefully crafted coffees, Rosecrans also carries select&nbsp;antique&nbsp;home decor.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://home-coming.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Homecoming</a></h3>\r\n<p>This Greenpoint cafe has an eclectic collection of small bites, warm drinks, art and flowers. The shop is filled with blooming green bouquets, so come to smell the roses and stay for their sweet marzipan latte.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.yelp.com/biz/cafe-flor-new-york-2?osq=flower+shop+cafe\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Cafe-Flor</a></h3>\r\n<p>Come to Cafe-Flor for a flakey ham and cheese croissant, new budding plant, bouquets&nbsp;or even some unique home decor. The reasonable prices at Cafe-Flor make it a perfect spot for your daily cup of coffee.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.bematchaful.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Matchaful</a></h3>\r\n<p>Matcha enthusiasts, check out this Canal Street coffee shop that has all the signature lattes and matcha soft serve you could dream of. With creations like creamy matcha white hot chocolate and vegan rose matcha soft serve ice cream, this cafe has some of the best green tea you can find in New York City.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.plantshed.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Plantshed</a></h3>\r\n<p>Whether you\'re looking for a succulent, matcha latte or custom floral bouquet, this Upper West Side shop won\'t disappoint. Grab a warm drink and browse through their nursery that\'s teeming with cacti, tropical foliage and European-inspired arrangements.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>What could be more enjoyable than a cup of coffee on a lovely day in a lovely city. While an apartment or <a href=\"../student-housing-nyc\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"> off campus houses </a>are fantastic places to be after work or school, don\'t rush home because the atmosphere of a flower coffee shop is unforgettable and deserving of your attention.</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo by <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/@_xotm?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Tania Miron</a> on <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/s/photos/pretty-latte?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Unsplash</a></p>', 'tania-miron-m1L96Q6EVPg-unsplash.jpg', 1, '2021-02-17 06:00:00', '2022-11-01 07:11:59', NULL, 0, 0),
(386, 'Guide to NYC\'s Best Museums ', 1, 'guide-to-nycs-best-museums-', '', 'Guide to NYC\'s Best Museums ', 'Guide to NYC\'s Best Museums ', 'Outpost Coliving Blog article: Guide to NYC\'s Best Museums. Follow the link to read the full post on our blog. We write about living in Brooklyn, Manhattan, Queens and other boroughs of New York City. ', '<p>On frigid winter days during the pandemic, there\'s no better way to escape the house than visiting some of the best museums in the U.S. Most of New York City\'s museums are open with timed-entry tickets and reduced capacity to keep you safe. Whether you want to see Picasso at the picturesque Metropolitan Museum or catch the hottest modern art at the Whitney, the city is brimming with beautiful displays worth checking out.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>On frigid winter days during the pandemic, there\'s no better way to escape the house than visiting some of the best museums in the U.S. Most of New York City\'s museums are open with timed-entry tickets and reduced capacity to keep you safe. Whether you want to see Picasso at the picturesque Metropolitan Museum or catch the hottest modern art at the Whitney, the city is brimming with beautiful displays worth checking out.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://whitney.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Whitney Museum of Modern Art</a></h3>\r\n<p>Located right next to the Hudson River, the Whitney offers eclectic art displays along with sweeping views of Manhattan. The museum features photography, painting and innovative modern art, so there\'s something for just about anyone. Tickets are only available online, so buy in advance before heading to the Whitney.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.metmuseum.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">The Metropolitan Museum of Art</a></h3>\r\n<p>The Met is arguably the most-celebrated museum in NYC, with massive galleries, historic architecture and renowned artists on display like Picasso, Rodin, Michelangelo and Rembrandt. You might need to visit more than once to take in all the art the Met has to offer, as it\'s the largest museum in the United States.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.moma.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Museum of Modern Art&nbsp;</a></h3>\r\n<p>The Museum of Modern Art, more commonly known as the MoMA, is filled with world-famous modern pieces from artists like Vincent Van Gogh, Alfred Barr and Rene Magritte. Be sure to buy your ticket in advance &mdash; and be aware that your time slot only lasts for an hour.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.newmuseum.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">New Museum of Contemporary Art</a></h3>\r\n<p>This Lower East Side museum is the ideal place to discover new emerging contemporary artists from all over the globe. Time and date-specific tickets are required for entry and go on sale roughly one week before the available dates, so be sure to plan in advance if you want to check out this contemporary gallery.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://www.bronxmuseum.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Bronx Museum of the Arts</a></h3>\r\n<p>This museum features over 800 works of 20th century and contemporary art and is located in the Grand Concourse Historic District in the Bronx. Admission is always free to the Bronx Museum, but you have to reserve tickets in advance to ensure safety.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.guggenheim.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Solomon R. Guggenheim Museum</a></h3>\r\n<p>This New York gem is known for its unique architecture, with rounded white walls, high ceilings and skylights that make it a must-see. The Guggenheim is open at 25% capacity, so you\'ll need to purchase a timed-entry ticket prior to your visit.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.amnh.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">American Museum of Natural History</a></h3>\r\n<p>If you\'re tired of typical art museums, check out the Museum of Natural History, which has exhibits on space exploration, dinosaurs and science! Tickets are only available for purchase online, so be sure to buy before you arrive at the museum. New York, New Jersey and Connecticut residents also receive free entry with a valid ID</p>\r\n<p>Photo by <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/@robertbye?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Robert Bye</a> on <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/s/photos/the-met?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Unsplash</a></p>', 'robert-bye-H1T4gvCscTg-unsplash.jpg', 1, '2021-02-23 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(387, 'Cheapest Bottomless Brunches in NYC', 1, 'cheapest-bottomless-brunches-in-nyc', '', 'Cheapest Bottomless Brunches in NYC | Outpost Club blog', 'Cheapest Bottomless Brunches in NYC', 'Outpost Coliving Blog article: Cheapest Bottomless Brunches in NYC. Follow the link to read the full post on our blog. We write about living in Brooklyn, Manhattan, Queens and other boroughs of New York City.', '<p>Once the weekend begins we\'re all in search of the best places to satisfy our brunch cravings. Whether your go-to is some loaded hashbrowns and a signature latte or you\'re just there for the bottomless mimosas, brunch in NYC can be both delicious and affordable. We\'ve rounded up our top picks where you can get the most bang for your brunch.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>Once the weekend begins we\'re all in search of the best places to satisfy our brunch cravings. Whether your go-to is some loaded hashbrowns and a signature latte or you\'re there for the bottomless mimosas, brunch in NYC can be both delicious and affordable. We\'ve rounded up our top picks where you can get the most bang for your brunch.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.sanmarzanonyc.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">San Marzano&nbsp;</a></h3>\r\n<p>We\'re headed to this Italian spot in the East Village for one of the best brunch deals in town. You pay $12 for one hour of bottomless mimosas and $10 for one hour of food, so your grand total for a mouthwatering meal is just $22. Bring your friends and sip away!</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://latinfusionnyc.net/brunch/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Fusion HK Bar &amp; Grill</a></h3>\r\n<p>If you\'re hungry for some Latin food, head to Fusion HK for their huevos rancheros or ceviche. While we certainly recommend the Latin-inspired dishes, Fusion offers classic breakfast foods like pancakes and omelets.&nbsp;For just $22 you get one entree and an hour of bottomless drinks that include mimosas, bloody marys, sangria, screwdrivers or margaritas.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://citizens.coffee/citizens-of-gramercy\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Citizens of Bleeker</a></h3>\r\n<p>For those that love brunch classics like avocado toast, breakfast wraps and belgian waffles, check out the brunch deal at Citizens of Bleeker. You can pay $14 for one hour of mimosas and $13 for food, coming to a grand total of just $27. With locations in Chelsea, Gramercy, Greenwich Village and Soho, so you won\'t need to travel far before digging in.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.pilpilnyc.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Pil Pil</a></h3>\r\n<p>This Spanish wine bar transports you to Barcelona with tapas like croquetas, escaldums de Pollo and pinxtos de chistorra. For brunch you can have three tapas and one hour of bottomless sangria/mimosa/bellini for only $20 &mdash; which makes this the perfect spot for your next boozy brunch.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Who said scrumptious brunches couldn\'t be affordable? Both office employees and students will like these locations. But keep in mind that housing costs can be less expensive as well. Outpost club can provide you with a variety of <a href=\"../coliving\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">co living </a>housing possibilities.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo by <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/@therachelstory?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Rachel Park</a> on <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/s/photos/brunch?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Unsplash</a></p>', 'rachel-park-hrlvr2ZlUNk-unsplash.jpg', 1, '2021-02-26 06:00:00', '2022-11-01 07:15:23', NULL, 0, 0),
(388, 'Spring Activities in NYC', 1, 'spring-activities-in-nyc', '', 'Spring Activities in NYC', 'Spring Activities in NYC', 'Outpost Coliving Blog article: Spring Activities in NYC. Follow the link to read the full post on our blog. We write about living in Brooklyn, Manhattan, Queens and other boroughs of New York City. ', '<p>Springtime is in full swing in New York City, and while the pandemic isn\'t over yet, there\'s still plenty of ways to get out and enjoy the warmer weather. Whether you\'re looking for a romantic date night in Manhattan or daytime activities to enjoy with friends, we\'ve rounded up the best spring activities to try out this year.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>Spring is in full bloom in New York City, and while the pandemic isn\'t over yet, there\'s still plenty of ways to get out and enjoy the warmer weather. Whether you\'re looking for a romantic date night in Manhattan or daytime activities to enjoy with friends, we\'ve rounded up the best spring activities to celebrate the end of winter.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.laduree.us/locations\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Laduree in SoHo</a></h3>\r\n<p>From the front, Laduree might look like another cozy cafe tucked into the scenic streets of SoHo. But out back, this Parisian tea salon boasts a beautiful tree-shaded garden that is especially beautiful in springtime. We recommend heading to the cafe during the day, so you can snap some dreamy photos and take advantage of the sunshine. Grab a cafe au lait, some world-famous macarons and relax in this blooming garden.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.google.com/search?q=bronx+zoo&amp;rlz=1C5CHFA_enUS826US828&amp;oq=bronx+zoo&amp;aqs=chrome..69i57j46i131i175i199i433j0i131i433l3j0i433j0l2j0i131i433i457j0.2593j0j9&amp;sourceid=chrome&amp;ie=UTF-8\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Bronx Zoo&nbsp;</a></h3>\r\n<p>Head to the Bronx Zoo for a quiet respite from the New York City hustle. With wide-open space, animals on display and spring blooms, this is a perfect day trip for a warm weekend. Be sure to reserve a date-specific ticket in advance and bring your mask and hand sanitizer!</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://littleisland.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Little Island&nbsp;</a></h3>\r\n<p>This much-anticipated park on the West side of Manhattan is opening late this spring for all New Yorkers to enjoy. The elevated concrete island sits above the Hudson River and is lush with greenery &mdash; making it the perfect springtime oasis to check out. Bring a blanket, picnic lunch and your closest friends to&nbsp;take in this futuristic and peaceful park.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://hudsonriverpark.org/activities/mini-golf/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Mini golf at Hudson River Park&nbsp;</a></h3>\r\n<p>Whether you\'re an avid golfer or a novice, mini-golfing at Hudson River is a great springtime activity to do with friends. Located at Pier 25, this professional-grade course features waterfalls, footbridges, sand traps and a view of Lower Manhattan, so you can catch a beautiful sunset over the Hudson while golfing.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.centralparknyc.org/locations/belvedere-castle\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Belvedere Castle in Central Park</a></h3>\r\n<p>The Belvedere Castle, located mid-park around 79th Street, looks straight out of a Disney movie with it\'s historic stone walls and spiral staircase. This landmark was completed in 1872, and can be seen rising above Turtle Pond with it\'s elegant pavilions and terraces. Explore the castle inside before enjoying the view from across the pond. This is another spot perfect for a spring picnic &mdash; bring a blanket and some treats for a picturesque view of historic Central Park.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://lunaparknyc.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Luna Park at Coney Island</a></h3>\r\n<p>The amusement parks at Coney Island are an iconic New York City experience for a reason &mdash; with sandy beaches, delicious carnival food and rollercoasters fit for any age group, Luna Park is a destination to add to your list. The park re-opened on April 9th at 33% capacity, so New Yorkers can return to their favorite rides this spring. Be sure to purchase your tickets ahead of time!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.lolataverna.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Lola Taverna&nbsp;</a></h3>\r\n<p>The outdoor setup at Lola Taverna takes the cake when it comes to aesthetically pleasing outdoor dining. The archways of floral arrangements and fairy lights make this a must-see for your next spring date night. Try out their fondue, babaganoush, lamb chop, rice pudding and greek salad.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Photo by <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/@crossingtheline?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Leslie Cross</a> on <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/s/photos/new-york-city-spring?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Unsplash</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>', 'leslie-cross-gQVrjMnr_zE-unsplash.jpg', 1, '2021-04-14 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(389, 'A Day\'s Activities in Williamsburg, Brooklyn', 1, 'a-days-activities-in-williamsburg-brooklyn', '', 'A Day\'s Activities in Williamsburg, Brooklyn', 'A Day\'s Activities in Williamsburg, Brooklyn', 'Outpost Coliving Blog article: A Day\'s Activities in Williamsburg, Brooklyn. Follow the link to read the full post on our blog. We write about living in Brooklyn, Manhattan, Queens and other boroughs of New York City. ', '<p>The streets of Williamsburg, Brooklyn, are lined with bustling restaurants, modern rooftop bars, hip boutiques, vibrant street art and the occasional artist market. Explore this lively and hip neighborhood and discover all the quaint and artistic flourish that the area is known for. Here\'s our roundup of the top places to visit in Williamsburg.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>The streets of Williamsburg, Brooklyn, are lined with bustling restaurants, modern rooftop bars, hip boutiques, vibrant street art and the occasional artist market. Explore this lively and hip neighborhood and discover all the quaint and artistic flourishes that the area is known for. Here\'s our roundup of a full day of activities to see what Williamsburg is all about.</p>\r\n<h3>Begin with brunch&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>To start the day off strong, head to <a href=\"https://www.sundayinbrooklyn.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Sunday in Brooklyn</a>&nbsp;for a delicious meal, latte and a relaxed artistic atmosphere. Dig in on their signature Sunday Pancakes, drizzled in hazelnut maple praline and brown butter, or if you prefer savory, opt for the smoked lox plate. We recommend making a reservation is advance, as this famous Brooklyn lunch spot is almost always booked well in advance.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Daydream at Domino Park&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>One of Williamsburg\'s most frequented green spaces, Domino Park is the perfect place to take in the&nbsp;view while sipping a coffee and catching up with a friend. The iconic Williamsburg Bridge stretches overhead, with the serene East River leading to a sweeping view of the Manhattan skyline.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Shop through the streets</h3>\r\n<p>Williamsburg offers many boutiques and artist markets, making it the perfect neighborhood to window show for eclectic finds. On the weekends, visit <a href=\"Weekend-only indoor market with hip, handmade arts &amp; crafts items &amp; vintage clothing.\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Artists &amp; Fleas</a>&nbsp;to peruse hip and handmade arts and crafts, as well as stunning vintage clothing. For those who love to thrift, be sure to check out&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.buffaloexchange.com/locations/new-york-city/brooklyn-williamsburg/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Buffalo Exchange,</a> <a href=\"http://crossroadstrading.com/used-clothes-stores/new-york/brooklyn/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Crossroads Trading</a> and <a href=\"http://motherofjunk2.blogspot.in/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Mother of Junk </a>for unique pieces you won\'t be able to find anywhere else.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Grab a snack while you stroll&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>If you\'re craving something sweet while you shop, stop at&nbsp;<a href=\"https://levainbakery.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Levain Bakery</a>&nbsp;for a treat to fuel your neighborhood exploration. Whether you grab a cinnamon butter brioche or one of their famous chocolate chip walnut cookies, this bakery won\'t disappoint you with its decadent creations.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Explore the art scene</h3>\r\n<p>While you\'re sure to get a glance at plenty of colorful murals and street art as you explore the neighborhood, the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.wahcenter.net/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Williamsburg Art and History Museum&nbsp;</a>has a diverse collection of artwork and local history worth checking out. Check their website for special events and gallery openings, so you can fully experience all the Williamsburg art scene has to offer.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Catch the sunset at a rooftop bar</h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">At nighttime, you can see iconic views of the Manhattan skyline from rooftop bars like <a href=\"https://www.elitewilliamsburg.com/menu\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Elite Williamsburg,</a> <a href=\"http://westlightnyc.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Westlight</a> and the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://westlightnyc.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Water Tower Bar.</a>&nbsp;Grab a few drinks, a bite to eat and take in the beauty of the surrounding Williamsburg neighborhood and sweeping views.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>Photo by <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/@enzoneti?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Enzo Tic&agrave;</a> on <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/collections/8369806/williamsburg%2C-brooklyn?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Unsplash</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'enzo-tica-kJVaFpO1VQg-unsplash.jpg', 1, '2021-05-21 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(390, 'A Days Activities in Greenpoint, Brooklyn', 1, 'a-days-activities-in-greenpoint-brooklyn', '', 'A Days Activities in Greenpoint, Brooklyn', 'A Days Activities in Greenpoint, Brooklyn', 'Outpost Coliving Blog article: A Days Activities in Greenpoint, Brooklyn. Follow the link to read the full post on our blog. We write about living in Brooklyn, Manhattan, Queens and other boroughs of New York City. ', '<p>At the uppermost edge of Brooklyn, you\'ll find the quaint neighborhood of Greenpoint, where quiet streets are dotted with restaurants, bars, thrift shops and coffee shops. Explore this hip, yet relaxed neighborhood to discover hidden gems and well-established watering holes. Here\'s our roundup of a full day of activities to see what Greenpoint is all about.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>At the uppermost Northern edge of Brooklyn, you\'ll find the quaint neighborhood of Greenpoint, where quiet streets are dotted with restaurants, bars, thrift shops and cafes. Explore this hip, yet relaxed neighborhood to discover hidden gems and well-established watering holes. Here\'s our roundup of a full day of activities to see what Greenpoint is all about.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong><a href=\"../the-greenpoint-house\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Check out our Greenpoint House</a></strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3>Start off strong with a signature coffee&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>Head to <a href=\"https://www.sweetleafcoffee.com/pages/greenpoint\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Sweetleaf Coffee Roasters</a>&nbsp;before doing anything else. Their coffee is hands-down the best brew I\'ve had in New York City, and the eclectic, brick-laden walls make for the perfect spot to read a book or catch up with a friend. I recommend either Rocket Fuel (cold brew, chicory, Vermont maple syrup) for a serious caffeine boost or the Voodoo Child (Vietnamese cold brew with sweet cream) if you\'re feeling sweet.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Picnic at McCarren Park</h3>\r\n<p>On any given day, you\'ll find McCarren Park bustling with activity&mdash;whether it\'s baseball games, outdoor comedy shows or family barbeques there\'s never a shortage of top-notch people-watching. Bring a blanket, some pastries and have your own picnic spread at this lovely Brooklynite hotspot.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Grab a signature Polish snack</h3>\r\n<p>While you\'re in Greenpoint, it\'s a mere obligation to grab some classic Polish food. The neighborhood is home to a large Polish-American community, so you can find an authentic pierogi just around the corner. We recommend Polka Dot, Pyza, or Krolewskie Jadlo.</p>\r\n<h3>Shop through the streets</h3>\r\n<p>From unique <a href=\"https://fengsway.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">home goods stores</a> stocked up with disco balls and vintage furniture to curated thrift shops like <a href=\"https://www.awokevintage.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Awoke Vintage</a>&nbsp;or <a href=\"https://beaconscloset.com/pages/greenpoint\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Beacon\'s Closet</a>, there\'s plenty of eclectic boutiques for you to meander through in Greenpoint. Unlike other shopping destinations like SoHo or Williamsburg, Greenpoint is fairly calm, so you won\'t need to elbow through hordes of people to snag a blouse.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Eat a delicious dinner</h3>\r\n<p>There\'s no better way to end the day than with some bites at a local Greenpoint eatery. Whether you\'re craving Thai, Polish, Vietnamese or a vegan meal, you can find the dish of your dreams in this neighborhood. We highly recommend <a href=\"https://www.diandi.nyc/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Di and Di\'s </a>modern Vietnamese food&mdash;the outdoor seating is always packed for good reason. Their caramel braised pork belly, fried fish sausage bowl, and egg noodles are all worth writing home about.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Catch the sunset at WNYC Transmitter Park&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>Before the day is done, head to the small waterside WNYC Transmitter park for a glorious sunset over the Manhattan skyline. Unlike other waterfront parks, this one isn\'t jam-packed, so you\'ll be able to find a bench and enjoy the stunning view as dusk settles in.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Photo by <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/@mirador9?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Bryan G.</a> on <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/s/photos/greenpoint-brooklyn?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Unsplash</a></p>', 'bryan-g-IuFgf-LncdI-unsplash.jpg', 1, '2021-05-27 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(391, 'Nightlife in NYC', 1, 'nightlife-in-nyc', '', 'Nightlife in NYC', 'Nightlife in NYC', 'Outpost Coliving Blog article: Nightlife in NYC. Follow the link to read the full post on our blog. We write about living in Brooklyn, Manhattan, Queens and other boroughs of New York City.', '<p>After over a year of closures and COVID-induced restrictions, the famed nightlife New York City is known for has re-opened to full capacity. Before you gear up for rooftop cocktails, late-night dance spots, and some much-needed socializing, make sure you\'re fully vaccinated with a record on hand. Then get ready for a summer full of late nights at New York City\'s best spots.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>After over a year of closures and COVID-induced restrictions, the famed nightlife New York City is known for has re-opened to full capacity. Before you gear up for rooftop cocktails, late-night dance spots, and some much-needed socializing, make sure you\'re fully vaccinated with a record on hand. Then get ready for a summer full of late nights at New York City\'s best spots.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.kindregardsnyc.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Kind Regards</a></h3>\r\n<p>For those that want a laid-back, yet funky scene to dance the night away in, Kind Regards just might take the cake. The upstairs bar is great for cocktails with friends and becomes more crowded as the night goes on, while the downstairs area is usually hosted by a DJ, complete with circling disco balls overhead. While the space is fairly tight, it rarely feels uncomfortable&mdash;just enough room to mingle while still being able to break it down.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.ponyboy.nyc/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Ponyboy</a></h3>\r\n<p>This Brooklyn dance club has become a go-to spot for Manhattanites and Brooklyn residents alike, as you can bet that the dance floor will always be lively with great music. Depending on the night, you may need to wait in line outside for a decent amount of time, but we think it\'s well-worth it to experience one of Brooklyn\'s best spots.</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.sixtyhotels.com/destinations/new-york-city/sixty-les/eat-and-drink/make-believe\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Make Believe&nbsp;</a></h3>\r\n<p>Located in the bustling Lower East Side, this aesthetic rooftop bar offers a variety of refreshing summer cocktails that are a great way to begin your evening. On Saturday and Sunday you\'ll find DJ\'s spinning at Make Believe, and the bar will become more of a dance spot as the night goes on.</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.lebainnewyork.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">le Bain at the Standard</a></h3>\r\n<p>For another stunning rooftop location, head to le Bain, where you can catch views of all of Manhattan while sipping a martini. While the drinks are on the pricier side (even for NYC), the views are worth the extra few dollars.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.shortstories.nyc/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Short Stories</a></h3>\r\n<p>Head to Bowery for an incredible DJ set and ample dance floor&mdash;perfect for a night out with a group of friends. This Manhattan eatery transforms into a nightlife scene, so you can grab dinner and drinks before getting groovy.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://moxyeastvillage.com/little-sister-lounge/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Little Sister</a></h3>\r\n<p>Admittedly the most clubby of the bunch, this spot is similar to famed spots like Catch and 1Oak in the Meatpacking District, minus the intense crowds and snaking line. The bar is located flights down in a dimly lit basement that offers both ambiance and plenty of tracks to dance to.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Photo by <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/@jannerboy62?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Nick Fewings</a> on <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/s/photos/nightlife?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Unsplash</a></p>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>', 'nick-fewings-9P1pZy3gwxg-unsplash.jpg', 1, '2021-06-24 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(392, 'Greenpoint, Brooklyn Living Guide 2021', 1, 'greenpoint-brooklyn-living-guide-2021', '', 'Greenpoint, Brooklyn Living Guide 2021', 'Greenpoint, Brooklyn', 'Greenpoint is Brooklyn’s northernmost neighborhood. While once a manufacturing center, today it is known for its nightlife, vintage stores, and historic buildings.', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Greenpoint is Brooklyn&rsquo;s northernmost neighborhood. While once a manufacturing center, today it is known for its nightlife, vintage stores, and historic buildings.</span></p>', '<ul>\r\n<li><a class=\"anchor\" href=\"#Rentals\">Greenpoint, Brooklyn Apartment Rentals</a></li>\r\n<li><a class=\"anchor\" href=\"#Cost\">Cost of Living in Greenpoint, Brooklyn</a></li>\r\n<li><a class=\"anchor\" href=\"#Crime\">Crime: Is Greenpoint Safe?</a></li>\r\n<li><a class=\"anchor\" href=\"#Restaurants\">Restaurants in Greenpoint</a></li>\r\n<li><a class=\"anchor\" href=\"#What\">What Is Greenpoint, Brooklyn Known For?</a></li>\r\n<li><a class=\"anchor\" href=\"#Apply\">Apply with Outpost Club Today</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><em>Greenpoint is Brooklyn&rsquo;s northernmost neighborhood. While once a manufacturing center, today it is known for its nightlife, vintage stores, and historic buildings. Waterfront views and authentic Polish food also make Greenpoint a unique place to live. Plus, it affords easy access to Manhattan by subway, while Long Island City, Queens, an emerging cultural hub, is just over a short bridge.</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong><a href=\"../the-greenpoint-house\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Check out private rooms at Outpost\'s Greenpoint House</a></strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Greenpoint, Brooklyn Apartment Rentals</h2>\r\n<p>In between the commercial corridors of Manhattan Avenue, Franklin Street, and Greenpoint Avenue, Greenpoint is primarily residential. Apartment buildings here are closely packed, but the streets have a cozy vibe and are often tree-lined. It can be hard to believe you&rsquo;re so close to Manhattan, or even the East River, where you&rsquo;ll find a couple of waterfront parks and piers.</p>\r\n<p>The Greenpoint House is just a few blocks from the waterfront. Recently renovated, it has spacious living rooms, hardwood floors, large windows, and basement and backyard amenities. It&rsquo;s hard to find a spacious apartment at a reasonable price in New York City, but we&rsquo;ve found the perfect spot right here in Greenpoint.</p>\r\n<p>Plus, it&rsquo;s only a 2-minute walk to the Greenpoint Ave. subway station, where you can take the G train, transfer to the L in two stops, and be in Manhattan in just 30 minutes. There are also multiple bus lines running through the neighborhood. And when you feel you need a little open space, WNYC Transmitter Park and McCarren Park are just blocks away, as are Bushwick Inlet Park and Marsha P. Johnson State Park.</p>\r\n<div class=\"img_slider\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"img\"><img title=\"Greenpoint, Brooklyn Living Guide 2021 (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/greenpoint-backyard-3.1200x1200.jpg\" alt=\"Greenpoint, Brooklyn Living Guide 2021 (Image-1)\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"img\"><img title=\"Greenpoint, Brooklyn Living Guide 2021 (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/greenpoint-common-area-5.1200x1200.jpg\" alt=\"Greenpoint, Brooklyn Living Guide 2021 (Image-2)\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"img\"><img title=\"Greenpoint, Brooklyn Living Guide 2021 (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/the-greenpoint-house-kitchen-2.1200x1200.jpg\" alt=\"Greenpoint, Brooklyn Living Guide 2021 (Image-3)\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"img\"><img title=\"Greenpoint, Brooklyn Living Guide 2021 (Image-4), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/the-greenpoint-house-bedroom-2_1.1200x1200.jpg\" alt=\"Greenpoint, Brooklyn Living Guide 2021 (Image-4)\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"img\"><img title=\"Greenpoint, Brooklyn Living Guide 2021 (Image-5), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/the-greenpoint-house-bedroom-1_1.1200x1200.jpg\" alt=\"Greenpoint, Brooklyn Living Guide 2021 (Image-5)\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"Cost\" class=\"anchor_block\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<h2>Cost of Living in Greenpoint, Brooklyn</h2>\r\n<p>The cost of living overall in Brooklyn is quite high. For one-bedroom apartments in Greenpoint, the median rent is about $2,600. By comparison, it is $2,500 in Park Slope and around $3,600 in DUMBO. In Greenpoint, the cost of living has risen over the years as the boom in nearby Williamsburg has expanded to other neighborhoods. The average rent overall is above $4,000, making Greenpoint one of the more expensive parts of Brooklyn to live.</p>\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s not uncommon for people, especially students, to look for apartments in Greenpoint with roommates. Waterfront development has driven up costs. Outpost Club is proud to offer solutions for businesses and individuals. Our affordable corporate housing options are suitable for corporate travel and to accommodate people during renovations and relocations. Whether you&rsquo;re a working professional or student, we have affordable apartments in the area that are fully furnished and secured, with utilities, cleaning, and maintenance covered.</p>\r\n<p class=\"img\"><img title=\"Greenpoint, Brooklyn Living Guide 2021 (Image-6), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/greenpoint-brooklyn-living-guide-2021-2.jpg\" alt=\"Greenpoint, Brooklyn Living Guide 2021 (Image-6)\" /></p>\r\n<div id=\"Crime\" class=\"anchor_block\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<h2>Crime: Is Greenpoint Safe?</h2>\r\n<p>Greenpoint is known as a generally safe neighborhood. Robberies and break-ins aren&rsquo;t unheard of, though, so it&rsquo;s best to take precautions whenever you can. The public schools are considered above average and the area is bustling with new activity. You&rsquo;ll find people from all backgrounds mingling in the many restaurants, coffee shops, and bars.</p>\r\n<p>Parts of Greenpoint are still industrial, but there is so much to enjoy along the livelier blocks in the neighborhood. The primary industrial section begins along Greenpoint Avenue past McGuinness Boulevard.</p>\r\n<p class=\"img\"><img title=\"Greenpoint, Brooklyn Living Guide 2021 (Image-7), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/greenpoint-brooklyn-living-guide-2021-1.jpg\" alt=\"Greenpoint, Brooklyn Living Guide 2021 (Image-7)\" /></p>\r\n<div id=\"Restaurants\" class=\"anchor_block\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<h2>Restaurants in Greenpoint</h2>\r\n<p><strong>There are many restaurants to choose from along Greenpoint&rsquo;s busy thoroughfares. Here are just a few of them to get you started:</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><em>Sama Street: 988 Manhattan Ave.</em></strong> &ndash; Provides a choice of Asian-inspired snacks and small plates, and mid-size as well as larger dishes on the high end, so there&rsquo;s always something to meet your price point. The restaurant&rsquo;s open layout and chic decor are inviting, as well.</p>\r\n<p><strong><em>Madre: 214 Franklin St.</em></strong> &ndash; This self-described contemporary restaurant focuses on providing warm service and a relaxed, casual vibe. According to the business, it sources produce, seafood, and meats from local farmers. Entrees include eggplant, octopus, and black bass, plus there&rsquo;s a - great selection of snacks, appetizers, and sides.</p>\r\n<p><strong><em>Five Leaves: 18 Bedford Ave.</em></strong> &ndash; The decor is rustic and there are plentiful food options on the menu. For brunch, you can get avocado toast, pancakes, sandwiches, oysters, and other choices at Brooklyn prices. The \"Sundowner\" menu consists of baked in-house goodies, burgers, appetizers, salads, and desserts while the dinner menu offers a choice of fish, chicken, pasta, and steak.</p>\r\n<p><strong><em>Greenpoint Fish &amp; Lobster Co.: 114 Nassau Ave.</em></strong>&ndash; When you&rsquo;re down for seafood, you can get fresh fish from the counter or dine outdoors at this corner market. Indulge in the raw bar or a cold shrimp cocktail or octopus salad. Maine or Connecticut-style lobster rolls are $30 apiece. Hot dishes range from mussels or fish and chips to a whole steamed lobster.</p>\r\n<p><strong><em>Glasserie: 95 Commercial St.</em></strong> &ndash; Located at the site of the former Greenpoint Glass Works factory built in 1880, Glasserie is just about as far north as you can go in Greenpoint. A sample seasonal menu is provided online, although actual menu choices change on a daily basis. Dinner, brunch, cocktails, and a range of beverage options are available at prices you&rsquo;d expect in the area.</p>\r\n<div class=\"anchor_block\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<h2>What Is Greenpoint, Brooklyn, Known For?</h2>\r\n<p>Besides being young, hip, and trendy, Greenpoint is mainly known for its history. The area, including Williamsburg and Bushwick, was purchased by the Dutch in 1638. It was named for an abundance of trees. During the 1800s, it became a center for glass and pottery making, cast-iron manufacturing, and printing, as well as for oil refineries. It was also a shipbuilding and heavy manufacturing center.</p>\r\n<p>The Monitor, a Civil War gunship, was launched from here in 1862. But Greenpoint&rsquo;s modern history is shaped by the settling of Polish, Russian, and Italian immigrants from the 1880s on, a trend that continued following World War II. Actress Mae West was born in Greenpoint in 1893. Starting in the 1990s, the neighborhood began a transformation as young newcomers sparked a surge in apartment rentals and opening of the small restaurants that line the busy streets today.</p>\r\n<p class=\"img\"><img title=\"Greenpoint, Brooklyn Living Guide 2021 (Image-8), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/greenpoint-brooklyn-living-guide-2021-3.jpg\" alt=\"Greenpoint, Brooklyn Living Guide 2021 (Image-8)\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div id=\"Apply\" class=\"anchor_block\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<h2>Apply with Outpost Club Today</h2>\r\n<p><em>We offer modern coliving at affordable prices in Brooklyn and Manhattan. Options include coliving apartments for working professionals and student housing. A shared housing model allows our members to find housing at reasonable rates compared to local rent prices.</em></p>\r\n<p><em> <a href=\"../online-questionnaire\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Apply now</a>&nbsp;and we&rsquo;ll contact you about pricing, availability, and options; all applicants must complete a rental application so are background checked. You can therefore feel safe making friends as soon as you move in.</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><strong>Browse online or call 833-707-6611 to learn more about our coliving apartments in Greenpoint, Brooklyn.</strong></em></p>', 'Greenpoint,_Brooklyn,_NY,_USA_-_panoramio_(1).jpg', 1, '2021-08-26 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0);
