(393, 'Harlem, Manhattan Living Guide 2021', 1, 'harlem-manhattan-living-guide-2021', '', 'Harlem, Manhattan Living Guide 2021', 'Harlem, Manhattan ', 'Harlem is a well-known neighborhood in the Upper Manhattan part of New York City. It has roots as a Dutch village organized in 1658, and is named after Haarlem, a city located in the Netherlands. The Harlem Renaissance in the 1920s and 1930s gave rise to the Apollo Theater and many other entertainment venues including jazz clubs, cabarets, and dance halls. Today, the neighborhood is known for its many dining hotspots and cultural and historic landmarks.', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Harlem is a well-known neighborhood in the Upper Manhattan part of New York City. It has roots as a Dutch village organized in 1658, and is named after Haarlem, a city located in the Netherlands.</span></p>', '<ul>\r\n<li><a class=\"anchor\" href=\"#Rentals\">Harlem, Manhattan Apartment Rentals</a></li>\r\n<li><a class=\"anchor\" href=\"#Cost\">Cost of Living in Harlem, Manhattan</a></li>\r\n<li><a class=\"anchor\" href=\"#Safety\">Safety in Harlem</a></li>\r\n<li><a class=\"anchor\" href=\"#Restaurants\">Restaurants in Harlem</a></li>\r\n<li><a class=\"anchor\" href=\"#SignUp\">Sign Up with Outpost Club Today</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><em>Harlem is a well-known neighborhood in the Upper Manhattan part of New York City. It has roots as a Dutch village organized in 1658, and is named after Haarlem, a city located in the Netherlands. The Harlem Renaissance in the 1920s and 1930s gave rise to the Apollo Theater and many other entertainment venues including jazz clubs, cabarets, and dance halls. Today, the neighborhood is known for its many dining hotspots and cultural and historic landmarks.</em></p>\r\n<div id=\"Rentals\" class=\"anchor_block\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<h2>Harlem, Manhattan Apartment Rentals</h2>\r\n<p>Harlem consists of numerous beautiful brownstones amidst the hustle and bustle of Manhattan. If you&rsquo;re looking for affordable housing here, The Harlem House has recently been renovated with new appliances, large windows, and hardwood floors. A plethora of historic details have been preserved. With its spacious living area and private bedrooms, this space is larger than most New York City apartments.</p>\r\n<p>We&rsquo;ve covered every detail, right down to cozy furniture, sleek countertops, and real wooden surfaces. Just like our other living options, our Harlem apartments are fully furnished and move-in ready, so you don&rsquo;t have to purchase a whole range of furniture, appliances, and supplies. Utilities are covered too, as we manage all electricity, gas, and water bills. We even have your Wi-Fi covered!</p>\r\n<p>Whether you&rsquo;re in town for school or business, or are starting out looking for the perfect spot to live, Outpost Club has made finding your home convenient. Cleaning and maintenance are managed by our staff. They clean common spaces regularly to save you time and effort. Our apartments are also extremely secure. We&rsquo;ve installed Nest security systems to make sure you are always protected.</p>\r\n<p>Harlem extends from the East River to the Hudson River on the west. Its southern extent borders Central Park, Martin Luther King Jr. Boulevard, and East 96th Street while 155th street marks its northern border. The New York City Subway (including the 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, A, B, C, and D trains), Metro-North Railroad, and numerous bus routes serve the area. In addition to access via local Manhattan streets, the area can be accessed using a number of bridges, including the 145th Street Bridge, Madison Avenue Bridge, and Triboro Bridge.</p>\r\n<div class=\"img_slider\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"img\"><img title=\"Harlem, Manhattan Living Guide 2021 (Image-1), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/galleries/harlem-house-2.1200x1200.jpg\" alt=\"Harlem, Manhattan Living Guide 2021 (Image-1)\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"img\"><img title=\"Harlem, Manhattan Living Guide 2021 (Image-2), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/galleries/harlem-house-8.1200x1200.jpg\" alt=\"Harlem, Manhattan Living Guide 2021 (Image-2)\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"img\"><img title=\"Harlem, Manhattan Living Guide 2021 (Image-3), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/the-harlem-house-kitchen.jpg\" alt=\"Harlem, Manhattan Living Guide 2021 (Image-3)\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"img\"><img title=\"Harlem, Manhattan Living Guide 2021 (Image-4), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/galleries/harlem-house-1.1200x1200.jpg\" alt=\"Harlem, Manhattan Living Guide 2021 (Image-4)\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"Cost\" class=\"anchor_block\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<h2>Cost of Living in Harlem, Manhattan</h2>\r\n<p>Harlem is known for its high cost of living. According to Best Places, it has an overall ranking of 206.7, compared to 120.5 for New York and 100 for the nation as a whole. For housing, Harlem has been given a housing ranking of 348.1; in fact, the median home cost is over $804,000 and the rankings for groceries, utilities, and transportation are high as well.</p>\r\n<p>According to the latest numbers (as of Q2 2021), the median asking rent for Central Harlem is $2,375, which is just a little higher than East Harlem or West Harlem, based on a study by StreetEasy. Fortunately, you can save by applying with Outpost Club and choosing one of our great options. And you can find opportunities to take in Harlem&rsquo;s live music and vibrant nightlife, not to mention cultural cuisine and so much more the area has to offer.</p>\r\n<p class=\"img\"><img title=\"Harlem, Manhattan Living Guide 2021 (Image-5), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/the-harlem-house-move-in-1.jpg\" alt=\"Harlem, Manhattan Living Guide 2021 (Image-5)\" /></p>\r\n<div id=\"Safety\" class=\"anchor_block\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<h2>Safety in Harlem</h2>\r\n<p>Despite its historical reputation for crime, Harlem is generally a very safe place to live. There has been lots of residential development in recent years. Its brownstone-lined blocks are often quaint and just fine for a daily stroll. In fact, Harlem is a great neighborhood to live in and explore. You might even encounter some intriguing street art or a delicious restaurant or pizzeria!</p>\r\n<p class=\"img\"><img title=\"Harlem, Manhattan Living Guide 2021 (Image-6), outpost-club.com\" src=\"../files/uploads/blog/the-harlem-house-move-in-2.jpg\" alt=\"Harlem, Manhattan Living Guide 2021 (Image-6)\" /></p>\r\n<div id=\"Restaurants\" class=\"anchor_block\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<h2>Restaurants in Harlem</h2>\r\n<p><strong>There are many different restaurants to choose from along Harlem&rsquo;s busy thoroughfares. You can frequent a favorite spot or always have something new to try. Some of Harlem&rsquo;s best-kept dining secrets include:</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><em>The Edge Harlem: 101 Edgecombe Avenue</em></strong> &ndash; If you like jerk chicken or jerk seafood dishes, expect to spend around $15 to $20. But if you&rsquo;re on a tighter budget, there are plenty of choices on the brunch menu and dinner menu reflecting a touch of British and Jamaican heritage. The Edge Harlem was established in 2014 to pay tribute to the spirit of Harlem; known for its cozy rustic d&eacute;cor, it is situated in a building where Langston Hughes and other key Harlem Renaissance figures met.</p>\r\n<p><strong><em>The Noodle: 370 Malcom X Boulevard</em></strong> &ndash; The menu is a plethora of spicy cumin and curry dishes, soup noodle dishes, vegetarian/vegan options, dumplings, wontons, and &ldquo;Street Eats&rdquo; like a Scallion Pancake, Bao Slider, and Veggie Spring Roll. Most main dishes are in the $14 to $16 range. And this is just its opening menu; on the restaurant&rsquo;s website, the owners promise new additions to come.</p>\r\n<p><strong><em>Clay: 553 Manhattan Ave.</em></strong> &ndash; The decor is rustic and there are plentiful food options on the menu. For brunch, you can get avocado toast, pancakes, sandwiches, oysters, and other choices at Brooklyn prices. The \"Sundowner\" menu consists of baked in-house goodies, burgers, appetizers, salads, and desserts while the dinner menu offers a choice of fish, chicken, pasta, and steak.</p>\r\n<p><strong><em>Clove Indian Restaurant &amp; Bar: 1592 Amsterdam Ave.</em></strong>&ndash; The menu consists of appetizers, soups, salads, curries, kurma, biriyani, malai, and other Indian delicacies. There&rsquo;s also a vegetarian menu, or you can select from a range of sizzling tandoori dishes and chef specialties. There&rsquo;s a lot to pick from but the prices are fairly standard for New York Indian food. And with a beer and alcohol menu, you can stay for the nightlife too.</p>\r\n<p><strong><em>Belle Harlem: 2363 Adam Clayton Powell Blvd</em></strong> &ndash; Originally opening as a chef&rsquo;s table concept, Belle modified this format with more distanced tables and a covered patio. The menu consists of fresh bagels and pastries and a compact selection of breakfast and lunch items, including an omelet, oatmeal, quiche, or elbow pasta with sausage and broccolini in an herbed garlic cream sauce. And, you can grab yourself a cup of hot chocolate while you&rsquo;re at it!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Sign Up with Outpost Club Today</h2>\r\n<p><em>Outpost Club offers affordable living options in urban areas where rental prices are high. Whether you&rsquo;re a working professional or a student looking for local housing, we can provide options that are most suited for you. We have large, fully furnished apartments throughout Manhattan and Brooklyn.</em></p>\r\n<p><em><a href=\"../online-questionnaire\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Apply now</a> If you&rsquo;re interested in our apartments in Harlem, Manhattan, or any other area and we&rsquo;ll contact you to discuss availability, options, and pricing.</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><strong>Fill out your rental application today to get started. For more information, call 833-707-6611.</strong></em></p>', 'the-harlem-house-move-in-2.jpg', 1, '2021-09-15 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(400, 'How to Stay on Budget in NYC', 1, 'how-to-stay-on-budget-in-nyc', '', 'How to Stay on Budget in NYC | Outpost Club blog', 'How to Stay on Budget in NYC | Outpost Club blog', 'It\'s no secret that New York City is one of the most expensive places you can live. And while that might deter, there are plenty of ways you can save money and still experience all New York has to offer.', '<p>It\'s no secret that New York City is one of the most expensive places you can live&mdash;it ranks as <a href=\"https://www.investopedia.com/articles/personal-finance/080916/top-10-most-expensive-cities-us.asp\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">number one</a> among U.S. cities year after year, and is consistently within the top 10 most expensive places to live <a href=\"https://www.cnn.com/travel/article/world-most-expensive-cities-2021/index.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">worldwide</a>. And while that might deter some eager wanderers from making the Big Apple home, there are plenty of ways you can save money and still experience all New York has to offer.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>It\'s no secret that New York City is one of the most expensive places you can live&mdash;it ranks as <a href=\"https://www.investopedia.com/articles/personal-finance/080916/top-10-most-expensive-cities-us.asp\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">number one</a> among U.S. cities year after year, and is consistently within the top 10 most expensive places to live <a href=\"https://www.cnn.com/travel/article/world-most-expensive-cities-2021/index.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">worldwide</a>. And while that might deter some eager wanderers from making the Big Apple home, there are plenty of ways you can save money and still experience all New York has to offer.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Transportation</h3>\r\n<p>We\'re not above a super-late night Uber ride, but let\'s be real, taxis and shared ride services add up&mdash;and quick. Getting aquainted with the MTA systems is one of the best ways you can save your hard-earned money in the city, as you can get virtually anywhere for the cost of 2.75. We recommend tallying up your monthly MTA charges before deciding if the month pass is worth the cost&mdash;it\'ll be $127 for a month of unlimited swipes or $33 for a week. If you\'re working from home or only taking the train on the weekends you can probably save your coins and purchase individual tickets.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>And in warmer months, biking is another affordable alternative so you can skip the wait times or crowded L train. Buying a bike of your own will be more of a long-term investment, or you can opt for a membership with <a href=\"https://citibikenyc.com/pricing/annual\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Citi Bike</a>, which are stationed all over the five boroughs. A one-month membership is $15, or you can get set-up for a full year for just $179.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Housing</h3>\r\n<p>You\'ll likely end up spending the largest amount on money on housing, as New York is also designated as the <a href=\"https://www.fortunebuilders.com/top-10-u-s-cities-with-the-highest-rents/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">most expensive place to rent</a> in the U.S. Don\'t let that discourage you&mdash;because there are more affordable options out there. The most essential tip is to plan on having roommates, as you\'ll split the apartment cost into a fraction of its original price. We also recommend looking outside of Manhattan for your next home, as it is the most expensive borough for both renting and day-to-day costs. And if you want to save money without skipping out on amenities like furnished apartments, laundry or even in-building fitness studios, co-living spaces are a no-stress way to get settled in the city on a budget.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Food&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>You won\'t want to miss out on the global cuisine NYC has to offer, with everything from vegan Ethiopian eats to flavorful hot pot to try. For meals out on a budget, scour your local listings for happy hours, bottomless brunch or other deals so you can save while still enjoying the city\'s foodie scene. We also recommend straying from the crowds and Insta-famous restaurants if you\'re serious about saving money&mdash;there are plenty of authentic restaurants that won\'t cost an arm and a leg for an appetizer.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>And when it comes time to grocery shop, compare prices from your nearest stores to find the cheapest option. If the nearest stores are all priced at a similar level (and a bit out-of-budget), you may want to trek to the nearest Trader Joe\'s. While not as convenient as walking down the block, you can usually save a significant amount of money on your weekly haul. For produce, always consult your local bodega to get unreal deals on fruits and vegetables. A grocery store might charge you as much as $5 for a container of blackberries, which you can get for around $1 at your nearest market.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Entertainment&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>One of the greatest parts of NYC is the never-ending myriad of places to see&mdash;from namesake museums to the next show on Broadway. You can still experience all the city has to offer without disrupting your budget with a bit of prior planning. Almost every museum in the city <a href=\"https://www.thefearlessforeigner.com/destinations/north-america/united-states/new-york/how-to-save-money-living-in-nyc/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">offers a free or pay-what-you-can day</a>, so you can get access to places like the MoMa or Guggenheim Museum without dropping a dime.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>You can also get your very own <a href=\"https://a069-idnyconlineportal.nyc.gov/IOPWeb/#/EN/NewApplication\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">NYC ID</a>, which unlocks deals, discounts and free tickets to a plethora of events, shows and entertainment throughout the city. It\'s free, and all you\'ll need to qualify is a proof of residence.&nbsp;Browse sites live <a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Eventbrite</a> or the <a href=\"https://www.nypl.org/events/calendar\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">New York Public Library</a> page to find free things to do any night of the week, whether you\'re in a mood for a comedy show or dance party.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Photo by <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/@mathildepb?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Mathilde Paret</a> on <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/s/photos/new-york-city?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Unsplash</a></p>', 'mathilde-paret-7shTDDZ_Bug-unsplash.jpg', 1, '2021-12-19 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(395, 'Cooking Without a Full Kitchen, Microwave Edition', 1, 'microwave-cooking', '', 'Cooking Without a Full Kitchen, Microwave Edition', 'Cooking Without a Full Kitchen, Microwave Edition', 'Just because your kitchen isn\'t outfitted with all the standard appliances doesn\'t mean you can\'t enjoy delicious meals. ', '<p>Takeout and restaurant bills tend to add up &mdash; but what happens when you don\'t have a fully equipped kitchen to whip up delicious meals from home? Before you consult your food delivery apps again, let\'s run through easy ways you can cook from home with only the help of a microwave. This standard, compact and cost-effective appliance can create surprisingly nutritious and satiating meals with the press of a button.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>Takeout and restaurant bills tend to add up&mdash;but what happens when you don\'t have a fully equipped kitchen to whip up delicious meals from home? Before you consult your food delivery apps again, let\'s run through easy ways you can cook from home with only the help of a microwave. This standard, compact and cost-effective appliance can create surprisingly nutritious and satiating meals with the press of a button.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Cook evenly</h3>\r\n<p>It\'s no secret that the dishes you put in the microwave will determine how much time they need to be nuked for. Generally, large, dense or thick ingredients will need more time to heat thoroughly. To prevent food from cooking unevenly, separate large ingredients from the smaller ingredients so you don\'t end up with raw food or unsavory overcooked bits. Another way to hack through this problem is to slice the larger ingredients into smaller pieces&mdash;think large vegetables, meat, and potatoes.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Another key way to ensure your dish cooks thoroughly is to arrange the food in a single layer on a microwave-safe dish, with the thicker or larger pieces away from the center of the dish. When using a microwave, the food at the outskirts of your plate will cook more quickly, so arranging your ingredients intentionally can help you achieve an even cook.</p>\r\n<p>We also recommend cooking in intervals and stirring or mixing to distribute the heat. For small items you can cook at one-minute intervals, while larger ingredients like meat can cook for longer periods like three minute intervals. While this takes a bit more patience then simply nuking your meal for seven minutes flat, it will ensure you don\'t have any frozen or cold portions in the center with steaming hot outskirts of your dish.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Avoid the mess</h3>\r\n<p>Cooking on the stovetop will generally mean a pile of dirty dishes to clean, which is yet another benefit of using a microwave to whip up your next meal. To avoid the dreaded microwave splatter, be sure to puncture foods with a skin like sausages and potatoes&mdash;otherwise they might burst and create a mess. We also recommend covering your dishes with a microwave-safe lid, while leaving a small gap for steam to escape. In addition to preventing splatter, a lid will also ensure even cooking and keep mositure locked in so you don\'t have any dry bites.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Play with the microwave\'s power</h3>\r\n<p>Many of us default to using the factory settings on our microwave while cooking, which leaves out an array of temperature adjustments that can help us cook more precisely using this appliance. We don\'t cook two dishes the exact same way on the stovetop, so why would we in the microwave? Most microwaves wattage can be adjusted using the set power button, so you can tailor your cooking experience to the meal at hand. Nuking with less power is one way to slow down the process, which can actually help you avoid overcooking certain portions of your meal.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Get it delivered</h3>\r\n<p>Feel like no amount of convenience beats opening Seamless? Meal delivery services like <a href=\"https://www.freshly.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Freshly</a> and <a href=\"https://www.cookunity.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">CookUnity</a> will deliver fresh, prepared meals straight to your door, so you can just pop one in the microwave and feel confident you\'re getting the nutrients you need without a bunch of added sugar and over-processing.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Meals to try</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://www.bbcgoodfood.com/recipes/microwave-kale-chilli-eggs\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Kale and chilli eggs</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://www.bbcgoodfood.com/recipes/microwave-mac-n-cheese\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Mac n\' cheese</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://www.bbcgoodfood.com/recipes/microwave-peanut-butter-and-jam-brownies\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Peanut butter and jam cookies</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://lifehacker.com/use-a-bowl-to-cook-crispy-bacon-in-the-microwave-5990895\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Crispy bacon</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://savorysweetlife.com/how-to-microwave-salmon/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Flaky salmon</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://greatist.com/health/surprising-healthy-microwave-recipes#lunch-and-dinner\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Mushroom risotto</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://www.cooksmarts.com/articles/microwaved-broccoli-with-lemon-and-garlic-recipe/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Steamed broccoli</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Photo by <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/@andreaedavis\" rel=\"nofollow\">Andrea Davis</a> on <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Unsplash</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'microwave-cooking.jpeg', 1, '2021-10-06 05:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(399, 'Holiday-Themed Bars in NYC', 1, 'holiday-themed-bars-in-nyc', '', 'Holiday-Themed Bars in NYC | Outpost Club blog', 'Holiday-Themed Bars in NYC', 'No better way to celebrate the holiday season in New York City than visiting an appropriately decorated and festive bar with friends.', '<p>When the weather outside is more than frightful, but you\'re tired of sitting at home in your apartment, there\'s no better way to celebrate the holiday season in New York City than visiting an appropriately decorated and festive bar with friends. Whether you\'re in the mood for a spiked hot cocoa or a gingery Moscow mule, these NYC spots will get you in the spirit.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>When the weather outside is more than frightful, but you\'re tired of sitting at home in your apartment, there\'s no better way to celebrate the holiday season in New York City than visiting an appropriately decorated and festive bar with friends. Whether you\'re in the mood for a spiked hot cocoa or a gingery Moscow mule, these NYC spots will get you in the spirit.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Oscar Wilde:</strong>&nbsp;Oscar Wilde has a well-known reputation amongst festive NYC bars for its rotation of incredible decorations and ornate Victorian interior. This spot is busy even on weeknights, so come with friends and snag a table early.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Sippin Santa:&nbsp;</strong>This themed pop-up destination at Boilermaker is where Tiki-drinks meet winter festivities for a charmingly unique holiday bar experience.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Lillies Victorian:&nbsp;</strong>This lavish Victorian bar trades out kitschy Christmas decor with elegant details and a stunning interior. Book a table in advance, or even head in early for a boozy and glamorous brunch.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Bell Book and Candle:</strong> Head to the West Village and visit this intimate eatery that offers American fare and seasonal cocktails like the \"Under the Mistletoe\", which features Bombay, lemon, raspbery and eggwhite, or the \"Scrooged\", which is concocted of rosemary-infudes mezcal, jalapeno infused tequila, lime, cucumber and agave.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Miracle on 9th:&nbsp;</strong>Festive holiday cocktails make even the coldest winter days more bearable, and Miracle on 9th\'s selection of drinks doesn\'t disappoint. With holiday music and kitschy decor, sipping a drink here makes you feel right at home.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Pete\'s Tavern:&nbsp;</strong>For a cozy and laidback night out, head to Pete\'s. This retro bar has been serving New Yorkers since 1829 and boasts vintage decor, delicious bites and a ceiling filled with red Christmas lights.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Molly\'s:&nbsp;</strong>If you\'re a fan of classic Irish pubs, Molly\'s pints, Shepherd\'s Pie and wood-burning fireplace is an ideal spot to spend a frigid winter evening.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Chalet de Ning:&nbsp;</strong>For a refined, yet spirited holiday destination, head to the Swiss-inspired Chalet de Ning on the Peninsula Hotel\'s Rooftop. The igloo enclosure keeps you cozy while you enjoy the Manhattan skyline and a decadent cocktail.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Papillon:&nbsp;</strong>While Papillon might not have holiday-themed drinks, their extensive decor more than makes up for it.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Rolf\'s:&nbsp;</strong>If the category is holiday decor, Rolf\'s is a clear winner. The ornate holiday landscape looks straight out a movie, with greenery, ornaments and twinkling lights everywhere you look.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Ophelia\'s at the Beekman:&nbsp;</strong>This chic holiday spot has picturesque icicles hanging from the ceiling and minimal, yet glamorous festive displays&mdash;making it a romantic date night spot or place to celebrate a special occasion.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Photo by <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/@heftiba?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Toa Heftiba</a> on <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/s/photos/christmas-drink?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Unsplash</a></p>', 'toa-heftiba-1CAFw4Yz_4w-unsplash.jpg', 1, '2021-12-10 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(398, '15 Cozy Bars in NYC', 1, '15-cozy-bars-in-nyc', '', '15 Cozy Bars in NYC | Outpost Club blog', '15 Cozy Bars in NYC | Outpost Club blog', 'Whether you\'re in search of a new go-to datenight spot or simple place to sip cocktails and read a book, New York City has no shortage of cocktail lounges, bars and pubs that make for a cozy night out.', '<p>Whether you\'re in search of a new go-to datenight spot or simple place&nbsp;to sip cocktails and read a book, New York City has no shortage of cocktail lounges, bars and pubs that make for a cozy night out. From vintage-inspired destinations in the Upper East Side to neighborhood favorites in Bushwick, these venerated city bars are favorites for good reason.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>Whether you\'re in search of a new go-to datenight spot or simple place&nbsp;to sip cocktails and read a book, New York City has no shortage of cocktail lounges, bars and pubs that make for a cozy night out. From vintage-inspired destinations in the Upper East Side to neighborhood favorites in Bushwick, these venerated city bars are favorites for good reason.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>The Back Room (LES):</strong> This bar-meets-speakeasy boasts a brilliantly moody yet&nbsp;alluring aesthetic that makes it a cozy spot for a weekday drink. Cozy up next to the fireplace with one of their teacup cocktails for a warm and boozy respite.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Achilles Heel (Greenpoint):</strong> Head to Achilles Heel for refreshing cocktails, a crackling fireplace and live piano music in an intimate setting.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Livingston Manor (Downtown Brooklyn):</strong> While this bar can become lively on weekend nights, on weekdays it offers a relaxed atmosphere and diverse cocktail menu.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Black Mountain Wine House (Carroll Gardens):</strong> New York is far-removed from any mountain retreat, but stumbling into this cabin-inspired wine bar will make you feel as if you\'ve briefly escaped the city. Grab a snack and glass of wine before snagging a seat by the fireplace.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>The Bowery Lobby (NoHo):</strong> With an authentic fire place, elegant wooden interior and cozy furniture to curl up on, this hotel lobby is the perfect place to drink a glamorous cocktail alone or with friends.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Valerie (Times Square):</strong> This luxe bar has a stunning retro interior, with craft cocktails to sip while sitting at the bar.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Left Hand Path (Bushwick):</strong> For those with a flair for the eccentric or quirky, head to Left Hand Path, where they serve up a unique cocktail selection and comfort food along with a homey aesthetic.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Black Rabbit (Greenpoint):</strong> Who said a pub can\'t be charming? Whether you head here with friends or solo, you might catch their occasional live music or trivia nights.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Auction House (Upper East Side):</strong> For anyone who loves vintage decor and cocktails, the Auction House\'s warm interior feels like the living room of a historic (and dramatic) mansion.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Garfunkel\'s (LES):</strong> If you\'re in the mood for a romantic&nbsp;and historic joint, Garfunkel\'s speakeasy is the ideal spot for your next date night&mdash;the cozy dark interior is perfect&nbsp;for bleak winter evenings. We recommend making a reservation in advance.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Rose Bar (Gramercy):</strong> Aptly named after its predominantly pink and red interior, this retro-style bar is great for a girl\'s night out or relaxed drinks with friends&mdash;though it will get more crowded after midnight.</p>\r\n<p><strong>The Immigrant (East Village):</strong> This neighborhood bar serves up cocktails along with a wide selection of wines. Cozy up to the bar alone or bring your next date here for a relaxed, yet homey atmosphere.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Ascent Lounge (Lincoln Square):</strong> Glimmering chandeliers, elegant decor and a sweeping view of Central Park make this cocktail lounge a glamorous place to get a post-work cocktail.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Tiny\'s &amp; the Bar Upstairs (TriBeCa):</strong> An equally romantic and rustic destination located in a historic brownstone, with three unique floors to explore throughout your evening.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Entwine (West Village):</strong> If you\'re in search of a classic and laid-back bar, Entwine offers delicious eats and a range of cocktails in an intimate atmosphere.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Photo by <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/@louishansel\" rel=\"nofollow\">Louis Hansel</a> on <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Unsplash</a></em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'louis-hansel-yLUvnCFI500-unsplash (1).jpg', 1, '2021-11-30 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(401, '5 Tips For Nailing New Year\'s Resolutions', 1, '5-tips-for-nailing-new-years-resolutions', '', '5 Tips For Nailing New Year\'s Resolutions | Outpost Club blog', '5 Tips For Nailing New Year\'s Resolutions | Outpost Club blog', 'With a few strategic tips and steps, you can forge forward into your resolutions with the confidence that they\'ll last. Here\'s our top five tips to keep your resolutions this year. ', '<p>Once the clock strikes midnight on December 31st, we&nbsp;welcome a New Year, filled with possibility and hope. And with some dedication, many set out to accomplish new goals in the form of resolutions. Whether it be to finally get in the gym on a consistent schedule or reading at least one book per month, the conquest of becoming a better version of ourself often coincides with January 1st. And while you can truly make lifestyle changes any time of year, the holiday is a momentous occasion that can act as a symbolic kickoff into a new journey.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>Once the clock strikes midnight on December 31st, we&nbsp;welcome a New Year, filled with possibility and hope. And with some dedication, many set out to accomplish new goals in the form of resolutions. Whether it be to finally get in the gym on a consistent schedule or reading at least one book per month, the conquest of becoming a better version of ourself often coincides with January 1st. And while you can truly make lifestyle changes any time of year, the holiday is a momentous occasion that can act as a symbolic kickoff into a new journey.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>It might be easy to set New Year\'s resolutions&mdash;but the true challenge comes as days, weeks and months go by&mdash;as motivation fades and old habits attempt to resurface. With a few strategic tips and steps, you can forge forward into your resolutions with the confidence that they\'ll last. Here\'s our top five tips to keep your resolutions this year.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Choose pinpointed goals</h3>\r\n<p>Lofty goals like&nbsp;<em>get fit&nbsp;</em>or&nbsp;<em>start a side hustle&nbsp;</em>can be aspirational, sure, but when push comes to shove it\'s rather challenging to achieve these lofty and fairly general goals. You\'re better off choosing a pinpointed resolution within a broader category, such as eating four vegetables per day, lifting weights four times a week or running your first marathon. These resolutions aren\'t subjective, so they\'re easier to quantify, track and monitor.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Hold yourself accountable</h3>\r\n<p>If you\'re the only person who knows about your New Year\'s resolution you\'re less likely to see it come to fruition.&nbsp;Make a promise to your friends, family, or even social media followers who will keep you accountable throughout the year, and even offer positive reinforcement when you give updates on your success. While avoiding the embarassment of failure might not be the most noble of motivations, it can certainly keep you from sliding into too great of a slump that you forgo your resolutions completely.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Create a plan</h3>\r\n<p>A concrete goal is a great place to start, but can also feel daunting if it\'s an entirely new habit or skill you\'re trying to pick up. This is where prior planning comes in hand&mdash;so you can design a toolbox that can get you from point A to point B with as little distractions as possible. For example, if your goal is to read one book per month, you could plan by picking your first four books and designating a certain time per day for reading (whether it be 15 minutes while you drink coffee in the morning or reading 20 pages per day before bed). Creating incremental changes will help you create long-term habits and patterns as they become established within your routine. Plus, planning out&nbsp;<em>how&nbsp;</em>you\'ll achieve this goal will save you from the stress of realizing you\'re 12 pages in to a new novel on the last day of the month.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Find inspiration that will last</h3>\r\n<p>This can look different depending on your goals&mdash;but when January is over and your new year rigor is fading, refer to external inspiration to keep motivated. If you have a friend who has a similar goal (re: does&nbsp;<em>not&nbsp;</em>need to be exactly the same), you can designate an accountability buddy that checks in with each other\'s progress and performance on a regular basis. It will help you both stay honest with how you\'re doing, plus can be a fun way to connect with someone who has shared interests.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>If you don\'t like the idea of relying on an accountability buddy, there are plenty of other ways to cultivate inspiration. You can create vision boards that incorporate your goals and place it in an easy-to-see location, print mantras or reminders to hang in your home or follow influencers or leaders who share insight and tips.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Reward yourself for success</h3>\r\n<p>Admittedly some New Year\'s resolutions can feel like a chore&mdash;whether it\'s improving your studying skills or starting a new fitness regimen, it\'s not always easy or fun to begin. If you find yourself struggling to self-motivate, instill a reward for following through with your goals. For example, if you want to walk for forty minutes every day, you can incentivize this new habit by adding a small reward to the task, like a latte at your favorite coffee shop to sip on while you stroll. Keep in mind that the reward should not counteract your goal&mdash;so if you\'re trying to dial down on screen time and read more, the treat for reading a chapter should not be an hour of Netflix binging.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Photo by <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/@rovenimages_com?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Roven Images</a> on <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/s/photos/new-years?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Unsplash</a></p>', 'roven-images-HxeBUWUiA1A-unsplash.jpg', 1, '2022-01-04 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(402, 'The Best Restaurants in Hell\'s Kitchen', 1, 'the-best-restaurants-in-hells-kitchen', '', 'The Best Restaurants in Hell\'s Kitchen | Outpost Club blog', 'The Best Restaurants in Hell\'s Kitchen | Outpost Club blog', 'While you might know Hell\'s Kitchen for it\'s Times Square-adjacent location, this slice of the city has plenty of culinary destinations worthy of a taste-test. ', '<p>While you might know Hell\'s Kitchen for it\'s Times Square-adjacent location, phenomenal happy hour deals and rotating Broadway shows, this mid-town Manhattan neighborhood also offers global cuisine and locally-loved restaurants. Whether you\'re craving a rich Cuban sandwich or a brimming bowl of ramen noodles, this slice of the city has plenty of culinary destinations worthy of a taste-test.</p>', '<p>While you might know Hell\'s Kitchen for it\'s Times Square-adjacent location, phenomenal happy hour deals and rotating Broadway shows, this mid-town Manhattan neighborhood also offers global cuisine and locally-loved restaurants. Whether you\'re craving a rich Cuban sandwich or a brimming bowl of ramen noodles, this slice of the city has plenty of culinary destinations worthy of a taste-test.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://tottoramen.com/menu/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Totto Ramen Midtown West&nbsp;</a></h3>\r\n<p>Ditch the packets of chicken flavoring and go treat yourself to a bowl of hearty and nourishing ramen over at Totto. It\'s no surpise that the restaurant has multiple locations across the city, as their decadent broth, range of customizable toppings and traditional appetizers make them an ideal spot for anyone hankering for noodles.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://kochinyc.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Kochi</a></h3>\r\n<p>Head to Kochi for Korean fare that is Michelin star approved. You can opt for the tasting menu to savor a wide variety of flavors, from seared scallops with tiger\'s milk to slow cooked pork tenderloin with kimchi. Certainly a pricer meal than some of our other contendors, but the flavors will be hard to find anywhere else.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.empmamanyc.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Empanada Mama</a></h3>\r\n<p>For those who want an affordable meal that won\'t sacrifice any flavor or satiety, check out Empanada Mama and pick up a few savory stuffed pastries for just $3.99 each. Whether you like your empanadas baked and filled with shredded chicken or reggaeton style filled with Caribbean&nbsp;roast pork, there\'s a wide variety of flavors to try.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.purethaicookhouse.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Pure Thai Cookhouse</a></h3>\r\n<p>This shophouse-style restaurant serves up authentic Thai fare, from popular street food to the classic noodle dishes that make your mouth water. We recommend the root vegetable puffs, wok ginger curry with calamari or nakorn-patom duck noodle soup.</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://torishinny.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Tori Shin</a></h3>\r\n<p>Hell\'s Kitchen is home to one of New York City\'s best yakitori spots, boasting a robust menu of Waygu, Iberico pork, tenderloin, mentai chazuke and rice dishes. While the prices and selection vary greatly, this is an ideal spot for a celebration, birthday or somewhat swanky date night. We recommend reserving in advance, as tables are in high demand.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://nizzanyc.com/menu/-dinner/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Nizza</a></h3>\r\n<p>No New York restaurant round-up can be completed without an Italian pick&mdash;and Nizza proudly takes the spotlight among the eateries in Hell\'s Kitchen. This spot serves up the area\'s best pizza and pasta, not to mention the entirely gluten-free menu they have on standby.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://www.donburiyany.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Donburiya</a></h3>\r\n<p>With an expansive menu offering everything from noodles and rice to ishiyaki and donburi, this is the place to be in Hell\'s Kitchen if you need a Japanese food fix. Donburiya\'s affordable prices and late night hours make it an ecclectic spot to have a dinner feast or grab a late night meal after hitting nearby bars.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://www.guantanamerany.com/nyc.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Guantanamera</a></h3>\r\n<p>Not every bodega or deli can make a sandwich worthy of a recommendation, so when you\'re in the mood for a hearty and flavorful \'wich, head to Guantanamera. With a menu featuring Cuban sandwiches, paellas and flavorful seafood and meat dishes, there\'s no shortage of options to feast on for either lunch or dinner.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Photo by <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/@stephenkbedase?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Stephen Bedase</a> on <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/s/photos/ramen?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Unsplash</a></p>', 'stephen-bedase-WjdOYhgTGCM-unsplash.jpg', 1, '2022-01-27 06:00:00', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
(403, '7 Things to Do in NYC This Valentine\'s Day ', 1, '7-things-to-do-in-nyc-this-valentines-day-', '', '7 Things to Do in NYC This Valentine\'s Day | Outpost Club blog', '7 Things to Do in NYC This Valentine\'s Day | Outpost Club blog', 'If you want to impress , we encourage you to participate in some of the city\'s most adventurous celebrations.  We\'ve put together some of the best events that will delight anyone. ', '<p>While a candelit romantic dinner at your favorite New York City restaurant might be your go-to for Valentine\'s Day, if you\'re aiming to impress we emplore you to venture a bit off the beaten path and revel in some of the cities more adventurous celebrations. From rompy drag shows to crooning love songs that last all night, we\'ve rounded up some of the best V-Day events that will wow any date.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>While a candelit romantic dinner at your favorite New York City restaurant might be your go-to for Valentine\'s Day, if you\'re aiming to impress we emplore you to venture a bit off the beaten path and revel in some of the cities more adventurous celebrations. From rompy drag shows to crooning love songs that last all night, we\'ve rounded up some of the best V-Day events that will wow any date.</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.getyourguide.com/new-york-city-l59/new-york-valentine-s-day-sunset-cruise-with-buffet-dinner-t353491/?date_from=2022-02-14&amp;date_to=2022-02-14\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Sunset Cruise with Dinner</a></h3>\r\n<p>Wine and dine your Valentine\'s Day date with sweeping views of the Manhattan skyline, Ellis Island, and the Statue of Liberty. With an included champagne toast or wine, full buffet dinner, and holiday-inspired desserts, there\'s no better way to show your affection than with this romantic water retreat. Tickets are $160 per person.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://feverup.com/m/107788?utm_source=secretnyc&amp;utm_medium=post&amp;utm_campaign=107788_nyc&amp;utm_content=galentine-valentines-day-events-nyc&amp;utm_term=cta2\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Valentine\'s Serenade at St. Ann and the Holy Trinity Church</a></h3>\r\n<p>Soak in incredible arcitecture bathed in golden candelight while listening to Broadway\'s best hits. Pianists and vocalists serve up stunning renditions in this iconic church, creating an intimate ambiance perfect for Valentine\'s Day. We recommend heading to a dinner afterwards for a full evening of romance. Tickets are $60 per person.</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://stayhappening.com/e/villain-edit-with-chevy-lace-E3LUTR50WFLM\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Villanous Valentines at the Villain Edit</a></h3>\r\n<p>Spend your Sunday evening among plenty of pomp and entertainment at the special V-Day event at Villian Edit. The&nbsp;show will include a variety of drag, dancers, and performers, plus giveaways and photo opps. Tickets are just $10, making this an affordable way to celebrate with a partner, friend, or hot date.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.getyourguide.com/the-basilica-of-st-patrick-s-old-cathedral-l166487/new-york-city-catacombs-by-candlelight-t282727/?date_from=2022-02-14&amp;date_to=2022-02-14\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">New York City Catacombs by Candelight</a></h3>\r\n<p>If you\'re more spooky than sweet, take an equally romantic and harrowing journey through the catacombs of New York City. This guided tour takes you behind the Basilica of St. Patrick\'s Old Cathedral and candelit catacombs&mdash;certainly a Valentine\'s Day celebration you won\'t forget. Tickets are $37.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.museumofsex.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Museum of Sex \"Love Lockdown\"</a></h3>\r\n<p>There\'s no better time to make a trip to the Museum of Sex than Valentine\'s Day, and with their special \"Love Lockdown\" event happening from February 11-14th, your typical entry ticket will come with perks and treats. While this might not be a great first date or for those faint of heart, it certainly kicks off the holiday on a high note. Tickets are $39 on February 11th and 12th and $55 on the 13th and 14th and include access to all exhibits and a special Love Infusion\'IV\' cocktail.</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.bluenotejazz.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Nella at Blue Note</a></h3>\r\n<p>Upgrade your typical Valentine\'s Day dinner with romantic live music from Nella, a 2019 Latin Grammy Award winner. Sip on a marigold and kaffir lime margarita or a burnt maple old fashioned, and then nab a table for sumptuous fare like lavendar French chicken breast with truffle mashed potatoes, lobster ravioli, or pan seared salmon. With sets at both 8:00 and 10:30, you can&nbsp;spend the whole evening with your date&nbsp;at this&nbsp;cozy&nbsp;jazz venue.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.thejanenyc.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Kiss and Tell at the Jane Hotel&nbsp;</a></h3>\r\n<p>If a romantic evening simply isn\'t your speed this Valentine\'s Day, opt for a raucous comedy show on Sunday night at the Jane Hotel. Whether you\'re celebrating Galentine\'s or want to ensure your date has a laugh, the comedy skits and storytelling from comedians Emmy Harrington, Bobby Hankinson, and Carly Ann Filbin are a certifiably fun way to enjoy Valentine\'s Day.</p>\r\n<p>Looking for something more traditional? Here are&nbsp;<a href=\"../blog/6-things-to-do-in-nyc-this-valentines-day\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">6 more NYC Valentine\'s Day recommendations.</a></p>\r\n<p>Photo by <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/@brunus?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Bruno Martins</a> on <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/s/photos/valentines-day?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\">Unsplash</a></p>', 'bruno-martins-byYar8P38LA-unsplash.jpg', 1, '2022-02-10 06:00:00', '2022-07-05 15:28:21', NULL, 0, 0);
