(98, 0, NULL, 'our-houses', '', 'Our houses', 'Our Houses — Coliving in New York | Outpost Club', 'Explore Outpost Club\'s New York City Houses', 'Check out our Homes', '<h1 class=\"h1\">Check out our Homes</h1>\r\n<h4>Co-Living Is So Much More Than Shared Housing. <br />Welcome To Your Built-In Community.</h4>', '', '', 1, '', 'our-houses.jpg', '', '', 100, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'Check out our Homes', 0, 0, 'a:0:{}', '', '', '', '', 0, '0.00000000', '0.00000000', 0, '', NULL),
(103, 253, NULL, 'the-east-bushwick-house', '', 'The East Bushwick House', 'East Bushwick (NYC) Room Rentals, Shared Apartments | Outpost Club', 'A contemporary house in up-and-coming East Bushwick', 'The East Bushwick House', '<p>Bushwick, Brooklyn</p>\r\n<p>Private rooms for $1050</p>', '<h1 class=\"h1\">The East-Bushwick House</h1>\r\n<h4>A contemporary house in up-and-coming East Bushwick</h4>', '<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">The scoop</h6>\r\n<p>The East Bushwick House features four floors of exclusively designed spaces, with three total apartments. We even have a spacious backyard!</p>\r\n<p>The house is a newly renovated space with central air, updated appliances and hardwood floors. This house is equipped with a common basement living room and coworking space. All of the common areas are massive in comparison to your average New York City apartment.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">The Neighborhood</h6>\r\n<p>This coliving space is in up-and-coming east side of the Bushwick neighborhood of Brooklyn.</p>\r\n<p><strong>The East Bushwick House is a five-minute walk to the Wilson Ave. stop on the L train and a 15-minute walk to the Halsey Street stop on the J, M and Z trains.</strong></p>\r\n<p>The location is near coffee shops (Father Knows Best is Outpost Club\'s favorite), pizza/taco joints and bars. Check out our neighborhood guide to get a feel of the area!</p>\r\n</div>', 5, '', 'eastbushwick_small-16.jpg', 'eastbushwick-background.jpg', '', 404, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The East Bushwick House', 0, 0, 'a:9:{i:6;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:20:\"Throughout the house\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:591:\"<p>{throughout}</p>\r\n<table class=\"table v2\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<th>12+ Months</th>\r\n<th>4-11 Months</th>\r\n<th>1-3 Months</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private</th>\r\n<td>$1050</td>\r\n<td>Not Offered</td>\r\n<td>Not Offered</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"5\">\r\n<p>*Price above do not include utilities</p>\r\n<p>**The prices shown indicate <strong>the prices valid for move-in between <strong>November 1</strong>, 2021, and December 31, 2021.</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div class=\"center\"><a class=\"button2 red\" href=\"join-us\" target=\"_blank\">Apply for free</a></div>\";}i:3;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:12:\"The bedrooms\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:340:\"<p>There are single and shared bedrooms, depending on availability and your price range. Bedding is available for an additional fee.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Amenities:</strong> memory-foam mattresses (twin-sized for shared rooms, full-sized for single rooms), pillows, shelving, hooks and closets/organizational tools.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:4:{i:0;s:26:\"east-bushwick-bedroom8.jpg\";i:1;s:26:\"east-bushwick-bedroom7.jpg\";i:2;s:26:\"east-bushwick-bedroom2.jpg\";i:3;s:20:\"east-b-bedroom-2.jpg\";}}i:0;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:24:\"The kitchens/dining room\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:613:\"<p>The kitchens form the core of each apartment, and for good reason. On each floor, the kitchen and dining room are the first rooms you enter. These spaces each have dining-room tables and the second-floor dining room is even large enough to sit 10-12 people. The kitchens are used for potluck dinners, solo meals and chats in the evening over a glass of wine.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Amenities include</strong> gas stoves, stainless-steel fridges, microwaves, large sinks, coffee makers, blenders, plenty of cabinets, cookware, tableware, cutting boards and anything else you would need in a kitchen.</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:3:{i:0;s:25:\"eastbushwick_small-24.jpg\";i:1;s:24:\"eastbushwick_small-8.jpg\";i:2;s:25:\"eastbushwick_small-16.jpg\";}}i:1;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:19:\"The (co)living room\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:397:\"<p>The living room has two separate nooks for people to hang out in. The larger part of the living room has a large couch and a 55-inch TV (with Netflix); this is where we host movie nights, game nights and chill hangouts. The smaller living room has a padded mat to lie on and beanbag chairs. This space is equipped with everything you need to relax.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Google Chromecast.</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:4:{i:0;s:25:\"east-bushwick-living3.jpg\";i:1;s:24:\"east-bushwick-living.jpg\";i:2;s:25:\"east-bushwick-living2.jpg\";i:3;s:25:\"east-bushwick-living4.jpg\";}}i:2;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:19:\"The coworking space\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:591:\"<p>The co-working space in this house will make sure you have everything you need to work productively! The area comfortably holds up to five people working simultaneously. There\'s a lot of desk space to make sure your work time is productive. Additionally, there are many common spaces throughout the house that our members use to work.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Amenities:</strong> Desks, chairs, conveniently placed outlets, a printer and a scanner to make sure you are prepared for anything work throws at you.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Security:</strong> 24/7 security in common areas.</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:2:{i:0;s:31:\"eastbushwick_small-co-space.jpg\";i:1;s:33:\"eastbushwick_small-co-space-8.jpg\";}}i:4;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:13:\"The bathrooms\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:183:\"<p>There are six full bathrooms and one half bathroom so you&rsquo;ll never have to wait..</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p class=\"h5\">The Laundry</p>\r\n<p>Every floor has its own washer and dryer.</p>\";s:6:\"images\";a:2:{i:0;s:27:\"east-bushwick-bathroom1.jpg\";i:1;s:26:\"east-bushwick-bathroom.jpg\";}}i:5;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:12:\"The backyard\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:187:\"<p>We even have a backyard! It has tables and chairs so you can hang outside in the spring, summer and autumn. The space holds many parties, get-togethers, barbecues and celebrations.</p>\";s:6:\"images\";a:1:{i:0;s:26:\"east-bushwick-backyard.jpg\";}}i:7;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:19:\"Additional benefits\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:172:\"<p><strong>We screen all candidates before approving applications so that there are no worries about moving into a new place with new people - only excitement!</strong></p>\";}i:8;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:6:\"Prices\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:714:\"<table class=\"table v2\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<th>12+ Months</th>\r\n<th>4-11 Months</th>\r\n<th>1-3 Months</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private</th>\r\n<td>$1050</td>\r\n<td>Not Offered</td>\r\n<td>Not Offered</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"5\">\r\n<p>*Price above do not include utilities&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>**The prices shown indicate <strong>the prices valid for move-in between <strong>November 1</strong>, 2021, and December 31, 2021.</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div class=\"center\"><a class=\"button2 red\" href=\"join-us\" target=\"_blank\">Apply for free</a></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Availability: Year-round / Minimum stay of 12 months / Minimum age 18</strong></p>\";}}', '', 'a:4:{i:0;s:3:\"198\";i:1;s:3:\"182\";i:2;s:3:\"202\";i:3;s:3:\"170\";}', '', '<div class=\"txt\">\r\n<h1 class=\"\">The East Bushwick House Move-In Guide</h1>\r\n<h2><em><strong>250 Schaefer Street, Brooklyn, NY, 11207</strong></em></h2>\r\n<hr class=\"hr\" />\r\n<h3><strong>The Community</strong></h3>\r\n<p>Welcome to Outpost! We&rsquo;re glad you&rsquo;re here. Coliving isn&rsquo;t just about having roommates or sharing a kitchen &mdash; it&rsquo;s about recognizing that we can do more, accomplish more and be more when we work together.</p>\r\n<p>We communicate with each other via our house&rsquo;s Messenger group, which your House Leader will add you upon arrival. We also offer an Outpost Slack channel where you can find other members with similar interests and meet new people in your area. We send out relevant updates and information via email, so keep an eye out!</p>\r\n<p>Your <strong>Member Portal</strong> is where you can RSVP for community events, submit maintenance and cleaning requests and access important documents. <a class=\"green\" href=\"../user/login\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Find it here</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Your <strong>House Leader</strong> will be your main point of contact with Outpost. Here&rsquo;s what they can help you with:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Info about community activities</li>\r\n<li>Restocking supplies</li>\r\n<li>Questions about Outpost</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>We have a lot of activities to help you get involved with our community and get to know the city. Pay attention to your Member Portal and your house&rsquo;s Messenger group to keep up with what&rsquo;s going on, or just ask your House Leader!</p>\r\n<h3><strong>The Logistics</strong></h3>\r\n<h3>Moving In</h3>\r\n<p>The outside code to your house is <strong>#2369</strong>. You&rsquo;ll use the August app to access your unit with the code <strong>#2311</strong>. Download the app and sign up for an account, and your House Leader will give you access.</p>\r\n<p>Here&rsquo;s how to use the app:</p>\r\n<div class=\"fx w vc ch2\">\r\n<div><img style=\"width: 70%; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"../files/uploads/august_lock.gif\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>When you move in, your House Leader will give you a tour of the house and talk to you a bit about the Outpost community. They&rsquo;ll also:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Take a photo of your ID (for our records and according to state law)</li>\r\n<li>Add you to your Messenger group</li>\r\n<li>Assign you cupboard and refrigerator space, according to your room number.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The WiFi name is Outpost (or something similar) and the password is <strong>befreenyc</strong>.</p>\r\n<h3>Living at Outpost</h3>\r\n<p>You&rsquo;ll find helpful information linked above in our Guide to Responsible Coliving, but there are a few more things you should know:</p>\r\n<p><strong>Recycling is required</strong>, and New York City has strict guidelines. Watch the video below to see what you should recycle:</p>\r\n<iframe style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/EUyVELb5PzY\" width=\"70%\" height=\"400\"></iframe><br /><br />\r\n<p><strong>Cleanliness is also required.</strong> That&rsquo;s especially true of common areas, including shared rooms. Here are some easy ways to think about cleanliness at Outpost:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Leave rooms in the condition in which you found them</li>\r\n<li>Clean up after yourself</li>\r\n<li>Don&rsquo;t leave your belongings in the common area unless you&rsquo;re returning immediately</li>\r\n<li>Pay attention to the signs around the house: They&rsquo;re there to help our community run smoothly!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Outpost is not responsible for lost or damaged mail or packages.</strong> Your House Leader will check the mail regularly. Make sure to put your full address, including your outside door code, in the delivery field when you order something. You may find your package left inside the main door, concealed outside, with a roommate who picked it up for you or returned to a distribution center for a later delivery. It&rsquo;s your responsibility to track your packages and make sure you&rsquo;re home to receive them when necessary.</p>\r\n</div>', 2, '40.69126000', '-73.90590000', 0, '', NULL),
