(155, 253, NULL, 'the-bushwick-house', 'the-schaefer-house-outpost-club', 'The Bushwick House', 'Rooms for Rent in Bushwick, NYC, Shared & Private', 'A cozy home in the heart of Bushwick', 'The Bushwick House', '<p>Bushwick, Brooklyn</p>\r\n<p>Private rooms from $1000</p>', '<h1 class=\"h1\">The Bushwick House</h1>\r\n<h4>A cozy community in the heart of Bushwick</h4>', '<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">The Scoop</h6>\r\n<p>The Bushwick House is nestled in the heart of trendy Bushwick, where you can find a bustling art and nightlife scene. With only a 5-minute walk between you and the nearest subway station, you can be in Manhattan in only 20 minutes. This house has three Outpost units, all with beautiful bedrooms ready for your arrival.</p>\r\n<p>The house has been recently renovated space throughout, with split-unit heating and air conditioning, stainless steel appliances and hardwood floors. This house includes three units with four bedrooms each, with each unit equipped with a full kitchen and living room. The spaces are arranged around bright and inviting common areas, and the bedrooms are spacious in comparison to your average New York City apartment.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">THE LOCATION</h6>\r\n<p>Look to the west of Williamsburg and you&rsquo;ll find the hip neighborhood of Bushwick. With trendy coffee shops, bars, art galleries and performance spaces on every block, Bushwick is the perfect neighborhood to experience a unique part of Brooklyn that is often overlooked. Our favorite eateries include the perfect pizza at Roberta&rsquo;s, Ethiopian cuisine at Bunna Cafe and the popular Taiwanese food at Win Son. If you&rsquo;re looking for a green space to retreat to, Saratoga Park is a 5-minute walk away, or you can explore Highland Park, which stretches across many Brooklyn neighborhoods.</p>\r\n<p><strong>The Bushwick House is a 5-minute walk to the Halsey St. subway station. You can hop on the J train and be in Williamsburg in less than 15 minutes and Manhattan in 20.</strong></p>\r\n</div>', 5, '', '1102-putnam-avenue-2-3-2.jpg', '1102-putnam-avenue-2-1-a-2.jpg', '', 411, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Bushwick House', 0, 0, 'a:7:{i:7;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:20:\"Throughout the house\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:821:\"<p>{throughout}</p>\r\n<table class=\"table v2\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<th>12+ Months</th>\r\n<th>4-11 Months</th>\r\n<th>1-3 Months</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Executive + Bath)</th>\r\n<td>$1300</td>\r\n<td>Not Offered</td>\r\n<td>Not Offered</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Standard Large)</th>\r\n<td>$1050</td>\r\n<td>Not Offered</td>\r\n<td>Not Offered</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Standard)</th>\r\n<td>$1000</td>\r\n<td>Not Offered</td>\r\n<td>Not Offered</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"5\">\r\n<p>*Prices above do not include utilities</p>\r\n<p>**The prices shown indicate <strong>the prices valid for move-in between <strong>November 1</strong>, 2021, and December 31, 2021.</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div class=\"center\"><a class=\"button2 red\" href=\"join-us\" target=\"_blank\">Apply for free</a></div>\";}i:3;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:12:\"The bedrooms\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:311:\"<p>Your room will be clean and furnished just like the rest of the house. Rooms at the Bushwick House are all private. Bedding is available for an additional fee.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Amenities: </strong>memory-foam full-sized mattresses, pillows, shelving, hooks and closets/organizational tools.</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:8:{i:0;s:28:\"1102-putnam-avenue-1-3-2.jpg\";i:1;s:28:\"1102-putnam-avenue-3-1-2.jpg\";i:2;s:28:\"1102-putnam-avenue-1-2-2.jpg\";i:3;s:30:\"1102-putnam-avenue-3-4-a-2.jpg\";i:4;s:30:\"1102-putnam-avenue-3-3-a-2.jpg\";i:5;s:28:\"1102-putnam-avenue-2-2-2.jpg\";i:6;s:28:\"1102-putnam-avenue-2-1-2.jpg\";i:7;s:30:\"1102-putnam-avenue-2-1-a-2.jpg\";}}i:0;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:24:\"The kitchens/dining room\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:465:\"<p>The kitchens in each unit have gas stoves and stainless steel appliances and are stocked with plenty of supplies, so you can meal prep or cook dinner without a worry.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Amenities</strong> include microwaves, dishwashers, large sinks, coffee makers, blenders, plenty of cabinets, cookware, tableware, cutting boards and anything else you would need in a kitchen.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Security:</strong> 24/7 security in common areas.</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:2:{i:0;s:34:\"1102-putnam-avenue-1-kitchen-2.jpg\";i:1;s:34:\"1102-putnam-avenue-2-kitchen-2.jpg\";}}i:1;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:19:\"The (co)living room\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:361:\"<p>The living rooms are at the heart of each unit within the Bushwick House, with their comfy couches and TVs, perfect for your next movie night. The space is equipped with everything you need to relax.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Living room also includes:</strong> Additional seating, pillows, lamps.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Tech:</strong> Google Chromecast.</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:3:{i:0;s:33:\"1102-putnam-avenue-1-dining-2.jpg\";i:1;s:33:\"1102-putnam-avenue-3-dining-2.jpg\";i:2;s:33:\"1102-putnam-avenue-2-dining-2.jpg\";}}i:4;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:13:\"The bathrooms\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:52:\"<p>We provide many bathroom essentials, as well.</p>\";s:6:\"images\";a:2:{i:0;s:37:\"1102-putnam-avenue-2-bahtroom-1-2.jpg\";i:1;s:37:\"1102-putnam-avenue-2-bathroom-3-2.jpg\";}}i:9;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:19:\"Additional benefits\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:178:\"<p><strong>We screen all candidates before approving applications so that there are no worries about moving into a new place with new people &mdash; only excitement!</strong></p>\";}i:10;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:6:\"Prices\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:944:\"<table class=\"table v2\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<th>12+ Months</th>\r\n<th>4-11 Months</th>\r\n<th>1-3 Months</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Executive + Bath)</th>\r\n<td>$1300</td>\r\n<td>Not Offered</td>\r\n<td>Not Offered</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Standard Large)</th>\r\n<td>$1050</td>\r\n<td>Not Offered</td>\r\n<td>Not Offered</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Standard)</th>\r\n<td>$1000</td>\r\n<td>Not Offered</td>\r\n<td>Not Offered</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"5\">\r\n<p>*Prices above do not include utilities&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>**The prices shown indicate <strong>the prices valid for move-in between <strong>November 1</strong>, 2021, and December 31, 2021.</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div class=\"center\"><a class=\"button2 red\" href=\"join-us\" target=\"_blank\">Apply for free</a></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Availability: Year-round / Minimum stay of 12 months / Minimum age 18</strong></p>\";}}', '', 'a:5:{i:0;s:3:\"177\";i:1;s:3:\"208\";i:2;s:3:\"205\";i:3;s:3:\"185\";i:4;s:3:\"212\";}', '', '<div class=\"txt\">\r\n<h1 class=\"\">The Bushwick House Move-In Guide</h1>\r\n<h2><em><strong>1102 Putnam Ave, Brooklyn, NY 11221</strong></em></h2>\r\n<hr class=\"hr\" />\r\n<h3><strong>The Community</strong></h3>\r\n<p>Welcome to Outpost! We&rsquo;re glad you&rsquo;re here. Coliving isn&rsquo;t just about having roommates or sharing a kitchen &mdash; it&rsquo;s about recognizing that we can do more, accomplish more and be more when we work together.</p>\r\n<p>We communicate with each other via our house&rsquo;s Messenger group, which your House Leader will add you upon arrival. We also offer an Outpost Slack channel where you can find other members with similar interests and meet new people in your area. We send out relevant updates and information via email, so keep an eye out!</p>\r\n<p>Your <strong>Member Portal</strong> is where you can RSVP for community events, submit maintenance and cleaning requests and access important documents. <a class=\"green\" href=\"../user/login\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Find it here</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Your <strong>House Leader</strong> will be your main point of contact with Outpost. Here&rsquo;s what they can help you with:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Info about community activities</li>\r\n<li>Restocking supplies</li>\r\n<li>Questions about Outpost</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>We have a lot of activities to help you get involved with our community and get to know the city. Pay attention to your Member Portal and your house&rsquo;s Messenger group to keep up with what&rsquo;s going on, or just ask your House Leader!</p>\r\n<h3><strong>The Logistics</strong></h3>\r\n<h3>Moving In</h3>\r\n<p>To unlock and enter the building, use the code <strong>#5875</strong>. Once inside, you&rsquo;ll use the August app to access your individual unit. Download the app and sign up for an account, and your House Leader will give you access. Here&rsquo;s how to use the app:</p>\r\n<div class=\"fx w vc ch2\">\r\n<div><img style=\"width: 70%; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"../files/uploads/august_lock.gif\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>When you move in, your House Leader will give you a tour of the house and talk to you a bit about the Outpost community. They&rsquo;ll also:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Take a photo of your ID (for our records and according to state law)</li>\r\n<li>Add you to your Messenger group</li>\r\n<li>Assign you cupboard and refrigerator space, according to your room number.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The WiFi name is Outpost (or something similar) and the password is <strong>befreenyc</strong>.</p>\r\n<h3>Living at Outpost</h3>\r\n<p>You&rsquo;ll find helpful information linked above in our Guide to Responsible Coliving, but there are a few more things you should know:</p>\r\n<p><strong>Recycling is required</strong>, and New York City has strict guidelines. Watch the video below to see what you should recycle:</p>\r\n<iframe style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/EUyVELb5PzY\" width=\"70%\" height=\"400\"></iframe><br /><br />\r\n<p><strong>Cleanliness is also required.</strong> That&rsquo;s especially true of common areas, including shared rooms. Here are some easy ways to think about cleanliness at Outpost:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Leave rooms in the condition in which you found them</li>\r\n<li>Clean up after yourself</li>\r\n<li>Don&rsquo;t leave your belongings in the common area unless you&rsquo;re returning immediately</li>\r\n<li>Pay attention to the signs around the house: They&rsquo;re there to help our community run smoothly!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Outpost is not responsible for lost or damaged mail or packages.</strong> Your House Leader will check the mail regularly. Make sure to put your full address, including your outside door code, in the delivery field when you order something. You may find your package left inside the main door, concealed outside, with a roommate who picked it up for you or returned to a distribution center for a later delivery. It&rsquo;s your responsibility to track your packages and make sure you&rsquo;re home to receive them when necessary.</p>\r\n</div>', 2, '40.68817190', '-73.91835235', 0, '', NULL),
