(158, 253, NULL, 'the-east-williamsburg-house', '', 'The East Williamsburg House ', 'East Williamsburg (NYC) Room Rentals, Shared Apartments | Outpost Club', 'Eclectic living in trendy East Williamsburg', 'The East Williamsburg House', '<p>East Williamsburg, Brooklyn</p>\r\n<p>Shared rooms from $790 | Private rooms from $1730</p>', '<h1 class=\"h1\">The East Williamsburg House</h1>\r\n<h4>Eclectic living in trendy East Williamsburg</h4>', '<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">THE SCOOP</h6>\r\n<p>The East Williamsburg House features 14 beautifully designed bedrooms and common spaces in a trendy East Williamsburg neighborhood. We even have a spacious courtyard!</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">LOCATION</h6>\r\n<p>Located in the eastern part of Williamsburg, Brooklyn, this coliving space is in an up-and-coming neighborhood.</p>\r\n<p><strong>The East Williamsburg House is a 12-minute walk to the L train and 16-minute walk to the G Train.</strong></p>\r\n<p>The location is near coffee shops, pizza joints, bars and music venues.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">THE SPACE</h6>\r\n<p>The house is a newly renovated space with updated appliances and hardwood floors. It&rsquo;s equipped with two kitchens, a basement living room and a co-working space. All of the common areas are massive in comparison to your average New York City apartment.</p>\r\n<p><strong>This space is move-in ready; all you have to do is show up with your suitcase.</strong></p>\r\n</div>', 5, '', 'the-east-williamsburg-main.jpg', 'the-east-williamsburg-1.jpg', '', 424, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The East Williamsburg House', 0, 0, 'a:9:{i:7;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:20:\"Throughout the house\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:1650:\"<p>{throughout}</p>\r\n<table class=\"table v2\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<th class=\"title\">\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><span class=\"gold\">Gold</span> Membership</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</th>\r\n<th colspan=\"2\">\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><span class=\"silver\">Silver</span> Membership</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"bronze\">Bronze</span> Membership</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"2\"><em>*Bronze members must move in on <strong>the first day</strong> of the month</em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<th>1-12 Months</th>\r\n<th>4+ Months</th>\r\n<th>1-3 Months</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Executive + Bath)</th>\r\n<td>$1990</td>\r\n<td>$2150</td>\r\n<td>$2290</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private</th>\r\n<td>$1730</td>\r\n<td>$1890</td>\r\n<td>$2050</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>2-person (Executive)</th>\r\n<td>$990</td>\r\n<td>$1100</td>\r\n<td>$1200</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>2-person (Basic)</th>\r\n<td>$930</td>\r\n<td>$1050</td>\r\n<td>$1150</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Multi-person</th>\r\n<td>$790</td>\r\n<td>$950</td>\r\n<td>$1050</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"5\">See the benefits of Bronze, Silver, and Gold Membership <a class=\"red\" href=\"../memberships\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">here</a>\r\n<p><em>**The prices shown indicate <strong>the prices valid for move-in between Dec. 15, 2019, and March 31, 2020</strong>. The exact price is indicated in your membership agreement and may vary depending on the length of commitment, your membership level and the size of your group, if applicable.</em></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div class=\"center\"><a class=\"button2\" href=\"join-us\">I`m intersted</a></div>\";}i:3;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:12:\"The bedrooms\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:524:\"<p>Your room will be move-in ready, just like the rest of the house. There&rsquo;s no need to even bring a pillow. There are single and shared rooms, depending on availability and your price range.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Amenities: memory-foam mattresses (twin-sized for shared rooms, full-sized for single rooms), pillows, extension cords to your bedside, shelving, hooks, bed linens, towels and closets/organizational tools.</li>\r\n<li>Services: <strong>Bed linens and towels available for you when you arrive.</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:8:{i:0;s:33:\"the-east-williamsburg-bedroom.jpg\";i:1;s:35:\"the-east-williamsburg-bedroom-2.jpg\";i:2;s:35:\"the-east-williamsburg-bedroom-3.jpg\";i:3;s:35:\"the-east-williamsburg-bedroom-8.jpg\";i:4;s:35:\"the-east-williamsburg-bedroom-7.jpg\";i:5;s:35:\"the-east-williamsburg-bedroom-6.jpg\";i:6;s:35:\"the-east-williamsburg-bedroom-5.jpg\";i:7;s:35:\"the-east-williamsburg-bedroom-4.jpg\";}}i:0;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:24:\"The kitchens/dining room\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:821:\"<p>There are two kitchens in the East Williamsburg House, and one of the them even has a balcony that\'s perfect for a relaxing outdoor meals with friends. These spaces each have dining room and everything your&rsquo;ll need to make a home cooked meal. These spaces are used for potluck dinners, solo meals and chats in the evening over a glass of wine.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Amenities include gas stoves, stainless-steel fridges, microwaves, large sinks, coffee makers, blenders, plenty of cabinets, cookware, tableware, cutting boards and anything else you would need in a kitchen.</li>\r\n<li>Also included: salt, pepper, sugar, coffee grounds, tea, olive oil, paper towels, dish soap, hand soap and garbage/recycling bags, all of which are routinely restocked.</li>\r\n<li>Security: 24/7 security in all common areas.</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:2:{i:0;s:35:\"the-east-williamsburg-kitchen-2.jpg\";i:1;s:35:\"the-east-williamsburg-kitchen-1.jpg\";}}i:4;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:13:\"The bathrooms\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:537:\"<p>We provide many bathroom essentials, as well. There are six full bathrooms and one half bathroom so you&rsquo;ll never have to wait. Some are en-suite bathrooms while some are for the whole house to use.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Also included: toilet paper, shampoo, body wash, hand soap and small garbage bags, which will never be empty! We also provide hairdryers, no need to bring your own.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The is a pay-per-use washer and dryer next to the living room.</p>\r\n<p>Security: 24/7 security in common areas, as well as lockers</p>\";s:6:\"images\";a:1:{i:0;s:34:\"the-east-williamsburg-bathroom.jpg\";}}i:1;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:19:\"The (co)living room\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:461:\"<p>The living room is located in the basement and has two large couches and 55-inch TV (with Netflix!); this is where we host movie nights, game nights and chill hangouts. The space is equipped with everything you need to relax.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Living room also includes: coffee tables, pillows, lamps, knickknacks, house slippers to walk around in and nice people.</li>\r\n<li>Security: 24/7 security in common areas.</li>\r\n<li>Tech: Google Chromecast</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:2:{i:0;s:36:\"the-east-williamsburg-coliving-2.jpg\";i:1;s:36:\"the-east-williamsburg-coliving-1.jpg\";}}i:2;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:20:\"The co-working space\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:533:\"<p>The basement is also equipped with everything you need to work! This room comfortably holds up to 10 people working simultaneously. There\'s lots of desk space to make sure your work time is productive. Additionally, there are many common spaces throughout the house that our members use to work.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Amenities: Desks, chairs, conveniently placed outlets, a printer, a scanner and a fax machine to make sure you are prepared for anything work throws at you.</li>\r\n<li>Security: 24/7 security in common areas.</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:1:{i:0;s:38:\"the-east-williamsburg-co-working-2.jpg\";}}i:5;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:24:\"The court yard and patio\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:208:\"<p>Yes, we even have a courtyard and patio! These spaces have tables and chairs so you can hang outside in the spring, summer and autumn. They hold many parties, get-togethers, barbecues and celebrations.</p>\";s:6:\"images\";a:2:{i:0;s:36:\"the-east-williamsburg-backyard-2.jpg\";i:1;s:34:\"the-east-williamsburg-backyard.jpg\";}}i:8;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:19:\"Additional benefits\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:403:\"<p>Your membership gives you the opportunity to move between all our houses from month to month, allowing you to see what it&rsquo;s like to live in different neighborhoods. Members are welcome to enjoy the parties and events at any of our locations. We screen all candidates before approving applications so that there are no worries about moving into a new place with new people - only excitement!</p>\";}i:9;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:6:\"Prices\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:1893:\"<p>We have flexible month-to-month commitment options. We do not require extensive documentation, guarantors or large deposits. A longer commitment on your end helps us to provide you with better prices.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table v2\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<th class=\"title\">\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><span class=\"gold\">Gold</span> Membership</p>\r\n<p class=\"price\">$690 One-Time Fee</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</th>\r\n<th colspan=\"2\">\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><span class=\"silver\">Silver</span> Membership</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"bronze\">Bronze</span> Membership</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p class=\"price\">$29 One-Time Fee</p>\r\n<p class=\"price\">No Fee*</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"2\"><em>*Bronze members must move in on <strong>the first day</strong> of the month</em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<th>1-12 Months</th>\r\n<th>4+ Months</th>\r\n<th>1-3 Months</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Executive + Bath)</th>\r\n<td>$1990</td>\r\n<td>$2150</td>\r\n<td>$2290</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private</th>\r\n<td>$1730</td>\r\n<td>$1890</td>\r\n<td>$2050</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>2-person (Executive)</th>\r\n<td>$990</td>\r\n<td>$1100</td>\r\n<td>$1200</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>2-person (Basic)</th>\r\n<td>$930</td>\r\n<td>$1050</td>\r\n<td>$1150</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Multi-person</th>\r\n<td>$790</td>\r\n<td>$950</td>\r\n<td>$1050</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"5\">See the benefits of Bronze, Silver, and Gold Membership <a class=\"red\" href=\"../memberships\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">here</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div class=\"center\"><a class=\"button2\" href=\"join-us\">Get your exclusive offer now</a></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Availability: Year-round / Minimum stay of 1 month / Month-to-month payment options available / Minimum age 18 / 30-day cancellation notice with Gold Membership</strong></p>\";}}', '', 'a:4:{i:0;s:3:\"180\";i:1;s:3:\"211\";i:2;s:3:\"187\";i:3;s:3:\"178\";}', '', '<div class=\"txt\">\r\n<h1 class=\"center\">The East Williamsburg Move-In Guide</h1>\r\n<h2><strong><em>Welcome to Outpost Club! This is a guide to make your move in successful. We&rsquo;ve done this many times before so we know the drill! To start, here is your address: 118 Kingsland ave, Brooklyn, NY, 11222</em></strong></h2>\r\n<hr class=\"hr\" />\r\n<h3>House Leader</h3>\r\n<p>First, get to know your house leader. They will be your point of contact for questions and concerns.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div class=\"fx w vc ch2\">\r\n<div><img style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"../files/uploads/august_lock.gif\" alt=\"\" />\r\n<p>How to use the August lock</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h3>Getting in the Building</h3>\r\n<p>All exterior and interior doors are locked with an August Lock. An August Lock is an electronic lock that uses an application called <a class=\"green\" href=\"http://august.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>August</strong></a>&nbsp;that you can use to unlock it. Find it in the app store, create an account, and ask your house leader to give you access.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Wifi</h3>\r\n<p>As always, you need wifi. The wifi name is Outpost (or some variation of that) and the password is befreenyc (all lower case).</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>ID</h3>\r\n<p>For our records and according to state law, we&rsquo;ll need a picture of your photo ID. Either a national ID or a passport will work. The house leader will take a picture of it when you move in.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Communication With Other Residents</h3>\r\n<p>We use facebook messenger to communicate, so the house leader will need to add you to the group. If you don&rsquo;t have a facebook, please continually check in with the house leader to see if there is important house news you need to know.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>See The House</h3>\r\n<p>The house leader will show you your room (if they haven&rsquo;t already). Note your bed number, which can be found on your bed frame. Take a look at the house with the house leader. If you would like to lock away your valuables, use the lockers in the basement. Outpost Club is not responsible for the safety of your valuables and we do not provide locks, just lockers.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Kitchen</h3>\r\n<p>You&rsquo;ll need a section of the fridge, which is partition by area so that everyone has equal access.&nbsp;If you open the fridge, you&rsquo;ll see each section has a letter and a number corresponding with your bed. Use this area of the fridge for your items, and talk to others in the house if you need more space. This goes for the cabinets as well: find your section, which will be labeled by your bed number.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Events</h3>\r\n<p>The Outpost Club will also be holding events at your place and at all the Outpost Club locations, so make sure to ask the house leader about any upcoming events. Additionally we have a facebook group for all Outpost Club members in New York. This group has announcement about events, opportunities in New York, general announcements, and more good stuff.&nbsp;<a class=\"green\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/groups/outpostclub/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>You can request to join that group here</strong></a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Cleanliness</h3>\r\n<p>The common spaces of the house are used by a lot of people so please keep them clean! There are some easy ways to think about cleanliness at Outpost Club:</p>\r\n<ul data-rte-list=\"default\">\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Leave rooms in the condition that you found them</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Clean up after yourself</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Do not leave your personal stuff out in common areas if you are not going to return immediately</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>When it\'s your turn to contribute, contribute! Check the cleaning boards for your day of resposibilities, and if your name is not there</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Additionally, the notes around the house are there to reduce confusion and make the community run smoothly, so follow the notes!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Mail</h3>\r\n<p>Make sure to address all mail to:</p>\r\n<p><strong>118 Kingsland ave, Brooklyn NY, 11222, Apartment 1, 2,&nbsp;Rear</strong></p>\r\n<p>Address the mail to the correct apartment to ensure the mail man/women delivers it successfully. The House Leader checks the mail periodically throughout the week, but if you know something has arrived and you need it sooner, ask your house leader</p>\r\n<p>If you are receiving a package, there are many ways it might be delivered due to the numurous delivery methods:</p>\r\n<ul data-rte-list=\"default\">\r\n<li>\r\n<p>The package may be left in the hallway by the delivery man/women, in which case you can pick it up on the way into the house</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>The package may have been accepted by another member of the house, in which case you can pick it up when you get inside the house</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>The package may have been left outside in a concealed location by the delivery man/women, in which case the delivery man/woman will leave a note on the front door informing you where the package was left</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>The package may have been attempted to be delivery but they could not becuase no one answered the door, it was raining so they couldn\'t leave it outside or other various factors, in which case they will put a note on the door saying where you can pcik up the package, or that they will try to deliver it again in the coming days.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Regardless of method, please:</p>\r\n<ul data-rte-list=\"default\">\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Copy and paste the text below into the \"delivery instructions part of your order:</p>\r\n<ul data-rte-list=\"default\">\r\n<li>\r\n<p>\"Code to the front door is (ENTER DOOR CODE HERE) if you can not leave the package inside, please either return the package to the delivery center where I can pick it up or (ENTER OPTION 2 IF DESIRED)\"</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Continually track the package</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Give the delivery service the code to the house</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Attempt to be their when it arrives,</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Do eveything from your end to ensure it\'s successful delivery.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Outpost Club is not responsible for delayed, lost, or damaged packages.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Cancellations And Extensions</h3>\r\n<p>We have a 15 days notice of cancellation policy. Please give us notice of cancellation 15 days before your next pay period. If the cancellation is drastically changing the committed stay-length, we will apply monthly pricing to your new commitment length. The difference in price will be deducted from your security deposit.</p>\r\n<p>Additionally, we happy to have our members stay longer, however we can\'t extend you stay if we don\'t know about your extension! As soon as you are aware of the need to extend your stay, let us know by emailing bookings@outpost-club.com.&nbsp;<strong>If you have not committed to an extension, your bed can be reserved by anyone admitted to Outpost Club.</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><em>That\'s all for now! Always look out for updates from Outpost, they will come through the Facebook group, the Facebook messenger, via email, or from the house leader.</em></h2>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"center\"><a class=\"button2\" href=\"current-members\">Return to Current Members Page</a></div>\r\n<hr class=\"hr\" />', 0, '0.00000000', '0.00000000', 0, '', NULL),
(157, 253, NULL, 'the-ridgewood-house', 'ridgewood-house-outpost-club', 'The Ridgewood House', 'Rooms for Rent in Ridgewood, Queens, Shared & Private	', 'A warm home in a dynamic Ridgewood community', 'The Ridgewood House', '<p>Ridgewood, Queens</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;Private rooms from $890</p>', '<h1 class=\"h1\">The Ridgewood House</h1>\r\n<h4>A Bustling Block In A Dynamic Ridgewood Community</h4>', '<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">THE SCOOP</h6>\r\n<p>The Ridgewood House is perfectly situated so you can easily explore both Queens and Brooklyn! This Queens neighborhood is home to many local bars and restaurants, so you won&rsquo;t need to go far to find your next bite or favorite cocktail. This house is also a short walk away from trendy Brooklyn neighborhoods like East Williamsburg and Bushwick, so you can explore two burroughs without hopping on the subway. This home is a five-unit property, with three units furnished.</p>\r\n<p>The house is a five-unit property, with split-unit heating and air conditioning, stainless steel appliances and hardwood floors. Our coliving units are fully furnished, while whole units are unfurnished.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">THE LOCATION</h6>\r\n<p>This space is in the homey neighborhood of Ridgewood bordering Brooklyn, known for its relaxed pace and historic streets. The Ridgewood House is a 2-minute walk from the Seneca Ave. subway station and a 20-minute ride into central Williamsburg, or a 30-minute ride into the Lower East Side.</p>\r\n</div>', 5, '', 'ridgewood-bedroom-4.jpg', 'ridgewood-bedroom-4.jpg', '', 413, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Ridgewood House', 0, 0, 'a:7:{i:1;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:20:\"Throughout the house\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:701:\"<p>{throughout}</p>\r\n<table class=\"table v2\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<th>12+ Months</th>\r\n<th>4-11 Months</th>\r\n<th>1-3 Months</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Executive + Bath)</th>\r\n<td>$1250</td>\r\n<td>Not Offered</td>\r\n<td>Not Offered</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Standard)</th>\r\n<td>$890</td>\r\n<td>Not Offered</td>\r\n<td>Not Offered</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"5\">\r\n<p>*Prices above do not include utilities&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>**The prices shown indicate <strong>the prices valid for move-in between November 1, 2021, and December 31, 2021.</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div class=\"center\"><a class=\"button2 red\" href=\"join-us\" target=\"_blank\">Apply for free</a></div>\";}i:2;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:12:\"The Bedrooms\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:286:\"<p>Each unit has four bedrooms. In our furnished units the room will come with full amenities. Bedding is available for an additional fee.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Amenities</strong>: memory-foam full-size mattresses, pillows, shelving, hooks and closets/organizational tools.</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:7:{i:0;s:23:\"ridgewood-bedroom-7.jpg\";i:1;s:23:\"ridgewood-bedroom-4.jpg\";i:2;s:23:\"ridgewood-bedroom-3.jpg\";i:3;s:23:\"ridgewood-bedroom-6.jpg\";i:4;s:23:\"ridgewood-bedroom-8.jpg\";i:5;s:23:\"ridgewood-bedroom-1.jpg\";i:6;s:23:\"ridgewood-bedroom-2.jpg\";}}i:3;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:24:\"The kitchens/dining room\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:454:\"<p>The kitchens in each unit have gas stoves and stainless steel appliances. The furnished units are stocked with plenty of supplies, so you can meal prep or cook dinner with your housemates without a worry.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Amenities</strong> in furnished units include microwaves, dishwashers, large sinks, coffee makers, blenders, plenty of cabinets, cookware, tableware, cutting boards and anything else you would need in a kitchen.</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:3:{i:0;s:23:\"ridgewood-kitchen-1.jpg\";i:1;s:23:\"ridgewood-kitchen-3.jpg\";i:2;s:23:\"ridgewood-kitchen-2.jpg\";}}i:4;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:20:\" The (co)living room\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:328:\"<p>The living rooms are at the heart of each unit within the Ridgewood House. The furnished units have comfy couches and TVs, equipped with everything you need to relax.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Living room also includes:</strong> Additional seating, pillows, lamps.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Tech:</strong> Google Chromecast.</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:3:{i:0;s:24:\"ridgewood-coliving-1.jpg\";i:1;s:24:\"ridgewood-coliving-2.jpg\";i:2;s:24:\"ridgewood-coliving-3.jpg\";}}i:5;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:13:\"The bathrooms\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:175:\"<p>Two of the bedrooms in each unit have private bathrooms, the remaining two bedrooms share a bathroom.</p>\r\n<p>In the furnished unit we provide many bathroom essentials.</p>\";s:6:\"images\";a:2:{i:0;s:24:\"ridgewood-bathroom-1.jpg\";i:1;s:24:\"ridgewood-bathroom-3.jpg\";}}i:6;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:19:\"Additional benefits\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:178:\"<p><strong>We screen all candidates before approving applications so that there are no worries about moving into a new place with new people &mdash; only excitement!</strong></p>\";}i:7;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:6:\"Prices\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:829:\"<table class=\"table v2\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<th>12+ Months</th>\r\n<th>4-11 Months</th>\r\n<th>1-3 Months</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Executive + Bath)</th>\r\n<td>$1250</td>\r\n<td>Not Offered</td>\r\n<td>Not Offered</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Standard)</th>\r\n<td>$890</td>\r\n<td>Not Offered</td>\r\n<td>Not Offered</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"5\">\r\n<p>*Prices above do not include utilities</p>\r\n<p>**The prices shown indicate <strong>the prices valid for move-in between <strong>November 1</strong>, 2021, and December 31, 2021.</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div class=\"center\"><a class=\"button2 red\" href=\"join-us\" target=\"_blank\">Apply for free</a></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Availability: Year-round / Minimum stay of 12 months / Minimum age 18</strong></p>\";}}', '', '', '', '<div class=\"txt\">\r\n<h1 class=\"center\">Ridgewood Move-In Guide</h1>\r\n<h2><em><strong>Welcome to Outpost Club! This is a guide to make your move in successful. We&rsquo;ve done this many times before so we know the drill! To start, here is your address: 719 Seneca Ave, Flushing, NY, 11385</strong></em></h2>\r\n<h3><strong>House Leader</strong></h3>\r\n<p>First, get to know your house leader. They will be your point of contact for questions and concerns.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div class=\"fx w vc ch2\">\r\n<div><img style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"../files/uploads/august_lock.gif\" alt=\"\" />\r\n<p>How to use the August Lock</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h3>Getting In The Building</h3>\r\n<p>The code to the outside door is 1212. All interior doors are locked with an August Lock. An August Lock is an electronic lock that uses an application called <strong><a class=\"green\" href=\"http://august.com/\" target=\"_blank\">August</a></strong>&nbsp;that you can use to unlock it. Find it in the app store, create an account, and ask your house leader to give you access.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Wifi</strong></h3>\r\n<p>As always, you need wifi. The wifi name is Outpost (or some variation of that) and the password is befreenyc (all lower case).</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><strong>ID</strong></h3>\r\n<p>For our records and according to state law, we&rsquo;ll need a picture of your photo ID. Either a national ID or a passport will work. The house leader will take a picture of it when you move in.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Communication with Other Residents</h3>\r\n<p>We use facebook messenger to communicate, so the house leader will need to add you to the group. If you don&rsquo;t have a facebook, please continually check in with the house leader to see if there is important house news you need to know.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>See the House</h3>\r\n<p>The house leader will show you your room (if they haven&rsquo;t already). Note your bed number, which can be found on your bed frame. Take a look at the house with the house leader. If you would like to lock away your valuables, use the lockers in the basement. Outpost Club is not responsible for the safety of your valuables and we do not provide locks, just lockers.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Kitchen</h3>\r\n<p>You&rsquo;ll need a section of the fridge, which is partition by area so that everyone has equal access.&nbsp;If you open the fridge, you&rsquo;ll see each section has a letter and a number corresponding with your bed. Use this area of the fridge for your items, and talk to others in the house if you need more space. This goes for the cabinets as well: find your section, which will be labeled by your bed number.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Events</h3>\r\n<p>The Outpost Club will also be holding events at your place and at all the Outpost Club locations, so make sure to ask the house leader about any upcoming events. Additionally we have a facebook group for all Outpost Club members in New York. This group has announcement about events, opportunities in New York, general announcements, and more good stuff.&nbsp;<strong><a class=\"green\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/groups/outpostclub/\" target=\"_blank\">You can request to join that group here</a></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Cleanliness</h3>\r\n<p>The common spaces of the house are used by a lot of people so please keep them clean! There are some easy ways to think about cleanliness at Outpost Club:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Leave rooms in the condition that you found them&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Clean up after yourself</li>\r\n<li>Do not leave your personal stuff out in common areas if you are not going to return immediately</li>\r\n<li>When it\'s your turn to contribute, contribute! Check the cleaning boards for your day of resposibilities, and if your name is not there&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Additionally, the notes around the house are there to reduce confusion and make the community run smoothly, so follow the notes!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Mail</h3>\r\n<p>Make sure to address all mail to:</p>\r\n<p><strong>719 Seneca Ave, Flushing, NY, 11385, Apartment, 1, 2, or 3</strong></p>\r\n<p>Address the mail to the correct apartment to ensure the mail man/women delivers it successfully. The House Leader checks the mail periodically throughout the week, but if you know something has arrived and you need it sooner, ask your house leader</p>\r\n<p><strong>If you are receiving a package, there are many ways it might be delivered due to the </strong>numurous<strong> delivery methods:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The package may be left in the hallway by the delivery man/women, in which case you can pick it up on the way into the house</li>\r\n<li>The package may have been accepted by another member of the house, in which case you can pick it up when you get inside the house</li>\r\n<li>The package may have been left outside in a concealed location by the delivery man/women, in which case the delivery man/woman will leave a note on the front door informing you where the package was left</li>\r\n<li>The package may have been attempted to be delivery but they could not becuase no one answered the door, it was raining so they couldn\'t leave it outside or other various factors, in which case they will put a note on the door saying where you can pcik up the package, or that they will try to deliver it again in the coming days.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Regardless of method, please:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Copy and paste the text below into the \"delivery instructions part of your order:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\"Code to the front door is (ENTER DOOR CODE HERE) if you can not leave the package inside, please either return the package to the delivery center where I can pick it up or (ENTER OPTION 2 IF DESIRED)\"</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Continually track the package</li>\r\n<li>Give the delivery service the code to the house</li>\r\n<li>Attempt to be their when it arrives,</li>\r\n<li>Do everything from your end to ensure it\'s successful delivery.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Outpost Club is not responsible for delayed, lost, or damaged packages.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Cancellations and Extensions</strong></h3>\r\n<p>We have a 15 days notice of cancellation policy. Please give us notice of cancellation 15 days before your next pay period. If the cancellation is drastically changing the committed stay-length, we will apply monthly pricing to your new commitment length. The difference in price will be deducted from your security deposit.</p>\r\n<p>Additionally, we happy to have our members stay longer, however we can\'t extend you stay if we don\'t know about your extension! As soon as you are aware of the need to extend your stay, let us know by emailing bookings@outpost-club.com.&nbsp;<strong>If you have not committed to an extension, your bed can be reserved by anyone admitted to Outpost Club.</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><em>That\'s all for now! Always look out for updates from Outpost, they will come through the Facebook group, the Facebook messenger, via email, or from the house leader.</em></h2>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"center\"><a class=\"button2\" href=\"current-members\">Return to Current Members Page</a></div>\r\n<hr class=\"hr\" />', 2, '40.70253000', '-73.90694000', 0, '', NULL),
(368, 0, NULL, 'the-ridgewood-house-2r-3d-tour', '', 'The Ridgewood House (2R) 3D tour', 'The Ridgewood House (2R) 3D tour', '', 'The Ridgewood House (2R) 3D tour', '', '', '<h1>The Ridgewood House (2R) 3D tour</h1>\r\n<p><iframe style=\"margin-top: 1em;\" src=\"https://geocv.com/Xj2mYlrLMa6CcWLal1zpLQ\" width=\"100%\" height=\"500\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"> </iframe></p>', 9, '', '', '', '', 372, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'The Ridgewood House (2R) 3D tour', 0, 0, 'a:0:{}', '', '', '', '', 0, '0.00000000', '0.00000000', 0, '', NULL),
