up for you or returned to a distribution center for a later delivery. It&rsquo;s your responsibility to track your packages and make sure you&rsquo;re home to receive them when necessary.</p>\r\n</div>', 8, '', '', '', '', 176, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'The Flatbush House Move-In Guide', 0, 0, 'a:0:{}', '', '', '', '', 0, '0.00000000', '0.00000000', 0, '', NULL),
(176, 0, NULL, 'move-in-guide-the-bushwick-house', '', 'The Bushwick House Move-In Guide', 'The Bushwick House Move-In Guide', 'Welcome to Outpost Club! This is a guide to make your move in successful', 'The Bushwick House Move-In Guide', '', '', '<div class=\"txt\">\r\n<h1 class=\"\">The Bushwick House Move-In Guide</h1>\r\n<h2><em><strong>1102 Putnam Ave, Brooklyn, NY 11221</strong></em></h2>\r\n<hr class=\"hr\" />\r\n<h3><strong>The Community</strong></h3>\r\n<p>Welcome to Outpost! We&rsquo;re glad you&rsquo;re here. Coliving isn&rsquo;t just about having roommates or sharing a kitchen &mdash; it&rsquo;s about recognizing that we can do more, accomplish more and be more when we work together.</p>\r\n<p>We communicate with each other via our house&rsquo;s Messenger group, which your House Leader will add you upon arrival. We also offer an Outpost Slack channel where you can find other members with similar interests and meet new people in your area. We send out relevant updates and information via email, so keep an eye out!</p>\r\n<p>Your <strong>Member Portal</strong> is where you can RSVP for community events, submit maintenance and cleaning requests and access important documents. <a class=\"green\" href=\"../user/login\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Find it here</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Your <strong>House Leader</strong> will be your main point of contact with Outpost. Here&rsquo;s what they can help you with:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Info about community activities</li>\r\n<li>Restocking supplies</li>\r\n<li>Questions about Outpost</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>We have a lot of activities to help you get involved with our community and get to know the city. Pay attention to your Member Portal and your house&rsquo;s Messenger group to keep up with what&rsquo;s going on, or just ask your House Leader!</p>\r\n<h3><strong>The Logistics</strong></h3>\r\n<h3>Moving In</h3>\r\n<p>To unlock and enter the building, use the code <strong>#5875</strong>. Once inside, you&rsquo;ll use the August app to access your individual unit. Download the app and sign up for an account, and your House Leader will give you access. Here&rsquo;s how to use the app:</p>\r\n<div class=\"fx w vc ch2\">\r\n<div><img style=\"width: 70%; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"../files/uploads/august_lock.gif\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>When you move in, your House Leader will give you a tour of the house and talk to you a bit about the Outpost community. They&rsquo;ll also:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Take a photo of your ID (for our records and according to state law)</li>\r\n<li>Add you to your Messenger group</li>\r\n<li>Assign you cupboard and refrigerator space, according to your room number.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The WiFi name is Outpost (or something similar) and the password is <strong>befreenyc</strong>.</p>\r\n<h3>Living at Outpost</h3>\r\n<p>You&rsquo;ll find helpful information linked above in our Guide to Responsible Coliving, but there are a few more things you should know:</p>\r\n<p><strong>Recycling is required</strong>, and New York City has strict guidelines. Watch the video below to see what you should recycle:</p>\r\n<iframe style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/EUyVELb5PzY\" width=\"70%\" height=\"400\"></iframe><br /><br />\r\n<p><strong>Cleanliness is also required.</strong> That&rsquo;s especially true of common areas, including shared rooms. Here are some easy ways to think about cleanliness at Outpost:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Leave rooms in the condition in which you found them</li>\r\n<li>Clean up after yourself</li>\r\n<li>Don&rsquo;t leave your belongings in the common area unless you&rsquo;re returning immediately</li>\r\n<li>Pay attention to the signs around the house: They&rsquo;re there to help our community run smoothly!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Outpost is not responsible for lost or damaged mail or packages.</strong> Your House Leader will check the mail regularly. Make sure to put your full address, including your outside door code, in the delivery field when you order something. You may find your package left inside the main door, concealed outside, with a roommate who picked it up for you or returned to a distribution center for a later delivery. It&rsquo;s your responsibility to track your packages and make sure you&rsquo;re home to receive them when necessary.</p>\r\n</div>', 8, '', '', '', '', 177, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'The Bushwick House Move-In Guide', 0, 0, 'a:0:{}', '', '', '', '', 0, '0.00000000', '0.00000000', 0, '', NULL),
(177, 0, NULL, 'move-in-guide-the-east-williamsburg-house', '', 'The East Williamsburg House Move-In Guide', 'The East Williamsburg House Move-In Guide', 'Welcome to Outpost Club! This is a guide to make your move in successful', 'The East Williamsburg House Move-In Guide', '', '', '<div class=\"txt\">\r\n<h1 class=\"center\">The East Williamsburg Move-In Guide</h1>\r\n<h2><strong><em>Welcome to Outpost Club! This is a guide to make your move in successful. We&rsquo;ve done this many times before so we know the drill! To start, here is your address: 118 Kingsland ave, Brooklyn, NY, 11222</em></strong></h2>\r\n<hr class=\"hr\" />\r\n<h3>House Leader</h3>\r\n<p>First, get to know your house leader. They will be your point of contact for questions and concerns.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div class=\"fx w vc ch2\">\r\n<div><img style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"../files/uploads/august_lock.gif\" alt=\"\" />\r\n<p>How to use the August lock</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h3>Getting in the Building</h3>\r\n<p>All exterior and interior doors are locked with an August Lock. An August Lock is an electronic lock that uses an application called <a class=\"green\" href=\"http://august.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>August</strong></a>&nbsp;that you can use to unlock it. Find it in the app store, create an account, and ask your house leader to give you access.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Wifi</h3>\r\n<p>As always, you need wifi. The wifi name is Outpost (or some variation of that) and the password is befreenyc (all lower case).</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>ID</h3>\r\n<p>For our records and according to state law, we&rsquo;ll need a picture of your photo ID. Either a national ID or a passport will work. The house leader will take a picture of it when you move in.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Communication With Other Residents</h3>\r\n<p>We use facebook messenger to communicate, so the house leader will need to add you to the group. If you don&rsquo;t have a facebook, please continually check in with the house leader to see if there is important house news you need to know.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>See The House</h3>\r\n<p>The house leader will show you your room (if they haven&rsquo;t already). Note your bed number, which can be found on your bed frame. Take a look at the house with the house leader. If you would like to lock away your valuables, use the lockers in the basement. Outpost Club is not responsible for the safety of your valuables and we do not provide locks, just lockers.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Kitchen</h3>\r\n<p>You&rsquo;ll need a section of the fridge, which is partition by area so that everyone has equal access.&nbsp;If you open the fridge, you&rsquo;ll see each section has a letter and a number corresponding with your bed. Use this area of the fridge for your items, and talk to others in the house if you need more space. This goes for the cabinets as well: find your section, which will be labeled by your bed number.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Events</h3>\r\n<p>The Outpost Club will also be holding events at your place and at all the Outpost Club locations, so make sure to ask the house leader about any upcoming events. Additionally we have a facebook group for all Outpost Club members in New York. This group has announcement about events, opportunities in New York, general announcements, and more good stuff.&nbsp;<a class=\"green\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/groups/outpostclub/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>You can request to join that group here</strong></a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Cleanliness</h3>\r\n<p>The common spaces of the house are used by a lot of people so please keep them clean! There are some easy ways to think about cleanliness at Outpost Club:</p>\r\n<ul data-rte-list=\"default\">\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Leave rooms in the condition that you found them</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Clean up after yourself</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Do not leave your personal stuff out in common areas if you are not going to return immediately</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>When it\'s your turn to contribute, contribute! Check the cleaning boards for your day of resposibilities, and if your name is not there</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Additionally, the notes around the house are there to reduce confusion and make the community run smoothly, so follow the notes!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Mail</h3>\r\n<p>Make sure to address all mail to:</p>\r\n<p><strong>118 Kingsland ave, Brooklyn NY, 11222, Apartment 1, 2,&nbsp;Rear</strong></p>\r\n<p>Address the mail to the correct apartment to ensure the mail man/women delivers it successfully. The House Leader checks the mail periodically throughout the week, but if you know something has arrived and you need it sooner, ask your house leader</p>\r\n<p>If you are receiving a package, there are many ways it might be delivered due to the numurous delivery methods:</p>\r\n<ul data-rte-list=\"default\">\r\n<li>\r\n<p>The package may be left in the hallway by the delivery man/women, in which case you can pick it up on the way into the house</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>The package may have been accepted by another member of the house, in which case you can pick it up when you get inside the house</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>The package may have been left outside in a concealed location by the delivery man/women, in which case the delivery man/woman will leave a note on the front door informing you where the package was left</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>The package may have been attempted to be delivery but they could not becuase no one answered the door, it was raining so they couldn\'t leave it outside or other various factors, in which case they will put a note on the door saying where you can pcik up the package, or that they will try to deliver it again in the coming days.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Regardless of method, please:</p>\r\n<ul data-rte-list=\"default\">\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Copy and paste the text below into the \"delivery instructions part of your order:</p>\r\n<ul data-rte-list=\"default\">\r\n<li>\r\n<p>\"Code to the front door is (ENTER DOOR CODE HERE) if you can not leave the package inside, please either return the package to the delivery center where I can pick it up or (ENTER OPTION 2 IF DESIRED)\"</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Continually track the package</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Give the delivery service the code to the house</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Attempt to be their when it arrives,</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Do eveything from your end to ensure it\'s successful delivery.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Outpost Club is not responsible for delayed, lost, or damaged packages.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Cancellations And Extensions</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Gold Membership</strong>: We have a 30-day notice of cancellation policy. Please give us notice of cancellation 30 days before your next pay period. You will be assessed a $250 fee for canceling your membership before the end of your membership agreement.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Bronze/Silver Membership:</strong>: We do not permit cancellations before the end of your membership agreement.</p>\r\n<p>Additionally, we happy to have our members stay longer; however, we can\'t extend <a href=\"mailto:customer.service@outpost-club.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">customer.service@outpost-club.com</a>&nbsp;you stay if we don\'t know about your extension! As soon as you are aware of the need to extend your stay, let us know by emailing customer.service@outpost-club.com. If you have not committed to an extension, your bed can be reserved by anyone admitted to Outpost Club.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><em>That\'s all for now! Always look out for updates from Outpost, they will come through the Facebook group, the Facebook messenger, via email, or from the house leader.</em></h2>\r\n</div>', 8, '', '', '', '', 272, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The East Williamsburg House Move-In Guide', 0, 0, 'a:0:{}', '', '', '', '', 0, '0.00000000', '0.00000000', 0, '', NULL),
(178, 0, NULL, 'the-downtown-brooklyn-house-move-in-guide', '', 'The Downtown Brooklyn House Move-In Guide', 'The Downtown Brooklyn House Move-In Guide', 'Welcome to Outpost Club! This is a guide to make your move in successful', 'The Downtown Brooklyn House Move-In Guide', '', '', '<div class=\"txt\">\r\n<h1 class=\"\">The Downtown Brooklyn House Move-In Guide</h1>\r\n<h2><em><strong>Welcome to Outpost Club! This is a guide to make your move-in successful. We&rsquo;ve done this many times before so we know the drill! To start, here is your address: <a class=\"green\" href=\"https://www.google.com/maps/place/126+Douglass+St,+Brooklyn,+NY+11217/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x89c25a5149796edd:0x96878e836ad44f9f?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwiE686AyczbAhWJpFkKHTg1BoIQ8gEIJjAA\" target=\"_blank\">126 Douglass Street, Brooklyn, NY, 11217</a></strong></em></h2>\r\n<hr class=\"hr\" />\r\n<div class=\"fx w vc ch2\">\r\n<div><img style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"../files/uploads/august_lock.gif\" alt=\"\" />\r\n<p>How to use an August Lock</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h3>Getting In The Building</h3>\r\n<p>All exterior and interior doors are locked with an August Lock. An August Lock is an electronic lock that uses an application called <strong><a class=\"green\" href=\"http://august.com/\" target=\"_blank\">August</a></strong>&nbsp;that you can use to unlock it. Find it in the app store, create an account, and ask your house manager to give you access. If your phone is dead or August will not work with your phone, the outdoor code to the first floor is <strong>#</strong><strong>0126</strong>. For the ground floor entrance, you will be given the front door code via email.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Wifi</h3>\r\n<p>As always, you need wifi. The wifi name is <strong>Outpost Club</strong>&nbsp;and the password is <strong>befreenyc</strong> (all lower case).</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>ID</h3>\r\n<p>For our records and according to state law, we&rsquo;ll need a picture of your photo ID. Either a national ID or a passport will work. The house leader will take a picture of it when you move in.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Communication With Other Residents</h3>\r\n<p>We use facebook messenger to communicate, so the house leader will need to add you to the group. If you don&rsquo;t have a facebook, please continually check in with the house leader to see if there is important house news you need to know.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>See the House</h3>\r\n<p>The house leader will show you your room (if they haven&rsquo;t already). Note your room-letter, which can be found on your bedroom door frame. Take a look at the house with the house leader. If you would like to lock away your valuables, use the lockers located in the basement.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Kitchen</h3>\r\n<p>You&rsquo;ll need a section of the fridge, which is partition by area so that everyone has equal access.&nbsp;If you open the fridge, you&rsquo;ll see each section has a letter and a number corresponding with your bed. Use this area of the fridge for your items, and talk to others in the house if you need more space. This goes for the cabinets as well: find your section, which will be labeled by your bed number.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Events</h3>\r\n<p>The Outpost Club will also be holding events at your place and at all the Outpost Club locations, so make sure to ask the house leader about any upcoming events. Additionally we have a facebook group for all Outpost Club members in New York. This group has announcement about events, opportunities in New York, general announcements, and more good stuff.&nbsp;<strong><a class=\"green\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/groups/outpostclub/\" target=\"_blank\">You can request to join that group here</a></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Cleanliness</h3>\r\n<p>The common spaces of the house are used by a lot of people so please keep them clean! There are some easy ways to think about cleanliness at Outpost Club:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Leave rooms in the condition that you found them&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Clean up after yourself</li>\r\n<li>Do not leave your personal stuff out in common areas if you are not going to return immediately</li>\r\n<li>When it\'s your turn to contribute, contribute! Check the cleaning boards for your day of resposibilities, and if your name is not there&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Additionally, the notes around the house are there to reduce confusion and make the community run smoothly, so follow the notes!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Mail</h3>\r\n<p>Make sure to address all mail to:</p>\r\n<p><em><strong>126 Douglass Street, Brooklyn, NY, 11217, Apartment 1, 2, or 3 (depending on your apartment)</strong></em></p>\r\n<p>Address the mail to the correct apartment to ensure the mail man/women delivers it successfully. The house manager checks the mail periodically throughout the week, but if you know something has arrived and you need it sooner, ask your house manager&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>If you are receiving a package, there are many ways it might be delivered due to the numurous delivery methods:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The package may be left in the hallway by the delivery man/women, in which case you can pick it up on the way into the house</li>\r\n<li>The package may have been accepted by another member of the house, in which case you can pick it up when you get inside the house</li>\r\n<li>The package may have been left outside in a concealed location by the delivery man/women, in which case the delivery man/woman will leave a note on the front door informing you where the package was left</li>\r\n<li>The package may have been attempted to be delivery but they could not becuase no one answered the door, it was raining so they couldn\'t leave it outside or other various factors, in which case they will put a note on the door saying where you can pcik up the package, or that they will try to deliver it again in the coming days.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Regardless of method, please:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Copy and paste the text below into the \"delivery instructions part of your order:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\"Code to the front door is (ENTER DOOR CODE HERE) if you can not leave the package inside, please either return the package to the delivery center where I can pick it up or (ENTER OPTION 2 IF DESIRED)\"</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Continually track the package</li>\r\n<li>Give the delivery service the code to the house</li>\r\n<li>Attempt to be their when it arrives,</li>\r\n<li>Do eveything from your end to ensure it\'s successful delivery.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Outpost Club is not responsible for delayed, lost, or damaged packages.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Cancellations And Extensions</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Gold Membership</strong>: We have a 30-day notice of cancellation policy. Please give us notice of cancellation 30 days before your next pay period. You will be assessed a $250 fee for canceling your membership before the end of your membership agreement.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Bronze/Silver Membership:</strong>: We do not permit cancellations before the end of your membership agreement.</p>\r\n<p>Additionally, we happy to have our members stay longer; however, we can\'t extend <a href=\"mailto:customer.service@outpost-club.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">customer.service@outpost-club.com</a>&nbsp;you stay if we don\'t know about your extension! As soon as you are aware of the need to extend your stay, let us know by emailing customer.service@outpost-club.com. If you have not committed to an extension, your bed can be reserved by anyone admitted to Outpost Club.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><em><strong>That\'s all for now! Always look out for updates from Outpost, they will come through the Facebook group, the Facebook messenger, via email, or from the house leader</strong></em></h2>\r\n</div>', 8, '', '', '', '', 178, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'The Downtown Brooklyn House Move-In Guide', 0, 0, 'a:0:{}', '', '', '', '', 0, '0.00000000', '0.00000000', 0, '', NULL),
