(183, 182, NULL, 'what-happens-to-my-mail-once-i-leave', '', 'What happens to my mail once I leave?', 'What happens to my mail once I leave?', '', 'What happens to my mail once I leave?', '', '', '<p>We know there are a lot of moving parts when packing &amp; preparing to move out, so here&rsquo;s a helpful reminder with important info for changing your mailing address with USPS 7-10 days before move-out:<br /><br />Change Your Address and Other U.S. Post Office Services: <a href=\"https://www.usa.gov/post-office\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://www.usa.gov/post-office</a></p>\r\n<p>*NOTE* The above site is an official website of the US Government! &nbsp;There are lots of scam sites for US Postal Service, Department of Motor Vehicles, etc., that try to make you think they&rsquo;re official US Government sites, and then try to get you to pay for their services. &nbsp;2 things to look for to tell if a site is an official US Government site:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>A site ending in &ldquo;.gov&rdquo; is an official US Government site (as opposed to &ldquo;.com&rdquo; or &ldquo;.co&rdquo; etc). &nbsp;All branches of US Federal government use &ldquo;.gov&rdquo; as domain name</li>\r\n<li>Look at the web address in the browser bar. &nbsp;An official US Government site will start start with &ldquo;https://&rdquo; NOT &ldquo;http://&rdquo; &nbsp;(the S means it is a secure, encrypted site)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.usa.gov/post-office\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://www.usa.gov/post-office</a> has all the info on changing your mailing address, but long story short, the two ways to change your mailing address are:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Change address online at: <a href=\"https://moversguide.usps.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://moversguide.usps.com/</a>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>*NOTE* You will get an immediate email confirmation, but know that if you want to change your address online, there is a $1 charge to a credit or debit card in your name as identity verification &nbsp;&amp; it says right on the site: You don&rsquo;t need to pay a separate company to change your address. Scammers may charge $40 or more to do what you can do for just $1 using the moving section of the official USPS.com website.</li>\r\n<li>Also, if your new address will be outside the US, it is recommended that you use the second method below and go into your local post office&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Go to local post office and request &ldquo;Mover&rsquo;s Guide Packet&rdquo;\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Inside the packet is PS Form 3575. Fill out this change of address form and give it to a postal worker behind the counter (RECOMMENDED IF NEW ADDRESS IS OUTSIDE THE US) or drop it into the letter mail slot inside the post office.</li>\r\n<li>You should receive a confirmation letter at your new address in five business days.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>If mail is still arriving for you 30 days post move-out, Outpost will return mail to post office as &ldquo;return to sender&rdquo;, so IF YOU ARE RECEIVING MAIL AT YOUR OUTPOST HOUSE, be sure to CHANGE/UPDATE YOUR MAILING INFORMATION 5-10 DAYS BEFORE MOVE-OUT</p>', 6, '', '', '', 'change-mailing-address', 198, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'What happens to my mail once I leave?', 0, 0, 'a:0:{}', '', '', '', '', 0, '0.00000000', '0.00000000', 0, '', NULL),
(184, 0, NULL, 'rooms-for-rent-in-brooklyn', '', 'Rooms for rent in brooklyn', 'Rooms for Rent in Brooklyn, NY | Outpost Club', 'Outpost Club has affordable Brooklyn rooms for rent, including private or shared rooms, fully furnished to meet your needs, in neighborhoods such as Bushwick, Flatbush and Williamsburg, with transportation to Manhattan and close to great social, dining, shopping and cultural amenities', 'Rooms For Rent in Brooklyn', '<h1 class=\"h1\">Affordable Rooms for Rent in Brooklyn</h1>', '', '', 13, '', 'downtown_brooklin_big.jpg', '', '', 191, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'Rooms For Rent in Brooklyn', 0, 0, 'a:0:{}', '', '', '', '', 0, '0.00000000', '0.00000000', 0, '', NULL),
(185, 253, 185, 'central-park-manhattan-house ', '', 'The Central Park Manhattan House ', 'The Central Park Manhattan House (NY 10026) | Outpost Club', 'We worked with interior designers to make The Central Park Manhattan House comfortable in every room. ✓ Fully furnished ✓ Security ✓ Gas ✓ Electricity ✓ Water ✓ Wi-Fi ✓ Cleaning and maintenance', 'The Central Park Manhattan House | Outpost Club', '<p>Upper Manhattan, New York</p>\r\n<p>Shared rooms from $850 | Private rooms from $1520</p>', '', '<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">The Scoop</h6>\r\n<p>The Central Park Manhattan House features five units of exclusively designed spaces and is just a 7-minute walk from Central Park.</p>\r\n<p>The house is a newly renovated space with air conditioning in every room, updated appliances and hardwood floors. Each apartment is furnished and comes equipped with everything you&rsquo;ll need to feel at home, from pots and pans to throw pillows. All of the spaces are massive compared to your average New York City apartment.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">The Neighborhood</h6>\r\n<p>Located near the border of the Upper West Side and Harlem in Manhattan, our Central Park Manhattan House is close to plenty of bars, restaurants and cafes.</p>\r\n<p><strong>The house is right around the corner from the 116th Street stop on the A, B and C trains, and a 13-minute walk from the 116th Street stop on the 1 train. </strong></p>\r\n<p>The location is two blocks from Columbia University and a 7-minute wall to Central Park. Check out our neighborhood guide to get a feel of the area!</p>\r\n</div>', 5, '', 'manhattan-main-2.jpg', 'manhattan-background-3-2.jpg', '', 329, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Central Park Manhattan House ', 0, 0, 'a:7:{i:0;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:20:\"Throughout the house\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:764:\"<p>{throughout}</p>\r\n<table class=\"table v2\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<th>12+ Months</th>\r\n<th>5-11 Months</th>\r\n<th>1-4 Months</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Standard+)</th>\r\n<td>$1910</td>\r\n<td>$1990</td>\r\n<td>$2590</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Standard)</th>\r\n<td>$1810</td>\r\n<td>$1890</td>\r\n<td>$2490</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Economy)</th>\r\n<td>$1720</td>\r\n<td>$1800</td>\r\n<td>$2400</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>2-person shared</th>\r\n<td>$850</td>\r\n<td>$890</td>\r\n<td>$950</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"5\">\r\n<p>*Prices above do not include $149/month/person utilities allowance fee</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div class=\"center\"><a class=\"button2 red\" href=\"join-us-manhattan\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Apply for free</a></div>\";}i:1;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:12:\"The Bedrooms\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:337:\"<p>All the bedrooms in the Central Park Manhattan House have been recently renovated. Bedding is available for an additional fee.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Amenities:</strong> memory-foam mattresses (twin-sized for shared rooms, full-sized for single rooms), pillows, shelving, hooks and closets/organizational tools.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:6:{i:0;s:39:\"manhattan-bedroom-2-2.1200x1200-3-2.jpg\";i:1;s:37:\"manhattan-bedroom-2-1.1200x1200-3.jpg\";i:2;s:37:\"manhattan-bedroom-2-1.1200x1200-2.jpg\";i:3;s:35:\"manhattan-bedroom-2.1200x1200-2.jpg\";i:4;s:38:\"manhattan-bedroom-21.1200x1200-4-2.jpg\";i:5;s:38:\"manhattan-bedroom-20.1200x1200-3-2.jpg\";}}i:2;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:24:\"The kitchens/dining room\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:588:\"<p>The kitchen forms the core of the house, and for good reason. In each apartment, the kitchen and dining room are the first rooms you enter. These spaces each have dining room tables and enough space for the entire unit to comfortably gather. These spaces are used for potluck dinners, solo meals and chats in the evening over a glass of wine.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Amenities include</strong> gas stoves, stainless steel fridges, microwaves, large sinks, coffee makers, plenty of cabinets, cookware, tableware, cutting boards, and anything else you would need in a kitchen.</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:4:{i:0;s:36:\"manhattan-kitchen-10.700x700-2-2.jpg\";i:1;s:35:\"manhattan-kitchen-2.700x700-2-2.jpg\";i:2;s:37:\"manhattan-kitchen-2-3.700x700-3-2.jpg\";i:3;s:37:\"manhattan-kitchen-2-2.700x700-2-2.jpg\";}}i:3;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:15:\"The Living Room\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:154:\"<p>Each living room is different, with its own unique mix of space and furniture, but all apartments have 35-inch TV and everything you need to relax.</p>\";s:6:\"images\";a:5:{i:0;s:37:\"manhattan-living-10.1200x1200-2-2.jpg\";i:1;s:36:\"manhattan-living-2.1200x1200-2-2.jpg\";i:2;s:36:\"manhattan-living-2-3.1200x1200-2.jpg\";i:3;s:36:\"manhattan-living-2-1.1200x1200-2.jpg\";i:4;s:36:\"manhattan-living-2-2.1200x1200-2.jpg\";}}i:4;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:13:\"The bathrooms\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:432:\"<p>We provide many bathroom essentials, as well. Each of the apartments has&nbsp;either two full bathrooms or one full bathroom, depending on the number of bedrooms in your apartment, so you&rsquo;ll never have to wait.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Also included:</strong> toilet paper, hand soap and small trash bags, which will never be empty!</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p class=\"h5\">Laundry room</p>\r\n<p>Every apartment has its own washer-dryer combo.</p>\";s:6:\"images\";a:3:{i:0;s:28:\"manhattan-bathroom-2_1-2.jpg\";i:1;s:26:\"manhattan-bathroom-2-3.jpg\";i:2;s:26:\"manhattan-bathroom-1-2.jpg\";}}i:5;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:19:\"Additional benefits\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:178:\"<p><strong>We screen all candidates before approving applications so that there are no worries about moving into a new place with new people &mdash; only excitement!</strong></p>\";}i:6;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:6:\"Prices\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:922:\"<table class=\"table v2\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<th>12+ Months</th>\r\n<th>5-11 Months</th>\r\n<th>1-4 Months</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Standard+)</th>\r\n<td>$1910</td>\r\n<td>$1990</td>\r\n<td>$2590</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Standard)</th>\r\n<td>$1810</td>\r\n<td>$1890</td>\r\n<td>$2490</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Economy)</th>\r\n<td>$1720</td>\r\n<td>$1800</td>\r\n<td>$2400</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>2-person shared</th>\r\n<td>$850</td>\r\n<td>$890</td>\r\n<td>$950</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"5\">\r\n<p>*Prices above do not include $149/month/person utilities allowance fee</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div class=\"center\"><a class=\"button2 red\" href=\"join-us-manhattan\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Apply for free</a></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Availability: Year-round / Minimum stay of 1 month / Month-to-month payment options available / Minimum age 18</strong></p>\";}}', '', '', 'a:3:{i:0;s:3:\"481\";i:1;s:3:\"404\";i:2;s:3:\"280\";}', '<div class=\"txt\">\r\n<h1 class=\"\">The Central Park House Move-In Guide</h1>\r\n<h2><em><strong>350 Manhattan Ave, New York, NY, 10026</strong></em></h2>\r\n<hr class=\"hr\" />\r\n<h3><strong>The Community</strong></h3>\r\n<p>Welcome to Outpost! We&rsquo;re glad you&rsquo;re here. Coliving isn&rsquo;t just about having roommates or sharing a kitchen &mdash; it&rsquo;s about recognizing that we can do more, accomplish more and be more when we work together.</p>\r\n<p>We communicate with each other via our house&rsquo;s Messenger group, which your House Leader will add you upon arrival. We also offer an Outpost Slack channel where you can find other members with similar interests and meet new people in your area. We send out relevant updates and information via email, so keep an eye out!</p>\r\n<p>Your <strong>Member Portal</strong> is where you can RSVP for community events, submit maintenance and cleaning requests and access important documents. <a class=\"green\" href=\"../user/login\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Find it here</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Your <strong>House Leader</strong> will be your main point of contact with Outpost. Here&rsquo;s what they can help you with:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Info about community activities</li>\r\n<li>Restocking supplies</li>\r\n<li>Questions about Outpost</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>We have a lot of activities to help you get involved with our community and get to know the city. Pay attention to your Member Portal and your house&rsquo;s Messenger group to keep up with what&rsquo;s going on, or just ask your House Leader!</p>\r\n<h3><strong>The Logistics</strong></h3>\r\n<h3>Moving In</h3>\r\n<p>The outside code to your house is <strong>#4749</strong>. To access the individual units inside the building you&rsquo;ll be given a key. Make sure to keep it in a safe and secure location, as it is the only way you will be able to unlock your apartment!</p>\r\n<p>When you move in, your House Leader will give you a tour of the house and talk to you a bit about the Outpost community. They&rsquo;ll also:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Take a photo of your ID (for our records and according to state law)</li>\r\n<li>Add you to your Messenger group</li>\r\n<li>Assign you cupboard and refrigerator space, according to your room number.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The WiFi name is Outpost (or something similar) and the password is <strong>befreenyc</strong>.</p>\r\n<h3>Living at Outpost</h3>\r\n<p>You&rsquo;ll find helpful information linked above in our Guide to Responsible Coliving, but there are a few more things you should know:</p>\r\n<p><strong>Recycling is required</strong>, and New York City has strict guidelines. Watch the video below to see what you should recycle:</p>\r\n<iframe style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/EUyVELb5PzY\" width=\"70%\" height=\"400\"></iframe><br /><br />\r\n<p><strong>Cleanliness is also required.</strong> That&rsquo;s especially true of common areas, including shared rooms. Here are some easy ways to think about cleanliness at Outpost:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Leave rooms in the condition in which you found them</li>\r\n<li>Clean up after yourself</li>\r\n<li>Don&rsquo;t leave your belongings in the common area unless you&rsquo;re returning immediately</li>\r\n<li>Pay attention to the signs around the house: They&rsquo;re there to help our community run smoothly!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Outpost is not responsible for lost or damaged mail or packages.</strong> Your House Leader will check the mail regularly. Make sure to put your full address, including your outside door code, in the delivery field when you order something. You may find your package left inside the main door, concealed outside, with a roommate who picked it up for you or returned to a distribution center for a later delivery. It&rsquo;s your responsibility to track your packages and make sure you&rsquo;re home to receive them when necessary.</p>\r\n</div>', 1, '40.80406000', '-73.95706000', 488, '', '2022-07-11 06:28:32'),
