(226, 225, NULL, 'advice-on-how-to-communicate-with-residents', '', 'Advice on how to communicate with residents', 'Advice on how to communicate with residents', '', 'Advice on how to communicate with residents', '', '', '<p>Sometimes communicating with members can be tricky: you know the American saying, &ldquo;the customer is always right.&rdquo; This is sort of true and sort of not true: some customers are simply breaking the rules and we must inform them, and some might feel offended by our actions when we don&rsquo;t even realize it. Because of this, let stick to some simple rules that will help us navigate our conversations with customers.</p>\r\n<h3>Getting approval from the community manager</h3>\r\n<p>If you&rsquo;re ever having trouble with members, or simply need to notify them of something, and need to have a serious conversation with them (in person, over the phone, or written) talk to the community manager first about what you are going to say.</p>\r\n<h3>Always try to talk in-person first</h3>\r\n<p>Like any conversation, the best way to make your point clear is to try to have the conversation in person. The second best form is phone call or facetime, and the third (and last) is text or email.</p>\r\n<h3>Ask for approval before entering bedrooms</h3>\r\n<p>The bedroom can be a sacred and private place for people, so always knock and get permission before entering. If no one responds, you may open the door, but please do not walk in immediately. If no one is there, make sure to leave the door closed, as you found it. People don&rsquo;t like coming home to an open bedroom door!</p>\r\n<p><strong>Lastly, make sure to knock at reasonable hours: after </strong>11am<strong> and before </strong>9pm.</p>\r\n<h3>When in doubt, spread it out</h3>\r\n<p>If you are talking to a member about not following the rules, and they continue to break them, let the community manager know! To give you an understanding of how things will go after that, we will:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Speak to them as Outpost Club management (usually this works, and we have no more issues)</li>\r\n<li>If that doesn&rsquo;t work, we send them a formal warning, notifying them if their actions continue, we reserve the right to discontinue their membership</li>\r\n<li>If all else fails, we ask them to leave, change houses, etc.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>So make sure to keep us updated on a situation, if one occurs!</strong></p>', 12, '', '', '', '', 229, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'Advice on how to communicate with residents', 0, 0, 'a:0:{}', '', '', '', '', 0, '0.00000000', '0.00000000', 0, '', NULL),
(227, 225, NULL, 'how-to-be-the-point-of-contact-at-the-house', '', 'How to be the point of contact at the house', 'How to be the point of contact at the house', '', 'How to be the point of contact at the house', '', '', '<h3>Acting as the point of contact at the house.</h3>\r\n<h3>You are the point of contact at your house for the members</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Anyone has any questions, comments, or concerns</li>\r\n<li>Someone wants to hold an event</li>\r\n<li>If someone wants to extend their stay &nbsp;have them contact the Bookings Department: <a href=\"mailto:bookings@outpost-club.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">bookings@outpost-club.com</a> - have people email this address</li>\r\n<li>There are questions about booking, payment, move-in/move-outs, have them email Valentyn&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:bookings@outpost-club.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">bookings@outpost-club.com</a> - have people email this address</li>\r\n<li>Answer questions/requests from members on Facebook Messenger</li>\r\n<li>You are the manager of the Facebook Messenger (You must add people when they arrive, and remove them when they leave (if they don&rsquo;t leave on their own)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>You are also the point of contact at the house for management</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If something is broken use the <a href=\"https://outpostclub.slack.com/\" target=\"_blank\">#houseissues</a> channel on Slack</li>\r\n<li>You will also act as the communicator to everyone in the house on behalf of Outpost Club, and will relay any messages to the facebook group that you feel are necessary or that Outpost Club management feels is necessary (e.g. &ldquo;please don&rsquo;t leave dishes in the sink&rdquo; or &ldquo;were having an event this sunday&rdquo; or the plumber is coming at 3pm, please let him in&rdquo;)</li>\r\n<li>Make sure to also let people who do not have facebook messenger as well</li>\r\n<li>Answer communications over <a href=\"https://outpostclub.slack.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Slack</a></li>\r\n<li>Every Monday, Tacia will send out a message to the <a href=\"https://outpostclub.slack.com/\" target=\"_blank\">#house-leader-comms</a> group, stating a set of questions and announcements. You are expected to respond the same day with the answers to those questions and confirmation that you received the announcements</li>\r\n</ul>', 12, '', '', '', '', 230, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'How to be the point of contact at the house', 0, 0, 'a:0:{}', '', '', '', '', 0, '0.00000000', '0.00000000', 0, '', NULL),
(228, 0, NULL, 'cleaning-maintenance-and-restocking', '', 'Cleaning, maintenance, and restocking', 'Cleaning, maintenance, and restocking', '', 'Cleaning, maintenance, and restocking', '', '', '', 12, '', '', '', '', 231, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'Cleaning, maintenance, and restocking', 0, 0, 'a:0:{}', '', '', '', '', 0, '0.00000000', '0.00000000', 0, '', NULL),
(229, 228, NULL, 'how-to-keep-the-kitchen-clean', '', 'How to keep the kitchen clean', 'How to keep the kitchen clean', '', 'How to keep the kitchen clean', '', '', '<p><em>Simply put, the house must stay clean at all times, and it&rsquo;s your responsibility as a volunteer to keep it that way. Here is how to do so.</em></p>\r\n<h3>Figure out a cleaning schedule that works for everyone</h3>\r\n<p>Some people use the kitchen, some people don&rsquo;t. Identify those who use the kitchen, and work with them to figure out how to keep a kitchen clean</p>\r\n<h3>IF PEOPLE DON&rsquo;T CLEAN THE KITCHEN you are responsible for keeping it clean. That means</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Take the dishes out of the dishwasher and put them in the cabinets</li>\r\n<li>Take the dishes out of the drying rack and put them in the cabinets</li>\r\n<li>Put dirty dishes that are sitting in the sink in the dishwasher</li>\r\n<li>Take out trash and recycling</li>\r\n<li>Replace the trash and recycling with fresh bags</li>\r\n<li>Clean countertops and tables</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Tactics to make sure people do their dishes</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Speak to people in person, ask them nicely &ldquo;did you happen to leave any dishes in the sink?&rdquo;</li>\r\n<li>Take pictures of the kitchen dirtiness, send them to the facebook group, the clean the kitchen</li>\r\n<li>Sit in the kitchen during breakfast and dinner - when you see people not doing their dishes KINDLY let them know that they must do their dishes, as per their contract</li>\r\n<li>If nothing else works, clean the very dirty kitchen, and let management know that you just cleaned the kitchen. The MINUTE you see kitchen has dishes in the sink, let management (community manager) know to check the cameras, and give them specific time frames. We&rsquo;ll find the person(s) responsible, and we&rsquo;ll give them a formal warning of the breach of their membership agreement.</li>\r\n</ul>', 12, '', '', '', '', 235, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'How to keep the kitchen clean', 0, 0, 'a:0:{}', '', '', '', '', 0, '0.00000000', '0.00000000', 0, '', NULL),
(230, 228, NULL, 'how-to-restock-the-house', '', 'How to Restock the house', 'How to Restock the house', '', 'How to Restock the house', '', '', '<ul>\r\n<li>When items come in the mail for restocking, take it out of the box and put it in it&rsquo;s designated location. (They will be addressed to Oleksander Prykhodko, and they will be coming from Amazon, Boxed (company name), or Target)</li>\r\n<li>If an item is missing from its location, go to the restocking area and replace it. Sometime the item runs out before the cleaners come.</li>\r\n<li>If something needs to be restocked, post in the <a href=\"https://outpostclub.slack.com/\" target=\"_blank\">#restocking</a> channel on slack</li>\r\n</ul>', 12, '', '', '', '', 240, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'How to Restock the house', 0, 0, 'a:0:{}', '', '', '', '', 0, '0.00000000', '0.00000000', 0, '', NULL),
