(248, 253, 248, 'montrose-williamsburg-house', '', 'The Montrose Williamsburg House', 'The Montrose Williamsburg House (NY 11206) | Outpost Club', 'We worked with interior designers to make The Montrose Williamsburg House comfortable in every room. ✓ Fully furnished ✓ Security ✓ Gas ✓ Electricity ✓ Water ✓ Wi-Fi ✓ Cleaning and maintenance', 'The Montrose Williamsburg House | Outpost Club', '<p>Williamsburg, Brooklyn</p>\r\n<p>Private rooms from $1750</p>', '<h1 class=\"h1\">Montrose Williamsburg House</h1>\r\n<h4>A SPACIOUS HOME IN A LIVELY NEIGHBORHOOD</h4>', '<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">The scoop</h6>\r\n<p>Located in the heart of Williamsburg, the Montrose Williamsburg House is just a 19-minute commute into Manhattan, and has plenty of cafes, shops and bars within walking distance. One of our smallest houses in terms of members, it features six bedrooms and four full bathrooms spread across a single level, with a full kitchen, living room and co-working area for members to enjoy.</p>\r\n<p>The house is a newly renovated space inside and out, with split-unit heating and air conditioning, updated appliances and hardwood floors. This house is a one-level, single-unit home, equipped with a full kitchen, living room, co-working area and free laundry facilities. There are four full bathrooms for the six bedrooms, so there&rsquo;s no need to worry about fighting for showers. The space is arranged around the bright and friendly common area, which is massive in comparison to your average New York City apartment.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">Location</h6>\r\n<p>This coliving space is located in the heart of Williamsburg, one of New York City&rsquo;s most desirable locations, and within walking distance of the popular neighborhoods of East Williamsburg and Bushwick.</p>\r\n<p><strong>The Montrose Williamsburg House is a 5-minute walk to the Lorimer St. stop on the J and M trains, a 5-minute walk to the Montrose Ave. stop on the L train and a 6-minute walk to the Broadway stop on the G train. You can be in the Lower East Side in only 19 minutes.</strong></p>\r\n</div>', 5, '', 'livingroom-montrose-williamsburg-5.jpg', 'bedroom-montrose-williamsburg-1.jpg', '', 311, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'The Montrose Williamsburg House', 0, 0, 'a:8:{i:0;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:20:\"Throughout the house\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:606:\"<p>{throughout}</p>\r\n<table class=\"table v2\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<th>12+ Months</th>\r\n<th>5-11 Months</th>\r\n<th>1-4 Months</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Large room with desk)</th>\r\n<td>$1850</td>\r\n<td>$1930</td>\r\n<td>$2630</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Standard)</th>\r\n<td>$1750</td>\r\n<td>$1830</td>\r\n<td>$2530</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"5\">\r\n<p>*Prices above do not include $149/month/person utilities allowance fee</p>\r\n.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div class=\"center\"><a class=\"button2 red\" href=\"online-questionnaire\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Apply for free</a></div>\";}i:1;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:12:\"The bedrooms\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:337:\"<p>There are single and shared bedrooms, depending on availability and your price range. Bedding is available for an additional fee.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Amenities</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>:</strong> memory-foam full-sized mattresses, pillows, shelving, hooks and closets/organizational tools.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:5:{i:0;s:35:\"bedroom-montrose-williamsburg-2.jpg\";i:1;s:35:\"bedroom-montrose-williamsburg-3.jpg\";i:2;s:35:\"bedroom-montrose-williamsburg-4.jpg\";i:3;s:35:\"bedroom-montrose-williamsburg-5.jpg\";i:4;s:35:\"bedroom-montrose-williamsburg-6.jpg\";}}i:2;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:20:\"The co-working space\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:559:\"<p class=\"h5\">The (co)living space</p>\r\n<p>The living room is located in the center of the Montrose Williamsburg House. The living room has comfortable couches and a 55-inch TV (with Netflix!); this is where we host movie nights, game nights and chill hangouts. The space is equipped with everything you need to relax.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>The Living room also includes:</strong> Additional seating, pillows, lamps and decor.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Security:</strong> 24/7 security in common areas.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Tech:</strong> Google Chromecast.</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:5:{i:0;s:38:\"livingroom-montrose-williamsburg-3.jpg\";i:1;s:38:\"livingroom-montrose-williamsburg-1.jpg\";i:2;s:38:\"livingroom-montrose-williamsburg-2.jpg\";i:3;s:38:\"livingroom-montrose-williamsburg-4.jpg\";i:4;s:38:\"livingroom-montrose-williamsburg-5.jpg\";}}i:4;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:24:\"The kitchens/dining room\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:614:\"<p>There is one kitchen in the house, located in the middle of the unit. Because of the design of the Montrose Williamsburg House, this central kitchen fosters a sense of community among all of our members. This open, airy space is used for potluck dinners, solo meals and chats in the evening over a glass of wine.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Amenities include</strong> gas stoves, stainless-steel fridges, microwaves, large sinks, plenty of cabinets, cookware, tableware, cutting boards and anything else you would need in a kitchen.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Security:</strong> 24/7 security in all common areas.</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:1:{i:0;s:33:\"kitchen-montrose-williamsburg.jpg\";}}i:5;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:13:\"The bathrooms\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:581:\"<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We provide many bathroom essentials, as well. There are four full bathrooms in the house so you&rsquo;ll never have to wait. </span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Also included</strong>: toilet paper, hand soap and small garbage bags, which will never run out!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p class=\"h5\">The laundry room</p>\r\n<p>The Montrose Williamsburg House also has a laundry room where members can do their laundry in the comfort of their own home.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Security:</strong> 24/7 security in all common areas, as well as lockers</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:2:{i:0;s:36:\"bathroom-montrose-williamsburg-1.jpg\";i:1;s:36:\"bathroom-montrose-williamsburg-2.jpg\";}}i:6;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:20:\"PERKS AND BENEFITS: \";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:588:\"<div class=\"fx ch3 w perc_advantages\">\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Fast, reliable WiFi</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Regular professional cleaning</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Furnished interiors</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">In-unit laundry</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Keyless entry</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Community events</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Dedicated community manager</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Updated appliances</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Dedicated maintenance team</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\";}i:7;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:6:\"Prices\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:764:\"<table class=\"table v2\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<th>12+ Months</th>\r\n<th>5-11 Months</th>\r\n<th>1-4 Months</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Large room with desk)</th>\r\n<td>$1850</td>\r\n<td>$1930</td>\r\n<td>$2630</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Standard)</th>\r\n<td>$1750</td>\r\n<td>$1830</td>\r\n<td>$2530</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"5\">\r\n<p>*Prices above do not include $149/month/person utilities allowance fee</p>\r\n.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div class=\"center\"><a class=\"button2 red\" href=\"online-questionnaire\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Apply for free</a></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Availability: Year-round / Minimum stay of 1 month / Month-to-month payment options available / Minimum age 18</strong></p>\";}i:8;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:34:\"Welcome to Williamsburg, Brooklyn.\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:640:\"<div>\r\n<p>Walk off the train and into this historic Brooklyn neighborhood that feels like home with its quaint, brownstone-lined streets and vibrant culture. Immerse yourself in the community and you&rsquo;ll find unique locally owned shops, neighbors who are always up for a good conversation, and a rich history worth honoring. The neighborhood features the lively Herbert Von King park, trendy coffee shops like Brooklyn Blend and eclectic cuisine ranging from Caribbean to Japanese. You can explore surrounding neighborhoods like Clinton Hill and Williamsburg by foot, or hop on the subway and be in Manhattan in 30 minutes.</p>\r\n</div>\";}}', '', '', '', '<div class=\"txt\">\r\n<h1 class=\"\">The Montrose House Move-In Guide</h1>\r\n<h2><em><strong>131 Boerum Street, Brooklyn, NY, 11206</strong></em></h2>\r\n<hr class=\"hr\" />\r\n<h3><strong>The Community</strong></h3>\r\n<p>Welcome to Outpost! We&rsquo;re glad you&rsquo;re here. Coliving isn&rsquo;t just about having roommates or sharing a kitchen &mdash; it&rsquo;s about recognizing that we can do more, accomplish more and be more when we work together.</p>\r\n<p>We communicate with each other via our house&rsquo;s Messenger group, which your House Leader will add you upon arrival. We also offer an Outpost Slack channel where you can find other members with similar interests and meet new people in your area. We send out relevant updates and information via email, so keep an eye out!</p>\r\n<p>Your <strong>Member Portal</strong> is where you can RSVP for community events, submit maintenance and cleaning requests and access important documents. <a class=\"green\" href=\"../user/login\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Find it here</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Your <strong>House Leader</strong> will be your main point of contact with Outpost. Here&rsquo;s what they can help you with:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Info about community activities</li>\r\n<li>Restocking supplies</li>\r\n<li>Questions about Outpost</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>We have a lot of activities to help you get involved with our community and get to know the city. Pay attention to your Member Portal and your house&rsquo;s Messenger group to keep up with what&rsquo;s going on, or just ask your House Leader!</p>\r\n<h3><strong>The Logistics</strong></h3>\r\n<h3>Moving In</h3>\r\n<p>The outside code to your house is <strong>#1750</strong>. You&rsquo;ll use the August app to access your unit. Download the app and sign up for an account, and your House Leader will give you access upon arrival.</p>\r\n<p>Here&rsquo;s how to use the app:</p>\r\n<div class=\"fx w vc ch2\">\r\n<div><img style=\"width: 70%; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"../files/uploads/august_lock.gif\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>When you move in, your House Leader will give you a tour of the house and talk to you a bit about the Outpost community. They&rsquo;ll also:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Take a photo of your ID (for our records and according to state law)</li>\r\n<li>Add you to your Messenger group</li>\r\n<li>Assign you cupboard and refrigerator space, according to your room number.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The WiFi name is Outpost (or something similar) and the password is <strong>befreenyc</strong>.</p>\r\n<h3>Living at Outpost</h3>\r\n<p>You&rsquo;ll find helpful information linked above in our Guide to Responsible Coliving, but there are a few more things you should know:</p>\r\n<p><strong>Recycling is required</strong>, and New York City has strict guidelines. Watch the video below to see what you should recycle:</p>\r\n<iframe style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/EUyVELb5PzY\" width=\"70%\" height=\"400\"></iframe><br /><br />\r\n<p><strong>Cleanliness is also required.</strong> That&rsquo;s especially true of common areas, including shared rooms. Here are some easy ways to think about cleanliness at Outpost:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Leave rooms in the condition in which you found them</li>\r\n<li>Clean up after yourself</li>\r\n<li>Don&rsquo;t leave your belongings in the common area unless you&rsquo;re returning immediately</li>\r\n<li>Pay attention to the signs around the house: They&rsquo;re there to help our community run smoothly!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Outpost is not responsible for lost or damaged mail or packages.</strong> Your House Leader will check the mail regularly. Make sure to put your full address, including your outside door code, in the delivery field when you order something. You may find your package left inside the main door, concealed outside, with a roommate who picked it up for you or returned to a distribution center for a later delivery. It&rsquo;s your responsibility to track your packages and make sure you&rsquo;re home to receive them when necessary.</p>\r\n</div>', 2, '40.70598000', '-73.94356000', 493, '', '2022-08-18 11:44:20'),
