(237, 0, NULL, 'private-room-with-a-private-bath-at-the-ridgewood-house', '', '(Ridgewood, Queens, NY 11385)', 'PRIVATE ROOM WITH A PRIVATE BATH AT THE RIDGEWOOD HOUSE', '', 'PRIVATE ROOM WITH A PRIVATE BATH AT THE RIDGEWOOD HOUSE', '', '', '', 11, '', '', '', '', 357, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'PRIVATE ROOM WITH A PRIVATE BATH AT THE RIDGEWOOD HOUSE', 0, 0, 'a:1:{i:0;O:8:\"stdClass\":7:{s:5:\"price\";s:5:\"$1250\";s:7:\"move_in\";s:22:\"by November 1st, 2021 \";s:8:\"min_stay\";s:9:\"12 months\";s:8:\"max_stay\";s:9:\"12 months\";s:3:\"url\";s:19:\"hot-deals-ridgewood\";s:6:\"images\";a:6:{i:0;s:12:\"DSC00680.jpg\";i:1;s:12:\"DSC00677.jpg\";i:2;s:12:\"DSC00653.jpg\";i:3;s:12:\"DSC00686.jpg\";i:4;s:12:\"DSC00629.jpg\";i:5;s:12:\"DSC00670.jpg\";}s:4:\"body\";s:411:\"<p>***Available NOW***</p>\r\n<p>For a limited time only you can get a room at $1250 with ANY length of your stay!</p>\r\n<p>The price is for 1 person per room. A second person in the same room is subject&nbsp;to an additional $200 per month.</p>\r\n<p>Security deposit (the equivalent of a one-month fee) is required and fully refundable after move-out.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;*Prices above do not include utilities&nbsp;</p>\";}}', '', '', '', '', 0, '0.00000000', '0.00000000', 0, '', NULL),
(238, 253, NULL, 'the-south-williamsburg-house', '', 'The South Williamsburg House', 'South Williamsburg (NYC) Room Rentals, Shared Apartments | Outpost Club', 'The South Williamsburg House is the most recent addition to the Outpost Club family', 'The South Williamsburg House | Outpost Club', '<p>South Williamsburg, Brooklyn</p>\r\n<p>Shared rooms&nbsp;from $690| Private rooms from $1650</p>', '<h1 class=\"h1 center\">The South Williamsburg House</h1>\r\n<h4>Modern Living Where Cultures Converge</h4>', '<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">THE SCOOP</h6>\r\n<p>The South Williamsburg House is a&nbsp;recent addition to the Outpost Club family. It features four floors of exclusively designed spaces and is within walking distance of multiple subway lines and plenty of dining and entertainment. We also have a spacious backyard and a rooftop with a view of Manhattan.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">LOCATION</h6>\r\n<p>This coliving space is located where the Brooklyn neighborhoods of Williamsburg, Bushwick and Bed-Stuy meet, in the up-and-coming Broadway area.</p>\r\n<p><strong>The South Williamsburg House is a 1-minute walk to the Flushing Ave. stop on the J, M and Z trains, a 10-minute walk to the Montrose Ave. stop on the L train and a 10-minute walk to the Flushing Ave. stop on the G train.</strong></p>\r\n<p>The central location is near restaurants, bars, coffee shops and more. Check out our neighborhood guide to get a feel for the area!</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">THE SPACE</h6>\r\n<p>The house is a newly renovated space inside and out, with split-unit heating and air conditioning, updated appliances and hardwood floors. This house is equipped with six kitchens, multiple common rooms and a co-working space. All of the common areas are massive in comparison to your average New York City apartment, as is the backyard. There&rsquo;s also a rooftop, giving you access to even more outdoor space.</p>\r\n<p><strong>This space is move-in ready; all you have to do is show up with your suitcase.</strong></p>\r\n</div>', 5, '', 'williamsburg-ackground.jpg', 's-williamsburg-background.jpg', '', 391, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The South Williamsburg House', 0, 0, 'a:8:{i:0;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:20:\"Throughout the house\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:1478:\"<p>{throughout}</p>\r\n<table class=\"table v2\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<th class=\"title\">\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><span class=\"gold\">Gold</span> Membership</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</th>\r\n<th colspan=\"2\">\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><span class=\"silver\">Silver</span> Membership</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"bronze\">Bronze</span> Membership</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"2\"><em>*Bronze members must move in on <strong>the first day</strong> of the month</em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<th>1-12 Months</th>\r\n<th>4+ Months</th>\r\n<th>1-3 Months</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private</th>\r\n<td>$1650</td>\r\n<td>$1790</td>\r\n<td>$1850</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>2-people shared</th>\r\n<td>$950</td>\r\n<td>$1100</td>\r\n<td>$1250</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>4-people shared</th>\r\n<td>$690</td>\r\n<td>$790</td>\r\n<td>$850</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"5\">See the benefits of Bronze, Silver, and Gold Membership <a class=\"red\" href=\"../memberships\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">here</a>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>**The prices shown indicate <strong>the prices valid for move-in between June 1, 2020, and August 31, 2020</strong>. The exact price is indicated in your membership agreement and may vary depending on the length of commitment, your membership level and the size of your group, if applicable.</em></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div class=\"center\"><a class=\"button2\" href=\"join-us\">I\'m interested</a></div>\";}i:1;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:12:\"The bedrooms\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:571:\"<p>Your room will be move-in ready, just like the rest of the house; there&rsquo;s no need to even bring a pillow. There are single and shared rooms, depending on availability and your price range.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Amenities:</strong> memory-foam mattresses (twin-sized for shared rooms, full-sized for single rooms), pillows, shelving, hooks and closets/organizational tools.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Services:</strong> <strong>If you are a Silver or Gold member, bed linens and towels will be available for you when you arrive.</strong></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:4:{i:0;s:28:\"s-williamsburg-bedroom-1.jpg\";i:1;s:28:\"s-williamsburg-bedroom-2.jpg\";i:2;s:28:\"s-williamsburg-bedroom-3.jpg\";i:3;s:28:\"s-williamsburg-bedroom-4.jpg\";}}i:2;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:20:\"The co-working space\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:1100:\"<p>The basement space is also equipped with everything you need &hellip; to work! This room comfortably holds up to 5-7 people working simultaneously. There\'s a lot of desk space to make sure your work time is productive. Additionally, there are many common spaces throughout the house that our members use to work.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Amenities: Desks, chairs, conveniently placed outlets, a printer, a scanner and a fax machine to make sure you are prepared for anything work throws at you.</li>\r\n<li>Security: 24/7 security in common areas.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>The (co)living room</p>\r\n<p>The living room is located in the basement of the South Williamsburg House. The living room has comfortable couches and a 55-inch TV (with Netflix!); this is where we host movie nights, game nights and hangouts. The space is equipped with everything you need to relax.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Living room also includes: A coffee table, additional seating, pillows, lamps, knickknacks and house slippers to walk around in.</li>\r\n<li>Security: 24/7 security in common areas.</li>\r\n<li>Tech: Google Chromecast</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:3:{i:0;s:31:\"s-williamsburg-livingroom-2.jpg\";i:1;s:31:\"s-williamsburg-livingroom-3.jpg\";i:2;s:31:\"s-williamsburg-livingroom-1.jpg\";}}i:4;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:24:\"The kitchens/dining room\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:650:\"<p>In each apartment, the kitchen and dining room are the first rooms you enter. These spaces are used for potluck dinners, solo meals and chats in the evening over a glass of wine.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Amenities include gas stoves, stainless-steel fridges, microwaves, large sinks, coffee makers, blenders, plenty of cabinets, cookware, tableware, cutting boards and anything else you would need in a kitchen.</li>\r\n<li>Also included: salt, pepper, sugar, coffee grounds, tea, olive oil, paper towels, dish soap, hand soap and garbage/recycling bags, all of which are routinely restocked.</li>\r\n<li>Security: 24/7 security in all common areas.</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:4:{i:0;s:28:\"s-williamsburg-kitchen-3.jpg\";i:1;s:28:\"s-williamsburg-kitchen-1.jpg\";i:2;s:28:\"s-williamsburg-kitchen-2.jpg\";i:3;s:28:\"s-williamsburg-kitchen-4.jpg\";}}i:5;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:13:\"The bathrooms\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:655:\"<p>We provide many bathroom essentials, as well. There are six full bathrooms and one half bathroom so you&rsquo;ll never have to wait. Some are en-suite bathrooms while some are for the whole house to use.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Also included: toilet paper, shampoo, body wash, hand soap and small garbage bags, which will never run out! We also provide hair dryers, so there\'s no need to bring your own.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>LAUNDRY ROOM</p>\r\n<p>The South Williamsburg House also has a laundry room where members can do their laundry in the comfort of their own home.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Security: 24/7 security in all common areas, as well as lockers</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:1:{i:0;s:33:\"south-williamsburg-bathroom-1.jpg\";}}i:6;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:8:\"Backyard\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:257:\"<p>The South Williamsburg House has a great backyard! It has tables, chairs and hammocks so you can hang outside in the spring, summer and autumn, and even has a fire pit. This spacious area holds many parties, get-togethers, barbecues and celebrations.</p>\";s:6:\"images\";a:2:{i:0;s:29:\"s-williamsburg-backyard-1.jpg\";i:1;s:29:\"s-williamsburg-backyard-2.jpg\";}}i:7;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:19:\"Additional benefits\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:413:\"<p>Your Gold membership gives you the opportunity to move between all our houses from month to month, allowing you to see what it&rsquo;s like to live in different neighborhoods. All members are welcome to enjoy the parties and events at any of our locations. We screen all candidates before approving applications so that there are no worries about moving into a new place with new people -- only excitement!</p>\";}i:8;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:6:\"Prices\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:1909:\"<p>We have flexible month-to-month commitment options. We do not require extensive documentation, guarantors or large deposits. A longer commitment on your end helps us to provide you with better prices.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table v2\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<th class=\"title\">\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><span class=\"gold\">Gold</span> Membership</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</th>\r\n<th colspan=\"2\">\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><span class=\"silver\">Silver</span> Membership</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"bronze\">Bronze</span> Membership</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"2\"><em>*Bronze members must move in on <strong>the first day</strong> of the month</em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<th>1-12 Months</th>\r\n<th>4+ Months</th>\r\n<th>1-3 Months</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private</th>\r\n<td>$1650</td>\r\n<td>$1790</td>\r\n<td>$1850</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>2-people shared</th>\r\n<td>$950</td>\r\n<td>$1100</td>\r\n<td>$1250</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>4-people shared</th>\r\n<td>$690</td>\r\n<td>$790</td>\r\n<td>$850</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"5\">See the benefits of Bronze, Silver, and Gold Membership <a class=\"red\" href=\"../memberships\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">here</a>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>**The prices shown indicate <strong>the prices valid for move-in between June 1, 2020, and August 31, 2020</strong>. The exact price is indicated in your membership agreement and may vary depending on the length of commitment, your membership level and the size of your group, if applicable.</em></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div class=\"center\"><a class=\"button2\" href=\"join-us\">Get your exclusive offer now</a></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Availability: Year-round / Minimum stay of 1 month / Month-to-month payment options available / Minimum age 18 / 30-day cancellation notice with Gold Membership</strong></p>\";}}', '', '', 'a:3:{i:0;s:3:\"102\";i:1;s:3:\"248\";i:2;s:3:\"273\";}', '<div class=\"txt\">\r\n<h1 class=\"center\">The South Williamsburg House Move-In Guide</h1>\r\n<h2><strong><em>Welcome to Outpost Club! This is a guide to make your move-in successful. We&rsquo;ve done this many times before, so we know the drill! To start, here is your address: 21 Fayette Street, Brooklyn, NY, 11206.</em></strong></h2>\r\n<hr class=\"hr\" />\r\n<h3>House Leader</h3>\r\n<p>First, get to know your house leader. They will be your point of contact for questions and concerns.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div class=\"fx w vc ch2\">\r\n<div><img style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"../files/uploads/august_lock.gif\" alt=\"\" />\r\n<p>How to use the August lock</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h3>Getting in the Building</h3>\r\n<p>The outside door code is #3131. All interior doors are locked with an August Lock. An August Lock is an electronic lock that uses an application called August that you can use to unlock it. Find it in the app store, create an account and ask your house leader to give you access.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>WiFi</h3>\r\n<p>As always, you&rsquo;ll need WiFi. The WiFi name is Outpost (or some variation of thereof) and the password is befreenyc (all lower case).</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>ID</h3>\r\n<p>For our records and according to state law, we&rsquo;ll need a picture of your photo ID. Either a national ID or a passport will work. The house leader will take a picture of it when you move in.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Communication With Other Residents</h3>\r\n<p>We use Facebook messenger to communicate, so the house leader will need to add you to the group. If you don&rsquo;t have Facebook, please regularly check in with the house leader to see if there is important house news you need to know.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>See the House</h3>\r\n<p>The house leader will show you your room and give you a tour of the house (if they haven&rsquo;t already). Note your bed number, which can be found on your bed frame, or your room letter if you have a single room. If you would like to lock away your valuables, use the lockers in the basement. Outpost Club is not responsible for the safety of your valuables and we do not provide locks, just lockers.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Kitchen</h3>\r\n<p>You&rsquo;ll need a section of the fridge, which is partitioned by area so that everyone has equal access. If you open the fridge, you&rsquo;ll see each section has a letter and a number corresponding with your bed. Use this area of the fridge for your items and talk to others in the house or to your house leader if you need more space. This goes for the cabinets as well: Find your section, which will be labeled by your bed number.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Events</h3>\r\n<p>Outpost Club will hold events at your place and at all Outpost Club locations, so make sure to ask the house leader about any upcoming events. Additionally, we have a Facebook group for all <a class=\"green\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/groups/outpostclub/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Outpost Club members in New York</strong></a>. This group has information about events, opportunities in New York, general announcements and more good stuff. Please RSVP to events either on Facebook or through the Current Members portal so we can plan events accordingly.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Cleanliness</h3>\r\n<p>The common spaces in the house are used by a lot of people, so please keep them clean! Here are some easy ways to think about cleanliness at Outpost Club:</p>\r\n<ul data-rte-list=\"default\">\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Leave rooms in the condition in which you found them</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Clean up after yourself</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Do not leave your personal stuff out in common areas if you are not going to return immediately</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>When it\'s your turn to contribute, contribute! Check the cleaning boards for your day to help, and if your name is not there, add it. Our cleaners come weekly to take care of major cleaning, but it&rsquo;s your responsibility to do your own dishes and to take out the trash and empty the dishwasher on your cleaning day.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Additionally, the notes around the house are there to reduce confusion and make the community run smoothly, so make sure to follow the notes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Mail</h3>\r\n<p>Make sure to address all mail to:</p>\r\n<p><strong>21 Fayette Street, Brooklyn, NY, 11206, with your apartment number</strong></p>\r\n<p>Make sure mail is addressed to the correct apartment to ensure the mail person delivers it successfully. The house leader checks the mail periodically throughout the week, but if you know something has arrived and you need it sooner, ask your house leader.</p>\r\n<p><strong>If you are receiving a package, there are multiple ways it may be delivered:</strong></p>\r\n<ul data-rte-list=\"default\">\r\n<li>\r\n<p>The package may be left in the hallway by the delivery person, in which case you can pick it up on the way into the house</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>The package may have been accepted by another member of the house, in which case you can pick it up when you get inside the house</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>The package may have been left outside in a concealed location by the delivery person, in which case the delivery person will leave a note on the front door informing you where the package was left</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>The package may have been attempted for delivery but not left for some reason, in which case they will try to deliver it again in the coming days.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Regardless of delivery method, please:</strong></p>\r\n<ul data-rte-list=\"default\">\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Copy and paste the text below into the \"delivery instructions&rdquo; part of your order:</p>\r\n<ul data-rte-list=\"default\">\r\n<li>\r\n<p>\"Code to the front door is #1542. If you cannot leave the package inside, please either return the package to the delivery center where I can pick it up or (ENTER OPTION 2 IF DESIRED)\"</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Continually track the package.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Attempt to be home when it arrives, or see if one of your roommates can bring it inside for you.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Do everything from your end to ensure its successful delivery.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Outpost Club is not responsible for delayed, lost or damaged packages.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Cancellations And Extensions</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Gold Membership</strong>: We have a 30-day notice of cancellation policy. Please give us notice of cancellation 30 days before your next pay period. You will be assessed a $250 fee for canceling your membership before the end of your membership agreement.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Bronze/Silver Membership:</strong>: We do not permit cancellations before the end of your membership agreement.</p>\r\n<p>Additionally, we\'re always happy to have our members stay longer; however, we can\'t extend your stay if we don\'t know about your extension! As soon as you are aware of the need to extend your stay, let us know by emailing customer.service@outpost-club.com. If you have not committed to an extension, your bed can be reserved by anyone admitted to Outpost Club.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><em>That\'s all for now! Always look out for updates from Outpost -- they will come through the Facebook group, Facebook messenger, via email or from the house leader.</em></h2>\r\n</div>', 0, '0.00000000', '0.00000000', 0, '', NULL),
