(239, 0, NULL, 'move-in-guide-the-south-williamsburg-house', '', 'The South Williamsburg House Move-In Guide', 'The South Williamsburg House Move-In Guide', 'Welcome to Outpost Club! This is a guide to make your move in successful', 'The South Williamsburg House Move-In Guide', '', '', '<div class=\"txt\">\r\n<h1 class=\"center\">The South Williamsburg House Move-In Guide</h1>\r\n<h2><strong><em>Welcome to Outpost Club! This is a guide to make your move-in successful. We&rsquo;ve done this many times before, so we know the drill! To start, here is your address: 21 Fayette Street, Brooklyn, NY, 11206.</em></strong></h2>\r\n<hr class=\"hr\" />\r\n<h3>House Leader</h3>\r\n<p>First, get to know your house leader. They will be your point of contact for questions and concerns.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div class=\"fx w vc ch2\">\r\n<div><img style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"../files/uploads/august_lock.gif\" alt=\"\" />\r\n<p>How to use the August lock</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h3>Getting in the Building</h3>\r\n<p>All exterior and interior doors are locked with an August Lock. An August Lock is an electronic lock that uses an application called <a class=\"green\" href=\"http://august.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>August</strong></a>&nbsp;that you can use to unlock it. Find it in the app store, create an account, and ask your house leader to give you access.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Wifi</h3>\r\n<p>As always, you&rsquo;ll need WiFi. The WiFi name is Outpost (or some variation of thereof) and the password is befreenyc (all lower case).</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>ID</h3>\r\n<p>For our records and according to state law, we&rsquo;ll need a picture of your photo ID. Either a national ID or a passport will work. The house leader will take a picture of it when you move in.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Communication With Other Residents</h3>\r\n<p>We use Facebook messenger to communicate, so the house leader will need to add you to the group. If you don&rsquo;t have Facebook, please regularly check in with the house leader to see if there is important house news you need to know.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>See The House</h3>\r\n<p>The house leader will show you your room and give you a tour of the house (if they haven&rsquo;t already). Note your bed number, which can be found on your bed frame, or your room letter if you have a single room. If you would like to lock away your valuables, use the lockers in the basement. Outpost Club is not responsible for the safety of your valuables and we do not provide locks, just lockers.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Kitchen</h3>\r\n<p>You&rsquo;ll need a section of the fridge, which is partitioned by area so that everyone has equal access. If you open the fridge, you&rsquo;ll see each section has a letter and a number corresponding with your bed. Use this area of the fridge for your items, and talk to others in the house or to your house leader if you need more space. This goes for the cabinets as well: Find your section, which will be labeled by your bed number.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Events</h3>\r\n<p>Outpost Club will hold events at your place and at all Outpost Club locations, so make sure to ask the house leader about any upcoming events. Additionally, we have a Facebook group for all <a class=\"green\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/groups/outpostclub/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Outpost Club members in New York</strong></a>. This group has information about events, opportunities in New York, general announcements, and more good stuff. Please RSVP to events either on Facebook or through the Current Members portal so we can plan events accordingly.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Cleanliness</h3>\r\n<p>The common spaces in the house are used by a lot of people, so please keep them clean! Here are some easy ways to think about cleanliness at Outpost Club:</p>\r\n<ul data-rte-list=\"default\">\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Leave rooms in the condition in which you found them</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Clean up after yourself</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Do not leave your personal stuff out in common areas if you are not going to return immediately</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>When it\'s your turn to contribute, contribute! Check the cleaning boards for your day to help, and if your name is not there, add it. Our cleaners come weekly to take care of major cleaning, but it&rsquo;s your responsibility to do your own dishes and to take out the trash and empty the dishwasher on your cleaning day.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Additionally, the notes around the house are there to reduce confusion and make the community run smoothly, so make sure to follow the notes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Mail</h3>\r\n<p>Make sure to address all mail to:</p>\r\n<p><strong>21 Fayette Street, Brooklyn, NY, 11206, with your apartment number</strong></p>\r\n<p>Make sure mail is addressed to the correct apartment to ensure the mail person delivers it successfully. The house leader checks the mail periodically throughout the week, but if you know something has arrived and you need it sooner, ask your house leader.</p>\r\n<p><strong>If you are receiving a package, there are multiple ways it may be delivered:</strong></p>\r\n<ul data-rte-list=\"default\">\r\n<li>\r\n<p>The package may be left in the hallway by the delivery person, in which case you can pick it up on the way into the house</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>The package may have been accepted by another member of the house, in which case you can pick it up when you get inside the house</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>The package may have been left outside in a concealed location by the delivery person, in which case the delivery person will leave a note on the front door informing you where the package was left</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>The package may have been attempted for delivery but not left for some reason, in which case they will try to deliver it again in the coming days.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Regardless of delivery method, please:</strong></p>\r\n<ul data-rte-list=\"default\">\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Copy and paste the text below into the \"delivery instructions&rdquo; part of your order:</p>\r\n<ul data-rte-list=\"default\">\r\n<li>\r\n<p>\"Code to the front door is #1542. If you cannot leave the package inside, please either return the package to the delivery center where I can pick it up or (ENTER OPTION 2 IF DESIRED)\"</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Continually track the package.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Attempt to be home when it arrives, or see if one of your roommates can bring it inside for you.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Do everything from your end to ensure its successful delivery.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Outpost Club is not responsible for delayed, lost or damaged packages.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Cancellations And Extensions</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Gold Membership</strong>: We have a 30-day notice of cancellation policy. Please give us notice of cancellation 30 days before your next pay period. You will be assessed a $250 fee for canceling your membership before the end of your membership agreement.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Bronze/Silver Membership:</strong>: We do not permit cancellations before the end of your membership agreement.</p>\r\n<p>Additionally, we happy to have our members stay longer; however, we can\'t extend <a href=\"mailto:customer.service@outpost-club.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">customer.service@outpost-club.com</a>&nbsp;you stay if we don\'t know about your extension! As soon as you are aware of the need to extend your stay, let us know by emailing customer.service@outpost-club.com. If you have not committed to an extension, your bed can be reserved by anyone admitted to Outpost Club.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><em>That\'s all for now! Always look out for updates from Outpost -- they will come through the Facebook group, Facebook messenger, via email or from the house leader.</em></h2>\r\n</div>', 8, '', '', '', '', 179, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'The South Williamsburg House Move-In Guide', 0, 0, 'a:0:{}', '', '', '', '', 0, '0.00000000', '0.00000000', 0, '', NULL),
(240, 231, NULL, 'whos-shit-is-this-event-checklist', '', 'Who’s Shit is This? Event Checklist', 'Who’s Shit is This? Event Checklist', '', 'Who’s Shit is This? Event Checklist', '', '', '', 12, '', '', '', 'fa-list-ul', 251, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'Who’s Shit is This? Event Checklist', 0, 0, 'a:9:{i:1;a:3:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"description\";s:362:\"This is a checklist for how to hold an event called “Whose shit is this?” The point of this event is to “reset” the house.\r\nThings get overlooked, or even completely ignored sometimes, and it\'s important to address these things. <strong>This event must be held by the house leader once a month. You get to decide when it is, but it must be held.</strong>\";}i:2;a:4:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:5:\"title\";s:7:\"Kitchen\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";s:3:\"sub\";a:11:{i:1;a:3:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:5:\"title\";s:109:\"Take things out of the sink, either clean or place in dishwasher (you’ll need the sink to wash other things\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:3:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:5:\"title\";s:53:\"Fridges - Take everything out and clean the shelves. \";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:3:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:5:\"title\";s:54:\"Freezers - Take everything out and clean the shelves. \";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:3:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:5:\"title\";s:46:\"Cabinets, cubbies, containers and food holders\";s:11:\"description\";s:70:\"Take everything out and clean them, as well as the shelves they sit on\";}i:5;a:3:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:5:\"title\";s:51:\"Throw out any obviously old, moldy, or smelly items\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";}i:6;a:3:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:5:\"title\";s:80:\"Once all shelves are cleaned, designate areas of the fridge based on room number\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";}i:7;a:3:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:5:\"title\";s:89:\"Put all <strong>claimed</strong> items back in the fridge and freezer in designated areas\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";}i:8;a:3:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:5:\"title\";s:133:\"Place all non-claimed items on the kitchen table, take a picture of them and send the picture of the items to the house group message\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";}i:9;a:3:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:5:\"title\";s:110:\"Place all pots and pans in their designated area and let everyone know that should always be re-placed there. \";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";}i:10;a:3:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:5:\"title\";s:168:\"Place all cups bowls, dishes, silverware and tupperware in their designated area and let everyone know that should always be place back in that location when not in use\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";}i:11;a:3:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:5:\"title\";s:135:\"Replace all common area items to the designated area and throw our anything place there that has gone bad (old ketchup, hot sauce, etc)\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";}}}i:3;a:4:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:5:\"title\";s:9:\"Bathrooms\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";s:3:\"sub\";a:5:{i:1;a:3:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:5:\"title\";s:128:\"Take everything out of the cabinets, off the shelves, out of the containers, around the bathtub, on the sink, and under the sink\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:3:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:5:\"title\";s:89:\"Clean the shelves, containers, cabinets, rim of the bathtub, and the area around the sink\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:3:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:5:\"title\";s:87:\"Throw out any obviously old and unused stuff (loofahs, soap bars that are unused, etc.)\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:3:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:5:\"title\";s:46:\"Put all claimed items back in designated areas\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:3:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:5:\"title\";s:131:\"Place all unclaimed items on the kitchen table, take a picture of them and send the picture of the items to the house group message\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";}}}i:4;a:4:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:5:\"title\";s:14:\"Lost and found\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";s:3:\"sub\";a:3:{i:1;a:3:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:5:\"title\";s:45:\"Place the unclaimed mail in the kitchen table\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:3:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:5:\"title\";s:29:\"Have people claim their items\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:3:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:5:\"title\";s:57:\"Send picture of remaining to items to house group message\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";}}}i:5;a:4:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:5:\"title\";s:5:\"Mail \";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";s:3:\"sub\";a:3:{i:1;a:3:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:5:\"title\";s:45:\"Place the unclaimed mail in the kitchen table\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:3:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:5:\"title\";s:46:\"Ask attendees if any of the mail is their’s \";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:4:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:5:\"title\";s:93:\"Take a picture of unclaimed mail and send the picture of the items to the house group message\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";s:3:\"sub\";a:1:{i:1;a:3:{s:4:\"type\";s:2:\"11\";s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:4:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:5:\"title\";s:47:\"Shoes, Umbrellas, and Other Miscellaneous Stuff\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";s:3:\"sub\";a:2:{i:1;a:3:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:5:\"title\";s:141:\"If there are items that you know belong to someone no longer lives at the house, either offer them to the current members to throw them away.\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:4:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:5:\"title\";s:151:\"If there are items that are out of place, have no reason for being in any room, or too many of an item, throw them away or put them back in their place\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";s:3:\"sub\";a:5:{i:1;a:3:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:5:\"title\";s:89:\"Plastic bags - if the cabinets are overflowing with plastic bags, throw many of them away\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:3:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:5:\"title\";s:75:\"If there are pieces of used printer paper near the printer, throw them away\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:3:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:5:\"title\";s:156:\"If the printer is low on ink, replace the cartridge (there should always be a new one available, they are ordered automatically when the current one is low)\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:3:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:5:\"title\";s:72:\"If there are pens or pencils that can no longer be used, throw them away\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:3:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:5:\"title\";s:58:\"Find the iron and place it back in its designated location\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:7;a:4:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:5:\"title\";s:15:\"Cleaning Boards\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";s:3:\"sub\";a:2:{i:1;a:3:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:5:\"title\";s:58:\"Erase peoples names who are no longer staying at the house\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:3:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:5:\"title\";s:52:\"Add members to the board who are not on it currently\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";}}}i:8;a:4:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:5:\"title\";s:10:\"Room board\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";s:3:\"sub\";a:2:{i:1;a:3:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:5:\"title\";s:58:\"Erase peoples names who are no longer staying at the house\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:3:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:5:\"title\";s:52:\"Add members to the board who are not on it currently\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";}}}i:9;a:4:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:5:\"title\";s:29:\"Messages that need to be sent\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";s:3:\"sub\";a:3:{i:1;a:3:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:5:\"title\";s:38:\"Send this message to the house group: \";s:11:\"description\";s:348:\"<i>We have cleaned out all the items from the fridge, cabinets, bathrooms, lost and found, shoes, and mail. The unclaimed items are left on the kitchen table(s). Please come and check the table for any of your belongings and put them in the proper place. The items left on the table will be thrown away the next time the cleaners come to clean.</i>\";}i:2;a:3:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:5:\"title\";s:28:\"Send message to the <a href=\";s:11:\"description\";s:254:\"<i>We have cleared out the fridges, cabinets, bathrooms, lost and found, shoes, and mail. The unclaimed items are left on the kitchen table(s). When you come to clean, if there is anything left, please bag them and toss them out in the outdoor trash.</i>\";}i:3;a:3:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:5:\"title\";s:61:\"If there is no ink available, report it to the house <a href=\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";}}}}', '', '', '', '', 0, '0.00000000', '0.00000000', 0, '', NULL),
(241, 222, NULL, 'how-to-do-a-move-out-checklist', '', 'How to Do a Move Out Checklist', 'How to Do a Move-Out Checklist', '', 'How to Do a Move-Out Checklist', '', '', '', 12, '', '', '', 'fa-list-ul', 224, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'How to Do a Move-Out Checklist', 0, 0, 'a:5:{i:1;a:3:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"description\";s:48:\"Use this as a CHECKLIST to complete the move out\";}i:5;a:3:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"8\";s:5:\"title\";s:12:\"Select House\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:3:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"5\";s:5:\"title\";s:10:\"Guest name\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:4:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:5:\"title\";s:19:\"Before the move-out\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";s:3:\"sub\";a:2:{i:1;a:3:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:5:\"title\";s:72:\"Read the schedule and prepare accordingly to be there for the move out. \";s:11:\"description\";s:93:\"You’ll receive the move-out schedule of the upcoming week every Friday/Saturday via Slack. \";}i:2;a:3:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:5:\"title\";s:74:\"On the day before any members move out, post to the facebook group saying \";s:11:\"description\";s:202:\"<i>“XXX is moving out tomorrow! Please take this chance to say goodbye to them!”</i> <br>\r\nThis can be done person by person, or you can post all the move ins and move outs of the week at one time\r\n\";}}}i:3;a:4:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:5:\"title\";s:26:\"On the day of the move-out\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";s:3:\"sub\";a:6:{i:1;a:4:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:5:\"title\";s:43:\"Make sure they have removed everything from\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";s:3:\"sub\";a:6:{i:1;a:3:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:5:\"title\";s:10:\"Their room\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:3:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:5:\"title\";s:18:\"Their fridge space\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:3:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:5:\"title\";s:23:\"Their cabinet/bin space\";s:11:\"description\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:3:{s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:5:\"title\";s:14:\"Their bathroom\";s:11:\