(252, 254, NULL, 'the-japantown-house', '', 'The Japantown House', 'Bay Area (SF) Room Rentals, Shared Apartments | Outpost Club', '', 'The Japantown House', '<p>Japantown, San Francisco</p>\r\n<p><span data-sheets-value=\"{&quot;1&quot;:2,&quot;2&quot;:&quot;Multi-person&quot;}\" data-sheets-userformat=\"{&quot;2&quot;:639,&quot;3&quot;:{&quot;1&quot;:0},&quot;4&quot;:[null,2,16777215],&quot;5&quot;:{&quot;1&quot;:[{&quot;1&quot;:2,&quot;2&quot;:0,&quot;5&quot;:[null,2,0]},{&quot;1&quot;:0,&quot;2&quot;:0,&quot;3&quot;:3},{&quot;1&quot;:1,&quot;2&quot;:0,&quot;4&quot;:1}]},&quot;6&quot;:{&quot;1&quot;:[{&quot;1&quot;:2,&quot;2&quot;:0,&quot;5&quot;:[null,2,0]},{&quot;1&quot;:0,&quot;2&quot;:0,&quot;3&quot;:3},{&quot;1&quot;:1,&quot;2&quot;:0,&quot;4&quot;:1}]},&quot;7&quot;:{&quot;1&quot;:[{&quot;1&quot;:2,&quot;2&quot;:0,&quot;5&quot;:[null,2,0]},{&quot;1&quot;:0,&quot;2&quot;:0,&quot;3&quot;:3},{&quot;1&quot;:1,&quot;2&quot;:0,&quot;4&quot;:1}]},&quot;8&quot;:{&quot;1&quot;:[{&quot;1&quot;:2,&quot;2&quot;:0,&quot;5&quot;:[null,2,0]},{&quot;1&quot;:0,&quot;2&quot;:0,&quot;3&quot;:3},{&quot;1&quot;:1,&quot;2&quot;:0,&quot;4&quot;:1}]},&quot;9&quot;:1,&quot;12&quot;:0}\">Shared</span>&nbsp;rooms from $790</p>', '<h1 class=\"h1\">The Japantown House</h1>\r\n<h4>Rent a Room in San Francisco Bay Area</h4>', '<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">The Scoop</h6>\r\n<p>When we decided to expand Outpost beyond New York City, we looked for a neighborhood with a strong sense of community, central to plentiful dining, shopping and entertainment options, and with easy access to public transportation. That&rsquo;s Japantown.</p>\r\n<p>Our house in Japantown features two floors of exclusively designed spaces above a ground-level restaurant, and is a stone&rsquo;s throw away from plenty of dining and entertainment options. It has a large co-working space perfect for group brainstorms or solo projects, relaxing common spaces and everything you&rsquo;ll need to feel right at home from the moment you step inside. All you need to bring is your suitcase.</p>\r\n<p>This house is newly renovated, with hardwood floors and updated appliances. The kitchen and common areas are massive compared to the average San Francisco apartment, and there&rsquo;re multiple co-working tables in the common area, so you&rsquo;ll never have to worry about finding room to be productive. And when you&rsquo;re ready to relax, the area is set up to help you do just that.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">The Neighborhood</h6>\r\n<p>This coliving house is located in the heart of Japantown, within walking distance of multiple parks and an array of coffee shops, bars, restaurants and entertainment. The closest BART station is Civic Center.</p>\r\n<p><strong>The closest Muni station is Van Ness, serving the J, K/T, L, M, N and S lines. Multiple bus lines serve the neighborhood. </strong></p>\r\n</div>', 5, '', 'the-japantown-house-livingroom-2.jpg', 'the-japantown-house-main.jpg', '', 525, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Japantown House', 0, 0, 'a:7:{i:0;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:20:\"Throughout the house\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:548:\"<p>{throughout}</p>\r\n<table class=\"table v2\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<th>12+ Months</th>\r\n<th>4-11 Months</th>\r\n<th>1-3 Months</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>3-people shared</th>\r\n<td>$790</td>\r\n<td>$850</td>\r\n<td>$890</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"5\"><em>**The prices shown indicate <strong>the prices valid for move-in between November<em><strong>&nbsp;11, 2020, and March 31, 2021</strong></em></strong>.</em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div class=\"center\"><a class=\"button2 red\" href=\"join-us\" target=\"_blank\">Apply for free</a></div>\";}i:4;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:12:\"The Bedrooms\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:358:\"<p>Your room will be move-in ready, just like the rest of the house; there&rsquo;s no need to even bring a pillow. There are single and shared rooms, depending on availability and your price range.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Amenities:</strong> memory-foam full-sized mattresses, memory-foam pillows, shelving, hooks and closets/organizational tools.</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:8:{i:0;s:33:\"the-japantown-house-bedroom-5.jpg\";i:1;s:33:\"the-japantown-house-bedroom-1.jpg\";i:2;s:33:\"the-japantown-house-bedroom-2.jpg\";i:3;s:33:\"the-japantown-house-bedroom-3.jpg\";i:4;s:33:\"the-japantown-house-bedroom-4.jpg\";i:5;s:33:\"the-japantown-house-bedroom-6.jpg\";i:6;s:33:\"the-japantown-house-bedroom-7.jpg\";i:7;s:33:\"the-japantown-house-bedroom-8.jpg\";}}i:6;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:24:\"The kitchens/dining room\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:616:\"<p>The kitchen is on the third floor of the house and has plenty of counter space for cooking on your own or with a group, as well as two fridges so everyone has plenty of space for their food. The spaces are used for potluck dinners, solo meals and chats in the evening over a glass of wine.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Amenities include</strong> gas stoves, stainless-steel fridges, microwaves, large sinks, coffee makers, blenders, plenty of cabinets, cookware, tableware, cutting boards and anything else you would need in a kitchen.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Security</strong>: 24/7 security in all common areas.</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:7:{i:0;s:33:\"the-japantown-house-kitchen-1.jpg\";i:1;s:33:\"the-japantown-house-kitchen-2.jpg\";i:2;s:33:\"the-japantown-house-kitchen-3.jpg\";i:3;s:33:\"the-japantown-house-kitchen-4.jpg\";i:4;s:33:\"the-japantown-house-kitchen-5.jpg\";i:5;s:33:\"the-japantown-house-kitchen-6.jpg\";i:6;s:33:\"the-japantown-house-kitchen-7.jpg\";}}i:7;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:18:\"The coliving space\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:779:\"<p>The living room is located on the third floor of the Japantown House. It comes equipped with a TV -- Netflix and Chromecast included -- and plenty of room to lounge around after a hard day&rsquo;s work. For co-working purposes, there are multiple tables in the common area, providing enough desk space to comfortably accommodate 12 people at a time. The area also includes a printer (paper and ink included), fax and scanner to make sure you\'ll always be ready to be productive.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Living room also includes:</strong> A coffee table, additional seating, pillows, lamps, knickknacks and house slippers to walk around in.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Security:</strong> 24/7 security in common areas.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Tech:</strong> Google Chromecast</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:6:{i:0;s:36:\"the-japantown-house-livingroom-4.jpg\";i:1;s:36:\"the-japantown-house-livingroom-1.jpg\";i:2;s:36:\"the-japantown-house-livingroom-2.jpg\";i:3;s:36:\"the-japantown-house-livingroom-3.jpg\";i:4;s:36:\"the-japantown-house-livingroom-6.jpg\";i:5;s:36:\"the-japantown-house-livingroom-5.jpg\";}}i:8;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:13:\"The bathrooms\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:604:\"<p>We provide many bathroom essentials, as well. There are two full bathrooms in the Japantown House, both of which are free to use regardless of which room you&rsquo;re in.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Also included:</strong> toilet paper, shampoo, body wash, hand soap and small garbage bags, which will never run out!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p class=\"h5\">Laundry room</p>\r\n<p>The Japantown House also has a washer and dryer where members can do their laundry for free in the comfort of their own home.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Security:</strong> 24/7 security in all common areas, as well as lockers</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:3:{i:0;s:34:\"the-japantown-house-bathroom-2.jpg\";i:1;s:34:\"the-japantown-house-bathroom-1.jpg\";i:2;s:34:\"the-japantown-house-bathroom-3.jpg\";}}i:9;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:19:\"Additional benefits\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:178:\"<p><strong>We screen all candidates before approving applications so that there are no worries about moving into a new place with new people &mdash; only excitement!</strong></p>\";}i:10;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:6:\"Prices\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:950:\"<p>We have flexible month-to-month commitment options. We do not require extensive documents from you, guarantors or large deposits. A longer commitment on your side helps us to provide you with better prices.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table v2\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<th>12+ Months</th>\r\n<th>4-11 Months</th>\r\n<th>1-3 Months</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>3-people shared</th>\r\n<td>$790</td>\r\n<td>$850</td>\r\n<td>$890</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"5\"><em>**The prices shown indicate <strong>the prices valid for move-in between November<em><strong>&nbsp;11, 2020, and March 31, 2021</strong></em></strong>.</em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div class=\"center\"><a class=\"button2 red\" href=\"join-us\" target=\"_blank\">Apply for free</a></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Availability: Year-round / Minimum stay of 1 month / Month-to-month payment options available / Minimum age 18 / 30-day cancellation notice</strong></p>\";}}', '', '', '', '<div class=\"txt\">\r\n<h1 class=\"\">The Japantown House Move-In Guide</h1>\r\n<h2><em><strong>1632 Post Street, San Francisco, CA, 94115</strong></em></h2>\r\n<hr class=\"hr\" />\r\n<h3><strong>The Community</strong></h3>\r\n<p>Welcome to Outpost! We&rsquo;re glad you&rsquo;re here. Coliving isn&rsquo;t just about having roommates or sharing a kitchen &mdash; it&rsquo;s about recognizing that we can do more, accomplish more and be more when we work together.</p>\r\n<p>We communicate with each other via our house&rsquo;s Messenger group, which your House Leader will add you upon arrival. We also offer an Outpost Slack channel where you can find other members with similar interests and meet new people in your area. We send out relevant updates and information via email, so keep an eye out!</p>\r\n<p>Your <strong>Member Portal</strong> is where you can RSVP for community events, submit maintenance and cleaning requests and access important documents. <a class=\"green\" href=\"../user/login\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Find it here</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Your <strong>House Leader</strong> will be your main point of contact with Outpost. Here&rsquo;s what they can help you with:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Info about community activities</li>\r\n<li>Restocking supplies</li>\r\n<li>Questions about Outpost</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>We have a lot of activities to help you get involved with our community and get to know the city. Pay attention to your Member Portal and your house&rsquo;s Messenger group to keep up with what&rsquo;s going on, or just ask your House Leader!</p>\r\n<h3><strong>The Logistics</strong></h3>\r\n<h3>Moving In</h3>\r\n<p>The outside code to your house is <strong>#7760</strong>. You&rsquo;ll use the August app to access your unit, and your HL will help you create a unique code for your door upon arrival. Download the app and sign up for an account.</p>\r\n<p>Here&rsquo;s how to use the app:</p>\r\n<div class=\"fx w vc ch2\">\r\n<div><img style=\"width: 70%; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"../files/uploads/august_lock.gif\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>When you move in, your House Leader will give you a tour of the house and talk to you a bit about the Outpost community. They&rsquo;ll also:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Take a photo of your ID (for our records and according to state law)</li>\r\n<li>Add you to your Messenger group</li>\r\n<li>Assign you cupboard and refrigerator space, according to your room number.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The WiFi name is Outpost (or something similar) and the password is <strong>befreenyc</strong>.</p>\r\n<h3>Living at Outpost</h3>\r\n<p>You&rsquo;ll find helpful information linked above in our Guide to Responsible Coliving, but there are a few more things you should know:</p>\r\n<p><strong>Recycling is required</strong>, and New York City has strict guidelines. Watch the video below to see what you should recycle:</p>\r\n<iframe style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/EUyVELb5PzY\" width=\"70%\" height=\"400\"></iframe><br /><br />\r\n<p><strong>Cleanliness is also required.</strong> That&rsquo;s especially true of common areas, including shared rooms. Here are some easy ways to think about cleanliness at Outpost:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Leave rooms in the condition in which you found them</li>\r\n<li>Clean up after yourself</li>\r\n<li>Don&rsquo;t leave your belongings in the common area unless you&rsquo;re returning immediately</li>\r\n<li>Pay attention to the signs around the house: They&rsquo;re there to help our community run smoothly!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Outpost is not responsible for lost or damaged mail or packages.</strong> Your House Leader will check the mail regularly. Make sure to put your full address, including your outside door code, in the delivery field when you order something. You may find your package left inside the main door, concealed outside, with a roommate who picked it up for you or returned to a distribution center for a later delivery. It&rsquo;s your responsibility to track your packages and make sure you&rsquo;re home to receive them when necessary.</p>\r\n</div>', 0, '37.78596000', '-122.42878000', 0, '', NULL);
