(254, 0, NULL, 'san-francisco', '', 'San Francisco', 'Coliving San Francisco | Outpost Club', '', '', '<h1 class=\"h1\">San Francisco Coliving Spaces<br /> Check Out Our Houses</h1>', '', '', 5, '', 'san-francisko.jpg', '', '', 482, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'San Francisco', 0, 0, 'a:1:{i:0;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:0:\"\";}}', '', '', '', '', 0, '0.00000000', '0.00000000', 0, '', NULL),
(258, 0, NULL, 'move-in-guide-the-japantown-house', '', 'The Japantown House Move-In Guide', 'The Japantown House Move-In Guide', 'Welcome to Outpost Club! This is a guide to make your move in successful', 'The Japantown House Move-In Guide', '', '', '<div class=\"txt\">\r\n<h1 class=\"\">The Japantown House Move-In Guide</h1>\r\n<h2><em><strong>1632 Post Street, San Francisco, CA, 94115</strong></em></h2>\r\n<hr class=\"hr\" />\r\n<h3><strong>The Community</strong></h3>\r\n<p>Welcome to Outpost! We&rsquo;re glad you&rsquo;re here. Coliving isn&rsquo;t just about having roommates or sharing a kitchen &mdash; it&rsquo;s about recognizing that we can do more, accomplish more and be more when we work together.</p>\r\n<p>We communicate with each other via our house&rsquo;s Messenger group, which your House Leader will add you upon arrival. We also offer an Outpost Slack channel where you can find other members with similar interests and meet new people in your area. We send out relevant updates and information via email, so keep an eye out!</p>\r\n<p>Your <strong>Member Portal</strong> is where you can RSVP for community events, submit maintenance and cleaning requests and access important documents. <a class=\"green\" href=\"../user/login\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Find it here</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Your <strong>House Leader</strong> will be your main point of contact with Outpost. Here&rsquo;s what they can help you with:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Info about community activities</li>\r\n<li>Restocking supplies</li>\r\n<li>Questions about Outpost</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>We have a lot of activities to help you get involved with our community and get to know the city. Pay attention to your Member Portal and your house&rsquo;s Messenger group to keep up with what&rsquo;s going on, or just ask your House Leader!</p>\r\n<h3><strong>The Logistics</strong></h3>\r\n<h3>Moving In</h3>\r\n<p>The outside code to your house is <strong>#7760</strong>. You&rsquo;ll use the August app to access your unit, and your HL will help you create a unique code for your door upon arrival. Download the app and sign up for an account.</p>\r\n<p>Here&rsquo;s how to use the app:</p>\r\n<div class=\"fx w vc ch2\">\r\n<div><img style=\"width: 70%; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"../files/uploads/august_lock.gif\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>When you move in, your House Leader will give you a tour of the house and talk to you a bit about the Outpost community. They&rsquo;ll also:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Take a photo of your ID (for our records and according to state law)</li>\r\n<li>Add you to your Messenger group</li>\r\n<li>Assign you cupboard and refrigerator space, according to your room number.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The WiFi name is Outpost (or something similar) and the password is <strong>befreenyc</strong>.</p>\r\n<h3>Living at Outpost</h3>\r\n<p>You&rsquo;ll find helpful information linked above in our Guide to Responsible Coliving, but there are a few more things you should know:</p>\r\n<p><strong>Recycling is required</strong>, and New York City has strict guidelines. Watch the video below to see what you should recycle:</p>\r\n<iframe style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/EUyVELb5PzY\" width=\"70%\" height=\"400\"></iframe><br /><br />\r\n<p><strong>Cleanliness is also required.</strong> That&rsquo;s especially true of common areas, including shared rooms. Here are some easy ways to think about cleanliness at Outpost:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Leave rooms in the condition in which you found them</li>\r\n<li>Clean up after yourself</li>\r\n<li>Don&rsquo;t leave your belongings in the common area unless you&rsquo;re returning immediately</li>\r\n<li>Pay attention to the signs around the house: They&rsquo;re there to help our community run smoothly!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Outpost is not responsible for lost or damaged mail or packages.</strong> Your House Leader will check the mail regularly. Make sure to put your full address, including your outside door code, in the delivery field when you order something. You may find your package left inside the main door, concealed outside, with a roommate who picked it up for you or returned to a distribution center for a later delivery. It&rsquo;s your responsibility to track your packages and make sure you&rsquo;re home to receive them when necessary.</p>\r\n</div>', 8, '', '', '', '', 239, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'The Japantown House Move-In Guide', 0, 0, 'a:0:{}', '', '', '', '', 0, '0.00000000', '0.00000000', 0, '', NULL),
(382, 0, NULL, 'the-greenpoint-house-3d-tour', '', 'The Greenpoint House 3D tour', 'The Greenpoint House 3D tour', '', 'The Greenpoint House 3D tour', '', '', '<h1>The Greenpoint House 3D tour (Apt D1)</h1>\r\n<p><iframe style=\"margin-top: 1em;\" src=\"https://geocv.com/lEY7aaB7On2COhFTumXPOw\" width=\"100%\" height=\"500\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"> </iframe></p>', 9, '', '', '', '', 393, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'The Greenpoint House 3D tour', 0, 0, 'a:0:{}', '', '', '', '', 0, '0.00000000', '0.00000000', 0, '', NULL),
(383, 253, 311, 'the-greenpoint-house', '', 'The Greenpoint House', 'The Greenpoint House (NY 11222) | The Outpost Club', 'We worked with interior designers to make The Greenpoint House comfortable in every room. ✓ Fully furnished ✓ Security ✓ Gas ✓ Electricity ✓ Water ✓ Wi-Fi ✓ Cleaning and maintenance', 'The Greenpoint House | The Outpost Club', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Greenpoint</span>, Brooklyn</p>\r\n<p>Private rooms from $1810</p>', '<h1 class=\"h1\">The Greenpoint House</h1>\r\n<h4>A TIGHT-KNIT COMMUNITY IN A LIVELY NEIGHBORHOOD</h4>', '<div>\r\n<p>The Greenpoint House is only a few short blocks from the East River, nestled among restaurants, coffee shops and a collection of cozy brick apartment buildings. The nearby waterfront is scattered with green spaces and high rises, or you can opt to explore the neighborhood&rsquo;s historic Polish shops and eateries.</p>\r\n<p>The house itself is a recently renovated building with updated appliances, hardwood floors and large windows. The Greenpoint House has three units altogether with spacious and beautifully decorated common rooms, and a gorgeous finished backyard.</p>\r\n<p><strong>The main draw:</strong> The common spaces, which include comfy seating, a pool table, plenty of space for co-working or game nights, a large flat-screen TV, a fully outfitted fitness center and a landscaped backyard with seating and a barbecue.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Perfect for you if:</strong> You&rsquo;re looking for a vibrant social life and love to explore. The Greenpoint House is set up to help you connect with your housemates, and the location is within an easy walk of plentiful nightlife options, as well as the subway and ferry.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Our suggestion:</strong> Greenpoint is packed to bursting with bars, cafes and restaurants &mdash; push your boundaries and try something you&rsquo;ve never had before!</p>\r\n</div>', 5, '', 'the-greenpoint-house-kitchen-2.jpg', 'the-greenpoint-house-bedroom-1.jpg', '', 248, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'The Greenpoint House', 0, 0, 'a:11:{i:0;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:20:\"Throughout the house\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:547:\"<p>{throughout}</p>\r\n<table class=\"table v2\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<th>12+ Months</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Executive + Bath)</th>\r\n<td>$2300</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Large+)</th>\r\n<td>$2150</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Large)</th>\r\n<td>$2050</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"5\">\r\n<p>*Prices above do not include $149/month/person utilities allowance fee</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div class=\"center\"><a class=\"button2 red\" href=\"online-questionnaire\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Apply for free</a></div>\";}i:1;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:12:\"The Bedrooms\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:324:\"<p>All of the bedrooms in the Greenpoint House are private and feature full-sized beds, closet space and enough room so you can feel at home. Bedding is available for an additional fee.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Amenities:</strong> full-size memory-foam mattresses, shelving, hooks and closets/organizational tools.</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:4:{i:0;s:36:\"the-greenpoint-house-bedroom-1_1.jpg\";i:1;s:36:\"the-greenpoint-house-bedroom-2_1.jpg\";i:2;s:36:\"the-greenpoint-house-bedroom-4_1.jpg\";i:3;s:36:\"the-greenpoint-house-bedroom-3_1.jpg\";}}i:2;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:19:\"The (Co)Living Room\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:295:\"<p>The living rooms are at the heart of each unit within the Greenpoint House. The furnished units have comfy couches and TVs, and are equipped with everything you need to relax.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Google Chromecast</li>\r\n<li><strong>Security</strong>: 24/7 security in all common areas.</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:1:{i:0;s:37:\"the-greenpoint-house-livingroom-1.jpg\";}}i:3;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:24:\"The kitchens/dining room\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:502:\"<p>In these apartments, the kitchen and dining room are the first rooms you enter. These spaces are used for cooking dinner and relaxing in the evening over a glass of wine.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Amenities</strong> include electric stoves, stainless-steel fridges, microwaves, large sinks, coffee makers, blenders, plenty of cabinets, cookware, tableware, cutting boards and anything else you would need in a kitchen.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Security</strong>: 24/7 security in all common areas.</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:2:{i:0;s:32:\"the-greenpoint-house-kitchen.jpg\";i:1;s:34:\"the-greenpoint-house-kitchen-2.jpg\";}}i:4;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:13:\"The bathrooms\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:490:\"<p>Every unit in the Greenpoint House has enough shared bathrooms so you can be sure you&rsquo;ll never have to wait. Some bedrooms have private bathrooms, depending on availability and your price range.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Also included</strong>: toilet paper, hand soap and small garbage bags, which will never be empty!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"h5\">Laundry room</p>\r\n<p>Each apartment also has an in-unit washer and dryer, so you can do your laundry in the comfort of your own home.</p>\";s:6:\"images\";a:2:{i:0;s:35:\"the-greenpoint-house-bathroom-2.jpg\";i:1;s:35:\"the-greenpoint-house-bathroom-1.jpg\";}}i:5;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:19:\"The (Co)Living Room\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"images\";a:9:{i:0;s:28:\"greenpoint-common-area-5.jpg\";i:1;s:28:\"greenpoint-common-area-3.jpg\";i:2;s:28:\"greenpoint-common-area-4.jpg\";i:3;s:28:\"greenpoint-common-area-2.jpg\";i:4;s:28:\"greenpoint-common-area-1.jpg\";i:5;s:28:\"greenpoint-common-area-6.jpg\";i:6;s:28:\"greenpoint-common-area-7.jpg\";i:7;s:28:\"greenpoint-common-area-8.jpg\";i:8;s:28:\"greenpoint-common-area-9.jpg\";}}i:6;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:3:\"Gym\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"images\";a:6:{i:0;s:25:\"greenpoint-gym-area-5.jpg\";i:1;s:25:\"greenpoint-gym-area-6.jpg\";i:2;s:25:\"greenpoint-gym-area-1.jpg\";i:3;s:25:\"greenpoint-gym-area-7.jpg\";i:4;s:25:\"greenpoint-gym-area-3.jpg\";i:5;s:25:\"greenpoint-gym-area-4.jpg\";}}i:7;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:8:\"Backyard\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"images\";a:7:{i:0;s:25:\"greenpoint-backyard-7.jpg\";i:1;s:25:\"greenpoint-backyard-3.jpg\";i:2;s:25:\"greenpoint-backyard-4.jpg\";i:3;s:25:\"greenpoint-backyard-6.jpg\";i:4;s:25:\"greenpoint-backyard-5.jpg\";i:5;s:25:\"greenpoint-backyard-2.jpg\";i:6;s:25:\"greenpoint-backyard-1.jpg\";}}i:8;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:19:\"PERKS AND BENEFITS:\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:646:\"<div class=\"fx ch3 w perc_advantages\">\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Fast, reliable WiFi</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Regular professional cleaning</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Furnished interiors</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">In-unit laundry</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Keyless entry</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Furnished backyard</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Community events</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Dedicated community manager</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Updated appliances</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Dedicated maintenance team</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\";}i:9;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:6:\"Prices\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:1596:\"<table class=\"table v2\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<th>12+ Months</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Executive + Bath)</th>\r\n<td>$2300</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Large+)</th>\r\n<td>$2150</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Large)</th>\r\n<td>$2050</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"5\">\r\n<p>*Prices above do not include $149/month/person utilities allowance fee</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div class=\"center\"><a class=\"button2 red\" href=\"online-questionnaire\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Apply for free</a></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Availability: Year-round / Minimum stay of 1 month / Month-to-month payment options available / Minimum age 18</strong></p>\r\n<div class=\"main_width partners_sb\">\r\n<div class=\"second_block fx w\">\r\n<div class=\"ico\"><img title=\"TheGuarantors Logo\" src=\"../files/uploads/TG-Mark-Color.png\" alt=\"TheGuarantors Logo\" width=\"135\" height=\"145\" /></div>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<h4 class=\"h1\">TheGuarantors</h4>\r\n<p>Don\'t quite meet application requirements? Meet Lease Guarantee. We\'ve partnered&nbsp;with <strong>TheGuarantors</strong> to make it easier for you to qualify for&nbsp;your dream home. To get started, simply fill out a <a class=\"green\" href=\"https://bit.ly/3Av1ivf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferer\">renter&nbsp;application</a>. Once you\'re approved, TheGuarantors will let us know and you\'ll be ready to sign your lease. Simple as that. Click <a class=\"green\" href=\"https://bit.ly/3A8mCpe\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferer\">here</a> for more detail.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\";}i:10;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:32:\"Welcome to Greenpoint, Brooklyn.\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:934:\"<div>\r\n<p>Take a stroll through this neighborhood nestled between Long Island City and Williamsburg, and you&rsquo;ll have no shortage of things to do and people to see. As home to one of the country&rsquo;s highest concentrations of Polish immigrants, Greenpoint has a meaningful history as a home to immigrants and multi-generational families. As with many New York neighborhoods, the avenues are busy and lined with shops, while the streets are more calm. If you&rsquo;re interested in getting involved in the community, environmental issues are the place to start &mdash; Greenpointers have a strong history of climate advocacy.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<p class=\"h5\">Location</p>\r\n<p>The closest subway station is Greenpoint Ave, served by the G train and only a 2-minute walk away. Multiple bus lines also serve the neighborhood. You can easily transfer onto the L two stops away and be in Manhattan in a mere 30 minutes.</p>\r\n</div>\";s:6:\"images\";a:4:{i:0;s:27:\"Brooklyn_August_2017_01.jpg\";i:1;s:49:\"Greenpoint,_Brooklyn,_NY,_USA_-_panoramio_(1).jpg\";i:2;s:44:\"Greenpoint,_Brooklyn_seen_from_Manhattan.jpg\";i:3;s:25:\"Greenpoint_Waterfront.JPG\";}}}', '', '', '', '<div class=\"txt\">\r\n<h1 class=\"\">The Greenpoint House Move-In Guide</h1>\r\n<h2><em><strong>107 Greenpoint Ave. Brooklyn, NY 11222</strong></em></h2>\r\n<hr class=\"hr\" />\r\n<h3><strong>The Community</strong></h3>\r\n<p>Welcome to Outpost! We&rsquo;re glad you&rsquo;re joining our New York coliving community. Outpost wants to create spaces where people never feel alone &mdash; as we all are stronger together. We hope you enjoy your time with us!</p>\r\n<p>We communicate with each other via our house&rsquo;s Messenger group, which your House Leader will add you upon arrival. We also offer an Outpost Slack channel where you can find other members with similar interests and meet new people in your area. We send out relevant updates and information via email, so keep an eye out!</p>\r\n<p>Your <strong>Member Portal</strong> is where you can RSVP for community events, submit maintenance and cleaning requests and access important documents. <a class=\"green\" href=\"../user/login\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Find it here</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Your <strong>House Leader</strong> will be your main point of contact with Outpost.</p>\r\n<p>Here&rsquo;s how to use the app:</p>\r\n<div class=\"fx w vc ch2\">\r\n<div><img style=\"width: 70%; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"../files/uploads/august_lock.gif\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>When you move in, your House Leader will give you a tour of the house and talk to you a bit about the Outpost community. They&rsquo;ll also:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Take a photo of your ID (for our records and according to state law)</li>\r\n<li>Add you to your Messenger group</li>\r\n<li>Assign you cupboard and refrigerator space, according to your room number.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>We have a lot of activities to help you get involved with our community and get to know the city. Pay attention to your Member Portal and your house&rsquo;s Messenger group to keep up with what&rsquo;s going on, or just ask your House Leader!</p>\r\n<h3><strong>The Logistics</strong></h3>\r\n<h3>Moving In</h3>\r\n<p>To access the building, you&rsquo;ll use a key provided to you by the House Leader. Once inside, you&rsquo;ll use the August app to access your unit. Download the app and sign up for an account, and your House Leader will give you access upon arrival. Here&rsquo;s how to use the app:</p>\r\n<p>You&rsquo;ll also receive a key card to access both the house and your individual unit in the case you don&rsquo;t have your phone. Your House Leader will provide you this key upon arrival &mdash; please keep it in a safe and secure location!</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>When you move in, your House Leader will give you a tour of the house and talk to you a bit about the Outpost community.</p>\r\n<p>They&rsquo;ll also:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Take a photo of your ID (for our records and according to state law)</li>\r\n<li>Add you to your Messenger group</li>\r\n<li>Assign you cupboard and refrigerator space, according to your room number.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The WiFi name is Outpost (or something similar) and the password is <strong>befreenyc</strong>.</p>\r\n<h3>Living at Outpost</h3>\r\n<p>You&rsquo;ll find helpful information linked above in our Guide to Responsible Coliving, but there are a few more things you should know:</p>\r\n<p><strong>Recycling is required</strong>, and New York City has strict guidelines. Watch the video below to see what you should recycle:</p>\r\n<iframe style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/EUyVELb5PzY\" width=\"70%\" height=\"400\"></iframe><br /><br />\r\n<p><strong>Cleanliness is also required.</strong> That&rsquo;s especially true of common areas, including shared rooms. Here are some easy ways to think about cleanliness at Outpost:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Leave rooms in the condition in which you found them</li>\r\n<li>Clean up after yourself</li>\r\n<li>Don&rsquo;t leave your belongings in the common area unless you&rsquo;re returning immediately</li>\r\n<li>Pay attention to the signs around the house: They&rsquo;re there to help our community run smoothly!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Outpost is not responsible for lost or damaged mail or packages.</strong> Your House Leader will check the mail regularly. Make sure to put your full address, including your outside door code, in the delivery field when you order something. You may find your package left inside the main door, concealed outside, with a roommate who picked it up for you or returned to a distribution center for a later delivery. It&rsquo;s your responsibility to track your packages and make sure you&rsquo;re home to receive them when necessary.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 2, '40.73023000', '-73.95596000', 504, '', '2022-10-14 09:20:11'),
