(352, 253, 306, 'the-fort-greene-house', '', 'The Fort Greene House', 'The Fort Greene House (NY 11205) | Outpost Club', 'We worked with interior designers to make The Fort Greene House comfortable in every room. ✓ Fully furnished ✓ Security ✓ Gas ✓ Electricity ✓ Water ✓ Wi-Fi ✓ Cleaning and maintenance', 'The Fort Greene House | Outpost Club', '<p>Fort Greene, Brooklyn</p>\r\n<p>Private rooms from $1550</p>', '', '<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">The Scoop</h6>\r\n<p>The Fort Greene House is less than half an hour from Manhattan. The house has plenty of cafes, restaurants and bars within walking distance, and is mere blocks from Downtown Brooklyn&rsquo;s bustling major arteries. It has eight units spread across four levels, and even includes access to in-house gym facilities.</p>\r\n<p>The house has been recently renovated space throughout, with split-unit heating and air conditioning, stainless steel appliances and hardwood floors. This house is a four-level, eight-unit home, with each unit equipped with a full kitchen and living room. The spaces are arranged around bright and inviting common areas, and the bedrooms are spacious in comparison to your average New York City apartment.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">Location</h6>\r\n<p>This coliving space is located in the cozy, leafy Fort Greene neighborhood bordering Downtown Brooklyn, in an area known for its creative scene and more relaxed pace. It&rsquo;s near plenty of green space, including the scenic Fort Greene Park, and is walking distance from the East River waterfront, where you can catch the ferry to Manhattan.</p>\r\n<strong>The Fort Greene House is a 15-minute walk to the B/D and N/Q/R/W trains on DeKalb Ave., the G train at Fulton St. and the A/C trains at Lafayette Ave. You can even reach the 2/3 and 4/5 trains at Nevins St. in less than 20 minutes. You can also walk 7 minutes to take the NYC Ferry from the Brooklyn Navy Yard stop.</strong></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>', 5, '', 'the-fort-greene-house-background.jpg', 'the-fort-greene-house-main.jpg', '', 292, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'The Fort Greene House', 0, 0, 'a:8:{i:0;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:20:\"Throughout the house\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:694:\"<p>{throughout}</p>\r\n<table class=\"table v2\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<th>12+ Months</th>\r\n<th>5-11 Months</th>\r\n<th>1-4 Months</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Large room with desk)</th>\r\n<td>$1840</td>\r\n<td>$1920</td>\r\n<td>$2620</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Standard)</th>\r\n<td>$1740</td>\r\n<td>$1820</td>\r\n<td>$2520</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Economy)</th>\r\n<td>$1550</td>\r\n<td>$1770</td>\r\n<td>$2470</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"5\">\r\n<p>*Prices above do not include $149/month/person utilities allowance fee</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div class=\"center\"><a class=\"button2 red\" href=\"online-questionnaire\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Apply for free</a></div>\";}i:1;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:12:\"The Bedrooms\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:314:\"<p>Your room will be clean and furnished just like the rest of the house. Rooms at the Fort Greene House are all private. Bedding is available for an additional fee.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Amenities</strong>: memory-foam full-sized mattresses, pillows, shelving, hooks and closets/organizational tools.</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:7:{i:0;s:34:\"the-fort-greene-house-bedoom-3.jpg\";i:1;s:34:\"the-fort-greene-house-bedoom-6.jpg\";i:2;s:34:\"the-fort-greene-house-bedoom-1.jpg\";i:3;s:34:\"the-fort-greene-house-bedoom-7.jpg\";i:4;s:34:\"the-fort-greene-house-bedoom-8.jpg\";i:5;s:34:\"the-fort-greene-house-bedoom-2.jpg\";i:6;s:34:\"the-fort-greene-house-bedoom-5.jpg\";}}i:2;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:24:\"The kitchens/dining room\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:392:\"<p>The kitchens in each unit have gas stoves and stainless steel appliances and are stocked with plenty of supplies, so you can meal prep or cook dinner with your housemates without a worry.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Amenities</strong> include microwaves, dishwashers, large sinks, coffee makers, plenty of cabinets, cookware, tableware and anything else you would need in a kitchen.</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:3:{i:0;s:35:\"the-fort-greene-house-kitchen-1.jpg\";i:1;s:35:\"the-fort-greene-house-kitchen-2.jpg\";i:2;s:35:\"the-fort-greene-house-kitchen-3.jpg\";}}i:3;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:20:\" The (co)living room\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:405:\"<p>The living rooms are at the heart of each unit within the Fort Greene House, with their comfy couches and TVs, these areas are where we host movie nights, game nights and chill hangouts. The space is equipped with everything you need to relax.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Living room also includes:</strong> Additional seating, pillows, lamps.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Tech:</strong> Google Chromecast.</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:5:{i:0;s:38:\"the-fort-greene-house-livingroom-1.jpg\";i:1;s:38:\"the-fort-greene-house-livingroom-4.jpg\";i:2;s:38:\"the-fort-greene-house-livingroom-3.jpg\";i:3;s:38:\"the-fort-greene-house-livingroom-5.jpg\";i:4;s:38:\"the-fort-greene-house-livingroom-2.jpg\";}}i:4;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:13:\"The bathrooms\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:352:\"<p>We provide many bathroom essentials, as well.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong> toilet paper, hand soap and small garbage bags, which will never run out!&nbsp;</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p class=\"h5\">Laundry room</p>\r\n<p>The Fort Greene House also has in-building laundry facilities where members can do their laundry in the comfort of their own home.</p>\";s:6:\"images\";a:3:{i:0;s:36:\"the-fort-greene-house-bathroom-1.jpg\";i:1;s:36:\"the-fort-greene-house-bathroom-2.jpg\";i:2;s:36:\"the-fort-greene-house-bathroom-3.jpg\";}}i:5;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:7:\"The gym\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:209:\"<p>At the Fort Greene House, you can keep fit without having to pay for a gym membership. The workout area at this house includes cardio equipment, with floor-to-ceiling mirrors so you can check your form.</p>\";}i:6;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:19:\"Additional benefits\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:178:\"<p><strong>We screen all candidates before approving applications so that there are no worries about moving into a new place with new people &mdash; only excitement!</strong></p>\";}i:7;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:6:\"Prices\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:852:\"<table class=\"table v2\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<th>12+ Months</th>\r\n<th>5-11 Months</th>\r\n<th>1-4 Months</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Large room with desk)</th>\r\n<td>$1840</td>\r\n<td>$1920</td>\r\n<td>$2620</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Standard)</th>\r\n<td>$1740</td>\r\n<td>$1820</td>\r\n<td>$2520</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Economy)</th>\r\n<td>$1550</td>\r\n<td>$1770</td>\r\n<td>$2470</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"5\">\r\n<p>*Prices above do not include $149/month/person utilities allowance fee</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div class=\"center\"><a class=\"button2 red\" href=\"online-questionnaire\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Apply for free</a></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Availability: Year-round / Minimum stay of 1 month / Month-to-month payment options available / Minimum age 18</strong></p>\";}}', '', '', '', '<div class=\"txt\">\r\n<h1 class=\"\">The Fort Greene House Move-In Guide</h1>\r\n<h2><em><strong>54 Cumberland St, Brooklyn, NY 11205</strong></em></h2>\r\n<hr class=\"hr\" />\r\n<h3><strong>The Community</strong></h3>\r\n<p>Welcome to Outpost! We&rsquo;re glad you&rsquo;re here. Coliving isn&rsquo;t just about having roommates or sharing a kitchen &mdash; it&rsquo;s about recognizing that we can do more, accomplish more and be more when we work together.</p>\r\n<p>We communicate with each other via our house&rsquo;s Messenger group, which your House Leader will add you upon arrival. We also offer an Outpost Slack channel where you can find other members with similar interests and meet new people in your area. We send out relevant updates and information via email, so keep an eye out!</p>\r\n<p>Your <strong>Member Portal</strong> is where you can RSVP for community events, submit maintenance and cleaning requests and access important documents. <a class=\"green\" href=\"../user/login\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Find it here</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Your <strong>House Leader</strong> will be your main point of contact with Outpost. Here&rsquo;s what they can help you with:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Info about community activities</li>\r\n<li>Restocking supplies</li>\r\n<li>Questions about Outpost</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>We have a lot of activities to help you get involved with our community and get to know the city. Pay attention to your Member Portal and your house&rsquo;s Messenger group to keep up with what&rsquo;s going on, or just ask your House Leader!</p>\r\n<h3><strong>The Logistics</strong></h3>\r\n<h3>Moving In</h3>\r\n<p>To access the house you&rsquo;ll need the app <strong>Openow</strong>, which your House Leader can help you connect to upon your arrival. This app will allow you to unlock the doors for the duration of your stay!</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>When you move in, your House Leader will give you a tour of the house and talk to you a bit about the Outpost community.</p>\r\n<p>They&rsquo;ll also:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Take a photo of your ID (for our records and according to state law)</li>\r\n<li>Add you to your Messenger group</li>\r\n<li>Assign you cupboard and refrigerator space, according to your room number.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The WiFi name is Outpost (or something similar) and the password is <strong>befreenyc</strong>.</p>\r\n<h3>Living at Outpost</h3>\r\n<p>You&rsquo;ll find helpful information linked above in our Guide to Responsible Coliving, but there are a few more things you should know:</p>\r\n<p><strong>Recycling is required</strong>, and New York City has strict guidelines. Watch the video below to see what you should recycle:</p>\r\n<iframe style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/EUyVELb5PzY\" width=\"70%\" height=\"400\"></iframe><br /><br />\r\n<p><strong>Cleanliness is also required.</strong> That&rsquo;s especially true of common areas, including shared rooms. Here are some easy ways to think about cleanliness at Outpost:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Leave rooms in the condition in which you found them</li>\r\n<li>Clean up after yourself</li>\r\n<li>Don&rsquo;t leave your belongings in the common area unless you&rsquo;re returning immediately</li>\r\n<li>Pay attention to the signs around the house: They&rsquo;re there to help our community run smoothly!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Outpost is not responsible for lost or damaged mail or packages.</strong> Your House Leader will check the mail regularly. Make sure to put your full address, including your outside door code, in the delivery field when you order something. You may find your package left inside the main door, concealed outside, with a roommate who picked it up for you or returned to a distribution center for a later delivery. It&rsquo;s your responsibility to track your packages and make sure you&rsquo;re home to receive them when necessary.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 2, '40.69659000', '-73.97474000', 495, '', '2022-09-07 08:26:54'),
(282, 0, NULL, 'soma-house-3d-tour', '', 'SoMa 3D Tour', 'The SoMa House 3D Tour', '', 'The SoMa House 3D Tour', '', '', '<h1>The SoMa House 3D Tour</h1>\r\n<p><iframe style=\"margin-top: 1em;\" src=\"https://my.matterport.com/show/?m=DvtFZYfMwLT\" width=\"100%\" height=\"500\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"> </iframe></p>', 9, '', '', '', '', 277, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'The SoMa House 3D Tour', 0, 0, 'a:0:{}', '', '', '', '', 0, '0.00000000', '0.00000000', 0, '', NULL),
(283, 254, NULL, 'soma-house', 'soma', 'The SoMa House', 'SoMa (SF) Room Rentals, Shared Apartments | Outpost Club', '', 'The SoMa House', '<p>SoMa, San Francisco</p>\r\n<p>Shared rooms from $790 | Private rooms from $2050</p>', '<h1 class=\"h1\">SoMa House</h1>\r\n<h4>The house is located right in the heart of San Francisco</h4>', '<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">The Scoop</h6>\r\n<p>Our SoMa House is an intimate community in the heart of a lively bay-side neighborhood. We chose SoMa because it&rsquo;s conveniently located near Union Square and with easy access to BART and multiple Muni lines. The neighborhood itself is full of things to eat, see and do, as well as multiple grocery stores, and the commute downtown is a breeze.</p>\r\n<p>Our SoMa House consists of just four bedrooms, which promotes a sense of community among our members. The apartment is spacious, with a common kitchen and living room with a large table for co-working and a comfy couch for movie nights. It&rsquo;s the perfect place for professionals and students alike.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">The Neighborhood</h6>\r\n<p>This coliving house is located a stone&rsquo;s throw from downtown. With Union Square just 14 minutes away and a range of dining, drinking and entertainment options in walking distance, the location is ideal for both work and weekend leisure activities. The house is located near the UC Hastings College of Law and the San Francisco Public Library.</p>\r\n<p>The nearest Muni station is Van Ness on the K-Ingleside and T-Third lines, just a 5-minute walk from the house. You can be in Union Square in just 14 minutes (or walk in 29 minutes). The SoMa House is just a 15-minute walk to the Civic Center, where transit links including BART are available, and multiple bus lines serve the neighborhood.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">The space</h6>\r\n<p>This house is an intimate yet spacious, newly renovated space with hardwood floors and updated appliances. The kitchen and common areas are massive compared to the average San Francisco apartment, and furnished with everything you&rsquo;ll need for work and play.</p>\r\n<p><strong>This space is move-in ready; all you have to do is show up with your suitcase.</strong></p>\r\n</div>', 5, '', 'soma-house.jpg', 'soma-background.jpg', '', 532, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The SoMa House', 0, 0, 'a:7:{i:0;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:20:\"Throughout the house\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:1495:\"<p>{throughout}</p>\r\n<table class=\"table v2\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<th class=\"title\">\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><span class=\"gold\">Gold</span> Membership</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</th>\r\n<th colspan=\"2\">\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><span class=\"silver\">Silver</span> Membership</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"bronze\">Bronze</span> Membership</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"2\"><em>*Bronze members must move in on <strong>the first day</strong> of the month</em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<th>1-12 Months</th>\r\n<th>4+ Months</th>\r\n<th>1-3 Months</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private&nbsp;(Executive)</th>\r\n<td>$2050</td>\r\n<td>$2190</td>\r\n<td>$2250</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>2-people shared</th>\r\n<td>$990</td>\r\n<td>$1150</td>\r\n<td>$1190</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>4-people shared</th>\r\n<td>$790</td>\r\n<td>$950</td>\r\n<td>$990</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"5\">See the benefits of Bronze, Silver, and Gold Membership <a class=\"red\" href=\"../memberships\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">here</a>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>**The prices shown indicate <strong>the prices valid for move-in between June 1, 2020, and August 31, 2020</strong>. The exact price is indicated in your membership agreement and may vary depending on the length of commitment, your membership level and the size of your group, if applicable.</em></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div class=\"center\"><a class=\"button2\" href=\"join-us\">I`m interested</a></div>\";}i:1;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:12:\"The Bedrooms\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:494:\"<p>Your room will be move-in ready, just like the rest of the house; there&rsquo;s no need to even bring a pillow. There are four bedrooms with a choice of private or shared rooms, depending on availability and your price range.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Amenities: memory-foam mattresses, memory-foam pillows, extension cords to your bedside, shelving, hooks and closets/organizational tools.</li>\r\n<li>Gold and silver members: Bed linens and towels will be available for you when you arrive.</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:8:{i:0;s:19:\"soma-background.jpg\";i:1;s:18:\"soma-bedroom-9.jpg\";i:2;s:18:\"soma-bedroom-4.jpg\";i:3;s:18:\"soma-bedroom-7.jpg\";i:4;s:18:\"soma-bedroom-8.jpg\";i:5;s:18:\"soma-bedroom-6.jpg\";i:6;s:18:\"soma-bedroom-5.jpg\";i:7;s:18:\"soma-bedroom-1.jpg\";}}i:2;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:24:\"The kitchens/dining room\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:829:\"<p>The kitchen has plenty of counter space for cooking on your own or with a group, as well as updated appliances and a spacious fridge. There is also a large dining table that can be used for eating, socializing or working. The kitchen is the center of social life at the house, playing host to potluck dinners, solo meals and chats in the evening over a glass of wine.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Amenities include a gas stove, stainless-steel fridge, microwave, large sinks, a coffee maker, plenty of cabinets, cookware, tableware, cutting boards and anything else you would need in a kitchen.</li>\r\n<li>Also included: salt, pepper, sugar, coffee grounds, tea, olive oil, paper towels, dish soap, hand soap and garbage/recycling bags, all of which are routinely restocked.</li>\r\n<li>Security: 24/7 security in all common areas.</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:5:{i:0;s:18:\"soma-kitchen-5.jpg\";i:1;s:18:\"soma-kitchen-4.jpg\";i:2;s:18:\"soma-kitchen-3.jpg\";i:3;s:18:\"soma-kitchen-2.jpg\";i:4;s:18:\"soma-kitchen-1.jpg\";}}i:3;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:20:\"The co-working space\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:384:\"<p>The large kitchen serves as the principal common area for the SoMa House. This open-plan room features a large dining table with ample room for co-working, and you can also use desk space throughout the house and within the bedrooms for your remote working needs. This space also includes a printer (paper and ink included) to make sure you\'ll always be ready to be productive.</p>\";s:6:\"images\";a:5:{i:0;s:21:\"soma-co-working-1.jpg\";i:1;s:21:\"soma-co-working-4.jpg\";i:2;s:21:\"soma-co-working-2.jpg\";i:3;s:21:\"soma-co-working-6.jpg\";i:4;s:21:\"soma-co-working-3.jpg\";}}i:4;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:13:\"The bathrooms\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:636:\"<p>We provide many bathroom essentials, as well. There are three bathrooms in the SoMa House, more than enough for the four bedrooms in this apartment, so you&rsquo;ll never have to wait.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Also included: toilet paper, shampoo, body wash, hand soap and small garbage bags, which will never run out! We also provide hair dryers, so there\'s no need to bring your own.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>LAUNDRY ROOM</p>\r\n<p>The SoMa House also has a washer and dryer where members can do their laundry for free in the comfort of their own home.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Security: 24/7 security in all common areas, as well as lockers.</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:2:{i:0;s:19:\"soma-bathroom-3.jpg\";i:1;s:19:\"soma-bathroom-2.jpg\";}}i:5;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:19:\"Additional benefits\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:382:\"<p>Your Gold Membership gives you the opportunity to move between all our houses from month to month, allowing you to see what it&rsquo;s like to live in different neighborhoods and even in other cities.</p>\r\n<p><strong>We screen all candidates before approving applications so there are no worries about moving into a new place with new people &mdash; only excitement!</strong></p>\";}i:6;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:6:\"Prices\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:1932:\"<p>We have flexible month-to-month commitment options. We do not require extensive documents from you, guarantors or large deposits. A longer commitment on your side helps us to provide you with better prices.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table v2\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<th class=\"title\">\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><span class=\"gold\">Gold</span> Membership</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</th>\r\n<th colspan=\"2\">\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><span class=\"silver\">Silver</span> Membership</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"bronze\">Bronze</span> Membership</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"2\"><em>*Bronze members must move in on <strong>the first day</strong> of the month</em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<th>1-12 Months</th>\r\n<th>4+ Months</th>\r\n<th>1-3 Months</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private&nbsp;(Executive)</th>\r\n<td>$2050</td>\r\n<td>$2190</td>\r\n<td>$2250</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>2-people shared</th>\r\n<td>$990</td>\r\n<td>$1150</td>\r\n<td>$1190</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>4-people shared</th>\r\n<td>$790</td>\r\n<td>$950</td>\r\n<td>$990</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"5\">See the benefits of Bronze, Silver, and Gold Membership <a class=\"red\" href=\"../memberships\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">here</a>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>**The prices shown indicate <strong>the prices valid for move-in between June 1, 2020, and August 31, 2020</strong>. The exact price is indicated in your membership agreement and may vary depending on the length of commitment, your membership level and the size of your group, if applicable.</em></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div class=\"center\"><a class=\"button2\" href=\"join-us\">Get your exclusive offer now</a></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Availability: Year-round / Minimum stay of 1 month / Month-to-month payment options available / Minimum age 18 / 30-day cancellation notice with Gold Membership</strong></p>\";}}', '', '', '', '', 0, '0.00000000', '0.00000000', 0, '', NULL),
(333, 0, NULL, 'covid-19', '', 'COVID-19', 'COVID-19 | The Outpost Club', 'All updates from The Outpost Club in one place', 'COVID-19', '<h1 class=\"h1\">COVID-19</h1>\r\n<h4>All updates from The Outpost Club in one place</h4>', '', '<h2><span class=\"red_text\">May 12, 2020</span></h2>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>AN UPDATE FROM OUTPOST REGARDING CORONAVIRUS RESTRICTIONS</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>As always, the well-being of our members is our top priority, and we\'re committed to providing a safe environment for members at all Outpost houses as the novel coronavirus pandemic continues to evolve. We\'re following expert recommendations within our houses to ensure your safety, including by leaving rooms empty for at least 24 hours after a move-out, providing our staff with appropriate PPE and using high-strength Lysol, Clorox and bleach disinfectants to clean after every guest departure. We\'ll continue to adapt our strategies moving forward to ensure the health and safety of all of our members.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em><strong>Sincerely,</strong></em></p>\r\n<p><em><strong>The Outpost Club Team</strong></em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><span class=\"red_text\">March 27, 2020</span></h2>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>AN UPDATE FROM OUTPOST REGARDING CORONAVIRUS RESTRICTIONS</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>On behalf of our entire team, we want to thank you for your efforts in keeping our community safe during this time by maintaining social distance and proper hygiene. We want to give you a quick update on how we plan to address potential cases of COVID-19 within our communities. We continue to closely monitor guidelines and regulations set by local, state and federal officials, as well as recommendations by the CDC and WHO.</p>\r\n<h3>Here\'s what we ask of all of our members as we navigate this pandemic together:</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If you begin experiencing symptoms or are tested for or confirmed to have COVID-19, stay in your unit and email <a class=\"green\" href=\"mailto:customer.service@outpost-club.com\" target=\"_blank\" data-hs-link-id=\"0\">customer.service@outpost-club.com</a>&nbsp;to let us know immediately. We\'ll protect your privacy.</li>\r\n<li>Continue to wash your hands with soap and water for 20 seconds upon entering the house and before/after touching high-contact surfaces like door knobs and handles.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Respect your housemates. Even if you don\'t feel like you\'re at risk for contacting COVID-19, <strong>it\'s your responsibility to follow all public health guidelines, including staying home as much as possible, so as not to put your housemates at risk.</strong> If you feel a housemate is unnecessarily putting your house at risk, please first talk to them, and let us know if the situation isn\'t resolved.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Here are the first steps we\'ll take if one of our community members reports a potential COVID-19 case:</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>We\'ll notify the other members of the unit immediately that someone in their unit may be ill.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Within 24 hours, we\'ll deliver masks, gloves, additional disinfectant and sanitizing chlorhexidine to the affected unit or house (subject to availability).</li>\r\n<li>We\'ll sanitize all common areas, including hallways, to reduce the risk of additional transmission.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Remember:</strong> If your symptoms are mild, health officials have asked that you don\'t go to the hospital. We recommend you stay in your unit and notify your relatives and Outpost. If you do need to go to the hospital or to a clinic, call the hospital first and explain that you\'re experiencing COVID-19 symptoms so they can prepare. If you are short of breath or have a very high fever, call 911.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>We appreciate your understanding as we navigate this situation as it evolves. We\'ll continue to keep you informed as we adapt based on the most up-to-date information from the CDC, WHO and the government.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Sources: <a class=\"green\" href=\"https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/if-you-are-sick/steps-when-sick.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">CDC</a> | <a class=\"green\" href=\"https://www.who.int/news-room/q-a-detail/q-a-coronaviruses\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">WHO</a> | <a class=\"green\" href=\"https://www1.nyc.gov/site/doh/covid/covid-19-main.page\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">City of New York</a> | <a class=\"green\" href=\"https://sf.gov/topics/coronavirus-covid-19\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">City of San Francisco</a> | <a class=\"green\" href=\"https://www.jerseycitynj.gov/CityHall/health/coronavirus\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">City of Jersey City</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em><strong>Sincerely,</strong></em></p>\r\n<p><em><strong>The Outpost Club Team</strong></em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><span class=\"red_text\">March 20, 2020</span></h2>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>AN UPDATE FROM OUTPOST REGARDING CORONAVIRUS RESTRICTIONS</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>As you may already know, the state has implemented restrictions on movements and businesses.&nbsp;While it\'s unclear whether or not our operations are directly affected by the restrictions, we wanted to reach out and update you on how things are going to go moving forward.</p>\r\n<h3>Cleaning</h3>\r\n<p>This week we will follow the usual schedule; however, we are not sure if we will be able to have our cleaners visit the houses next week.</p>\r\n<p>Therefore, we ask everyone to do their part: Please be very, very, very neat. Clean up after yourselves. Follow the trash schedule. Clean the bathroom after you use it.<br />It&rsquo;s not JUST about the coronavirus. We all must work together to make sure that healthy people stay healthy, and also to protect each other and not overwhelm the medical system. In other words, at this point it&rsquo;s everyone&rsquo;s responsibility to keep our houses as clean as possible to avoid ANY illness, and it does start with everyone doing their part.</p>\r\n<h3>Maintenance</h3>\r\n<p>We will limit responses to maintenance requests to emergencies. If something happens, don&rsquo;t hesitate to reach out. But we won&rsquo;t be able to attend to routine things, so please make sure you use the house things responsibly and carefully. In the past we&rsquo;ve seen toilets clogged with paper towels and hygiene products. We&rsquo;ve cleaned bathroom drains of balls of hair and ... well, God knows what. We might not be able to send anyone to do this while restrictions are in place, so please be responsible tenants, and mindful of our limited ability to address minor issues. Again, if there&rsquo;s an actual emergency we will do our best to attend to it immediately or as soon as possible.</p>\r\n<h3>Supplies</h3>\r\n<p>We have created some supply reserve, so we should be good for some time in case there continue to be disruptions with deliveries. In the houses where we don&rsquo;t have a House Leader living on premises, however, <strong>we need volunteers who are willing to distribute a reasonable amount of supplies so we don&rsquo;t run out.</strong> If you feel like you can and want to do that, please do reach out to me (george@outpost-club.com) for additional information.</p>\r\n<h3>Outside guests and gatherings</h3>\r\n<p>We are not closing the common spaces in the houses. However, we are absolutely and strictly going to enforce a no-guest policy, as prescribed by Gov. Cuomo of New York: \"Nonessential gatherings of individuals of any size or for any reason are canceled or postponed.&rdquo; (NY Times)</p>\r\n<p>Additionally, Gov. Newsom of California has ordered all Californians to stay in their houses as much as possible, and Gov. Murphy of New Jersey will implement further restrictions this weekend. (NY Times)</p>\r\n<p><strong>Let me explain why this matters:</strong></p>\r\n<p>You and your friends may be in low-risk groups. You may both have strong immune systems and won&rsquo;t end up getting sick, but without knowing, you may both be carriers of the new coronavirus. So you open the door, they open the door, and the virus is now on that door knob. And then your housemate who isn&rsquo;t lucky to have a super strong immune system opens that door and is exposed to the virus ... You get the idea, and I&rsquo;m sure no one wants that on their conscience. I know it sucks not to be able to see your friends. It sucks not to live the life we took for granted. But the more responsible we are now &mdash; the more we sacrifice for everyone&rsquo;s well being now &mdash; the sooner things will go back to normal. <strong>So, please: no outside guests.</strong> No gatherings in the common areas unless you can ensure the suggested 3-6 ft distance. Please, do your part so that we all are safer.We all at Outpost are trying our best to make sure all of us, members and our team alike, stay healthy and stay safe. If there&rsquo;s something you believe we can do additionally, please do let us know, through your House Leader or by email.</p>\r\n<h3>Most importantly: Outpost is OUR home. Let&rsquo;s all do our part to protect and upkeep our home in this crisis.</h3>\r\n<p><strong><em>With love and wishes of health,</em></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><em>George</em></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><span class=\"red_text\">March 18, 2020</span></h2>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>We know you still need a home in times of uncertainty, so we&rsquo;ve lowered our prices and changed our cancellation policy.</h3>\r\n<p>Book by April 5, 2020, with move-in by Aug. 31, 2020, and you can cancel or reschedule your stay up until 7 days before your move-in date.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><span class=\"red_text\">March 16, 2020</span></h2>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>WHAT TO EXPECT OVER THE NEXT FEW WEEKS</h3>\r\n<p>We know this is a challenging time for everyone, and hope you\'re doing what you can to stay healthy and in good spirits.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>At midnight, a shelter in place order will go into effect in San Francisco in an effort to slow the spread of coronavirus, meaning that <strong>non-essential movement within the city will be banned until April 7</strong>. That means you\'ll have to stay inside your house as much as possible over the next three weeks, but there are some exceptions,&nbsp;<a class=\"green\" href=\"https://www.sfchronicle.com/local-politics/article/Bay-Area-must-shelter-in-place-Only-15135014.php\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">according to the San Francisco Chronicle</a>:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>You\'ll still be able to go shopping for items like food and household supplies.</li>\r\n<li>You\'ll still be able to order delivery from restaurants.</li>\r\n<li>You\'ll still be able to seek emergency medical care if you need it.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>You\'ll still be able to go outside for walks or exercise as long as you keep 6 feet away from anyone you don&rsquo;t already live with.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>We plan to continue servicing and cleaning our houses in San Francisco for the time being</strong>, but will be sure to let you know if anything changes. We\'ll have to adapt our schedules as needed, so we ask for your patience as we all work on getting through this together.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>In the meantime, as you prepare to stay at home, we remind you that the best defense against the coronavirus is to practice basic hygiene, <a class=\"green\" href=\"https://www.who.int/emergencies/diseases/novel-coronavirus-2019/advice-for-public\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">according to WHO</a>:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Stay at least 1&ndash;3 feet away from someone who is coughing or sneezing.</li>\r\n<li>Wash your hands with soap and water regularly.</li>\r\n<li>Avoid touching your eyes, nose and mouth.</li>\r\n<li>Cough or sneeze into a tissue or your elbow. If you use a tissue, wash your hands afterward.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>At Outpost, we\'re all about community, and that means doing our best to help one another feel safe and welcome in our houses. We know this will be a challenge, but we also know you\'re up to it. Please let us know if you have any questions.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><em>Sincerely,</em></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><em>The Outpost Club Team</em></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><span class=\"red_text\">March 13, 2020</span></h2>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>A CLEANING CHANGE, AND HOW TO FIND OUT IF CORONAVIRUS RUMORS ARE TRUE</h3>\r\n<p>As the situation with the novel coronavirus develops, we\'ve made one more change you should know about: <strong>We\'ve added additional disinfectant to our cleaning process</strong> to make sure your common areas are as sanitary as possible.</p>\r\n<p>We\'re continuing to monitor the advice of local, state and federal healthcare experts and government officials, and will continue to adjust our processes to do our part in making sure everyone at Outpost is safe. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>We need your help to keep our community healthy, though.&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>Throughout this outbreak, it\'s up to each of us to make sure we\'re acting responsibly, because it\'s not just our own health that\'s at stake; it\'s the health of everyone around us.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Here are a few simple tips for protecting yourself and your housemates healthy, <a class=\"green\" href=\"https://www.who.int/emergencies/diseases/novel-coronavirus-2019/advice-for-public\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">according to the World Health Organization</a>:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Wash your hands frequently (for 20 seconds with soap and water).</li>\r\n<li>Keep at least 3 feet (1 meter) between yourself and anyone who is coughing or sneezing.</li>\r\n<li>Avoid touching your eyes, nose and mouth.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>And here are a few more important guidelines:&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Wash your hands upon entering the house, before touching any surfaces.</li>\r\n<li>Take out the trash regularly.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Keep the sink free of dishes.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Wipe down surfaces with a household cleaner after using them.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>One last thing...</h3>\r\n<p>We know some rumors have been floating around that have caused some concern. We urge everyone to check reliable, verified sources before sharing information on the coronavirus and the government\'s response. Here are a few reliable sources you can count on for verified information:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>For everyone:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a class=\"green\" href=\"https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/about/index.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Centers for Disease Control and Prevention</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>New York City:&nbsp;</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a class=\"green\" href=\"http://nyc.gov/coronavirus\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">NYC Dept. of Health and Mental Hygiene</a></li>\r\n<li><a class=\"green\" href=\"https://twitter.com/nycmayor\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Mayor Bill de Blasio on Twitter</a></li>\r\n<li><a class=\"green\" href=\"https://twitter.com/nycgov\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">City of New York on&nbsp;Twitter</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em><strong>An important note for New York members:</strong> New York City has guaranteed healthcare for ALL residents experiencing COVID-19 symptoms, whether they have insurance and American citizenship or not. Additionally, if you\'re being harassed due to your race, nation of origin or other identities, call 311 to report discrimination or harassment to the NYC Commission on Human Rights.</em></p>\r\n<h4>Jersey City:</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a class=\"green\" href=\"http://jcnj.org/CORONAVIRUS\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Jersey City Dept. of Health</a></li>\r\n<li><a class=\"green\" href=\"https://twitter.com/JerseyCity\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Jersey City on Twitter</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4>San Francisco:</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a class=\"green\" href=\"https://www.sfdph.org/dph/alerts/coronavirus.asp\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">San Francisco Dept. of Public Health</a></li>\r\n<li><a class=\"green\" href=\"https://twitter.com/sfgov\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">City of San Francisco on Twitter</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Please let us know if you have any questions. As always, we\'ll let you know if anything changes moving forward.</strong></p>\r\n<p><em><strong>Sincerely,</strong></em></p>\r\n<p><em><strong>The Outpost Team</strong></em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><span class=\"red_text\">March 11, 2020</span></h2>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>A TEMPORARY CHANGE TO OUR GUEST POLICY</h3>\r\n<p>As a valued member of Outpost, your safety is our top concern. That\'s why, as we\'ve continued to watch developments surrounding COVID-19,<strong> we\'ve made the decision not to accept any new guest requests for the next 14 days.</strong> After 14 days, we\'ll re-evaluate based on the most recent updates about the coronavirus.</p>\r\n<p>As a reminder, according to the <strong><a class=\"green\" href=\"https://www.who.int/emergencies/diseases/novel-coronavirus-2019/advice-for-public\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">World Health Organization</a></strong>, most people who become infected experience mild illness and recover, but since some people experience more severe symptoms, you should take care of yourself and those around you with a few simple steps:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Wash your hands frequently (for 20 seconds with soap and water).</li>\r\n<li>Keep at least 3 feet (1 meter) between yourself and anyone who is coughing or sneezing.</li>\r\n<li>Avoid touching your eyes, nose and mouth.</li>\r\n<li>Please let us know if you have any questions. As always, we\'ll let you know if anything changes moving forward.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Outpost Team</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><span class=\"red_text\">March 3, 2020</span></h2>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>WHAT YOU SHOULD KNOW ABOUT CORONAVIRUS &mdash; AND HOW TO FIGHT IT</h3>\r\n<p>We know some of our members are concerned about the spread of coronavirus, or COVID-19, so we want to answer a few questions we\'ve gotten about it.</p>\r\n<h2>What is the coronavirus, anyway?</h2>\r\n<p>\"Coronavirus\" is actually the name for a large family of viruses known to cause respiratory infections including the common cold, <a class=\"green\" href=\"https://www.who.int/news-room/q-a-detail/q-a-coronaviruses\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">according to the World Health Organization</a>. The current outbreak that is most often referred to as \"coronavirus\" is actually a recently discovered coronavirus that causes a disease called COVID-19.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>How can I protect myself from coronavirus?&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<p>The simple answer here is to practice basic hygiene, <a class=\"green\" href=\"https://www.who.int/emergencies/diseases/novel-coronavirus-2019/advice-for-public\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">according to WHO</a>:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Stay at&nbsp;least&nbsp;1&ndash;3 feet away from someone who is coughing or sneezing.</li>\r\n<li>Wash your hands with soap and water regularly, and use hand sanitizer when hand-washing isn\'t an option.</li>\r\n<li>Avoid touching your eyes, nose and mouth.</li>\r\n<li>Stay home when you are sick.</li>\r\n<li>Cough or sneeze into a tissue or your elbow. If you use a tissue, wash your hands afterward.</li>\r\n<li>If you have fever, cough and difficulty breathing, go to the doctor early.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>At this time, NYC Mayor Bill de Blasio is urging&nbsp;New Yorkers to <strong>avoid crowded subway cars and wait for the next train if cars are full</strong>, <a class=\"green\" href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/08/nyregion/coronavirus-newyork.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">according to The New York Times</a>.</p>\r\n<h2>Do I need to get a&nbsp;face&nbsp;mask?&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<p>Unless you\'re actually sick, <a class=\"green\" href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/29/health/coronavirus-n95-face-masks.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><strong>no, it is not advised to buy a face mask</strong></a>. According to the Surgeon General and the medical community around the world, face masks aren\'t effective in preventing the general public from catching coronavirus. Additionally,&nbsp;with everyone out buying up all the face masks, we\'re actually putting medical professionals who actually need them at risk.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Is it safe to receive mail from China, Italy or other countries facing an outbreak?</h2>\r\n<p><a class=\"green\" href=\"https://www.who.int/emergencies/diseases/novel-coronavirus-2019/advice-for-public/myth-busters\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">According to WHO</a>, yes, it is safe. People receiving packages from China, Italy and other affected locations are not at risk of contracting the new coronavirus. Coronaviruses do not survive long on objects like letters and packages.</p>\r\n<h2>What will Outpost do?&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<p>Right now, the most important thing we can do is urge our members to follow the advice in this email to keep coronavirus at bay. We encourage you to wash your hands as soon as you get home every day, and to practice good hygiene out of respect for your housemates.</p>\r\n<p>Currently, the only change we\'re making to our operations is scaling back plans for larger community events, for our members\' peace of mind. We will also adjust things in compliance with any requirements put in place by New York City, the state of New York or the federal government. We\'re closely monitoring reports from the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) and the World Health Organization (WHO) and will adjust our processes if needed &mdash; and we\'ll keep you informed every step of the way.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Please let us know if you have any questions.</p>\r\n<p><em><strong>The Outpost Team</strong></em></p>\r\n<hr />', 9, '', 'covid-19-outpost-club-2.jpg', '', '', 109, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'COVID-19', 0, 0, 'a:0:{}', '', '', '', '', 0, '0.00000000', '0.00000000', 0, '', NULL),
