(292, 288, NULL, 'the-journal-square-house', '', 'The Journal Square House', 'The Journal Square House, Jersey City | Outpost Club', '', 'The Journal Square House', '<p>Journal Square, Jersey City</p>\r\n<p>Shared&nbsp;rooms from $630| Private rooms from $990</p>', '<h1 class=\"h1\">Journal Square House</h1>\r\n<h4>This magnificent home in perfect condition is available for you to rent</h4>', '<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">The Scoop</h6>\r\n<p>Our Journal Square House is located in the historic Journal Square area of Jersey City, New Jersey. The Journal Square House is made up of three brick row houses, all of which share a common backyard, and is a short walk from public transportation and multiple historic sites of interest.</p>\r\n<p>The Journal Square House consists of six apartments spread across three houses, with two floors each. With easy access to public transportation, it&rsquo;s the perfect base from which to commute to Lower and Midtown Manhattan. Members enjoy spacious common areas with plenty of entertainment options, as well as a large backyard with plenty of room to lounge or host a barbecue.</p>\r\n<p>This newly renovated space features hardwood floors, updated appliances and exposed brick. The kitchen and common areas are spacious and welcoming, with skylights in some apartments and entertainment like air hockey and ping pong on the lower levels. The best part? It&rsquo;s all furnished with everything you&rsquo;ll need for work and play, whether you&rsquo;re meal prepping or hosting a movie night.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">Location</h6>\r\n<p>This coliving house is located in the revitalized Journal Square neighborhood, filled with historic buildings, newer high rises and plenty of dining options. It&rsquo;s only a short commute into New York City on public transportation and is an easy commute to downtown Jersey City and Hoboken.</p>\r\n<p>The house is a 10-minute walk from the Journal Square Transportation Center Path Plaza, where you can catch the Journal Square-33rd Street train into Midtown Manhattan, or the Newark-World Trade Center train into Lower Manhattan. Multiple bus lines also serve the neighborhood.</p>\r\n<p><strong>You can be in the Financial District in less than 30 minutes and to Times Square, Rockefeller Plaza or Downtown Brooklyn in 50 minutes.</strong></p>\r\n</div>', 5, '', 'the-journal-square-house-main.jpg', 'the-journal-square-house-background.jpg', '', 480, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Journal Square House', 0, 0, 'a:8:{i:0;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:20:\"Throughout the house\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:729:\"<p>{throughout}</p>\r\n<table class=\"table v2\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<th>12+ Months</th>\r\n<th>4-11 Months</th>\r\n<th>1-3 Months</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Executive + Bath)</th>\r\n<td>$1230</td>\r\n<td>$1290</td>\r\n<td>$1380</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private</th>\r\n<td>$990</td>\r\n<td>$1050</td>\r\n<td>$1140</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>2-people shared room</th>\r\n<td>$630</td>\r\n<td>$690</td>\r\n<td>$780</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"5\"><em>**The prices shown indicate <strong>the prices valid for move-in between November<em><strong>&nbsp;11, 2020, and March 31, 2021</strong></em></strong>.</em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div class=\"center\"><a class=\"button2 red\" href=\"join-us\" target=\"_blank\">Apply for free</a></div>\";}i:1;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:12:\"The Bedrooms\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:579:\"<p>Your room will be move-in ready, just like the rest of the house; there&rsquo;s no need to even bring a pillow. There are six apartments in the Journal Square House, each of which have five to six bedrooms. Most of the bedrooms at the Journal Square House are private, although there are limited shared-room options available.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Amenities</strong>: memory-foam mattresses (twin-sized for shared rooms; full-sized for single rooms), memory-foam pillows, extension cords to your bedside, shelving, hooks and closet/organization tools.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:20:{i:0;s:39:\"the-journal-square-house-bedroom-28.jpg\";i:1;s:39:\"the-journal-square-house-bedroom-26.jpg\";i:2;s:39:\"the-journal-square-house-bedroom-25.jpg\";i:3;s:39:\"the-journal-square-house-bedroom-24.jpg\";i:4;s:39:\"the-journal-square-house-bedroom-23.jpg\";i:5;s:39:\"the-journal-square-house-bedroom-22.jpg\";i:6;s:39:\"the-journal-square-house-bedroom-21.jpg\";i:7;s:39:\"the-journal-square-house-bedroom-17.jpg\";i:8;s:39:\"the-journal-square-house-bedroom-16.jpg\";i:9;s:39:\"the-journal-square-house-bedroom-15.jpg\";i:10;s:39:\"the-journal-square-house-bedroom-14.jpg\";i:11;s:39:\"the-journal-square-house-bedroom-13.jpg\";i:12;s:39:\"the-journal-square-house-bedroom-12.jpg\";i:13;s:39:\"the-journal-square-house-bedroom-10.jpg\";i:14;s:38:\"the-journal-square-house-bedroom-8.jpg\";i:15;s:38:\"the-journal-square-house-bedroom-7.jpg\";i:16;s:38:\"the-journal-square-house-bedroom-5.jpg\";i:17;s:38:\"the-journal-square-house-bedroom-4.jpg\";i:18;s:38:\"the-journal-square-house-bedroom-2.jpg\";i:19;s:38:\"the-journal-square-house-bedroom-1.jpg\";}}i:2;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:24:\"The kitchens/dining room\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:648:\"<p>The kitchen in each apartment features updated appliances, with plenty of counter space for cooking on your own or with a group. Each kitchen includes a dining table that can be used for eating, socializing or co-working, and includes a breakfast bar. The kitchen is the gathering place for potluck dinners, solo meals and chats in the evening over a glass of wine.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Amenities include a gas stove, stainless-steel fridge, microwave, large sinks, a coffee maker, plenty of cabinets, cookware, tableware, cutting boards and anything else you would need in a kitchen.</li>\r\n<li>Security: 24/7 security in all common areas.</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:6:{i:0;s:38:\"the-journal-square-house-kitchen-3.jpg\";i:1;s:38:\"the-journal-square-house-kitchen-2.jpg\";i:2;s:36:\"the-journal-square-house-kitchen.jpg\";i:3;s:38:\"the-journal-square-house-kitchen-7.jpg\";i:4;s:38:\"the-journal-square-house-kitchen-4.jpg\";i:5;s:37:\"the-journal-square-house-kitche-6.jpg\";}}i:3;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:20:\"The co-working space\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:274:\"<p>The individual kitchens in every apartment serve as the principal co-working area for the Journal Square House. These open-plan rooms feature dining tables with ample room for co-working, and the downstairs living rooms also include plenty of room to get things done.</p>\";s:6:\"images\";a:5:{i:0;s:42:\"the-journal-square-house-living-room-1.jpg\";i:1;s:42:\"the-journal-square-house-living-room-5.jpg\";i:2;s:42:\"the-journal-square-house-living-room-4.jpg\";i:3;s:42:\"the-journal-square-house-living-room-3.jpg\";i:4;s:42:\"the-journal-square-house-living-room-2.jpg\";}}i:4;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:13:\"The bathrooms\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:411:\"<p>Each unit in the Journal Square House includes two full bathrooms, so you&rsquo;ll never have to wait.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Also included</strong>: toilet paper small garbage bags, which will never run out!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>LAUNDRY ROOM</p>\r\n<p>The Journal Square House includes in-unit washers and dryers for your convenience.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Security: 24/7 security in all common areas.</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:5:{i:0;s:39:\"the-journal-square-house-bathroom-7.jpg\";i:1;s:39:\"the-journal-square-house-bathroom-5.jpg\";i:2;s:39:\"the-journal-square-house-bathroom-4.jpg\";i:3;s:39:\"the-journal-square-house-bathroom-3.jpg\";i:4;s:39:\"the-journal-square-house-bathroom-1.jpg\";}}i:5;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:12:\"The backyard\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:269:\"<p>The Journal Square House features a large backyard that spans the width and is accessible from all three houses. With ample seating and multiple grills, its the perfect spot in which to get to know your housemates or have get-togethers while it&rsquo;s warm out.</p>\";s:6:\"images\";a:1:{i:0;s:37:\"the-journal-square-house-backyard.jpg\";}}i:6;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:19:\"Additional benefits\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:178:\"<p><strong>We screen all candidates before approving applications so that there are no worries about moving into a new place with new people &mdash; only excitement!</strong></p>\";}i:7;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:6:\"Prices\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:1131:\"<p>We have flexible month-to-month commitment options. We do not require extensive documents from you, guarantors or large deposits. A longer commitment on your side helps us to provide you with better prices.</p>\r\n<table class=\"table v2\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<th>12+ Months</th>\r\n<th>4-11 Months</th>\r\n<th>1-3 Months</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Executive + Bath)</th>\r\n<td>$1230</td>\r\n<td>$1290</td>\r\n<td>$1380</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private</th>\r\n<td>$990</td>\r\n<td>$1050</td>\r\n<td>$1140</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>2-people shared room</th>\r\n<td>$630</td>\r\n<td>$690</td>\r\n<td>$790</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"5\"><em>**The prices shown indicate <strong>the prices valid for move-in between November<em><strong>&nbsp;11, 2020, and March 31, 2021</strong></em></strong>.</em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div class=\"center\"><a class=\"button2 red\" href=\"join-us\" target=\"_blank\">Apply for free</a></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Availability: Year-round / Minimum stay of 1 month / Month-to-month payment options available / Minimum age 18 / 30-day cancellation notice</strong></p>\";}}', '', '', '', '', 0, '40.73168000', '-74.07166000', 0, '', NULL);
