(293, 253, 307, 'the-lafayette-house', '', 'The Lafayette House', 'The Lafayette House (NY 11216) | Outpost Club', 'We worked with interior designers to make The Lafayette House comfortable in every room. ✓ Fully furnished ✓ Security ✓ Gas ✓ Electricity ✓ Water ✓ Wi-Fi ✓ Cleaning and maintenance', 'The Lafayette House | Outpost Club', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Bedford-Stuyvesant</span>, Brooklyn</p>\r\n<p>Private rooms from $1420</p>', '<h1 class=\"h1 center\">The Lafayette House</h1>\r\n<h4>A SPACIOUS HOME IN A LIVELY NEIGHBORHOOD</h4>', '<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">The Scoop</h6>\r\n<p>The Lafayette House is located in Bed-Stuy, a charming and central Brooklyn neighborhood with plenty of restaurants, cozy bars and hip boutiques. You can explore surrounding neighborhoods like Clinton Hill and Williamsburg, or hop on the subway and be in Manhattan in 30 minutes. This brand new building is home to spacious apartments with modern amenities.</p>\r\n<p>The house is a brand new building with updated appliances, hardwood floors, large windows and in-unit washer/dryers. The Lafayette House has fifteen units altogether, a spacious shared lounge and a fitness center. All of the common areas are massive in comparison to your average New York City apartment.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">Location</h6>\r\n<p>The closest subway station is Bedford-Nostrand, served by the G train and just a 5-minute walk away. Multiple bus lines also serve the neighborhood. You can reach the Lower East Side in 30 minutes and Midtown Manhattan in 45 minutes, or easily explore Downtown Brooklyn in 15 minutes.</p>\r\n<p>The neighborhood features a small park, trendy coffee shops and eclectic cuisine ranging from Cuban to Japanese.</p>\r\n</div>', 5, '', 'SC2029_OMD_Comm1_205-2.jpg', '1.jpg', '', 254, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'The Lafayette House', 0, 0, 'a:10:{i:0;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:20:\"Throughout the house\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:901:\"<p>{throughout}</p>\r\n<table class=\"table v2\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<th>12+ Months</th>\r\n<th>5-11 Months</th>\r\n<th>1-4 Months</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Executive Extra Large)</th>\r\n<td>$1850</td>\r\n<td>$1930</td>\r\n<td>$2530</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Executive + Bath)</th>\r\n<td>$1550</td>\r\n<td>$1630</td>\r\n<td>$2230</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Large room with desk)</th>\r\n<td>$1520</td>\r\n<td>$1600</td>\r\n<td>$2200</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Standard+)</th>\r\n<td>$1480</td>\r\n<td>$1560</td>\r\n<td>$2160</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Standard)</th>\r\n<td>$1420</td>\r\n<td>$1500</td>\r\n<td>$2100</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"5\">\r\n<p>*Prices above do not include $149/month/person utilities allowance fee</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div class=\"center\"><a class=\"button2 red\" href=\"online-questionnaire\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Check Availability</a></div>\";}i:1;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:12:\"The Bedrooms\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:298:\"<p>All of the bedrooms in the Lafayette House are private and feature full-sized beds, blackout shades and closets. Bedding is available for an additional fee.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Amenities:</strong> full-size memory-foam mattresses, shelving, hooks and closets/organizational tools.</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:5:{i:0;s:12:\"DSC02230.jpg\";i:1;s:12:\"DSC02202.jpg\";i:2;s:12:\"DSC02233.jpg\";i:3;s:12:\"DSC02184.jpg\";i:4;s:12:\"DSC02199.jpg\";}}i:2;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:24:\"The kitchens/dining room\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:505:\"<p>In these apartments, the kitchen and dining room are the first rooms you enter. These spaces are used for cooking up dinner and relaxing in the evening over a glass of wine.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Amenities</strong> include electric stoves, stainless-steel fridges, microwaves, large sinks, coffee makers, blenders, plenty of cabinets, cookware, tableware, cutting boards and anything else you would need in a kitchen.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Security</strong>: 24/7 security in all common areas.</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:7:{i:0;s:33:\"the-lafayette-house-kitchen-4.jpg\";i:1;s:33:\"the-lafayette-house-kitchen-3.jpg\";i:2;s:33:\"the-lafayette-house-kitchen-1.jpg\";i:3;s:33:\"the-lafayette-house-kitchen-2.jpg\";i:4;s:33:\"the-lafayette-house-kitchen-6.jpg\";i:5;s:33:\"the-lafayette-house-kitchen-7.jpg\";i:6;s:33:\"the-lafayette-house-kitchen-5.jpg\";}}i:3;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:19:\"The (Co)Living Room\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:553:\"<p>The common living room and workspace is located in the basement of the Lafayette House. This is where members can go to relax, work and hang out! The space is equipped with everything you need, from huge couches to sprawling tables that can fit up to eight people simultaneously.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Google Chromecast</li>\r\n<li><strong>Security</strong>: 24/7 security in all common areas.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"https://my.matterport.com/show/?m=D95VPZpEefK\" width=\"100%\" height=\"500\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\";s:6:\"images\";a:5:{i:0;s:38:\"the-lafayette-house-coliving-area4.jpg\";i:1;s:38:\"the-lafayette-house-coliving-area6.jpg\";i:2;s:38:\"the-lafayette-house-coliving-area1.jpg\";i:3;s:38:\"the-lafayette-house-coliving-area3.jpg\";i:4;s:38:\"the-lafayette-house-coliving-area5.jpg\";}}i:4;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:13:\"The bathrooms\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:514:\"<p>Every unit in the Lafayette House is equipped with enough shared bathrooms so you can be sure you&rsquo;ll never have to wait. Some bedrooms have private bathrooms, depending on availability and your price range.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Also included</strong>: toilet paper, hand soap and small garbage bags, which will never be empty!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p class=\"h5\">Laundry room</p>\r\n<p>Each apartment also has an in-unit washer and dryer, so you can do all your laundry in the comfort of your own home.</p>\";s:6:\"images\";a:4:{i:0;s:34:\"the-lafayette-house-bathroom-1.jpg\";i:1;s:34:\"the-lafayette-house-bathroom-2.jpg\";i:2;s:12:\"DSC02193.jpg\";i:3;s:12:\"DSC02181.jpg\";}}i:8;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:12:\"Fitness Area\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:337:\"<p>Our Lafayette House even has a fitness area! This is equipped with the basics you need to work out, giving you the opportunity to skip a gym membership.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Amenities</strong>: Soft matting, yoga mats, yoga balls and a cycling machine.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Security</strong>: 24/7 security in common areas.</li>\r\n</ul>\";}i:9;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:8:\"Backyard\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:159:\"<p>Yes, we even have a back yard! This cozy backyard area has plenty of chairs so can work, read, or relax outside in the warmer months and catch some sun.</p>\";}i:10;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:18:\"PERKS AND BENEFITS\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:640:\"<div class=\"fx ch3 w perc_advantages\">\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Fast, reliable WiFi</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Regular professional cleaning</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Backyard access</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">In-unit laundry</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Keyless entry</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Community lounge</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Community events</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Dedicated community manager</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Updated appliances</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Dedicated maintenance team</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\";}i:11;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:6:\"Prices\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:1059:\"<table class=\"table v2\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<th>12+ Months</th>\r\n<th>5-11 Months</th>\r\n<th>1-4 Months</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Executive Extra Large)</th>\r\n<td>$1850</td>\r\n<td>$1930</td>\r\n<td>$2530</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Executive + Bath)</th>\r\n<td>$1550</td>\r\n<td>$1630</td>\r\n<td>$2230</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Large room with desk)</th>\r\n<td>$1520</td>\r\n<td>$1600</td>\r\n<td>$2200</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Standard+)</th>\r\n<td>$1480</td>\r\n<td>$1560</td>\r\n<td>$2160</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Standard)</th>\r\n<td>$1420</td>\r\n<td>$1500</td>\r\n<td>$2100</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"5\">\r\n<p>*Prices above do not include $149/month/person utilities allowance fee</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div class=\"center\"><a class=\"button2 red\" href=\"online-questionnaire\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Check Availability</a></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Availability: Year-round / Minimum stay of 1 month / Month-to-month payment options available / Minimum age 18</strong></p>\";}i:12;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:31:\"Welcome to Bed-Stuy, Brooklyn. \";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:640:\"<div>\r\n<p>Walk off the train and into this historic Brooklyn neighborhood that feels like home with its quaint, brownstone-lined streets and vibrant culture. Immerse yourself in the community and you&rsquo;ll find unique locally owned shops, neighbors who are always up for a good conversation, and a rich history worth honoring. The neighborhood features the lively Herbert Von King park, trendy coffee shops like Brooklyn Blend and eclectic cuisine ranging from Caribbean to Japanese. You can explore surrounding neighborhoods like Clinton Hill and Williamsburg by foot, or hop on the subway and be in Manhattan in 30 minutes.</p>\r\n</div>\";s:6:\"images\";a:4:{i:0;s:58:\"aee22cb703e77c3c63e13bf273a93b2f-rimg-w720-h478-gmir_2.jpg\";i:1;s:27:\"bed-stuy_corcoran_08_10.jpg\";i:2;s:34:\"bed-stuy-brooklyn-new-york-4_2.jpg\";i:3;s:60:\"Fulton-street-brooklyn-bedford-stuyvesant-nyc-new-york_2.jpg\";}}}', '', '', 'a:3:{i:0;s:3:\"330\";i:1;s:3:\"248\";i:2;s:3:\"159\";}', '<div class=\"txt\">\r\n<h1 class=\"\">The Lafayette House Move-In Guide</h1>\r\n<h2><em><strong>340 Clifton Pl, Brooklyn NY 11216</strong></em></h2>\r\n<hr class=\"hr\" />\r\n<h3><strong>The Community</strong></h3>\r\n<p>Welcome to Outpost! We&rsquo;re glad you&rsquo;re here. Coliving isn&rsquo;t just about having roommates or sharing a kitchen &mdash; it&rsquo;s about recognizing that we can do more, accomplish more and be more when we work together.</p>\r\n<p>We communicate with each other via our house&rsquo;s Messenger group, which your House Leader will add you upon arrival. We also offer an Outpost Slack channel where you can find other members with similar interests and meet new people in your area. We send out relevant updates and information via email, so keep an eye out!</p>\r\n<p>Your <strong>Member Portal</strong> is where you can RSVP for community events, submit maintenance and cleaning requests and access important documents. <a class=\"green\" href=\"../user/login\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Find it here</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Your <strong>House Leader</strong> will be your main point of contact with Outpost. Here&rsquo;s what they can help you with:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Info about community activities</li>\r\n<li>Restocking supplies</li>\r\n<li>Questions about Outpost</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>We have a lot of activities to help you get involved with our community and get to know the city. Pay attention to your Member Portal and your house&rsquo;s Messenger group to keep up with what&rsquo;s going on, or just ask your House Leader!</p>\r\n<h3><strong>The Logistics</strong></h3>\r\n<h3>Moving In</h3>\r\n<p>The outside code to your house is <strong>0340#</strong>. You&rsquo;ll use the Kastle Resident app to access your unit. Download the app and sign up for an account, and your House Leader will give you access upon arrival.</p>\r\n<p>You&rsquo;ll also receive a key card to access both the house and your individual unit in the case you don&rsquo;t have your phone. Your House Leader will provide you this key upon arrival &mdash; please keep it in a safe and secure location!</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>When you move in, your House Leader will give you a tour of the house and talk to you a bit about the Outpost community.</p>\r\n<p>They&rsquo;ll also:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Take a photo of your ID (for our records and according to state law)</li>\r\n<li>Add you to your Messenger group</li>\r\n<li>Assign you cupboard and refrigerator space, according to your room number.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The WiFi name is Outpost (or something similar) and the password is <strong>befreenyc</strong>.</p>\r\n<h3>Living at Outpost</h3>\r\n<p>You&rsquo;ll find helpful information linked above in our Guide to Responsible Coliving, but there are a few more things you should know:</p>\r\n<p><strong>Recycling is required</strong>, and New York City has strict guidelines. Watch the video below to see what you should recycle:</p>\r\n<iframe style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/EUyVELb5PzY\" width=\"70%\" height=\"400\"></iframe><br /><br />\r\n<p><strong>Cleanliness is also required.</strong> That&rsquo;s especially true of common areas, including shared rooms. Here are some easy ways to think about cleanliness at Outpost:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Leave rooms in the condition in which you found them</li>\r\n<li>Clean up after yourself</li>\r\n<li>Don&rsquo;t leave your belongings in the common area unless you&rsquo;re returning immediately</li>\r\n<li>Pay attention to the signs around the house: They&rsquo;re there to help our community run smoothly!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Outpost is not responsible for lost or damaged mail or packages.</strong> Your House Leader will check the mail regularly. Make sure to put your full address, including your outside door code, in the delivery field when you order something. You may find your package left inside the main door, concealed outside, with a roommate who picked it up for you or returned to a distribution center for a later delivery. It&rsquo;s your responsibility to track your packages and make sure you&rsquo;re home to receive them when necessary.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 2, '40.68896080', '-73.95070581', 490, '', '2022-08-22 13:21:51'),
(294, 0, NULL, 'the-metropolitan-house-3d-tour', '', 'The Metropolitan House 3D Tour', 'The Metropolitan House 3D Tour', '', 'The Metropolitan House 3D Tour', '', '', '<h1>The Metropolitan House 3D Tour</h1>\r\n<p><iframe style=\"margin-top: 1em;\" src=\"https://my.matterport.com/show/?m=1ZWCRUTCmDQ\" width=\"100%\" height=\"500\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"> </iframe></p>', 9, '', '', '', '', 356, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Metropolitan House 3D Tour', 0, 0, 'a:0:{}', '', '', '', '', 0, '0.00000000', '0.00000000', 0, '', NULL),
(297, 253, NULL, 'the-metropolitan-house', '', 'The Metropolitan House', 'The Metropolitan House | Outpost Club', '', 'The Metropolitan House', '<p>Williamsburg, Brooklyn</p>\r\n<p>Private rooms from $1730</p>', '', '<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">THE SCOOP</h6>\r\n<p>The Metropolitan House is located on the border of the popular neighborhoods of Williamsburg and East Williamsburg, just a stone&rsquo;s throw from bustling Metropolitan Avenue.</p>\r\n<p>The Metropolitan House is made up of just four bedrooms in a single-unit apartment, located on the first floor of a classic Brooklyn walk-up. Members enjoy private bedrooms along with a spacious living room and kitchen, as well as ample room for socializing and co-working.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">LOCATION</h6>\r\n<p>This coliving house is ideally located on the border of Williamsburg and East Williamsburg, in the heart of the creative and entertainment scenes of the two neighborhoods. The house is just a few minutes&rsquo; walk from Metropolitan Avenue, known as a hub of restaurants, cafes and bars, making it the perfect place for weekends and evenings, while still being within close reach of downtown Manhattan.</p>\r\n<p><strong>The nearest subway station is Grand St. on the L train, just a 2-minute walk away, and the G train is just a 7-minute walk from the house at Nassau Avenue. You can be on the Lower East Side in just 11 minutes, Times Square in 26 minutes and Wall Street in 27 minutes, plus multiple bus lines serve the neighborhood.</strong></p>\r\n<p>The neighborhood itself is both vibrant and leafy, with Cooper Park just a 7-minute walk and the famous McCarren Park just a 23-minute walk.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">THE SPACE</h6>\r\n<p>This recently renovated space features hardwood floors and updated appliances throughout. The kitchen and common areas are spacious compared to the average New York City apartment, with a&nbsp;a large living area and kitchen, both furnished with everything you&rsquo;ll need for work and play.</p>\r\n<p><strong>This space is move-in ready; all you have to do is show up with your suitcase.</strong></p>\r\n</div>', 5, '', 'metropolitan-house-main.jpg', 'metropolitan-house-background.jpg', '', 427, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Metropolitan House', 0, 0, 'a:7:{i:0;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:20:\"Throughout the house\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:1541:\"<p>{throughout}</p>\r\n<table class=\"table v2\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<th class=\"title\">\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><span class=\"gold\">Gold</span> Membership</p>\r\n<p class=\"price\">$690 One-Time Fee</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</th>\r\n<th colspan=\"2\">\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><span class=\"silver\">Silver</span> Membership</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"bronze\">Bronze</span> Membership</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p class=\"price\">$79 One-Time Fee</p>\r\n<p class=\"price\">No Fee*</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"2\"><em>*Bronze members must move in on <strong>the first day</strong> of the month</em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<th>1-12 Months</th>\r\n<th>4+ Months</th>\r\n<th>1-3 Months</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private</th>\r\n<td>$1730</td>\r\n<td>$1890</td>\r\n<td>$2050</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>2-people shared</th>\r\n<td>$950</td>\r\n<td>$1100</td>\r\n<td>$1200</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"5\">See the benefits of Bronze, Silver and Gold Membership <a class=\"red\" href=\"../memberships\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">here</a>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>**The prices shown indicate <strong>the prices valid for move-in between Dec. 15, 2019, and <em><strong>April 30</strong></em>, 2020</strong>. The exact price is indicated in your membership agreement and may vary depending on the length of commitment, your membership level and the size of your group, if applicable.</em></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div class=\"center\"><a class=\"button2\" href=\"join-us\">I\'m interested</a></div>\";}i:1;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:12:\"The bedrooms\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:739:\"<p>Your room will be move-in ready, just like the rest of the house; there&rsquo;s no need to even bring a pillow. There are four bedrooms to choose from in the Metropolitan House, spread over a single first-floor unit and linked by a common living and dining area. Each bedroom features large windows overlooking the neighborhood with plenty of light, as well as a personal closet. This house consists of private rooms only, so you can relax away from the busy rush of city life.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Amenities: memory-foam mattresses, pillows, extension cords to your bedside, shelving, hooks, bed linens, towels and closets/organizational tools.</li>\r\n<li>Services: Bed linens and towels will be available for you when you arrive.</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:9:{i:0;s:32:\"metropolitan-house-bedroom-9.jpg\";i:1;s:32:\"metropolitan-house-bedroom-8.jpg\";i:2;s:32:\"metropolitan-house-bedroom-7.jpg\";i:3;s:32:\"metropolitan-house-bedroom-6.jpg\";i:4;s:32:\"metropolitan-house-bedroom-5.jpg\";i:5;s:32:\"metropolitan-house-bedroom-4.jpg\";i:6;s:32:\"metropolitan-house-bedroom-3.jpg\";i:7;s:32:\"metropolitan-house-bedroom-2.jpg\";i:8;s:32:\"metropolitan-house-bedroom-1.jpg\";}}i:2;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:24:\"The kitchens/dining room\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:676:\"<p>The large kitchen in the Metropolitan House features updated appliances with counter space for cooking on your own or with a group. The kitchen includes a large dining table that can be used for eating, socializing or co-working, as well as an adjacent living area for relaxing after work. The kitchen is the gathering place for potluck dinners, solo meals and chats in the evening over a glass of wine.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Amenities include a gas stove, large fridge, microwave, large sinks, a coffee maker, plenty of cabinets, cookware, tableware, cutting boards and anything else you would need in a kitchen.</li>\r\n<li>Security: 24/7 security in all common areas.</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:2:{i:0;s:32:\"metropolitan-house-kitchen-2.jpg\";i:1;s:32:\"metropolitan-house-kitchen-1.jpg\";}}i:3;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:20:\"The co-working space\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:191:\"<p>The spacious kitchen in the Metropolitan House serves as the principal co-working area for this house. This open-plan room features a large dining table with ample room for co-working.</p>\";}i:4;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:13:\"The bathrooms\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:330:\"<p>We provide many bathroom essentials, as well. There are two bathrooms for just four bedrooms in the Metropolitan House, so you&rsquo;ll never have to wait.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Also included: toilet paper and small garbage bags, which will never run out! We also provide hair dryers, so there\'s no need to bring your own.</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:2:{i:0;s:33:\"metropolitan-house-bathroom-2.jpg\";i:1;s:33:\"metropolitan-house-bathroom-1.jpg\";}}i:5;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:19:\"Additional benefits\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:417:\"<p>Your membership gives you the opportunity to move between all our houses from month to month, allowing you to see what it&rsquo;s like to live in different neighborhoods. Members are welcome to enjoy the parties and events at any of our locations.</p>\r\n<p>We screen all candidates before approving applications so that there are no worries about moving into a new place with new people &mdash; only excitement!</p>\";}i:6;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:6:\"Prices\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:1978:\"<p>We have flexible month-to-month commitment options. We do not require extensive documents from you, guarantors or large deposits. A longer commitment on your side helps