(298, 253, 305, 'the-united-nations-house', '', 'The United Nations House', 'Room Rentals Near United Nations House | Outpost Club', '', 'The United Nations House', '<p>Manhattan, New York</p>\r\n<p>Private rooms from $1620</p>', '<h1 class=\"h1\">The United Nations House</h1>\r\n<h4>This conveniently located&nbsp;home in great condition is available for you to rent</h4>', '<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">The Scoop</h6>\r\n<p>The United Nations House is located on the popular Upper East Side, within the leafy area of Lenox Hill and within walking distance of the United Nations. This house is in the heart of Manhattan, surrounded by coffee shops and restaurants and just 20 minutes from Times Square, while still feeling serene, thanks to its close proximity to the East River and several parks.</p>\r\n<p>The United Nations House is one of our smallest in terms of members, with only three bedrooms, offering a sense of tranquility in the center of busy Manhattan. The house itself is a single unit situated on the third floor of a classic Manhattan walkup, with ample space compared with your average New York City apartment, all recently renovated throughout.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>This newly renovated space features hardwood floors, updated appliances and natural light throughout, all furnished with everything you&rsquo;ll need for work and play.</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">Location</h6>\r\n<p>This coliving space is located in the Lenox Hill area of the Upper East Side, a popular neighborhood with ideal transit links to downtown Manhattan. The house is just a 4-minute walk from the Q/R or M trains at 72nd Street Station, and the neighborhood itself is filled with coffee shops, movie theaters and parks. From the UN House, you can be in Times Square in less than 15 minutes and Wall Street in half an hour. The house is also just a short 5-minute walk from The Rockefeller University and a 7-minute walk from Hunter College.</p>\r\n<p>St. Catherine&rsquo;s Park is just a 1-minute walk away, while Central Park is a short 15-minute walk. The neighborhood is also within a short walk to renowned museums, such as The Metropolitan Museum of Art and The Frick and&nbsp;the famed 5th Avenue shopping district, as well as being just two blocks from the East River.</p>\r\n</div>', 5, '', 'DSC00139.jpg', 'DSC00164.jpg', '', 388, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The United Nations House', 0, 0, 'a:7:{i:0;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:20:\"Throughout the house\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:921:\"<p>{throughout}</p>\r\n<table class=\"table v2\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<th>12+ Months</th>\r\n<th>4-11 Months</th>\r\n<th>1-3 Months</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Large room with desk)</th>\r\n<td>$1620</td>\r\n<td>$1700</td>\r\n<td>$2300</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Standard)</th>\r\n<td>$1470</td>\r\n<td>$1550</td>\r\n<td>$2150</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Economy)</th>\r\n<td>$1270</td>\r\n<td>$1350</td>\r\n<td>$1950</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"5\">\r\n<p>*Prices above do not include $75/month/person utilities allowance fee</p>\r\n<p>**The prices shown indicate <strong>the prices valid for move-in between August 1, 2021, and April 30, 2022.<br /> </strong>If you are applying with a move-in date after April 30, 2022, we will send you applicable pricing.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div class=\"center\"><a class=\"button2 red\" href=\"join-us-manhattan\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Apply for free</a></div>\";}i:1;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:12:\"The Bedrooms\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:503:\"<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">There are three bedrooms to choose from in the United Nations House, all of which are private and share a communal living area and kitchen. Each bedroom features large windows, as well as plenty of storage space. Bedding is available for an additional fee.</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Amenities</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><s