(397, 253, 319, 'the-cypress-house', '', 'The Cypress House', 'The Cypress House', 'We worked with interior designers to make The Cypress House comfortable in every room. ✓ Fully furnished ✓ Security ✓ Gas ✓ Electricity ✓ Water ✓ Wi-Fi ✓ Cleaning and maintenance', 'The Cypress House', '<p>Ridgewood, Queens</p>\r\n<p>Private rooms from $1410</p>', '<h1 class=\"h1 center\">The Cypress House</h1>\r\n<h4>A SPACIOUS HOME IN A LIVELY NEIGHBORHOOD</h4>', '<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">The scoop&nbsp;</h6>\r\n<p>The Cypress House is located in Ridgewood, a relaxed Queens neighborhood that has plenty of restaurants, coffee shops and shopping nearby. You can explore surrounding neighborhoods like Bushwick and East Williamsburg, or simply hop on the subway and be in Lower Manhattan in 30 minutes. This renovated building is home to spacious apartments with modern amenities.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">Location</h6>\r\n<p>This space is in the homey neighborhood of Ridgewood bordering Brooklyn, known for its slower pace and historic streets. The Cypress House is a 8-minute walk from the Seneca Ave. subway station, which is served by the M train, and a 6-minute walk from the Halsey St. station, served by the L train. You can easily access all New York City has to offer.</p>\r\n<p>The neighborhood features multiple gyms, a local brewery and eclectic cuisine ranging from Nepalese to Venezuelan eats.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">The space</h6>\r\n<p>The house is a brand-new building with updated appliances, hardwood floors, large windows, paid laundry facilities and skylights. The Cypress House has two units altogether, each with three bedrooms, three bathrooms and a spacious living area as you enter the apartment. All of the common areas are massive in comparison to your average New York City apartment.</p>\r\n<p><strong>This space is move-in ready; all you have to do is show up.</strong></p>\r\n</div>', 5, '', 'cypres-main.jpg', 'cypres-main.jpg', '', 352, 