(398, 253, 318, 'the-lewis-house', '', 'The Lewis House ', 'The Lewis House (NY 11221) | Outpost Club', 'We worked with interior designers to make The Lewis House comfortable in every room. ✓ Fully furnished ✓ Security ✓ Gas ✓ Electricity ✓ Water ✓ Wi-Fi ✓ Cleaning and maintenance', 'The Lewis House | Outpost Club', '<p>Bedford-Stuyvesant, Brooklyn</p>\r\n<p>Private rooms from $1390</p>', '<h1 class=\"h1 center\">The Lewis House</h1>\r\n<h4>A SPACIOUS HOME IN A LIVELY NEIGHBORHOOD</h4>', '<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">The scoop&nbsp;</h6>\r\n<p>The Lewis House is located in Stuyvesant Heights, a historic Brooklyn neighborhood that has classic city charm. The brownstone-lined streets are home to plenty of restaurants, coffee shops and boutiques, making it the perfect place to explore. You can visit surrounding neighborhoods like Crown Heights and Bushwick, or hop on the subway and be in Manhattan in 30 minutes. This brand new building is home to spacious apartments with modern amenities.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">Location</h6>\r\n<p>The Myrtle Av station is a 15-minute walk away and is served by the both the M and J train, which run frequently into Manhattan. The Lower East Side is only 5 stops away, so you can easily explore all New York City has to offer.</p>\r\n<p>The neighborhood has a nearby park, bars and restaurants that offer everything from Jamaican to Latin-inspired eats.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">The space</h6>\r\n<p>The house is a brand-new building with updated appliances, hardwood floors, large windows and paid laundry facilities. The Lewis House has two units altogether, each with three bedrooms, two bathrooms and a spacious living area as you enter the apartment. All of the common areas are massive in comparison to your average New York City apartment.</p>\r\n<p><strong>This space is move-in ready; all you have to do is show up.</strong></p>\r\n</div>', 5, '', 'lewis-main.jpg', 'lewis-main.jpg', '', 284, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'The 