(315, 253, 294, 'the-lexington-house', '', 'The Lexington House', 'The Lexington House (NY 10029) | Outpost Club', 'We worked with interior designers to make The Lexington House comfortable in every room. ✓ Fully furnished ✓ Security ✓ Gas ✓ Electricity ✓ Water ✓ Wi-Fi ✓ Cleaning and maintenance', 'The Lexington House | Outpost Club', '<p>Manhattan, New York</p>\r\n<p>Private rooms from $1700</p>', '<h1 class=\"h1\">The Lexington House</h1>\r\n<h4>A SPACIOUS HOME IN A LIVELY NEIGHBORHOOD</h4>', '<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">The Scoop</h6>\r\n<p>The Lexington House is located in Spanish Harlem in Manhattan, just two blocks from Central Park and near the border of the Upper East Side. The neighborhood is known for its dynamic culture and access to well-known cultural institutions like the Conservatory Garden, Museum of the City of New York and the 92nd Street Y.</p>\r\n<p>These gorgeous apartments feature exposed brick walls and classic French doors, with two spacious bedrooms separated by a warm and inviting Common area. There is one studio apartment available, which has plenty of room to entertain guests.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">The space</h6>\r\n<p>TThe Lexington House is a traditional New York City walk-up, while the units have been renovated with brightened interiors, hardwood floors, and security systems in place. You can choose between four units at the Lexington House, three with two bedrooms each, and one studio. Air conditioning throughout the house is via window units.</p>\r\n<p><strong>This space is move-in ready; all you have to do is show up with your suitcase.</strong></p>\r\n</div>', 5, '', 'lexington-bedroom-11.jpg', 'lexington-bedroom-11.jpg', '', 297, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'The Lexington House', 0, 0, 'a:9:{i:0;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:20:\"Throughout the house\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:610:\"<p>{throughout}</p>\r\n<table class=\"table v2\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<th>12+ Months</th>\r\n<th>6-11 Months</th>\r\n<th>1-4 Months</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Standard with desk)</th>\r\n<td>$1790</td>\r\n<td>$1880</td>\r\n<td>$2480</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Economy with desk)</th>\r\n<td>$1700</td>\r\n<td>$1790</td>\r\n<td>$2390</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"5\">\r\n<p>*Prices above do not include $149/month/person utilities allowance fee</p>\r\n.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div class=\"center\"><a class=\"button2 red\" href=\"join-us-manhattan\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Apply for free</a></div>\";}i:1;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:12:\"The Bedrooms\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:316:\"<p>All of the bedrooms in the Lexington House are private and feature full-sized beds and desks.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Amenities:</strong> full-size memory-foam mattresses, shelving, hooks and closets/organizational tools.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Services:</strong> Bedding is available for an additional fee.</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:8:{i:0;s:24:\"lexington-bedroom-11.jpg\";i:1;s:23:\"lexington-bedroom-9.jpg\";i:2;s:24:\"lexington-bedroom-10.jpg\";i:3;s:23:\"lexington-bedroom-8.jpg\";i:4;s:23:\"lexington-bedroom-6.jpg\";i:5;s:23:\"lexington-bedroom-5.jpg\";i:6;s:23:\"lexington-bedroom-2.jpg\";i:7;s:23:\"lexington-bedroom-1.jpg\";}}i:2;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:20:\"The (Co)Living Rooms\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:240:\"<p>Each unit in the Lexington House includes a furnished, open common area with plenty of room hang out with your roommate or entertain guests. A flat-screen TV and high-speed WiFi mean you&rsquo;ll always be ready to work or entertain.</p>\";}i:3;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:24:\"The Kitchens/Dining Room\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:386:\"<p>The kitchen and dining room are the centerpieces of each unit. These spaces are used for cooking dinner and relaxing in the evening over a glass of wine.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Amenities:</strong> plenty of cabinet space, cookware, tableware, cutting boards and much of what you would need in a kitchen.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Security: </strong> 24/7 security in common areas</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:3:{i:0;s:23:\"lexington-kitchen-3.jpg\";i:1;s:23:\"lexington-kitchen-2.jpg\";i:2;s:23:\"lexington-kitchen-1.jpg\";}}i:4;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:12:\"The bathroom\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:635:\"<p>The Lexington House features renovated bathrooms to suit all your needs. You&rsquo;ll only share a bathroom with one other person, so you&rsquo;ll never need to wait!</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Also included</strong>: toilet paper, hand soap and small garbage bags, which will never be empty!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><strong>LAUNDRY</strong></p>\r\n<p>The Lexington House also features convenient in-unit laundry, so you can wash your clothes without leaving home! In-unit laundry is a rarity for New York apartments, and it won&rsquo;t take you long to realize how much time and headache you save by not having to visit a laundromat!</p>\";s:6:\"images\";a:2:{i:0;s:24:\"lexington-bathroom-2.jpg\";i:1;s:24:\"lexington-bathroom-1.jpg\";}}i:5;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:17:\"The Neighborhood \";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:960:\"<p>Spanish Harlem, also known as East Harlem, is conveniently located in uptown Manhattan, bordering Central Park, the East River and the Upper East Side. The Lexington House is located in the southwestern corner of the neighborhood, two blocks from Central Park. You can easily walk to the park or the river, do some shopping on the Upper East Side&rsquo;s famed Madison Ave., or stay closer to home and visit some of our favorite places in Spanish Harlem, including El Museo del Barrio, a museum devoted to Latin culture in the Americas.</p>\r\n<p>The neighborhood has multiple public transit options, whether you prefer traveling via subway or bus. The closest subway station is just a 2-minute walk away, at the 103rd St 6 station, which will quickly take you to transfer points all over Manhattan. You can also take a walk to the 96th Street Q train station. As is the case all over Manhattan, there are plenty of bus routes for faster crosstown access.</p>\";}i:6;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:20:\"PERKS AND BENEFITS: \";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:588:\"<div class=\"fx ch3 w perc_advantages\">\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Fast, reliable WiFi</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Regular professional cleaning</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Furnished interiors</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">In-unit laundry</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Flat-screen TV</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Spacious bedrooms</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Community events</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Dedicated community manager</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Dedicated maintenance team</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\";}i:7;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:6:\"Prices\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:768:\"<table class=\"table v2\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<th>12+ Months</th>\r\n<th>6-11 Months</th>\r\n<th>1-4 Months</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Standard with desk)</th>\r\n<td>$1790</td>\r\n<td>$1880</td>\r\n<td>$2480</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Economy with desk)</th>\r\n<td>$1700</td>\r\n<td>$1790</td>\r\n<td>$2390</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"5\">\r\n<p>*Prices above do not include $149/month/person utilities allowance fee</p>\r\n.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div class=\"center\"><a class=\"button2 red\" href=\"join-us-manhattan\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Apply for free</a></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Availability: Year-round / Minimum stay of 1 month / Month-to-month payment options available / Minimum age 18</strong></p>\";}i:8;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:37:\"Welcome to Spanish Harlem, Manhattan.\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:480:\"<div>\r\n<p>Spanish Harlem, also known as East Harlem and El Barrio, is conveniently located in uptown Manhattan, bordering Central Park, the East River, the Upper East Side and Harlem. You can easily walk to Central Park or the East River, do some shopping on the Upper East Side&rsquo;s famed Madison Ave., or stay closer to home and visit some of our favorite places in Spanish Harlem, including El Museo del Barrio, a museum devoted to Latin culture in the Americas.</p>\r\n</div>\";}}', '', '', '', '', 1, '40.78978445', '-73.94891412', 491, '', '2022-08-22 15:17:54'),
