(326, 253, 298, 'the-newkirk-house', '', 'The Newkirk House', 'The Newkirk House (NY 11210) | Outpost Club', 'We worked with interior designers to make The Newkirk House comfortable in every room. ✓ Fully furnished ✓ Security ✓ Gas ✓ Electricity ✓ Water ✓ Wi-Fi ✓ Cleaning and maintenance', 'The Newkirk House | Outpost Club', '<p>Flatbush, Brooklyn</p>\r\n<p>Shared rooms from $790 | Private rooms from $1250</p>', '<h1 class=\"h1\">The Newkirk House</h1>\r\n<h4>Located in the heart of the historic Flatbush neighborhood</h4>', '<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">The Scoop</h6>\r\n<p>The Newkirk House is located just a few blocks from Brooklyn College, and is an easy walk from plenty of local restaurants and shops. This house features three newly renovated floors, with plenty of common space for members to work, entertain or just chill.</p>\r\n<p>The house is a newly renovated space inside and out, with split-unit heating and air conditioning, updated appliances and hardwood floors. This is a three-story, two-unit home, and each unit comes equipped with a full kitchen and living room, as well as access to a large downstairs common area.</p>\r\n<p>There are two full bathrooms and one half bathroom in each five-bedroom unit, so you&rsquo;ll never have to wait. The space is designed to feel open and airy, with light colors and large windows to let in plenty of sun. Additionally, two of the bedrooms have access to a large private terrace, a perfect spot for morning coffee or an evening cup of tea.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">Location</h6>\r\n<p>This coliving space is conveniently located just a 10-minute walk from Brooklyn College, on the neighborhood&rsquo;s main thoroughfare. It&rsquo;s an 8-minute walk from the Newkirk Ave. stop on the 2 and 5 trains, and a 15-minute walk from the Newkirk Plaza stop on the B and Q trains.</p>\r\n<p><strong>You can be in downtown Brooklyn in less than half an hour, and in lower Manhattan in just a few minutes more.</strong></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>', 5, '', 'newkirk-bedroom-2.jpg', 'newkirk-background.jpg', '', 300, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'The Newkirk House', 0, 0, 'a:8:{i:0;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:20:\"Throughout the house\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:789:\"<p>{throughout}</p>\r\n<table class=\"table v2\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<th>12+ Months</th>\r\n<th>5-11 Months</th>\r\n<th>1-4 Months</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Standard large room with a desk)</th>\r\n<td>$1460</td>\r\n<td>$1540</td>\r\n<td>$2140</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Standard)</th>\r\n<td>$1400</td>\r\n<td>$1480</td>\r\n<td>$2080</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Economy)</th>\r\n<td>$1300</td>\r\n<td>$1380</td>\r\n<td>$1980</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>2-person shared</th>\r\n<td>$790</td>\r\n<td>$840</td>\r\n<td>$890</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"5\">\r\n<p>*Prices above do not include $149/month/person utilities allowance fee</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div class=\"center\"><a class=\"button2 red\" href=\"online-questionnaire\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Apply for free</a></div>\";}i:1;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:12:\"The Bedrooms\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:346:\"<p>There are eight private rooms and two shared rooms at the Newkirk House. Bedding is available for an additional fee.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Amenities</strong>: memory-foam mattresses (twin-sized for shared rooms; full-sized for single rooms), pillows, extension cords to your bedside, shelving, hooks and closet/organization tools.</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:9:{i:0;s:21:\"newkirk-bedroom-2.jpg\";i:1;s:22:\"newkirk-bedroom-12.jpg\";i:2;s:22:\"newkirk-bedroom-13.jpg\";i:3;s:22:\"newkirk-bedroom-18.jpg\";i:4;s:22:\"newkirk-bedroom-11.jpg\";i:5;s:21:\"newkirk-bedroom-1.jpg\";i:6;s:22:\"newkirk-bedroom-17.jpg\";i:7;s:22:\"newkirk-bedroom-16.jpg\";i:8;s:22:\"newkirk-bedroom-14.jpg\";}}i:2;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:24:\"The kitchens/dining room\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:519:\"<p>There is one kitchen in each unit within the house, with cabinets and fridge space assigned to each member. This open space is used for dinners, solo meals and chats in the evening over a glass of wine.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Amenities</strong> include gas stoves, stainless-steel fridges, microwaves, large sinks, coffee makers, plenty of cabinets, cookware, tableware, cutting boards and anything else you would need in a kitchen.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Security</strong>: 24/7 security in all common areas.</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:5:{i:0;s:21:\"newkirk-kitchen-1.jpg\";i:1;s:21:\"newkirk-kitchen-2.jpg\";i:2;s:21:\"newkirk-kitchen-4.jpg\";i:3;s:21:\"newkirk-kitchen-3.jpg\";i:4;s:21:\"newkirk-kitchen-5.jpg\";}}i:3;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:20:\" The (co)living room\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:563:\"<p>Each unit in the Newkirk House has its own living area, and there&rsquo;s also a communal living room located downstairs, which members in both units have access to. The living room has comfortable couches and a 55-inch TV (with Netflix!); perfect for your next movie night. The space is equipped with everything you need to relax.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Living room also includes</strong>: Additional seating, pillows and lamps</li>\r\n<li><strong>Security:</strong> 24/7 security in common areas.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Tech</strong>: Google Chromecast.</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:3:{i:0;s:24:\"newkirk-livingroom-3.jpg\";i:1;s:24:\"newkirk-livingroom-1.jpg\";i:2;s:24:\"newkirk-livingroom-2.jpg\";}}i:4;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:13:\"The bathrooms\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:626:\"<p>We provide many bathroom essentials, as well. There are two full bathrooms and one half bathroom in each unit within the house. Our mirrors are even heated, so you&rsquo;ll never have to wait for&nbsp;it to defog!</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Also included: </strong>toilet paper,&nbsp;hand soap and small garbage bags, which will never run out!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p class=\"h5\">The Laundry room</p>\r\n<p>The Newkirk House also has laundry facilities where members can do their laundry in the comfort of their own home.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Security:</strong> 24/7 security in all common areas, as well as lockers.</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:2:{i:0;s:22:\"newkirk-bathroom-1.jpg\";i:1;s:22:\"newkirk-bathroom-2.jpg\";}}i:5;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:19:\"PERKS AND BENEFITS:\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:644:\"<div class=\"fx ch3 w perc_advantages\">\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Fast, reliable WiFi</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Regular professional cleaning</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Furnished interiors</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">In-unit laundry</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Keyless entry</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Community lounge</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Community events</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Dedicated community manager</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Updated appliances</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Dedicated maintenance team</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\";}i:6;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:6:\"Prices\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:947:\"<table class=\"table v2\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<th>12+ Months</th>\r\n<th>5-11 Months</th>\r\n<th>1-4 Months</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Standard large room with a desk)</th>\r\n<td>$1460</td>\r\n<td>$1540</td>\r\n<td>$2140</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Standard)</th>\r\n<td>$1400</td>\r\n<td>$1480</td>\r\n<td>$2080</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Economy)</th>\r\n<td>$1300</td>\r\n<td>$1380</td>\r\n<td>$1980</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>2-person shared</th>\r\n<td>$790</td>\r\n<td>$840</td>\r\n<td>$890</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"5\">\r\n<p>*Prices above do not include $149/month/person utilities allowance fee</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div class=\"center\"><a class=\"button2 red\" href=\"online-questionnaire\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Apply for free</a></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Availability: Year-round / Minimum stay of 1 month / Month-to-month payment options available / Minimum age 18</strong></p>\";}i:7;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:30:\"Welcome to Flatbush, Brooklyn.\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:506:\"<div>\r\n<p>Flatbush is one of the city&rsquo;s most diverse neighborhoods, and one way it shows is in the sheer number of different things to eat, drink and experience. Wander down the neighborhood&rsquo;s wide, leafy streets and take in the seemingly endless array of mom &amp; pop shops and delicious cuisine. Flatbush is filled with history, something that will hit you when you walk by the large, expansive Victorian homes along Bedford Avenue and other pre-war houses near Brooklyn College.</p>\r\n</div>\";s:6:\"images\";a:8:{i:0;s:29:\"Copy of Copy of MA_251639.jpg\";i:1;s:29:\"Copy of Copy of MA_251680.jpg\";i:2;s:29:\"Copy of Copy of MA_251688.jpg\";i:3;s:29:\"Copy of Copy of MA_251730.jpg\";i:4;s:29:\"Copy of Copy of MA_251737.jpg\";i:5;s:29:\"Copy of Copy of MA_251750.jpg\";i:6;s:21:\"Copy of MA_251666.jpg\";i:7;s:13:\"MA_251618.jpg\";}}}', '', '', '', '<div class=\"txt\">\r\n<h1 class=\"\">The Newkirk House Move-In Guide</h1>\r\n<h2><em><strong>1389 Flatbush Ave, Brooklyn, NY, 11210</strong></em></h2>\r\n<hr class=\"hr\" />\r\n<h3><strong>The Community</strong></h3>\r\n<p>Welcome to Outpost! We&rsquo;re glad you&rsquo;re here. Coliving isn&rsquo;t just about having roommates or sharing a kitchen &mdash; it&rsquo;s about recognizing that we can do more, accomplish more and be more when we work together.</p>\r\n<p>We communicate with each other via our house&rsquo;s Messenger group &mdash; <a class=\"green\" href=\"https://m.me/join/AbbyBQMLLOg2TIYQ\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">join us here</a>!</p>\r\n<p>Your <strong>Member Portal</strong> is where you can RSVP for community events, submit maintenance and cleaning requests and access important documents. <a class=\"green\" href=\"https://ne-bo.com/user/login\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Find it here</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Your <strong>House Leader</strong> will be your main point of contact with Outpost. Here&rsquo;s what they can help you with:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Info about community activities</li>\r\n<li>Restocking supplies</li>\r\n<li>Questions about Outpost</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>We have a lot of activities to help you get involved with our community and get to know the city. Pay attention to your Member Portal and your house&rsquo;s Messenger group to keep up with what&rsquo;s going on, or just ask your House Leader!</p>\r\n<h3><strong>The Logistics</strong></h3>\r\n<h3>Moving In</h3>\r\n<p>The outside code to your house is <strong>#1001</strong>. You&rsquo;ll use the August app to access your unit. Download the app and sign up for an account, and your House Leader will give you access.</p>\r\n<div class=\"fx w vc ch2\">\r\n<p><strong>Here&rsquo;s how to use the app:</strong></p>\r\n<div><img id=\"cldfkgliklaggnopdgnepabenoiiopbi\" style=\"display: block; top: 1033px; left: 1089px; z-index: 1999; position: absolute; cursor: pointer; background-color: transparent; background-image: none; border: none; opacity: 1; max-width: 24px; max-height: 24px; transition: all 50ms ease 0s;\" src=\"chrome-extension://cldfkgliklaggnopdgnepabenoiiopbi/ptlite-icon_32.png\" alt=\"\" /><img style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"../files/uploads/august_lock.gif\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>When you move in, your House Leader will give you a tour of the house and talk to you a bit about the Outpost community. They&rsquo;ll also:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Take a photo of your ID (for our records and according to state law)</li>\r\n<li>Add you to your Messenger group</li>\r\n<li>Assign you cupboard and refrigerator space, according to your room number.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The WiFi name is Outpost (or something similar) and the password is <strong>befreenyc</strong>.</p>\r\n<h3>Living at Outpost</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Coliving houses aren&rsquo;t hotels, and they aren&rsquo;t hostels, either.</strong> This is your home for as long as you choose, so please treat it as such:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Respect your roommates.</li>\r\n<li>Respect your house.</li>\r\n<li>Respect your neighborhood.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Recycling is required</strong>, and New York City has strict guidelines. Watch the video below to see what you should recycle:</p>\r\n<iframe style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/EUyVELb5PzY\" width=\"70%\" height=\"400\"></iframe><br /><br />\r\n<p><strong>Cleanliness is also required.</strong> That&rsquo;s especially true of common areas, including shared rooms. Here are some easy ways to think about cleanliness at Outpost:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Leave rooms in the condition in which you found them</li>\r\n<li>Clean up after yourself</li>\r\n<li>Don&rsquo;t leave your belongings in the common area unless you&rsquo;re returning immediately</li>\r\n<li>Pay attention to the signs around the house: They&rsquo;re there to help our community run smoothly!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Outpost is not responsible for lost or damaged mail or packages.</strong> Your House Leader will check the mail regularly. Make sure to put your full address, including your outside door code, in the delivery field when you order something. You may find your package left inside the main door, concealed outside, with a roommate who picked it up for you or returned to a distribution center for a later delivery. It&rsquo;s your responsibility to track your packages and make sure you&rsquo;re home to receive them when necessary.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 2, '40.63700000', '-73.95166000', 507, '', '2022-07-11 06:31:08'),
(404, 253, 320, 'the-harlem-house', '', 'The Harlem House', 'The Harlem House (NY 10030) | Outpost Club', 'We worked with interior designers to make The Harlem House comfortable in every room. ✓ Fully furnished ✓ Security ✓ Gas ✓ Electricity ✓ Water ✓ Wi-Fi ✓ Cleaning and maintenance', 'The Harlem House | Outpost Club', '<p>Harlem, Manhattan</p>\r\n<p>Private rooms from $1390</p>', '<h1 class=\"h1 center\">The Harlem House</h1>\r\n<h4>A SPACIOUS HOME IN A LIVELY NEIGHBORHOOD</h4>', '<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">The scoop&nbsp;</h6>\r\n<p>The Harlem House is located in the historic and diverse neighborhood of Harlem in Manhattan, known for its soul food, storied jazz clubs and beautiful brownstones. This renovated building has the modern amenities you&rsquo;ll need without losing the quaint touch of a historic Harlem walk-up, including wood floors and exposed brick walls.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">Location</h6>\r\n<p>This space is in the homey neighborhood of Harlem, giving you easy access to the entirety of Manhattan. The Harlem House is a 5-minute walk from two 135 St subway stations, which are served by the 2,3, A, B and C lines. You can easily access all New York City has to offer.</p>\r\n<p>The neighborhood features a nearby YMCA, the sprawling St. Nicholas Park and eclectic cuisine ranging from West African dining to French food.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">The space</h6>\r\n<p>The house is a renovated building with updated appliances, hardwood floors, large windows and historic details. The Harlem House has three units altogether, each with private bedrooms, a modern bathroom and a spacious living area as you enter the apartment. All of the common areas are massive in comparison to your average New York City apartment.</p>\r\n<p><strong>This space is move-in ready; all you have to do is show up.</strong></p>\r\n</div>', 5, '', 'harlem-house-1.jpg', 'harlem-house-1.jpg', '', 158, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'The Harlem House', 0, 0, 'a:8:{i:0;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:20:\"Throughout the house\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:596:\"<p>{throughout}</p>\r\n<table class=\"table v2\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<th>12+ Months</th>\r\n<th>5-11 Months</th>\r\n<th>1-4 Months</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Standard Large)</th>\r\n<td>$1500</td>\r\n<td>$1590</td>\r\n<td>$2190</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Standard)</th>\r\n<td>$1390</td>\r\n<td>$1480</td>\r\n<td>$2080</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"5\">\r\n<p>*Prices above do not include $149/month/person utilities allowance fee</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div class=\"center\"><a class=\"button2 red\" href=\"join-us-manhattan\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Apply for free</a></div>\";}i:1;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:8:\"Bedrooms\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:312:\"<p>All of the bedrooms in the Harlem House are private and feature full-sized beds,</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Amenities</strong>: full-size memory-foam mattresses, pillows, shelving, hooks and closets/organizational tools.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Services</strong>: Bedding is available for an additional fee.</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:4:{i:0;s:18:\"harlem-house-1.jpg\";i:1;s:18:\"harlem-house-4.jpg\";i:2;s:18:\"harlem-house-2.jpg\";i:3;s:18:\"harlem-house-5.jpg\";}}i:2;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:24:\"The kitchens/dining room\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:644:\"<p>In these apartments, the kitchen and dining room are the first rooms you enter. These spaces are used for cooking up dinner and relaxing in the evening over a glass of wine.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Amenities</strong> include electric stoves, stainless-steel fridges, microwaves, large sinks, coffee makers, blenders, plenty of cabinets, cookware, tableware, cutting boards and anything else you would need in a kitchen.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Also included:</strong> paper towels, dish soap, hand soap and garbage/recycling bags, all of which are routinely restocked.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Security:</strong> 24/7 security in common areas.</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:2:{i:0;s:18:\"harlem-house-9.jpg\";i:1;s:18:\"harlem-house-3.jpg\";}}i:3;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:19:\"The (Co)Living Room\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:432:\"<p>The living room is the center of each apartment in the Harlem House, with couches, flatscreen TVs and a table for working or eating. Whether you&rsquo;re cooking with your roommates or watching the latest Netflix series, the shared spaces in these units are equipped with everything you need.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Security:</strong> 24/7 security in common areas.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Tech:</strong> Google Chromecast.</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:2:{i:0;s:18:\"harlem-house-8.jpg\";i:1;s:18:\"harlem-house-6.jpg\";}}i:4;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:13:\"The bathrooms\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:239:\"<p>The Harlem House features sleek and renovated bathrooms with modern appliances to suit all your needs.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Also included</strong>: toilet paper, hand soap and small garbage bags, which will never be empty!</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:1:{i:0;s:18:\"harlem-house-7.jpg\";}}i:5;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:19:\"PERKS AND BENEFITS:\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:533:\"<div class=\"fx ch3 w perc_advantages\">\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Fast, reliable WiFi</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Regular professional cleaning</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Furnished interiors</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Updated appliances</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Keyless entry</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Community events</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Dedicated maintenance team</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Dedicated community manager</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\";}i:6;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"tit