(329, 253, 300, 'the-knickerbocker-house', '', 'The Knickerbocker House', 'The Knickerbocker House (NY 11237) | The Outpost Club', 'We worked with interior designers to make The Knickerbocker House comfortable in every room. ✓ Fully furnished ✓ Security ✓ Gas ✓ Electricity ✓ Water ✓ Wi-Fi ✓ Cleaning and maintenance', 'The Knickerbocker House | The Outpost Club', '<p>Bushwick, Brooklyn</p>\r\n<p>Shared rooms from $790 | Private rooms from $1190</p>', '<h1 class=\"h1\">The Knickerbocker House</h1>\r\n<h4>Newly renovated brick building in the heart of Bushwick</h4>', '<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">The Scoop</h6>\r\n<p>Located at the heart of Bushwick, the Knickerbocker House is just a 20-minute commute from Manhattan. The house has plenty of cafes, restaurants and bars within walking distance, and is located near some of Bushwick&rsquo;s most beloved murals. It has five units spread across three levels, and a backyard accessible through the basement.</p>\r\n<p>The house has been recently renovated space throughout, with split-unit heating and air conditioning, updated appliances and hardwood floors. This house is a three-level, five-unit home, with each unit equipped with a full kitchen and living room, and the first-floor unit with an additional basement common area and co-working area. The spaces are arranged around bright and inviting common areas, which are spacious in comparison to your average New York City apartment.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">Location</h6>\r\n<p>This coliving space is located in the Bushwick neighborhood in North Brooklyn, in an area known for its creative scene and nightlife.</p>\r\n<p><strong>The Knickerbocker House is a 2-minute walk to the M train on Knickerbocker Ave, and a 5-minute walk to the L train on DeKalb Ave. You can be on the Lower East Side in 20 minutes. </strong></p>\r\n</div>', 5, '', 'knickerbocker-main.jpg', 'knickerbocker-background.jpg', '', 298, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'The Knickerbocker House', 0, 0, 'a:9:{i:0;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:20:\"Throughout the house\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:789:\"<p>{throughout}</p>\r\n<table class=\"table v2\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<th>12+ Months</th>\r\n<th>5-11 Months</th>\r\n<th>1-4 Months</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Standard large room with a desk)</th>\r\n<td>$1520</td>\r\n<td>$1600</td>\r\n<td>$2200</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Standard)</th>\r\n<td>$1440</td>\r\n<td>$1520</td>\r\n<td>$2120</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Economy)</th>\r\n<td>$1340</td>\r\n<td>$1420</td>\r\n<td>$2020</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>2-person shared</th>\r\n<td>$790</td>\r\n<td>$840</td>\r\n<td>$890</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"5\">\r\n<p>*Prices above do not include $149/month/person utilities allowance fee</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div class=\"center\"><a class=\"button2 red\" href=\"online-questionnaire\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Apply for free</a></div>\";}i:1;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:12:\"The Bedrooms\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:454:\"<p>Your room will be clean and furnished just like the rest of the house. Rooms at the Knickerbocker House are either private or shared, depending on availability and your budget. Bedding is available for an additional fee.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Amenities</strong>: memory-foam mattresses (twin-sized for shared rooms; full-sized for single rooms), pillows, extension cords to your bedside, shelving, hooks, and closets/organizational tools.</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:6:{i:0;s:34:\"Copy of 235-himrod-street-2r-2.jpg\";i:1;s:36:\"Copy of 235-himrod-street-3r-1-b.jpg\";i:2;s:29:\"knickerbocker-bedroom-3_1.jpg\";i:3;s:26:\"knickerbocker-bedroom3.jpg\";i:4;s:26:\"knickerbocker-bedroom2.jpg\";i:5;s:28:\"knickerbocker-bedroom5-2.jpg\";}}i:2;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:24:\"The kitchens/dining room\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:469:\"<p>The kitchens in each unit have gas stoves and updated appliances and are stocked with plenty of supplies, so you can meal prep or cook dinner with your housemates without a worry.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Amenities</strong> include microwaves, large sinks, coffee makers, blenders, plenty of cabinets, cookware, tableware, cutting boards and anything else you would need in a kitchen.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Security</strong>: 24/7 security in all common areas.</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:3:{i:0;s:29:\"knickerbocker-kitchen-2_1.jpg\";i:1;s:27:\"knickerbocker-kitchen-4.jpg\";i:2;s:29:\"knickerbocker-kitchen-1_2.jpg\";}}i:3;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:20:\" The (co)living room\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:393:\"<p>The living rooms are at the heart of each unit within the Knickerbocker House, with their comfy couches and TVs, this is the perfect spot for your next movie night. The space is equipped with everything you need to relax.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Living room also includes:</strong> Additional seating, pillows, lamps and decor.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Tech:</strong> Google Chromecast.</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:3:{i:0;s:26:\"knickerbocker-coliving.jpg\";i:1;s:28:\"knickerbocker-coliving-2.jpg\";i:2;s:28:\"knickerbocker-coliving-1.jpg\";}}i:4;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:13:\"The bathrooms\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:356:\"<p>We provide many bathroom essentials, as well.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Included: </strong>toilet paper, hand soap and small garbage bags, which will never run out!&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p class=\"h5\">Laundry room</p>\r\n<p>The Knickerbocker House also has paid laundry facilities where members can do their laundry in the comfort of their own home.</p>\";s:6:\"images\";a:2:{i:0;s:30:\"knickerbocker-bathroom-3_1.jpg\";i:1;s:28:\"knickerbocker-bathroom-5.jpg\";}}i:5;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:8:\"Backyard\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:130:\"<p>Yes, we even have a back yard! This space has tables and chairs so can work outside in the spring, summer and autumn.&nbsp;</p>\";s:6:\"images\";a:1:{i:0;s:26:\"knickerbocker-backyard.jpg\";}}i:6;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:20:\"PERKS AND BENEFITS: \";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:644:\"<div class=\"fx ch3 w perc_advantages\">\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Fast, reliable WiFi</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Regular professional cleaning</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Furnished interiors</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">On-site laundry</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Keyless entry</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Private backyard</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Community events</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Dedicated community manager</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Updated appliances</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Dedicated maintenance team</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\";}i:7;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:6:\"Prices\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:947:\"<table class=\"table v2\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<th>12+ Months</th>\r\n<th>5-11 Months</th>\r\n<th>1-4 Months</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Standard large room with a desk)</th>\r\n<td>$1520</td>\r\n<td>$1600</td>\r\n<td>$2200</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Standard)</th>\r\n<td>$1440</td>\r\n<td>$1520</td>\r\n<td>$2120</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private (Economy)</th>\r\n<td>$1340</td>\r\n<td>$1420</td>\r\n<td>$2020</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>2-person shared</th>\r\n<td>$790</td>\r\n<td>$840</td>\r\n<td>$890</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"5\">\r\n<p>*Prices above do not include $149/month/person utilities allowance fee</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div class=\"center\"><a class=\"button2 red\" href=\"online-questionnaire\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Apply for free</a></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Availability: Year-round / Minimum stay of 1 month / Month-to-month payment options available / Minimum age 18</strong></p>\";}i:8;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:30:\"Welcome to Bushwick, Brooklyn.\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:642:\"<div>\r\n<p>Bushwick is deservedly known for its public art &mdash; the famous street murals &mdash; and its legendary nightlife scene. It&rsquo;s also home to people from all different walks of life, and you won&rsquo;t be surprised to experience what feels like a beautiful celebration of culture just walking down a street like Knickerbocker Avenue, listening to the languages being spoken while deciding which food cart to stop at. The neighborhood features the cherished Maria Hernandez Park, trendy cafes like Variety, a plethora of nightlife options, and an active community that encourages you to get to know your neighbors.</p>\r\n</div>\";s:6:\"images\";a:7:{i:0;s:79:\"45f35bd23f049a76a8ec91d6dda27135--bushwick-brooklyn-williamsburg-brooklyn_3.jpg\";i:1;s:9:\"90_3.jpeg\";i:2;s:19:\"bikes-771x466_3.png\";i:3;s:51:\"Bushwick-Collective-Mural-Brooklyn-New-York-8_3.jpg\";i:4;s:29:\"GettyImages_817252928.0_3.jpg\";i:5;s:38:\"shutterstock_1047264637_1047264640.jpg\";i:6;s:104:\"stock-photo-peace-new-york-rainy-street-art-brooklyn-bushwick-f8a5ec13-63d8-451e-af4b-b75183ecd9de_3.jpg\";}}}', '', '', '', '<div class=\"txt\">\r\n<h1 class=\"\">The Knickerbocker House Move-In Guide</h1>\r\n<h2><em><strong>235 Himrod St, Brooklyn, NY 11237</strong></em></h2>\r\n<hr class=\"hr\" />\r\n<h3><strong>The Community</strong></h3>\r\n<p>Welcome to Outpost! We&rsquo;re glad you&rsquo;re here. Coliving isn&rsquo;t just about having roommates or sharing a kitchen &mdash; it&rsquo;s about recognizing that we can do more, accomplish more and be more when we work together.</p>\r\n<p>We communicate with each other via our house&rsquo;s Messenger group, which your House Leader will add you upon arrival. We also offer an Outpost Slack channel where you can find other members with similar interests and meet new people in your area. We send out relevant updates and information via email, so keep an eye out!</p>\r\n<p>Your <strong>Member Portal</strong> is where you can RSVP for community events, submit maintenance and cleaning requests and access important documents. <a class=\"green\" href=\"../user/login\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Find it here</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Your <strong>House Leader</strong> will be your main point of contact with Outpost. Here&rsquo;s what they can help you with:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Info about community activities</li>\r\n<li>Restocking supplies</li>\r\n<li>Questions about Outpost</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>We have a lot of activities to help you get involved with our community and get to know the city. Pay attention to your Member Portal and your house&rsquo;s Messenger group to keep up with what&rsquo;s going on, or just ask your House Leader!</p>\r\n<h3><strong>The Logistics</strong></h3>\r\n<h3>Moving In</h3>\r\n<p>To unlock and enter the building, use the code <strong>#5676</strong>. You&rsquo;ll use the August app to access your unit. Download the app and sign up for an account, and your House Leader will give you access.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Apt 1</strong>: 2542</li>\r\n<li><strong>Apt 2L</strong>: 5676</li>\r\n<li><strong>Apt 2R</strong>: 7890</li>\r\n<li><strong>Apt 3</strong>: 3579</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Here&rsquo;s how to use the app:</p>\r\n<div class=\"fx w vc ch2\">\r\n<div><img style=\"width: 70%; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"../files/uploads/august_lock.gif\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>When you move in, your House Leader will give you a tour of the house and talk to you a bit about the Outpost community. They&rsquo;ll also:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Take a photo of your ID (for our records and according to state law)</li>\r\n<li>Add you to your Messenger group</li>\r\n<li>Assign you cupboard and refrigerator space, according to your room number.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The WiFi name is Outpost (or something similar) and the password is <strong>befreenyc</strong>.</p>\r\n<h3>Living at Outpost</h3>\r\n<p>You&rsquo;ll find helpful information linked above in our Guide to Responsible Coliving, but there are a few more things you should know:</p>\r\n<p><strong>Recycling is required</strong>, and New York City has strict guidelines. Watch the video below to see what you should recycle:</p>\r\n<iframe style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/EUyVELb5PzY\" width=\"70%\" height=\"400\"></iframe><br /><br />\r\n<p><strong>Cleanliness is also required.</strong> That&rsquo;s especially true of common areas, including shared rooms. Here are some easy ways to think about cleanliness at Outpost:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Leave rooms in the condition in which you found them</li>\r\n<li>Clean up after yourself</li>\r\n<li>Don&rsquo;t leave your belongings in the common area unless you&rsquo;re returning immediately</li>\r\n<li>Pay attention to the signs around the house: They&rsquo;re there to help our community run smoothly!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Outpost is not responsible for lost or damaged mail or packages.</strong> Your House Leader will check the mail regularly. Make sure to put your full address, including your outside door code, in the delivery field when you order something. You may find your package left inside the main door, concealed outside, with a roommate who picked it up for you or returned to a distribution center for a later delivery. It&rsquo;s your responsibility to track your packages and make sure you&rsquo;re home to receive them when necessary.</p>\r\n</div>', 2, '40.70048000', '-73.91977000', 496, '', '2022-07-11 06:30:31'),
