(385, 0, NULL, 'move-in-guide-the-greenpoint-house', '', 'The Greenpoint House Move-In Guide', 'The Greenpoint House Move-In Guide', '', 'The Greenpoint House Move-In Guide', '', '', '<div class=\"txt\">\r\n<h1 class=\"\">The Greenpoint House Move-In Guide</h1>\r\n<h2><em><strong>107 Greenpoint Ave. Brooklyn, NY 11222</strong></em></h2>\r\n<hr class=\"hr\" />\r\n<h3><strong>The Community</strong></h3>\r\n<p>Welcome to Outpost! We&rsquo;re glad you&rsquo;re joining our New York coliving community. Outpost wants to create spaces where people never feel alone &mdash; as we all are stronger together. We hope you enjoy your time with us!</p>\r\n<p>We communicate with each other via our house&rsquo;s Messenger group, which your House Leader will add you upon arrival. We also offer an Outpost Slack channel where you can find other members with similar interests and meet new people in your area. We send out relevant updates and information via email, so keep an eye out!</p>\r\n<p>Your <strong>Member Portal</strong> is where you can RSVP for community events, submit maintenance and cleaning requests and access important documents. <a class=\"green\" href=\"../user/login\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Find it here</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Your <strong>House Leader</strong> will be your main point of contact with Outpost.</p>\r\n<p>Here&rsquo;s how to use the app:</p>\r\n<div class=\"fx w vc ch2\">\r\n<div><img style=\"width: 70%; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"../files/uploads/august_lock.gif\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>When you move in, your House Leader will give you a tour of the house and talk to you a bit about the Outpost community. They&rsquo;ll also:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Take a photo of your ID (for our records and according to state law)</li>\r\n<li>Add you to your Messenger group</li>\r\n<li>Assign you cupboard and refrigerator space, according to your room number.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>We have a lot of activities to help you get involved with our community and get to know the city. Pay attention to your Member Portal and your house&rsquo;s Messenger group to keep up with what&rsquo;s going on, or just ask your House Leader!</p>\r\n<h3><strong>The Logistics</strong></h3>\r\n<h3>Moving In</h3>\r\n<p>To access the building, you&rsquo;ll use a key provided to you by the House Leader. Once inside, you&rsquo;ll use the August app to access your unit. Download the app and sign up for an account, and your House Leader will give you access upon arrival. Here&rsquo;s how to use the app:</p>\r\n<p>You&rsquo;ll also receive a key card to access both the house and your individual unit in the case you don&rsquo;t have your phone. Your House Leader will provide you this key upon arrival &mdash; please keep it in a safe and secure location!</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>When you move in, your House Leader will give you a tour of the house and talk to you a bit about the Outpost community.</p>\r\n<p>They&rsquo;ll also:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Take a photo of your ID (for our records and according to state law)</li>\r\n<li>Add you to your Messenger group</li>\r\n<li>Assign you cupboard and refrigerator space, according to your room number.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The WiFi name is Outpost (or something similar) and the password is <strong>befreenyc</strong>.</p>\r\n<h3>Living at Outpost</h3>\r\n<p>You&rsquo;ll find helpful information linked above in our Guide to Responsible Coliving, but there are a few more things you should know:</p>\r\n<p><strong>Recycling is required</strong>, and New York City has strict guidelines. Watch the video below to see what you should recycle:</p>\r\n<iframe style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/EUyVELb5PzY\" width=\"70%\" height=\"400\"></iframe><br /><br />\r\n<p><strong>Cleanliness is also required.</strong> That&rsquo;s especially true of common areas, including shared rooms. Here are some easy ways to think about cleanliness at Outpost:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Leave rooms in the condition in which you found them</li>\r\n<li>Clean up after yourself</li>\r\n<li>Don&rsquo;t leave your belongings in the common area unless you&rsquo;re returning immediately</li>\r\n<li>Pay attention to the signs around the house: They&rsquo;re there to help our community run smoothly!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Outpost is not responsible for lost or damaged mail or packages.</strong> Your House Leader will check the mail regularly. Make sure to put your full address, including your outside door code, in the delivery field when you order something. You may find your package left inside the main door, concealed outside, with a roommate who picked it up for you or returned to a distribution center for a later delivery. It&rsquo;s your responsibility to track your packages and make sure you&rsquo;re home to receive them when necessary.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 8, '', '', '', '', 385, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'The Greenpoint House Move-In Guide', 0, 0, 'a:0:{}', '', '', '', '', 0, '0.00000000', '0.00000000', 0, '', NULL),
(388, 253, NULL, 'the-fresh-pond-house', '', 'The Fresh Pond House', 'The Fresh Pond House | Outpost Club', '', 'The Fresh Pond House', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ridgewood</span>, Queens</p>\r\n<p>Private rooms from $890</p>', '', '<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">The Scoop</h6>\r\n<p>The Fresh Pond House is situated near the border of Ridgewood, so you can easily explore your neighborhood or take a short walk into Bushwick! This neighborhood has local bars and restaurants on every street, from delicious Thai joints to authentic Latin restaurants. If you&rsquo;re in search of a NYC neighborhood that feels more relaxed, the Fresh Pond House is a perfect place for you to enjoy the city while living in a more residential area.</p>\r\n<p>The house is a two-unit property, with stainless steel appliances, hardwood floors and carefully designed furniture. These units are equipped with everything you&rsquo;ll need for your stay &mdash; so all you need to bring is your suitcase!</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">Location</h6>\r\n<p>This space is in the homey neighborhood of Fresh Pond in Ridgewood, known for its historic streets and slower-paced lifestyle. The Fresh Pond House is a 6-minute walk from the Fresh Pond subway station, which is served by the M train, so you won&rsquo;t need to transfer to get into Williamsburg or Manhattan.</p>\r\n</div>', 5, '', 'the-fresh-pond-bedroom-1.jpg', 'the-fresh-pond-bedroom-1.jpg', '', 423, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Fresh Pond House', 0, 0, 'a:7:{i:0;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:20:\"Throughout the house\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:597:\"<p>{throughout}</p>\r\n<table class=\"table v2\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<th>12+ Months</th>\r\n<th>4-11 Months</th>\r\n<th>1-3 Months</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Private</th>\r\n<td>$890</td>\r\n<td>Not Offered</td>\r\n<td>Not Offered</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"5\">\r\n<p>*Prices above do not include utilities&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>**The prices shown indicate <strong>the prices valid for move-in between <strong>November 1</strong>, 2021, and December 31, 2021</strong></p>\r\n.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div class=\"center\"><a class=\"button2 red\" href=\"join-us\" target=\"_blank\">Apply for free</a></div>\";}i:1;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:12:\"The Bedrooms\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:208:\"<p>Each unit has four private bedrooms with full mattresses.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Amenities:</strong> memory-foam full-size mattresses, pillows, shelving, hooks and closets/organizational tools.</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:4:{i:0;s:28:\"the-fresh-pond-bedroom-2.jpg\";i:1;s:28:\"the-fresh-pond-bedroom-1.jpg\";i:2;s:28:\"the-fresh-pond-bedroom-3.jpg\";i:3;s:28:\"the-fresh-pond-bedroom-4.jpg\";}}i:2;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:24:\"The Kitchens/dining room\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:444:\"<p>The kitchens in each unit have gas stoves and stainless steel appliances. They&rsquo;re stocked with plenty of supplies, so you can meal prep or cook dinner with your housemates without a worry.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Amenities</strong> in furnished units include microwaves, dishwashers, large sinks, coffee makers, blenders, plenty of cabinets, cookware, tableware, cutting boards and anything else you would need in a kitchen.</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:2:{i:0;s:28:\"the-fresh-pond-kitchen-1.jpg\";i:1;s:28:\"the-fresh-pond-kitchen-2.jpg\";}}i:3;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:19:\"The (Co)Living Room\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:330:\"<p>The living rooms are at the heart of each unit within the Fresh Pond House. The furnished units have comfy couches and TVs, equipped with everything you need to relax.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Living room also includes:</strong> Additional seating, pillows, lamps.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Tech:</strong>: Google Chromecast.</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:3:{i:0;s:29:\"the-fresh-pond-living-3_1.jpg\";i:1;s:29:\"the-fresh-