(430, 253, 345, 'the-hells-kitchen-house', '', 'The Hell\'s Kitchen House', 'The Hell\'s Kitchen House (NY 10036) | Outpost Club', 'We worked with interior designers to make The Hell\'s Kitchen House comfortable in every room. ✓ Fully furnished ✓ Security ✓ Gas ✓ Electricity ✓ Water ✓ Wi-Fi ✓ Cleaning and maintenance', 'The Hell\'s Kitchen House | Outpost Club', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Hell\'s Kitchen</span>, Manhattan</p>\r\n<p>Private rooms from $1900</p>', '<h1 class=\"h1 center\">The Hell\'s Kitchen House</h1>', '<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">The Scoop</h6>\r\n<p>The Hell&rsquo;s Kitchen House is located in the heart of Manhattan&rsquo;s Hell&rsquo;s Kitchen neighborhood, perfectly situated between the Theater District and the Hudson River piers, and with convenient access to the rest of the city. Restaurant Row is just down the block, while the neighborhood itself is known for its plethora of LGBTQ+ bars and businesses, as well as its strong theater community.</p>\r\n<p>The Hell&rsquo;s Kitchen House is our Ecoliving House, meaning it was built with sustainability in mind. The green roof features one of the few solar canopies in Manhattan, motion sensor lights have been installed strategically throughout the building, mirror arrays redirect sunlight to the lower floors, and low-flow showerheads and toilets are in every bathroom. But the heart of The Ecoliving House is our community &mdash; and every member is encouraged to adopt sustainable practices outlined at move-in, like participating in our composting and gardening program on the roof.</p>\r\n<p>The building itself is a classic Manhattan walk-up that has been completely renovated and furnished to support modern lifestyles, with updated appliances and plenty of open space so you&rsquo;ll never feel crowded.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">Location</h6>\r\n<p>The Hell&rsquo;s Kitchen House is well-situated in an exciting neighborhood with plenty of dining and entertainment options, while nearby subway stations give you convenient access to the rest of the city. The closest station is a 5-minute walk away at the 50th Street A/C/E station. You can also walk just 12 minutes to the Times Square-42nd St station, which serves the 1/2/3, 7, and N/Q/R/W lines, as well as the A/C/E via the connected Port Authority Station, and the S shuttle to Grand Central.</p>\r\n</div>', 5, '', 'Hells Kitchen House 29.jpg', 'Hells Kitchen House 29.jpg', '', 283, 1, 0, 0, 1, 'The Hell\'s Kitchen House', 0, 0, 'a:10:{i:0;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:20:\"Throughout the House\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:744:\"<p>{throughout}</p>\r\n<table class=\"table v2\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<th>12+ Months</th>\r\n<th>5-11 Months</th>\r\n<th>1-4 Months</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Standard</th>\r\n<td>$1900</td>\r\n<td>$2080</td>\r\n<td>$2680</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Standard Large</th>\r\n<td>$2050</td>\r\n<td>$2230</td>\r\n<td>$2830</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Executive</th>\r\n<td>$2400</td>\r\n<td>$2510</td>\r\n<td>$3180</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Executive Large</th>\r\n<td>$2490</td>\r\n<td>$2580</td>\r\n<td>$3110</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"5\">\r\n<p>*Prices above do not include $149/month/person utilities allowance fee</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div class=\"center\"><a class=\"button2 red\" href=\"join-us-manhattan\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Apply for free</a></div>\";}i:1;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:12:\"The Bedrooms\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:228:\"<p>All of the bedrooms in the Hell&rsquo;s Kitchen House are private and feature full-sized beds. Many include private bathrooms, and one bedroom in each unit includes a fireplace. Bedding is available for an additional fee.</p>\";s:6:\"images\";a:6:{i:0;s:26:\"Hells Kitchen House 10.jpg\";i:1;s:25:\"Hells Kitchen House 8.jpg\";i:2;s:26:\"Hells Kitchen House 17.jpg\";i:3;s:26:\"Hells Kitchen House 20.jpg\";i:4;s:26:\"Hells Kitchen House 21.jpg\";i:5;s:25:\"Hells Kitchen House 7.jpg\";}}i:2;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:20:\"The (Co)Living Rooms\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:390:\"<p>Within each unit, the living room includes a flat-screen TV and comfortable seating. On the ground floor, a tastefully designed common lounge is accessible to all members, highlighted by a Mondrian-inspired sequin wall in the lobby. The lounge has plenty of seating and a large table for co-working. Storage cages and bike racks are available in the cellar, and a gym is coming soon!</p>\";s:6:\"images\";a:4:{i:0;s:25:\"Hells Kitchen House 1.jpg\";i:1;s:25:\"Hells Kitchen House 2.jpg\";i:2;s:25:\"Hells Kitchen House 4.jpg\";i:3;s:26:\"Hells Kitchen House 16.jpg\";}}i:3;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:24:\"The Kitchens/Dining Room\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:222:\"<p>The kitchens in these units are appointed with high-end cabinets imported from Germany, Dekton countertops and induction cooktops, and are fully stocked with dishware, cooking tools, appliances and other essentials.</p>\";s:6:\"images\";a:4:{i:0;s:25:\"Hells Kitchen House 5.jpg\";i:1;s:26:\"Hells Kitchen House 13.jpg\";i:2;s:26:\"Hells Kitchen House 18.jpg\";i:3;s:26:\"Hells Kitchen House 19.jpg\";}}i:4;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:16:\"The Laundry Room\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:257:\"<p>Each unit comes furnished with a washer and dryer. There&nbsp;are also free washers and dryers in the common area of the building &mdash; a luxury in New York City &mdash; so you won&rsquo;t have to wait for your roomates to finish their wash cycles!</p>\";s:6:\"images\";a:2:{i:0;s:26:\"Hells Kitchen House 11.jpg\";i:1;s:26:\"Hells Kitchen House 12.jpg\";}}i:5;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:13:\"The Bathrooms\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:275:\"<p>Many of the bedrooms have private en-suite bathrooms, and every apartment has three bathrooms for three or four bedrooms, meaning you&rsquo;ll never have to wait. All bathrooms are equipped with Bio-bidet heated smart toilet seats and low-flow High Sierra showerheads.</p>\";s:6:\"images\";a:3:{i:0;s:25:\"Hells Kitchen House 3.jpg\";i:1;s:25:\"Hells Kitchen House 9.jpg\";i:2;s:26:\"Hells Kitchen House 14.jpg\";}}i:6;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:11:\"The Rooftop\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:435:\"<p>Crowning the building is a stunning Shigeo Kawasaki-designed green roof with a spectacular front-row seat to the Midtown skyline. The rooftop includes a spacious patio and multiple seating areas, perfect for time alone or with a group.</p>\r\n<p>The green roof also features a 40-panel, 14.4 kW solar canopy, mirror arrays to redirect sunlight to the lower floors of the building, and space for community gardening and composting.</p>\";s:6:\"images\";a:4:{i:0;s:26:\"Hells Kitchen House 25.jpg\";i:1;s:26:\"Hells Kitchen House 24.jpg\";i:2;s:26:\"Hells Kitchen House 28.jpg\";i:3;s:26:\"Hells Kitchen House 23.jpg\";}}i:7;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:19:\"Additional benefits\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:178:\"<p><strong>We screen all candidates before approving applications so that there are no worries about moving into a new place with new people &mdash; only excitement!</strong></p>\";}i:8;O:8:\"stdClass\":3:{s:5:\"title\";s:6:\"Prices\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"body\";s:902:\"<table class=\"table v2\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<th>12+ Months</th>\r\n<th>5-11 Months</th>\r\n<th>1-4 Months</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Standard</th>\r\n<td>$1900</td>\r\n<td>$2080</td>\r\n<td>$2680</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Standard Large</th>\r\n<td>$2050</td>\r\n<td>$2230</td>\r\n<td>$2830</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Executive</th>\r\n<td>$2400</td>\r\n<td>$2510</td>\r\n<td>$3180</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Executive Large</th>\r\n<td>$2490</td>\r\n<td>$2580</td>\r\n<td>$3110</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"5\">\r\n<p>*Prices above do not include $149/month/person utilities allowance fee</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div class=\"center\"><a class=\"button2 red\" href=\"join-us-manhattan\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Apply for free</a></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Availability: Year-round / Minimum stay of 1 month / Month-to-month payment options available / Minimum age 18</strong></p>\";}i:9;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:16:\"The Neighborhood\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"body\";s:1515:\"<p>The Hell&rsquo;s Kitchen neighborhood is a microcosm of our city of nearly 9 million people, with all the vibrancy and energy you would expect from living in the heart of New York City. People of all cultures and backgrounds call Hell&rsquo;s Kitchen home, and the neighborhood has an artistic streak due to its proximity to the Theater District.</p>\r\n<p>Due to zoning regulations in Hell&rsquo;s Kitchen, you&rsquo;ll find gorgeous 360-degree views of the Manhattan skyline throughout much of the neighborhood, and easy access to Bryant Park, Central Park and the Hudson River piers will give you the chance to escape the rush of the city when you&rsquo;re craving time in nature.</p>\r\n<p>Regardless of your preferred cuisine or choice of entertainment, you can probably find it nearby &mdash; or you can hop on a train and be in a different neighborhood in no time.</p>\r\n<p>Hell&rsquo;s Kitchen is world-renowned for its vibrant LGBTQ+ scene, with plentiful bars and clubs that keep New York&rsquo;s world-class nightlife scene right at your fingertips. The neighborhood is also home to a wide variety of locally owned small businesses, which remain relatively affordable compared to many parts of Manhattan.</p>\r\n<p><strong>All-inclusive travel distance to popular destinations:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Empire State Building: 15 min. via the N/R/W</li>\r\n<li>Central Park: 10 min. via the 1 or C</li>\r\n<li>Washington Square Park: 20 min. via the A/C/E</li>\r\n<li>Brooklyn Bridge: 28 min. via the A/C</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:6:\"images\";a:3:{i:0;s:25:\"pexels-pixabay-259987.jpg\";i:1;s:25:\"pexels-pixabay-327502.jpg\";i:2;s:41:\"alex-simpson-N3vSMOoKgNM-unsplash (1).jpg\";}}}', '', '', '', '', 1, '40.76211292', '-73.99152410', 485, '', '2022-10-04 12:14:43'),
