(478, 253, 363, 'the-bryant-park-residences', '', 'The Bryant Park Residences', 'The Bryant Park Residences (NY 10036) | Outpost Club', 'We worked with interior designers to make The Bryant Park Residences comfortable in every room. ✓ Fully furnished ✓ Security ✓ Gas ✓ Electricity ✓ Water ✓ Wi-Fi ✓ Cleaning and maintenance', 'The Bryant Park Residences | Outpost Club', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Manhattan</span></p>', '<h1 class=\"h1 center\">The Bryant Park Residences</h1>\r\n<h4>A SPACIOUS HOME IN A LIVELY NEIGHBORHOOD</h4>', '<div>\r\n<p>The newly renovated Bryant Park Residences are right in the center of some of New York&rsquo;s most well-known destinations, including Bryant Park, Rockefeller Plaza, Grand Central Terminal and Times Square. World-class dining, culture and entertainment are always just steps away in Midtown, and street vendors and outdoor dining bring the neighbrohood to life. Easy access to public transit will help you get anywhere you need to go, and when you get home, your Midtown apartment will be the perfect place to rest your head.</p>\r\n<p>The main draw: Besides the obvious &mdash; location! &mdash; apartments at the Midtown Manhattan Residences feature gorgeous views of the Midtown skyline.</p>\r\n<p>Perfect for you if: You live for the energy of Manhattan, but want to come home to a sanctuary.</p>\r\n<p>Our suggestion: Walk around and find the hidden pockets of Midtown most people don&rsquo;t know about. Thanks to New York City zoning laws, Midtown is home to a plethora of spaces that are open to the public despite looking like private plazas and courtyards. Get to know the neighborhood and you&rsquo;ll always have a peaceful place to take a break.</p>\r\n</div>', 5, '', 'Common area-11.jpg', 'Common area-11.jpg', '', 326, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'The Bryant Park Residences', 0, 0, 'a:3:{i:0;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:34:\"Explore the Bryant Park Residences\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:6:\"images\";a:9:{i:0;s:18:\"Common area-10.jpg\";i:1;s:17:\"Common area-7.jpg\";i:2;s:17:\"Common area-4.jpg\";i:3;s:17:\"Common area-2.jpg\";i:4;s:13:\"Kitchen-4.jpg\";i:5;s:17:\"Common area-5.jpg\";i:6;s:13:\"bedroom-1.jpg\";i:7;s:13:\"bedroom-7.jpg\";i:8;s:13:\"bedroom-4.jpg\";}s:4:\"body\";s:654:\"<div>\r\n<p>The Bryant Park Residences are 14 one-bedroom apartments, all located on or above the 28th floor of a classic Midtown skyscraper. Each unit comes fully furnished, with updated appliances and hardwood floors. Each apartment has a washer, dryer and dishwasher in-unit &mdash; a luxury in New York City. All private units have corner exposure and large windows, allowing for beautiful views and tons of natural light.</p>\r\n<p>Guests have access to the 10th-floor gym, which features floor-to-ceiling windows with sweeping views of Midtown Manhattan. The high-class New York staple Butter is located on the ground floor of the building.</p>\r\n</div>\";}i:1;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:18:\"Perks and Benefits\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:6:\"images\";a:4:{i:0;s:38:\"the-bryant-park-residences-supply1.jpg\";i:1;s:38:\"the-bryant-park-residences-supply4.jpg\";i:2;s:38:\"the-bryant-park-residences-supply2.jpg\";i:3;s:38:\"the-bryant-park-residences-supply3.jpg\";}s:4:\"body\";s:586:\"<div class=\"fx ch3 w perc_advantages\">\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Fast, reliable WiFi</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">In-unit laundry</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Updated appliances</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Furnished interiors</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Spacious bedrooms</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Dishwasher</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Regular professional cleaning</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Dedicated community manager</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h4 class=\"title\">Dedicated maintenance team</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\";}i:2;O:8:\"stdClass\":4:{s:5:\"title\";s:17:\"Midtown Manhattan\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"2\";s:6:\"images\";a:7:{i:0;s:38:\"the-midtown-manhattan-residences-8.jpg\";i:1;s:38:\"the-midtown-manhattan-residences-2.jpg\";i:2;s:38:\"the-midtown-manhattan-residences-4.jpg\";i:3;s:38:\"the-midtown-manhattan-residences-5.jpg\";i:4;s:38:\"the-midtown-manhattan-residences-6.jpg\";i:5;s:38:\"the-midtown-manhattan-residences-7.jpg\";i:6;s:38:\"the-midtown-manhattan-residences-1.jpg\";}s:4:\"body\";s:1702:\"<div>\r\n<p>Midtown Manhattan is home to the majority of New York&rsquo;s skyscrapers and has perhaps the most recognizable skyline in the world. The neighborhood is home to some of the most well-known buildings and institutions in the world, including the Empire State and Chrysler buildings, Rockefeller Center, Grand Central Terminal, Broadway, Times Square, St. Patrick&rsquo;s Cathedral and Bryant Park. Midtown is home to the main branch of the New York Public Library, known worldwide for its architecture.</p>\r\n<p>Midtown is also the largest business district in the world and is home to the flagship stores of many major companies, including Nordstrom, Saks Fifth Avenue, Bloomingdale&rsquo;s, Apple, Macy&rsquo;s and Adidas, among others. The streets are dotted with vendors and outdoor dining cafes, and the sidewalks are nearly always bustling.</p>\r\n<h6 class=\"h5\">Location</h6>\r\n<p>Because the Midtown Manhattan Studios are located in the core of Manhattan, you&rsquo;ll be within walking distance of any transit option you could need:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>42 St-Bryant Park: B/D/F/M trains; 4-minute walk</li>\r\n<li>5 Av: 7 train; 6-minute walk</li>\r\n<li>Grand Central-42 St: 4/5/6, 7 trains; 8-minute walk</li>\r\n<li>Times Sq-42 St/Port Authority Bus Terminal: N/Q/R/W, A/C/E, 1/2/3, 7, S trains; 7-minute walk</li>\r\n<li>5 Avenue-53 St: E, M trains; 12-minute walk</li>\r\n<li>33rd St: Journal Square and Hoboken PATH trains</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>You&rsquo;ll also be a 17-minute walk from Penn Station, the busiest transit hub of any kind in the entire Western Hemisphere, with access to the New York City Subway (1/2/3, A/C/E, B/D/F/M, N/Q/R/W), Long Island Rail Road, Amtrak and NJ Transit.</p>\r\n</div>\";}}', '', '', 'a:3:{i:0;s:3:\"430\";i:1;s:3:\"404\";i:2;s:3:\"315\";}', '', 1, '40.75633130', '-73.98219450', 509, '', '2022-07-11 06:35:14'),
